name: Void
description: You can do this by typing 'sendmail tesseract', and following the directions.

name: The Tree of Life
description: The Tree of Life is symbolically one of the most interesting phemonena in Oceancrest.  From here, you can see the splendor of the city of  Oceancrest.  The Tree of Life provides much of the life-giving energy you can see and sense throughout the land.  It has always been a mystery to everyone, but no one seems to argue it.  You may start your quest in the Land of Mordor by heading down the tree.

name: Void
description: This is a place with nothing in it.  You stare in the distance in all directions but do not see anything, except upwards where there is a shimmer of light being emitted.

name: Black Market Alley
description: Wall Road West is very close to here, and a hodge-podge of shops line the alley on the north side.  There is a high fence on the south side. It looks like you can buy just about anything you ever imagined in these run-down little places.  A lot of shopkeepers wave merchandise at you.

name: Garth's Room of Quiet Thought
description: Tacked up on the walls are lists of m0dz he is planning to make to the game as well as posters of users who have been naughty and deserve to be deleted.  There are three buttons next to the door.  One is red, one is blue and the other is grey.

name: Hans' and Frans' Workout Gym
description: This room is filled with literally tons of workout equipment.  The eastern wall is mirrored to allow exercisors to get positive feedback during their workouts.  In the southwest corner you see Frans, Hans' twin brother, pressing with all his might on the bench press machine.  A ventilator in the roof gently blows fresh air around the room, lessening the stench from Frans' armpits.  Emanating from a powerful set of loudspeakers is the  raucous of rock music.  You flex in the mirror and notice how puny your muscles look in comparison to Hans' and Frans' iron biceps.

name: Black Market Alley
description: On the south side is the side entrance to a custom leather armor shop. There are at least six shops crammed together in a very small space on the north side of the alley, and even more upstairs above them.  Shop owners stand outside and hawk their wares.

name: Wall Road West/Goldenrod Avenue
description: You have reached the northwest corner of the village of Brownhaven. A guard's tower is set in the corner of the wall, and you can see a stairwell just inside the wall which appears to provide access to the station up there.  The Brownhaven militia isn't very large, but they have recruited the meanest and toughest citizens they could find.  The guards at this post seem to be typical of the Brownhaven force.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: You are walking along a narrow road between the village wall and the open back doors of several shops.  The shop entrances are actually on another  alley to the south.  Looks like a lot of garbage gets thrown out along this alley, judging from the stink and the piles of fresh refuse.  Alley cats and dirty little kids fight each other for anything edible.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: The village wall is a uniform dirty brown on the north side of the road. The appearance of the wall is how the village of Brownhaven got its name. This narrow little road might better be called an alley along here.  It seems to twist and turn every few meters as it winds along behind the back doors of a number of shops.  A faded old sign above one of the doors says the place was established about four hundred years ago by a dwarf named Ahabanabanazzer.

name: Goldenrod Avenue/Brownhaven Way
description: Goldenrod Avenue is actually a narrow, winding little lane to the west, but seems to be a little wider as you look east.  An imposing building is at the southeast corner of this intersection.  A fairly new sign says its the tax collector's office.  Across the street on the southwestern corner is the village militia's headquarters.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: Directly to the south, across the road, is the tax collector's building. The main entrance is on Brownhaven Way, but there is a small side door here.  Next door is the Boar's Tit Pub, a rather rowdy little pub known for its strong drink.  A few tax collectors have been known to slip over for a quick drink during working hours.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: There is a tall guard tower set in the wall on the north side of the road. Stone steps inside an alcove look like they probably wind their way to the top.  Several village guards can be seen up there, lounging around and lazily watching the people below.  Looking to the west, on the south side of the road, you can see the entrance to a pub.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: The road is badly paved, and a great many potholes have been untended for a very long time.  There is a busted wagon standing in the roadway, blocking most of the road.  On the south side of the road is the Begger's Guild.  No one is allowed to beg in the streets of Brownhaven unless they are a member of the guild, and pay membership dues.  The door appears to be heavy oak with a gold door knocker.

name: Main Street/Goldenrod Avenue
description: Main Street comes to an end here at Goldenrod Avenue but it continues to the south.  Main Street is the broadest street in the village of Brownhaven. Most of the more respectable businesses and shops are to the south of you. There is a very wide gate set in the north village wall, and you can see a dusty road leaving the village heading into the foothils.  The shabby looking building on the southeast corner is a warehouse and camel stable   for the caravans which arrive monthly.

name: North Village Gate
description: This gate is closed at sundown to avoid being overrun by mountain trolls and other unwelcome creatures.  Promptly at sunrise the gates are opened to traffic.  Most of the stuff you see in the shops in Brownhaven is brought in by travelers or the monthly caravan.  South is the intersection of Goldenrod Avenue and Main Street.

name: Wall Road West
description: On the east side is a run-down little business called the Wayfarer's Rest. Travelers stop there on their way in and out of the city.  It's always best to start a journey in the morning hours.  The roads are trecherous during the night-time, as many of the creatures who prey on travelers do not like the heat of the sun.

name: Wall Road West/Black Market Alley
description: On the west side of the road there is a burned building.  A sign says, "Keep Out - Order of Brownhaven Militia."  No ordinary fire swept through here.  You can see all the indications of a magical flame.  At one time this was the home of Khallazar and Gharalara before they separated.  She was a powerful cleric, dedicated to her deity, and he was a young alchemist. What he saw in her, no one could tell.   She was considerably older than he.

name: Oceancrest Reclaimation Plant
description: Great piles of broken and discarded items from all over the city are in several separate mounds, awaiting disposal.  Several city workers are busy sorting and moving trash, and a great machine sits in the center of the plant, receiving material from them.  Over in one corner is a pile of broken armor, and another pile nearby is made up of shattered blades and daggers.  Just about anything you have ever seen in the city winds up here when it breaks.

name: Plasnelt Park
description: Trees and nicely trimmed bushes form a nice park where you may sit and contemplate your existance in this Land of Mordor.  An old mage, white  bearded and ugly, sits on a park bench, looking you over.  He looks like  he would like to talk, if you have the time.  He wears a warm looking  cloak, evidently stuffed with a great many things.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: Several small but expensive shops can be seen along here.  Directly to the west is a custom leather armor shop.  Frebadis, the old hobbit who runs the shop brags that his great, great grandfater established the place when Brownhaven was just a wide spot in the road to Oceancrest.  On the east is a custom knife shop where you can buy a knife of any size.  For a little extra, you can even get it enchanted.

name: Brownhaven Main Post Office
description: It's easy to see you are in a post office, because of all the postal workers you see standing around doing absolutely nothing.  Fortunately the postal system is almost completely automated, and you do not need these people to send a letter.  You need to type:  sendmail <person> and then your message. If you hit the return key twice, it will end the letter.  Be sure to hit the return key at the end of each line.  There is no automatic line-wrap. ...Styx...

name: Main Street
description: There is a large lot and several warehouses and camel stables on the east side of the street.  An auction is held when the caravans arrive from other cities, and it is usually an exciting event.  Even people who do not intend  buy come just to watch.

name: Frodorab's Fine Boots and Shoes
description: Hobbits have long been known for their craftsmanship with shoes and tools, and Frodorab is one of the best.  He makes boots and shoes of all sizes, for any race.  If you have seven toes or three, he can make the shoe fit.

name: Frodorab's Boot Storage
description: You are in the storage room for Brownhaven's finest bootery.

name: Wall Road West
description: The neighborhood is rather squalid and dirty, yet was once the pride of its residents.  But no more.  These days the village is threatening to tear the old buildings down, but eveyone knows they won't.  Too many more people would become homeless, and the rich would miss their help.  A fence is on   the east side of the road, and the village wall on the west.

name: Limbo
description: Lost and lonely souls wander about aimlessly, hopelessly seeking to gain an insight into the meaning of their past and wasted lives.  Adventurous souls who wish to return to the city of Oceancrest to start their lives again should go through the blue door.  The green door goes to the Tree of Life.

name: Vickers Wine Cellar
description: Wine bottles in dusty racks line the walls, and a small sampling table is near the center of the room.  You see a corking machine and several empty bottles near a large wooden vat.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: The Brownhaven Ladies Garden supply is located on the east side of the road. Next door is the Roseleaf Tea and Cakes restaurant, where only the most elite of Brownhaven's ladies gather.  There's an unfounded rumor that more than tea and cakes can be found in the back room of the little shop, however.

name: Mayor's Office
description: Like most political figures, the mayor is off on a junket most of the time. He does, however, have influential friends at Lyanden court, so he is able to do a lot of good for the town.  Maybe that's why he has been re-elected so many times.

name: Brownhaven Central Library
description: The library is known for miles around because of its collection of magical tomes and detailed books on combat, armor and weapons.  A short librarian eyes you suspiciously as you walk among the shelves of books.

name: Main Street
description: A lot of people are gathered on the east side of the street where an auctioneer is holding up items for the buyers to see.  The crowd is noisy, and the buyers are using hand signals to make their bids.  be careful what you do with your hands.

name: Vickers Estate Drive
description: On the hill to the north is the old Vickers place, now boarded up tight. No light comes from the windows, but there does seem to be a glow that  flits from room to room occasionally.

name: Vickers Estate Front Door
description: The Vickers family established their home here soon after the village was founded.  No one lives here now, but someday the residence may be reclaimed by the sons of old man Vickers.  The story is that they were taken from Brownhaven after their father was murdered.

name: West Gate
description: Caledonia Road runs to the east from here, heading into the business and cultural center of the village.  Wall Road West parallels the western perimeter of the wall which surrounds the village.  A major guard station is close to the gate amd the militia maintains a barracks nearby.  On the northeast side of the corner is a small, two story inn where travelers often rent rooms while they rest from their journey.

name: Caledonia Road
description: There are several run-down old mansions set back away from the main part of the road, and looking to the northeast, there appears to be one with its windows completely boarded up.  A small post office can be seen on the south side of the road.

name: Caledonia Road
description: Caledonia Road continues to the east and west, but the gate to the mansion is north.  It doesn't look as if anyone has lived in the mansion for quite some time, because it's windows are totally covered and all the lights are completely out.  If you didn't know any better, you'd say it was haunted.  Of course, every village has its mystery old house.

name: Leviathan Way/High Street
description: Leviathan Way is to the east and west, while High Street continues to the north and south.  To the west you can see the western gates  of Celduin, and to the east you can see the town square.

name: Leviathan Way
description: To the east you can see the bustling center of Celduin, and to the west is High Street.  Leviathan Way is the longest road in all of Isengard, and without it being open commercial traffic in the land would come to a standstill.  High Street is popular with the local students, as it is the location of the University of Celduin.

name: Grady's Second Hand Shop
description: The shop is crowded with everything you can imagine, some of it hanging from the ceiling.  There is a weapons display and a corner where you see used magical items.  Grady drives a good bargain, but usually not for his customers.  Grady is fair, however, and will give you at least what his competitors offer.  Ask him the value of what you are offering.

name: Caledonia Road
description: Directly west is the Town Square of Brownhaven.  Caledonia Road intersects with Main Street over to the east.  As you look north, you see the famous Brownhaven Central Library, world famous for its collection of books on magic and alchemy.  Of course, the most famous of all alchemists once resided here in Brownhaven, and when his house burned he gave the library the books he salvaged.  Khallazar has since moved to somewhere in an enchanted forest.

name: Caledonia Road/Main Street
description: Main Street is a commercial district where you might find just about anything for sale.  Looking for armor or perhaps a good horse?  Or perhaps you would like to buy an enchanted staff?  all of its available somehwere along Main Street.  There is a bazaar that takes place during the summer months that attracts visitors even from the sophisticated cities of Kista and Oceancrest.

name: Caledonia Road
description: Many years ago, the owner of the inn was told he would never die until the Caledonia Inn was finished.  Since that time he has kept workmen constantly adding to and tearing down the great inn, so that the building can never be said to be finished.  There is a maze of rooms and halls in there, some of which were sealed overnight, and built around.

name: North Bridge
description: The river rushes by rapidly below your feet.  There must have been a good deal of snow last winter.. The Baldywyne River has its headwaters high on Mount Caledonia to the north.  Of course, its never been fully explored, so that's just a guess since it flows from there.  No one has actually  seen where it comes from.

name: Limbo
description: Lost souls wander about aimlessly, hopelessly seeking to gain an insight into the meaning of their past lives.  Adventurous souls who do not wish to return to Celduin to start their lives again should go through the blue door.

name: Wall Road West
description: There are some very strange beasts kept in there, and not all of them are happy to be there.  The noise can be horrendous at times.  The  Brownhaven militia has given the owner of the compound a contract to train copper dragons as mounts.  When its done properly, they make  excellent steeds for flying patrols high over the village.  When its not done properly, the dragons eat their riders.  It's a tough life.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: To the west is a high-class magic shoppe with a sign which seems to be floating with no supports just above its entrance.  There is a quiet little inn to the east where you can hear a group of people singing and occasionally laughing.  Brownhaven Way has a great many trees along the broad roadside, and the inn is set back away from the road.

name: Matilda's Overnight Inn
description: This place is pretty active.  A number of people you've seen in town are in here.  They seem to all be friends of the mayor, although you don't see him here.  You do see a number of waitresses wearing short skirts and not much else.  One comes up to you and asks you what you would like to drink.  Please keep your eyes in your face.

name: Small Alley
description: To the north is Brownhaven Town Square, to the west is the back entrance to an inn, and to the east is a back entrance to a shoppe.   There's quite a bit of noise coming from the pub.  Either they're having a good time, or  a very bad time in there.  You hear a lot of yelling and cheering on the other side of the south wall.

name: Shrine of the White Rose
description: A simple altar stands at the south end of the room, and a pulpit is at the side of the shrine's holy icon.  There are doors on the east side that go to palaidn training rooms.

name: Main Street
description: To the east is the town park, and to the north and south Main Street continues.  To the west you can see a shoppe with a weathered wooden sign across the front of it.  The sign has a sword and a mace on it.  It must be a weapons shoppe, but probably run of the mill stuff.

name: North Plasnelt Park
description: Plasnelt Road is south of you.  This park is generally frequented by only  members of the upper class of the village.  They like to come listen to the strolling musicians and watch the mimes who pretend to be in a box.

name: North Plasnelt Park
description: The water is cold and deep, and the river is wide at this point.  Willow trees line the bank, and small boats are pulled up on the shore.  there is a short pier extending into the water.  Shady elms and other ornamental  trees line the park walks.  A short path goes under South Bridge.

name: Wall Road West
description: High overhead, there is a copper dragon and rider circling in preparation  for landing at the pits, which is northeast of here.  The high wall on the west side blocks any view in that direction, but you know there are low rolling hills that way, which eventually rise to the Nartiz Mountain Range. On the east side of the road there is a low fence enclosing the Animal Training Compound.

name: Saint Thenoir's Discount Supplies for Clerics
description: Of course, the owner doesn't call them mumbo jumbo supplies, but what's the difference?  One man's bag of hair and toe nail clippings is another man's eternally blessed gateway to the supreme being he believes is the all-powerful creator. What will you buy?

name: Brownhaven Way
description: Not far to the south you can see the entrance to a village concert hall. The people of Brownhaven pride themselves on their understanding of culture, and try to attend most of the recitals given here.  Unfortunately, they often have good excuses for not attending, so generally only a few patrons can be found at any particular evening.  But if you are really looking for a good time, the Boar's Tit Pub is popular every night.

name: Main Arena
description: Blood stains the walls and grounds of the entire arena.  You wonder just  how many poor souls have died on the floors of this place.  Citizens have packed the stands to see you fight, and loud cheers erupt as you enter the arena.  Are you ready for this?

name: Arena Warmup
description: Blood stains the walls and grounds of this side of the arena.  To the west you hear loud cheers and cries of battle.  There's really not much to do  in the evening in a small village, so the people come here to keep from being bored at home.

name: Ready Room
description: You smell the fear of neophytes as they suit up and prepare for battle in the arena, west of here.  To the north is the weapon shop, to the south is the armor shop, and to the east is Main Street.

name: Main Street
description: One of the most attractive entertainment centers in the entire village is the Sportsman's Arena, located just to the west.  A great banner across the top indicates there are three arenas going at all times, even one for the kids.  It's a family affair, with door prizes and a set of dishes to the lucky winner.

name: South Plasnelt Park
description: Actually, when the park was built, the village elders thought of the north and south parks as simply one park.  It didn't take long however, for the residents to segregate themselves into separate groups.  The poor people who generally live on the east side of town come to this southern section, and leave the northern side to the rich snobs who live on the west side.

name: Caretaker Training Room
description: She will tell you about many of the help commands and how to use them. Pay attention to what she says, as each time she speaks you will be provided with several choices.  The words that are in caps (LIKE THIS) are other topics that she will talk about.  Words in braces [like this] are commands that you can type to get more information, or to test a command.  Finally, words in apostrophes ('like this') give information on the syntax of a command.

name: Wall Road West
description: You are at the western most side of the village of Brownhaven, walking beside a high, brown wall.  The village took its name from the color of the wall, which was built centuries ago to protect the residents from the marauding mountain trolls.  A large clan of trolls live to the north of the village.

name: Under South Bridge
description: The entrance to the shack is on the north side, but there appears to be a back door here.  there are a lot of wine bottles lying on the ground and the smell of urine and vomit is strong.  An old mattress is against the bridge buttress, and a few dirty dishes are around a campfire.

name: Under South Bridge
description: A wooden shack takes up most of the available space, going nearly to the water's edge.  there is a path leading south to the other side of the bridge, but you almost have to walk in the water to go that way.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: Fruit trees and shady elms line the way, and several old homes are set back away from the roadway.  The homes look like old money.  A little further to the north is where the professional people of Brownhaven have their business establishments.  Perhaps this is the section of  town where they live.

name: Arena Challenge
description: The action is a little faster and the fighters a little meaner. A great many of your predecessors have died here, entertaining the masses who come to see the blood spurt, and the eyes bulge.  You do want to entertain them, don't you?  Loud cheering erupts as you step into the  center of the arena.  they're cheering for you!

name: Gladitor Champion's Arena
description: Only the champions from previous fights are allowed in here, and this is the part of the arena that is the most packed with blood-thirsty crowds. There is bloody sawdust on the floor, and a few pieces of bodies that  were not picked up when the cleaning crew was at work.  Remember, your opponent has already won all of his previous fights.

name: Campus Walk East
description: To the west is the main Quad for the campus, and to the  north you can see the Randiforth Systems building.  Randiforth Systems provides offices, labs, and classrooms for the engineering school.  You can see to the south a large building that is the student union for all of campus.  To the east is main street and the rest of Celduin.

name: Main Street
description: To the north and south continue Main Steet.  To the west you can see a shoppe with a large wooden sign hanging in front of it.  The sign has a shield on it that says, "Discount Armor."  Another armor shop is a little farther north, on the other side of the street, next to the park.

name: Trunbull's Fine Armor
description: Racks of different kinds of armor line the wall, but the sizes are enormous. Even the owner here is a half-giant, and and he looks down on you from his four meters of height.  He waits impatiently for you to either buy something or leave.  Oh, yeah....   He doesn't approve of shoplifting.

name: Storage Room for Trunbull's Fine Armory
Plasnelt Road/Wall Road West
description: Plasnelt Road goes all the way across the village in an east-west direction. Wall Road West parallels the western village wall.  This is the better part of the village, and a number of old mansions are on the east side of the road.  Lately, a few shops have been established to service the homes.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: A small park is on the south side of Plasnelt Road.  Trees and gardens with well kept paths can be seen.  There are park benches, and if you are in need of rest, it might be a nice place to sit and think for awhile. You might consider this:  Why does everyone want to kill everything in sight?  What's the meaning of this cycle of death followed by life?

name: Plasnelt Road
description: A very ornate gate set in a tall, stone wall partially hides a mansion on the north side of Plasnelt Road.  Just inside the gate there is a pair of guards, each wearing a crimson coat and a high, fur hat.  They stand stiffly, as if made of wood.  A flag snaps in the breeze just above the guard station at the gate.  A general store is on the south side of the road.

name: Brownhaven Way/Plasnelt Road
description: You are in the nicer part of the village and see many fine homes along the roads.  You can go along Plasnelt Road to the east toward the center of the village, or west toward the village gate.  There are a lot of nice shops and stores going north and south.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: Off in the distance to the northeast you can see a large building of some sort.  You can barely hear yells and screams from inside -- sounds like an arena.  On the south side is a small shop with three brass balls hanging over the door.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: There are a number of small shops along here on the south side of the road.  On the north side is an impressive building where a lot of noise can be heard.  There are posters plastered all over the building's wall, and it looks like you could challenge a gladitor, if you wanted to.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: The road continues east and west.  Not far to the east you can see the intersection with Main Street.  On the north side of the road there is a very large building, which seems to be some sort of arena.  A sign says the entrance is on Main Street.  Sure is a lot of noise in there.

name: Plasnelt Road/Main Street
description: Main Street is the major north-south street, while Plasnelt Road runs across the village in an east-west direction.  On the southeast corner there is a large stable and several barns.  Merchants often sponsor expeditions to the Kista Forest, and pack animals are needed to make up a caravan.  There is a thriving trade with the gnomish craftsmen who live in the forest.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: To the north and south are the village parks which provide picnic areas for visitors.  Over time, it has become a tradition that the people from the west side of the village use the northen park, while the poor people who live to the east usually go to the south park.

name: South Bridge
description: The water flows from the heights of the mysterious Mount Caledonia, which has never been fully mapped.  Many adventurers have made expeditions to it, but few have returned.  The water is cold and refreshing, and is the main source of drinking water for the village.

name: Wall Road West
description: One of the richest families in the village is that of squire Frebineb, a very old name in hobbitry society.  The squire's family has lived here since the village was founded, and his ancesters helped drive off the mountian trolls when they attacked centuries ago.  Since that time there have been minor skirmishes, and the squire's relatives have always been the first to volunteer for the dangerous jobs.  His mansion is east of the road.

name: Legolas' Private Study
description: As you curiously scan this room you find that it is constantly changing. Strange animals enter from time to time and you hear a booming voice echo : There is absolutely no killing allowed in this room.  Punishable by death!

name: Wall Road West
description: There is a very old but well kept mansion on the east side of the road.  It belongs to squire Frebineb, the commander of the Brownhaven militia. A wide path leads east to the carriage house on the estate.  On the west side you see the high wall that surrounds the village.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: A large mansion with a gated wall sits on beautifully kept grounds to the west.  Large trees grow close to the wall, and limbs hang over to the other side.  The gate appears to be locked.  If one were interested in climbing, these trees certainly look like they could be climbed easily.

name: Discount Armor Shoppe
description: A big, dumb looking half-giant stands behind the counter, wearing a leather apron and a slack-jawed look.  His eyes are quite dull, so don't ask for advice.  He might give you some, and if you took it, you might be sorry.  He has a list of armor for sale.  If you are looking for small-race armor, why don't you try across the street?

name: Main Street Militia Headquarters
description: Guards handle most of their daily business here.  To the south is their private rec room.  A number of them can be seen coming and going.  They look at you funny, and you hear the remark, "who's the wimp?"

name: Main Street
description: The shrine of the White Rose, a holy chapel for paladins, is on the east side of Main Street.  Across the street on the west side is the militia guard station for this area of the village.  Farther to the north, on the east side, is a stable.  You can see South Plasnelt Park much farther to the east, behind the stable area.

name: Caledon's Secret Inner Sanctuary
description: High above the city of Oceancrest is a strange and mysterious room that Caledon uses for special projects and tests.  Not just anyone can get here.  There are scattered tomes and large books lying around with various maps and diagrams scattered throughout.

name: Detention and Rehabilitation Center
description: You are buried hundreds of meters below ground level in a cell quarried out of grey marble.  The only opening you can find is a narrow slit, barely large enough to put your hand in, which lets light and air come from the surface down a tiny shaft.  The walls are smooth and seamless with no exit.  Although Oceancrest prides itself on the name of this institution, do not be deceived.  Prisoners in this cell are never rehabilitated and must spend the rest of their life (and then some) in this small room.  You will never again be a part of society, but you may  send or receive mail.

name: Prison Storage Room
description: This is the storage room where a prisoner's belongings are kept.  However, few prisoners have ever been known to leave the Detention and Rehabilitation alive or dead, and so the stuff in here is seldom reclaimed.

name: Brownhaven Way
description: The street is almost park-like in its setting, and the shops are set with wide distances between them and grassy walkways.  To the west is small white building where you can hear cries of relief.  Looking south, you can see the southern section of the wall which surrounds the village. There is a cemetery with an odd tree in it on the east side of the street.

name: Nanette's Spa and Massage
description: Nanette has the best healing hands to be found, and the spa is the most relaxing you can find.  At one time, Nanette studied to be a mage, but  after a few spells went awry, she decided it wasn't the profession for her.  Her best friend is still a toad, and she continues to try to change him back.    Now if she could only decide which toad is him.

name: Guard's Rec Room
description: The guards are bothered by you.  Oops, looks like you got yourself in a bit of trouble.  You might be able to grab one of the nice, new weapons you see in a rack by the door, if you need it.  Then again, you might not.

name: Main Street
description: A large building on the west side glistens in the light.  It seems to be plated with some sort of metal.  Could it be gold?  At each corner there is a tall, round tower with an even taller spire atop it.  Lightning and static seems to ionize the air between the two towers at the front of the building.  Across the street on the east side is a school for thieves  and pickpockets.

name: Brownhaven Thieve's Guild
description: Pickpocketing and burglery are the main courses taught here, but others are occasionally taught in seminars.  Successful students must pay a proportion of their earnings, according to the level they have achieved.

name: Wall Road West/Nathan Drive
description: You are at the southwest corner of the city, where the commander of the militia has his office.  An honor guard maintains a small barracks on the corner.  Looking east, you see a line of posh little shops which cater to the expensive tastes of the higher class in Brownhaven.

name: Nathan Drive
description: You are also just south of a string of expensive little shops, where you can buy most anything if you have the gold.  Directly north of you is a jewelry shop.  Next door is a shop which is known to specialize in footwear for all races.  The shop belongs to a very old hobbitish shoemaker.

name: Nathan Drive
description: You are walking near the southern village wall, near several nice little shops.  North of you is the only herb kitchen in the village.  Herbs can be very costly, depending on what they can do for you.  The road continues to the east and west from here.

name: Brownhaven Way/Nathan Drive
description: Nathan Drive runs parallel to the village wall.  Brownhaven Way is one of the nicer streets in the village, and as you look north, it appears to be a shady, tree lined street with quiet little shops tucked into amongst the bushes.  There's an odd looking tree growing here, however.  Looks  like it may well be several hundred years old.  It stands in a very small cemetery on the northeast side of the intersection.

name: Nathan Drive
description: On the north side of the road is an old church, which used to belong to a hobbitish congregation, but was abandoned when a group of screaming ghosts invaded it from the cemetery next door.  The church door hangs open, and no one has ever had the courage to nail it shut.   Nathan Drive runs to the east and west from here.

name: Nathan Drive
description: A large warehouse is on the north side of the road, and another building is on the other side of it.  Painted on the side of the warehouse is a  new sign.  It says, "We make the finest rods and staves in all of the Land or Mordor.  Our mages can enchant them for any purpose.  Try us."

name: Nathan Drive
description: There is a warehouse on the north side of the road, and the entrance seems to be a little further to the west.  A building with twin minerets stands to the east a short distance.  Looks like the entrance is around the corner. There is a clerical supply store next door the the warehouse.

name: Main Street/Nathan Drive
description: Main Street has most of the commerical and entertainment places located on it.  It continues to the north, running to the village wall on the other side of Town Square.  A lot of the entertainment in Browhaven tends to be rather bloody, since the culture is not up to that of Kista or Oceancrest.

name: Champion's Ready Room
description: This is a healing room reserved for arena champions.  Anyone who comes in here is a fighter who has won many battles on the arena floor.  A healing mage stands by, ready to cast healing spells on any who needs them.  She is impartial in whom she treats, and will treat everyone, but if you want a spell cast on you, you must ask her for it.

name: Goldenrod Avenue/East Ulandia
description: Goldenrod Avenue is to the east.  Directly west is the banks of the Baldywyne, a fast moving river which flows from the mysterious heights of Mount Caledonia.  There is a boat rental for those interested in  seeing the river first-hand.  A small sword shoppe, with glittering blades on display, is next door.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: To the west is the end of the avenue.  From here its possible to see the intersection with East Ulandia, which runs north and south through the village.  Further west you can see the banks of the rives which separates the two parts of the village.  The eastern part of the village is mostly used for low-rent housing and huge warehouses.  The militia also keeps equipment here.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: There are a number of small shops and stores along the south side of the road.  There's nothing but a great, brown wall on the other side.  The brown color of the wall is how the village got its name, by the way.  Atop the wall you can see a few lounging village militia, who are supposed to be on lookout duty.  Mostly they just look for pretty girls on this side of the wall, however.

name: Goldenrod Avenue
description: The north wall is covered with grafitti, some of it several hundred years old.  There are many names scrawled on the wall that any long-time resident of the Land of Mordor would recognize:  Pyro, Conan, Princess, Ogre, Fin, Omnipotent, Niemand, Eastman, Ironwolf, Arcana, Shadowhawk, and many more.

name: Goldenrod Avenue/Taragon Road
description: A large guard tower stands at the intersetion of the north and east walls. There is a long ramp also, which is used to move heavy equipment to the top of the wall.  Stored near the base of the ramp are several old and obsolete catapults, but the village is reluctant to dismantle them, since they are still in working condition.

name: East Ulandia
description: Great pepper trees and weeping willows line the bank of the river, and a gentle, grassy slope runds down to the water's edge.  On the east side of the road is an open-air market with scores of vendors and milling customers. Gayly colored and brightly striped tents are set up as vending booths, and a number of very strange races can be seen.

name: Thieve's Guild
description: Checking your inventory, you begin to wander who...

name: Taragon Road
description: The barns you see contain food and other necessities in the event of a long-term siege.  Once, about six hundred years ago, the village was  attacked by mountain trolls and the residents almost starved before they drove the trolls away.  Since that time, the village has stored just about anything you can imagine in there.

name: East Ulandia
description: On the east side of the road is a huge, dusty lot where an open-air market has been established.  There are pennants flying, and banners everywhere. It looks like the annual Brownhaven Fair has arrived.

name: Taragon Road
description: Looking south, you can see the eastern village gate and the intersection with Caledonia Way.  To the north are the village's storage barns and silos. The surrounding farms keep Brownhaven well supplied with food, and in the event of a long-term siege the village could probably hold out for several years.  Of course, that's not likely, but its best to be prepared.

name: Caledonia Road/East Ulandia
description: Caledonia Road crosses a bridge going west, and East Ulandia runs north and south parallel to the river.  On the northeast corner there are a great many tents and temporary booths set up in a great outdoor fair. There are certainly a lot of people wandering around looking at things over there.

name: Caledonia Road/Poor Alley
description: You are in a very shabby part of the village, and everywhere you look, you see tiny, makeshift houses.  They appear to have be constructed of anything that was at hand.  The house on the corner was apparently made from old packing boxes, each labeled, "Uland Rum."  A rather wide alley extends to the south.  People who live here refer to it as Poor Alley.

name: Caledonia Road
description: Ramshackle houses are packed closely together on both sides of the road, and people are hanging out windows, talking to each other.  A small church is almost to the corner on the north side, but why is there an upside down cross outside, and why is the head of a horned billy goat proudly on display at the door?

name: East Gate
description: Caledonia Road to the west will take you to the center of the village. Taragon Road follows along the eastern village wall to the north and south. The great gate is almost always open, and leads out of the village.  The only time it closes is after sundown, except in times of emergency.  There is a city militia barracks a short distance to the north.

name: East Ulandia
description: There's a lot of cheering and noise coming from the building to the east. A large poster indicates the building houses a cock fighting arena.  The poster says that there is no-limit betting allowed, and your bet of any size will be covered.  There's a picture of two fighting cocks staring at each other, and the print underneath says they are both undefeated.

name: Poor Alley
description: There s a surprisingly large number of peoplw in this dark and cold alley. Many of them are going to a wine shop located down some stairs.  Next door is a missionary.  A group of missionary musicians stand outside, playing in a small band and loudly proclaiming that all sinners will go to hell and be eaten by Fenris.  A fat lady in an ankle-length black dress bangs a tambourine against her ample hip, and wildly rolls her eyes as she sings.

name: Mordichi's Wine Shoppe
description: You are below ground level in a cool and dark cellar which belongs to Mordichi the wine merchant.  Mordichi specializes in bottles of the cheaper variety of wines.  If you wish to buy in bulk, there is a 1000 gallon cask standing in the center of the room.  A number of people are here with empty jugs, waiting their turn at the cask spigot.

name: Taragon Road
description: On the east side is a vine-covered wall which surrounds the village, and on the west side is a dim little pub known as the Deft Hand.  It's not a real popular place because more people go in there than come out.  The village militia seem to have a hands-off policy concerning the Deft Hand, as they never go in, except to collect a handful of gold and then leave.

name: East Ulandia
description: A row of nice little shops are on the east side of the road, each appearing to be clean and neat.  There's a wild-game butcher shop directly east, and next door to that is a tiny little restaurant with chairs and tables set out on the walk so that customers can enjoy the view of the river.

name: Poor Alley
description: There is a chapter of the Begger's Guild on the west side of this disgusting throughfare, and an open door on the east side is a Conjurer's Guild.  The beggers coming out of the guild seems to be mostly maimed and blind, but some get around amazingly well in spite of their apparent handicap.  A very strong and unpleasant odor wafts on the breeze.

name: Taragon Road
description: A few steps north is the Deft Hand, a rather dark and dismal little place. Immediately to the west is a tailor's shop, which advertises they can fit a half-giant or an elf.  A number of nice looking capes are on display in the window, and a couple of wizard's gowns are on display dummys.

name: East Ulandia
description: A row of some of the better shops for this part of the village are on the east side of the road.  There seems to be small living quarters above each shop, and the sidewalk is swept clean in front each store. A wooden sign swings in the breeze over the door of a store that seems to specialize in leather armor for mages.

name: Sharkey's Bordello
description: As you look about, you notice a wonderfully sexy woman, who gives you a wink back.  It must be time for you to make your move.  The furniture seems to be rather shabby and poorly kept, and the doctor's certificate on the wall is long out of date.  The place has a very musty smell to it.

name: Poor Alley
description: This place doesn't smell very good, and you are constantly being pulled at by grubby and dirty hands.  Beggers plead for money, and sneakthieves look you over to see where you purse might be.  If you had a serious fight here, there's not much room, and who knows how many of them might decide to gang together against you?  There seems to be some action to the west.

name: Quaymanire's Repair Shop
description: A huge forge gives off an immense amount of heat as you stand here. Racks of used armor and gleaming swords and daggers line the wall, and a half-giant wearing a leather apron waits behind the counter.  he looks a little impatient.

name: Taragon Road
description: The mayor's office keeps promising to send a construction crew to repair the wall, but it has ben seventeen years since a copper dragon crashed into the wall, destroying a section of it and killing the dragon's rider.  Through the break in the wall, you can see sheep in a green pasture, and a heavily wooded area further to the east.  On the west side of the road is a fortune teller's small shack.

name: Plasnelt Road/East Ulandia
description: Plasnelt Road continues east and west, while East Ulandia meanders along the banks of the Baldywyne River.  To the west you can see the South Bridge, which crosses over to the west part of the village.  The bridge is safe enough during the day, but many bad things have been reported about it at night.  Some say there is a monster that lives under it who sleeps by day.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: There are several wagons pulled up at the gate, and some are waiting to enter while a few are just leaving.  There is a gatekeeper holding a key and waving the wagons through.  Looks like there is a small administration building for the disposal pits just to the east.  On the north side of the road there is a stone cutter's place of business.  A sign says, "Why not order your tombstone while you can enjoy it?"

name: Plasnelt Road/Poor Alley
description: A fighting academy is located on the north side, near the entrance to the alley.  The only way many of the kids who grow up in this section of the village can ever escape poverty is to fight their way out, and perhaps be hired by some rich family to serve as a bodyguard.  The academy helps to train many of them.

name: Plasnelt Road
description: The village of Brownhaven sits at the western end of Gotland Glenn, near the eastern edge of the Nartiz Mountain Range.  It's a rather idealic spot, but its proximity to Mount Aphinix means its sometimes subject to raids by mountain trolls.   On the north side of the road there is a repair shop.

name: Plasnelt Road/Taragon Road
description: Taragon Road runs north and south, and a militia armory is on the corner. Long ago the wise village elders recognized the need for a militia, so they set up a barracks and recruited the nastiest and meanest citizens they could for the job.  The tradition has continued to this day.  However, knowing the ways of drunken militia, they wisely put the armory at the opposite end of town from the main barracks.

name: East Ulandia
description: Most of the bank for as far as you can see is lush and green, but for some reason, there's no vegetation here.  The ground looks absolutely sterile, without even a weed growing.  In places it even looks scorched. The Brownhaven South Bridge is just up the road to the north, and this unhappy condition seems to extend to the underside of the bridge.

name: The Northern Dump
description: Constant fires burn here twenty four hours a day, every day.  Not only does the garbage of the village get burned, but since there is such a limited amount of space in the cemetery, many of the poor who die also wind up here, thrown on some garbage pile waiting to be torched.  Rats and some larger animal you cannot quite identify seem to be running in all directions,  looking for food.

name: Assassin's Guild
description: Its a strange feeling, since the room appears to be empty, but you feel as if there are eyes watching you from every corner of this dark, little room. A small note lies on the floor.  It reads, "Assassins for hire.  Enquire within."  If anyone were here, you probably could ask where experienced assassins train for a higher level.

name: Taragon Road
description: There is a ladder leaning against the village wall and it looks as though you could make it to the top easily.  Why anyone other than the militia might want to do that is another matter.   Taragon Road continues to the north and south from here.  A trickle of sewage disappears into a street drain.

name: East Ulandia
description: The cave is on a vacant lot to the east, and seems to be a tunnel that heads in the direction of the Brownhaven Garbage Pits.  There's a rotten smell coming the entrance to the cave.  A little to north of the cave entrance there is an old wooden shack.  Someone appears to be living  there as smoke issues from a slender smoke stack.  Even the smoke stinks.

name: The Southern Dump
description: The disposal is swarming with flies and rats, searching for any scrap of food (or dung) they can get their nasty little teeth into.  Boy, does this garbage heap stink.  If you drop anything, you'll never get it back.

name: Taragon Road
description: This is a rather desolate area of the village with a great many boarded up houses and shops.  A sign on one of the shop doors, which looks as though it has been closed for a long time, says, "Beware the Red Fever." A sign on the shop next door says, "This place for sale.  Cheap."  The road you are on is not far from southeast corner of the village.

name: Phexton Road/East Ulandia
description: You can go east or north, but you are in a corner of the village, and  cannot go in any other direction.  There is a speciality armor shop on the corner, catering only to large sized people.  Seems like blatent discrimination, but who's going to complain?  The owner is a retired fighter who rose to a very high level in the ranks of fighters.

name: Phexton Road
description: A rather ornate little shop can be seen on the north side of the road.  A sign over the door says a resident healer can make you well again, no matter what condition you are in, as long as you can make it through the door.  Next door to the healer is another little shop that seems to specialize in Tarot cards for fortune tellers.  All manner of them are on display.

name: Phexton Road
description: On the north side of the road is a tacky little shop with three brass balls suspended over the door.  A sign on the door says, "No questions asked."  Inside, you see a fat little gnome fingering his gold.  The village wall on the south side of the road seems to be getting higher in the eastern direction.

name: Phexton Road
description: The great, brown wall on the south side of the road is much higher here than most of the wall.  Strange that the builders would deliberately make this section so much different from the rest of the uniform wall.  A series of steps will take you to the top, if you desire to go that way.  There used to be a village law about citizens climbing up there, but then the elders decided there was no harm in it, so feel free to climb if you desire.

name: Phexton Road/Taragon Road
description: There appears to be a narrow alley tucked in between a brick warehouse and an old theater, long since closed and nailed shut.  The alley is on the  northwest side of the corner, and apparently runs at an angle for a short ways before making a turn.  It's impossible to see very far in the alley. The village wall makes a right angle turn here.

name: Vickers House Front Room
description: White sheets cover the furniture, which in turn are covered with a fine layer of dust.  Nothing has been moved in this room since the death of old man Vickers.  His coffin still stands in the middle of the living room.

name: Vickers House Library
description: Bookshelves extend from floor to ceiling on three walls of the room.  The windows on the fourth wall are so covered with dust that you cannot see out. A large wooden desk, covered with a sheet, and a leather couch are the only furniture.  It looks as though someone has been searching here.  You see books scattered on the floor.

name: Vickers House Music Room
description: A grand piano is near the window, and several chairs and music stands form a ring in the center of the room.  There is a harpsicord and bass viola with several other instruments near the door.  Rumor has it that Lady Vickers could charm the dead and sooth the undead with her music.  You feel an invisible force in the room, and hear the faint sounds of a flute.

name: Vickers House Dining Room
description: This is the elegant dining room of the Vickers House. A very long table with at least a dozen chairs around it takes up most of the center of the room.  At one time the Vickers family was the leader in Brownhaven's social and community gatherings.  At least until the present mayor killed old man Vickers in a card game.  The two young Vickers boys were taken to their uncle's in a tiny village of Phexton in the mountains. No one knows what happened to Lady Vickers.  Perhaps suicide?

name: Butler's Pantry in the Vickers House
description: There is an unlocked liquor cabinet here, and a trapdoor leads to the wine cellar.  This is where the good silver and fine china was stored.

name: Magic Shop
description: You see Mythrandir floating in front of you, waiting for your order. There are not too many magical potions shops here in the village, so  this little place does a pretty good business.

name: Storage Shack
description: This shack is for Magic Shop storage only.

name: Bags and Lights Store
description: It's really odd that a store could stay in business when all they sell are bags and a few other things.  The store owner prides himself on his vast selection on all kinds of bags, and seems to do a thriving business.

name: Weaponsmith
description: Standing behind the counter is Jarl Thornthistle, Brownhaven's most renowned weaponsmith.  He's currently pounding the dents out of an old vorpal sword. When he sees you enter his shop, he looks up at you briefly and returns to his work.

name: Storage Shack
description: It is probably used by the weaponsmith to hold surplus when he's got too much stock.

name: Starrine's Armor Shoppe
description: As you walk through the door, you notice attractive pieces of small armor hung on pegs all about the room.  Behind a counter in the back of the shoppe stands a swarthy little man who looks as if he's probably killed a few dragons in his day.  He only sells armor for small races.

name: Storage Shack
description: This shack is for Armor Shop storage only.

name: Secret Archive Room
description: Stacked up on shelves all around you are fat books and glass-encased scrolls. None of them interest you particularly, however.  The library is up.

name: Main Ball Room
description: A loud and drunken party is taking place, and a piano is being played loudly in the corner of the grand room.  A wide stairway leads upstairs, and a veranda runs around the entire outside of the house.  Through the south french doors you see a view of the bay and a long dock where a pirate ship is moored.  Most of the men are crew members from that ship.

name: Wide Stairs
description: Below you is the main ball room where a wild party is in full swing, and above you is a long hallway with at least a dozen bedrooms.  There is a bright red carpet covering the stairs, but it looks like blood has stained it a darker red in places.  Madame Ruthie hires some tough bouncers.

name: Upstairs Hallway
description: Madame Ruthie believes in two things, money and pleasure, and has found a way to combine them.  Roaring laughter comes from several of the rooms, while from the others you hear grunts and squeals.  Several doors are open, and you avert your eyes as you pass.  (Well, you sorta avert them.)

name: Blue Room
description: A huge feather bed takes up most of the room, and soft light comes from a candle-lit hurricane lamp at the side of the bed.  The great bed is in total disarray, with pillows on the floor and covers in a heap.  Leather shackles are mounted on the headboard, and a smoky mirror is overhead on the ceiling.

name: Green Room
description: The Green Room is reserved for Madame Ruthie's oldest customer's and is quite rich in its furnishings.  Silk pillows are stacked everywhere, and brocaded covers are on the bed.  Soft lamp light flickers in the room, giving a pleasant glow to the beautiful materials.  An open window looks over the bay, and birds twitter outside.

name: Red Room
description: There are no frills here, just a stout bed and several strong wooden chairs with a makeup table and mirror against one wall.  An open closet is stuffed with furs, long gowns and silks.  Only long-time friends of the madame ever see the inside of this room.  Are you one of her oldest friends?

name: Back Bedroom
description: This is the bedroom for quick service, and the traffic in and out is pretty heavy.  There are several beds here, and even a pallet on the floor for those who can't wait.  There is a strong smell of unwashed and sweaty bodies in the room, but it's not really that unpleasant.  Madame Ruthie makes money by the high volume here, because even the poorest of customers can get what they came in for.

name: Storage Closet
description: Madame Ruthie has a rule that the only way you can leave this room is totally naked, prepared for a little action.  Her motto is keep 'em moving. There are a number of valuable pieces of armor and weapons in here, but it would probably make someone mad if you took what isn't yours.  When he remembers to do it, a drunken old dwarf will retrieve your clothes and armor for you, and return them to you when you leave, if you have paid your bill.

name: Foyer of the old mansion
description: Before you to the north lies a large, twisting staircase that leads up into the unknown darkness of the house above.  To the east is what appears to be a living room of some sort, except that it hasn't been lived in for ages.  To the west is another room which you are unable to see very well.

name: Living room
description: There are old, rotting couches lining the walls of this room, and cobweb-crusted tables in the center.  An occasional rat or mouse runs past your feet as you walk through what they have made their home.

name: The Mansion Dining Hall
description: To the north the dining hall continues, while the foyer lies to the east.  There is a huge dining table in the center of the room made completely of varnished oak.  It's covered in cobwebs now, and there are even dining placements still at the table.

name: North end of the Dining Hall
description: The dining hall continues to stretch to the south, and a narrow hallway leads to the north.  Off to the east there is what appears to be a kitchen where food was obviously prepared for this dining room.

name: Kitchen
description: A huge oven, a kettle and a large rinse sink cover the east and south walls of this kitchen.  Like everything else in this mansion, none of them appear to have been used within the last several years.  Everything is cobweb-covered.

name: Dark Hallway
description: To the south you can see what appears to be a very large dining hall with a regal-looking dining table in it.  Directly to the north is a beautiful mahogany door.

name: Study
description: There is a plush reclining chair in the corner of the room sitting under a long burnt-out lantern.  In front of the chair is a mahogany desk with old papers strewn across its surface.

name: Hallway
description: At the north end of the hallway is a wooden door beyond which you suspect is a bedroom.  The living room of the mansion is the large room south of this one.  You hear some are odd noises for a deserted house.

name: Secret Alcove
description: The passage, from which you entered the alcove, leads south back into the living room, and a hatch in the floor probably leads down into a basement of some sort.  The only problem is that it is padlocked.

name: Bedroom
description: An old canopy bed rests against the northern wall, completely covered in cobwebs and dust.  An occasional spider can be seen walking across its moth-eaten covers.  A portrait of a handsome woman hangs on the eastern wall.  Strangely enough it has not been harmed over the years by wear and tear.  The same cannot be said, however, for the room's wallpaper.  It's full of blotchy holes where spiders and other little critters now live.

name: Top of the Stairwell
description: The stairs twist in a corkscrew-like manner from this floor to the one below. There is a hallway that extends from east to west, and you see a door in the west wall.  At least it might be a doorway.  It's really difficult to tell with all the cobwebs covering everything.

name: Hallway
description: A dusty, old oaken door is set in the wall to the north, and the hallway  heads east toward a large, twisting stairwell and west toward a corner in the hall.

name: Den
description: The den looks more like a spook-shop now, though.  It's covered with creepy cobwebs and all the paintings are knocked off the wall or smeared with centimeters of dust.

name: Southwestern Hallway Corner
description: Back to the east is the stairwell which led you here.  To the north is another cobwebbed-filled hallway and a rather long one at that.  You can't quite tell what is at the end of it.

name: Western Hallway
description: You can hear eerie, clanging noises coming from a large room to the north. Back to the south the hallway makes a turn toward the east.

name: Southeastern Hallway Corner
description: The hallway continues to the north and the west.  On a western wall to the north you can see a door.

name: Eastern Hallway
description: On the western wall is a door, probably leading into a bedroom of some sort.  From the north you can hear an eerie, clanging noise, but you're not quite sure what it is.

name: Decrepit Training Room
description: Old and rotting fencing paraphernalia lie across the floor of the room, draped in a delicate fabric of dusty cobwebs.  Old foils, fencing gear and trophies have been left in practically every corner of this very large room.  All the valuables have either been looted or destroyed.

name: Musty Basement Entrance
description: There is a ladder leading up to the hatch from which you entered the basement.  Loud and disturbing creaking noises can be heard from all around you, except that it's completely dark so you don't know where they are coming from.  The basement opens up toward the west.

name: Western Basement
description: Old bits of memorabilia and worm-eaten clothing that no one would dare to wear anymore are piled up or strewn across the floor of this basement.  You probably should stay away from the clothing, for fear of whatever might be living under it.  This is a spooky place, indeed.

name: Northeastern corner of the Basement
description: A dirty pile of worthless things is sitting along the northern wall  gathering dust and cobwebs.  On the eastern wall near the corner is a  small wooden chair with the word "Evan" written on its back.

name: Southwest Corner of the Basement
description: This basement has not been visited by anyone in ages.  You can tell by all the tracks you're leaving in the dust and by the untouched cobwebs. Everything here has a damp and musty smell to it.

name: Southeastern Corner of the Basement
description: A wall separates you from the ladder and hatch to the north, while the basement continues off to the west.  A pungent, musty smell overtakes your senses.  It's almost the smell of death.

name: Child's Bedroom
description: You can tell by the size of the canopy bed that stands against the northern wall.  It's much too small for an adult.  Of course, no child would want to live in this room now  it's full of insects, cobwebs, dust and ...??

name: Central Sewer Channels
description: One stream of water runs northwest to southeast, and another runs from northeast to southwest.  It's not so deep that you can't walk in it, so all four exits are a distinct travelling possibility for you.  Above you is the sewer grate through with many adventurers (as well as sewer workers and other nasties) enter the sewage canals.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The sounds of scurrying rats and other varmints echo off the walls of these sewers.

name: Valve chamber
description: There are dozens of valves along the southern wall of the room.  You have no idea what parts of the sewer they might open (if any at all).

name: Sewer Passage
description: Brownish-gray water floods past your legs as you walk through this dank, cool sewer.

name: Sewer T-Intersection
description: To the south is another sewer passage, and to the west you can see a small room of some sort.  A small leak above your head is letting in quite a bit of water.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The water in this passage of the sewer smells horrible, mostly because it is almost completely stagnant.  There is a door on the sewer ledge that rises out of the floor to the south.

name: Sewer Valve Chamber
description: Several rusty valves and valve-wheels stand up against the western wall of this dark and humid valve chamber.  A loud hissing noise can be heard coming from behind the wall to the north -- a sound like steam.

name: Drainage Chamber
description: Water rushes into this chamber through small holes in the bottom of all four walls.  As you stare down into the huge drains upon which you stand, you see only deep, dark blackness.  The water sounds as if it hits the bottom miles below.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The stench that fills this passage is overpowering.  Either something has died here, or else you're directly beneath one of the town's public  bathrooms.

name: Fork in the Sewer Passage
description: Curious scraping and scratching sounds can be heard coming both from the north and from the west.

name: Sewer Hallway
description: Curiously there is little water running through this sewer passage.  Upon closer inspection, you notice that it is because there are several large drains at the eastern end of the hallway.

name: Dead End
description: Not only is this a dead end figuratively, but also literally.  Corpses of dead rats and other rodents litter the floor of this passage, making you wish you had lost your nose to a ranger's long sword.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The sewer water flows freely here, and nearly reaches your hips as you struggle to make your way through it.

name: Sewer Valve Chamber
description: It is here where sewer workers are able to open and close certain drains throughout parts of the sewers.  This are many other valve chambers like this one scattered through the sewer.

name: Fork in the Sewer Passage
description: One passage heads to the southwest, while two other lead north and east.

name: Sewer Passage
description: A small pipe in the northern wall is not so small that you can't scurry your way through it.

name: Cramped Sewer Alcove
description: Several families of rodents must make their homes here, because there  droppings absolutely carpet the floor.  You are unable to avoid stepping in them.

name: Sewer Passage
description: You're surprised to notice just how complex the Oceancrest sewer system actually is.  It seems to run underneath all the major buildings of the city, and would seem to be a weak spot in the city's defensive system.

name: Sewer T-Intersection
description: At the end of the passage to the west you can see a stone door of some sort, but cannot make out any other details.  The passage continues on endlessly to the east and south.

name: Sewer Passage and Stone Door
description: Upon closer inspection, you notice that the door has been etched with the words "STAY OUT."  A few small blots of blood are noticeable on the floor directly below the door.

name: Accident Room
description: Huge piles of rubble cover the floors, and several nicely-stacked piles of bones lay in each of the room's corners.  Blood has been splattered across the walls in a random and completely hideous fashion leading you to wonder just what kind of accident took place here.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The water is not so high here, however.  It rises only to your ankles. A small drainage hole can be seen on the floor of the southern wall.

name: Secret Sewer Chamber
description: Several pornographic pictures are hung upon the walls, probably the mark of a sewer worker who hasn't visited the bordello in quite some time. A little desk with several papers including some old blueprints for the sewer system is resting against the southern wall.

name: Sewer Y-Intersection
description: Passages lead to the northwest, west and south.  However, the water only travels south and west due to a high-wall placed across the northwestern passage entrance.  It's just high enough to step over.

name: Dry Sewer Passage
description: This passage is completely dry due to the fact that a high-wall was used at the southeastern end of it to keep the sewer water from the south out of here.

name: Circular Room
description: You're led to wonder what a room like this is doing in the sewer.  After considering it for several minutes, you finally come to the conclusion  that it must have been used by some religous cult.  Mystical markings and  animals skulls sit atop obsidian black tables all throughout the room. Tablets with strange letters marked upon them stand shakily against the northern wall.

name: Sewer Passage
description: The sound of running water can be heard from the south, while the sound of dripping sewer water can be heard to the north.

name: Edge of a Black Hole
description: It's really strange, but you cannot hear the dripping water hit the bottom. There used to be a guard rail here, but scavengers took it long ago and sold it at the recycling center for five gold pieces.

name: Below the South Bridge
description: You spy a small door in the massive bridge pier, but its closed.   Lucky for you it's not open, because there's a bloody trail to it.  Lying about are rotting pieces of flesh, and rusted pieces of armor.  Strange that they haven't been noticed and given a proper burial.

name: Large Ocean Going Raft
description: There seems to be crates of fruit and large kegs of beer and other spirits stored here.  There are a number of hammocks strung below the canvas sun- shade which look quite inviting.  The tranquil sounds of the water lapping against the side and the smell of the sea air may help you to relax after your long swim.

name: Salvage Boat
description: The boat is larger than you thought, and appears a little worse for wear, but it looks quite seaworthy and apparently it can hold large amounts of treasure.  A couple of nasty looking brutes are guarding the hatch which leads below.  The captain is followed by a diminitive elf, who has a set of books under his arm.  He is the clerk, and apparently does all the buying for the captain.

name: Wedding Shop
description: This is a one-stop shop for all your wedding needs.  You may leave mail here for the DM describing your coming wedding, and later you will be able to buy wedding invitations here.  Be sure to specify the time, date and location of your coming marriage, and the name of your intended.  You may buy a sample invitation at any time.

name: Pier Lithium Imports
description: The store overlooks the Lithium Bay, where ships, carrying a variety of goods from far away lands, dock daily to trade with the Oceancrest  merchants.  A great variety of goods and services may be purchased here. You must contact the Dungeonmasters if you wish to do business.

name: Entrance to the Avatar Ruins
description: The Avatar Ruins were supposedly created eons ago when the avatars of the gods clashed, creating odd rock formations and even stranger anti- magic zones.  The Avatar Ruins are one such zone where no magic can be used against anyone else.

name: Avatar Ruins Central Path
description: The land looks like it's been turned upside down many times until just rocks and dirt are left.  The strange place seems to lack just about any sort of natural beauty, as if the gods just turned their back on the area.  Oddly enough, no magic works in this area as well.

name: Avatar Ruins West Intersection
description: The path through the Ruins splits here, heading to the north, south,  east and west.  The path to the west leads back towards the entrance to the Ruins.  There are to large, mountainous structures located to the  north and south.

name: Avatar Ruins Center Path
description: There are two predominant structures in the Ruins, those being the two large mountain-like masses located to the north and south.  These strange structures look like massive chunks the the ground were thrust up by unnatural forces, creating these odd formations.

name: Avatar Ruins Center Path
description: The Avatar Ruins are rumored to have been created by the massive destruction caused by the fighting avatars.  Although this is just superstition, many people like to believe that supernatural forces created regions of land such as this where magic appears to have no effect.

name: Avatar Ruins East Intersection
description: The center path joins the outer paths which circle around the two  mountain-like structures located to the north and south.  The center path runs to the west, and the outer paths run to the north and south.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: This path runs around the northern mountainous structure that you can see to the northwest.  The strange surface looks very jagged and sharp, making it very dangerous to climb.  The structure starts from almost nothing on the ground, seeming to appear out of nothingness.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: The outer path circles around the northern structure which you can see to the south.  The strange mountain-like rock appears to just come out of the ground, with no sign of any prior instability.  This, coupled with the fact that magic has no effect here suggests that something might be amiss.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: Occassionally, you can see small animals flying about in the Ruins, but seldom do they seem to attack you.  They appear to just be watching your progress from a distance.  At times, they may come close enough to  examine you, but it's hard to make out just what they are.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: The path you are on reaches the northernmost point of the Avatar Ruins here, sweeping away from the mountain-like structure you see to the southeast.  The path runs towards the structure to the southeast, and around the northern side to the east.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: The path comes unusually close to the mountain-like object you have been walking around.  It appears to just come out of the ground, with no granularity at all.  The sharp peaks and edges make the mountain look unclimbable, but you do see some niches in the mountain.

name: Avatar Ruins Outer Path
description: It's not really a mountain that you see, but it's the closest thing you can think of that resembles what you're looking at.  The massive structure juts out of the surface, seemingly out of nothingness.  The jagged edges and sharp points make it relatively unclimbable.

name: Paladin Test Arena
description: The knight before you will test your abilities, and will not let you pass to the training room if you are found lacking in skill.  Only the bravest and purest of paladins may serve the kingdom, and if you search your soul and find you are not ready, you should come back at a later time.

name: Paladin Testing Arena
description: It is a long and honored tradition that a paladin who wishs to advance in rank must show his courage and valor by defeating a knight who is the next level above what he aspires to obtain.  The Red Knight, with head bowed, awaits your move.

name: Paladin Testing Arena
description: The White Knight stands with his sword across his chest, awaiting your move.  All paladins who aspire to serve the Lyanden Kingodm must be tested for bravery and purity of heart.  So that you may know you are worthy, the White Knight, who is one level above you, has volunteered to provide you with a trial.  When you are ready you may strike the first blow.

name: Holy Order of the Red Rose
description: The paladin represents living truth and goodness, and dedicates his person to the elimination of evil in the world.  However, at each step in his advancement, he must be tested to see that he has remained pure of heart, thought and deed.  To that end, high level paladins often come here and voulnteer to serve as mentors for newly advancing members of their holy order.  Do not enter the training areas if you are not ready.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: And now you should search your heart, and be absolutely certain that the role of paladin is one you desire.  The paladin is a holy knight, and must protect the weak and the rightious, and must never show fear of evilness. As you advance farther, you will be called upon to fight against dark forces, and must never flee from a such a fight.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: And now, if you are spiritually ready to accept the added duties of an advanced paladin, kneel and receive your transformation.  An intense, white light shines down on you, as you are now one of the chosen.  From this day forward, you will know peace and serenity, so long as you fight against evil.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: Only the bravest and purist of paladins may serve in the kingdom, and many have failed to reach this exalted level.  You are to be congratulated on your fine accomplishment.  Kneel, and accept your transformation and added responsibilities and duties.  You are a credit to knighthood.

name: Cygnus' Cave
description: The cave is strangely dark, depsite the bright sunlight outside.  In the shadows, you can see a large creature moving from within.  The cave is quite lavish, decorated in gold and jewels.  It doesn't look like anyone has entered this area in ages, though.

name: Distillery Office
description: The smell of rum is almost strong enough to give you a buzz by itself. The office is small, with a great oaken desk and a broken down couch. A glass window looks out onto the floor of the distillery, where you see great vats and a number of workers going about the business of making rum.  A sign on the door says, "If you're not dwarven, don't bother to apply for work."

name: The Shrine of Truth and Fairness
description: The path of the Paladin is a noble and honorable one.  Truth and fairness are the words the Paladin lives by.
