In order to advance yourself to the rank of Protector, you must first show your worthiness by defeating an equally equiped Paladin of the rank you aspire to be.  Gallant Warriors should enter the green door to be promoted to Protector.  Protector  Warriors should enter the red door to be promoted to Protector, Second Class.  Finally, Protector, Second Class Paladins should enter the  white door to be promoted to the level of Protector, First Class.  Good luck, mighty warriors.  Advanced levels should find the Holy Order of the Red Rose on the east side of town.

name: Ogre's Play Pen
description: Ogre's Play Pen appears to be a rather old but well kept building of stone and brick.  Many years have passed since the days of the legendary adventures of the two Brownhaven heros, Ogre the barbarian and his comrade in arms, the wise cleric Lorinin.  Now the tales of Ogre are mostly unknown. In his retirement, Ogre used his fortune to build a place for barbarians and fighters to play and practice. To the north, you see a sign for "Bashing Unlimited" and to the south another sign saying "Arena".

name: Bashing Unlimited
description: Behind the counter you can see a nice assortment of blunt weapons.

name: Ogre's Arena
description: The blood of less fortunate fighters is splattered across the walls and You wonder what fate holds in store for you. To the northeast you see a door leading to The Cage, which is the one-on-one combat arena   for Matriess the destroyer. Only the most skilled warriors should attempt to fight there.

name: The Cage
description: Matriess, the insane offspring of an ogre and a hill giant, stands before you. She grins with anticipation for her newest victim.

name: Warm-Up Room
description: Even though this is a warm up arena, a fair amount of skill and luck are still required to survive here.

name: Roland's Royal Fighting Academy
description: Roland's Academy trains all the knights that wish to eventually enter the services of Lyanden Castle.  Warriors coming here for the first time should  enter the green door to advance to the level of Punisher.  A Punisher should enter the blue door to advance to Punisher, Second Class.  Finally, a Punisher, Second Class should enter the red door to complete your training at Roland's Royal Fighting Academy.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy - Green Training Room
description: In order to advance to the level of Punisher, you must first prove your worth to the Academy that you are in deed ready.  This proof lies in your defeating the green knight which stands before you.  The green knight is waiting for your first move.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy Training Room
description: A vial of holy water has been left here for your use to mend some of the very bad wounds you might have suffered in battle.  You are now worthy to  train to the level of Punisher.  When you are ready to advance again, come back to Roland's Fighting Academy and we will continue your training.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy - Blue Training Room
description: In order to advance to the next level, you must first defeat a knight of the level you wish to attain.  Roland's Fighting Academy does not promote wimps that cannot fight!  The blue knight stands before you, waiting for your first move.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy Training Room
description: Only the bravest and most powerful knights may advance through the Roland Royal Fighting Academy, and you have earned your rank of Punisher,  Second Class.  This vial of holy water will help you recover some of the dammage you sustained in battle.  Good luck in your adventures and return here when you are ready for your final lesson.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy - Red Training Room
description: In order to advance to the next level, you must first prove yourself to the instructors at the academy by defeating this knight.  The Academy is proud of your success, but requires proof of your strengths in order to advance you to the next level.

name: Roland's Fighting Academy Training Room
description: You are now ready to advance to the level of Punisher, First Class.  This is the last step in your training at the Roland Royal Fighting Academy as your skills have surpassed the limits of our training.

name: Advanced Level Fighter's Room
description: To advance your fighting skills further, you must journey to the City of Kista and talk to the Jinsuti Master, who has studied every form of hand-to- hand fighting known to living kind.  He will guide your training from this point forward.  Good luck in your quest for enlightment.

name: North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa
description: The North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa circulates in warm spring water from a natural source in the ground below the building into large pools where patrons can go to relax and recover.  The natural mineral water comes from the mountains and is heated by a strange lava flow, located about two miles below the city.

name: Bendine Aquarium Main Entrance
description: The Bendine Aquarium and Marina provides a number of strange and interesting creatures for public viewing.  However, visitors should be warned that  although many of the creatures living in the Aquarium are friendly, some will attack you, especially if you enter the tanks where they are swimming. The hallway continues to the east.

name: Bendine Aquarium Kiddie Tank
description: There are a number of small children playing around a small pool in the center of the room.  The pool appears to be filled with playful dolphins and a few very large crabs and crayfish on the bottom of the tank.   Occassionally, a few giant sea horses swim by.

name: Bendine Aquarium Kiddie Tank Surface
description: The large water pool is quite warm and relaxing.  Every so often, a dolphin or two will nudge you.  They sort of see you as an invader of their habitat, but are usually fairly friendly unless attacked.  A number of large fish and sea horses also swim by.

name: Bendine Aquarium Kiddie Tank Depths
description: The floor of the Children's Tank is not really kid's stuff.  Large crabs and crayfish inhabit this area and don't always like invaders to their domain.  You can also see a number of large fish and an occassional eel swim by as well.

name: Bendine Aquarium Main Hallway
description: The hallway continues to the east and west.  To the west, you can see the giant Fresh Water Aquarium where all kinds of wierd and strange creatures live.  To the north, you can see the room where the octopi are kept.  The Octopus Tank can hold a number of octopi, which are inherently dangerous. Caution should be exercised when entering this tank.

name: Bendine Aquarium Octopus Tank Room
description: Octopi are not very friendly creatures, and with eight tenticals each, they tend to be very deadly.  Although they are very graceful to watch, they probably don't like being disturbed.  The tank lies in the center  of the room.

name: Bendine Aquarium Octopus Tank
description: The management of the Bendine Aquarium and Marina takes no responsibility for your obviously foolish decision to enter the Octopus Tank.  But since you're here, you should watch out for approaching octopi, as they attack without warning and with deadly accuracy.

name: Bendine Aquarium Main Hallway
description: This section of the Main Hallway runs through the pirahna exhibit.  The Pirahna Pit, as it is so named, lies to the west.  Although the small fish are not very powerful or strong, they tend to travel in packs,  making them a very deadly threat to their victim.  Encouraging them by jumping into the pirahna pool is not recommended.

name: Bendine Aquarium Main Hallway
description: The hallway turns to the southeast, heading towards the exit into the Bendine Marina, where the Whale Tank and the Salt Water Exhibit are located.  To the north is the Shark Tank, where a number of exotic species of shark are kept for observation.  It should be noted, though, that the giant megalodon sharks are said to have swallowed people whole.

name: Bendine Marina Foyer
description: The Aquarium is located to the west.  On the north side of the entranceway is the gigantic whale tank where various species of whales are kept to amuse children and adults alike.  To the east is the Salt Water Exhibit in the Rhinestone Marina itself.  The Bendine Bay is cut off from the Marina by a large, iron gate, preventing the animals in the bay from escaping and keeping the carniverous creatures of the marina out.

name: Bendine Aquarium Piranha Exhibit
description: The large pool in the center contains many vicious piranha swimming around in packs of up to twenty.  It is not really advised that you even touch the water around the pool because piranha can smell blood miles away.  It is said that a swarm of piranha can debone a living horse in less than a couple of minutes.

name: Bendine Aquarium Piranha Pool
description: You can already see a pack of piranha swimming towards you at a rapid rate. It would be best to get out now while you still can.  The packs of piranha tend to focus on just one victim at a time.  Too bad you can't use a fireball spell on all of them at once.

name: Bendine Aquarium Shark Tank Room
description: Sharks are perhaps one of the most deadly creatures of the sea.  Although they usually travel alone, they will often converge on a single prey when they smell blood.  The management suggests that you do not enter the large tank, but watch the sharks from the outside.

name: Bendine Aquarium Shark Tank
description: Most sharks don't come up to the surface very often, but occassionally one or two will get curious and poke around at objects in the water.  The depths of the tank are pretty dangerous, inhabited by great white sharks and other deadly sharks of the deep.

name: Bendine Aquarium Shark Tank Depths
description: The depths of the shark tank are inhabited by a number of great white sharks and other deadly species, all looking for some lunch.  You also notice that there are a lot more sharks down here, moreso than up at the surface.  It's probably not a good idea to stay down here too long.

name: Rum Road North
description: On the east side you see a large red house, and from here you can the side yard.  There appears to be a small building a little detached from the main structure, and you can see steps leading down toward the beach beyond the out building.  Sure seems to be a good party going on inside.  The road continues north with a few boarded up buildings on either side, and a newly painted shop with a sign that says, "Watch for Grand Opening." When you look closer at the sign, you realize it says this will be a magic repair shop, but the opening date was last month, and no one seems to be here.

name: Uland Way/Rum Road
description: Rum Road is the major north-south road on the island, but Uland Way is by far an older road.  Some place through the jungle of this tropical  paradise is the old Uland Mansion, built by the most famous pirate ever to sail the Respitial Sea.  Some say that Uland Way was the carriage road to the house.

name: Uland Way
description: A number of small shops line the twisting street, catering mostly to the people who live here on the island.  Immediately to the north is a dirty llittle fish market, which gives the street a pleasant smell.  Shopkeepers lounge in their doorways and eye you as you stroll along.  Uland Way seems to twist out of sight to the west.

name: Uland Way
description: The way is muddy and not very wide, making it difficult to travel along here.  A couple of shops are open, but there is also one that has a for sale sign on the door.  As you look closer you see in small letters that the previous owner died of the red death, and that the widow is willing  to sell cheap.  On the south side is Herman's Blacksmith Shop.

name: Herman's Blacksmith Forge
description: Herman is the only smith on Uland Island, and does a good business in the repair of armor and light weapons.  He doesn't know anything about magic however, and cannot repair such items.  He has a couple of helpers who handle the bellows, and his young son is the clerk who takes care of customers.

name: The Red Eye Pub and Grill
description: The Red Eye Pub is ideal for finding out information about various items or objects of interest.  The pub is freqented by numerous bards who know much more than they let on.  Many bards gain the confidence of great leaders, thus find out more information that they can effectively put into riddles and songs.

name: The Temple of Ahto
description: The magnificent Temple of Ahto pays homage to the powerful God of the Seas and Waters.  The god Ahto was worshiped by many of the northern folk living on the northern island Rustallik'n.  These people often traded with the people of Oceancrest, and some started migrating here.  Nevertheless, Ahto became a major icon to the sailors and seamen who live day to day on the open seas.

name: The Temple of Ahto Meditation Chamber
description: The Meditation Chamber is strictly off limits to all outsiders except the priests and priestesses of Ahto, who will attack you if you stay in here too long.  In addition, the powerful presence of the god Ahto himself will sometimes be present.

name: Kishijoten's Sushi Bar
description: Kishijoten is the goddess of luck in many of the eastern cultures on the other side of the island.  Iisika, the founder of the bar, decided to pay homage to her favorite goddess and luck has not ceased to shine upon her very popular business.  Fresh fish and other seafood is a delicacy among many of the eastern cultures as well as many of the oceanic cultures, who will often show up here to talk and have something to eat.

name: Danielle's Mystical Mage Emporium
description: Danielle's Mystic Mage Emporium stocks all kinds of potions, oils and other mysterious waters of life.  You can buy just about anything you might desire here, but it will cost you a lot.  Potions are not that easy to make, and Danielle needs to make enough money to pay the rent on this place.

name: Danielle's Mystic Mage Emporium Storage Shack
Danielle's Mystic Mage's Emporium Back Room
description: Among the various trinkets and doodads that are lying around, there are two large circles of glass on the floor in the room.  On the wall is a sign which says "Teleporter - USE ONLY IN EMERGENCIES".  Apparently, it is used should anyone be brave or stupid enough to attack the city.  On the wall near the right circle are four buttons: black, red, green and orange.  On the wall near the left circle are four more buttons: grey, yellow, blue and purple.  They must be used to control the teleporters.

name: Leviathan Dock
description: The Leviathan Dock runs west into the bay, providing access to the various ships and vessels docked inside the breakwater of the Nylandian Bay.  Most of the bay is empty right now, but a few merchant ships are nearby.  The near part of the dock is where the pirate ship Widow Maker berthes when she is in port.  Marina Way is located to the east, and the dock continues to the west.

name: Uland Island Dock
description: The island is famous for the strong rum it makes and exports, but there is very little else here.  That is, unless you count the long line of pubs, bars and saloons that line the single road in the village.  Most of the island is uninhabited except for the dwarves who work in the distillery, and the shopkeepers who run the saloons.  And of course,  there are the women who live in the large red house at the north end of the village's single road.  Young ladies go there to learn a trade.

name: Rum Road/Long Dock Intersection
description: At the southern end of Rum Road you see the island's famous dwarven distillery where the finest and strongest rum is made.  Both sides of the road have an equal number of garish pubs and saloons, and a great deal of noise is coming from them all.  Standing by itself at the north end of the road is a bright red house.  Quite a few women of all races are hanging out the windows and lolling on the veranda.  They don't seem to be wearing much in the way of clothes, and they seem to know a lot of the sailors and pirates walking nearby.

name: Rum Road South
description: The Pink Lady bar and grill is on the west side of the road.  Some kind of a disturbance seems to be taking place in there.  Next door is a small place called the Green Goat, but it seems to be popular only with dwarves. Further to the south you can see a huge wooden building that must be the distillery.  It seems to have a tin roof, and a ramshackle loading dock.

name: Rum Road South/Thieve's Alley Intersection
description: The alley is known by the local folk as Thieve's Alley, but perhaps a  better name would be garbage alley.  The smell of urine and vomit is very strong, and filth litters the narrow walkway.  Hungry cats seem to be everywhere, silently watching you.  Your presence has brought a momentary truce to the war raging between the cats and some very large rats.

name: Rum Road South
description: Wagons are pulled up to the double doors of the old wooden building, and great barrels and kegs stand everywhere.  Some are empty, but most appear to be full of rum.  All of the workmen you see are dwarves, but for the  most part they simply ignore you.  On the east side of the road is the Red Dog Saloon, one of the most popular places in the village.

name: Red Dog Saloon
description: The place is crowded and smoky, making it difficult to find a table. As you look around you note that most of the patrons are pirates, and that most of them are roaring drunk.  This might not be a fun place to be for a landlubber.  There is a long, polished bar over at one side, and a great many tables and chairs around the room.  A curtain covers a small stage at the end of the room.

name: Officer's Drinking Room
description: The room is quieter than the main public room outside, but the pirates in here are just as drunk.  These men are older and meaner, and you notice they stare quietly at you as you stand here.  Several barmaids pass among them, and a couple of entertainers are taking a break.

name: Thieve's Alley
description: The large cats circle away from you, staying out of your reach, but never turning their backs on you either.  The stench makes you want to hold your nose.  Why on earth did you come in here, anyway?  A doorway is slightly open in the old building, and a sign says "Welfare."  The alley is littered with garbage and broken kegs and boxes.

name: Dead End Alley
description: A small grate has been removed from its vault in the ground, exposing a narrow entry to the cellar below the old wooden building here. Large black cats prowl the alley, and several look at you hungrily.  A body of a sailor is decomposing on the ground, partially hidden by rags and trash.  A couple of the larger cats crouch beside the body.

name: Cellar of the Dwarven Drinking Society
description: The room is dark, but there is a door at the top of some stairs where light seeps around the edges.  The door is only slightly over a meter  tall however, so you conclude some very short people probably use this room.  The smell of rum is quite strong and you are a little sickened by its overpowering odor in such a small place.  There is a new padlock on the side door.  A broken window leads to a vault in the alley outside.

name: Uland's Long Dock End
description: The Widow Maker sometimes moors here at the end of the dock for a few days, making Uland Island her home port while she waits for the weather to change. This is a deepwater dock, meant for large ships.  Merchant ships also tie up here, but seldom when the Widow Maker is in port.  A tangy smell of salt air and decaying fish is in the air.  Several fishermen are on the dock today.

name: Rum Road North
description: Although old, it looks to be very large, with at least twenty bedrooms. Several of the upstairs windows are open, and laughing women lean out them, looking you over.  There is a veranda on all sides of the house and the front door is open.  A party seems to be in full swing inside, and one of the women inside smiles and waves for you to come in.

name: Red House Veranda
description: The main room is through the wide entry to the north, while a broad and winding stairway goes to the upstairs area of the house.  Several women and rough looking men are in animated conversations around you, and a  small dwarf makes his way through the crowd carrying a tray of drinks.

name: Seaman's Welfare Office
description: This is a welfare office run by a group of missionaries from a store-front church in Oceancrest.  The place used to be a front for a bunch of sly pawn dealers who bought things with no questions asked.  But no more.  Now the bible thumpers run it, having chased out the previous owner.  They say they plan to clean up the entire island, but everyone just laughs at that.

name: Green Goat Inn
description: Rum is the only thing they sell, so if you want to drink anything else you had best be going.  Besides, why did the music stop when you came in? A lot of sullen looks seem to be directed toward you, and you notice a couple of young dwarves over at the side appear to be fingering their knives.  A snot-nosed and giggling troll seems to have blocked the exit.

name: Pink Lady Saloon
description: The place is quiet and flies buzz in circles around the room and the free lunch at the end of the counter.  Now you know why this place is called the Pink Lady - The woman behind the bar must weigh at least four hundred pounds and has a glowing pink complexion.  She wears a flimsy see-through blouse, which you would rather not see through.  A sign on the walls says, "We don't want any trouble in here.  Take it outside to the alley."

name: Jungle Road
description: The beach is not far from here, and a road is cut through the jungle which seems to go in the direction of the sound of the surf.  Tall palms and heavy banana trees are overhead, and the ground is covered with soft ferns and creeping vines.  The back doors of several buildings open onto this cleared area, and garbage has been thrown into heaps nearby.

name: Jungle Road
description: The road heads toward the sound of surf to the west, while to the east you can see a group of ramshackle buildings and hear a lot of loud music and laughter.  A crudely lettered sign nearby has an arrow pointing west, and tells you the island cemetery is that way.  A human skull hangs from the top of the sign, and it seems to still have eyes which glare at you. A hasty hand has added to the sign, "Stay Away!  Voodoo!!"

name: Dark Jungle Road
description: A soft chanting can be heard in the distance, mingling with the sound of the surf even further away.  A dead goat is impaled on a stout pole by the side of the road, and chicken feathers make a necklace for the hapless animal.  Do you recall that voodoo doctors often use such grotesque   symbols to keep out the unbelievers?

name: Cemetery Gate
description: The gate hangs at an odd angle, and looks as though the next strong breeze will knock it down completely.  The cemetery behind the overgrown fence has not had any care in a long time.  The road here continues to the east and the west.  The smell of salt air comes from the east, and it sounds like surf in that direction.

name: Jungle Cemetery
description: A coffin has been pulled from the ground and hacked open, the wreckage strewn under the large trees.  The ground is still steaming, and a freshly killed chicken lies on top of the casket, its blood used to write unusual symbols there.  A string of chicken entrails look to be carefully placed in a circle around the wooden casket, and a single candle still burns atop it.  Thick jungle brush separates you from an area where you hear chanting.

name: Beach Road
description: The road disappears into the sand on the beach, but seems to be an old and established way through the tropical jungle toward the west.  A pile of small animal bones is stacked neatly beside the road, just as it enters the jungle.  Some of the bones are placed so as to form a kind of message, but you are unable to read their meaning.

name: Bird Cliff
description: The island jungle is at your back as you look out over the beach and the Respitial Sea to the east.  There is the remains of a rutted road here, leading through the trees and into the wet and dark jungle.  It looks like you might be able to climb down to the beach, but probably won't be able to climb back up here again.  At least, not at this point along the cliff.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The magnificent Dragon's Citadel lies to the south of Orchard Lane, but the entrance to the Citadel is located on the other side of the building. The fantastic structure was built ages ago and is thought to be abandoned by its original owners.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The Swallow's Nest is a rather large bar exclusively for officers of the city guard.  Although they do allow members of the other guard affiliations, they do not much care for outsiders, and will do whatever they can to get rid of people who do not belong there.

name: Orchard Lane
description: You are walking casually along Orchard Lane, looking for a little excitement. The Swallow's Nest is a rather large bar for some rather large people, and might be the excitement you've been looking for.  The Swallow's Nest is an exclusive club for city guard officers, so it is unlikely that your presence there will be welcome.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The Tranquility Patrol Station is located on the north side of the road and provides peacekeeping support to the bars and nightclubs around the area.  The Tranquility Patrol is dedicated to keeping order and peace. They wander around the streets and bars, breaking up fights and brawls.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The Fiesty Kitten Nightclub and Bar is perhaps one of the most dangerous bars in all of Oceancrest.  It is frequented by many officers of the city guard or other "peacekeeping" forces.  The bar is also raided a lot by Morality Patrol for solicitation.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The Oceancrest Ministries are located on the southern block, south of Orchard Lane.  Directly to the south is the Ministry of Tranquility, which is in charge of domestic peace.  The Tranquility Patrol is run from this facility.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The Healer's Eye is a small healing shop on the south side of the road. The healers there will help you recover from whatever accidents or battles you might have been in, and do not charge for their services.  On the  north side of the road is the Brunskid Trader's Guild, a place where many goods trade hands, some of questionable origin.

name: Orchard Lane
description: Oolan's Armory specializes in unique and interesting armors that may  not be common in other parts of town.  Most of these armors are not out of the ordinary, but usually tend to last longer than conventional  leather or chain armors.

name: Orchard Lane
description: Orchard Lane cuts through a large forest region on both sides of the road. The thick brush and high concentration of trees prevents you from casually looking into the forest.  Most people don't think anything can survive in those forests, while others think they're inhabitted by mystical beings.

name: Orchard Lane
description: The small stream appears to be the only thing that can get in and out of the forests on both sides of the road.  Unfortunately, the river is very shallow and appears to be the nesting ground of a few unfriendly looking alligators and other beasts.

name: Orchard Lane
description: Wit the exception of the trickling stream to the east, you can't here much in this dense forest.  It's quite odd that the forest exists in the middle of the large city.  For some reason, the city decided to keep the forests intact, building the city around them.

name: Orchard Lane
description: Orchard Lane runs east and west through a dense forest on both sides of the road.  The thick brush makes it virtually impossible to see any sort of activity within the forests.  In fact, the forests are noticably and strangely very quiet.

name: Tranquility Way
description: There is an old-growth forest to the north which the city fathers have left completely undisturbed.  At one time a land developer tried to go in there, thinking he would make a lot of money, but nobody ever saw him again.  The forest on the south side seems to be a little younger then the north side, but its still quite mature.

name: Tranquility Way
description: There is a wonderful old forest on both sides of the road, but the trees on the south side of the road seem younger than those on the north.  Shadows in the forest seem to move, but only out of the corner of your eye.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The northern City Walls are quite impressive, standing more than ten meters high at some places, and higher at others.  The wall was designed to keep out invading hordes of barbarians and other aggressive foes.  After the walls were built, no attack on Oceancrest has been successful.

name: Hofton Avenue Bridge
description: The wide and rapid river seems to head into the forest on the south side of the road, but there doesn't seem to be any way to get down to the river. Hofton Avenue continues to the east and west, running parallel to the northern City Walls.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The massive City Walls on the north side of the road are a constant  reminder of what lies outside the city.  Although there hasn't really been a major offensive against the city in over half a century, the threat of invasion is always present and the city garrison is always in top form, ready to take on any threat that might come its way.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: You can see Leviathan Drive in the distance to the west.  On the north side of the road is the massive City Walls, surrounding and protecting  the city.  To the south, you can see a large forest region, but cannot seem to find any way to get into it, or see or what it could possibly hide.

name: Everborough Way/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Directly to the north, you can see the North Oceancrest Guard Station and the north entrance to the town.  There is a popular Inn on the south- western corner of the intersection and the Evenborough Stables and  Riding Facilities are located on the southeastern corner.  The city asks that visitors and guests leave their horses at the stables to prevent accidents with pedestrians on the roads.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The Evenborough Inn provides luxurious accomodations for the weary  traveller for either single night visits or prolonged stays in Oceancrest. There is a magnificent fountain in front of the main entrance to the building, suggesting the price of staying here might be a little expensive. The Evenborough Stables are located on the eastern side of the road.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The Evenborough Stables and the Evenborough Inn are located across the street from each other to provide easy access for the travellers just coming into the city.  There are a number of small shops in the northern side of town where you can buy something to eat, watch some bards play some annoying tunes, or just walk along the Nylandian Bay beach.

name: Evenborough Way/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Evenborough Way runs north and south through the northern part of town. Looking to the north, you can see the northern entrance to the city of Oceancrest.  There are a number of small shops on the southwestern corner of this intersection, and the Evenborough Stables and Inn located off of the northeastern and northwestern corners respectively.

name: Evenborough Way
description: On the west side of the road, you can see a well-protected jewelry shop called "Doberman's Fine Jewels".  The shop looks very well protected, perhaps by some vicious dogs or some other guard animal.  On the east side of the road, you can see the Darmanian Memorial, a large park-like  facility, preserved by the Darmanian Society through a number of healthy donations.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The Darmanian Center, on the east side of the road, is a monument dedicated to the first civilizations that existed in what is now Oceancrest.  Or so the Darmanian Society wishes to believe.  The entrance to the center is located to the east.  On the west side of the road is Caldea's Fine Silk shop, where various imported items can be purchased.

name: Evenborough Way
description: Elaine's Bow shop supplies archers and knights from the Lyanden Castle with superior quality crossbows and longbows for use in battle or defending the city.  The high quality bows are more mechanical than natural, but nothing can really match an elven longbow.

name: Evenborough Way/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Islandia Drive runs east towards the main entrance to Lyanden Castle and west towards the Bendine Aquarium.  It also passes by numerous shops and facilities providing services to the citizens.  Evenborough Way runs north towards the Northern Entrance to the city, and south towards the Lithium Inlet.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The large Evenborough Park rests on the eastern side of the road.  The park lies just to the west of the Lyanden Castle, and is often used as  a public auditorium so that the King may make any announcements to the general public.  On the west side of the road is a small armory for Knights of the Castle.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The lush, green grass of the Everborough Park makes it an ideal place to sit down for a rest between walks.  It is a long way from one end of the city to the other.  On the west side of the road, you can see Sir Edward's Royal Swordsmith, where most of the swords used by the Knights of the Castle are forged.

name: Evenborough Way/Nissiau Lane Intersection
description: Nissiau Lane runs west from here, through a number of small shops on both sides of the road.  The northwestern section of town is known for its great selection of shops and facilities, and Nissiau Lane runs between most of them.  Evenborough Way continues to the north and south from here.

name: Evenborough Way
description: Evenborough Way makes a sharp turn to the north and east to avoid the Lithium Inlet to the south.  The small area of land between the inlet and the road is being used as a nightclub by some of the discouraged students from Iilandi University.  A dirt path leads south towards the inlet and the nightclub.

name: Lorian Parkway/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Hofton Avenue runs east and west, parallel to the northern City Walls.   Lorian Parkway runs south out of the intersection through some of the busier businesses in town.  The northwestern section of town is known for some of its fine craftsmen and women, most doing business in small shops scattered around the area.

name: Lorian Parkway
description: The Evenborough Inn covers nearly one city block square, catering to the weary adventurers wandering in from the north gate for a good nights rest. On the west side of the road is the Red-Eye Pub and Grill, where many adventurers come to discuss what perils lie ahead should they be venturing out of the town.

name: Lorian Parkway
description: Leather is perhaps one of the most versitile materials in the world, being used for everything from armor to shoes to weapons.  Ivan carries just  about anything you could want.  On the west side of the road is the  Evenborough Inn, a popular overnight stop for weary travellers.

name: Lorian Parkway/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Darmanian Way runs east and west, intersecting Lorian Parkway, which runs north and south out of the intersection.  Both streets are lined with  various shops and facilities for just about everyone for almost any  reason.  On the southwest corner of the road is the Temple of Clerical Science, where clerics from all around the region come to discuss the issues involved in modern clergy.

name: Lorian Parkway
description: Pandora carries all kinds of interesting and useful items for the novice mage and even a few items for the general public.  Potions and spells are her specialty.  On the west side of the road is the Temple of Clerical Science, where modern science meets the clerical hierarcy in an explosive combination of technology and religion.

name: Lorian Parkway
description: Fire itself is not very rare in Oceancrest, but getting something to start a fire isn't always as easy as one would like.  Handel's House of Fire  provides for these needs, as well as the possibility of having to put them out.  On the west side of the road is Xanthar's Holy Supplies, where a variety of clerical items may be purchased.

name: Lorian Parkway
description: On the east side of the road is Jeane's Glass and Glazing shop, where you can pick up all kinds of fancy and interesting glass objects, for windows, doors, or whatever.  Glass, however, is very expensive, and should be used sparingly.  On the west side of the road is the Paladin's Shrine of Truth and Fairness.  The entrance to the shrine is located off of Islandia Drive to the south.

name: Lorian Parkway/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Lorian Parkway runs north from Islandia Drive, which runs east and west.  On the south side of the road, you can see a pet store called Nicole's World of Animals, where a number of small pets and companions may be purchased. No one should be without a pet.

name: Bendine Way/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Hofton Way runs east and west from the intersection, running parallel to  the northern City Walls.  Bendine Way heads south out of the intersection through many of the more popular shops and facilities lining both sides of the road.  On the southeast corner of the intersection is the Red-Eye Pub and Grill Stage, where various bards and other minstrels come to  perform before live audiences.

name: Bendine Way
description: The Oceancrest Municipal Library provides the northern section of town  with a number of historical, scientific and magical references dating back nearly two hundred years, if not more.  On the east side of the road is the Red-Eye Bar and Grill Stage, where a number of young bards go to practice their routines.

name: Bendine Way
description: Xedora's Magic Shop provides a number of unique and different potions which may or may not be useful for any adventure you might be going out on.  On the west side of the road is the Oceancrest Municipal Library, holding a plethora of knowledge to be utilized by the city's citizens.

name: Bendine Way/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Darmanian Way runs east and west out of the intersection while Bendine  Way runs north and south.  On the southeastern corner of the intersection is the Blue Rose Meditation Chamber.  On the southwestern corner is the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss, and on the northwestern corner is the Oceancrest Municiple Library.

name: Bendine Way
description: The Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is the center of all clerical bodies in  Oceancrest, and much of the outlying lands.  All the clerics usually come here to discuss the various problems with the society and find remedies to fix them.  It is a well known notion that mankind cannot think for themselves, therefore they must have religion to create morality.

name: Bendine Way
description: The Blue Rose Meditation Chamber is a small study area for young clerics who need to meditate and/or pray to their dieties for whatever reason.   The Meditation Chamber provides a quiet building for these clerics, monks or druids to relax in the peacefullness of meditation.

name: Bendine Way
description: The North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa provide countless people with deluxe accomodations in small pools of flowing, natural mineral water,  heated by the lava flow underneath the city.  Being so close to the ocean puts Oceancrest on a bad fault line where quakes sometimes happen. The upshot of this being the lava flow heats up the natural mineral water beneath the city.

name: Bendine Way/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Bendine Way runs north and south, intersecting Islandia Way, running  east and west.  On the northeast corner of the intersection, you can see the North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa.  On the northwest corner is  the famous Cathedral of Worldly Bliss.  Bendine Way heads south towards the Nylandian Bay and Islandia heads west towards the Bendine Aquarium and Marina.

name: Bendine Way
description: The Kimber Family has, for many generations, provided custom locks and  bolts for nearly everyone who has ever wanted to keep something protected. Furthermore, they're likely to be able to open up any known lock.  On the west side of the road is the Adlermann Center of Marine Research and Oceanography, bordering the Rhinestone Marina.

name: Bendine Way
description: The west side of the road is more or less dominated by mucky, swamp-like terrain, bordering the Rhinestone Marina.  The Adlermann Center is located further to the west.  On the east side of the road is the Oceancrest Homeless Soup Kitchen where out of work Oceancrest citizens can get some hot food and a cool glass of water.

name: Bendine Way/Nissiau Lane Intersection
description: Nissiau Lane heads east through the very popular shopping centers and facilities in this side of the town.  Separated by the Nylandian Bay, the northwest corner of town more or less provides for itself.  Bendine Way heads north and south from here.

name: Bendine Way
description: Steve's Fishing and Tackle Shop provides an assortment of fishing gear  needed to land a large bass or even a shark.  He also provides boat and gear rentals for those who dare to go out on the open seas.  The Rhinestone Marina is located to the west, where a number of small boats are moored.

name: Bendine Way
description: Bendine Way ends here at the beach along the northern coast of the Nylandian Bay.  On the east side of the road is a small import shop called Highland Trade Imports.  A small dirt road runs along the northern beach between the Bay and a few more shops.

name: Delaney Drive/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Hofton Avenue runs east and west from the intersection, running parallel to the north City Walls.  Delaney Road is a short street running south from Hofton Avenue between the Oceancrest Municiple Library and the Oceancrest City Guard Barracks.

name: Delaney Drive
description: The Oceancrest North City Guard Barracks are located on the west side of the road.  Most of the City Guards who are stationed here patrol the Northwestern Observational Station and the City Walls.  On the east side of the road is the Oceancrest Municipal Library.  The entrance to the Library is located off of Hofton Avenue or Darmanian Way.

name: Delaney Drive
description: Knowledge is essential to all societies, and making knowledge public strengthens the society.  The Municipal Library is nothing compared to the University Library or the Ministry of Knowledge, but it does provide the average citizens of Oceancrest with basic knowledge about whatever they might be interested in.

name: Delaney Drive/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Delaney Drive running north and south, is intersected by Darmanian Way, running east and west at this point.  The Oceancrest Municiple Library is located on the northeast corner of the intersection, and the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is located on the southeast.  A number of shops are on the southwest corner and the Oceancrest North City Guard Barracks are  located on the northwest corner.

name: Delaney Drive
description: The Guard Surplus and Supply shop located on the west side of the road provides a number of useful armors and weapons used by the city guards. Of course these weapons are used, and can't be expected to be worth much more than souveniers.  On the east side of the road is the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss.

name: Delaney Drive
description: The entrance to the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is located to the east of here.  A large monument in the center of the square depicts the entire world and the various sections of religious control.  On the west side of the road is Martha's World of Water and Ice.  Clean, fresh water is usually a rare commodity, and ice is even more so.

name: Delaney Drive
description: Good shoes are hard to find, but the Oceancrest Cobbler will provide you  with a good pair of leather boots or walking shoes for a small price. He might even personalize them for you.  On the east side of the road is the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss.  The entrance to the cathedral is to the north.

name: Delaney Drive/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Delaney Drive runs north from Islandia Road, which runs to the east and west.  On the south side of the road is the Adlermann Center of Marine Research and Oceanography.  The fancy academy is located off the coast of the Rhinestone Marina.  On the northeast corner of the road is the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss, and the War Veteran's Historical Library is located on the opposite corner.

name: Adlermann Way/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Hofton Avenue runs east from the intersection, running parallel to the northern City Walls, while Adlermann Way runs south, also running parallel to the western City Walls.  To the north is the Northwestern Oceancrest Observational Station, a large, tall building allowing the guards to watch for early signs of an assult or invasion.

name: Adlermann Way
description: The City Guard Officer's Club is one of the most exclusive bars in  Oceancrest.  The guards and other patrol personnel don't really like to see outsiders in their personal clubs, so it might not be a really good idea to go in there without a very heavy escort.

name: Adlermann Way
description: The impressive structure on the east provides housing for the many hundreds of city guards on patrol in this section of town.  The Observational Station to the north and the Northern Entrance to the town all require a large number of guards to patrol the area in addition to the day-to-day patrolling of the city and the City Walls.

name: Adlermann Way/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Darmanian Way runs east from the intersection with Adlermann Way, which runs north and south.  On the west side of the intersection is the  impressive west City Wall which looks heavily guarded.

name: Adlermann Way
description: The Lithium Lanterns shop provides the guards and everyday citizens with the essential lanterns to light up their paths in the dark areas of town. No one should be without a lantern.  On the west side of the road is the west City Wall, which runs parallel to Adlermann Way.

name: Adlermann Way
description: Josie's Ropery provides people with high quality rope and other climbing goods to get around the caverns beneath the city as well as in the mountains to the east of the city.  Both are potentially very dangerous and one  should always carry rope and other mountain climbing equipment if they  intend to climb.

name: Adlermann Way
description: Al's Woodwork provides a number of interesting, but otherwise useless wood statues and other carvings to decorate homes and castles.  He is supposed to know a lot about the wood, though, and claims wood spirits inhabit all the wood growing inside the city of Oceancrest.  All the wood he uses comes from outside the city.

name: Adlermann Way/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Islandia Drive heads off to the east from Adlermann Way, which runs north and south.  On the southeast side of the road is the Bendine Aquarium and Marina.  To the west, you can see the impressive City Walls, which tower above the ground, overlooking the Respital Sea and the Nylandian Bay, protecting Oceancrest from invasions.

name: Adlermann Way
description: The large Bendine Aquarium and Marina houses some of the most unique species of animals in the world.  However, many of them are also very dangerous and perhaps deadly.  On the west side of the road is the west City Wall, which runs parallel to Adlermann Way.

name: Adlermann Way
description: The large facility provides its guests with a first-hand look at all the wonderous and mysterious creatures of the deep.  The Bendine Aquarium  houses many fresh water fish and creatures, while the Marina houses many salt water creatures, including a few untamed ones.  The Aquarium entrance is to the east.  You can get to the Marina through the Aquarium.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The large building marking the Northern Entrance to the city is located to the north.  You can leave the city through Evenborough Way, which is located to the east.  On the south side of the road is the Evenborough Inn, a popular overnight stop for weary adventurers.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Travelers coming in from the north side of the town often stop at the Evenborough Inn before heading into town, assuring them of a good place to stay the night.  It is a very long walk to the southern side of town, where the rest of the Inns are located, although there are a couple near the marina.  The Evenborough Inn is also ideal for visitors to Lyanden Castle, which lies to the east of the Inn.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: You can see the intersection with Lelion Parkway to the west.  Lelion  Parkway runs through the center part of the northwestern quadrant of town, passing by all the major shops and stores in the area.  On the south, you can see the large Evenborough Inn, where numerous travelers stop off for a good evening's rest.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The large Red-Eye Pub and Grill is a very popular hang out for travelers to tell stories and tall tales about their various adventures outside of the town.  The Pub and Grill also extends to a patio outside where a stage has been set up for bards and minstrels to perform and really annoy the public.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: A silvery metal gate separates you from the patio of the Pub and Grill, and the road.  Looking to the south, you can see various people sitting around talking about their adventures and life in general.  There is a stage a little further to the west.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The City Walls rise nearly ten meters up from the ground you are walking on, giving the city's guards a very good lookout into the wilderness and deserts around Oceancrest.  On the south side of the road is the Red-Eye Pub and Grill Stage, where various bards and minstrels go to practice in front of an audience.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Oceancrest Municiple Library is a small public library where anyone can come to check out various books on various subjects from history to science to magic.  The entrance to the library is located to the west of here, in front of a number of large statues.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The three great statues represent various people in the community who have brought the municiple library together.  These include the great thinkers of the times and a number of philanthropists who have given large sums of gold to fund portions of the library.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The impressive library is nothing compared to the University Library  and the Ministry of Knowledge, but it does contain a number of mystical tomes and dusty ledgers of boring city statistics.   Civilization only  remembers what it wants to remember.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Oceancrest Guard Barracks house more than a thousand of Oceancrest's finest troops, providing protection to the city by patrolling the streets, city walls and the observational stations.  The large City Walls can be seen to the north, as they run parallel to Hofton Avenue.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The City Guard Officer's Club on the south side of the road is a popular nightclub where many of the city guards go during their recreational time. The bar is rather noisy and you can see many tough characters leaving the bar all the time.

name: Darmanian Way
description: Fine gold and jewels are hard to find in Oceancrest, but Doberman has quite a stock of them for himself.  He will often buy some goods if they look like they might be worth their weight in gold.  On the north side of the road is the Evenborough Inn.

name: Darmanian Way
description: Handmade Herbs and Spices provides its customers with a wide variety of rare herbs and spices, prepared specifically for your use, whether it be for cooking or for magic spells.  Spices usually come in handy when trying to bribe guards in other cities, as some spices can be rarer than gold itself.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Evenborough Inn is located on the southern side of the road.  The entrance to the Inn is on the other side of the building, off of  Evenborough Way or Hofton Avenue.  On the south side of the road is  Pandora's Apothocary, where various, mysterious potions and oils can be bought for just about any purpose.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Temple of Clerical Science is an interesting churched formed as a  merging of clerical mysticism and mathematical certainty, bringing  together the clergy and technology.  Unfortunately, no one in the community really takes them seriously, so very little has come out of this church.

name: Darmanian Way
description: Issac's Bard Cant is a small place were bards can come to exchange  various songs and incantations between others of their kind.  Unfortunately, there is not a lot of bard activity in Oceancrest, and most of them stick around this area of town in order to get some inspiration from the various travelers who wander in and out around this area.

name: Darmanian Way
description: John's Music Shop provides bards and minstrels with all sorts of strange and exotic musical instruments to entertain guests.  The Blue Rose  Meditation Chamber on the south side of the road provides clerics and priests with a quiet meditation area, free from the hastles and chaos of the city streets.

name: Darmanian Way
description: Quite an odd combination, but the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is located on the south side of the road, while the Oceancrest Municiple Library is  located on the north side.  Although not always at odds with each other, there is usually quite a rift between science and the clergy, usually resulting in violent riots.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The three large statues in front of the southern entrance to the Oceancrest Municiple Library represent the various factors that put together a public library for anyone who wanted information to get it.  Books are rather expensive, and are not easilly obtained.  Some of the statues represent philanthropists who have given so much to the community.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is perhaps one of the most powerful factors in religious control in Oceancrest.  Much of the common law is dictated by the church, and the Cathedral forms much of that opinion.  The final authority comes from Lyanden Castle.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The large building on the north houses the more than a thousand guards  who patrol the city and the city walls, protecting the citizens of  Oceancrest from every and any possible threat to their peaceful existance. There is a Guard Surplus and Supply shop on the south side of the street, selling various extra equipment usually used by the guard patrols.

name: Darmanian Way
description: You can see the intersection with Adlermann Way to the west and the large City Walls just to the west of the road.  On the north side of the road  are the Oceancrest North City Guard Barracks, housing more than one  thousand highly trained guards.  On the south side of the street is the Lithium Lanterns shop, selling all varieties of light sources.

name: Islandia Drive
description: As you walk to the west, you can see the streets lined with various shops catering to just about every need.  On the north side of the road is Elaine's Bows, a small elven bow shop where you can purchase the finest elven craftmanship.  On the south side of the road is Dubson's Armory for Knights and Steeds, where armor can be fitted for most knights of the Castle and their trusted horses.

name: Islandia Drive
description: More shops lie along both the north and south side of the road.  On the north side of the road is Harold's Boots and Leather Footwear shop, where fine leather boots and other strong, leather footwear may be purchased at an excellent price.

name: Islandia Drive
description: Jeane's Glass and Glazing provides much, if not all, of the glass products in the realm.  Glass is expensive to manufacture, and only the finest, richest houses even have glass.  Hansel's General Provisions and Supplies shop provides essentials for travelling beyond Oceancrest.  Travelers  usually stop off here before continuing on.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Paladin's Shrine of Truth and Fairness is a testing ground to which the worthy paladin will test their skills and the shrine will determine their worthiness to advance in the ranks of the holy knights.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Golden Shield has a reputation for being one of the best shield makers in all of Oceancrest.  All the Royal Shields are made here, as well as many other fighter's prized shields from all over the land.  On the north side of the road is the North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa, where tired warriors can go for a quick break before continuing on.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Kimbler Family Locksmith provides some of the best, most secure storage chests and safes in the land.  They are also well known for being able to open almost any lock in the world.  On the north side of the road is the North Oceancrest Hot Springs and Spa, where you can go for a short break in some warm, natural springs.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Cathedral of Worldly Bliss is one of the largest facilities of its kind in Oceancrest, and perhaps much of the world.  Only the most powerful and most worthy clerics are allowed inside, and very few are ever seen wondering around in the first place.  Occasionally, the Cathedral will hold festivities and other events for the public's benefit, but this is usually just a front to collect more money from the poor.

name: Islandia Drive
description: Various things might be said about the Cathedral of Worldly Bliss, but  most of it isn't all that great.  This is primarily because the people  don't fully understand the power of these great clerics and their purpose in Oceancrest.  Without the Cathedral, it is likely the city would plunge into the first level of hell, if not deeper.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Cathedral of Worldly Bliss holds much of the moral fiber in the city together, providing a number of moral rules to live one's life by.  Since the people of Oceancrest obviously can't think for themselves, the  Cathedral must do it for them.  On the south side of the road is the Adlermann Center of Marine Research and Oceanography, a large site where numerous studies of the oceans and bays are always taking place.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The War Veteran's Historical Library is really of little importance to the common person, but a few historians and a couple of proud fighters might occasionlly stop by to do some research.  On the south side of the road is the Bendine Aquarium and Marina, where all sorts of strange and exotic creatures can be found.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Bendine Aquarium and Marina is a very large facility, connected to the Adlermann Center of Marine Research and Oceanography.  Bordering the facility is the Bendine Bay, a closed off section of the Bay where a number of monsterous creatures are kept for study and to perform for children.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: Nissiau Lane runs west from Evenborough Way, through a number of small shops and stores.  On the north side of the road is Sir Edward's Royal Swordsmith, craftsman of the finest swords in the kingdom.  On the south side of the road is the Pier Lithium Imports building, where all incoming ship supplies must be checked and registered.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: Hagar's Meat shop imports a number of fine meats and other delicacies from throughout the lands.  Although Oceancrest is well supplied with  more than enough cattle to survive for years, it is occasionally nice to have some venison or even some bear for supper.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: Icthor's Repair Shop is located on the north side of the road and repairs most weapons and armor that have worn out due to extensive wear.  No  guarentee is made, however, on the items because some might be beyond repair.  On the south side of the road is Victory Travels, a small travel broker that can tell you where other cities are and how to get to them via boat or ship.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: Rowland's Royal Fighting Academy is one of the finest training facilities for great fighters aspiring to enter the service of Lyanden Castle.  The Castle only accepts brave, strong and experienced fighters.  On the south side of the road, you can see Dixon's Polearms, a small shop where large polearms are sold.  Between Dixon's Polearms and Victory Travels, there is a small alley running towards the bay.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: Yolanda's Intricate Weavings and Tapestries on the north side of the road provides a number of fancy carpets and other fine weavings for sale.  Some are even said to be enchanted.  On the south side of the road is the  Knives 'R Us Cutlery, where various knives and blades may be purchased for just about any usage.

name: Nissiau Lane
description: The Oceancrest Soup Kitchen provides food and supplies to the homeless and displaced people in Oceancrest.  Although there aren't that many people so poor that they cannot even afford to live in the housing complexes,  many can barely put food on the table.  To the south, you can see Steve's Fishing and Tackle Shop where you can buy fishing supplies, bait and even book a boat ride into the harbor to do some relaxing fishing.

name: Sewage Pit
description: Between the biting flys and the terrible stink, you are getting sick to your stomach.  The fumes down here are deadly, and you cannot last much longer.  Somewhere at this end of the pit is an exit, but you had better hurry and find it before you are overcome by the smell.

name: Lithium Beach
description: The Highland Trade Shop imports a number of specialty items from the highlands beyond the great sea.  Most of these items are common there, but not seen often on this side of the ocean.  Much of the stuff is  purely decorative.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The grassy green park stands as a reminder of what nature is like and how it must be preserved.  Since the city is surrouned by a large city wall, not many people ever leave the city to explore the wilderness.  Small parks like this one serve as a substitute.  On the south side of the road, you can see the Evermore Development Agency, a large group of architechs that manages the building of new buildings in Oceancrest.

name: Evenborough Way
description: Althoguh Chateau Richland owns most of the grape fields in Oceancrest,  the Delgado family grows a small orchard of grapes that they use to make their wines.  Being in such limited supply makes them very popular and highly demanded.  Although the Chateau Richland wines are a bit more popular, the Delgado wines have a small, but powerful following.

name: Evenborough Way
description: The beautiful park on the north side of the road is used by many citizens and tourists alike to meet people, picnic, or just rest after a long day at work.  On the south side of the road, you can see the Delgado Family Winery, a small family operation which produces some of the best wines in the land.

name: Rosecrest Street/Evenborough Way Intersection
description: Evenborough Way runs west from here, towards the commercial areas of the northwestern section of town.  Rosecrest continues to the north and south, passing by the main entrance to Lyanden Castle.  There is a large guard station on the east side of the road, preventing people from accidentally (or purposely) entering Lyanden Lake, which surrounds the castle.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest continues to the north and south from here, eventually running past the main entrance to Lyanden Castle about three blocks to the north. On to the south, you can see the Cetacean Bridge which crosses over the Lithium Inlet, leading out to the Nylandian Bay.

name: The Cetacean Bridge
description: The Cetacean Bridge easily separates the northern section of Oceancrest from the southern section.  Nylandian Bay and the Lithium Inlet more or less physically separate the two sections of town, but there is not much of a cultural difference between the two areas of land.  The Cetacean  Bridge was so named because the workers building the bridge were constantly amused by the playful dolphins in the Lithium Inlet, enjoying the warmer waters.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Cetacean Bridge, located to the north along Rosecrest Street, connects the north and south portions of town together.  The Lithium Inlet and the Nylandian Bay create a natural barrier between the two sections of town.  As you look to the north, you can usually see a number of playful dolphins swimming in the warm Lithium Inlet.

name: Rosecrest Street/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Lelion Way runs east and west along the shores of the Lithium Inlet and the subsequent river it forms to the east.  Rosecrest Street runs north and south across the Lithium Inlet, towards the Lyanden Castle in the  north and eventually ends at the southern City Walls in the southwestern corner of town.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Fairy Dust Inn is a small inn and tavern where people coming in from the ocean entrance to Oceancrest can get a good night sleep without paying a fortune or walking a long distance to many of the other inns near the land entrances to town.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Lawrence LeMaande runs a rather large sporting goods shop, where you can  purchase a number of useful items for whatever sport you enjoy, from light shoes for long distance walking to mountain climbing equipment for those who enjoy the adrenaline rush of possibly falling hundreds of feet to an unyielding rock floor.

name: Rosecrest Street/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: Hillborough Way runs east and west from the intersection and is one of the main roads through the center of Oceancrest.  Rosecrest Street runs north and south from the intersection, heading north past the Lithium Inlet  towards Lyanden Castle, and south towards the southwestern corner of the city.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Fellowship Hall is a meeting building for the Fellowship, a philosophical group of thinkers whose alternative philosophies have brought on mass ostracation by both the general public and many of the religious orders in Oceancrest.  Strange sacrificial rituals are said to have taken place within the halls of the building.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Hunting trophies are a big thing among many hunters, and Roger's Taxidermy Shop has no problem providing magnificent stuffed heads and torsos of any animal brought in to him.  On the west side of the road is the Great Fellowship Hall, a strange group of fanatical religious philosophers who probably think the world is going to end tomorrow.

name: Rosecrest Street/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs to the east and west, fron the Nylandian Bay, all the way to the eastern entrance to the City.  This large road runs through the heart of Oceancrest, which is probably why it was named Oceancrest Avenue.  Rosecrest Street runs north and south, heading past the great Lyanden Castle near the northern entrance to town.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Occasionally, you can hear shouts of victory or defeat coming from  inside the stone walls of the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, where people are challenged to take on gladiators literally one-on-one, without the assistance of other people.  On the west side of the road, you can see the Oceancrest Central Recycling Plant and Reclaimation Center, where all the trash in Oceancrest is processed.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Oceancrest Recycling Plant and Reclaimation Center processes every  piece of garbage that everyone has ever thrown out onto the street in order to make more useful products.  The citizens are encouraged to bring trash to the recycling centers throughout town and offer five gold pieces for each piece of trash recycled.  On the east side of the road, you can see the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, the entrance to which is located to the south off of Netherworld Lane.

name: Marina Way/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: To the west, you can see the Catlania Marina and Docks within the Nylandian Bay.  The crystal clearness of the water in the bay is  viturally unblemished by the invasion by the Oceancrest docks in this natural bay.  Oceancrest Avenue runs east from Marina, heading through the center of town.

name: Marina Way
description: It is no surprise to see a fishery on the east side of the road, being that you are so close to Nylandian Bay.  On the west side of the road is the Leviathan Small Boat Rental shop and a bit to the north is the Nylandian Bay Shipmaster's Office.  Just beyond these buildings to the west is the Nylandian Bay itself.  The Bay is usually pretty busy as much of Oceancrest's commerce comes from the seas.

name: Marina Way
description: The Shipmaster is in charge of all ships entering and leaving the harbor. This is a thankless job as everyone is always in a hurry to either enter and quickly get rid of their cargo, or to get out of the harbor.  On the  east side of the road is the Temple of Ahto, the Finnish God of the Oceans and Seas.  Ahead to the north is Marina Circle.

name: Marina Circle
description: Marina Circle is the first monument to greet incoming guests coming from the harbor.  The Circle acts as a junction between Hillborough Way, running east, Marina Way, running north and south, and the Nylandian Bridge, heading west into the Bay, onto Catlania Island.  Catlania Island is the home to the Marine Headquarters.

name: Marina Circle
description: Hillborough Way runs east from the Circle, heading towards the center of town.  There are a number of small monuments around dedicated to the sailors and shipmen who were lost at sea.  On the southeastern corner, you can see the Temple of Ahto, the God of the Oceans and the Sea.  Just ahead to the west, you can also see the Temple of Poseidon, a Greek God of the Sea.  Superstitious sailors pray to both gods, but most are fond of just one.

name: Marina Circle
description: Nylandian Bridge heads out to the west, across the Nylandian Bay and onto Catlania Island, a rather large island in the middle of the Bay.  The  island houses the Oceancrest Marine Headquarters.  It is not uncommon for attacks against the City to come from the sea, thus the Marine  Headquarters is permanently stationed on the island for an early warning alert of invasion.

name: Marina Circle
description: Marina Circle is an interesting monument to sailors and marines of all ages and ranks.  The Marine Guards are fairly tough seafaring soldiers who protect the City from the sea.  Many battles have been fought for control of Nylandian Bay.  For Oceancrest, the Bay is an essential part of the economy, providing much of the commercial and industrial activity in the city.

name: Marina Way
description: Silver is a valuable commodity in Oceancrest, although not as valuable as gold or as useful as adamantine.  Nevertheless, the Regal House of Silver does some fine craftsmanship in weapons, armors and even some  fancy houseware items like candlesticks and silverware.

name: Marina Way
description: Although there is not much of a beach, you can look over the short cliffs into the crystal blue waters of the Nylandian Bay.  Marina Way swings  around the rocks and mineral buildups around the west and south sides of the road, eventually leading to Lelion Way or Marina Circle.

name: Marina Way
description: Marina Way runs along the coastline of the Nylandian Bay, so you can see all the various ships and cargo entering and leaving the bay.  The crystal clear waters seem unpolluted from the massive industrial buildup which has made Oceancrest the town that it is.  On the east is the Lelion Public Works station, responsible for the upkeep of the Lelion Beach and Park.

name: Lelion Way
description: The Lelion Beach and Park is a small beach in the Nylandian Bay forming half of the Lithium Inlet.  At the beach, you can watch the various cargo ships entering and leaving the city, bringing with them a wealth of investments, both material and spiritual.  Oceancrest's carnival and fair usually sets up tents on the lot to the west.  Late spring is carnival time.

name: Marina Way/Lelion Way Intersection
description: The intersection lies just east of the Lelion Beach and Park, one of the only beaches open to the public in Oceancrest.  Most of the beaches are not accessible because of the City Walls surrounding the city.  Such is a small price to pay for the security the City Walls provide.

name: Lelion Way
description: The Lelion Public Works station is responsible for the upkeep and continual maintanence of the Lelion public parks and beaches.  The Lelion Beach, to the west past Marina Way, is one of the few beach areas in Oceancrest, as the rest are taken up by docks, marinas, or trapped behind the City Walls.

name: Lelion Way
description: Lynn deals with all kinds of imports, usually from far way countries and islands that are only accessible through ship.  Much of the stuff that  comes in here is very strange or unique from the new lands, far to the west across the Respitial Sea.

name: Lelion Way
description: Lithium Bay Boat Tours provides its customers with various tours of the Bay and the river that drains into the bay.  Maps are also available.  The Lithium Inlet leads east into the city, eventually forming Lyanden Lake.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard runs south out of the intersection with Lelion Way, which runs east and west.  Lelion Way runs parallel to the Lithum Bay, eventually running into the Lelion Beach and Park to the west.  Eidenhoft Boulevard runs south through the major sections of the southwestern section of town.

name: Lelion Way
description: The Fairy Dust Inn is a nice establishment for people coming in from the ocean entrance to Oceancrest.  Most of the inns in town are located near the major entrances to the city, as this is the most likely place to get business.  You can see the Lithium Inlet to the north.

name: Lelion Way
description: Many of the town's visitors and guests come from the ocean, primarilly because traveling by ship is the safest means of travel.  The ocean is relatively calm and pirates have not been spotted all that often because the ships always follow the coastline.  Barbarian raiders have been known to attack caravans and travelers moving across the open plains.  The Fairy Dust Inn, to the south, provides comfortable lodgings for guests, close to the Nylandian Bay and the Catlania Docks.

name: Lelion Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see Lyanden Lake which flows  into the Nylandian Bay.  The large lake houses the Lyanden Castle, home to the King of Oceancrest and most of his staff.  On the south, you can see Lawrence's Sporting Emporium, where just about anything the average sportsman could want may be obtained.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Lankshire Parkway runs south from Lelion Way, which continues to the east and west.  On the north side of the intersection, you can see Lyanden  Lake and the island which the Lyanden Castle is built on.  The swamp-like river area on the north side of the road is probably the home to numerous animals, including a few species of alligators.

name: Lelion Way
description: It looks like a large shopping center, but you're on the wrong side of the complex to enter it.  On the south, you can see a sign which reads "Deni's World of Spices".  To the north, you can see (and smell) the Lyanden Swamp, a mushy wasteland of useless land.

name: Lelion Way
description: The large swamp on the north side of the road is formed by the collection of stale water in the basin as a result of building Lelion Way.  Normally, the water would exit to the ocean, but poor planning resulted in a sort of artificial dam, which left the area underwater.  On the south side of the road are a number of shops in a large complex.

name: Lelion Way
description: The swamp has no real purpose in Oceancrest, but provides a home to some of the displaced animals that were removed from the land which is now Lyanden Castle.  The alligators also provide good security against anyone stupid enough to try to infiltrate the castle through the lake.  There is a large complex on the south, but it appears that you can only enter it from the other side of the building.

name: Lelion Way
description: There's nothing really to see on the north side of the road except a lot of stale swamp water.  There are supposed to be some good magical components in the swamp, though.  On the south, you can see the back side of a large shopping center, the entrance to which is located on the other side of the building.  Necropolis Avenue is to the east.

name: Lelion Way
description: This is a big old testy test test test to see if adrian can figure out how to make the descriptions line up better. Im hoping this flag will do the job otherwise im trying a different command  well now this is another test Test number three n hellotesttesth

name: Avatar Boulevard/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Avatar Boulevard, running north and south, intersects Lelion Way, which runs east and west, through the intersection.  On the southeast, you can see a large facility for the numerous wounded people of Oceancrest.  Many if not all of the people entering the facility are being carried in on stretchers, bleeding profusely.

name: Lelion Way
description: The most modern science goes into healing patients, but many things cannot be overcome.  The Oceancrest Caretaking Facility for the Mortally Wounded provides care for people who are beyond recovery.  The facility also acts as a hospital, providing relief to many thousands of Oceancrestillians who are constantly getting hurt somehow.  On the north side of the road is Leia's Repair Shop.  The entrance to her shop is located off of Avatar Boulevard.

name: Lelion Way
description: A small bakery is located on the north side of the road, providing bread and other pasteries to the community.  On the south side of the road is the Oceancrest Caretaking Facility for the Mortally Wounded, which also takes care of people who may have had some mishaps in the local arenas or playing in sewers.

name: Amberton Lane/Lelion Way Intersection
description: On the northeast corner of the intersection, you can see a number of  small temples and shrines dedicated to the lesser appreciated dieties of lesser appreciated races such as the drow, goblins and kobalds.  Although they are authentic, people usually visit these temples mostly out of  curiosity rather than to pray.

name: Lelion Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the kobold Temple of Kurtulmak, the chief diety of the kobold pantheon.
