Kurtulmak is a hateful diety,  despising all races except kobolds and works to destroy life for everyone else.  Kobolds are usually only found in the sewers, but occasionally they can be seen entering the temple.

name: Lelion Way
description: The Knightly Order of the White Cross is an exclusive society for very high level Paladins.  Upon proper completion of lower level training, a paladin may try to enter the White Cross by proving his worthiness and skill through tests of courage, knowledge and strength.

name: Leviathan Drive/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive runs north and south, intersecting Lelion Way, which runs to the east and west.  On the northwest corner of the intersection, you can see a number of small shrines dedicated to the lesser known and lesser accepted dieties of different races, such as goblins, drow and kobolds.  An apple orchid is guarded by a wooden fence on the southeast corner of the intersection.

name: Hillborough Way
description: The Fairy Dust Inn is located on the north side of the road and the large Fellowship Hall is located on the southern side of the road.  To the east, you can see the intersection with Rosecrest Street.  Hillborough runs  east and west through the center of town, between a number of small shops and facilities.

name: Hillborough Way
description: On the south side of the road is the Great Fellowship Hall.  An order known only as the Fellowship meets here regularly to pass along thier philosophy of law and order through religious supremacy.  Of the many religious orders in Oceancrest, the Fellowship is usually the most unbelievable, yet the most alluring.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard runs north and south, intersecting Hillborough Way, which runs east and west.  Hillborough Way heads east towards the center of town, and through the numerous shops and stores located there.  On the southeast corner of the intersection is the Great Fellowship Hall, and on the northeast is the Fairy Dust Inn.  A small pub called the Groggy Thimble is located on the southwest corner, and the Shrine of Poseidon is on the northwest corner.

name: Hillborough Way
description: The Groggy Thimble Pub is located on the south side of the road, and caters to all kinds of people, from sailors to peasants to adventurers. The Pub is a good place to hang out and meet people.  On the north side of the road is the Shrine of Poseidon, one of the many gods of the oceans that many sailors pray to before disembarking on a long voyage.

name: Hillborough Way
description: Ahto is one of the more popular gods of the sea, second only to Poseidon. Ironically, both obviously cannot exist at the same time, and many also believe they're one in the same person.  The Regal House of Silver is  located on the north side of the street, providing customers with the finest silver trinkets, weapons and some limited armors.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the great Fellowship Hall,  home of the religious cult known to most as just the Fellowship.  On the south side of the road is the Oceancrest Recycling Plant, where useless goods are disposed of and recycled into more useless goods.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: Among other things, the Fellowship tries to convert people to their cult, as do many of the religious centers in Oceancrest.  The Fellowship members are a little more pursuasive, though, and tend to really annoy people.  It may not be a good idea to read any of the material handed out by the  Fellowship, as it's likely to be very confusing.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue, running east and west, intersects Eidenhoft Boulevard, running north and south, at this point.  Oceancrest Avenue is the road  which runs through the center of the town, and eventually ends up a the eastern entrance to the town.  Eidenhoft Boulevard runs north and south, eventually ending at the Lithium Inlet and the southern City Walls.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Leviathan Fishery provides a number of freshly caught fish and other seafood in their open air market to the public on a daily basis.  The demand for fish is not real strong as there is only one major fish seller in town.  However, a fresh fish now and then is an excellent change from beef and venison, especially during the colder months when meat is scarce.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The large Adrilite Museum of Natural History gives the citizens of  Oceancrest a glimpse into the world outside of the City Walls, without actually having to leave the safety of the city.  The museum houses many exotic species, rarely seen in Oceancrest, including a few very dangerous and deadly ones.  On the north side of the street there is a shop almost hidden from view.  A faded sign says World of Magical Wonders.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Lithium Bay Tours office provides guided tours of the Lithium Inlet and the various rivers which run into the bay, including some detailed schematics of the Lyanden Lake.  On the east side of the road is the  Fairy Dust Inn, where a number of sailors and other sea-going people often spend the night.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Fairy Dust Inn is a popular inn for people coming into the city from the ocean.  The other inns are well to the north and south, near their respective entrances to the city via land.  The Fairy Dust provides a good nights sleep for a good rate, though.  On the west, you can see the Shrine of Poseidon, and a number of sailors entering and leaving the shrine.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Fellowship Hall is an odd religious society that is profound in  believing that the world is going to end tomorrow.  Most religions say  that the world will eventually end, say in two thousand years, give or  take a few centuries, but the Fellowship is the only cult which believes armageddon comes tomorrow, and are constantly annoyed that they wake up each morning.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The large, open market on the west side of the road provides a number of fresh fish and other ocean delicacies to the general public, caught daily off the shores.  The large fish market is a popular place to get fresh fish and seafood for a change of pace from beef and venison.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Adrilite Museum of Natural History gives a concise and complete look at the various stages of life in various parts of the world from the  strange and exotic, to the downright deadly.  The museum entrance is  located on the west side of the building off of Marina Way.  A row of quaint, multicolored small buildings line the west side of the road.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Oceancrest Central Recycling Plant and Reclaimation Center is the main recycling and remanufacturing plant of trash in Oceancrest.  All the  smaller centers bring their recycled goods here to be used in other, less useful objects in a vain attempt to keep the city clean.  A small reward is given out to people who recycle. To the west is an alley which winds out out of sight in that direction.  Several shops are there.

name: Leviathan Drive/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive heads off to the south out of the intersection with Hofton Avenue, which runs east and west.  Running parallel to Hofton Avenue is the north City Wall, protecting the city from invasions, attacks and  assaults from various factions from the wastelands outside the city.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The strange Avatar Ruins were formed mysteriously by avatars of the gods fighting raging battles with each other over superiority.  Avatars, being the physical representation of the gods on this world, had powers beyond those even dreamed of by anyone, and caused more destruction than any war had ever done.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: In the pubs and the temples you sometimes hear an old tale of druids and dragons, but you never hear the same story told the same way twice.  Maybe  nobody nobody really knows the truth.  Very often though, the tales involve this very forest you see to the east.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The entrance to the Ruins is along Avatar Boulevard, which is the next north-south street to the west.  On the east side of the road you can see a very old and undisturbed forest.  There has been some mention of  druids by members of the clergy.

name: Leviathan Drive/Tranquility Way Intersection
description: Tranquility Way runs east from the intersection with Leviathan Drive,  heading north and south.  To the west, you can see the magnificent Avatar Ruins, a mysterious formation caused by the massive destructive forces of the Avatars many eons ago.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: On the west side of the road, you can see the mysterious Avatar Ruins, extending nearly forever across at least two or three city blocks.  On the east side of the road is a magnificent forest, kept preserved by the city, although no one ever seems to go in there.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: On the east side of the road is a spectacular forest, like none you've ever seen.  No one ever seems to go near it, as if it were haunted or something.  On the west side of the road are the magnificent Avatar Ruins, created by a wave of destruction by the Avatars.  Most of the destruction has been cleaned up by the passage of time, and the development of the city, but the monument stands as a warning for everyone to remember.

name: Leviathan Drive/Orchard Lane Intersection
description: Orchard Lane runs east from the intersection with Leviathan Drive, running north and south.  Orchard seems to run through the large forest area on both sides of the road.  On the west side of the intersection, you can see the mysterious Avatar Ruins.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: On the east side of the road, you can see a large park formed between Leviathan on the west and Orchard on the north.  The park, or more appropriately, forest, seems to be deserted.  Not even animals are wandering around in the patch of trees and birds fly completely around the square of land all together.

name: Leviathan Drive/Yellow Marsh Road Intersection
description: Yellow Marsh Road is a short road which runs west from Leviathan, forming the southern edge of the Avatar Ruins.  Leviathan Drive continues to the north and south.  On the east side of the road is a strange, mysterious forest where trees seem to grow very tall, but no one dares to venture in.

name: Karlberg Bridge
description: The River Othax is not a very hospitible one, and tends to be the cause of many deaths of children who enjoy playing in the rapid waters.  The Karlberg Bridge runs across the river along Leviathan Drive.  The bridge is very sturdy, but it still is a long way down.

name: Leviathan Drive/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Neilian Drive, which runs east and west, intersects Leviathan Drive, which runs north and south.  You can see the raging river Othax to the north and the Karlberg Bridge which connects the two sides of Leviathan Drive together.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Orcs have built a large shrine in dedication to Gruumsh, the orc god of all that is and will be.  He is said to rule over the other orcish  gods with an iron fist and never sleeps.  Gruumsh is not a very friendly god, but when you're omnipotent, it doesn't really matter.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Drow are fairly rare in Oceancrest, but the center to the west provides worship places for more exotic and less accepted religious icons.  Most of these dieties are not widely accepted by most of the people, but there are always the curious and a few lost Drow wandering around.  Lolth is the spider queen of the drow elves.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Shrine of Maglubiyet is dedicated to the goblin diety.  Maglubiyet enjoys wars and conflicts, believing that they bring out the best traits in all goblins and hobgoblins.  Being of a similar philosophy to Gruumsh,  both factions are usually fighting to see which is more superior and more worthy of their respective god's praise.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Directly to the west is a superb apple orchid, with some of the most beautiful trees you have ever seen.  Each tree is loaded with large and shiny apples.  In the distance to the southeast, across the orchid, you can see the towers of the Ashton Falls Resort, where the rich and famous stay when they are visiting Oceancrest.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Knightly Order of the White Cross is a large facility dedicated to  the advanced training of honorable Paladins in their quest for truth and justice.  The Order is funded primarily by the Paladins who are members, giving away most of their treasures to help other worthy Paladins advance in their ranks.

name: Leviathan Drive/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: Hillborough Way runs west out the intersection with Leviathan Drive, which runs north and south.  Hillborough runs between a number of the  small shopping centers in the center of Oceancrest.  Leviathan Drive runs all the way from the north city walls in the northern end of the city to the south city walls in the southern end.  It is one of the longest streets in Oceancrest.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: On the east side of the road is the spectacular Ashton Falls Resort and Inn, where a number of the more famous visitors to Oceancrest and even a number of high powered officials stay from time to time to get away from the chaos of life.  The magnificent resort overlooks the equally impressive Ashton Falls (a waterfall), to which the resort is named after.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Knightly Order of the Black Cross acts in conjunction with the Order of the White Cross to establish order and harmony.  There is a border between the two Orders that all Paladins must pass through.  Knowledge and control of one's dark side will make the Paladin all the more stronger in his or her quest.

name: Leviathan Drive/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs east and west through the center of the town, eventually ending up at the eastern entrance to the city.  Leviathan Drive runs north and south, making a direct path from the northern City Walls all the way to the southern City Walls without interruption.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Rodaisl Community Housing Complex is located on the east side of the road, providing housing to thousands of Oceancrest citizens.  Individual houses cannot be built inside the city due to the large population and the confining City Walls.  The compromise was the construction of two Housing Complexes to house the citizens of Oceancrest within the safety of the City Walls.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Elven Shrine of Corellon Larethian is used by all elves of the forests in the surrounding lands, and even on the other islands.  Corellon Larethian is the elven god of everything that is, and this magnificent shrine is dedicated to his greatness.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Elven Shrine of Corellon Larethian, the elven god of everthing that is, lies to the west of here.  The magnificent Shrine was built centuries ago by the elves who used to live in the area.  There are still many elves who follow Larethian's banner, but the number of elves in Oceancrest has diminished over the years.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: You can see the intersection with Netherworld Lane to the south.  On both sides of the street are large structures.  The Rodaisl Complex houses many thousands of Oceancrestillians.  Since individual houses for everyone can not be built in the city, the Housing Complexes were built to house the people who needed and wanted to live inside the city.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Sleepy Traveler Inn is a small residence for long-term visitors to Oceancrest.  The accomodations are less comfortable than in the Evenborough Inn, but made primarily for people who plan to stay for weeks or months at a time.  On the west side of the road is the Evenborough Stables, where visitors may leave their horses while visiting Oceancrest.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Evenborough Stables are provided for visitors to leave their horses while visiting Oceancrest.  Sharing the streets with horses and pedestrians can be quite dangerous, both to the horse and the people on the street. All visitors are therefore requested to leave their steeds in the capable hands of the stable managers.

name: Rosecrest Street/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Darmanian Way runs along the northern border of Lyanden Lake, while Rosecrest Street forms the western border.  In the center of the lake is a large island upon which the Lyanden Castle is built.  The entrance to the castle is located off of Rosecrest Street to the south.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: A large park opens up on the east side of the road, leading towards the drawbridge used to enter the Lyanden Castle.  On the west side of the road is the Darmanian Memorial Park where remains of very ancient civilizations are said to have existed.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Lyanden Castle is the political center of the City of Oceancrest.   All foreign affairs are conducted from the castle.  There are many diplomats from the various cultures around Oceancrest wandering about the street, waiting to meet with the High Lord Chamberlain.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Both the entrance to the Castle and to the Darmanian Memorial Park are  located to the north along Rosecrest Street.  The Castle supports most of the people of the land, providing order and justice.  Although anyone may enter the Castle, only very powerful characters seek to train in  such an honorable place.

name: Rosecrest Street/Islandia Drive Intersection
description: Rosecrest Street runs north and south, forming the western edge of the great Lyanden Lake.  In the center of the lake is a very large island on which the Lyanden Castle is built upon.  Islandia Drive runs west from the intersection, into the busy part of town.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The magnificent Lyanden Lake can be seen to the east.  A small beach is formed as the water nears the shore formed by Rosecrest Street.  On the west side of the road is the Evenborough Park, a quiet, serene park  ideal for picnics, parties or just resting peacefully under the warming rays of the sun.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The entrance to the Evenborough Park is located to the west.  The park is formed around four small paths leading into the park from each  direction, and then forming two concentric circles in the center of the park.  On the east side of the road, you can see the shoreline of the Lyanden Lake.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The large Evenborough Park seems out of place in the busy city, next to the prime commercial districts to the south and west, and just across the lake from the Lyanden Castle.  However, the park provides a serene atmosphere for people to talk without being bothered.  This restful meditation makes the citizens of the city much happier and therefore, more productive.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Avatar Boulevard runs south out of the intersection with Hofton Avenue, which continues to the east and west.  On the north, you can see the magnificent City Walls, which protect the citizens of Oceancrest from any and all attacks or sieges which might be launched against the city.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: There are three major races which inhabit Oceancrest, those being humans, elves and dwarves.  Although Oceancrest is considered a "mannish" town, many elves and dwarves also call Oceancrest "home".  However, occasionally, they will require to talk to officials of their same race, which is why the Embassy Court was set up.  Delegations from both the elven and dwarven races are represented there.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: On the east side of the road, you can see the magnificent Avatar Ruins, created by the waring Avatars of ancient history as they tried to destroy each other.  On the west side of the road is the Embassy Court, where the elven and dwarven delegations are located.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Darmanian Way heads off to the west from the intersection with Avatar Boulevard, which continues to the north and south.  On the southwestern corner of the intersection, you can see the beach formed by the massive Lyanden Lake.  In the center of the lake, you can see the magnificent Lyanden Castle.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: A large building opens up into the wonderous Avatar Ruins, a virtually desolate place where the world has more or less just opened up.  Various pieces of rock and debris lie scattered about.  The Ruins are said to  hold a number of secrets about the past and the future, but no one has really ever been able to figure them out.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: To the distance, you can see the magnificent Lyanden Castle resting on the island formed near the center of Lyanden Lake.  There are three powerful towers rising out of the castle, reaching towards the clouds. Avatar road continues on to the north and south.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: There are many sights to look at as you walk along Avatar Boulevard.   Quite obviously, on the west, you can see the majestic Lyanden Lake and the Lyanden Castle.  To the east, you can see the mysterious Avatar Ruins, where the gods once fought over control of the land and its people.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: You are approaching the southern edge of the Ruins.  The magnificent structures of the Avatar Ruins are said to hold magnificent treasures and dangerous perils.  No one entering the Ruins have ever returned with anything, but there's always the hope that one will find something of great value.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Yellow Marsh Road Intersection
description: Yellow Marsh Road is a small road leading east from the intersection with Avatar Boulevard, which runs north and south.  Yellow Marsh Road marks the southern end of the Avatar Ruins.  To the south, you can see the Anthian Bridge, crossing over the river flowing into Lyanden Lake.  Looking up, you can see a single cloud in the otherwise clear sky.

name: The Anthian Bridge
description: The Anthian Bridge crosses over the River Othax, flowing rapidly beneath your feet.  The bridge does not look very sturdy, but luckily, it's not too far across the river.  The river banks form quite an impressive cliff along Yellow Marsh Road and Neilian Drive, to the north and south respectively.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Neilian Drive heads off to the east from the intersection with Avatar Boulevard, which continues to run to the north and south.  To the north, you can see the Anthian Bridge, which crosses over the river Othax, which flows into the Lyanden Lake.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The river which flows into Lyanden Lake leaves behind a small marsh of mud and quicksand in the region to the west, which really starts to smell after a long day in the hot sun.  This is not necessarily good for the businesses that have to work here.  There is a large complex to the east which houses a number of shops.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The large center to the east is known as Neilian Plaza, which houses a  number of specialty shops, including the Neilian Boat Rentals shop, Fantine's Realm of Relics, Aaron's Armory, Loafy's Bakery and Leia's Repair Shop.  Despite the marsh to the west, the center appears to be doing fairly well.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: You can see the intersection with Lelion Way to the south.  On the east side of the road, there is a large center with a number of shops.  The entrance to the center is located to the north.  On the west side of the road is a rather smelly swamp or marsh.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The Mystic Mage Emporium, located on the west side of the road, provides a number of vital potions and spells that could be useful to any mage who finds themselves in a tight spot.  Always better to be prepared than dead.  The entrance to the shop is on the west side of the shop, off of Necropolis Avenue.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: On the east side of the road is the Oceancrest Caretaking Facility for the Mortally Wounded, a hospital for people who have suffered great injuries.  On the west side of the road is Danielle's Mystic Mage's  Emporium, where all sorts of potions and spells may be purchased.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: This rather buys intersection near the center of town has a number of useful shops and facilities on each corner.  To the southeast is Altihmin's Academy of Advanced Fighting Techniques.  On the northeast is the Oceancrest Caretaking Facility and on the northwest is Danielle's Mystic Mage's  Emporium.  Finally, on the southwest is the Shrine of Life and Death, a very symbolic icon to all clerical persons.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: Altihmin's Academy of Advanced Fighting Techniques is a large facility where very high level fighters go to train.  Training is very difficult at high levels for fighters as they must prove themselves by fighting a similar fighter of a more powerful level.  Only through this test can any fighter advance to the higher levels.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The symbolic Shrine of Life and Death is the single most important shrine in Oceancrest for all clerics despite their individual diety of worship. All religion is based on the cycle of life and death, and the balance  between the two.  Understanding this fundamental cycle is the first step towards understanding one's own religion.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs east and west through the central part of town, eventually connecting the Eastern Entrance to the city to the marina in the Nylandian Bay in the west.  Avatar Boulevard runs north and south through the intersection, spanning the width of the entire city.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The Bushman Estate includes a ranch house, plantation and farm.  The  plantation grows a number of staples needed for the society like potatoes, rice and other starches.  The farms grows the fruits and vegetables, varying by the season, and the ranch house oversees all of the operations.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The vast plantation of the Bushman Estate is located to the west of the road.  On the east, you can see the Bushman Ranch and House, where the Bushman Family runs their agricultural operation.  Additionally, they raise and nurture horses and other domesticated animals on their ranch to be used and sold as needed.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The large farmlands that the Bushman Family owns provides much of the required fruit and vegetable allowances to the citizens of the city.   Without the estate being used towards growing fruits, vegetables and other commodities, the city would have to import these items at an outrageous price.

name: Avatar Boulevard
description: The Plantation to the west grows a number of precious commodities that  Oceancrest uses to trade with other cities who are not so fortunate. Luckily, there is not much the City of Oceancrest needs in addition to what is already farmed within the city.  However, it is always nice to get in some good elven bows or strong dwarven armors.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The Great Outdoorsman is a small shop located on the west side of the road in a small shopping complex.  The small shop specializes in unique hunting and sporting equipment.  On the east side of the road, you can see Deni's World of Spices, which caters to fancy spices and herbs which might even be useable as magical components.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: On the east side of the road is the Hillborough Adamantine Works shop, where various artifacts of adamantine can be bought.  Adamantine is one of the stronger metals in the world, second only to mithril.  On the west side of the road is David's Used Books shop, where one might get lucky and find an old magic spell or an ancient scroll.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: You are in the heart of the central trading district in the center of the town.  Hillcrest Way runs east and west through the intersection and Lankshire Parkway runs north and south.  There are two large complexes on the northeast and southeast corners of the intersection, and a couple of smaller shops on the northwest and southwest corners.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway runs between two shopping centers on both sides of the  road.  On the east side of the road, you can see a large complex, whose entrance is located off of Hillborough Way.  On the west, you can see  Leo's Waxworks shop, where all sorts of wax figures, candles or other useful wax items are made and sold.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large center on the east side of the road contains a number of small shops that might be of interest to some people.  The shop directly to the east, called the House of Hides, is well known for their good leather and other hide armors for all races.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue, running east and west through the intersection, is often considered the central road through Oceancrest.  It will eventually end at the Eastern Entrance to the city to the east, and at the Nylandian Bay to the west.  Lankshire continues to the north and south, becoming one of the major roads in the southern section of town.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: On the east side of the road, you can see the large Bushman Farms estate where various fruit trees of nearly every variety grow in plenty.  The peace and quiet of the road is only interrupted by the occassional shouts of encouragement from the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, located to the west.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large Bushman Farms fruit and vegetable garden feeds virtually all of Oceancrest.  Although fruits are not in great demand here, they are nevertheless required as a good source of vitamins.  The Bushman Farms does fairly good business with both the city and as an exporter to other less fortunate towns.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, located to the west of here, is geared towards simple, one-on-one combat with a more powerful foe.  Here, good characters can test their skills versus an opponent without having to  worry about other people in the arena except themselves.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: You can see the intersection with Netherworld Lane to the south of  here through the clear plains of the farm land.  On the east side of the road, you can see the Bushman Farms Fresh Farm Fruit market where they sell all the interesting varieties of fruits and vegetables that they grow on the farm.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: Mistress Danielle Chanteclaire is one of the only arch-mages in Oceancrest and has achieved this rank at but the mere age of 623, very young for a grey elf.  There are only a handful of known arch-mages that ever existed in the world.  This is usually very good because the power which comes with this rank is also very powerful and manipulative.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: There is a large complex on the west side of the road that appears to be fairly popular.  You can hear a lot of cheering and otherwise drunken  laughter coming from the other side of the building.  The complex has an entrance on the south side of the building off of Hillborough Way.  On the east is Danielle's Mystic Mage Emporium, almost every known potion may be purchased.

name: Necropolis Avenue/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: Hillborough Way, running east and west, intersects Necropolis Avenue, running north and south, at this rather busy intersection.  To the south, you can make out the Harvest Circle, connecting Necropolis Avenue with  Oceancrest Avenue in the center of the town.  There are numerous shops on the west side of the intersection, and a magic shop on the northeast  corner.  The Shrines of Life and Death are located to the southeast.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: The philosophy of good vs. evil has long been a topic of great debate among clerics and philosophers for ages.  The Shrine of Death opposes the Shrine of Life, forming the perfect union.  This cycle of life and death is the center of the clerical mystique, to which all clerics must struggle to understand.

name: Harvest Circle
description: The Harvest Circle marks the center of the town of Oceancrest.  It connects Necropolis Avenue, running north and south, with Oceancrest Avenue, running east and west through the center of the city.  The Harvest Circle more or less gets its name because every autumn, the town gathers at the Circle in celebration of the end of the harvesting season.

name: Harvest Circle
description: The Harvest Circle more or less marks the geographic center of the City of Oceancrest.  Oceancrest Avenue continues to the east and eventually reaches the eastern entrance to the city.  The Circle is large enough that numerous people can come to celebrate the annual harvest day festival here.

name: Harvest Circle
description: The Harvest Circle is the home to the annual Harvest Day Festival, to  which all the townspeople are invited.  The festival, which lasts for many days, celebrates the past year's harvest and a toast to the future.  The large farms to the south benefit the most from the publicity.

name: Harvest Circle
description: The Harvest Circle is a magnificent structure built to celebrate the end of the year's harvest and thoughts for the next year.  To the south, Necropolis Avenue runs towards the Necropolis, surrounded on both sides by the Bushman Plantation and Farms, where much of the fruits and vegetables are grown.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: The Bushman Plantation is located on the east side of the road, and the Bushman Farms are located on the west side.  The Plantation grows a number of commodities like peanuts and indigo.  The Farms grows fruits and  vegetables.  There is a small Fresh Fruit and Vegetable Stand on the  northeastern corner of the Farm where the produce is sold to the public.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: Robert Bushman is one of the richest men in Oceancrest, primarily because of his large estate.  The Plantation on the east grows much of the basic commodities that the city requires to survive.  The Farms on the west side of the road produce nearly all of the fruits and vegetables consumed by  the city.

name: Necropolis Avenue
description: Between the farmland on either side of the road, you can see to the south the intersection with Netherworld Lane and the infamous Oceancrest Necropolis.  The Necropolis is a large monument to all those citizens who have given their lives towards the betterment of the society.  Nearly anyone who is anyone is buried there.

name: Amberton Lane/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Amberton Lane heads to the south from the intersection of Neilian Drive, which runs east and west.  To the north, you can see the short cliffs overlooking the river Othax.  On the southeast corner of the road, you  can see a number of more unique religious shrines for other humanoid dieties.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Ilsensine is the mental and spiritual diety of the illithids.  The illithids are a race of ultra-powerful mental and magical masters who have been known to wipe out parties without ever actually touching  their opponents.  Ilsensine is one of the most feared and most powerful dieties a non-illithid can encounter.

name: Amberton Lane
description: On the east side of the road are a number of small temples and shrines dedicated towards some of the goblinoid and other non-humanoid dieties. Directly to the east is the Temple of Hruggek, the dominant god of the bugbear pantheon.  Hruggek is a relatively passive diety, not  actively involved in the everyday work of the bugbear clans.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Kurtulmak is the chief diety of the kobold clans that inhabit the sewers beneath Oceancrest.  He hates just about everyone else except kobolds in the world and seeks the day that his kobold followers can take over the surface world from the hideous humaniod creatures.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Knightly Order of the White Cross is designed to be the ultimate  training facility for the Holy Knights of Lyanden Castle.  Once admitted into knighthood at Lyanden Castle, further training is required at the Order of the White Cross.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Knightly Order of the White Cross provides superior training for  paladins of high rank who have already been admitted to the ranks of Lyanden Castle's knights.  This powerful fraternity is the home to all holy knights in the land.

name: Amberton Lane/Hillborough Way Intersection
description: Amberton Lane continues north and south through the intersection with Hillborough Way, which runs east and west.  The Knightly Orders of the White and Black Cross are located on the northeast and southeast corners respectively.  To the southwest, you can see Altihmin's Academy of Advanced Fighting Techniques.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Walking along Amberton Lane is perhaps one of the more exciting things you can do when you're bored.  Further to the north are the non-human diety shrines and near the end of the road to the south is Keslar Palace.  On the east side of the road, you can see the powerful presence of the  Knightly Order of the Black Cross, the dark half that all paladins must overcome.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Altihmin's Academy is reserved for only the most powerful of fighters in the realm.  He trains fighters to be powerful leaders and even more powerful on the battlefield.  On the east side of the road is the Knightly Order of the Black Cross, the dark side which all paladins must enter and overcome.

name: Amberton Lane/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs east and west through the center of the town,  intersecting Amberton Lane, which runs north and south.  To the south, you can see the rural plains of the Bushman Farms and Estate.  On the southeast is the large elven shrine dedicated to Corellon Larethian.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Bushman Estate grows nearly every variety of fruit, vegetable and just about anything else you can think of.  Their large farmland estate runs west from Amberton Lane all the way to Lankshire Parkway.  Fresh fruits and vegetables are often for sale on the corners around their farmlands.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Holy Order of Corellon Larethian is located on the east side of the road.  The powerful diety is the head of the entire religious pantheon for the elves of the land.  Although there are many different and distinct races of elves, almost all of them worship Larethian.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Amberton Lane continues to the north and south, passing by the Holy Order of Corellon Larethian on the east and the Bushman Farms and Estate on the west.  The magnificent shrine, dedicated to the elven god of everything that is, rises high into the sky, as a monument to all elves of good faith.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Elven Shrine of Corellon Larethian lies on the east side of the road as a religious reminder to all elves.  The elven race is the most pre- dominant race on the land, but they tend to keep to themselves.  Oceancrest is primarily a human settlement, but once outside of Oceancrest, elves vastly outnumber humans.

name: Center Drive/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Center Drive heads south out of the intersection with Hofton Avenue, which continues to the east and west, running parallel to the City Walls.  On the southeast, you can see the impressive Hofton Ziggurat, where all the top delegates go to discuss various matter of importance.

name: Center Drive
description: The impressive Hofton Ziggurat is based roughly on the Allakaren Pyramid, found in the southeastern corner of the town.  Although it wasn't  duplicated in the same size, the resemblance is fairly clear.  The Ziggurat is used by many of the foreign policy makers to create stable relations between the various city-states in the land.

name: Center Drive
description: The Sleepy Traveller Inn is popular among the people who are staying in Oceancrest for long lengths of time.  The accomodations are not quite as nice as the Evenborough Inn or some of the other inns in town, but the prices are right for a week or month long stay in Oceancrest.

name: Center Drive/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Center Drive runs north from the intersection with Darmanian Way, which runs east and west.  To the south, you can see the crystal waters of the Lyanden Lake.  You can also make out the magnificent Lyanden Castle, built on the island in the middle of the lake for security purposes.

name: Delegation Way/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Delegation Way runs south from Hofton Avenue, which runs to the east and west, parallel to the northern City Walls.  On the southeast corner of the intersection, you can see the Embassy Court, housing the Elven and Dwarven Embassies.  On the southwest, you can see the Hofton Ziggurat, which is the  primary location for political delegations to meet and discuss problems.

name: Delegation Way
description: The large Embassy Court houses the embassies of the elven and dwarven delegations.  Both delegations are rather small, primarily because the number of elves and dwarves in Oceancrest is also relatively small. The delegation serve as the collective body of all the elves or dwarves in Oceancrest for political and social purposes.

name: Delegation Way
description: The Hofton Ziggurat is one of the largest structures in the city of  Oceancrest, and acts as the foreign affairs office for the city.  The Lyanden Castle, just to the south in the center of Lyanden Lake, is used primarily by heads-of-state, whereas the Ziggurat is used by all the foreign ministers for general policy making.

name: Delegation Way/Darmanian Way Intersection
description: Delegation Way heads to the north from the intersection with Darmanian Way, which runs east and west.  To the south, you can see the crystal clear waters of the Lyanden Lake and the magnificent Lyanden Castle, situated on the small island in the middle of the lake.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The mysterious Avatar Ruins, located to the south of the road, is said to be the site of a massive meeting of a number of avatars fighting for control of the lands and its people.  The result being massive destruction of just about all the lands.  It is said that this battle created the oceans, which previously did not exist.  The water is salty because of the blood spilled by the avatars.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Hofton Avenue runs east and west, parallel to the northern City Walls which protect the City of Oceancrest from all kinds of assaults and attacks.  On the south side of the road, you can see the mysterious Avatar Ruins, said to be the only remaining reminder of the clash of the avatars.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The City Walls on the north side of the road protect the city from the future, that being future attacks upon the city.  The Avatar Ruins, on the south side of the road, remind the city of the past and the various  destructions which occurs when compromises cannot be reached.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Looking to the north, you can see the massive City Walls, which protect the City of Oceancrest from any attacks or sieges by any faction outside of Oceancrest.  Although there hasn't been an uprising in a long time, the city knows that when their guard is let down, some rebel force will begin an attack.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Since Oceancrest is primarily a human town, sometimes, some of the other races which inhabit Oceancrest feel like their needs are not being fully addressed.  The Elven Embassy to the south provides a voice for the elven people to the government.  It also connects communications lines between Oceancrest and other elven cities.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The two predominant minority races in Oceancrest are the elves and dwarves. Both races have cities of their own, and the embassies to the south provide their people with a link to their heritage.  In addition, the embassies  provide a unified, political voice to the government with sympathies towards their own race.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Hofton Ziggurat is a large, pyramid-shaped building which houses the primary political policy making bodies.  Delegations from various races from around the world come here to discuss the problems of the world and what they plan to do about them.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The impressive City Walls still dwarf the tall Hofton Ziggurat in size, completely protecting it from bombardment from the outside.  The City Walls provide security to the people of Oceancrest, which is why most of the political conferences take place within the city.  No other city in the lands provides as much protection.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Hofton Ziggurat has an octagonal base, which rises up in a pyramid  shape approximately fifty meters up.  The fancy architecture is based on the ancient Allakaren Pyramid, but is not quite as impressive as the latter.  Although replicated, no one has ever really captured the style of the ancient pyramids.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Sleepy Traveler Inn is designed to provide a comfortable place to  sleep and eat.  The Inn is more or less used for longer stays in Oceancrest, and the accomodations are much more comfortable than the Evenborough Inn. However, for entertainment, you probably need to head west into the  commercial district.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The imposing City Walls provide much of the security for the town. Being on the coast of the Respitial Sea, it is has been easy to attack and overpower the city.  Of course, this has happened many times, so in order to prevent something like this happening again, the City Walls were built around the town on the land and even into the ocean for the ultimate in city defense.

name: Rosecrest Street/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Hofton Avenue runs east and west, parallel to the northern City Walls. Rosecrest Street heads south out of the intersection, passing along the western side of the Lyanden Castle.  Rosecrest Street is the longest street in Oceancrest, stretching from the northern City Walls, all the way to the southern City Walls.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Evenborough Stables are provided for guests to leave their steeds while visiting the city.  Horses can be dangerous to pedestrians walking along the streets.  Furthermore, the people on the streets can frighten the horses, causing them to hurt themselves.  For this reason, the city asks that visitors leave their horses in the provided stables.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Looking up, you can see the massive City Walls on the north side of the road, protecting the people of Oceancrest from any invasion of any kind from any foe.  Oceancrest has learned some hard lessons in the past, and is now always prepared for just about anything.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The City Walls on the north side of the road protect the city from any attacks or invasions of virtually any kind.  On the south side of the  street, you can see the Evenborough Stables, where visitors are requested to leave their horses.  To the west, you can see the intersection with Evenborough Way, and the North Entrance to the City.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The large Evenborough Stables are able to accomodate over one hundred  horses at any given time.  This is useful when there are large festivals or other meetings in town.  On the south side of the road is the Darmanian Memorial, a museum-like preservation of ancient ruins of long dead civilizations.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Evenborough Stables are located on the north side of the road, and provide visitors with a safe and inexpensive place to leave their horses while visiting in town.  Although horses and other steeds are not illegal in Oceancrest, for the safety of both the animal and citizens, they should be left in the stables while in town.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Darmanian Memorial is a preservation of ancient artifacts from early settlements in what is now the Oceancrest Valley.  The vast exhibit  provides interested patrons with a look back into time when things weren't as complicated as they are now.

name: Darmanian Way
description: To the south is the North Oceancrest Post Office, where you can send mail to people, even in other cities.  The postal service is very efficient and seldom loses mail.  Darmanian Way continues to the east and west, intersecting with Rosecrest Street to the west.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Sleepy Traveller Inn is a large facility where travellers can come and stay for many nights in Oceancrest without having to pay those  outrageous rates charged by some of the fancier inns.  The Sleepy Traveller Inn offers many "deals" for people spending a week or even a month in Oceancrest.

name: Darmanian Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the Hofton Ziggurat towering above the other structures in the city.  To the south, you can see the crystal clear waters of Lyanden Lake and the Lyanden Castle rising  high into the clouds near the center of the lake.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The northern coast of Lyanden Lake creates a beautiful beach along the southern side of the road.  Through the mist which often covers the lake, you can see the towering Lyanden Castle, rising high above the small island which it is built upon.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Hofton Ziggurat towers over the landscape with its unique pyramid shape rising towards the heavens.  It is not nearly as tall as the Lyanden Castle, which you can see to the south on the lake, but never- theless, it is quite an impressive work of art.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The Embassy Court, located on the north side of the road, provides a voice for the minority races in the huge city of Oceancrest.  Without this sort of representation, the dwarves and elves might not get as much  attention as they would like.  The Embassy is also a means to get in touch with or find out information about other elven or dwarven cities.

name: Darmanian Way
description: The crystal waters of the Lyanden Lake come ashore to the south of the road, creating a small beach where children often go to play.  The large lake is supplied by two rivers flowing in from the north and east.  The high mountains in the east supply most of the water to Oceancrest.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Evenborough Park, located on the south, is a lush, green park covered with trees and flocks of birds.  Most birds are smart enough to know that people leave seeds and other trash around the park to eat.  Unfortunately, they're not smart enough to see that sometimes this is just bait to catch them with.  Some birds in the park are particularly good in a white cream sauce garnished with mushrooms.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The lush green Evenborough Park is the home to many of birds and other small animals of the forest.  The path into the Park is directly to the south.  On the north side of the road is the Darmanian Memorial, a preservation for ancient artifacts of old civilizations.

name: Islandia Drive
description: The Darmanian Memorial is a preservation for the ancient relics and other findings of an ancient civilization known only as the Darmanians (roughly translated by one of the mages with an expertise in ancient languages). The preservation is carefully assembled to allow anyone interested to  look at and examine the various artifacts from the ancient society.

name: Yellow Marsh Road
description: There is a modest cliff heading down into the river Othax.  Although it is not that high up, it doesn't really look like it'd be an easy climb either way.  The river is on the southern side of the road, and eventually flows into the Lyanden Lake.

name: Yellow Marsh Road
description: On the north side of the road is the mysterious Avatar Ruins, where it has been said that the ancient avatars of the gods fought great battles throughout the land, creating massive mountains, the oceans and much of the features of the land.  The strange structures in the Avatar Ruins are said to be some of these remains.

name: Yellow Marsh Road
description: The odd Avatar Ruins are said to hold mysterious secrets about the lives of the ancient gods, and even said to prove that they exist.  Apperently, there was a great clash between the gods of the universe, and they used this planet to fight out their differences.  Most people no longer believe this theory, but still marvel at the mysterious Avatar Ruins.

name: Yellow Marsh Road
description: The River Othax flows smoothly across the plains of the city, originating from the high mountains outside of Oceancrest, eventually emptying into the Nylandian Bay.  The relatively modest cliffs to the south might be interesting to climb, but there doesn't seem to be anything around.  Looking up, you can see a solitary cloud a bit to the west.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The river Othax, to the north, is not a very vigorous river, but brings much of the fresh water Oceancrest needs to survive, in from the  mountains to the east.  On the south side of the road, you can see the mysterious Shrine of Gruumsh.

name: Neilian Drive
description: Neilian Drive continues to the east and west.  On the north, you can peer over the cliffs, looking down into the great river Othax, although right now, there doesn't appear to be a lot of water flowing.  On the south side of the road is the Temple of Ilsensine.

name: Neilian Drive
description: On the south side of the road, you can see a number of small shops in a rather large complex.  You appear to be on the back side of the shops. The entrance to the complex is located one block to the west off of Avatar Boulevard.

name: Neilian Drive
description: Although you cannot get into the Neilian Boat Rental Shop from here, a sign proudly advertises their products.  You can enter the plaza from the west off of Avatar Boulevard.  The Neilian Boat Rental Shop will rent you a boat for a small deposit, so that you can explore the river and all the dangers therein.

name: Hillborough Way
description: This is not necessarily a good place to be.  The great holy warriors of Oceancrest built these two facilities to further train and challenge themselves.  It was eventually discovered that there must be evil in everything that is also good, but in order to truly be good, you must in fact face evil and be able to walk away from it.

name: Hillborough Way
description: The Holy (Knightly) Order of the White Cross, on the north side of the road, is the epitome of goodness in the world, while the Holy (Knightly) Order of the Black Cross, on the south side of the road, is the epitome  of evil and despair in the world.  Paladins must be able to face ultimate evil in order to obtain a higher ranking in the paladin hierarchy.

name: Hillborough Way
description: Altihmin's Academy of Advanced Fighting Techniques is located on the south side of the road, offering advanced courses in fighting strategy for high level fighters only.  On the north side of the road is the Oceancrest Caretaking Facility for the Mortally Wounded, a sort of hospital for the badly injured.

name: Hillborough Way
description: You can see the intersection with Avatar Boulevard to the west.  The  busy intersection is, as always, crowded with people looking around for things to do.  Going west, you enter the main shopping district for the center section of Oceancrest.

name: Hillborough Way
description: There are two shrines on the south side of the road: the Shrine of Life and the Shrine of Death.  They are essentially contained in the  same building, but are distinctly separate.  All clerics must go through the Shrines in order to complete their intermediate level training.

name: Hillborough Way
description: Danielle Chanteclaire is one of the only living archmages in all of Oceancrest.  Not many people ever reach the status of archmage, and, in fact, there have only been ten archmages in all of history.  Only two are living today, which is quite amazing in itself.  Ironically, most of the archmages are still "alive" in the form of liches.

name: Hillborough Way
description: On both sides of the street, you can see a large shopping complex with all sorts of armors, weapons, gems and jewelry for sale.  There's even a small pub in the northern complex, which looks kind of rowdy.  To the east, you can see the intersection with Necropolis Avenue.

name: Hillborough Way
description: Hillborough Way continues to the east and west, running between two large shopping complexes.  To the north, you can see the Lankshire Hall of Wonders and to the south is Nathan's Light Armory.  Both shops may be entered from their respective plaza entrances (located to the west of  here on Hillborough Way).

name: Hillborough Way
description: The entrance to both centers is to the north and south of here.  The large complex on the north houses a weapons shop, a pub and a few other smaller establishments.  The southern complex appears to cater to armors and armory of various sizes and shapes.

name: Hillborough Way
description: You are in the center of town where a number of small businesses have  come together to try to sell you stuff.  There are two large shopping centers on the north and south sides of the road.  On the north, you can see the Hillborough Adamantine Works shop, and on the south, you can see the Might and Magic Mystery Shop.

name: Hillborough Way
description: David's Used Book Store is known for having strange and mysterious tomes that no one can seem to understand.  Most of the mages see his stuff as junk, but there might be a few surprises.  On the south side of the road is Leo's Waxworks, where wax is formed, melted and created into candles and other useful items.

name: Hillborough Way
description: Larry's sporting goods shop is known for its selection of various weapons and equipment used in everyday hunting and camping.  Most people go into the wilderness to hunt down a bear or two, and Larry's shop will be more than happy to provide you with equipment.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The massive elven shrine to the south is the Holy Order of Corellon  Larethian, the elven god of all that is and will be.  There are many  races of elves scattered throughout the land, but almost all of them worship Corellon Larethian, with the exception of the drow (dark) elves.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Holy Order of the Black Cross is located on the north side of the  road, opposite the Holy Order of Corellon Larethian on the south side of the street.  Luckily, there is not much hostility between humans and elves so they can practice their own religions and beliefs without annoying the other race.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The magnificent Bushman Estates run on the south side of Oceancrest Avenue from Amberton Lane to the east, all the way to Lankshire Parkway in the west.  The large estate and farm provides Oceancrest with much of the basic fruits and vegetables the city needs to survive nutritionally.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: On the north side of the road, you can see Altihmin's Academy of Advanced Fighter Training, where advanced level fighters can go to receive  superior training in hard-to-master fighting skills.  Altihmin only accepts proven fighters and won't allow people who do not meet his strict criterion.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs west into the Harvest Circle and continues to the east through the eastern half of the city.  On the north is the Clerical Shrine of Life and Death, the shrine which examines the complex, philosophical questions of life and death, integral to every form of religion.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The large Harvest Circle, located to the west, is formed by the inter- section of Oceancrest Avenue and Necropolis Avenue.  Every year, towards the autumn months, a celebration is held at the Harvest Circle to toast the year's crops and pray for a successful winter.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: Behind the fence enclosing the Bushman Farms estate, you can see nearly every known fruit tree imaginable, and possibly a few that you've not seen before.  On the north side of the road is a large complex.  There appears to be a large general store in the plaza named "Madeline's All Purpose Shop of Wares".  The entrance to the plaza is located on the opposite side of the building.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The large shopping complex on the north side of the road cannot be entered from this side of the building.  The entrance must be on the other side, off of Hillborough Way.  On the south side of the road, you can see the large Bushman Farms estate, where all kinds of fruits and vegetables are grown.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The loud cheers of triumph are coming from the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility located to the south of the road.  The large facility is geared primarily towards one-on-one combat.  On the north side of the road are a number of small shops and stores.  Further to the east, you can see the intersection of Oceancrest Avenue with Lankshire Parkway.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: After a good hunting trip, many hunters prefer to have their catch  stuffed as a trophy to display proudly and tell friends how they single handedly cut down this towering grizzly bear.  On the south side of the road, you can hear the faint cheers from the spectators at the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility.

name: Highland Avenue/Orchard Lane/Tranquility Way Intersection
description: Highland Avenue runs south out of the intersection, forming the eastern boundary of the city.  Tranquility Way runs to the northwest, passing by the Oceancrest Military Headquarters on the north side of town, and Orchard Lane heads to the west.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The City of Oceancrest prides itself on it's very quick and reliable mail system.  You can send mail to anyone, anywhere they might be, even in different towns, by merely stepping into one of the many post offices in Oceancrest or where evere else you might be.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The Dragon's Citadel is a rather unedifying place of massive proportions. The off green color has faded over long years through wars and natural disasters.  But the facility still stands proudly.  Too bad no one has ever been able to get into the Citadel, even though it's thought to have been abandoned centuries ago.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The entrance to the massive Dragon's Citadel is located off of Neilian Drive, just to the south of here.  The massive structure has remained undisturbed for as long as anyone can remember because no one has ever been able to get into the Citadel past the Great Hall.

name: Highland Avenue/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Highland Avenue forms much of the eastern edge of the city.  The large road runs north and south through the intersection with Neiliand Drive, which runs west out of the intersection.  On the northwest corner of the road, you can see the omnimous Dragon's Citadel.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The magnificent Temple of Harmonic Discord is one of the most impressive works of art in the land, although the clerics which inhabit it deny this.  The temple is the source of great power in the land, as the gods look down on the site of worship with generosity.

name: Highland Avenue
description: Highland Avenue continues to the north and south, running parallel to  the massive City Walls which lie on the east side of the road.  The City Walls act as a protective device from any and all sieges from the untamed lands beyond the city's boundaries.

name: Highland Avenue/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Lelion Way runs west out of the intersection with Highland Avenue, which continues to the north and south.  On the southwestern corner of the  intersection you can see the Wakarimasu Park, a beautiful section of land that is the first thing people see when they enter the city.  On the northwestern corner is the Temple of Harmonic Discord.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The massive park on the west side of the road is very beautiful, inspired by ancient eastern structures from the other side of the continent that few people ever get the chance to see.  The massive park boasts a number of shrines to ancient gods and goddesses no longer believed to exist.

name: Small Bridge
description: As you look over the railings of the bridge, you can see the wide river bringing cold and fresh water down from the mountains into the large park to the west.  The river appears to flow evenly into the forest-like wooded  park, bringing fresh water from the mountain icepacks.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Ahead, to the north, you can see a grand bridge crossing over a very powerful looking river.  The river appears to be flowing into the park. Highland Avenue continues to the north and south, running parallel to the eastern border of the city and the City Walls.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The massive City Walls on the east side of the road, provide the ultimate in personal security for the entire town.  Ever since they were built, no attack against the city has ever been successful.  The people and military pray that any attack in the future will also fail.

name: Highland Avenue/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Oceancrest Avenue runs west from the intersection with Highland Avenue, which runs north and south.  On the east side of the intersection is the eastern entrance to the city.  Leaving through the east will take you into the plains beyond the city, a relatively dangerous place, roamed by barbarian hordes and other bandits.  This path is the quickest way to the mountains, but is also the most dangerous.  The cities of Brownhaven, Hafnia and Kista lie to the east.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The wide grassy plot on the west of the road is guarded by a tall fence through which you can see many of the richer travelers lounging around. The elegant Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge is a very popular among travelers and other visitors to Oceancrest.

name: Highland Avenue
description: Highland Avenue runs north and south, parallel to the eastern City Walls, which form the eastern boundary of the city.  The City Walls were built to protect the citizens of the city from attacks and sieges from the barbarian cultures in the plains beyond the city.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The elegant Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge is one of the more popular inns in the city.  Of course, being as elegant and well-kept as it is, the Lodge tends to cost quite a bit to stay in for just a couple of nights.  There are stables to the south where you can leave horses while visiting Oceancrest.

name: Highland Avenue
description: Highland Avenue forms the eastern end of the City of Oceancrest.  On the east side of the road is the massive City Wall which protects the  citizens of the city from any unwarranted attacks against them.  On the west side of the road is the elegant Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge.

name: Tranquility Circle
description: Tranquility Circle marks the intersection of three major roads running through Oceancrest.  Hofton Avenue runs northwest out of the circle, forming the northern border of the city.  Tranquility Way runs east and west through the circle and Wakeforest Drive runs south past the Dragon's Citadel and eventually meets the Oceancrest Circle.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Fiesty Kitten Night Club and Bar is one of the more dangerous places to be seen at, especially if you're not an officer in the City Patrol.  The Bar is a very loud and dangerous place where people have a tendency not to leave ever again.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Tranquility Patrol Station is located on the east side of the road and provides assistance in keeping the peace in Oceancrest.  These domestic guards patrol the streets of Oceancrest, cleaning up crime where ever they can.  Unfortunately, the Tranquility Patrol is rather small and cannot handle much of the action which can take place in a city as large as Oceancrest.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Orchard Lane Intersection
description: Orchard Lane runs east and west out of the intersection with Wakeforest Drive, which continues to the north and south.  On the southeast, you can see the mysterious Dragon's Citadel.  On the north side of the  intersection, you can see a number of administrative buildings, primarily guard patrol buildings and barracks.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: On the east side of the road, you can see the mysterious Dragon's Citadel. No one has really had the guts to go into the Citadel for ages, so no one really knows what goes on inside the haunted halls of the long abandoned old church.  The entrance to the Citadel is located on the north side of Neilian Drive.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The North Oceancrest Ministry Building is located on the west side of the road, and consists of the Ministry of Tranquility, the Ministry of Rumor Control and the Hall of Discipline.  The entrance to the Ministries is located along Ministry Way, located one block to the west.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Dragon's Citadel is filled with both mystery and danger.  Although it has long been thought to have been abandoned, strange sounds are often heard from it at night.  The entrance to the Citadel is located along Neilian Drive.  On the west side of the road are a number of governmental building, the entrance to which are located on the other side of the building along Ministry Way.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Wakeforest Drive continues to the north and south through the intersection with Neilian Drive, which runs east and west.  On the northeast corner of the intersection, you can see the magnificent Dragon's Citadel, an odd building constructed many centuries ago, now believed to be abandoned.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Holy Order of the Red Rose is one of the Paladin's training centers in Oceancrest.  This center is designed to train intermediate level Paladins before they enter the services of Lyanden Castle.  The Shrine of Creation is a monument to life in general, although no one can really figure out who built it or why.  Many people, however, still frequent the small shrine, hoping for a miracle of some sort.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: On the east side of the road is the Nowhere Fast Traveler's Guild, where every weary traveler should check into before leaving the town.  The Guild will carry important information about the conditions of the roads, possible ambush points and city status.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Lelion Way runs east and west out of the intersection with Wakeforest Drive, which continues to the north and south.  On both sides to the south of the intersection, there is some thick brush that prevents you from seeing into what appears to be a small park.  There appear to be a couple of shops and facilities to the north along Wakeforest Drive.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: As you approach the northern end of the park, you see that a heavy brush  and thick trees block off what you can see.  This protective cover on the north side of the park prevents people from seeing the real purpose of the park, which is actually a shrine to ancient oriental gods.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: As you cross over the ancient bridge over the Ashton River, you can see the impressive design of the Wakarimasu Park.  The Ashton River is relativly wide, but that is to be expected as the mountains snows have produced a lot of water lately.  The river flows west towards the ocean.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The massive Wakarimasu Park was built nearly two decades ago with the unclaimed land on the north side of Oceancrest Avenue.  Since that plot of land was the first thing seen by visitors to Oceancrest, the City decided to build an elegant park, which spans approximately two city blocks.

name: Oceancrest Circle
description: The Oceancrest Circle welcomes visitors and friends to the City of Oceancrest.  The entrance to the city is located to the east of the Circle about a block away.  There is a magnificent tree centered in the middle of the circle, but there appears to be no significance attached to it.

name: Oceancrest Circle
description: These magnificent circles scattered throughout Oceancrest display the proud heritage of the city.  The Oceancrest Circle welcomes all visitors to Oceancrest.  Visitors to Oceancrest are warned that some of the less desirable elements of any city are likely to be found in the northeastern quadrant of the town, and are therefore advised to avoid the area.

name: Oceancrest Circle
description: Walking around the Circle, you see that it is not just a dirt path, like most of the other roads, but is finely decorated with ornate bricks and cement.  Although there are a few paved roads in town, it is not common to see such fancy artwork that people can step on.

name: Oceancrest Circle
description: The Oceancrest Circle welcomes people to the city of Oceancrest.  The entrance to this magnificent city is located to the east of the circle, about a block away.  Wakeforest Drive continues to the south, running through the poorer parts of town.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: You can see the brilliance of the Oceancrest Circle to the north.  It was designed to be a powerful symbol of the unity and power in Oceancrest, and the pride the people take in living and working in such a city.  The Circle was built and privately funded by the citizens of Oceancrest and then donated to the City.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge is one of the most popular Inns in the City, mostly because of its very luxurious rooms and the atmosphere surrounding the Inn.  It is considerably safer than most of the other  Inns, located around troubled spots in the city.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: On the west side of the road, you can see the magnificent building known as the Chancellor's Hall in the Illandi University complex.  The University is one of the most prestigious in the realm, and gladly accepts any student who has a desire to learn.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The magnificent design of the park on the north side of the road is roughly based on ancient oriental themes.  Wakarimasu Park, as it is named, includes a number of beautiful shrines dedicated to ancient dieties that haven't been worshipped in centuries.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The posh Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge on the south side of the road is a very popular lodging place for visitors to Oceancrest.  Its luxurious accomodations are not without a price, though.  On the north side of the road is the Wakarimasu Park, an elegant park based on ancient oriental architectures.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Oceancrest Circle welcomes all visitors to Oceancrest and all the splendor the city has to offer.  On the north side of the road is the magnificent and beautiful Wakarimasu Park.  On the south side of the road is the Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the large Wakarimasu Park, based primarily on ancient oriental architecture.  There is a large building in the park a bit to the west along Oceancrest Avenue.  On the south side of the road is the Iilandi University.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Kobiyo Observatory is a large building in the Wakarimasu Park dedicated to examining the stars and other celestial bodies in space.  The Observatory is an extension of the Iilandi University, located to the south.  On the south side of the road is the Iilandi University Visitor's Center and the Recreational Facilities.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Kobiyo Observatory, located to the north on the grounds of the  Wakarimasu Park, is one of the few scientific stations dedicated towards astronomy and astrophysics.  Very few people have time to deal with such trivialities in everyday life, but it is somewhat interesting to visit every so often.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: The Iilandi University is one of the most prestigious schools in all the realms, mostly because it not only lets anyone who has a desire to learn enroll, but also because the professors must have a genuine desire to teach and do research.  The various scientific stations around the  University provide an infinite amount of researchable activity that could keep the great minds of the time busy for generations to come.

name: Tranquility Way
description: Tranquility Way makes a turn towards the southeast, heading towards the eastern border of the city.  On the south, you can see the Tranquility Patrol Station, a police-like force that attempts to keep the peace in the streets of Oceancrest.

name: Tranquility Way
description: The great Oceancrest Military Headquarters is located on the north side of the road, and covers much of the northeastern section of town.  The City of Oceancrest is very proud of their military might, which is about the only way to keep the barbarian cultures outside the city at bay.

name: Tranquility Way
description: You can see the intersection with Highland Avenue and Orchard Lane coming up to the southeast.  This rather large intersection is more or less the northeastern corner of town, as Highland Avenue forms the eastern boundary and the Military Headquarters to the north forms much of the northern  boundary.

name: Entrance to the Dragon's Citadel
description: The Dragon's Citadel is known for it's mystical healing powers and superior magical spells.  No one has really ventured further into the Citadel beyond the Great Gates which you can see to the distance in the north.  Those who have, have never returned, but just entering the Citadel, travelers and explorers have felt a mystic wave of power overwhelming them.

name: Citadel Hallway
description: The Citadel's Hallway continues to the north and south.  To the north, you can see two great gates, but can't quite make out exactly where they go.  You can see some writing on the walls up ahead, but that's about it.  To the south, you can see two large oak doors that appear to lead out back into the city.  The walls are surrounded with gold and jewels.  Portraits of apparently great dragons line the walls on both sides.  You fees a cold gust of wind hit you as you continue to explore this strange place.

name: The Great Gates
description: Two massive iron gates stand in front of you, one to the east and one to the west.
