To the north, a large plaque is inscripted with the  following message: "Only the Worthy and Pure of Heart may Enter the Citadel of the Dragons or be Forever Destroyed."  On the east gate, you can see a white plaque with black writing that you can't read. On the west gate is a similar plaque, except it is black with white writing.  The gates appear to be locked.  The locks glow in a greenish hue and do not appear to be unlockable with an "ordinary" key.

name: Orange Jacinith Hall
description: An apparition appears before you in the form of a beautiful maiden in glimmering white.  She wears a robe and amulet with a mysterious symbol shaped like a large, upside-down Y.  She says to you: "Your quest begins here.  Before you can enter the East Gate, you must find a key that  is more magnificantly yellow than gold.  The Crystal Alcove is filled  with illusions.  Trust your senses and you cannot fail.  Do not enter the Alcove until you have found an object which light cannot penetrate."   She disappears into a puff of smoke before you can ask any more questions, such as, what is this quest she talks about.

name: Crystal Intersection
description: A small sign above the staircase says "Crystal Alcove".  As you peer down the staircase, you can see your reflection, as if you were waiting at the bottom of the staircase looking up.  A cool breeze can be felt coming from the bottom of the stairwell.

name: Orange Jacinith Hallway
description: The mirror is oddly placed at a 45 degree angle to the two hallways. In the mirror, you can see yourself walking towards yourself in a  very wierd optical illusion.  Or is it an illusion?  As you look into the mirror to the west, you see a seemingly endless hallway.  Turning to the east, you can still see the magnificent crystal intersection.

name: Orange Jacinith Hall
description: This hallway is very deceptive.  You appear to be heading around in  circles but can't really tell one way or another.  As you continue to explore this very odd hallway, you notice that to the north and south are two giant crystals that reflect light, giving an appearance of an endless corridor.

name: Orange Jacinith Hall
description: In an almost symetrical hallway, you see both to the east and west a  crystal intersection.  The intersection to the east appears to be a little closer than the west one, but it's hard to tell.  Careful examination  of the west wall reveals a large crystal that reflects light around a  bend to the south.

name: Crystal Intersection
description: The room reflects a lot of light, making it hard to tell which direction you are actually heading.   Far to the south, you can make out another crystal room and a stairway.  Looking to the east, you can see yourself in the distance standing in a crystal hallway.  Is it an illusion or isn't it?

name: Orange Jacinith Hall
description: Upon careful examination of the corridor, you notice that you cannot in fact go east without breaking your neck.  As you walk east, you bump into a large crystal object that acts like a giant mirror.  The mirror is so proportioned that the corridor at which you are looking  appears to go straight through to the iron gate.

name: Red Ruby Hall
description: You try to escape the brilliant red light of the ruby hall but without much success.  Carefully examining the hallway, you find a short, cryptic  message written on the floor near the west wall.  It says: "HELP."  As you walk closer to it, the letters disappear into the redness of the hallway.

name: Mirrored Hall
description: Upon careful examination of the room, you find a small note on the floor which reads: "What to do if you find yourself in a mirrored room with no exits and no hope of escape.  Consider how good life has been to you so far.  If life has not been good to you, which is more likely the case in your present situation, consider the fact that it will not be bothering you for much longer."  You toss the note down and bang your head against one of the mirrors.  When you come to your senses, as often a good bump on the head does to a person, you can somewhat make out a room to the south.

name: Mirrored Hall
description: Upon considering how good life has been to you so far, you stop to rest along one of the mirrors you've bumped into.  Bones lie scattered about this room (but strangely, not in the north room).  Another note lies on the floor that you almost overlook.  It says: "What to do if you encounter the ravenous beast of Traal.  Wrap your head with a towel, being sure to cover your eyes.  The beast of Traal is so stupid that it thinks that if you can't see it, it can't see you and goes about it's business.  Since you left your towel behind, your other option is to run away, terribly fast."  You continue to bang your head against the crystal wall.

name: Guardian of the Dragon's Citadel
description: As you approach the alter, a large plume of smoke and fire rises to  greet you.  In the flame, you can make out a human-like face that speaks to you: "Go into the darkness and you will find light.  The Crystal Alcove is an illusion to prevent the unworthy from finding the treasures of the Alcove.  Only the most skilled will pass."  With that being said, the flame retreats back into the alter.

name: Guardian's Treasure Room
description: Upon further examination, you notice that the glittering object is in fact some sort of sword.  However, it's embedded in a large stone idol standing some eight feet tall.  You find it impossible to get the sword out of the idol.  Looking more carefully at the idol, you notice a  necklace engraved in the stone, but it's missing a gem.  It looks like it's been pried out by looters.

name: Inside the Dragon's Lair
description: The rooms all look the same, glimmering with gold and jewels.  You wonder how many warriors have given their lives for this fantastic lair.

name: Inside the Dragon's Lair
description: All the rooms look the same, glistneing in gold and jewels.  Sounds like there's a lot of activity ahead.  A blood-curling scream almost makes you jump out of your armor.

name: Dragon's Feeding Grounds
description: This is where the dragons come to eat.  At first you seem interested in the activity of the dragons, but then you realize that you are probably the main course.

name: Dead End
description: Dead ends are the last place you would want to be in this dangerous lair.  You have seen a number of guards patrolling the area and  there's no place to hide in here.

name: Dark Staircase
description: You can easily make out the stairs with the light you have generated, but the ground is very slippery.  It appears to be covered with moss and other slime.  The ornate staircase reveals nothing about the upper or lower realms you are venturing into except for the incredible detail of which the staircase is crafted.

name: Crystal Alcove Entrance
description: As you peer into the large alcove, you notice that there is no order or logic to the design.  You can see an infinite number of exits to the alcove, but you're not sure if those exits are real or just illusions. The alcove begins to the north.

name: Crystal Alcove
description: It's a good thing your compass works because there's no way to figure out which direction you're going.  All you can make out that iis significant are the various exits out of the place.  There appear to be an infinite  number of stairways up and down, but strangely about three times more exits going down than up.  All the exits look like they're very far away.

name: Crystal Alcove
description: It's a good thing your compass works because there's no way to figure out which direction you're going.  All you can make out that iis significant are the various exits out of the place.  There appear to be an infinite  number of stairways up and down, but strangely about three times more exits going down than up.  All the exits look like they're very far away.

name: Red Curtain Room
description: This place is bizzare.  You see red curtains in all directions.  The floor is made in a zig-zag pattern of red and white stripes.  There are three chairs in the center of the room.

name: White Hallway
description: This place is getting wierder and wierder.  At the end of the hall is a bust of some sort.  You can't really make out the figure, as it's someone you haven't seen before.  There's another one at the other end of the hallway.

name: White Hallway
description: This place is getting wierder and wierder.  At the end of the hallway is a bust of some sort.  You can't really make out the figure, as it's someone you haven't seen before.  There's another one at the other end of the  hallway.

name: Klaw's Room
description: This is Klaw's room.  Klaw is the deadly black devil from the sixth plane of hell.  He also doesn't care much for visitors and will try to steal your soul.

name: Crystal Alcove
description: It's a good thing your compass works because there's no way to figure out which direction you're going.  All you can make out that iis significant are the various exits out of the place. name: Dark Stairwell
description: The stairwell is rather unremarkable and made of old, creaking boards that will probably break as soon as you step on them.  Miraculously,  they don't but it's best not to stay on them for very long.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: The walkway continues to the east and west and curves south at each  corner.  A small engraving in the wall on the south says "Do Not  Trust Your Compass!".  As you look to the east and west, you can see a number of bones lying about and glowing brightly.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: As you stumble around in the mist, you begin bumping into walls and realize that you're still in the same corridor and it does not appear to curve or bend.  It would help if you had a compass that worked because yours keeps going around in circles.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: As you stumble around in the mist, you begin bumping into walls and realize that you're still in the same corridor and it does not appear to curve or bend.  It would help if you had a compass that worked because the one you have keeps going around in circles.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: The walkway continues to the east and west and curves south at each  corner.  A small engraving in the wall on the south says "Do Not  Trust Your Compass!".  As you look to the east and west, you can see a number of bones lying about and glowing brightly.

name: Lycantrope's Den
description: Despite the horror stories you've heard about lycanthropes, these appear to be elves that have been cast out of their society.  They hold the form of great silver foxes, but have an insatiable desire for flesh (particularly elven, but anything will do).  The stench of rotting flesh is starting to get to you, but you can't seem to find a way out.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: The lime-green walls are surprisingly slick and clean.  A strange mist appears to the south and obstructs your view of exactly where you're going or where the hallway leads.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: The lime-green walls are surprisingly slick and clean.  A strange mist appears to the south that obstructs your view of exactly where you're going or where the hallway leads.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: After some experimentation, you manage to find the slick green walls, that almost feel slimy.  By following the walls, you can more or less find  your way through this wierd maze of sorts.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: After some experimentation, you manage to find the slick green walls, that almost feel slimy.  By following the walls, you can more or less find  your way through this wierd maze of sorts.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: After some experimentation, you manage to find the slick green walls, that almost feel slimy.  By following the walls, you can more or less find  your way through this wierd maze of sorts.

description: After some experimentation, you manage to find the slick green walls, that almost feel slimy.  By following the walls, you can more or less find  your way through this wierd maze of sorts.

name: Jade Green Hallway
description: After some experimentation, you manage to find the slick green walls, that almost feel slimy.  By following the walls, you can more or less find  your way through this wierd maze of sorts.

name: Worn Path
description: The path is rather crooked, so you cannot see very far in either direction, but the city street appears to be to the east.  A large grove of trees to the west looks like it may be a campground of some sort.  You can hear music in that direction, and the sound of merry voices.

name: Smooth Path
description: Tall trees shade the path and a gentle breeze skitters through the leaves.  The path is broad and clear, and seems to lead to a noisy campground to the west.  The path narrows in the eastern direction, and you can see a city street in the distance.

name: Gypsy Camp
description: A large campfire burns brightly in the center of the camp, and a group of dancers swirl to the music from a wild violin played by a tall youth wearing bright clothing.  A brown bear in a harness shuffles with them, waving his giant paws in time to the music.  The good smells from the cooking pots are making you hungry.  Several large wagons are pulled into a circle around the clearing to the north, while there appears to be an animal keep to the west.  Easterly is a smooth, worn path leading away from the camp.

name: Green Wagon
description: The players look up as you enter, but go back to their game as you stand here.  A short, very fat man sits alone in a corner and stares at you as he slowly strokes a strange animal in his lap.  The animal is a cross between a lynx and an elven cat, and apparently does not like you.  The lynxven is brightly colored with tassled ears and sabre teeth.

name: Orange Wagon
description: A young boy, perhaps seven years old, sits amidst the pillows on the floor attended by several old men.  He speaks and they listen intently, while one of them writes swiftly in a large book.  A curtain hangs between you and the scene inside, and a hand motions for you to enter.  You may speak to the boy, known as Vlassen the Wise.

name: Wagon Clearing
description: The large blue wagon belongs to the king of the gypsys, while Madame Nicolov occupies the bright red wagon.  Some type of heavy animal, with a great shaggy head, grazes between the wagons.  A faded green wagon is next to an orange one, and a huge brown wagon is a little apart from the others.  The campfire in the clearing is to the south.

name: Blue Wagon
description: A multi-colored cloth hangs over a doorway separating this room from the bedroom.  A trestle table stands in the middle of the room, loaded with food and bottles of wine.  The king of the gypsys talks to his chiefs in this room, planning their activities which will part a few gold pieces from the citizens of Oceancrest.  there is a rumor that a lot of gold is stored in this wagon.

name: Gypsy King's Sleeping Quarters
description: The massive oak bed takes up most of the room, leaving little space for the clutter of strange items that have been gathered after years of travel in the Land of Mordor.  A mechanical bird in a cage watches your every step as you move about the room.  On a high shelf you can see a brass vial which gives off a sweet smelling vapor, contending with a pungent odor coming from a salve in a blood-red container marked "eternal youth."

name: Vlassen's Plane
description: Vlassen sits on pillows, a small boy with a smooth face and a tender young body.  His eyes follow you, and appear to be ancient pools of darkness as they peer into your soul.  He slowly twists a heavy strand of knotted human hair in his small hands as he waits for you to speak. The elderly men mutter and glare as they also wait.  Do not anger them further, as they are powerful in spite of their appearances.

name: Madam Nicolov's Wagon
description: Madame Nicolov is a world famous phrenologist who has given lectures at all of the great universities on the meaning of head bumps and methods for reading them.  A very low chair is in the center of the room, and another, higher chair is directly behind it.  Standing nearby is an armature with a human head mounted on it.  The mouth looks about ready to speak, but the eyes are closed and the head remains silent.

name: Animal Keep
description: A number of stalls have been setup and a training circle looks well-worn. There are small animal wagons lined up on one side, and bags of feed and piles of straw are on the other side of the compound.  Gypsys are known as great animal trainers and this is apparently where much of that training takes place.  Several of the great horses that pull the wagons are tethered at one end of the keep, and some very exotic animals are at the other end. The campground is to the east.

name: Rutted Road
description: Heavy wagons have been pulled down this road, and the ruts are deep. The vines on either side of the road are heavy with this year's crop of grapes, and the field hands who pick them can be seen in the distance. The road seems to run between a grove of trees to the east and some farm buildings to the west.

name: Dirt Road
description: The road has been in use for a long time and is bare of weeds.  It is apparently used fairly often.  There is a mid-day rest area immediately to the north, and in the distance to the east you see a large grove of trees.  Several farm buildings lie to the southwest.

name: Road Fork
description: The wider road heads to the northeast, while the smaller and less used one continues to the north.  You can see several farm buildings a short distance to the north, and several farm workers appear to be trudging in that direction.

name: Orchard Compound
description: One building appears to be a storage shack for farm tools, and another is the foreman's office.  A small general store is on the western side of the compound.  Further to the west are a number of small homes for the field hands who work for the Chateau Richland Winery.

name: Farm Road
description: A large billboard stands beside the road and advertises wine as a healthy choice.  The Chateau Richland Winery grows some of the best grapes in all of the Land of Mordor in the orchard you are presently passing through.  The road appears to lead toward some farm buildings.

name: General Store
description: Workers for the winery can run up an account here, which is one of the reasons so many of them continue to work for the winery.  They are so far in debt, they cannot leave.  The store will also buy items, if they feel they can make a profit on them later.

name: Grape Picker's Shacks
description: The shacks are well cared for, but they are still just shacks.  A small pond of water lies to the west and you can see a number of very ugly children playing there.  A large barn is to the north, and you can see a few people working in there.  The grape vines cover a vast area behind the barn and past the pond.

name: Foreman's Shack
description: The walls of the dirty room are covered with pictures of naked gnomes, and a tall, wooden vat, half-filled with wine, stands in the corner. A poster advertises a new line of short-handled hoes for field work. The foreman is brutish half-gnome with a terrible disposition and a quick temper.  If the field workers were not so heavily in debt to the company store, they would have left long ago because of him.  He is at his worst when drunk, and none have ever seen him sober.

name: Orchard Path
description: The path meanders in an east-west direction, following a drainage ditch filled with sewage.  The grape vines along the sewage ditch appear to be particularily healthy and productive.  To the west is a number of small shacks, lovingly called homes by the grape pickers who live there.

name: Rest Area
description: A small stream pools here, providing a reflecting surface for the tree branches above.  A lone picnic table stands in the middle of the area. Someone has wedged a wine keg in the lower boughs of the tree, and it seems to have a good amount still in it.  Perhaps this would be a good place for a nap after a nip.

name: Storage Room
description: The king of the gypsys collects a trubute from every gypsy in the land once a year, and not trusting banks, has decided to stash his gold here. Of course, he has provided the place with safeguards just in case some one finds this place.

name: Sewage Pit
description: Not only does it stink here, but the bite of the flys is drawing blood. Directly overhead is a closed trap door which you fell through, and can- not go back into.  Looks like the only way out is to slog through the shit and climb out from underneath the wagon.  Better hurry though,  there really isn't much oxygen down here.

name: Secret Quick Car Transporter
description: The quick cars were developed by the elves to let them move around the mountains quickly and safely without having to deal with all the threats on the surface.  With the help of dwarven miners and elven ingenuity, the quick cars zip through the tunnels at speeds close to 60 kilometers per hour.  Hold on tight.

name: Secret Quick Car Transporter
description: You've found an old quick car terminal.  There's a car here for you to use but you're not sure if it'll get you anywhere.  The quick cars were created by the elves to get around the mountains quickly and efficiently.

name: Secret Quick Car Transporter
description: The quick cars are a fast and efficient mode of transportation between different places in the mountains and valleys.  The elves of Caledonia created these cars and passages to travel great distances in minimal amounts of time.  Brownhaven is about as far west as these cars go. At one point, the elves held a fascination with the humans, but  decided that their basic nature was too violent to peacefully coexist together.

name: Secret Quick Car Transporter
description: The elves used quick cars to get around the mountain quickly and  efficiently.  Powered by gravity and literally no friction, quick cars can travel between cities in a matter of seconds.  Hold on, though.  These cars can travel at speeds up to 200 miles per hour. And who knows where you'll end up.

name: Hafnia Post Office
description: You can send and receive mail from here to any other post office in Mordor.  It's nice to have a modern postal system that works. There are several "wanted" posters on the bulletin board.  Is your name there?

name: Secret Underground Passage
description: You assume you're somewhere under the city of Hafnia.  The torches have all burned out.  You have reached a dead-end in the passage.  The passage  continues to the northeast.  You notice that the floor is rather slick. It has been covered with moss and mildew so much so that the floor just looks green.

name: Secret Underground Passage
description: The smell is getting worse.  You see a light in the passage to the northwest.  As you try to turn your attention away from the stench of decaying bodies, you notice some ritualistic paintings and carvings on the wall.  It appears to be a sacrifice of a young virgin elf to some evil looking gods.

name: Elven Sacrificial Temple
description: You see a large table in the center of the room.  This is probably  where the old elves gathered for their ritualistic sacrifices to their gods.  From the pictures on the wall, you notice that most of the  pictures depict sacrifices to evil looking beings.  The statues in the room look rather scary.

name: Secret Underground Passage
description: You've deduced that you must now be under the cemetery.  It's quite dark in here.  All the torches have burned out.  You notice that the floor is covered in sickly green moss, making it quite slippery.  The smell in here is also pretty atrocious.

name: Crematorium
description: You see a large furnace in the middle of the room.  You can safely assume that this is the place where people are cremated for burial. Even though it's pretty much deserted, it still sends shivers up your spine.

name: Mausoleum
description: The door has shut as you walked in.  The only way out is to find the right key.  In the center of the dark room, you see a large marble sarcophagus.  It's about nine feet long and two feet wide, decorated in an ornate elven style.  The inscription reads: "Here lies Dabin, Founder of the Great City of Caledonia".

name: Cemetery
description: What looked like a vacant lot from the road turned out to be a small cemetery.  It has been kept up quite well over the years, but still looks like it's deserted.  You see no visitors at all.  You wonder if any of the ghosts of these people will show up to haunt those who killed them so many years ago.

name: Polearms Retailer
description: The polearms shop is very useful for those who cannot find polearms anyplace else.  The Hafnia Polearms Retailer sells polearms to just about every retailer in the world and probably has the best prices. If you know what you want, but can't find it anywhere, come here.

name: Hafnia Mage Emporium
description: You've never seen this many magic supplies in your life.  Everything  you could imagine is here.  Hafnia prides itself on the quality and quantity of it's supplies and this magic shop is no different.  If you want a magical potion, this is the place to be.

name: Terrel's Tavern
description: There are numerous people all around you.  Most of them are just drinking and having a good time.  As you walk in, everyone glances at you and then goes back to their own business.

name: Strumpet's Bedchambers
description: People wander in every now and then.  I think you can figure out what happens in here.  The room is kept fairly tidy considering the amount of traffic in and out of this room.

name: One Eyed Jack's
description: So this is where all the people disappear to in the evening.  You see slot machines, poker tables, blackjack tables and more.  There's more money on the tables than you've seen in your whole life.  There's also more alcohol and drunks here than you seen in your whole life too.   This place makes the local Brownhaven Pub look like a day care center.

name: Side Alley South
description: You would have missed the entrance to this if you were not such a careful  observer.  This area appears to be very well traveled.  There seems to be  a lot of footprints leading north.  Maybe it's just a short cut.

name: Side Alley North
description: You would not have normally seen this alley here if you were not looking so carefully.  You have been following a number of footprints and they all seem to lead to this one door.  Unfortunately, the door is locked. Do you have the right key or do you think you can pick it?

name: Rear Alley
description: This is where most of the shoppes receive their inventories from the elves in town who make such fine goods.  Of course, the caravans also deliver their goods here too.  Some of the rarest and finest items in all of the Land of Mordor are sold from the shoppes in Hafnia.

name: Bowyer's Shoppe
description: You can see all the intricate bows he as created and perfected.  The elves take pride in their long history of bowmanship and perhaps make the best bows known to exist.  It has been rumored that the elves also made the magical flame bow, but it was so long ago, no one really  remembers.  There is a famous elven bowyer who lives in the Enchanted Forest.  His name is Llanandar.  He might remember if the story is true.

name: Reclaimation Center
description: As you enter the center, you first notice how clean it is.  It still smells, of course, but no where near as bad as Brownhaven.  As you drop items in the reclaimation center, it returns money, in appreciation of not just dumping your junk in the mountains somewhere.  On the wall you see a sign which says "Thank You For Recycling - Have a Nice Day".

name: Hafnia Circle
description: You are at the most southern end of town.  The road curves back to the north in both directions.  To the north is the business district of the city.  This is the less well-to-do section of Hafnia, but a few artisans keep   their shops here because of the low rent. A sign nearby says "Bowyer."

name: South Hafnia Circle/Rue Caledonia Intersection
description: Rue Caledonia is the street directly north, connecting to Hafnia Boulevard. You seem to notice a lot of activity in this area of town.  On the west side of the street, farther north, you see a caravan assembly lot.  Toward  the south you detect an unpleasant odor, and notice a road sign directing  you to the city's dump.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: The elves are very proud of Hafnia, but they still tell stories of the lost city of Caledonia.  Long ago the elves were driven out of Caledonia by the mountain trolls, and then the dragons took over the city and will not allow them to return.  The road continues to the southeast, and intersects Hafnia Boulevard to the north.

name: The Dragon Arena
description: The elves have captured a number of dragons to fight with in an eventual attempt to learn their techniques and defeat them once and for all.  This is where the real warriors train for their adventures in the Dragon's Lair.

name: Hand-To-Hand Combat Arena
description: Elves often come here to settle disputes between themselves, usually ending in one of their deaths.  Are you sure you want to challenge these people?

name: Elven Training Grounds
description: The Elven Training Grounds is a place to go to practice your skills  against the best warriors.  To the southeast are the hand-to-hand combat areas where elves fight each other (usually to settle disputes). To the southwest are the dragon combat areas.  The elves would like to eventually reclaim their city from the dragons and have managed to cature a number of them to practice their fighting skills on.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: This is the entrance to the Elven Training Grounds.  To the south is the reception area.  The elves use this area to test out weapons, magic and new techniques on easy to hard monsters.    You are invited to practice.

name: Back Alley
description: There is an entry, or exit depending on your point of view, to the west. The south side of the alley seems to be a series of locked doors, but on the north side you see several municipal offices and warehouses.  This alley is not very clean.  You would think the city would be embarrassed.

name: Back Alley
description: The alley is not very clean, but it is wide.  Most of the shops have locked doors on the south side of the alley, but the city maintains a Public Works Department which is located on the north side of this wide alley.  The elves supervise the work of the department, but mostly they hire gnomes to do the dirty work.

name: Small Alley
description: The alley smells of excrement and urine, and you see boxes and barrels have been stacked so as to form temporary shelters for the homeless.  This is not a place the city fathers would want a visitor to see.  Glittering eyes peer at you from under a pile of rags.  All of the doors you see appear locked. Well, that is, all except one.

name: Hafnia Circle Road/Rue Caledonia Intersection
description: This road goes clear around the city.  Immediately to the west is Jacob's Repair Shoppe, where you may have an elven smith work on your weapons and armor.  There is a field behind the shoppe, but you cannot enter it from here.  It seems to be some kind of training grounds.  A lot of people are coming and going further north.

name: Jacob's Repair Shoppe
description: You breathe a sigh of relief as you walk into the repair shop.   You didn't really want to travel all the way back to Brownhaven to fix your broken equipment.  Hopefully the smithy won't break your weapons as often.

name: Small Alley
description: Like almost all alleys, this one is pretty dirty and smells bad.  Be careful where you step.  A lot of the smell seems to come from an open sewer grate in the center of the alley.  A trickle of dirty water disappears down the grate opening into the black depths below.  The alley continues to the north and south, becoming more congested and dirty in the northern direction. Hafnia Boulevard is south.

name: Hafnia Armory
description: This is where you come when you want armor of the best quality.  The elves make the best armor in the world, but it does not come cheap.

name: Hafnia Mountaineer's Supply Store
description: Everything's here that you will need to tackle the wilderness including mountain gear and torches.  The storekeeper peers at you from behind the counter.  Although the elves are very trusting, humans have betrayed them in the past and sometimes still do.

name: Weaponsmith
description: The elven weaponsmith carries only the very best quality weapons.  His prices are a little high, but elven quality cannot be exceeded.  You see a lot of magical and strange weapons adorned on the walls, but (of course) these are not for sale.  If you are looking for a missile weapon, try the bowyer on the south side of town.  All weapons sold here have been enchanted by the resident mage.

name: Hafnia Circle Road/West Gate Avenue Intersection
description: The elves lay out beautiful cities, and Hafnia is no exception.  The road you are on follows a geometrically perfect curve.  A short distance to the north there seems to be an entrance to a combat field of some sort.  The road splits to the west towards the western city gates.  Along the east side of the road there are several shops, and what looks like a social hall for some of the elven elite.

name: West Hafnia Boulevard/Hafnia Circle Road
description: The circle continues to the north and south bringing you around to the other side of the city.  The circle is more or less deserted with the exception of some cheers and noise to the north.  The east/west boulevard will take   you through the center of this beautiful little mountain city.

name: West Hafnia Boulevard
description: You are at the end of the shopping district.  The city starts to calm down as you begin to reach its outskirts.  To the north, you see a weapons shop and to the south, a polearms retailer.  You are curious why such peaceful elves would be selling such deadly weapons.

name: West Hafnia Boulevard
description: More stuff to buy.  The supply store has all sort of useful items for the mountaineer.  To the south is a potions shop.  It doesn't look as fancy as the magic shop in Oceancrest, but the elves are not known for their eccentricity.  The road continues to the east and west.

name: West Hafnia Boulevard
description: The elves of Hafnia are known for their trading.  To the north, you see an armory.  To the south is a tavern for weary travelers to get a cold beer.  For the first time, you look into the sky and notice how clear it is.  Amazing how such a small community could thrive as it does.

name: West Hafnia Boulevard
description: The beautiful mountain city of Hafnia is small, but you must remember it was rebuilt after the war with the dragons and trolls.  Long ago, Hafnia was much larger but most of it was crushed during the wars.  Some say there are still portions of the old city deep underground, and that it may be possible to recover some of the valuables that still be down there.

name: Hafnia Boulevard/Rue Caledonia Intersection
description: This is the central part of the city, and a small park is located in the  center of the intersection.  A statue and park benches are under beautiful lavender trees in flower.  The natives say the trees flower all year long. The elves erected a statue to some of the adventurers from other races who helped them in their time of trouble with the dragons and the cowardly mountain trolls.

name: East Hafnia Boulevard
description: This small city was built by elves.  Over to the west is the popular central park and meeting area.  To the east is the end of the city and the path down the mountain.  To the south you see a postal facility, where   there seems to be some people looking at pictures.

name: East Hafnia Boulevard/Hafnia Circle Intersection
description: A giant arch overhangs the gates of the city.  A majority of the city was created by elves when they fled from the dragons hundreds of years ago.  Since then, humans have wandered in and enjoyed the hospitality the elves have to offer.  Perhaps you can help them reclaim the lost city of Caledonia from the dragons.

name: Hafnia East Gate/Mountain Path
description: There is snow all around you, but you notice that the trail has been well cleared of it.  To the west, you see the massive gates of Hafnia,  a mountain city.  As you approach the gates, you start to see more and  more people.  Some wave to you as they pass by.

name: Plankway to the Widow Maker
description: The dangerous pirates and their trusty sidekicks don't much care for land lovers aboard their ship, and will probably make you walk the plank for coming aboard their ship.  However, pirates are pretty stupid and can probably be bribed to leave you alone.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: Pirates are very civil when they are in a friendly port, but when at  sea, they can be very dangerous.  Of course, most of the facade they put on while in town is really just a farce.  They only come into town when they require supplies or other necessities before going out onto the seas again to attack other ships.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The ship you are on is rather large and can hold roughtly three dozen pirates or so.  Hopefully you won't be able to find out how many are actually still on the ship.  You can see the mast to the north where the crow's nest is, and the aft deck to the south.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: Over the port side of the ship, you can see the magnificent Nylandian Bay.  The large ship is docked in the Nylandian Bay, where her crew is picking up supplies and other needed accessories that they could not  steal at sea.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: To the south, you can see the stairway leading up to the aft deck of  the pirate ship Widow Maker.  The aft deck is where all the steering and command functions are performed, usually by the ship's first officer. The aft deck is always manned, and you are likely to encounter resistance if you go up there.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: To the south is the stairway leading down into the crew's quarters, the mess hall, captain's room and the infamous brig.  The large ship has a complement of over three dozen people.  The area beneath the main deck must be quite large to accomodate that many people.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: To the south, you can see the stairway leading up to the aft deck of the pirate ship Widow Maker.  The aft deck is where the control of the ship is performed, allowing the captain of the ship or his first officer to monitor the path of the voyage and to look for easy prey on the high seas.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The port side of the ship appears to be in good shape.  You are near the center of the ship.  Looking up, you can see the crow's nest hovering high above the deck.  The mast that the crow's nest is attached to is located to the east, toward the starboard.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: At the center of the ship, you can see the masthead where you can try to climb up to the crow's nest.  The crow's nest is the official look- out for the captain and the crew.  However, since the ship is docked in the port, it is unlikely that anyone is up there right now.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The pirate ship Widow Maker is in relatively good condition considering the fact that it's out at sea nearly every day of the year.  The ship is kept up by the various midshipmen and other ensigns that haven't yet proven  themselves to the pirate captain and his officers.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The pirate ship is docked at the Nylandian Bay Harbor while the pirates go in search of food and other provisions.  Of course, while their flag is not waving, no one would know that this ship is in fact a pirate's ship.  The pirates often go in search of other pirates to steal their treasures.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: You are towards the center of the large pirate ship.  The masthead is located to the south.  Looking up, you can see the crow's nest high above the deck, which acts as a lookout for the ship.  Since the ship is docked, it is unlikely that anyone is in the crow's nest.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The pirates are rather restless, but will allow people to wander around their ship so long as they don't go below deck or up to the aft deck. Nevertheless, they still don't much care for people mucking around with their stuff.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The dreaded pirates are hardly a threat to the civilians in Oceancrest, as they put on a facade to prevent themselves from being caught.  There's probably a good stash of stolen goods and objects hidden somewhere below the deck.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: The front of the ship is not unlike any of the other part of the main deck except that you can see where you're going and what's ahead.  Of course, if you really wanted to do that, you should just go up to the crow's nest or up to the aft deck.

name: The Widow Maker Main Deck
description: You are at the very front end of the large pirate ship Widow Maker.  Looking up you can see the crow's nest high above the ship, and the aft deck towards the rear of the ship.  This part of the ship is a bit higher than most of the rest of the main deck, allowing you to see what's going on throughout the ship.

name: The Widow Maker Aft Deck
description: The aft deck is the command center for the powerful pirate ship Widow Maker, and you are likely to encounter more powerful pirates up here than you would down on the main deck.  You can see the pirate captain watching over the people on the main deck to the east.

name: The Widow Maker Aft Deck
description: Most of the time, the pirate captain will be sitting up here, navigating through the treacherous seas, looking for vulnerable ships to attack. No doubt, he is an opponent to be feared.  He is also surrounded by his own personal group of guards which do not really like your presence here.

name: The Widow Maker Aft Deck
description: The large aft deck supports the command center of the ship, and it is very likely that you will encounter much resistance as you walk around this forbidden area.  Even most of the crew is not allowed up onto the aft deck unless there is an emergency.

name: The Widow Maker - Below Deck
description: This is not a good place to be if you get sea sick often.  The continuous rocking of the boat, even in the Nylandian Bay, makes walking tough and keeping your lunch down even tougher.  There is a stairway that leads up to the main deck and the hallway continues to the north.

name: The Widow Maker - Below Deck
description: The hallway continues to the north for quite a distance.  On the port side of the ship are a number of doors leading into small crew cabins.   On the starboard side, there is but a single door, probably leading into the captain's quarters.

name: The Widow Maker - Below Deck
description: Ahead to the north is the galley.  You can smell the cook stiring up something delicious for dinner, but the continuous rocking of the ship under the main deck prevents you from enjoying that sensation.  The  hallway you are in continues to the south from here, past most of the crew cabins.

name: The Widow Maker Galley
description: The aroma from the boiling pots of various foods and soups is quite appealing.  The galley is fairly busy as the cook and his assistance scurry to get dinner ready on time, or the captain will be quite upset.  The last cook was literally thrown off the ship for not having dinner ready on time.

name: The Widow Maker - Crew's Quarters
description: The large crew quarters provides sleeping accomodations for nearly four dozen pirates, who probably don't much care for your invasion of their privacy.  The large crew quarters expands to the north, taking up most of the port side of the ship.  Rows of cots lie on each side of the room.

name: The Widow Maker - Crew's Quarters
description: Seeing how most pirates don't really have that much for themselves in the first place, they probably don't really like you lounging around in their private quarters while they're on duty.  You're likely to find some resistance if you are determined to stay in here.

name: The Widow Maker - Crew's Quarters
description: The large quarters extends to the south, covering most of the port side of the ship.  There are at least two dozen beds on each side of the room housing nearly fifty pirates.  The stench down here is pretty unbearable, but somehow these people manage to go months at sea with only the fish as company.

name: Captain's Personal Quarters
description: Not even the other pirates are allowed into the Captain's Personal Quarters on penalty of death.  It'd probably be a good idea to leave while you can before the captain comes back.  The fancy quarters look nothing like the rest of the ship, decorated with gold, jewels and fancy paintings.

name: Annetol's Cave
description: Annetol is a rather large blue dragon that you didn't think was still alive.  The very old blue dragon is therefore much more powerful than a standard, mature dragon you've seen in museums, but he's also a bit slower.  Annetol has a bad temper, but tends to be cordial to avoid  wasting his energy.

name: Cloudy Alcove
description: Well, it's virtually impossible to see the city below you, but you can make out various landmarks.  The cloudy alcove on top of the castle is guarded by a single cloud giant guard who was unlucky or inexperienced enough to get chosen for this detail.

name: Mondrake's Throne Room
description: The majestic cloud castle cannot compare to the powerful presence of Mondrake sitting at his throne.  The vast throne room extends at least a hundred yards in every direction with Mondrake's giant throne taking up a good fifty square yards.  The cloud giant king looks down upon your puny figures.

name: The Cloud Castle Main Hallway
description: The massive doors ahead of you, to the north, are guarded by a very large cloud giant.  The doors appear to be clouds, but seem solid enough that you couldn't just fly through it.  The cloud giant guard doesn't look like he's having a very good time guarding the door and might decide to attack you just for the fun of it.

name: Cloud Castle Entryway
description: The hallway you are in extends to the east.  The ceiling in the hall is more than twenty meters straight up.  The walls and floor look like they're just clouds, yet seem solid enough that you can stand on them. A massive room lies to the east.

name: Castle in the Clouds
description: The castle is huge to the average person.  The doorway into the castle must be nearly fifty yards high.  If that's any indication of the size of the people living in this castle, you're not so sure it was such a good idea to come here.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: The Skies Above Oceancrest
description: The clear blue skies over the city are magnificent to soar through.  You just hope that your fly spell does not wear off.  With the sky as blue and clear as it is, you're likely to get quite lost if you don't watch where you're flying.

name: Nathan's Cloud
description: You find yourself high above the city of Oceancrest, on top a cloud  where Nathan, the lord of the unicorns rests.  The vast cloud seems solid,, yet you can't help but fell like you're going to fall if you step in the wrong spot.  Nathan sits before you, waiting to hear what it is that you disturb him for.

name: Cloudy Grotto
description: The majestic clouds make for a very peaceful place to relax and enjoy the scenery.  Occassionally, you can see passing pegasi and unicorns flying around, but they seem to be going towards the cloud to the south. There appears to be a green keyhole in one of the clouds shaped similar to a unicorn's horn.

name: Cloudy Grotto
description: The mysterious grotto you find yourself in appears as a huge, fluffy cloud  high above the city.  The cloud-like land appears to be solid, but you better watch out that you don't fall back to the surface.  If humanoids were meant to fly, they would have been given wings.

name: Secret Compartment Under the Fountain
description: This is a nice, quiet area where Caledon comes to work on Oceancrest and other areas of Mordor.  On the walls are very detailed drawings of the vast city of Oceancrest.  The only exit out of here is a small  ladder leading back up into the Fountain.

name: Oceancrest Memorial Fountain
description: The Oceancrest Memorial Fountain was built to commemorate the victory  over the orcs of Kandmanni nearly two centuries ago.  It stands as a proud memorial to those who live in Oceancrest, and is generally  considered to be the center of town, even though it's in the southwest corner of Oceancrest.  There is a circular path around the fountain.

name: Oceancrest Memorial Fountain Path
description: The great fountain to the south looms above you as you enter the circular path.  The fountain has three statues: one of man, elf and dwarf.  The three together show the cooperation between the two  races in their victory over the orcs.  Main Street continues to the north and Eidenhoft Boulevard branches off to the northeast.  The circular path continues to the southeast and southwest.

name: Oceancrest Memorial Fountain Path
description: The fountain to the west is a combination of modern and classical artwork bringing together very lifelike statues with abstract backgrounds.  The fountain is very large and you can occasionally see people with their feet in it.  To the east is Regalia Drive, which takes you directly to the Regalia Convent.  The circular path continues to the northwest and  southwest.

name: Oceancrest Memorial Fountain Path
description: The large fountain to the north is a popular place for people to meet  on a warm summer day.  The adults sit on the edge with their feet in the water while the children play towards the center.  The fountain is kept spotless by the government and is nevertheless constantly being cleaned.  The circular path around the fountain continues to the north- east and northwest.  Main Street continues to the south.

name: Oceancrest Memorial Fountain Path
description: The fountain is one of the first things most visitors to Oceancrest see when they enter the town, if they travel along Main.  This larger-than- life fountain is very inspiring to both young and old alike.  The  circular path continues to the northeast and southeast.  The fountain is to the east, where you can occasionally see young children playing in.  Regalia Drive continues to the west.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street is one of the major roads through Oceancrest.  To the south, you can see the large Oceancrest Memorial Fountain.  Main continues to the north where it intersects with Hillcrest Drive.  To the east, you can make out the large building which houses the Clerical Order of the  Rising Moon.  There doesn't seem to be an entrance on this side of the building, though.

name: Main Street/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: This is a very busy intersection.  Main Street, which continues through to the north and south, is the backbone for most of the commercial  industry in the southwestern corridor of Oceancrest.  Hillcrest  continues to the east and west.  To the east, you can start to make out the large estates which populate the richer sections of town.

name: Main Street
description: Being that Main Street is one of the major roads in Oceancrest, it would not be unnatural not to see a few inns and taverns along the way.  To the west is the Dragon Tooth Inn, a very popular and rather expensive Inn  for the very exclusive upper class.  The entrance to the Inn is off of Hillcrest Drive, to the south.  There is also a large building on the east side of the road which seems to radiate a lot of magical energy.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street continues to the north and south.  To the north, you can see Overland Drive, a smaller access road which runs east to west.   The Dragon Tooth Inn lies to the east, but it's entrance is on the north side of Hillcrest Drive.  On the east side, you see a large  building with an illuminated sign which reads "Chanteclaire Magical Supplies".  There is a door on the building below the sign.

name: Main Street/Overland Drive Intersection
description: Main Street is one of the larger roads running through the southwestern part of Oceancrest.  It continues north as far as the Nylandian Bay.  Overland Drive runs east to west, and is a smaller access road to the large estates to the east.  The estates are in the more exclusive, richer sections of town where snobbery is bred in, and commoners are not welcome, except as help.

name: Main Street
description: You are getting close to Nylandian Bay  you can smell the warm salt water and can hear the sounds of ship horns in the distance.  This section of town also houses the administrative offices of Oceancrest. Directly to the west is the Oceancrest Guard Crime Patrol Headquarters. The city guards on patrol look pretty mean, but they do keep the streets safe for the public.  To the east is the entrance to the Oceancrest  Arena Events and Information Center.

name: Main Street
description: This is a popular shopping district for the citizens of Oceancrest. Small shops and cafes line the street on both sides, providing a variety of goods and services.  The Oceancrest Opera House is on the east side of the street, and immediately to the west is a wedding shop.

name: Main Street
description: A rather nice shop lies in the building to the east of Main Street.   The sign above the door reads "Rosyln's Ornate Wood Carvings".  The entrance to the small shop is decorated in fancy wood totempoles and other strange carvings you're not really familiar with.  To the west is the large City Guard Barracks, which is not necessarily the best place for a criminal to be standing around.

name: Main Street/Rosecrest Street Intersection
description: Main Street continues to the north and south, and intersects Rosecrest Street, which runs east and west.  To the north, you can start to see Nylandian Bay.  The warm ocean breeze is quite refreshing.  Rosecrest  Street leads west towards the administrative buildings and north towards the Oceancrest Main Arena.  South of Main lies the magnificent Oceancrest Memorial Fountain and one of the city's primary shopping districts.

name: Main Street
description: Darby Reynolds builds any size ship for any person with the correct amount of gold.  His ships are said to be works of art  most of them are still sailing the many oceans.  Darby's Shipyard Office is on the west side of Main Street.  Heading North, you can now see the blue- green water of Nylandian Bay.  On the east, there is a shop with a  large banner which reads "Empirial Flags".  The banner is ornately stitched with the finest silks.

name: Main Street
description: The larger portion of Darby Reynold's Shipyard is located to the west of Main Street here.  This large drydock is where most of the ships are constructed.  On the east is an advertising shop owned by Margaret  O'Conner.  The sign above the shop is decorated in ornate silks with the wording "Magnificent Banners".

name: Main Street/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Netherworld Lane is aptly named because it passes just north of the entrance to the Oceancrest Necropolis.  Netherworld Lane spans the width of the City of Oceancrest, from the Bay in the west to the City Walls on the east side. Main Street travels from north to south, and passes through major shopping districts.  From here, the Nylandian Bay is actually northwest.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street reaches Nylandian Bay.  Netherworld Lane, to the south,  marks the beginning of the southwestern district of Oceancrest.  On the west side of Main, a solitary small building rests with a sign which reads "Misty's Travel Services".  The docks are to the north.  You can hear some rowdy noises coming from the building on the east, which  appears to be some sort of pub or tavern.

name: Main Street Corner
description: Main Street turns to the south or east, depending on which direction you're facing at the time.  Directly north are the long docks of Nylandian Bay, although you cannot get there from this spot.  The picturesque, rocky coast provides fishermen with excellent sport and income, but is also a little dangerous.  Several people have mysteriously disappeared while strolling or fishing there.  The Notoriously run Grinning Sailor Pub is southeast.  It seems to be a hangout for sailors returning from long voyages.

name: Main Street
description: A very loud and chaotic noise breaks out from the Grinning Sailor Pub to the south.  The pub appears to be a popular hangout for sailors and their comrades.  Unfortunately, there are also a lot of drunks and other vagrants who pester the incoming patrons for a gold piece or a spot of whiskey.  To the west lies Nylandian Bay.  Main Street continues to the east, heading towards the geographic center of town.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard - Walk of Heroes
description: You are at the famed Walk of Heroes, where Oceancrest's braves fighters, mages and priests are commemorated in large bronze statues.  The statues line Eidenhoft Boulevard on both sides of the road.  To the southwest  is the Oceancrest Memorial Fountain, commemorating those who gave their lives in battle.  To the northeast, you can see Hillcrest Drive.

name: Eidenhoft/Hillcrest/Marina Intersection
description: Three major roads come together at this intersection.  Marina Way runs from the south end of town all the way to Nylandian Bay and into the harbor.  Hillcrest is a long road which travels from the west City Wall to the east City Wall, going through three major sections of town.   Eidenhoft Boulevard is a strange road which leads through most of  Oceancrest's famous monuments.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: To the south of Hillcrest Drive resides the Walk of Heroes monument, which is primarily just a lush, green park with numerous bronze and marble  statues of heroes past and present.  There is a large building on the north side of Hillcrest which seems to glow with a magical aura.   Unfortunately, there's nothing much to distinguish it from this point of view.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street tends to be a very busy avenue where just about anything  may be bought or sold.  Towards the south, you can make out the primary shopping district of southwestern Oceancrest.  To the east, there is a large building labled "Sleeping Deer Real Estate".  To the west of Main, there is a small stable.  There appears to be someone training horses over there.  A small building is located to the south.

name: Main Street/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: Main Street intersects Nagaritha Drive here.  Both roads are fairly large and the intersection of the two results in lots of foot traffic.  Horses are not real common in most of the town, but seem to be present here.   To the south, you can see the primary shopping district in this section of Oceancrest, where just about anything may be traded or bought.

name: Main Street
description: You are in the primary shopping district.  There are sets of buildings both to the east and west of Main Street.  To the west, you can see Varga's Gold and Fine Jewelry Shop.  There is an entrance to the large center in the east to the south.  The shopping district seldom shuts down no matter what time of day it is.

name: Main Street
description: A large shopping complex is located to the east of Main Street.  The  center boasts a repair shop, a fighting academy and other fine imports from throughout the lands.  Main Street continues to the north and south. Heading south leads you towards the town's southern entrance, about a  block away.  Heading north brings you into the center of Oceancrest.

name: Main Street
description: The Main Street shopping centers are known for their exquisite quality goods and services.  There is a large complex to the east which is  accessible from Main Street to the north.  To the west, there is a small building with thick smoke bubbling out from under the door.  A faint sign above the door says "Nevermore Alchemy".

name: Main Street/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Main Street is one of the larger streets in Oceancrest, which will  eventually bring you into the center of town.  To the south, you can make out the City Walls and the Southern Entrance to the city, about a block away.  Waterfront Way travels east to west.  East on Waterfront brings you towards the farmlands and graineries of town.  West on Waterfront leads into more shopping centers and towards the eastern city wall.

name: Main Street
description: There is a large inn to the east of Main Street called "The Golden  Dolphin Inn", which caters to the average traveler travelling between cities.  The modest accomodations and excellent food are well worth the few gold pieces it costs to stay there.  Heading north on Main  brings you towards the shopping districts of town, where just about  anything may be bought or sold.

name: Netherworld Lane/Oceanview Drive Intersection
description: Netherworld Lane heads east from this point and proceeds all the way to the east side of town.  The road gets its name by passing on the north side of the Necropolis, towards the center of town.  Oceanview Drive is a more scenic route with less traffic for those who want to enjoy the many pleasures the city has to offer.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: Darby Reynold's famous shipyard is located east of Oceanview Drive.  This location has been the center of the ship-building industry ever since  ships were introduced to Oceancrest.  To the west is the South Nylandian Bay Guard Station, where marines and other city guards constantly patrol the open seas for pirates and other hooligans unworthy of freedom.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: Darby Reynold's shipbuilding offices are located east of Oceanview Drive. For a considerable sum of money, just about any ship may be custom built for the discriminating customer.  There is a loud, partying-type noise coming from the building to the west.  It appears to be some sort of  cantina, but there's no entrance on this side of the building.

name: Oceanview Drive/Rosecrest Street Intersection
description: The wide and scenic Oceanview Drive continues to the north and south of this intersection, while Rosecrest Street will take you through the business area of the city.  Rosecrest Street changes direction a few times, and along here it takes an east-west route.  It eventually runs north and south again, and in fact it runs past the west side of Lyanden Castle at the northern end.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: Oceanview Drive runs straight through the administrative section of town. At this point, the City Guard Barracks lie to the east and the Oceancrest Detention and Rehabilitation Center lies to the west.  Entrances to both centers are located on Rosecrest Street, which lies to the north.  Ocean- view continues to the north and south, heading towards Nylanden Bay and the commercial districts, respectively.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: There are two large buildings taking up and entire block on both the east and west sides of the road.  On the east side is the city guard barracks and offices.  On the west is the Oceancrest Detention and  Correctional Facility.  There are no doors or other entrances on this side of both of these buildings.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: On the east side of the road is the City Guard Crime Patrol Headquarters, where a number of rough looking guards walk in and out of the building. On the west side of the road is the Oceancrest Detention and Rehabilitation Facility where criminals and other vagrants are "rehabilitated" into useful contributors to society.

name: Oceanview Drive/Overland Drive Intersection
description: You have come to a rather busy intersection.  Each of the four corners of the intersection seem to be quite busy with activity.  On the north- east, there's the Guard Headquarters.  To the northwest is the Prison (or Detention and Rehabilitation Center).  To the southeast is the  Dragon Tooth Inn, one of the more luxurious inns in Oceancrest.  And to the southwest is Dillsdale Memorial Park, which is used for official gatherings and public announcements.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: Dillsdale Memorial Park is located to the west of Oceanview Drive.  This large park is used by the officals of Oceancrest for parties, invitationals, or just public gatherings.  Dillsdale can also be used for making public announcements and other informative uses.  The park is opened to the  public, and reservable for weddings and other religious activities so long as it doesn't interfere with the lawn golf tournaments.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: The Dragon Tooth Inn is located to the east of Oceanview Drive.  This is one of the more luxurious Inns in Oceancrest, and is heavily guarded at all times, for the protection of the guests.  Although crime isn't  a major concern in this part of town, the presense of security guards  makes the customer's stays more relaxing.  Royalty also stays here.

name: Oceanview Drive/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Oceanview Drive is a rather scenic route used primarily by visitors to Oceancrest to get out of the crowded Main Street.  It runs from the Nylandian Bay to the south wall and southern shopping district.  Hillcrest is another large road which provides primary access to most of the  large estates located to the east in the fairly well-off sections of Oceancrest.  The Dragon Tooth Inn is north of here.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: To the east, you can see the impressive Temple of the Rising Moon, run by a clerical order which is dedicated to the balance of lunar power.  Since the moon often symbolizes the hunt, many hunters come here before they leave the city.  They seek the blessing of the goddess who resides in the temple.  To the west is the famous Oceancrest Ministry of Knowledge.  This is the site of the main Library and reference desk for nearly any researchable subject. Of course, not just anyone can enter the Ministry.  It is a restricted to only the wisest of scholars.  You probably don't qualify.

name: Oceanview Drive/Regalia Drive Intersection
description: Oceanview Drive is a fairly scenic route which is a pleasant detour from the hectic, busy roads like Main and Rosecrest.  It travels north to south, ending in the north at Nylandian Bay and in the south at the City Walls.  Regalia Drive is a short street which runs west through the Fountain and ends at the Regalia Convent, which acts as both a nunnary and a school  for wayward women.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: To the east is the magnificent Shrine of the Protectors.  Although there is no particular clerical order which oversees the shrine, it is maintained at public expense for all the citizens of Oceancrest.  They may come to pray or ask for protection from whatever god they happen to belive in.  It all comes out the same, right?  To the west is the Oceancrest Public Amphitheatre, a place where bard and minstrels entertain.  The entrance is located on either Regalia Drive or Nagaritha Drive.

name: Oceanview/Eidenhoft/Nagaritha Intersection
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard runs awkwardly from northeast to southwest.  The road eventually turns northward and ends up at Lithium Inlet.  Oceanview Drive is a scenic alternative to the always busy and crowded Main Street. It runs parallel to Main Street for almost its entire distance.  Nagaritha Drive runs east to west and borders both the large estates and the vast farmlands in the east.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: To the north is the intersection of Oceanview Drive, Nagaritha Drive and Eidenhoft Boulevard.  The intersection is extremely busy but most people don't stop to talk there.  To the east is a fairly new shopping complex. By contrast, the sign above the shop on this side of the road is pretty old and faded.  It reads, "Bysantal's General Goods and Services."

name: Oceanview Drive
description: You are in the primary shopping district for the southwestern portion of Oceancrest.  It is not the largest shopping district, but by far the most exclusive and expensive.  The shops here cater to the discriminating shopper, not to the bums on the street.  To the west, there is a large building.  One of the signs on the door reads "Batton Locks & Picks". There is another door on both the east and west sides of the street to the south.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: On the west side of the street there is a large wooden sign with a painting of ferocious red dragon on it.  Inscripted upon it is, "Dragonwares."  Now what do you suppose that could be?  Across the street, on the east side, is another shop called, "The Angry Camper Hunting Supplies."  Further to the south, about a block away, is the City's Southern Wall.

name: Oceanview Drive/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: This somewhat modest-sized intersection appears to be the hub of a southern shopping district, with very busy shopping centers on all four corners. The ancient foundry to the southeast can only be entered from Main Street, but there are entrances to the other shops on Oceanview Drive.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: The City Walls lie approximately a block to the south at Golden Dolphin Way.  On the east side of Oceanview is Leonardo's Foundry.  The only entrance to the foundry is located on Main Street, which runs parallel to Oceancrest, one block to the east.  On the west side, there is a small gem shop entitled "Eye of the Dragon Fine Gemstones".  The entrance appears to be on the south side of Waterfront Way.

name: Oceanview Drive
description: The most imposing thing to see here is the back of Leonardo's Foundry.  The entrance one block west of here, on Main Street.  On the west side of the street is a building with a plaque over the door which seems to be in elven script and reads, "Denise's Imported Elven Silks."  Oceancrest is one of the major trading stops of the cities located in the Land of Mordor, and often gets many non-human items as part of the bartering and trading that goes on.

name: Oceanview Drive/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Oceanview Drive meets Golden Dolphin Way at this intersection.  South of the intersection is the massive City Wall which protects the citizens of Oceancrest from the ever-present threat of attack by orcs, pirates and other unfriendly enemies.  Golden Dolphin Way runs east to west along the side of the City Wall.

name: Main Street
description: The Southern Entrance to Oceancrest is just south of Golden Dolphin Way. Although security is fairly lax, not just anyone may enter the city  without the proper papers in order.  Leaving the city is just as  important, as without the proper papers, you may not be able to get back in.  On the east, there is a rowdy-looking tavern called "The Rusty Nail Saloon", which appears to be filled with drunk travelers having a drink before continuing on the road.  To the west is a large center known as Leonardo's Foundry, where metals may be converted to useful weapons and armor for sale.

name: Main Street/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection - South Gate
description: You are at one of the primary entrances to the town.  In fact, its only one of four basic ways into town, not including scaling the City Walls.  The City Walls are constantly patrolled by guards.  Golden Dolphin travels  along the southern wall of the city going east to west.  Main Street heads into the center of town, and more immediately, the main shopping districts of Oceancrest, south of Nylandian Bay.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: To the south of Eidenhoft Boulevard is a large stable.  You can see a  number of horses running around with a few trainers.  There is a building on the south side of the lot, off of Nagaritha Drive.  On the north  side of the road is the Shrine of the Protectors, a monument which  is said to protect the town against invaders both by land and sea.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Shrine of Protectors, located north of Eidenhoft Boulevard, is more of a monument to the gods.  Fighters leaving for battle often leave a small sacrifice on the alters to appease the gods and to give them some added strength.  The Shrine is not guided by a group of clerics or  priests, but is upkept by those who pray and leave sacrifices there. The intersection of Oceancrest Drive and Nagaritha Drive is southwest of here.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard was named after Edmund Eidenhoft, the premire  architech who designed most of Oceancrest.  The road runs diagonally through the southern portion of town as to provide a very quick path from the southwest corner to the Arena and other notable buildings  towards the center of town.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard cuts through a large city block.  On the south side of the road, there are three shops: Batton Locks & Picks, Dragonwares  and Leomund's Water Purification.  The entrances to these shops is  probably on Oceancrest Drive or Waterfront Way, but there might be a rear entrance to some of these buildings here.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: Directly to the south, you see Leomund's Water Purification shop.  Of course, all Leomund does is take the water from the river and boil it to get rid of all the bacteria.  He does pretty good business because  either people are too lazy to do it themselves or too stupid.  There is a small building to the west with a sign that reads "Silk Dreams" and a rather large bouncer guarding the door.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: Because of Eidenhoft Boulevard's diagonal nature, small portions of the city block became unusable, notably the sections directly to the south and east of here.  To make the area more aesthetically pleasing, the  slivers of land were converted to small parks.  There is a large  intersection to the southwest where three roads come together.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest Street takes a turn either towards the southwest or the northeast, depending on your orientation.  Going south it travels parallel to the City Wall, which protects the city from the coastline of the Respitial Sea.  To the southeast is an impressive building that was built in memory of one of  early peacekeepers in the city.  The building is dedicated to Sir Millwood of Uxtiva, and is now the residence of the present Mayor.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Millwood Memorial Mayor's Office is the seat of power for most of the domestic affairs with regards to the city.  Of course, Lyanden Castle  is the real center of power for the City of Oceancrest, but the mayor's job is to keep the peace and provide for domestic tranquility.  Rosecrest Street takes a turn towards the northeast as it approaches Nylandian Bay.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Ministry of Order is charged by the crown with the responsibility of maintaining peace in the city.  They have the largest taxpayer supported budget of all the ministries.  Actually, to call it a Ministry of Order is sort of an oxymoron.  It's more like a maze of beauracracy.  The Ministry is in charge of the Oceancrest Detention and Rehabilitation Facility, and most people know that once you enter there, even if you are just visiting, you will probably never be seen again.  The rule is that any paper inside there must be signed in triplicate by four different department heads before it is valid.  Most papers also require the signature of the Mayor, but he has been dead for three years now.

name: Rosecrest Street/Overland Drive Intersection
description: Rosecrest Street is parallel to the great City Wall on the west.  The waters of Nylandian Bay are on the other side of the wall, and before the wall was built the sea would often swell up and flood the city, destroying everything in its path.  Overland Drive heads east from this point, and connects the commercial and administrative areas located in this area to the estates of the rich and powerful farther east.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Ministry of Truth is hardly what it appears to be, but the people in it honestly believe that what they say is in fact true and that therefore everyone else in the world must be lying.  Although the premise no doubt  was originally good, the corrupt nature of the job managed to destroy their integrity.  Nevertheless, many citizens believe them to be the wisest people in Oceancrest.  Rosecrest Street continues parallel to the City Walls,  running north and south.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The monumental building on the east side of the street is known throughout the city as the Oceancrest Ministry of Truth.  The ministry verifies every fact it can, and tries to define life and death in a philosophic sense.
