Unfortunately, no one in the Ministry of Truth can figure out what their compatriots are talking about, and as a consequence they have decided that all things are both true and false at the same time.  The result of this is that the Ministry of Truth is considering opening a Ministry of Untruth to balance the philosphy they seek to impose on the citizens.

name: Rosecrest Street/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Hillcrest Drive runs east of here towards the large family estates, and past the numerous monuments and fountains dedicated to the people who are brave enough to stand up to tyranny and oppression.  Rosecrest Street runs north and south, parallel to the City Wall on the west side of the street.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest runs from north to south at this point in the city, and passes by the famous Oceancrest Ministry of Knowledge.  Although not quite the same as the Ministry of Truth, the Ministry of Knowledge is much more interested in preserving documents and records then it is in arguing about the meaning of life or the purpose of the universe.  The Ministry is very secretive, and access is restricted to only the few who know the correct protocol.

name: Rosecrest Street/Regalia Drive Intersection
description: Regalia Drive runs east to the Memorial Fountain, and eventually ends at the Regalia Convent.  The convent is one of the few remaining institutions just for women.  Rosecrest continues to the north and south, parallel to the City Wall on the west.  Guards patrol the top of the wall in a regular pattern.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The large City Walls on the west of Rosecrest Street are a constant  reminder of the engineering technological superiority of the city.  No other city boasts such a wall, nor such an elite security force.  On the east of Rosecrest is the lawn section of the Oceancrest Public Amphitheatre, where visiting bards and minstrels will entertain the people, usually around dusk, and hoping for a few pieces of gold.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Oceancrest Amphitheatre is more like a large gathering party that occurs daily around dusk.  The minstrels and bards entertain the people while they talk and eat dinner after a long day's work.  Occasionally, the administration will sponser concerts or other orchestral plays and musicals to increase their waning revenues.

name: Rosecrest Street/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: Nagaritha Drive runs east from Rosecrest Street, and continues east to the City Wall.  It is one of the longest roads in Oceancrest.  Rosecrest Street is perhaps the longest street, though.  It runs from the most southern part of the city to the north City Wall.  It changes direction several times.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Nagaritha Drive is directly to the north of this point.  To the east, you can see a large banner which reads "Dangerous Destinations: Guide to the Universe."  The entrance appears to be around the corner off of Nagaritha Drive.  There seems to be a bit of a ruckus towards the south.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: In mysterious glowing letters, the words "Silk Dreams" lights up the sky and the building to the east.  There appears to be a lot of activity in the building, but it looks like access is pretty restrictive.  There is a burly bouncer at the door into the building that doesn't look like he's having that good of a time watching people walk by.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The large intersection to the south brings together three main roads in Oceancrest: Rosecrest Street, Eidenhoft Boulevard and Waterfront Way. You can see Eidenhoft Boulevard to the east as it is running northeast from the intersection, creating a small sliver of a park between the two roads.  There is quite a bit of laughter and screaming to the north.

name: Rosecrest/Eidenhoft/Waterfront Intersection
description: This intersection brings together Rosecrest Street, which runs parallel to the City Wall on the west, Eidenhoft Boulevard, which runs northeast from here towards the Memorial Fountain and the center of town, and Waterfront Way, a more rural path which heads towards the farms and  grainery after it passes the shopping centers to the east.  This intersection is not quite as busy as others because it runs along the west City Wall.  It is however patroled regularly by the city guards.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: To the north, you can see the intersection of Eidenhoft and Waterfront Way to Rosecrest Street.  Although it is not a "major" intersection, it does seem to be adequately busy for this time of day.  On the west is, of course, the large City Wall.  On the east, you see large building which appears to house a number of small shops.  The one on the east  side of Rosecrest appears to be a supply shop.  The storefronts are facing Waterfront Way and are inaccessable from here.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: You are near the southwestern corner of the city, which is marked by the Southwest Observational Station, located south of Golden Dolphin Way.  On the east, you can see a small store with a plaque which  reads "Dryfus' Elephant Leather Works."  Elephant leather is one of the strongest forms of leather available, but also very heavy.  It tends to be more comfortable for thieves and assassins than metallic armors. Although mages may use elephant leather, it tends to be very heavy and uncomfortable for these people.

name: Rosecrest Street/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Rosecrest Street and Golden Dolphin Way break off in their own directions, north and east, respectively, meeting here at the southwestern corner of Oceancrest.  To protect the citizens, a large observational station has been placed to the south which connects the Southern and Western City Walls, and provides an adequate early warning system for incoming intruders.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: Golden Dolphin Way runs parallel to the Southern City Wall for almost the entire span of the city.  On the north side of the road, you can see some buildings in a shopping complex.  Directly to the north, there is an elephant leather shop.  The entrance to the shop is located on Rosecrest Street to the west.  There are two more shops to the east.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: You are at the center of this city block between Rosecrest Street and Oceanview Drive.  On the north, you can see three buildings in a small shopping complex.  Directly to the north is the Silver Tears Gambling Hall.  Security appears to be pretty lax around the small building, so it's unlikely that there's any serious gambling going on.  It seems to be a small-time operation for amusement during lunch or dinner.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The small shopping complex to the north appears to have three buildings along the south end of the block.  Directly to the north, you can see Denise's Imported Elven Silks shop.  Elven materials are not all that uncommon in Oceancrest as one of the largest trading partners provides services throughout the lands, even deep into elven territory.  It's too    that the high costs of importing elven material is passed on to the public.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The large City Wall is a constant reminder of the threat that exists outside the protective wall surrounding Oceancrest.  The entrance to the city is located to the east at the Main Street Intersection.   You can look up the ten meter walls and see the guards walking by  approximately once every minute or so.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: On the north side of Golden Dolphin Way, Leonardo's Foundry greets the incoming visitors to Oceancrest.  The foundry caters to specialized  metals and alloys, however, this service is not without a cost.  Most of the prized metals, such as adamantine and mithril, are very rare and also very expensive.  The entrance to the foundry is located off  of Main Street, to the east.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The large city walls seem to dwarf you in size, especially if you are a dwarf.  They rise nearly twenty feet high at some points, especially on the south side.  The Southern Entrance to the city is located to the west of here off of Main Street.  Although leaving the city is easy, it isn't always as simple to get back in.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Golden Dolphin Inn was named after the road and caters to the average crusader tracking their way across the wilderness.  There are stables to the east of here just past the Hafnia Way intersection.  There is a small Saloon called the Rusty Nail off of Main Street in the same block which provides a fairly laid-back atmosphere to drink and socialize without the hassle of being in the "in" crowd.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Golden Dolphin Inn is directly to the north.  You can see through  some of the windows to see that it is a modestly priced inn with just moderate quality service.  Although well kept, it lacks some of the glitter and money that some of the other, fancier inns have, such as the Dragon's Tooth Inn.

name: Golden Dolphin Way/Hafnia Way Intersection
description: hafnia Way is a short road which connects Golden Dolphin Way and Nagaritha Drive to the north.  Hafnia Way passes between the Golden Dolphin Inn on the west and a great caravan embarkment area on the east.  Oceancrest supplies many of the surrounding cities with grain and products made by the craftsmen in the city.  Caravans are put together here, and depart when enough travelers feel safe to venture into the outside world.

name: Hafnia Way
description: A short way to the north, on the east side of Hania Way, is a large vacant area that was once part of the DeNail corn field, but is now used by merchants to assemble caravans to take supplies out of the city.  A camel lot creates quite a smell.  There are a number of brightly colored tents there, with banners snapping in the breeze.

name: Hafnia Way
description: The Golden Dolphin Inn is located to the west.  However, the entrance to the Inn is located on Golden Dolphin Way, which is south of here.  From what you can see, it is a very large inn, and seems to cater to visitors from outisde the city.  Directly east are the visitors stables for those who traveled by horse, and to the northeast is the city's caravan assembly lot.  There seems to be a rather large group of people there, and camels and horses appear to be heavily packed.

name: Hafnia Way/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Waterfront Way runs east to west, taking people from the western gates surrounding the city, through the farmlands and orchards a couple blocks to the east, all the way to the other side of town.  Hafnia Way connects Golden Dolphin Way and Nagaritha Way in order to alleviate some of the traffic congestion on Main Street.

name: Hafnia Way
description: Several large and colorful tents are to the east, and bright banners, flags and pennants fly above them.  There are a couple hundred people there, and many camels and horses.  The Oceancrest merchants are putting together a caravan to take supplies to surrounding cities.  They hope to return with a handsome profit, and perhaps some exotic goods they can sell here for  even more gold.  They're a greedy bunch.

name: Hafnia Way
description: There is a large shopping complex to the west called Waterfron Plaza.  The plaza boasts an elven leather shop, a repair shop, and various other shops featuring imports from around the world.  Directly to the east is a large field that belongs to the DeNail family, but has often been used as a camp for the assembly of caravans to leave the city.  The shops are usually the first to buy the goods arriving from far off places.   There is also a fighting academy in the Waterfront Plaza to the west.

name: Hafnia Way
description: Hafnia Way is a short road between Nagaritha Drive and Golden Dolphin Way. On the west side of this short street is the Marina Plaza shopping center. The entrance to this center is located to the south.  The plaza boasts shops selling various leather goods, a repair shop, a training arena and other fine imports.  On the east is the the DeNail Corn Field.

name: Nagaritha Drive/Hafnia Way Intersection
description: Hafnia Way runs south from here, connecting Nagaritha Drive to Golden Dolphin Way.  This short road runs past the Marina Plaza shopping center and the Golden Dolphin Inn.  Nagaritha Drive continues to the east and west.  To the north is the Regalia Convent.  The entrance to the convent is located off of Marina Way, west of here.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Nagaritha Drive continues east and west through most of the town.  To the east, Nagaritha passes the various orchards and farmlands encompassed by the Oceancrest walls, to ensure adequate grain during times of war.  On the north is the Regalia Convent, a large building dedicated to mono- theistic research.  The entrance to the building is to the west off of Marina Way.

name: Nagaritha Drive/Marina Way Intersection
description: Marina Way starts off to the north from here and heads towards the  center of town.  Nagaritha Drive runs east to west, bringing you  across the entire town from City Wall to City Wall.  There is a large shopping plaza to the south, but the entrance to the center appears to be on a different street.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: This small section of road connects Main Street with Marina Way, both running north to south.  Directly to the north is the Sleeping Deer Real Estate Office, where many people go to purchase land for development in Oceancrest.  There are quite a few places that are still under construction, even in a town as old as Oceancrest.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Nagaritha Drive provides town access to the larger estates in the richest portions of town, to the east.  On the north side of the road is Natasha's Arabian Horses, and a small stable.  It looks like you can buy and have horses trained here.  On the south side of the road, a small shop called Varga's Gold and Fine Jewelry does business.  The entrance to the shop is located on Main Street.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Natasha's stables are located in the sliver of land created by the strangely shaped Eidenhoft Boulevard, which runs northeast to southwest. South of Nagaritha Drive is a small shop.  The sign above the door reads "Bysantal's General Goods and Services" in proud, bold lettering. Oceanview Drive is just west of here.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: To the north of Nagaritha Drive, you can see the Oceancrest Public  Amphitheatre.  There are two stages that you can see, but they can combine into one when a really large event takes place.  Around dusk, most of the people come out from their day jobs and have dinner there among friends while being entertained by travelling minstrels and  bards.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Amphitheatre entrance lies to the north of Nagaritha Drive.  It is composed primarily of grass, with a little bit of boxed seating towards the front of the theater near the stage.  As dusk approaches, more and  more people begin to arrive.  There is a large building on the south side of the road which has a sign that reads "Dangerous Destinations: Guide to the Universe".  The entrance to this building appears to be to the  west.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The large Amphitheatre extends for the entire city block, and provides enough access so that no one in the city is ever really denied entrance to the public location.  On the south side of Nagaritha Drive is a large door which sports the words "Dangerous Destinations" above it in bright red letters.  A small plaque beside the door says "Guide to the Universe".

name: Waterfront Way
description: Since Eidenhoft Boulevard runs northeast from the intersection to the  west, a small wedge is created between the two roads, which has been carefully decorated with trees and shrubs.  To the south of Waterfront Way, there is a large building with three shops.  Directly to the south is a door with a sign which reads "Treasure Cove Exotic Supplies" in sparkling green letters.

name: Waterfront Way
description: There are two shopping centers on both the north and south sides of the road.  On the south side of the road is a large building with three shops in it.  Directly to the south is a door entrance to "Richard's Rare  Herbs".  A distinct yet unknown odor seems to radiate from the shop. On the north side of the road is a sign which reads "Leomund's Water Purification" next to a rounded door.  Water purification is a useful idea, but can more easily be accomplished by boiling the water.  But as they say, there's a sucker born every minute.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The large building on the south houses three small shops.  The door on the south reads "Eye of the Dragon Fine Gems" in glittering platinum. There are two more doors to the west along Waterfront Way.  On the north side of the road is another building.  A large golden sign with a mean looking red dragon appears to say "DRAGONWARES".  The massive metal door to the north is an entrance into this strange shop.

name: Waterfront Way
description: Waterfront Way runs through the southwestern shopping district, which is one of the larger areas dedicated to commerce.  Most of the items for  sale here are very rare and expensive, compared to other places in  Oceancrest.  To the north are two large buildings which run parallel to Oceanview Drive and Main Street respectively.  The one directly north of here appears to be a hunting supplies store.

name: Waterfront Way
description: On the north, you can make out an alchemy shop which appears to be venting some blue smoke from its roof.  Another entrance is on   Main Street, which is just east of here.  On the south, you can see portions of Leonardo's Foundry, where nearly any metal can be melded into swords, armors, shields and anything else you can possibly think of.  The entrance to the Foundry is also on Main Street.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The entrance to the city of Oceancrest is located south of Main Street, which is just south of here.  Being so close to the entrance, the Golden Dolphin does pretty good business as an inn.  Stables for customers  traveling on horseback are provided a block to the east of the Inn. On the north side of the road, there is Michael's Repair Shop, where just about anything may be fixed up for a price.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The entrance to the Golden Dolphin Inn is to the south from here.  There is a small saloon on the southwestern corner of this block that appears to be fairly relaxed and easy-going.  To the north is Waterfront Plaza, where you can have weapons repaired and buy all sorts of interesting items from friendly merchants.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The intersection with Hafnia Way lies to the east of here.  There is a long stretch of road between here and the next section of town, as you must pass through the various agricultural fields to the east.  The Golden Dolphin Inn lies to the South and Waterfront Plaza is located to the north.  You cannot enter the plaza from here, though.  Entrances are on Main and Hafnia.

name: Marina Way
description: Nagaritha Drive is directly to the south of here.  On the east, you can see the Regalia Convent, a large estate dedicated to the blasphemous  monotheistic philosophy.  The only reason it even exists in Oceancrest is because a wealthy resident wanted more diversity in the area of religion and dedicated this building for its study.  There are large oak doors on the east which lead into the Convent.

name: Marina Way/Regalia Drive Intersection
description: Regalia Way runs west from here towards the Oceancrest Memorial Fountain and eventually reaches the western City Wall.  Marina Way runs north to south.  The Regalia Convent is located to the east of Marina Way.  It is a strange religious order as the nuns and priestesses strongly  believe in a monotheistic philosophy, thus are often shunned by other religious orders.  The entrances to the Convent are located to the north and south of here.

name: Regalia Drive
description: This short road connects you with Marina Way to the east.  Just past Marina Way is the Regalia Convent, a nunnary and school for women only.  The Regalia Convent was formed by a grant by one of the large  estate owners, but does not really follow any major religon.  Instead, they strongly belive in a monotheistic philosophy, which is considered hypocritical to most of the other religious orders in Oceancrest.

name: Marina Way
description: To the east, you can see the great Regalia Convent.  Although most of  their teachings are considered blasphemous, many scholars and other thinking persons find some amusement in their existance.  The entrance to the Convent is located to the east.  The Convent caters exclusively to women and teaches a monotheistic philosophy.

name: Marina Way
description: Marina Way is often considered a back road through some of the central shops in town.  The reason being that almost all deliveries are made from this side of the buildings.  The main entrances to most of the buildings is off of Main Street, one block to the west.  To the west, you can see a large, mysterious looking building which seems to  radiate a blue-green smoke.

name: Marina Way
description: Ironically, the Davis Brothers Mortuary is situated just south of the Oceancrest Central Arena and Gaming Facility.  After the combat, the deceased are brought here to be prepared for burial or cremation.  The arena may be entered north of Overland Drive in the next city block. A large building to the west seems to glow with an unusual blue-green haze, which continues to puzzle you.

name: Marina Way/Overland Drive Intersection
description: Marina Way runs north to south through most of town, and acts primarily as a delivery route for most of the shops to the west.  The main entrance to these shops is located off of Main Street.  Overland Drive heads  through the large estates of the wealthy Oceancrestillians to the east. It also heads west towards the administrative sections of the town.

name: Marina Way
description: The Oceancrest Central Arena is notorious for its lack of compassion when it comes to duels and brawls.  Most contestants join to have the chance to fight with some of the great gladiators of all time, but also end up dying soon thereafter.  The Arena offers many levels of difficulty from sheer brute strength to wisdom and skill in outmanuvering your opponent. it is definately not for the weak of heart.  The Arena entrance is  located to the north.

name: Marina Way
description: Directly to the east is the entrance to the Oceancrest Central Arena and Gaming Complex.  Anyone may enter the complex, but it is highly unadvised for those of the weak of heart.  Not just anyone survives...only the  strongest and braves can challenge the terrors of the Arena.  The city, however, is always looking for a few brave gladiators to fight for the pleasure and entertainment of the public.

name: Marina Way
description: The Oceancrest Central Arena is located to the east.  You can hear loud shouts of encouragement from inside the thick stone walls.  Unfortunately, you don't know if the cheers are for the competitors or the gladiators. The entrance to the Arena is located to the south.  It is advised that you visit the Arena Events and Information Center off of Main Street and Overland Drive before visiting the Arena itself.

name: Marina Way/Rosecrest Street Intersection
description: Marina Way is a popular street which runs north and south.  South of here the street runs past the entrance of the Oceancrest Central Arena, where many fantastic battles have been fought for glory and the entertainment of the populace.  On the northeast corner of the intersection is a strange building which has a great gem atop it.  The gem radiates a purplish hue. Rosecrest Street runs east and west here.  The City Wall is to the west.

name: Marina Way
description: Marina Way continues to the north and south, traveling though the  central parts of Oceancrest.  There is a large building to the east with a large, sparkling gem positioned above the building, casting a purplish hue over the building and some of the nearby streets.  Rosecrest Street is directly to the south.

name: Marina Way
description: There is a large building to the east which appears to encompass an entire city block.  There is a large, sparkling gem which appears to be hovering over the building.  When radiated with the sun's rays, it gives off a purplish hue which covers the entire building and some of the  street.  Marina Way continues to the north and south.  The Central Arena is to the south, past Rosecrest Street.

name: Marina Way/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Marina Way continues to the north and south, intersecting Netherworld Lane, which runs east and west.  Marina Way heads south towards the Oceancrest Central Arena.  It is advised that if you are going to the arena you should first stop at the Arena Events and Information Center found on Main Street, north of Overland Drive.  You may obtain a map there.  Netherworld Lane runs east towards the Necropolis, where Oceancrest's brave and elite are buried.

name: Marina Way
description: Marina Way continues to the north and south, intersecting Main Street to the north and Netherworld Lane to the south.  On the west side of the road, you can see a large pub called the Grinning Sailor, filled with sailors and other marine personnel.  It looks like it could get pretty rough in there.  On the east side of the road is a small block of shops, accessible from Main Street.

name: Marina Way/Main Street Intersection
description: Main Street runs west towards the Nylandian Bay and east towards the center of the city.  Similarly, Marina Way also heads north towards the center of town, but close to the Nylandian Port.  Going south will bring you near to the Oceancrest Central Arena, where brave combatants battle to the death for the amusement of spectators who can't get enough of the sight of blood.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: This small city block boasts two somewhat large buildings on both the north and south sides.  The entrances to these buildings are located  off of Main Street.  Marina Way serves mostly as a back-road for the delivery of supplies and other accessories to these booming businesses. Marina Way is to the east and Main Street is to the west.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: To the east, you can see the intersection with Main Street.  Main is one of the longer roads in Oceancrest which runs through most of the western side of town.  Netherworld Lane continues east and west from here.  On the south, you can see Reynold's Drydock, where Darby Reynolds and his crew construct ships and other sailing vessels.  The business is pretty lucrative at this time since ship-building is just starting to take its place in society.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Netherworld Lane ends just west of here at Oceanview Drive, just before the South Nylandian Bay Guard Station.  The guard station is positioned near the entrance to Nylandian Bay to prevent pirates and other invasion forces from entering the city.  Netherworld Lane continues east towards the center of town.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest is probably the longest street in Oceancrest and one of the few streets that changes directions.  It starts in the south at the Southwest Oceancrest Observational Station and runs north beside the west City Wall, turns east and west along the south side of Nylandian Bay, then continues north and south again to eventually go past the Lyanden Castle before ending at the northern City Wall.  Right now, you are between Marina Way and Main  Street.  Most building entrances are on Main Street.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: On the north of Rosecrest Street is Darby Reynold's Shipyard, where most of the tall ships that ever sailed out of Nylandian Bay were originally built.  To the south is the Oceancrest Central City Guard Barracks, where the City Guards go to relax after a long day patrolling the city and eating  donuts.  The entrance to the barracks is to the west.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Oceancrest Central City Guard Barracks are located to the south of Rosecrest Street.  The wide entrance itself is guarded by two burly looking guards.  The Barracks are designed to be the recreational area and living quarters for the guards who protect the city from thugs and hooligans.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: To the north of Rosecrest Street is a rowdy-looking bar and grill called the Golden Dragon Cantina.  It looks like a popular hangout for the people who work for a living.  You see many of the people who hold administrative jobs within the city entering and leaving the bar.  Rosecrest Street continues to the east towards Oceanview Drive and west towards the City Wall.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest Street takes a turn towards the southwest as it reaches the City Wall.  Beyond the high City Wall to the west lies the Respitial Sea, which has claimed many ships and sailor's lives throughout the years.  The  Wall not only protects the city from invaders, but also from the Sea God  when he gets angry and sends twenty meter waves crashing on the shore.

name: Overland Drive
description: This narrow city street contains a long line of small shops and stores where you can find a number of exotic items.  To the west is Main Street, where most of the entrances to the shops are located.  East is Marina Way, which  which brings you towards the rear of the stores.  Oceanview Drive continues  to the east and west.

name: Overland Drive
description: The City Guard Crime Patrol Headquarters is located to the north of  Overland Drive.  Two large guards patrol the entrance and you can see a number of city guards leave to patrol the streets.  The guards at the front entrance are looking at you funny as you continue to stare at them.  Main Street is to the east of here.  On the south side of the street is the Dragon Tooth Inn, an exclusive inn for the discriminating visitor.  The entrance is to the west.

name: Overland Drive
description: The City Guard Crime Patrol Headquarters provides security for the entire city.  The Crime Patrol Division is charged with the keeping of domestic tranquility, although they can be called upon to defend the city should the need arise.  The entrance to the headquarters is located to the east. Ocanview Drive is located to the west.  On the south is the entrance to the Dragon Tooth Inn.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive is a scenic road which runs from the West Wall towards the Necropolis to the east.  The Oceancrest Detention and Rehabilitation Center is located to the north and Dillsdale Memorial Park is located to the south.  The Detention Center is more of a maze, as are most administrative institutions.

name: Overland Drive
description: The Administration Complex houses the Oceancrest Detention and Rehabili- tation Center, the Mayor's Office and the Ministry of Order.  All in one city block, this allows the administration to concentrate their  work to a limited area instead of having to be spread out all over the city.  On the south is the Dillsdale Memorial Park and the Ministry of Truth.

name: Overland Drive
description: You can see the West Wall just beyond Rosecrest Street to the west.  On the south side of the road, you can see the Oceancrest Ministry of Truth. The Ministry of Truth spends most of its time verifying that what is true is true and what is false is false.  Unfortunately, what one person thinks as true is seldom what another believes is true, thus everything in  creation is both true and false.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: Hillcrest Drive runs between the Dragon Tooth Inn, a very luxurious inn for the wealthy travelers, on the north, and the Temple of the  Rising Moon, a clerical order of balance, to the south.  The Temple cannot be reached from this side  the entrance is off of Regalia Drive, one block to the south.  The entrance to the Dragon Tooth Inn is  located to the west, and around the corner to the north.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The entrance to the Dragon Tooth Inn is to the north of here.  The small path leads up past a small fountain into the reception area.   There is a very nice bar and other more expensive items to be found in such a lavish establishment.  It is always crawling with city guard  patrols as well as their own security force.  Oceanview Drive is to the west of here.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: You can make out the western City Walls just past Rosecrest Street, to the west.  Rosecrest Street runs parallel to the city wall and evenutally ends up at the Southwestern Observational Station.  To the south of Hillcrest Drive is the Ministry of Knowledge, which is a large library of sorts where information may be found on just about anything or anybody that ever existed in Oceancrest.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: On the north side of Hillcrest Drive is the Ministry of Truth building where everyone in the building insists that everyone else in the building is in fact lying.  In their attempt to figure out what is true, they have stumbled upon the problem that truth is what one makes it out to be, therefore nothing is true, but then again, nothing is false.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: Dillsdale Memorial Park is used primarily by Oceancrest officials to  deliver messages to the people.  The park, located east of the Oceancrest Ministry of Truth, is designed for official gatherings and some public  announcements.  It can also be reserved for weddings and other festive occasions if you have the right connections.

name: Regalia Drive
description: The Oceancrest Memorial Fountain lies directly to the east, and is  visited by most of the visitors to Oceancrest.  On the north side of Regalia Drive is the Temple of the Rising Moon.  The priests of the Rising Moon are dedicated towards balance and harmony.  This order is very druidic.  However, the moon also represents the forest and the hunt, thus many hunters and trackers also visit to gain the priests' blessings. On the south side of the road is the Shrine of the Protectors, which is  more of a monument than a religious shrine.

name: Regalia Drive
description: Regalia Drive intersects Oceanview Drive to the east.  On the south, you can see the stage area of the Oceancrest Public Amphitheatre.  The  Amphitheatre is used by the public for general gatherings, usually after dusk, where people can come to relax and listen to the bards and minstrels play their mandolins.

name: Regalia Drive
description: The entrance to the Amphitheatre is to the south.  The large, grassy hill provides space for thousands of people.  Some benches are set up but most people are content to sit on the grass and discuss the day's events, problems and other worries.  To the north is the Oceancrest Ministry of Knowledge, where the collective knowledge of the town is stored and guarded.

name: Regalia Drive
description: The intersection with Rosecrest Street lies to the west, and the City Walls are just beyond Rosecrest.  To the south is the Oceancrest Public Amphitheatre and to the north is the Oceancrest Ministry of Truth. Both places are usually pretty busy with activity, but usually for the opposite reasons.  The Ministry houses numerous tome of various works  which people enjoy studying, while the Amphitheatre is a venue to get away from the hassles of everyday life.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard is easy to remember because it is one of the few roads in Oceancrest which run diagonally.  Heading southwest, Eidenhoft heads towards the Oceancrest Memorial Fountain and other unique monuments dedicated towards the heroes of the realm.  Further to the northeast, Eidenhoft begins to straighten out and head due north past the Oceancrest Central Arena.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The Davis Brothers Mortuary lies to the west of here.  It is typically where most of the deceased end up when they die, it being one of the few funeral arrangement centers in Oceancrest.  The large villa to the east is the Odgen Family Estate.  The large fountains to the south  are made of finely crafted marble and gold.  Although this is one of the smaller villas in Oceancrest, the Odgen Family is one of the richest.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The intersection of Overland Drive lies to the northeast.  From that intersection, Eidenhoft runs due north.  Eidenhoft Boulevard is one of the easiest streets to remember since it is one of the few that travel diagonally through the town.  Heading southwest down Eidenhoft brings you towards the Oeancrest Memorial Fountain and eventually towards the southwestern corner of Oceancrest.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Overland Drive Intersection
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard takes a turn towards the southwest at this intersection. The turn looks a little odd, considering how well the other streets in the city are laid out, but if it continued to the south it would run into the Ogden Family Villa.  The Ogden family, being one of the richest and most influential in Oceancrest, paid the city to make the road go around their house instead of having to move.  Overland Drive heads east and west, and eventually passes by what most people believe to be a haunted house.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The long stretch of road runs east of the Oceancrest Central Arena, the entrance to which is located just to the north.  The intersection with Overland Drive is located to the south, and the Khelleva Stables are to the east.  You can see the many beautiful riding horses the Khelleva Stables train.  Although most of the horses belong to the  Khelleva Family, some are available for trade or purchase.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The large Oceancrest Central Arena is located to the west of here.  The giant complex is designed to challenge the bravest of warriors in bloody, hand-to-hand combat.  It is rumored that there are even some dragons in here that may be called upon to do battle in the name of entertainment. To the east, you can see the Khelleva Stables, the entrance to which is located off of Khelleva Drive.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The large plaza circle you see to the north is called Khelleva Circle because it connects three major roads which run east directly into the Khelleva Estate.  The large traffic circle was in fact built by the Khelleva Family just as a show of wealth and commitment to the city that they live in.  The Oceancrest Central Arena is located to the west, where you can hear loud cries of both victory and agony.

name: Khelleva Circle
description: Khelleva Circle is named after the Khelleva Family, who in fact built this fine architectural circle.  The traffic circle connects Eidenhoft Boulevard, which runs to the south, Rosecrest Street and Khelleva  Drive.  The circle continues around to the northwest and northeast. There is a large tree in the center of the circle that a number of people have decided to rest under in the warm sun.

name: Khelleva Circle
description: Khelleva Circle continues to the northeast and southeast.  To the west, Rosecrest Street branches off along the north side of the Oceancrest Central Arena.  On the northwest corner, you can see a large building with a single gem apperently hovering over the building.  The gem casts a purple hue over most of the building and some of the adjacent roads.

name: Khelleva Circle
description: Eidenhoft Boulevard continues to the north from Khelleva Circle.  The Circle itself continues to the southeast and southwest. On the western side of the road, you can see a strange building with a large gem hovering about it.  When the sunlight hits the gem, it radiates a vigorous purple hue over the building and its adjacent roads.

name: Khelleva Circle
description: Khelleva Circle continues to the northwest and southwest.  Rosecrest Street branches out from the circle to the northeast and Khelleva  Drive, which runs past the Khelleva Mansion, branches to the southeast. The large circle was built by the Khelleva Family a couple of decades ago to alleviate traffic around their home and also to give some  support to the income-poor city.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: To the east, Rosecrest Street heads into Khelleva Circle, a sort of plaza intersection with Eidenhoft Boulevard.  The Oceancrest Central Arena is located to the south.  Loud cheers come from that direction.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The famous arena is the home of numerous gladiators and fearsome foes who are there to test the skills of brave adventurers.  The entrance to the Central Arena is located off of either Marina Way to the west or Eidenhoft  Boulevard to the east.  There is a strange looking building on the north of  Rosecrest Street with a large gem above it, radiating a purple hue over the building and parts of the street.

name: Overland Drive
description: You can hear the cheers and jeers from the large Oceancrest Central Arena Complex located to the north.  There are main entrances on both Eidenhoft Boulevard and Marina Way.  It is suggested that you first visit the  Arena Events and Information Center before heading into the unknown to an almost certain death.  The Center is located off of Main Street.

name: Overland Drive
description: Ironically, across the street from the Oceancrest Central Arena is the Davis Brothers Mortuary, where all the bodies of those who ended up on the wrong side of the sword in the arena usually end up.  The entrance to the Mortuary is located on either Eidenhoft Boulevard to the east or Marina Way, to the west.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: To the south is the Khelleva Circle, which is a circular traffic path with a large oak tree in its center.  The Circle was designed to alleviate the traffic in this part of the city, and was bui8lt by the Khelleva Family as a memorial to themselves.  West of you is an odd looking building with a huge gem perched on top of it.  No one has ever figured out exactly what it is that holds the gem up there, though.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: On the east, you can see a gray building called "Kaldeas' Mansion of Illusion".  The building is not very tall and seems mysteriously narrow. It's not a very good engineering job on the part of the architech.  There  doesn't appear to be a door on this side of the building.  Over to the west you can see a large building that appears to span the entire city block. There is a large gem hovering about the building, radiating a purple glow as the sunlight hits it.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Netherworld Lane crosses Eidenhoft Boulevard in an east to west direction. The wide street gets its name because it passes on the north side of the Necropolis, an eerie "City for the Dead."  Eidenhoft Boulevard continues to the north and south, bisecting most of the city.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard
description: The long stretch of road travels in a north to south direction, and passes through the central part of the city.  The Marine District is rather a rough part of town, however.  Although the sailors and marines serve the people of Oceancrest, it doesn't necessarily mean they have to like them.  They really don't like it when commoners and landlubbers drop in their private clubs, such as the Golden Dragon Cantina, off of Rosecrest Street.

name: Eidenhoft Boulevard/Main Street Intersection
description: Main Street runs east to west and intersects Eidenhoft Boulevard which is a popular north south throughfare.  There are a lot of little shops along Main Street, and many of them have strange and unfamiliar things on display.   Most merchandise comes from far off lands, brought here by seamen hoping to earn a little gold before wasting it at the pubs.  Over on the southwest corner is a shop called, "Dante's Daggers and Darts."  The entrance is just off of Main Street.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street continues to run east and west.  On the south side of the road are two shops.  The one directly to the south is called, "Dante's Daggers and Darts."  Another shop further to the west is called "Ennia's Venemous Pets."  Along the length of the north side is a great building which houses the Adrilite Museum of Natural History.  The Museum boasts a fantastic magic shop and numerous "living" exhibits.  It's almost as good as Kista's Museum.

name: Main Street
description: On the south side of the road you see a shop filled with snakes and spiders. The sign above the door says, "Ennia's Venemous Pets."  There is a very ugly spider painted on the window.  She really doen't get much business.  On the north side of the road is the Adrilite Museum of Natural History, a place of civic pride for citizens of Oceancrest.  The entrance is on Marina Way.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Netherworld Lane is wide and busy road which gets its name because it passes along the north side of the Necropolis, an infamous "City of the Dead" monument which was built to honor those who have died in battle defending the city.  The Necropolis is about three city blocks wide and contains a number of monuments and statues for the viewing pleasure of the public.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: On the north side of Netherworld Lane, you can see the back side of a small shopping complex.  The entrance to the complex is probably on the other side of the building.  To the south, there is a large building with a moderate-sized gem hovering about it.  When the sun hits the gem, it radiates a brilliant purple glow over the entire building and some of the adjacent streets.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: There is a strangely shaped mansion to the south of Netherworld Lane. A large banner reads "Kaldeas' Mansion of Illusion".  There appears to be an entrance to the east on Netherworld Lane.  On the north side of the road, there is a public storage facility.  On a first-come,  first-served basis, citizens may rent or use some of the storage  locations in the complex.  The entrance to the facility is to the north.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The intersection with Rosecrest Street lies to the east of here.  On the south, you can see a strangely shaped door into Kaldeas' Mansion of Illusion.  What is actually in the Mansion has yet to be determined as it is often different for each person.  It was set up more as a sick  trick by the crafty wizard/illusionist Mardic Kaldeas some years ago to discourage snooping around by curious and bothersome adventurers.

name: Rosecrest Street/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Netherworld Lane continues to the east and west.  About a block to the east, you can start to see the outline of the Necropolis.  Rosecrest  is a strangely shaped road, running north to south.  Taking Rosecrest Street to the north brings you to the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, a moderatly interesting gaming center, similar to the Oceancrest Central Arena, except geared more for one-on-one battle.  The games are not as popular with the people, but just as interesting for the competitors.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Ivanhouse Sporting Facility is located to the north.  There is an entrance to the north labeled "Challenger's Ready Room".  Those  who wish to compete in the Arena may do so by entering this large room to the north.  On the south side of Netherworld Lane is the Khelleva Estate.  This massive estate covers nearly two whole city blocks and has been the home of the Khelleva Family for nearly twenty generations.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The large Khelleva Estate lies to the south of here, surrounded by a  white, picket fence, and constantly guarded by ferocious watch dogs. On the north side of the road is the Ivanhouse Sporting Facility, a smaller version of the Oceancrest Central Arena, speciallizing more  on individual, one-on-one type battles.  Contestants may enter the Facility through the Challenger's Ready Room to the west.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: The intersection of Lankshire Parkway and Netherworld Lane marks the northwestern corner of the great Necropolis.  The entrance to the  Necropolis is located to the east on Netherworld Lane.  There is a  small memorial facility on the southeastern corner called "Nevermore Funeral Services".  The facility has entrances on both Lankshire  Parkway and Netherworld Lane.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Nevermore Funeral Services building is located to the south.  A  number of your comrades have ended up there, as they cater specifically to the heroes of Oceancrest.  On the north, there is a fresh fruit stand where you can buy a variety of freshly, grown fruits and vegetables  from the Bushman Farm.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The large farmland to the north provides much of the fruits and vege- tables to the people of Oceancrest.  Being located next to the Necropolis, there's not much else one can do.  Reginald Bushman makes a good living harvesting the fruits and vegetables in his orchards, and can often use some unskilled labor to rid the garden of unwanted pests.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Necropolis reaches the road at this point.  You can look to the  south through the iron bars which surround the Necropolis and see that you wouldn't really want to be trapped in there at night.  The large trees and statues almost seem to take on a life of their own as light reflects off in different directions.  On the north side of the road is Bushman Farms, an orchard where apples, oranges and other delicious  fruits are grown.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Necropolis Avenue lies to the north, where the Main Entrance to the  Necropolis is located.  You can see smoke rising from some building to the south in the Necropolis.  You can only assume it's the smokestack from the Crematorium, since nothing else should be burning, or giving off that much black smoke.  On the north is Bushman Farms.  Reginald Bushman is always looking for some unskilled labor to help him farm his land.

name: Necropolis Avenue/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Necropolis Avenue runs south directly into the Main Entrance of the  Necropolis, which is probably why it is named that way.  Netherworld Lane continues to the east and west, making the north border of the Necropolis.  The Necropolis is surrounded by iron bars.  The only entrance is to the south.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The entrance to the massive Necropolis lies to the west at the intersection of Netherworld Lane and Necropolis Avenue.  The large Necropolis lies to the south, surrounded by iron gates that keep graverobbers from defiling the gravesites and buildings.  Security is pretty tight so there haven't been too many incidents lately.  The Bushman Plantation is located to the north.  It is also owned by Reginald Bushman and is used to grow soybeans and other comodities.  As usual, he is always looking for some cheap, unskilled labor.

name: Avatar Boulevard/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Avatar Boulevard heads off to the north from here, bringing you to the west side of the Avatar Ruins.  The Avatar Ruins are essentially just a set of boulders where the ancient Avatars used to study and practice to keep in prime mental, physical and spiritual shape.  Netherworld Lane continues to run to the east and west.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Netherworld Lante continues to the east and west from here.  The magnificent Necropolis to the south holds the remains of many great and noble warriors, priests, mages and, of course, the remains of King Lyanden.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: A new building is on the north side of the street, and as you look closer, you see it is a retail store which specializes in coffins.  Several of the  more ornate models are standing just outside the door.  Customers are encouraged pick one out now, while they can enjoy it.

name: Amberton Lane/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Amberton Lane runs north and south through most of the northern section of town.  There is a large plaza to the southeast that appears to deal with weapons and other specialty items.  The entrance to the center is located to the east along Netherworld Lane.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: There is a large center dedicated towards the manufacturing and sales of weapons and other collectables to the south.  It appears that the main entrance to the plaza is to the east along Netherworld Lane.  There is a large, empty field on the north side of the road.  You can see a number of druids and bards enjoying the day on the grass.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Evander's World of Weapons boasts the largest selection of the best weapons money can buy.  There are separate shops for polearms, armors and swords. Evander doesn't really cater to bows and missile weapons because the elves make much better products.  The entrance to the center is located to the south.  Evander also buys used weapons to recycle into new ones.

name: Leviathan Drive/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive runs north and south from one end of town to the other.   Most notably, Leviathan runs on the west side of most of the major parks and natural facilities.  Much of this land was set aside by the town to preserve the natural beauty of the land without giving up the protection of the City Walls.  Netherworld Lane gets its name because it passes along the north side of the eerie Necropolis, located a block to the west.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Amberton Lane, if it continued past Kafkarn Way, forms the eastern boundry of the Necropolis.  Due to some strange magic from the Mages of Keslar, a large hill was pulled out from the earth and severed Amberton Lane into two separate roads.  The Mages of Keslar are  the strongest and most powerful of the creatures in Oceancrest not directly affiliated with the undead.

name: Amberton Lane
description: Amberton Lane intersects Kafkan Way to the south, where the street abrubtly ends.  You can see the large palace on top of an almost artificial looking mountain.  The eerie palace overlooks the Necropolis. On the east side of the road, there is a large shopping complex which appears to specialize in various types of weaponry.  There are no entrances on this side of the road, but you can probably get into the center from Kafkan Way.

name: Amberton Lane/Kafkan Way Intersection
description: Kafkan Way heads off to the east from here, ending at the Necropolis. If the Keslarian Mages didn't create their castle right on this spot, Amberton Lane would continue to the south.  Unfortunately, the mages  did erect their palace on this spot, and Amberton Lane was destroyed. The large, looming castle appears to the southeast, high up a large mountain face.

name: Kafkan Way
description: To the south is an iron gate.  Past that gate, a long, winding path leads up the artificial mountain to a large palace on the top.  The Mages that built the palace, also build the mountain and all the surrounding magical effects.  The Mages of Keslar, as they are commonly known as, are not really evil, but appear to be by the people who do not really understand the use and power of magic.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The large shopping plaza to the north is called Evander's World of  Weapons, where all kinds of weapons can be bought and sold.  The entrance to the center is to the north.  Kafkan Way intersects Leviathan Drive to the east, and continues west until it reaches the Necropolis at Amberton Lane.

name: Leviathan Drive/Kafkan Way Intersection
description: On the southwest corner of this intersection, you can see the large  castle known as Keslar's Palace standing high on the ridge above.  The entrance to the palace consists of a narrow, winding road up the hill on Kafkan Way.  Leviathan Drive continues to the north and south,  intersecting Kafkan Way, running east to west.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Riverdell Tranquility Park is a large city block, set aside primarily for natural preservation purposes.  The large number of trees and shrubs protected by the park makes it an ideal location for rangers of all levels to train in the skills of tracking and searching.  On the west is a large weapons and armor retailer.  Known as Evander's World of Weapons, the  center sells many exotic and rare items.  The center must be entered from either the north or south.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The large center to the west is known as Evander's World of Weapons, where you can purchase any number of finely crafted weapons and armors. Evander boasts the best polearms shop in the lands, and has one of the finest repair shops available.  The plaza may be entered from either Netherworld Lane or Kafkan Way on the north and south, respectively.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: Rosecrest Street breaks off from Khelleva Circle at a diagonal to avoid the Khelleva Estate.  It continues to the northeast and eventually turns north.  To the southwest is Khelleva Circle, a rather nice circular  path which alleviates some of the conjestion that usually occurs when three streets merge together.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: You are now walking along the borders of the Khelleva Estates.  A short picket fence encloses the large land estate of the Khelleva Family.   You can see the large mansion towards the south off of Khelleva Drive. Rosecrest continues to the northeast and southwest, but you can see  that the road turns north up ahead.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The massive estate is extended for more than two city blocks to the south. There is a majestic mansion on the south side of the estate.  From this  vantage point, you can see the estate lies next to Khelleva Drive.  Not surprisingly, Khelleva Drive was built by the family to provide easy  access to the mansion  however, it was never expected to be a large road.

name: Rosecrest Street
description: The Ivanhouse Sporting Facility is located to the east of Rosecrest  Street.  The large facility sports three distinct arenas, where you can challenge your skills versus various opponents of varying strength. The entrance to the facility is located off of Netherworld Lane, to the south, through the Challenger's Ready Room.

name: Rosecrest Street/Main Street Intersection
description: Main Street heads west out of Rosecrest Street, traveling through the central part of the southwestern section of town.  The Ivanhouse  Sporting Facility is located to the east where combatants fight  more evenly-matched gladiators on a one-on-one confrontation to the death.  The entrance to the facility is located off of Netherworld Lane, to the south.

name: Main Street
description: Main Street ends to the east of here at the intersection with Rosecrest Street.  Main travels west and eventually turns south, traveling through the main centers in the southwestern quadrant of town.  On the north side of Main, you can see the Oceancrest Central Recycling Plant and  Reclaimation Center.  On the south is the Eiden Public Storage Facility where various articles may be stored for a fee.

name: Main Street
description: The large Oceancrest Central Recycling Plant and Reclaimation Center, a fancy name for a dump, is used to collect old and used up trash from  all over the city.  There are smaller collection sites around the  city, but they all end up here eventually.  Most of the equipment that finds its way here usually ends up as scrap metal, used to create new weapons at a cheaper cost.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The DeNail Corn Fields are a prime source of income for many of the less able people of Oceancrest.  DeNail is very lenient and lets just about anyone work there if they cannot find other suitable work.  Of course  that means that he doesn't have to pay them very much either.  The entrance to the fields is located off of Hafnia Way, to the west.

name: Nagaritha Drive/Regalia Way Intersection
description: Regalia Way, not to be confused with Regalia Drive, is a small connector road, which cuts through the Regalia Convent towards the Allisk Circle. Regalia Way is not a very popular road, but it is a short cut out of the corn and wheat fields in the southern section of town.  The large corn fields are located on the southern side of the road, protected by a mesh wire fence.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The rolling corn fields on the south side of the road provide food for most of the residents of Oceancrest.  Mr. DeNail owns and operates the large complex, and is always willing to hire on some unskilled labor  to work the fields and scare off the crows and other pests that plague the corn fields.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The corn fields to the south supply the city of Oceancrest with all the corn it needs for both human and animal survival.  The fields cover quite a few acres, and are protected by a tall fence.  On the north there is a barn and a new silo being constructed to supplement the current one, which has already reached capacity.  Oceancrest likes to keep extra food in storage in case of a prolonged attack from outside the city walls.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The DeNail Corn Fields are located to the south of here.  Farmer DeNail is always willing to hire on any unskilled laborers to pick corn and scare away crows and other pests.  The entrance to the Corn Fields is  located off of Lankshire Parkway to the east.  On the north side of the road, you can see the Oceancrest Grannary building, which is currently under construction.  The current grannary has exceeded its capacity, thus a new one is being built to supplement it.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: The intersection of Nagaritha and Lankshire is just north of the Klondike Wheat Fields and the DeNail Corn Fields, both of which may be entered off of Lankshire Parkway to the south.  Nagaritha Drive runs east and west through most of the southern part of town.  Lankshire runs north and  south, eventually passing the Necropolis towards the center of town.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: You can barely see Lankshire Parkway intersecting Nagaritha Drive to the west.  On the south side of the road are the Klondike Wheat Fields.  The management of the fields is always on the lookout for unskilled labor that they can exploit.  The entrance to the fields is located off of Lankshire Parkway.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Of course, walking through the farm lands of Oceancrest isn't all that exciting.  On the south side of the road are the Klondike Wheat Fields, where more wheat is harvested than the mind can comfortably comprehend. On the north side of the road is the Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch and  Slaughterhouse.  More food is provided from this area of town than any other.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch is located on the north side of the road, separated by Appleton Road, which runs diagonally through the ranch.  On this side of the ranch, you can see the Slaughterhouse where scores of cattle are killed each day to provide for the necessities of the city's citizens.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The large wheat fields cover many acres of land on the southern side of Nagaritha Drive.  The large plantation harvests more than enough wheat  and grain to provide for the entire city, and exports the rest to make some much needed capital for the farmers.  The Klondike Wheat Field is always in need of unskilled labor to help with the harvesting and reduce the number of pests infiltrating the wheat.  The entrance to the fields is located off of Lankshire Parkway.

name: Appleton Road/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: This is a rather minor intersection between the farming estates on the south and the cattle ranch on the north.  Appleton Road runs diagonally through the city to the northwest and southeast.  On the southeastern corner of the intersection, there is a small pub between Appleton Road and Overland Drive.  The main entrance to the pub is on Nagaritha Drive.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Thackery's Pub is a run-down little family pub catering mostly to the farm workers who live in the area.  The wine is particularly good, however, since they buy it from the Chateau Richland Winery across the way to the north.  You hear ribald singing coming from the door.

name: Overland Drive/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: Overland drive is one of the longest streets in Oceancrest and has the unique feature of being the road which runs between the Manor of Natasha de Allisk and the mysterious Necropolis.  Nagaritha Drive runs east and west from one end of the city to the other.  On the southwest corner of the intersection is the local favorite, Thackery's Pub.  The main entrance to the pub is on Nagaritha Drive, but there is also an entrance on Overland Drive.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Circle-Bar Butcher is located on the south side of the road, providing meats of various cuts from their ranch to the general public.  On the north side of the road is the Chateau Richland Grape Orchard, where, as one  would guess, grapes are grown and harvested.  The grapes are then pressed and fermented into wine.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Circle-Bar Farm Fresh Prime Meats shop is located on the south corner of the road, where all the fresh meat is sold to consumers.  The butcher shop is ideally located around the various ice and preservative shops so that the meat can be kept relatively edible for long periods of time  without having to worry about bacteria or other nasty diseases.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The large Chateau Richland Grape Orchard provides for nearly all the grapes which go into the production of the various wines and juices that the  Winery makes.  On the south side of the road is the Deep Freeze Storage Facility where cold items may be preserved without worrying about decay or melting.  The facility is maintained using dry ice, a relatively modern approach to cold preservation.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The complex on the south provides much of the meat and grains to the community as well as other essentials to day-to-day survival.  Directly to the south is the Downtown Ice and Water Supply Facility where, obviously, ice and water can be purchased for storage of meats and, of course, a  nice cool glass of iced tea.

name: Leviathan Drive/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive, running north and south, intersects Nagaritha Drive, running east and west, at this point.  The large Melbourne Entertainment Arena is located on the northeast corner of the intersection and may be entered along Nagaritha Drive to the east.  On the southeast corner is the glorious Shrine of Victory, where many warriors go to offer a sacrifice before a battle.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: On the east side of the road, you can see the large Klondike Wheat  Fields, where acres and acres of wheat are harvested.  On the west side of the road are DeNail's Corn Fields, where enough corn is grown to  easily feed all of Oceancrest and many other small cities in the  lands.  The entrance to the fields is to the south off of Lankshire Parkway.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Facing east, you can see the entrance to the Klondike Wheat Fields.  The Klondike Office is always willing to hire unskilled labor to help them harvest their wheat and rid the fields of unwanted pests like rats and other vermin.  On the west side of the road is the entrance to the DeNail Corn Fields.  Farmer DeNail is also always willing to get some unskilled labor into the fields to do some work.  After all, it helps the economy.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway runs between the Klondike Wheat Fields on the east side of the road and the DeNail Corn Fields, on the west side of the road. To the south, you can see Waterfront Way intersecting Lankshire Parkway. Both the corn and wheat fields are more than happy to provide unskilled labor with some temporary jobs, plowing fields and scaring away the vermin that poison their crops.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Waterfront Way, running east and west, intersects Lankshire Parkway, running north and south.  Lankshire Parkway runs from the southern City Wall to just past the Necropolis, located towards the geographic center of town.  Waterfront Way is also a long, busy street running from the east City Wall to the west City Wall without interruption.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large Oceancrest Stables and Walking Yards are located to the west of Lankshire Parkway, where guests and visitors to the town may leave their steeds while visiting.  Horses, although permitted in town, create a hazard to the pedestrians on the road.  Since it's not really safe for either the horse or the people, most just leave them in the stables.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway intersects Golden Dolphin Way ahead to the south.  Golden Dolphin Way marks the southern border of Oceancrest.  You can see the  large City Walls looming in the background.  On the east side of the road are the various Oceancrest silos and grannaries, used to store the unused wheat and corn from the fields for the colder winter months.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Lankshire Parkway runs north from Golden Dolphin Way.  Golden Dolphin Way marks the southern border of the city of Oceancrest.  The large City Walls loom in the background to the south, preventing unwanted people from  entering the city and preventing criminals from leaving.  The city is more or less self-sufficient and does not depend on caravans and other trading for its survival, although smaller cities depend on Oceancrest.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The Nevermore Funeral Services office is located to the east and provides all sorts of services for the recently deceased.  It is conveniently  located on the northwestern corner of the Necropolis to provide easy  access to the burial, cremation and embalming services provided by the Necropolis.  Lankshire Parkway continues to the north and south,  intersecting with Netherland Lane to the north.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Just walking next to the large Necropolis sends shivers down your spine. The large Necropolis must cover nearly ten city blocks and is packed with more dead bodies than the mind can comfortably imagine.  The large metal bars separate the road from the Necropolis to prevent grave robbers and other raving lunatics from defacing the graves and tombs.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large Necropolis appears to continue on forever.  The large, metal bars prevent you from entering the Necropolis from this side of the road. The Main Entrance is located off of Netherworld Lane, to the north.  On the west side of the road, you can see the Khelleva Estate and Mansion. The large Estate is covered with gold and jewels, and is constantly  guarded by a number of highly trained security guards.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: You can see clearly the Khelleva Mansion and Estate to the west.  The Mansion is constructed of marble and concrete, making it a virtual fortress against any attack.  Before Oceancrest was founded and the City Walls built, the Khelleva Mansion was about the only structure  that actually survived attacks against it.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large Oceancrest Necropolis lies on the east side of Lankshire Parkway, surrounded by tall, metal bars preventing looters, grave robbers and other lunatics from entering the facility.  The Main Entrance to the Necropolis is located off of Netherworld Lane to the north.  On the west, you can see the Khelleva Mansion, a powerful monument to the most powerful family in Oceancrest.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway runs south towards the Overland Drive intersection.  On the east side, you can still see tha large Necropolis looming in the  darkness.  On the west, you can see the magnificent Khelleva Mansion. There appears to be no entrance to the Mansion from this road, but you  do see another small road running northwest from the Overland Drive  Intersection.

name: Lankshire Parkway/Overland Drive Intersection
description: Lankshire Parkway continues to the north and south, intersected by  Overland Drive, running east and west.  Overland Drive runs through much of the wealthy residental estates in town.  To the east is the notorious Mansion of Natasha de Allisk.  To the west, you can get to both the  Iilandi Family Estate and the Khelleva Stables.  On the northeast, you can see the corner of the Necropolis.  Lankshire Parkway forms the  western end of the Necropolis.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: The large Iilandi Mansion is located to the west.  The Iilandi Family owns much of the farming properties in Oceancrest, working them up from mere plots of land to the comodity producers that they are today.  On the east side of the road is the Allisk Manor, home of Natasha de Allisk, one of the last known vampires in the lands.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway runs south into the Allisk Circle.  On the east is the famous (or infamous) Manor of Natasha de Allisk, rumored to be the last "real" vampire in Oceancrest.  Although many parties have tried to destroy her, she always seems to come back, much stronger than before.  On the  west is the Iilandi Family Estate.  The Iilandi Family is probably the only family to earn their status as one of the wealthiest families of  Oceancrest, owning and operating both the Richland Grape Orchards and the Klondike Wheat Fields.

name: Allisk Circle
description: Allisk Circle is named after the Countess Natasha de Allisk, or more formally, the Allisk Mansion, which is located to the east of Lankshire  Parkway, just south of the Necropolis.  A corner of the estate is visible from here.  You can see it on the northeast corner, surrouned by wall of metal bars.  The Allisk Circle is about as close as anyone dares to get to the Allisk Manor, but it can be entered from Overland Drive.

name: Allisk Circle
description: You can see the mysterious Allisk Manor on the northeast side of the  circle, surrounded by metal bars.  The Manor is believed to still be haunted by the ghosts of previous owners and even the notorious Countess Natasha de Allisk herself.  Luckily, she hasn't been seen outside of  her mansion so perhaps she has gone into hibernation.  Hillcrest Drive continues off to the east.

name: Allisk Circle
description: You are walking along the western rim of the Allisk Circle.  Oddly, the center of the circle is not very well kept up and is covered with dead grass and wilting weeds.  Hillcrest Drive continues to the west from here.  There is a strange-looking gazebo towards the southwest.  The circle continues to the northeast and southeast.

name: Allisk Circle
description: As you walk around the Allisk Circle, you notice that the center is unlike most of the other "traffic circles" you have encountered.  The center is almost devoid of all life.  It is covered in dead grass and wilting weeds. Regalia Way, not to be confused with Regalia Drive, runs southwest from here.  Lankshire Parkway continues to the south out of the Circle.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: There is a large cattle ranch off to the east, off of Appleton Road. When they reach a certain age, they are herded off to the Slaughter- house, located to the east of this road.  To the north, you can see the Allisk Circle, where Lankshire Parkway, Hillcrest Drive and  Appleton Road intersect.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: There is a small, open-air market to the west where you can purchase a number of small commodities, such as wheat, grain, corn, some  fruits and vegetables, and some meat products.  The large market is run by Maria, who also buys grains and other supplies that might be used elsewhere.

name: Lankshire Parkway
description: Lankshire Parkway intersects Nagaritha Drive to the south.  On the east side of the road, you can see the large Slaughterhouse facility and the various preservation and packaging routines.  The large center provides much of the beef the city needs to survive.  Luckily, Oceancrest is very self-sufficent, and relies little on outside sources for day-to-day needs.

name: Khelleva Road
description: This small road runs southeast from the Khelleva Circle, located to the northwest.  It passes by the Khelleva Mansion and the Khelleva Stables, to the east and south respectively.  This small road was originally constructed to provide easy access to the Khelleva Mansion, but has since turned into a quick short-cut through town.

name: Khelleva Drive
description: Khelleva Drive is a small road which runs through the Khelleva Estate, splitting the great Mansion apart from the Khelleva Stables.  The  mansion can be seen to the east of the road and the stables are located on the south side of the road.  The entrance to both establishments may be found on Khelleva road to the southeast.

name: Khelleva Drive
description: The Main Entrance to the Khelleva Mansion is located to the east.  The large estate is made almost completely of carved marble and concrete, making the Mansion an almost invulnerable fortress.  The large marble statues and other trinkets decorate the entrance hall, almost dwarfing the tallest half-giants.  The stable entrance is located to the south.

name: Khelleva Drive
description: The Khelleva Mansion main entrance is located to the north of here.  The large, marble statues and eloquent art design set the Khelleva Estates  apart from every other city structure in Oceancrest.  The Stables are located to the west and may be entered off of Khelleva Drive further to the northwest.

name: Khelleva Drive
description: The Khelleva Family, the virtual financial founders of the city of  Oceancrest, claimed this land for themselves many decades ago before the city was even planned out.  This road runs straight past their Mansion and the Khelleva Stables.  It runs northwest, eventually  hitting the Khelleva Circle.  To the southeast is the intersection of Lankshire Parkway and Overland Drive.

name: Overland Drive
description: Lankshire Parkway intersects Overland Drive to the east.  On the north side of the road, you can see the Khelleva Stables.  There is a small road running between the Stables and the Khelleva Mansion, which joins the road at the Lankshire intersection.  On the south side of the  road, you can see the Iilandi Family Mansion.

name: Overland Drive
description: The large Iilandi Estate was build only a few decades ago.  The Iilandi Family earned most of its wealth by managing and maintaining the Richland Grape Orchard and the Klondike Wheat Fields, both very prosperous ventures. Both sites produce enough food for most of the town to survive comfortably, and the excess gets exported to other, less well-off cities.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive passes by three of the wealthiest estates in Oceancrest.   You are now approximately at the center of all three.  On the north is the Khelleva Stables, part of the Khelleva Estate.  On the southeast is the Iilandi Family Estate, owners of the Richland Grape Orchard and the Klondike Wheat Fields.
