On the southwest is the Odgen Family Villa.

name: Overland Drive
description: The Khelleva Stables run east for nearly two regular-sized city blocks. You've never seen so many horses in your life.  On the south side of the road is the Odgen Family Villa, a small, but very powerful family who actually runs most of the town.  They say money corrupts, but if you're the one with the money, you won't hear any complaints.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive intersects with Eidenhoft Boulevard to the west.  On the south side of the street, you can see the Odgen Family Villa, where much of the politics of the city are usually decided.  The Odgen Family have their hands in nearly every aspect of the political activity in the city, and they even have some connections with Lyanden Castle.

name: Center of Allisk Circle
description: Apperently, not much was done to keep the center of this circle growing. The only thing which remains is dead grass and a couple of weeds, but  even those are withering.  The Allisk Manor is located on the northeastern corner of the circle, which is where the Circle gets its name.  It is rumored that the Allisk Manor is still haunted by the ghosts of past  owners and even Natasha de Allisk herself.

name: Entrance to the Crypt Caverns
description: The crypt caverns hold the remains of the deceased mages of Keslar.  These 'good' mages were banished with the coming of Kaylar and the crypts were sealed forever.  Some say the ghosts of these mages still haunt the  cavern crypts and will not rest until Keslar is released from evil.

name: The Cavern Crypts
description: The caverns are quite dark and damp.  For centuries, no one has dared to enter this realm of good which has been guarded by evil.  The evil mages of Keslar cannot enter the crypt because of the overwhelming spirit of the ancient mages.

name: Crypt Intersection
description: The crypt does not look very big, but with the number of intersections and dead-end paths, it's very easy to get lost.  The great mages also knew people would try to invade their tomb to retrieve lost artifacts and have made a number of traps to prevent this.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The crypt passage is quite narrow and only allows a couple of people to pass through at any given time.  Along the walls, you can see a number of skeletons, resting silently in their tombs.  The passage continues to the east and southwest.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The narrow passage continues to wind downward.  You appear to be traveling deeper and deeper into the land the further south you go.  The walls are decorated with paintings and other trinkets, but most are fading due to age and are now quite worthless.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The crypt passage intersects another passage heading back towards the surface to the east.  The passage continues to descend to the south- east.  Both passages look very narrow.  It doesn't look like more than a couple of people could squeeze through them at any one time.

name: Secret Crypt Passage
description: The crypt is filled with many secrets.  This passage must be one of them. It leads due west to a large room with a number of bright lights.  At least the room looks well illuminated as your torch is starting to burn out.  It looks like a good place to rest before moving on.

name: Mage Hold
description: This hold was designed to hold many of the artifacts of the ancient mages so that they could be used in the afterlife.  A magical force-field seems to have been raised as you are the only one that can get into this hold.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The crypt passage continues to creep along through the crypt.  There's not a lot of activity here despite the large number of rats you've seen lately.  The passage you are in is rather tight.  It doesn't look like more than three people could fit in here.

name: Entrance to Deneb's Tomb
description: You are in a small, crowded passageway.  Only a couple people can fit in here at once.  To the west, you can see the great tomb of Deneb, the founding mage of Keslar.  Deneb was the first human to master  the art of magic from the elves.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The passage leads you through walls of small crypts, each containing one skeleton of a mage who died many centuries ago.  The mages formed a brotherhood and have stuck together through life and through death. The crypt was created as a monument to that brotherhood.

name: Tomb of Deneb
description: This tomb is huge and covered with gold and jewels.  Deneb formed a group of mages that met at Keslar Palace centuries ago to practice magic taught to him by the elves.  Deneb was the first recorded human to master the art of magic.  The elves never trusted humans with their magic for fear of what would happen if it got into the wrong hands.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The passage doesn't seem to get any lower than it already is.  There's a small cave to the south.  You can hear a lot of moaning coming from the cave, which is a shock since it has been deathly silent since  you've entered the crypt.

name: Crypt Passage
description: Both paths lead northward from here.  It doesn't look like they have dug any new crypt passages for centuries.  Although the crypts are quite crowded, no further development has occured.  Since the crypt was sealed centuries ago, no one has dared to enter it.

name: Tomb Entrance
description: To the northwest, you can see the great tomb of Rowland, the last great wizard of Keslar.  Rowland had the tomb built well before his death and his followers placed him there when Keslar was taken over by the evil wizard Kaylar.

name: Tomb of Rowland
description: Rowland was the last of the great wizards of Keslar that used his magic for the good of mankind.  The power of Keslar and the magic contained therin has fallen into the hands of evil and constantly threatens the fabric of man's existance.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The cavern crypts creep lower and lower the further south you head.  There's a distinct odor throughout the crypts, but not the kind you would  normally associate with rotting dead corpses.  The passage continues to the south and west.

name: Cave of Restless Spirits
description: The cave seems to moan out at you.  Every so often, you catch a glimpse of a ghost wandering around the cave.  The ghosts appear afraid and too weak to leave the cave which gives them their strength.  They have been banished here until the evil of Keslar Palace has been removed.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The crypt passage starts to head deeper into the island the further east you head.  Although it's not a steep decline, you do notice a drop in temperature the lower you get.  Corpses lie on both sides of the wall completely motionless, undisturbed by visitors for centuries.

name: Crypt Passage
description: The passage forks to the southeast and southwest.  You don't see as many corpses here as you did further west.  Both passages seem to drop drastically just after the paths split.

name: Passage Over the Cyclops Den
description: It looks like the Cyclops dug too high and broke through this passage. The mystical, yet deadly, creature is rumored to have a number of good weapons and other stashes of treasure.  The only way to get down there is to repel down.

name: Passage Over the Cyclops Den
description: Peering down over the edge of the crater, you notice that there's actually a room down there.  It appears to be the den of the great Cyclops.  He is rumored to have a number of great and powerful weapons that no one has been able to duplicate efficiently.

name: Cyclops Cavern
description: The cyclops is a deadly giant with only one eye.  He feeds on human flesh.  He has burrowed under the crypt and broke through some of the paths to lure unsuspecting victims.  The room you are in is huge and there's priceless treasures all around.

name: Secret Crypt Passage
description: This small, secret passage is so small, only you can get through it. The others in your party will have to wait for you to get out before they can come in after you.  You just hope there's something good at the other end of the passage.

name: Ancient Bibliotheke
description: The Great Bibliotheke (rumored to be only a mere myth) houses the most powerful spells in creation.  It is the storehouse for all of Kelsar's ancient mages and was thought to have been destroyed centuries ago. There are bookshelves upon bookshelves of ancient books along the walls. It's a mage's paradise.

name: Bibliotheke Hall
description: This narrow hallway is well lit and connects the bibliotheke to it's prized vault.  The hallway is decorated in the ancient colors of the Keslarian Mages and includes a number of portraits including those of Deneb and Rowland (they look better as ghosts).

name: Bibliotheke Vault
description: The Vault is used to store the mages most precious scrolls and artifacts. Although a number of items have already been looted from the vault, a couple may still remain hidden.

name: Forest Path
description: To the southeast is Forest Road, a major throughfare cut in the woods. To the north is a broad path, but quite dark due to the high cover of dense tree foliage.  The path is clear, the brush on either side is quite thick, and the trees overhead form a tunnel leading only north and south.  Somewhere in the distance you hear strange animal sounds and an owl hoots nearby.

name: Dark Path
description: The trees have an ominous look to them, and seem almost alive.  At times they seem to actually clutch at you as you walk in the center of the path.  The path gets even darker to the north, and seems to get narrower as well.

name: Cleared Path
description: The path appears to lead to a pleasant rest area toward the west, and to a dark area of the woods in the east.  A small stream gurgles its way along beside the path, making a pleasant sound in an otherwise silent woods.  Wildflowers grow along the way.

name: Ashton Creek Pool
description: Shy creatures peek out at you from the ferns and flowers growing wild all around you.  The grassy bank overlooking the stream seems to invite you to relax and forget your troubles for awhile.  Wild berrys and an apple tree grow nearby, providing you with fresh fruit.

name: Dark Path
description: The path to the northwest leads towards a freshly cleared area where you can smell cooking and woodsmoke in the air.  The trees don't seem as dense in that direction.  The path crosses over a small footbridge spanning a friendly little creek running to the north.  The eastern path leads deeper into the dark part of the forest, while the southern path may lead out of the Enchanted Forest.

name: Gravel Slope
description: near the top of the slope is a stand of ancient trees, thick with moss at ground level.  The gravel bank is bare of vegetation and extends for at least a hundred meters in either direction along the creek.  Close to the water you can see an exposed vein of what looks like gold!  In the distance you can see the path continues through the forest in in a northerly direction and also to the southeast.

name: Small Waterfall
description: Ashton creek is very wide at this point as it continues to flow toward the Ashton river to the south.  Great boulders give way to gravel toward the south, and tall, stately trees are on both sides of the stream.  Across the creek is a yellow stone cottage in a  cleared area.

name: Ashton Creek
description: To the west is a stone cottage near the bank and in a cleared area, and to the east are great boulders on the shore line.  To the north the stream tumbles over a broad but shallow waterfall.  In the distance to the north you can see a rope bridge traversing the stream where it narrows and starts to run deep.

name: Stone Cottage
description: The small stone house has an earthen roof and no windows, but appears to be clean and well maintained.  The chimney emits a good smelling smoke, and there is also the smell of roasting meat.  The walk way is lined with river rock, and flowers grow on the roof.  A small pen of goats is around to the back.

name: Ashton Creek Bank
description: The creek flows to the south where it will eventually join the Ashton River as it makes its way to the Nylandian Bay.  On the east side of the path, away from the water, you can see several tiny houses under the forest ferns.  The houses are not more than a meter tall, and are painted in the brightest of colors.

name: Mighty Tree Stump
description: The stump is perhaps two to three meters high, and is easily ten meters in diameter.  The path seems to circle it, and one side of the tree appears to be no better than the other in terms of getting around it. Further to the west is the stream, and to the east is thick underbrush.

name: West Side of Stump
description: The path continues in a circle, staying close to the great stump.  The gnarly roots twist and turn in every direction, making it difficult to to climb over them in places.  Not far to the west is the creek, and a little further to the north you can see a rope bridge going from east to west across it.

name: Quick Car Subsidiary Hub
description: The Subsidiary Hub connects the main hub to the western mountains and parts of Brownhaven.  The quick cars were invented by the elves centuries ago to travel around the high mountains without having to deal with the griffons, abominable snowmen and the notorious mountain raiders.

name: Riverdell Way/Hofton Avenue Intersection
description: Riverdell Way runs south out of the intersection with Hofton Avenue, which continues to the east and west, running parallel to the northern City Walls. To the southwest, you can see a large forest area that appears to continue as far down Riverdell Way that you can see.  The large forest seems  undisturbed by the passage of time and the development of the city.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Riverdell Way runs north and south through most of the eastern section of Oceancrest.  To the west, you can see a dense forest area that doesn't look inhabitable.  To the east, you can see the East Oceancrest City Guard Barracks, where a good portion of the guards are stationed.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The City Guards provide much of the needed security for the citizens of the town.  The Guards are primarily responsible for external, foreign affairs, such as conflicts with neighboring communities, and will seldom get involved in domestic disputes.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Despite the fact that the East Oceancrest City Guard Barracks are located to the east of the road, Riverdell Way is strangely quiet as you walk along the street.  To the west is a dense forest covered with shrubs, trees and other brush.

name: Riverdell Way/Tranquility Way Intersection
description: Tranquility Way is a short street running east and west through the northern section of town, intersecting Riverdell Way, which runs north and south. There is a large forest formed on the west side of the road, interrupted only by a few small streets which cut through it.  The Guard Barracks are located to the northeast and the Brunskid Trader's Guild is located to the southeast.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Brunskid Trader's Guild is a notoriously dangerous place to do  business, but the business can be quite profitable.  The Guild is filled with thieves and assassins out to make a quick buck.  To the distress of the city patrols, they have been unable to shut down this establishment.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Even though you are west of the East Oceancrest Guard Barracks, you  notice that the surrounding area is very quiet.  It is quite annoying, as the city should be quite busy with activity.  Riverdell Way continues to the north and south.  A dense forest can be seen to the west, but it doesn't look like you can get through the thick brush.

name: Riverdell Way/Orchard Lane Intersection
description: Riverdell Way runs north and south through the intersection with Orchard Lane, which continues to the east and west.  The Brunskid Trader's Guild is located on the northeastern corner of the intersection and known for it not-so-legitimate dealings with goods of questionable origins.  The Guild often gets raided, but they never find anything to shut them down.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Oolan's Armory is like every other armory in town, but specializes in exotic leather items such as dragon's leather and shark leather.  The fancy leathers are not without a cost, though, and they seldom last much longer than standard leather armors, if even that long.  They do make a good fashion statement, though, and occasionally Oolan has some really durable stuff.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Ironically, Nicholas has no enchanted weapons for sale, but likes to  advertise that he does to get people to buy his less powerful but more common stock.  The large shopping center to the east boasts a number of simple stores and services.  The center continues around the block.  On the west side of the street is a dark forest.

name: Riverdell Way
description: it's odd to be walking along the street and seeing on the east side of the road, a number of buildings housing shops and services, and on the west side, a dense forest.  The forest to the west is very thick, covered with shrubs and thorn bushes, making it virtually impossible to enter.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Riverdell Way continues to the north and south, traveling through the eastern section of town.  On the east side of the road is a funny shop called "The Glyph Master", a sort of fortune telling/deciphering store where you can probably figure out what a number of the cryptic scrolls and writings mean.

name: Riverdell Way/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Riverdell Way runs north and south through the intersection with Neilian Drive, which runs east and west.  There is a large forest on both sides of the western part of the road.  The thick brush and trees make it hard to see what's inside, if indeed there is something inside.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Snake Eyes Gambling Facility is a notorious bar and casino where people are known to enter but never leave from.  The police have tried to stop the activity, but seem to have little success.  Gambling is not at all illegal in Oceancrest, but losing money and owing a shark thousands of gold pieces with 200% interest per hour tends to cause problems.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The forest on the west side of the road is protected by the thick trees and shrubs growing around its perimiter, preventing anyone from actually entering the forest, save for a couple of rangers who happen to be  searching for tracks.  Riverdell continues to the north and south.

name: Riverdell Way/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Riverdell Way, running north and south, intersects Lelion Way, which continues to the east and west.  The fantastic Ashton River can be seen in the distance to the southwest, along with the Ashton Falls Resort, a fancy inn where the rich and famous spend their free time.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The large Wakarimasu Park was constructed a few decades ago in an effort to beautify the eastern entrance to the city.  The project was rather  successful, and the park is visited often by visitors and residents of the city.

name: Riverdell Way
description: You can see the Ashton River flowing north as you walk along the road. The Ashton Waterfall is visible up ahead to the south, along with the Ashton Falls Resort.  The Resort is a very exclusive club for only the upper crust of society.

name: Ashton Bridge
description: The Ashton River flows west across Riverdell Way.  The bridge is not too high above the flowing river, which has been known to overflow onto the bridge in heavy rainy seasons.  You can see the spectacular Ashton  Waterfall to the west.  The best place to view the waterfall is from within the Ashton Falls Resort.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Ashton Bridge crosses over the Ashton River, which appears to flow to the west across Riverdell Way.  To the west is the exclusive Ashton Falls Resort, reserved for only the most exclusive group of people. The entrance to the resort is off of Oceancrest Avenue.

name: Riverdell Way/Oceancrest Avenue Intersection
description: Riverdell Way runs north and south through the intersection with Oceancrest Avenue, which runs east and west through town.  Oceancrest Avenue runs from the eastern entrance to the city towards the docks in Nylandian bay in the west.  Riverdell Way runs from the north city walls all the way to the southern city walls.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The large Iilandi University has long been known as the best learning institution in the lands.  The great people of the lands come to teach here not for gold, but for prestige.  Since most are already rich, there isn't much of a need to pay them more gold.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Rodaisal Community Housing Complex provides simple, communal housing for most of the population who choose to live within the city of  Oceancrest.  Individual housing is impossible in the city due to the lack of free space, so these large complexes were built to give people a place to live.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Chancellor's Hall is one of the major buildings on the Iilandi  University Campus.  It is the primary hall for most of the lectures and other activities that take place on the campus.  To the west is the Rodaisal Community Housing Complex.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Rodaisal Community Housing Complex lies to the west of the road, providing much of the housing in Oceancrest.  The Iilandi University is one of the most popular learning facilities in the city, and does not charge students for the privilage of learning at the campus.

name: Ministry Way/Orchard Lane Intersection
description: Ministry Way runs south out of the intersection with Orchard Lane, which runs east and west.  On the north side of the intersection is the Brunskid Trader's Guild, where all sorts of items are sold.  These items are usually not legal, or possibly stolen.  It is also a very dangerous place where theives and assassins abound, lurking in the shadows.

name: Ministry Way
description: The Healer's Eye, located on the west side of the road, is one of the many healers in the land that will provide services for no charge.   Unfortunately, the shop is rather small and they can only accomodate a few people at a time.

name: Ministry Way
description: The North Oceancrest Ministries are located to the east, and include the Ministry to Tranquility, the Hall of Discipline and the Ministry of Rumor Control.  To the west, you can see a small shop called Iilian's Potions, where various potions and other strange stuff may be purchased.

name: Ministry Way
description: Miriam is one of the finest blacksmiths in the town, but limits his work to just repairing armor, claiming that more people are willing to fix their armors instead of buying new stuff.  On the east side of the road are the three North Oceancrest Ministries.

name: Ministry Way
description: It is very important to recycle in Oceancrest as all the junk lying around could seriously injure innocent people who accidentally trip over it.  The idea behind the recycling plants is to exchange used up junk for cash as an incentive to get people to bring in worn and useless items.

name: Ministry Way/Neilian Drive Intersection
description: Ministry Way runs north and south through the intersection with Neilian Drive, which runs east and west.  Ministry Way is a small road which runs between Orchard Lane and Lelion Way.  On the southeast are a number of small religious centers and on the northeast are the Oceancrest Ministries.

name: Ministry Way
description: The Snake Eyes Gambling Facility is one of the rowdiest bars in Oceancrest, short of the Fiesty Kitten.  On the east side of the road is the Gnomen Temple of Garl Glittergold.  The gnomen diety is one of the most powerful gods in gnomen mythology.

name: Ministry Way
description: Yondalla is the halfling goddess of creation.  The small halfling race, also known as hobbits, are quite religious and come to worship at the temple at least once a week.  The large, Snake Eyes Gambling Facility is located to the west.

name: Ministry Way/Lelion Way Intersection
description: Ministry Way runs north from the intersection with Lelion Way, which runs east and west.  Ministry Way runs past the North Oceancrest Ministries of Tranquility, Discipline and Rumor Control.  Lelion Way runs east and west across the north side of the Wakarimasu Park.

name: Lelion Way
description: The large park on the south side of the road is surrounded by thick brush and trees preventing the casual walker from seeing inside the mysterious park.  On the north side of the road is the Temple of Harmonic Discord.

name: Lelion Way
description: Lelion is a long road, spanning from the eastern city walls to the east, all the way to the Nylandian Bay, many miles to the west.  On the north side of the road is the Temple of Harmonic Discord, one of the most powerful clerical temples in Oceancrest.

name: Lelion Way
description: The vast park on the south side of the road is the home of many shrines to long thought to be dead dieties.  Of course since dieties never die, they still exist, but are not as powerful anymore because they lack  people to worship them.

name: Lelion Way
description: On the south side of the road, you can see a dense forest covered with shrubs and trees.  On the north is the Nowhere Fast Traveller's Guild. Anyone visiting Oceancrest or leaving Oceancrest should check with the Traveller's Guild about potential problems they might encounter in new or unfamiliar terrain.

name: Lelion Way
description: On the north side of the road is the Paladin's Holy Order of the Red Rose, where worthy paladins train.  To the south is the large Wakarimasu Park, home of a number of old dieties from ancient times, no longer believed in.  However, their presence is still felt within the park.

name: Lelion Way
description: The Shrine of Yondalla is on the north side of the road.  Yondalla is one of the primary dieties of the halfling culture.  Most hobbits are quite religious and visit the temple at least once a week.  Wakarimasu Park is located to the south.

name: Lelion Way
description: The large Wakarimasu Park, located to the south, is one of the larger city parks in Oceancrest.  The primary function of the park is to give a positive image of the city as people walk in from the eastern city gates.  To the north is the Snake Eyes Gambling Facility.

name: Lelion Way
description: The large gambling hall takes up most of the city block surrounded by  Lelion Way, Neilian Drive, Riverdell Way and Ministry Way.  This huge facility is notorious for high stakes betting and other illegal activities that usually get by the morality patrols.

name: Thernardier's Alley
description: The Highland Stables is a rather nice place to board your horse, and they also rent horses to travellers coming out of the city.  It really is an honest mistake when they rent your horse to some drunken lout who doesn't know how to treat a horse.  The alley connects to Wakeforest Drive on the west.

name: Thackery's Pub
description: A lot of mismatched furniture is scattered throughout the room, and a fire burns in a large fireplace.  A group of loud singers are gathered at one end of the room, and a number of girls carry wine to the customers at the tables.  This place is frequented mostly by farmers and local merchants, and they all seem to be having a good time.  A few field  hands and grape pickers are playing darts.

name: Brig on the Widowmaker
description: Pirates don't really believe in brigs, preferring instead to simply toss overboard anyone who misbehaves on their ship.  Several years ago, a small hobbitish pirate got drunk, and accidently was locked in here. The other pirates tried to get him out, but when they coldn't find the key they left him in here.  Since he was in against his will, they called it the brig.  Some say the chief bosun knew where the key was all the time and simply hid it as a joke.  Some joke.

name: Chief Bosun's Quarters
description: There is a massive bunk on one bulkhead, and single, giant chair sits nearby.  A lone hurricane lantern swings slowly from the overhead, casting moving shadows in a dismal and damp room.  The chief bosun is not known for his good humor, and even the hardiest of swashbucklers and pirates do not come here willingly.  Why are you here?

name: Lelion Way
description: On the north side of the road is a dense stand of trees so thick you cannot see more than a few meters that way.  Tree branches overhang the road, making it quite shady along here.  There are apple trees to the south, but they are not quite so dense in that direction.

name: Lelion Way/Apple Orchid
description: An incredibley beautiful apple orchid is guarded by a small wooden fence on the south side of Lelion Way, while the forest on the north provides a home for a number of wood creatures and folk.  Rumors in the city speak of odd happenings in the forest, and not all of them good things.  Some say a great wizard makes his summer home in the forest.

name: Lelion Way
description: The forest trees are old and stately, forming a canopy of branches overhead.  Lelion Way continues to the east and west through the woods.  To the east is a wooden bridge spanning the Ashton River. Further to the southeast is the famed Ashton waterfalls and the Ashton Falls Resort.  On the south side is an apple orchid.

name: Ashton River Bridge
description: Directly to the east is the intersection of Lelion Way and Riverdell Way.  Below is the Ashton River, which runs north/south at this part of its course.  A sign on the bridge says to beware of trolls who have been known to accost travelers at this point of their journey. In the South you can see the Ashton Waterfalls, a spectacular sight visited by locals and tourists alike.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The powerful Dragon's Citadel is one of the few landmarks that have existed before the City of Oceancrest was actually built.  On the south side of the road is the Temple of Harmonic Discord, an odd sort of group of people who try to solve problems without wars or other means of violence.  This is, of course, impossible.

name: Neilian Drive
description: A large gate seems to be open as you approach the Citadel.  Many believe that the Citadel has been long abandoned, but no one has really ventured into the depths of the strange building.  The Dragon's Citadel awaits those who dare to enter it.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The Temple of Harmonic Discord is a strange cult of hypocrits who somehow think that if there's a problem, there's a peaceful way around it.  This is never true because no one ever wants to give up what they have "for the better good".  Nevertheless, they keep trying.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The two things in Oceancrest which really hold some mystery to the  citizens and visitors of the city are the Allakaren Pyramid and the Dragon's Citadel.  The City was essentially formed around these two landmarks which have probably existed longer than anyone can remember.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The Paladin's Holy Order of the Red Rose is located to the south of Neilian Drive, but the entrance to the large building is located off of Wakeforest Drive, to the east.  The Holy Order provides advanced training to Paladins before they apply to the Lyanden Castle for service.  On the north side of the road is the North Oceancrest Ministry of Rumor Control, a sort of media controller for the city.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The North Oceancrest Ministries are located on the north part of the street, providing order and wisdom for the city.  The Ministry of Rumor Control is one of the more interesting bodies in city politics, and is responsible for detailed information about events which happen in the city.  This is kind of like the media, except slightly better.

name: Neilian Drive
description: To the north is one of the numerous recycling plants in Oceancrest.  Most of the junk that people can't use gets pulverized and then re-used as something else.  There are a number of shops in the center to the north. The entrance to these shops is on the other side of the building along Ministry Way or Riverdell Way, to the east or west respectively.

name: Neilian Drive
description: Gambling has never really been illegal in Oceancrest, but highly discouraged. Not so much because of the gambling itself, but what the loss of large amounts of money does to people.  After all, the house always has an  advantage, otherwise they wouldn't be doing it.

name: Keslar Mountain Trail
description: To the west, you can see the great Necropolis.  From this high up, you can see just how big the Necropolis is.  It must span about three city blocks square.  The path up the mountain continues towards the top of the mountain and towards the Palace.  To the north, you can see the gate that you originally used to get in.

name: Mountain Trail to the Palace
description: The trail up the mountain is not quite as treacherous as you had first imagined.  Nonetheless, danger lurks everywhere.  As you head further south, you can start to make out the features of the large palace  sitting on top the mountain.  The Palace appears to be magically kept in place since it would otherwise collapse and fall down the mountain.

name: Mountain Trail to the Palace
description: The trail up the mountains is starting to level out towards the summit. Ahead to the south, you can see the great palace you saw from below.  The "Forbidden" Palace, as many locals like to call it, seems very desolate, but everyone seems to know that someone or something still inhabits the old mansion.

name: Etolosian Bridge
description: The small river you are crossing changes its name often as it passes by different cultures.  This area of Oceancrest is filled with various cults and cultures that may not always agree with everything else.  Nevertheless, they are protected by the city and have their own defenses.

name: Neilian Drive
description: On both sides of the road, you can see some thick forests that completely obstruct your view inside them.  Not that there's anything to really see if you could see past the trees.  The trees and brush tend to be so thick that people seldom ever try to get into the forests.

name: Neilian Drive
description: Two dense forests are separated by Neilian Drive as it cuts through the thick brush.  It is unsure whether or not there was a natural break between the two forests or whether the forest was carved out to make way for this bypass.  No one ever seems to enter or exit from the forests, so it would seem that no one would care.

name: Neilian Drive
description: The dense forests on both sides of the road do not appear as omnimous as they had originally appeared from Leviathan or Riverdell.  Nevertheless, the forests seem rather spooky.  Sometimes you might be able to find  tracks into the forests if you look very carefully.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The massive complex to the north is the Oceancrest Military Headquarters, where all the decisions about defense and wars are addressed.  Since there are so many barbarian tribes beyond the city walls of the city, it is essential to have a good military to defend and wake up the city.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Despite the heavy military presence in the area, the northeastern quadrant of town tends to be the rowdiest of them all.  Numerous nightclubs and bars line the streets, filled with officers and enlisted men after a long day at work. They tend not to be in very good moods.  You might think twice before entering any bar on this side of the town.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: You have reached the western edge of the great Military Headquarters on the north side of the road.  The building must extend nearly two city blocks as you can't see the eastern end of the building no matter how hard you look.  The Headquarters is the central controlling body for the Oceancrest defenses.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: Hofton Avenue turns to the southeast as it approaches the Oceancrest  Military Headquarters, which you can see to the east.  To the south, you can see the East Oceancrest City Guard Barracks, where the guards and other personnel are housed.  Much of Oceancrest's economy depends on the military force keeping barbarian cultures outside of Oceancrest from breaching the city walls.

name: Hofton Avenue
description: The Northern City Walls disappear behind the large military building  located to the east as Hofton turns to the southeast up ahead.  To the west, you can see the intersection with Riverdell Way.  On the south are the East Oceancrest City Guard Barracks, where much of the city guard is stationed.

name: Hallway Intersection
description: The place is odd in a way that you do not notice at first.  Its a strange feeling that is in the back of your mind, but keeps coming back to your thoughts.  The completely bare walls make the halls look desolate and ancient.  There's no dust, though, as if the halls were cleaned on a daily basis.  Yet they have an old, dirty yellow look to them.

name: Desolate Hallway
description: You are shocked by the condition of this particular hallway.  For some reason, it is in a complete mess, with dust and dirt collecting on the floor and walls.  Strange how such a nice place could turn into such a mess.

name: Desolate Hallway Corner
description: The hallway makes an abrubt 90 degree turn here making a small alcove that monsters like to hide in.  You can't see very well around the  corners so you had better stay on guard.

name: Desolate Hallway
description: The one thing that catches your eye is the large number of crushed skeletons on the floor.  In fact, a number of them have been crushed into dust.  It's quite bizzare, but at the same time quite curious.

name: Hallway
description: There are a number of small holes in the walls indicating that something might set off a trap in this room.  You should be careful what you do in  here because it might set off some poisoned darts or worse.  Obviously someone doesn't want you snooping around.

name: End of the Hall
description: You have come to a large door that blocks your entrance to whatever's behind it.  There is a large padlock on the door.  It looks like it's used quite often, but you don't see anyone around right now.

name: Secret Hallway
description: The hallway has a musty smell, but it's a relief compared to what really smells behind the door.  The hallway continues to the south, getting darker the further south you go.

name: Secret Hallway
description: The musty hallway continues to the north.  At the south, it turns sharply to the west.  Although it's very dark in here, you have a strange feeling that something is not right in here or that something bad is going to happen.

name: Secret Hallway
description: The dark hallway continues to the west and makes a sharp turn to the south.  The eerie silence of the hallway makes you take each step very cautiously.  Who knows what is lurking behind the corner.

name: Hallway Intersection
description: Strangely, the hallway now splits into four separate hallways, each leading in a different direction.  You seem to be getting closer to some sort of building, although you can't quite make out exactly  what it is.

name: Secret Hallway
description: You have wandered into a secret hallway behind the torture chamber.  You can hear the tortured screams of victims being eternally punished.  The door appears to be bolted from the inside.  Something just doesn't seem right, though, although you can't really tell why.

name: Secret Hallway
description: The secret hallway starts and continues to the north.  There is a door here but it looks like it's bolted shut.  A sign near the door says "Enter At Own Risk".

name: Secret Hallway Dead End
description: The room is covered with pulverized skeletons of people who were  unfortunate enough to walk into the room unprepared.  You can see a giant block hanging on the ceiling ready to crash down on a new victim.  It's a good thing you prepared for this.

name: Inquisition Room
description: The people in the dungeon aren't as friendly as the people in town.  You are in a small questioning room where prisoners are asked to answer a number of questions.  Failure to do so may result in punishment.  By the looks of the weapons on the wall, you don't really want to know what that punishment is.

name: Torture Chamber
description: The torture chamber is used quite extensively.  The room is covered in blood and miscellaneous organs.  Ironically, it doesn't really smell of dead, rotting flesh, which leads you to believe things are cleaned up here regularly.

name: Dungeon Hallway
description: By the smell of things, you think something just died.  In fact, it's just the kitchen cooking up some grub for the prisoners.  Forcing them to eat that food is probably enough torture for one person.  The door to the north is inscribed "Inquisition Room/Authorized Use Only".  The door looks like it's bolted shut.

name: Dungeon Hallway
description: The dungeon hallway continues to the east and west.  To the east, you can make out what appears to be a dungeon.  There are a number of  doors on both sides of the hallway in both directions.

name: Dungeon Hallway
description: The west end of the hallway is quiet with an occasional guard wandering in to check up on things.  There is a door to the south that reads "Laboratory".  Rumor has it that a mad scientist works on creating human-like monsters out of human parts in there.  There's also a door to the north leading to the Mausoleum.

name: Laboratory
description: The mad scientist is working on a number of experiments including a large monster-like being made up of mostly human body parts.  There are a number of jars on the walls with what looks like human brains stored in them.  There's a stairwell in the southwest corner of the laboratory.

name: Dungeon Kitchen
description: The kitchen is filthy.  Small rats run around grabbing pieces of meat or what looks like meat (arguably) whenever they can.  The large pot on the stove contains what looks like some sort of stew, but you can't really tell what's in there, not that you'd really want to know.

name: Dungeon Guard Quarters
description: There doesn't seem to be any order in the lower ranks.  In fact, there's no discipline visible.  The room is a mess and the guards probably like  it that way.  This place probably get's pretty busy so it's probably not a good idea to stand out in the open.

name: The Crypt
description: This crypt was used to store the ashes of ancient generations of  ancestors to the Keslar family.  A few are embalmed, but most are in urns lining up along the wall.

name: Secret Passage
description: Although not really a 'secret' hallway, most people visiting the Mausoleum never give it a second glance.  The east hallway leads to the Crematorium.  The ashes are then returned to either the Mausoleum or placed in the Crypt.

name: Ghoul's Dining Hall
description: If you haven't already figured it out, ghouls live off of human flesh. They also don't mind elves and dwarves.  There are a number of dead carcasses scattered around the room.  One is prepared on the table for dinner.  The stench and atmosphere in here is really making you ill.

name: Storage Room
description: This is where the ghouls keep their meat relatively fresh, although the bodies are already starting to decay.  The smell is unbearable. Two doors lead out of this room.  There is a similar stench in the direction of the first door.

name: Mausoleum
description: The Mausoleum is well furnished with the great art and works of deceased members of the family.  Each is given a small crypt where their ashes are placed for all eternity.  This place does not seem all that 'scary'. In fact, the place looks well visited.

name: Cremetorium
description: This is the place where the deceased are consumed by fire and returned to the earth as dust and ash.  There is a large furnace at the north end of the room.  The hallway to the west leads back into the Mausoleum.

name: Dungeon
description: There are a couple of large community cells where prisoners are kept, usually on a permanent basis.  Most, conviniently, don't stay very long.  The dungeon cell doors are made of heavy oak making it impossible to see what's inside without actually going in.

name: Stairwell
description: The stairway leads up into the main level of the palace. At the top of the stairway, you can see what looks like the back of a bookcase. The door at the top must be a secret door.  At the bottom, you can see the makings of a large laboratory.

name: Entryway to the Palace of Keslar
description: The sign on the door says "Welcome to Keslar's Palace / Now Go Home!".   Not a very friendly person, but mages seldom are.  The palace, from what you can see of it, is huge.  Two great oak doors stand to the south of you leading into the palace.

name: Main Foyer
description: This magnificent palace is made of the most solid granite and is  constantly protected by magic.  The mages of Keslar are considered the most powerful in the world.  Be prepared for quite a fight if you decide to cross them.

name: Foyer Hallway
description: The main hallway takes you around the palace.  To the west, you can see the lounge.  A number of guests and apprentice mages are socializing there.  To the east, you see the recreation room, again with a number of guests and mages socializing.  It's a pretty busy place.

name: Northern Hall
description: The palace hallway continues to the west.  To the north is the Recreation Room, where visitors and apprentice mages gather to discuss their latest creations or what new spells they have learned.  The eastern hallway begins to the south.

name: Recreation Room
description: A number of mages have gathered around to play with their newly acquired magic.  The palace of Keslar has long been the training grounds of a number of great and powerful mages.  Watch out...if you're not careful, you're likely to be the target of this magic.

name: Stairwell
description: This stairwell provides the servants and guards direct access to the palace's main levels and their quarters.  All the servants and guards have quarters in the lower part of the basement.  Their lives are  modest, but not overbearing.

name: Northern Hall
description: The north hall continues to the east.  To the west, you can see the western hall and the glass enclosed garden where a number of enchanting plants grow.  To the north is the lounge where great mages come to tell some fantastic stories of their battles.  To the south is the central hall, leading directly to the main dining hall.

name: Lounge
description: The lounge is a busy place with a number of mages both new and old  sharing stories and adventures of times when mages literally ruled the world.  It is well known that Keslar Palace has been training  the most elite mages the world has known, both past and present.

name: Passage to the Greenhouse
description: This remarkably modern hallway allows you to look out at the mountains of Eeste Island as you approach the Greenhouse.  It also leads back to the main lounge where a number of people are socializing.  The  greenhouse is filled with a lot of interesting and unusual plants.

name: Greenhouse
description: The greenhouse houses a number of exotic and unusual plants.  Little did you know, they were man-eating.  A couple of them snap at you as you walk in but most are firmly rooted.  Some, however, seem to be moving towards you.

name: Garden
description: The garden is used mostly for relaxation after the day is done.  It's a pretty quiet place to relax for a while.  To the north is the  greenhouse where a number of plant experiments are supposedly being performed.  Perhaps it's not a very good idea to go exploring in there.

name: Gardener's Shack
description: Unfortunately, there's no gardener here right now.  He's probably out in the garden cleaning up.  The shack apperently has nothing fancy in it besides some hoes and shovels which could be used as weapons if you got desperate.  The gardener won't like you taking his supplies from him, though.

name: Western Hall
description: The western hall runs along the west side of the large palace.  To  the north is the large, glass-enclosed garden.  The mages accidentally invented glass while testing high-energy fireballs on the sandy shores of Eeste Island.  No one else seems to realize that it's just sand.  Most of the humans still think it's just more of the mages' magic.

name: Dim Hallway
description: This passage leads to two doors at the end of the hallway.  The one to the north leads to a den.  The one to the south leads to the  library.  The walls are outlined with pictures of the conquests of the family dating back to when magic was first harnessed by humans.

name: Western Hall
description: The western hall is decorated with more portraits of mages and wizards who had a desire to conquer the world.  Unfortunately, they failed and retreated to this mountain hide-away where they wait for the time when they can return and reclaim the world.

name: Keslar's Den
description: The Keslar den is used as a small meeting place where people can meet in privacy to conduct business.  There's a large desk in the exact center of the room and a table with a flask of brandy.  The books on the bookshelf appear to be just old ledgers showing the financial stability of the  family.

name: Keslar's Library
description: This small library is used by many visitors and other mages to better their basic mage skills.  Scanning through the books, there's nothing of real value that you haven't seen before.  Looks like a place where many apprentices go to study.

name: Southern Hall
description: The southern hall continues to the east.  The west hallway has formed to the north and a small guard's hall is to the south.  As you have been surveying the palace, you notice that the mages have accomplished much more in the ways of technology than the humans in Brownhaven.  You are astonished by the grandeur and sophistication of such a place.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: This narrow hallway proceeds behind the main dining hall and is used primarily by the servants bringing food into the dining hall.  The hallway curves to the east and the southern end of the hall.  As you start to turn the corner you see a number of servants bringing food into the dining hall.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: You appear to be behind the main dining hall.  The mages meet there every evening and often invite their important guests.  You can see a number of maids entering the dining hall to the east.  The  delicious smell of the food is making you hungry.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: A door leads into the main dining hall.  The place appears to be fairly busy as the maids rush around bringing dinner to the hungry people in the hall.  You can see a stairway to the east that must lead up to the main kitchen since that's where all the maids are coming from.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: There is a stairway here leading up to the main kitchen.  All the maids are rushing around, trying to get the dinner served to the very hungry guests.  It's usually not a good idea to make the mages angry and hungry mages tend to become angry ones.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: You are in the eastern servant and guard hallway.  The hallway is  primarily used by the maids and servants to deliver food to the main dining hall.  It also provides a passage for security guards to make sure order is kept without alarming the guests.

name: Guard and Servant Hallway
description: You are at the entrance to the servant and guard hallway.  It is  restricted to authorized servants and guards, but there doesn't seem to be anyone around to stop you.  Since the hall is in plain sight, you don't see any harm in a little exploration.

name: Southern Hallway
description: The hallway continues to the west.  The east hallway starts to the north bringing you back towards the front of the palace.  A small guard's and servant's hallway has started to the southeast.

name: Southern Hall
description: The south hall continues to the east and west from here.  In front of you are two great oak doors leading into the main dining hall.  To the north, you see yet another hallway leading back towards the front of the palace.

name: Main Dining Hall
description: The dining hall is majestically huge consisting of a number of large tables all around the room.  A number of people have already started to eat.  At the head, you see a number of the high mages.  Most of the people have ignored your intrusion of their dinner.

name: Central Palace Hallway
description: This hallway brings you directly to the front of the palace.  Following it south leads you to the great dining hall where a number of guests are assembling for dinner.  There is a large door on the east side of the hallway leading into what appears to be a meeting room.

name: Main Meeting Hall
description: The mages come here to discuss their plans for the day and a number of other important topics which vary from day to day.  A large table in  the center of the room provides seats for ten mages.  The meeting is headed by one of the sorceresses.

name: Eastern Hall
description: The eastern hall brings you from the front of the palace to the rear. At the southern end, another hallway has formed which appears to take you towards the main dining hall.  The Keslar palace has long been entertaining the most powerful people of the land in order to influence their decisions over power in this region.

name: Gaming Lounge
description: The gaming lounge is used by many of the mages of Keslar to try out new magic and weapons on their unsuspecting victims.  The powerful mages can cast deadly spells with pinpoint accuracy.  High above you, you can see a number of people gathered to watch the mages.

name: Stairwell
description: This stairwell is used primarily by the mages coming down to challenge the prisoners who are in the game lounge.  The mages enjoy using their magic on the prisoners as there is no one else in the world to use it on.  The mages have not dared to leave the palace in numbers for ages.

name: Gaming Preparation Lounge
description: The preparation lounge is used to prepare prisoners for their battle with the wizards of Keslar.  The mages use prisoners as test dummies to try out their new spells and other magical items.  Some of the more powerful mages deal out instant death to many of the common people off the street and can make the most powerful barbarians cringe.

name: Stairwell
description: The panels making up the stairs creak as you walk on them.  The stairwell leads up to the main level arena.  The door has a plaque marked "Prison" bolted to it.

name: Main Prison Hold
description: The prison is used to hold people who show disrespect towards others in the palace.  Actually, prison is a blessing compared to what has happened to other people who anger the wrong person.  There are a number of cells in this room.  Some are vacant.

name: Prison Cell
description: This prison is pretty small compared to the others you have been unfortunate enough to be locked into.  The food is descent so most of the people aren't complaining, or so the guards would have you believe.

name: Prison Cell
description: The palace likes to keep unwanted vagrants away from their honored  guests.  This is the place most of them go.  You see a number of prisoners in the cells around you.  You've heard, however, that there is a much darker dungeon somewhere below you.

name: Prison Cell
description: You are in a small cell isolated from the rest of the prisoners.  It's hardly solitary as the prison itself is very small.  Like most prisons, this one is pretty dreary.

name: Prison Cell
description: The prison is well kept, for a prison, that is.  The bars prevent you  from escaping.  Every so often, a guard passes by.  Perhaps you should try to get his attention.

name: Prison Cell
description: This cell is rather large, in comparison to the other cells.  Of course they compensate by putting more prisoners in here.  The stench in here is almost unbearable.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The basement hallway turns sharply to the north and east.  This area of the basement appears to be much less active than the rest of the area, but there are a number of guards which pass by checking in on everything.  The hallway to the east heads towards the servant  quarters.

name: Basement Hallway
description: This hall is used primarily by the maids and servants cleaning up the palace.  A hallway forms to the east taking you to the servant's quarters. A door on the west appears to go into the dining hall and recreation area where the guards and servants go to relax after a long day's work.

name: Basement Hallway
description: This basement passage continues to the north and south.  To the north, you can see the stairwell that will take you back up the the main level of the Palace.  Another hallway has formed to the west which appears to go into the servant's quarters.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The basement corridor has turned to the north and west from here, the southern most portion of the basement.  This area is pretty desolate with an occasional guard wandering by just making sure things are  ok.  You see a number of servants and maids to the north.

name: Basement Hallway
description: With the exception of a passing guard, this area of the basement  appears to be quite desolate.  To the north, you can see a bit more activity.  A lot of people appear to be going into a large room in the west.

name: Servant's Quarters Hallway
description: Two rooms are located on both sides of this hallway, one to the north and one to the south.  The quarters on the north appear to be mostly for the servants who clean the house.  The quarters to the south appear to be for the maids who serve the guests and mages of the Palace.

name: Servant's Quarters
description: The servants are in charge of keeping the palace clean and tidy.  These quarters house about ten servants.  The quarters are quite clean and well taken care of.  Despite their status, most of the people employed by the Palace are well taken care of.

name: Maid's Quarters
description: The maids are responsible for serving the guests and mages of the  Palace.  Most of them are used in the dining hall but occassionally they bring drinks to the guests in the lounge and entertainment  rooms.  Like the servants quarters, these are well cleaned with  ample space for each maid.

name: Dining and Recreation Area
description: This hall is the primary dining area for the servants and guards.  The food that is served is typically just leftovers of the food which is served to the mages and their guests.  The food is top quality so on one is complaining.  This hall is also used for meetings and other gatherings.  There's also a card table in one corner and a variety of other entertainment items around.

name: Central Basement Hallway
description: Two hallways meet here, one going north and south, the other going east and west.  They essentially divide the basement in half.  Most of the southern half of the basement is reserved for the servants and maids. The northern area is primarially used by the elite palace guards.

name: Servant and Guard Quarters
description: You are in a small, plain hallway taking you around the various quarters in the basement of the Palace.  This is where most of the common servants sleep and relax.  It is also the headquarters for the palace guards.   The hallways continue to the west, north and south.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The hallway wraps around a corner here and continues to the south and west.  There is a large room to the south of you that is labeled "Guard Commander".  There's another door to the west.  There seem to be a lot of people wandering around down here.

name: Guard Meeting Room
description: The palace guards meet here regularly to discuss their shifts and work out movement schedules.  There is a large table in the center of the room.  A door on the east wall is labled "Guard Commander's Office". The door on the north wall heads back out into the hallway.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The basement hallway you are in splits to the south and continues to head east and west.  To the south, you see a door labeled "Meeting Hall".   You can also see a number of guards wandering in and out of the hallways and rooms.  Luckily they haven't seen you yet (or have they).

name: Basement Corner
description: The hallway forms to the east and south of here.  You can see to the east of you a door leading into what appears to be guards quarters. With the large number of guards you have seen wandering the halls in this area, you figure that's probably a good guess.

name: Main Guard's Quarters
description: The palace guards are known for their masterful skill of weapons and strenght.  Not many people dare to confront them.  The mages rely heavily on the guards to protect the palace from intruders as they have much more important things to plan.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The basement hallways continue to the north and south.  Another hallway branches out from this one to the east.  There is a door on the north wall that appears to lead to the main guards quarters.  There's a  pretty high concentration of guards in this area.

name: Basement Hallway
description: The hallway you are in continues to the north and south.  There's a door on the east wall which appears to lead into a small dining hall for the servants and guards.  You see a number of people walking in and out of that room, so it'll be hard to sneak around in here.

name: Stairway to Main Floor
description: You can enter the balcony from here to the north.  The balcony overlooks most of the island and is used by a number of people to get away from the hassle and activity of the main floor.  The stairway leads down to the lounge.

name: West Balcony
description: The view of Eeste Island is spectacular from this vantage point.  You can see majestic mountains rising up from the lake and the small paths and caves that make the island so unique.  The balcony is a good place to relax without having to worry about people bothering you.

name: East Balcony
description: You can see the lake and the mountains surrounding the lake from this part of the balcony.  You can also see a giant sea monster attacking a small boat in the middle of the lake.  You continue to rest on the balcony as people wander in and out of this room.

name: Stairway to Main Floor
description: This stairway connects the main floor to the second floor.  It allows guests to go onto the balcony to rest without worrying about business or other transactions.  Not to mention, the view from the balcony is supposed to be spectacular.

name: Main Hallway
description: The main hallway is primarily used by the maids and chefs to bring food to the lounge and recreation rooms.  Guests are welcome to come up and look around.  There are guest quarters on the west side of the second floor and the balcony is to the north.

name: Main Hallway
description: The main hallway is used by the servants and maids to bring food and refreshments down from the kitchen to the lounge and recreation room. The mages and their guests often use it as well to show them around the palace and to direct them to their quarters.  The hallway  continues to the north and south.  You can see the large balcony  overlooking the island to the north.

name: Main Hallway
description: Something sure smells good up here.  It's probably coming from the  kitchen to the east.  To the west, there is a door that is marked "Guest".  Many of the visiting dignitaries are given temporary  quarters for the duration of their stay here.  Being so close to the kitchen, they can have their choice of what they want to eat at any time of the day.

name: Southern Access Hallway
description: This access hallway allows servants and maids to bring dinner down to the mages and guests in the main dining hall.  To the east, you can see a balcony leading across into some sort of large lounge.  You can't make out just what it is.

name: Meat Freezer
description: It has long been known that meat must be kept cold or it would spoil. Since the mages don't have dinner meetings every night, some meat needs to be kept without it spoiling.  The mages use a number of tricks to accomplish this using their magical powers, specifically through the powerful iceblade spell.  Don't stay in here too long or you're liable to get frostbite.

name: Main Kitchen
description: The main kitchen is not only used to prepare meals, but is also the  main wine storage area and meat freezer.  Cocktails, refreshments and food are prepared for delivery to the main dining hall or to the guests throughout the mansion.  The door to the west takes you back into the main hall.  There is a freezer to the south that holds all the meats so that they don't spoil.

name: Southern Access Hall
description: This hall is used mostly by the servants and maids to bring drinks and food to the mages and their guests in the dining hall and in the  lounge.  The mages also use this hall to get to the Gaming Lounge (to the west) which is used to test out their new magical weapons.

name: Balcony Over Gaming Lounge
description: The gaming lounge is used to test out magical weapons and spells on helpless prisoners who were caught intruding on the palace.  There is a stairway down into the lounge to the southeast.  The balcony continues to the north.

name: Balcony Over Gaming Lounge
description: You are at the southeastern balcony overlooking the gaming arena.  The mages come here to safely watch others test out their magical abilities against helpless prisoners.  There is a small stairway leading down into the gaming lounge.

name: Balcony Over Gaming Lounge
description: Many mages have come here to witness the slaughter of prisoners who have disobeyed the mages or intruded on the palace.  There are many interested third parties here as well who may be interested in hiring mages for their adventures.  To the northeast, you can see the great sorceress who is guarded by many of here elite palace guards.

name: Balcony Edge
description: The edge of the balcony is reserved for the sorceress to view her pupils best work.  Every so often, she herself will go down to  practice here magic on some unsuspecting victim.  There are also a number of palace guards here protecting her from intruders such as yourself.

name: Eastern Corridor
description: The eastern corridor brings you around to the back of the palace.  This area is primarily used by the servants and maids to bring refreshments to the guests in the lounge and recreation room.  To the north, you can see the front of the palace and the front balcony.

name: Eastern Corridor
description: This corridor provides access to the front and rear of the palace for  maids and servants.  A short hallway to the west connects this corridor to the main corridor which is used by most of the guests to get to their quarters or the gaming lounge.

name: Western Corridor
description: The western corridor connects the front of the second floor to the rear of the palace.  It is used mostly by the servants and guards who patrol the area.  To the east is a small hallway that connects this corridor to the main hallway.

name: Guest Lounge
description: The lounge is primarily a private meeting room next to the guest  quarters.  The two doors to the south lead to individual guest rooms where the dignitaries and other people of importance can remain for the night.  Many visitors prefer to meet up here as the atmosphere is much more private.

name: Western Corridor
description: The western corridor runs (obviously) along the west side of the palace. There's relatively little going on here  the corridor's main use is for security.  You see a few guards wandering around making sure the area is secure.

name: Guest Quarters
description: This room provides a bed and all the necessities for a good night's rest.  The mages allow their most honored guests to remain here for the night with their hospitality.  The room is rather well furnished with gold and jewels all over the walls.

name: Guest Quarters
description: You are in the plush quarters of a visiting dignitary.  The mages allow certain people of importance to remain in these quarters for the night or for many days at a time while they discuss their negotiations.  The dignitaries come from all over.

name: Southern Access Hallway
description: This hallway is used mostly to deliver food and refreshments to the mages and dignitaries in the main dining hall.  To the southwest, you can head around the balcony circling the dining hall.  The passage is also used by the palace guards for security.

name: Dining Hall Accessway
description: The dining hall is some 15 feet below you, but you can see all the mages and dignitaries eating their dinner.  Across the hall to the east, you can see the other balcony.  You disappear behind a wall as you go to the northeast or southeast.

name: Dining Hall Accessway
description: The accessway is used primarily by the maids bringing down food for the dining hall, but you often see a few guards passing by making sure  everything is safe.  To the east, you see a stairway going down.

name: Dining Hall Accessway
description: There is a stairway here leading down to the accessway behind the dining hall on the first level.  You can see all the maids and servants rushing around to get dinner in on time.  There's nothing worse than an angry, hungry mage.

name: Dining Hall Accessway
description: You are in the small accessway leading around the main dining hall.  This is where the maids and servants go through to get from the kitchen to the rear of the hall where they serve dinner.  You can see through the balcony to the large dining hall.  Across the way to the west, you can see the other balcony.

name: Main Keslarian Library
description: This is the place where all the great spells of the mages are stored for safe keeping.  Many spells are one-of-a-kind and you can't even read the printing on the paper.  A number of potions are spilt on the ground leading you to believe that this place is also used as some sort of laboratory for mixing potions and other neat magical items.

name: Master Hallway
description: There is a stairwell leading back down to the second level of the palace.  You're not really sure you should be up here, but since there's no one else around, it couldn't hurt to look around.  You just have to watch out for the sorceress and the elusive Wizard of Keslar.

name: Master Hallway
description: To the north, you see a door labled "Wizard of Keslar".  The Wizard is an old mage who has obtained a level of magic which puts him near  immortality.  You had better think twice before going through that door.  The hallway continues to the east and west.

name: Master Hallway
description: The master hallway continues to the east and west.  To the south, there is a door labled "Sorceress".  Apperently, it must be where the  sorceress goes at the end of the day to relax.  There's a small  servant's hallway to the north that appears to go to a small, private kitchen on this floor.

name: Master Hallway
description: The hallway ends here at the private dining chamber, which is to the south.  The dining room is reserved for special guests of the palace and for the daily meals of the Wizard.  Being so old, the Wizard seldom leaves the upper level of the palace, even to eat.

name: Private Dining Hall
description: This dining hall is used primarily by the Wizard himself as he does not like moving up and down the stairs to get to the main dining hall. When important guests come, they are usually invited to stay and dine with him up here.

name: Sorceress' Chambers
description: Chances are, the sorceress doesn't like people rummaging through her chambers without her permission.  A number of palace guards are stationed around her chambers just in case someone should decide to try to  steal something from inside here.

name: Wizard's Chambers
description: You're really pressing your luck being in here.  Although the Wizard is an old man and will soon be succeeded by another, he is still quite powerful.  He utilizes magic almost endlessly and can cut down the mightiest warriors with but a mere flick of his wrists.

name: Kitchen Access Hallway
description: This hallway brings you around the rear of the kitchen for delivery of goods for preparation specifically for the Wizard and his esteemed guests.  Only the finest ingredients go towards making the Wizard's meals.  The hallway continues to the east.

name: Men's Restroom
description: As a matter of fact, there's nothing here in the way of plumbing, either. The room is quite bare except for a dark hole in the floor, and there's an awful smell coming from the hole.  The floor is wet where a few drunks have missed their opportunity, so it's a good thing you are wearing boots.

name: Women's Restroom
description: As a matter of fact, there's nothing here but a dark and smelly hole in the floor.  If you want to use it, you should also know there's no paper in  sight.  Maybe you can hold it a little longer, eh?

name: Dragon Tooth Inn Waste Treatment Tank
description: You didn't actually mean to come down here, did you?  You slipped, right? Oh, gawd, look what you are standing in up to your knees.  If you move, you  might slip and fall in up to your eyebrows, so be veerrryy careful!

name: Stairwell
description: This stairway brings you up to the third level of the Palace.  It is strictly forbidden by any outsiders except personal guests of the  Wizard himself.  The sorceress' chambers are also up here along with a training area for the higer level mages.

name: Outside Brownhaven Gate
description: A large gate, watched by guards leads into the town to the east, and the wide path continues westward toward Lake Kellevah.  You can see the masts of several ferry-boats even from here.

name: Kellevah Road
description: In the distance to the south is a vast farmland, farmed by several of the area's best farmers.  It appears that corn is being grown.

name: Kellevah Road
description: In the distance to the south is a vast farmland, farmed by several of the area's best farmers.  It appears that corn is being grown.

name: Kellevah Road
description: The sounds of town-life emanate from the east where the town of Brownhaven lies, nestled among the great mountains of Garadruin.

name: Path to the Lake
description: Only experienced players should proceed.

name: Hallway
description: There is an unbearable stench behind the door you see to the north.  The hallway you are in continues to the west.  You still haven't figured out exactly where you are.

name: Hallway
description: There is a door to the south.  By the looks of it, there appears to be a secret door into this hallway.  The door probably leads to some large hallway or room.  The hallway continues to the east.

name: Main Hallway
description: This main hallway leads directly into the Mausoleum of the Keslar clan, a family of great mages.  There is also another door to the south that is labeled 'Crypt'.  The door is of rusted iron and oak and looks like it has never been used.

name: Narrow Hallway
description: The hallway is rather long and extends to the north and south.  Every so often, you notice a number of guards walking by, but quickly hide in the shadows before they spot you.  There's another hallway breaking off from the main hall to to the south.

name: Entrance to Etolos
description: Etolos has been the historical gathering grounds for the great druids of the world.  The druids are mystical people who have mastered the art of divine thought and healing.  They pride themselves on their unwavering belief in nature and it's awesome power.  It is rumored that even the  grounds of Etolos hold mystical powers.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: The Druids of Etolos, only rumored to even exist, are all peace-loving humans who have obtained a spiritual awareness of their life and place in the world.  Etolos is a rather large area consisting of a number of concentric circles.  You also notice that all the druids are female and have pretty much ignored your existance here.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: As you roam around the forest, you can see a number of druids going about their everyday business.  It doesn't look like they do anything all day except study.  The druids are rumored to be experts at casting healing  spells.  In fact, they supposedly are the ones who created the mysterious philospher's stone.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: It's strange that the druid initiates seem to be of various strengths. The druid hierarchy consists of a number of initiate circles starting from one and going to eleven, after which one becomes a full druid.   You have to look at the druids before you consider attacking them.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: The striking beauty of the forest amazes you.  It is much better kept up than the dying forests near the mountains outside of the city.  All around you, you can see druid initiates studying their scrolls and  meditating silently under the trees and brooks.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: To the east, you can see the inner circle of Etolos.  Unfortunately, there doesn't appear to be a quick, easy path in.  There must be a secret entrance around here somewhere.  You have started to see more important druids in this circle, compared to those you've encountered in the outer circle.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: The trees in this forest seem to create a path that you can follow  around Etolos.  To the northeast, you can see one of the inner circles. Strangely enough, you don't see a lot of physical structures in the forest.  The population of druids, however, seems to increase the further east you head.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: You can see a number of higher level druids here working on perfecting their magical abilities.  Although they are not nearly as powerful as mages, they have been compared to clerics with their mystical ability to heal the wounded.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: This middle circle appears to continue around the entire forest.  The outer circle seems to end to the north at it hits a path heading in and out of the main circle.  There are a number of higher level druids meditating around the trees as you approach the center of the circle.

name: Outer Circle of Etolos
description: To the east, you can see the outer circle being absorbed in an arm extending in and out of the center of the circle.  Etolos is built in this fantastic forest that is rumored to have mystical healing powers. You can see a number of druids relaxing in the open fields to the east.

name: West Etolian Exercise Yard
description: In order to keep fit, both physically and mentally, most of the druids go to the exercise field to practice their various fighting exercises  and improve their physical skills.  The field is rather large and continues to the east.

name: Forest Brook
