description: The small brook does not really catch your attention until you step into the mud.  The brook is fairly well hidden under the brush and trees, but it manages to bring a lot of water into the forest of Etolos.  The brook heads off to the south through the inner circles of Etolos.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: The circle you are on continues to the east and west around the complex. You notice that the outer circle seems to disappear into the large field to the north, where you can see a lot of activity.  It looks somewhat like an exercise yard where the druids go to play games after a long day of studying and meditating.

name: East Etolian Exercise Yard
description: It looks like everyone around you is training for some sort of competition. The fighting the druids are doing is very precise, strongly resembling the martial arts.  Although they are not great fighters, they will offer some resistance if they are ever attacked.

name: Recreation Field
description: There's not a lot to see here.  The druids go about their games as if you did not even exist.  They seem to be playing some sort of variation of croquet.  It's quite boring to watch so you move on without taking much notice.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: You notice that this area of the dense forest is beginning to thin out a little the further east you go.  You can see a small brook bringing water out from the northwest.  To the southeast, you can see a number of druids farming a small garden.  The brook appears to act as an irrigation ditch, bringing water to the otherwise dry ground.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: Despite the primative nature of the druids, you sense that they are actually more civilized than the modern townsperson.  The peace and tranquility are resounded in the atmosphere of group participation and cooperation.  Outsiders have mocked the Etolian Druids because of these primative attitudes, but in fact, they have survived longer than any other human civilization in the world.

name: Meditation Area
description: You can see a number of druids meditating near the groves, by the small brook and under the trees.  Surprisingly, the druid community seems to enjoy their simple lifestyles of study and work, although you haven't seen many druids working.

name: Small Brook
description: This small brook must bring water dwon from the mountains.  It's not a very large brook, but it provides enough water for the druids to survive and grow their crops.  There appears to be a natural spring that is also bringing fresh water to the surface.

name: Middle Circle of Etolos
description: The path you are on continues around the complex.  As you head to the northeast, you notice the trees get sparcer and see a number of small gardens growing.  Since the druids are primarily vegetarians, they have no need for cattle or other grazing animals.

name: Meditation Area
description: You can see a number of druids meditating in the quiet atmosphere of the woods of Etolos.  To the south, you can see a spring bringing fresh water into the community.  The center of the circle is located to the north of the meditation area.

name: Natural Spring of Health
description: The fresh spring brings fresh water from the depths of the earth to the surface.  Perhaps like the rest of the forest, the water itself is  mystical as well.  You see a number of druids taking water from the spring and bringing it back towards the center of the circle.

name: Middle Circle/Garden
description: You have entered an area that appears to be reserved for gardening.   The druids survive solely on the food that they grow in their gardens, which appears to be quite large.  There is a small orchard to the  southeast where a number of large fruit trees are growing.

name: Middle Circle/Orchard
description: You are surrounded by the dense forest on the east side of the path, but in the immediate area, you can see numerous fruit trees of virtually every known fruit in existance.  A large ditch brings water from the west  into the orchard.  The trees appear to grow impressively large fruit, larger than most of the fruit you've ever seen.

name: Middle Circle/Garden
description: The garden, although small, appears to generate many vegetables of all different types from carrots to tomatoes.  The plants seem to be quite small but the vegetables they produce are surprisingly large.  The  tomatoes are about the size of grapefruits.

name: The Shrine of Honesty
description: You have come upon the sacred Shrine of Honesty.  The druids honor six basic virtues, and have built up a shrine for each of them.  This one signifies honesty and the importance of honesty in the daily dealings of life.  Without honesty, the world would be thrust into chaos and honor would have no value.

name: Rose Orchard
description: The rose bushes are not really aligned in any real order, but rather seem to have natually grown in.  The druids have kept the rose bushes as they are, rather than uproot them and organize them.  It gives the area a sense of wilderness combined with nature's beauty.

name: The Shrine of Truth
description: The druids believe strongly in six basic virtues, and have built up a shrine in dedication of each.  The Shrine of Truth is dedicated (quite obviously) to truth.  Withouth truth, there would be no honesty and no honor.  The druids hold truth as one of their most important virtues.

name: Briar Bushes
description: This is by far not one of the best places to visit.  There are many  thorny briar bushes everywhere and they seem to be cutting you up.  The forest to the east blocks any plans you might have about leaving Etolos from any direction other than the way you came in.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: The inner circle is forbidden, even to most druids.  Only druids of the fifth circle and above may enter.  Outsiders are not at all allowed  near the inner circle, and you being here has alarmed and shocked the druid community.  You had better leave now before the guards come and force you to leave.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: The inner circle is really not at all like the outer circles of Etolos. There is much less activity here.  Most of the druids are meditating or studying under trees.  The entire area is surrounded by rose and  briar bushes, making it virtually impossible to get out of the center circle.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: The inner circle has been forbidden to any non-druids by the declaration of the Great Druid.  You see a number of druids here, meditating quietly around the trees.  Most don't really mind that you are here, except for a few guards who will try to force you out.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: You're pressing your luck being here, but it is an interesting place to look around in.  The druids are known for their hospitality, but strictly forbid anyone entering the center circle, reserved for only druids.  You see a number of high ranking druids present as you walk around the circle.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: The inner circle appears to be surrounded by rose and briar bushes, making it almost impossible to leave the area.  Somehow or another, you managed to find your way into the inner circle, so there must obviously be some way out.  You can tell the druids are not particularly happy about you being here.

name: Inner Circle of Etolos
description: With the exception of a few guards passing you by, you notice that the center of the druid community is quite tranquil.  There was much more activity in the outer circles  however, you notice that there are a lot more higher level, more powerful druids roaming around.  Most are just meditating, and quite obviously would not enjoy being disturbed.

name: Shrine of the Great Druid
description: If being in the center circle of Etolos was not enough, now you've gone and invaded the private realm of the Great Druid herself.  It is well known that the Great Druid does not ever leave this shrine and strictly forbids anyone to enter without prior expressed permission by one of the arch druids.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: The large trees will support a number of people by themselves, but the druids have laid planks along the trees to allow easy access to the  area.  It is up here in the trees that the druids and archdruids meet to talk about what is best for their society.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: This is a rather common place for the higher level druids to meditate and take in all that nature has to offer.  The druids take care of nature and in turn, nature takes care of them.  The trees around the inner  circle of Etolos are very tall and strong, being able to support many people on their limbs.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: The trees are always a source of pure power and knowledge, given to the druids by the sun goddess.  Without the trees, there would be no life on the planet.  The druids therefore take great care of the trees, plants and other shrubs in the small area of land they inhabit.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: It's probably not a good idea for you to be up here.  After all, only the most powerful druids in the hierarchy are even allowed up here.  There are a number of guards that are always on patrol looking for intruders like you sitting up in the trees.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: You can see the layout of the entire Etolian Forest from this point, and are completely amazed at the symmetry of the paths in the forest.  Up in the tree, you can see a number of things, including a good number of higher leveled druids meditating in the warmth of the sun, and the druidian guards, who would like to throw you off the trees.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: High up above the inner circle of the Etolian culture, you find yourself in a predicament.  The further inward you get, the more druidian guards come out.  Yet curiosity has been cursed upon you.  The planks in the trees have been set up by the druids to allow easy travelling between the tall tress in the forest.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: Being up so close to the clouds has a very powerful effect on you.  The majesty of the druidian forest and the peace they have with nature is quite astounding.  Most people just ridicule the druidian clans, but these clans have survived longer than any other civilization in the history of the world.

name: Trees Above Etolos
description: The trees are packed so close together that it is relatively easy to walk between the trees.  But there's always the chance that you might slip and fall down.  The druids have made almost a second home up here, setting up planks of wood along the tree's branches to make walking around much easier.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive runs in between the Necropolis on the north side of the road and the Estate of Natasha de Allisk on the south side.  It is  rumored that the Manor is still haunted by old ghosts and the previous owner of the mansion.  It is also rumored that Natasha herself still roams the halls.

name: Overland Drive
description: The large Necropolis on the north is guarded by a wall of cast-iron bars that prevent looters and other grave robbers from entering the Necropolis at night and defiling the gravesites.  On the south, you can see the  mysterious Mausoleum on the Allisk Manor grounds.  This is rumored to be Natasha's final resting location.

name: Overland Drive
description: Natasha de Allisk came to Oceancrest many centuries ago, and was at the time rumored to be a vampire.  This was soon proved to be true as many children and women mysteriously disappeared and were found on the Allisk Estate.  Unfortunately, Natasha had "died" and no one could do anything about it.  It was later figured out that she was in fact a vampire and was merely hibernating once her cover was blown.  No one has since tried to enter the Manor and Natasha has not been seen for ages.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive takes a funny turn towards the southeast here.  The Necropolis continues along the north side of the road, even past the turn.  You can now see the large Manor of Natasha de Allisk to the south.  There are two large gates located to the southeast of here that appear to lead into the Manor.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive passes by the entrance to the Allisk Manor here and  continues to the northwest and southeast.  The gates have been locked for ages and no one knows how to get in, not that anyone has really tried, nor wanted to enter this place.  It has been rumored to be  haunted by every known spirit that was ever believed not to exist in the world.

name: Overland Drive
description: It has been long rumored that Natasha de Allisk was indeed a vampire,  and that she comes out some nights when the weather is just right to pick up little children and take then away to drink their blood.  At least, this is what parents like to tell their children who stay out late at night, regardless of what their parents say.

name: Overland Drive
description: You can make out the Allisk Manor to the west of here.  The entrance  appears to be at the two large gates a little ways to the northwest. On the northeast side of the road, you can see the southern borders of the Necropolis.  The Necropolis is protected by a wall of iron bars preventing people from entering the facility without going  through the proper channels.

name: Overland Drive/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Hillcrest Drive has the reputation of forming the southern borders of both the Necropolis and the Manor of Natasha de Allisk.  Of course this isn't as bad as being the road going between the two deathly areas, as  Overland Drive does.  Overland Drive runs northwest and south out of  this intersection, while Hillcrest continues to the east and west.

name: Overland Drive
description: The Chateau Richland Grape Orchard is well known for their finely  fermented wines and juices, bottled yearly just days after the grapes are harvested.  The Chateau is always looking for cheap, inexperienced labor to do work clearing the fields of vermin and other disease-ridden pests that might destroy the grapes.

name: Overland Drive
description: The Circle-Bar Ranch House provides much of the meat and meat by-products that are consumed by the citizens of Oceancrest.  Many of the best butchers have at one time worked for the Circle-Bar Ranch, preparing the cattle for consumption.  The Cattle Ranch is located west of the Ranch House.  The Chateau Richland Grape Orchard is located to the east.

name: Overland Drive
description: Overland Drive intersects Nagaritha Drive a little way to the south.  On the east side of the road, you can see the vast Chateau Richland Grape Orchard.  The west side of the road is dominated by the Circle-Bar Ranch House and the Cattle Ranch, where most of the cattle in Oceancrest are raised and slaughtered.

name: Overland Drive
description: Loud noises and laughter echo out of Thackery's Pub, located on the west side of the road.  Although a bit run down and cockroach infested, it is very popular amongst the poorer classes in town, and many farm workers in the area like to gather there.  The food might be bad, but the wine is excellent and the people make the atmosphere festive.

name: Overland Drive/Appleton Road Intersection
description: Appleton Road runs diagonally through the southern portion of town and crosses Overland Drive, running north and south from here.  On the west side of the intersection, you can see the Klondike Wheat Fields where wheat and grain is harvested for the town.  On the east side of the  road are a number of small shops, but not accessible from here.

name: Overland Drive
description: The reason there are not more diagonally running roads in town is because they create useless slivers of land that no one in their right minds would want to develop.  Such is the case with the sliver of land created by the crossing of Appleton Road, Overland Drive and Waterfront Way.  A small  monument has been placed in the sliver of land on the east.  The Klondike Wheat Fields are located to the west, the entrance to which is located  along Lankshire Drive on the west side of the fields.

name: Overland Drive/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Overland Drive, running north and south, intersects Waterfront Way, running east and west from here.  Overland Drive heads north towards the Necropolis and eventually runs between the Necropolis and the eerie Manor of Natasha de Allisk.

name: Overland Drive
description: Understanding the need for the farmers of the lands to have a private residence just like everyone else in town, a small community has been set up on both sides of Overland Drive for them.  The community is rather small, but is close to the farming areas and relatively inexpensive to maintain.

name: Overland Drive
description: Although there is not much to see around here, the rural atmosphere of the region is pleasant if not relaxing.  To the south, you can see the extend of the city's boundaries.  The large City Wall looms to the  south of Golden Dolphin Way.  Oceancrest is surrounded by a large City Wall to protect the citizens from both internal and external threats.

name: Overland Drive/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Overland Drive heads off to the north, eventually turning to the west as it reaches the Necropolis and the Manor of Natasha de Allisk, two of the most frightening places in Oceancrest.  Golden Dolphin way runs east and west, running parallel to the large City Walls that protect the city from threats of attack by orcs and other barbarians.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: A large intersection to the west joing Hillcrest Drive, Eidenhoft  Boulevard and Marina Way.  The small sliver of land formed by Eidenhoft Boulevard as it runs off to the northeast is owned by the Odgen Family and is used to display their famous statues for the public's admiration. On the south, you can see the large Regalia Convent.  The entrance to the Convent is located off of Marina Way.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The large Regalia Convent looms on the south side of the road, almost looking like a giant slab of marble with a few giant statues sticking  out from its sides.  The large Odgen Family Villa is located on the  north of the road.  The Odgen Family has been in Oceancrest for a long time, but is not quite as wealthy as they would like to have people believe.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Odgen House is located on the north side of the road and is one of the older family houses in the city.  On the south side of the road, you can see the Regalia Convent building.  It is a large, white building  with many statues and other marble sculptures to scare away the evil spirits that may accompany the people of the wrong faith.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: On the south side of the road, you can see the magnificent Regalia Convent, known not really for the word that they spread, but the philosophy of an monotheistic deity, which is usually considered blasphemous by literally every major religion in Oceancrest, including some of the orc and  bugbear religions, which are also outcasted among the holy order of  sacred, acceptable religions.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The large Iilandi Family Estate and Mansion can be seen to the north of Hillcrest Drive.  The Iilandi Family owns much of the producing land in Oceancrest including the Richland Orchard and the Klondike Wheat Fields. They also hold some stock in some of the smaller productions in town, as well as some political offices here and there.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The outer yard of the Regalia Convent lies to the south of Hillcrest  Drive, surrounded by a white fence of wood.  Looking over the fence, you can see a large, grassy yard where a number of nuns and other  religious figures are walking about the yard enjoying the day's sun. The entrance to the Regalia Convent is located to the west off of Marina Way.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: Oddly enough, there's a large, white gazebo located more or less in the middle of no where on the south of Hillcrest Drive.  It doesn't seem to have a purpose there, but stands between Hillcrest and Regalia Way, which runs southwest out of Allisk Circle.  Allisk Circle is located  to the east of here, intersecting with Lankshire, Appleton, Regalia and Hillcrest Roads.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Allisk Circle is a moderate-sized traffic circle around which three roads intersect.  Hillcrest Drive runs east and west.  Lankshire Parkway runs north and south, and Appleton Road runs to the southeast.  On the north side of the road you can see the dreaded Allisk Manor.  On the  south, you can see the western corner of the Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The large cattle ranch to the south provides much of the meat required by a city the size of Oceancrest.  The cattle are raised on the ranch to the south and then brought over to the Slaughterhouse across the street to be humanely destroyed and then packaged for consumption.  The farmers are always in need of a few more cattle slaughterers at the Slaughterhouse off of Appleton Road, but do not approve of killing their cattle on the ranch.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The large cattle ranch survives relatively well, considering the fact that it lies only a few yards away from the Allisk Manor.  Not being one for superstition, the cattle ranchers usually ignore the idle threats and curses the other ranchers sling at them for being so relaxed in their defenses.  Nonetheless, they alway have a few cloves of garlic on hand just in case.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: Natasha de Allisk is thought to be one of the last remaining vampires in Oceancrest, most of the others being vanquished some decades ago by some overly pompus paladins who didn't like the way the vampires were killing the children.  Natasha escaped capture by putting a curse on her Mansion making it nearly impossible to reach her.  She also built the Allisk  Labyrinth to provide an accessible escape for her vampire brothers and sisters.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Circle-Bar Ranch is a large cattle ranch where cows are raised and then slaughtered for their meat.  Being a very precious commodity, the cows are guarded very carefully by the cattle ranchers and dangerous ranch dogs.  The intersection with Overland Drive lies to the east.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Richland Grape Orchard, owned by the Iilandi Family, grows the finest and tastiest grapes in all the lands.  The grapes are harvested and  fermented into the finest wines, distributed throughout Oceancrest and often exported in exchange for other needed goods.  The Richland Bordeaux wines often command quite a price.

name: Amberton Lane/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Amberton Lane heads to the north from this intersection, interrupted a brief distance to the north by the Keslar Mountain, which seems to have absorbed the road.  It does connect with Monument Avenue before it ends, though.  The large Chateau Richland Wine Orchard to the south smells deliciously of ripening grapes as the sweet smell of fermenting wine  comes from the northeast.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The vast Chateau Richland Orchard stretches out for a number of acres to the south, covered with lines of grape vines.  The Richland Orchard is always looking for unskilled labor to harvest some of their crops and scare off pests that come into the orchard looking for food.  The Winery is located to the north, where the grapes are pressed and fermented.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Chateau Richland Winery is located to the north and the Chateau  Richland Grape Orchard is located to the south.  This convinience lowers the cost of transportation and other nasty overheads to provide their customers with the finest wines at the lowest cost.  The Richland  Winery produces one of the best Bordeaux wines in the land.

name: Leviathan Drive/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Hillcrest Drive, running east to west, intersects Leviathan Drive, running north and south.  Hillcrest Drive is one of the longer roads in town, running from the east city walls to the west city walls without being detoured or interrupted.  Similarly, Leviathan Drive spans the city from north to south city walls.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: A large mountain of dirt has strangely risen on the west side of the  road, where the Keslar Palace stands.  The sheer cliffs which run up the virtually impossible mountain prevent people from entering the  Palace except through the proper route.  On the west is a large black- smith's shop and a couple of other smaller shops.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The strangely created mountain on top which Keslar Palace stands has long been covered in mystery.  The high and mighty wizards under the great archmage Keslar established the Palace some centuries ago by combining their powers to build themselves an impenitrable mountain fortress.  On the east side of the road is a large weapons and armor center, but geared towards the less wealthy people.  The entrance to the center is located off of Monument Avenue or Kafkan Way.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The large shopping center on the east caters to the less wealthy  people in town who need some light protection without having to pay an arm and a leg for armor they don't need.  Catherine's Weapons Shop provides adventurers with light weapons to handle themselves on the some of the more dangerous streets at night.

name: Leviathan Drive/Monument Avenue Intersection
description: This rather busy intersection forms the southeastern border of the Keslar Mountain, which was built artificially by the Keslarian Mages as a show of their powers.  On the southeastern corner of the intersection is the Holy Order of the White Rose, where young Paladins go to get their basic training and skills.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Oceancrest is kind of divided into a number of major sections.  You are in the southeastern section of town, which is primarily a residental sector.  There are a number of general purpose stores and small pubs  for the average citizens in this area.  On the east side of the road, you can see the Order of the White Rose building where Paladins go to get their basic training skills.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Leviathan Drive continues to the north and south, being one of the only roads in town that you can travel on and get from the north to the south city walls without leaving the road.  On the east, you can see the Holy Order of the White Rose, the entrance to which is located to the north. On the west side of the road is the Chateau Richland Winery, where all varieties of wines may be purchased.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The large Chateau Richland Grape Orchard to the west provides much of  the refreshments in the means of wine and juice to the city.  The Chateau produces the finest Bordeaux wines in the land, and a bottle can run upwards of two or three gold pieces.  You can hear some light cheering from the inside of the Melbourne Entertainment Arena, to the east.  The entrance to the Arena is located off of Nagaritha Drive, to the south.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Melbourne Arena is a small entertainment facility where common people can go and fight the dregs of society.  Most often, thieves and assassins are thrown to the masses where they are trampled, stomped, stoned and  otherwise mutilated to a pulp until they're dead, and then stompted on some more.  It is an interesting challenge for less skilled adventurers, but not much of a challenge for more powerful ones.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Leviathan Drive intersects with Nagaritha Drive to the south.  On the western side of the road, you can see the Chateau Richland Grape Orchard and a path leading to a grove of trees in the fields.  On the east you can see and hear the crowd in the Melbourne Arena where thieves and pick- pockets are thrown to the gladiators.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Shrine of Victory is more of a superstitious holy point where many fighters converge before going into some large battle where perhaps the odds are that they will not come back.  In fact, it has worked often, so many fighters still do come to the Shrine of Victory because every little bit hurts and you can't really argue with divine intervention.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The trading center on the east side of the road appears to be a small  armory and a medical supply shop where you can tend to your wounds.  On the west side of the road, you can see another, larger center where much of the food that is supplied by the Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch and the various fields are processed and made available to the public.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: Leviathan Drive intersects Waterfront Way to the south.  A large building on the west side of the road reads "Iila's Cocking Herbs" where a number of light herbs and spices may be purchased, including a number of rarer spices that you might not find elsewhere.

name: Leviathan Drive/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive, which runs north and south, intersects Waterfront Way, running east to west here.  The Dentra Central Archery Range, one of the finest in the lands, is located on the southeastern corner of the  intersection, where you can find a number of sharpshooting archers as well as some fletchers and shops to add to your collection of fine bows.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range is one of the finest ranges in Oceancrest, not to mention the world.  The Range is divided into two sections for  optimal usage.  As many of the archer enjoy wagering on shots, the eastern section of the Range is used primarily by the marksman archers.  The western section of the Range may be used by walk-ons and other, less able archers that just want some practice.

name: Leviathan Drive
description: You are just north of Golden Dolphin Way, the road which marks the southern boundary of the city.  The large City Walls protect the people from  invading forces, but also help in law enforcement, as it is very hard, if not impossible to scale the walls from either side without being  noticed from a distance.

name: Leviathan Drive/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Leviathan Drive heads off to the north from here, and continues uninterrupted until it reaches the northern City Walls, many miles to the north.  Golden Dolphin Way marks the southern edge of the City of Oceancrest, running parallel to the great City Walls, which enclose  the entire city.

name: Monument Avenue
description: Monument Avenue barely survived the creation of Keslar Mountain, which was created some centuries ago when the Mages of Keslar decided that a mountain would look nice here.  High on top of the mountain is the Palace where many of the mages still reside.  There is a spooky path up to the Palace on the other side, off of Kafkan Way.

name: Monument Avenue
description: The Chateau Richland Winery is divided into three major sections, the front entrance, the winery itself and the fermenting buildings.  All are within the same city block, with the Grape Orchard on the other side of the road.  The full-bodied wines the Chateau Richland Winery makes  usually sell for much more than most people can make in a week.

name: Amberton Lane/Monument Avenue Intersection
description: Amberton Lane was not so lucky when the mages of Keslar decided that  this would be a good place to put a mountain, and subsequently destroyed a portion of Amberton Lane.  In order to continue on Amberton Lane, you must go east on Monument and then head north on Levaithan.  You may then take any western-heading road back to Amberton.

name: Amberton Lane
description: As the grapes in the Chateau Richland Winery are pressed and bottled, it gives off a distinct aroma, bringing out the most disorientated drunk. The smell of the grapes fermenting in the building to the east is also very fragrant.  The large mountain to the north was created by the  Keslarian Mages some centuries ago, and appears to have destroyed part of Amberton Road.

name: Amberton Lane
description: The Chateau Richland Grape Orchards lie to the south of Hillcrest Drive, located to the south of here.  The large grape orchard supplies nearly all of the grapes used in making the Chateau Richland Wines and other natural drinks.  Chateau Richland is well known throughout the land as being one of the finest producers of wine in the world.

name: Regalia Way
description: The large Regalia Convent is noted most for being a monotheistic religion.  Although they claim to be significantly superior to the other polytheistic religions which dominate the land, they have yet to be fully recognized.  Most of the theories they teach are so ludicrous that most people don't even take them seriously.

name: Regalia Way
description: On the east side of the road, you can see Maria's Market, a small grocery store which caters to the lower, working classes, providing meat and vegetables from the various small farms both inside and outside of Oceancrest.  The Convent is located on the western side of the road.

name: Regalia Way
description: Regalia Way runs along the eastern border of the Regalia Convent, an order of women following a monotheistic approach to religion.  Their  mythos claim that only one god exists, which is omnipotent.  By putting the fear of God into their subjects, they can manipulate them as they please in order to get whatever they desire.  The fanciest buildings, ironically, are the churches, which supposedly use their alms to help the poor.

name: Regalia Way
description: Maria's Market is a small, outdoor marketplace where some goods may be purchased.  Much of the fruits and vegetables are not grown in Oceancrest and need to be imported.  However, most of the grain and corn comes from inside the city.  Maria's Market provides a little bit of diversity for the the citizens' diets.

name: Regalia Way
description: You can see the odd Allisk Circle to the northeast.  A strange feeling comes over you as you stare in that direction, almost as if you were  being watched.  The Allisk Manor extends as far as the Allisk Circle. Both Lankshire Parkway and Hillcrest Drive form the Manor's deathly  boundaries.

name: Appleton Road
description: Appleton Road runs diagonally through the southern edge of town, passing between the Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch and the Slaughterhouse.  It continues southeast until it reaches the southern City Walls at Golden Dolphin Way. To the northwest, you can see the Allisk Circle, one of the centers of unnatural activity in Oceancrest.

name: Appleton Road
description: The Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch is located to the east of the road where the cattle are born, fed and nurtured, and then shipped across Appleton Road to the Slaughterhouse where they are humanely destroyed and sold to the civilians as meat for their daily diets.  The large number of cattle that go through the Slaughterhouse daily leaves a nice river of blood running down Appleton Road.

name: Appleton Road
description: Appleton is one of the strange, diagonal roads which travels northwest  and southeast from here.  To the northwest, Appleton Road heads towards the Allisk Circle.  Appleton heads southeast towards the city walls in the southeastern quadrant of town.  Between the road is the Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch and the Slaughterhouse.  There is a small trickle of blood running out from the Slaughterhouse on the west side of the road.

name: Appleton Road
description: The Circle-Bar Cattle Ranch furnishes Oceancrest with much of the fresh, domesticated meat to its citizens.  The cattle are born and raised on the Ranch and then herded to the Slaughterhouse, located on the west side of the road.  The Circle-Bar Ranch gladly accepts help from any outsiders that might want to help slaughtering the cows as most people pass out from all the blood and stench.

name: Appleton Road
description: Appleton runs northwest to southeast through the southern section of town.  On the east side of the road, you can partially see the Circle- Bar Ranch House and the Cattle Ranch, where hundreds of cows must be grazing.  On the west side of the road is the Slaughterhouse and the Preservation Center, where the cattle are humanely destroyed and then brought to town to be sold.

name: Appleton Road
description: You can see the thin, mesh-wire fence which protects the large Klondike Wheat Fields on the west side of the road.  There is no entrance to the  Fields from this side of the road.  The only entrance is located on the western edge of the Wheat Fields off of Lankshire Parkway.  On the east side of the road, you can see a small inn and tavern where a number of people are wandering in and out.  The entrance to the inn is located off of Nagaritha Drive.

name: Appleton Road
description: One of the few roads in Oceancrest that run diagonally through the town is Appleton Road, which were created more or less for convinience before the city planners decided to limit and prevent the further development of skewed roads that deviated from the strict, grid-like pattern of the  city's roads.

name: Appleton Road
description: One of the reasons there aren't more diagonally running roads in Oceancrest is because of the useless land they create.  There is a small, triangular sliver of land between Appleton, Waterfront and Overland, which is more or less undevelopable.  A couple of small monuments have been put up in dedicated to the farmers, but nothing else really can fit there.

name: Appleton Road
description: Small, individual houses, a rarity in Oceancrest, lie on the west side of the diagonally running road.  These houses are provided for by the city for the numerous farmers that live in the area and work the fields.   Although there is not really a lack of regular housing in the city, the residences are quite a distance from the fields.

name: Appleton Road
description: You can see the intersection with Golden Dolphin Way to the southeast, and the City Walls which surround the city just to the south of the street.   A large number of small houses are located on the west side of the street where the various farmers and their families live.  These houses provide the quickest access to the various fields in this area of town.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The large shopping complex on the north side of the road provides much of the fresh meats and grains to the town.  There are also a couple of  preservative shops to keep the meat fresh while being stored for long periods of time.  Iila runs the preservatives shops on this side of the center.  To the north is Iila's Fresh Cooking Herbs shop.  Further to the west is her Salts and Preservatives shop.

name: Waterfront Way
description: Food storage is a very important part of today's society, as who knows when a famine can strike.  However, most perishable goods don't last for more than a couple of days.  When you by some meat, you usually have to buy the whole cow, and a whole cow can last a family for months.  Therefore, the quick solution may be found at Iila's, who specializes in long-term food storage.

name: Appleton Road/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: You are in a relatively minor intersection as Appleton Road is usually not a very traveled road.  Appleton Road continues in a diagonal path to the southeast towards Golden Dolphin Way.  Waterfront Way runs east and west from one end of town to the other.

name: Waterfront Way
description: There is not much on this side of the town.  On the south side of the road, you can see a number of small houses where the farmers and their families live.  The proximity of the farm lands and fields in the southern part of town makes their lives much simpler.  The intersection with  Overland Drive lies to the west.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The Farmers, being one of the most powerful lobbying groups, somehow got the city to allow them to build their own, individual houses near the farm lands.  On the north side of the road is the Klondike Wheat Fields, where the wheat and grain for the entire city is grown.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The vast wheat fields continue on for miles in apparently all directions on the north side of the road.  The wheat is used by many of the local bakeries to bake fresh breads and pasteries.  Luckily, Oceancrest grows so much wheat, there is seldom ever a shortage.  Most of the excess grain gets stored away in the silos, but some is exported out of the city to other less fortunate cities.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The vast wheat fields seem to extend for miles to the east and west.  On the southern side of the road, you can see some of the individual houses used by the farmers and their families.  The personal residences are unique because they are separated  most housing in the city is communal due to  the lack of space for individual houses.  However, the communal housing is relatively spacious, so there isn't much complaining.

name: Waterfront Way
description: As with most farmers in modern societies, the farmers must form a sort of union where they can fight for their rights as a single entity instead of just a number of whining peasants.  The Federation Building located to the south provides a meeting place for such events.  The Klondike Wheat Fields are located to the north of the road.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The large Grainery and equally impressive silos on the south side of the road store the year's crops for the devastating winter months.  Although Oceancrest is close to the ocean, winter months can bring on some snow. Nevertheless, it gets quite cold out and crops just don't grow when the water doesn't even flow.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The Klondike Wheat Fields produce more wheat and grain than one can comfortably imagine.  Most of the grain is eventually stored in the graineries and silos on the south side of the street.  The Wheat Fields may be entered from the west side off of Lankshire Parkway.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The DeNail Corn Fields provide much of the corn required by many of the ranches for their herds, as well as for public consumption.  Corn is one of the more basic commodities of the town, and such as it is, it usually fetches a high price.  The Oceancrest Stables and Walking Yards are  located on the south side of the street.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The Oceancrest Walking Yards and Stables are provided as a convenience  to guests and vistors when they bring in steeds.  Although horses are allowed on the street, this tends to be very dangerous as they do tend to scare easily.  The Stables and Walking Yards provide a safe and  protective environment for your trusty steed.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The large corn fields cover most of the northern landscape that you see before you.  The Fields provide corn for all the agricultural and civilian needs year round.  The excess corn is stored in silos to the east, south of the Klondike Wheat Fields.  The Oceancrest Stables are located to the south where you can leave your steeds and walk around town freely.

name: Waterfront Way
description: There is a small post office located on the southern side of Waterfront Way where you can send mail to friends and relatives without actually having to leave the town.  On the north side of the road are the DeNail Corn Fields, where, quite obviously, corn is grown in massive quantities. Waterfront Way continues to the east and west.

name: Waterfront Way
description: A small road called Hafnia Way intersects Waterfront Way to the west.   The large Corn Fields are starting to wind down, leading into the more  commercial areas of town to the west.  On the south are the Visitor's Stables, where horses may be left in comfort while you travel through town.  It is not always wise to have horses wondering through town, as it is both a risk to the people and to the horses.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: Golden Dolphin Way runs parallel to the Southern City Walls through most of the southern part of the city.  On the north side of the road, you can see the visitor's stables, where short-time visitors may leave their steeds, and walk around town without having to worry about where their horses are or what havoc they're getting into.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The omnimous City Walls rise up nearly ten meters, preventing just about any attack from the outside regions.  Oceancrest has had a long history of wars and sieges, which is the primary reason the walls were built. As an additional benefit, it also serves as an ideal law-enforcement  agent, preventing wanted criminals from fleeing the town.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Oceancrest Stable and Walking Yards are located on the north side of the road and provide long-term services to visitors and guests that come to Oceancrest on horseback.  Horses are allowed in town, but they are dangerous both to the themselves and the citizens walking along the streets. It doesn't take that much to scare a horse.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Oceancrest Stables and Walking Yards are to the north of Golden  Dolphin Way, providing very luxurious accomodations for long term visitors of Oceancrest.  The Walking Yard allows horses to get their daily exercise without having to take them out into the fields or out of town.  There is not a lot of walking space along the streets with all the other pedestrian traffic.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: You can see the intersection with Lankshire Parkway ahead to the east.   The large Oceancrest Stables and Walking Yards are located on the north side of the road, and the looming City Walls surround the southern side of the road.  Golden Dolphin Way continues to the east and west, literally from one end of the city to the other.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the numerous silos used by the farmers to store the corn and wheat for the dangerous winter months when literally nothing is growing.  Careful planning prevents famines and starvation even under the worse conditions.  Although Oceancrest  borders an ocean, it is far enough north that all the air that gets  brought down this far is very cold.  It is not uncommon for temperatures to go below zero.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: There are a total of three silos on this side of the road, and one grainery to the north of those.  The large silos store enough corn and wheat to maintain the city for more than six months without replenishing. Excess wheat and corn can then be exported out of the city to less fortunate cities that are not so self-sufficient.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The vast City Walls have been the protectors of Oceancrest for as long as anyone can remember.  On the north side of the road, you can see the Farmer's Federation Building, where the farmers all gather to discuss local politics and how it will adversly affect their well-being. The farmer's lobby is one of the most powerful political units in  Oceancrest and should not be taken lightly.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: With the exception of the massive City Walls on the southern side of the street, there isn't much to actually look at in this part of the town.   On the north side of the street are the small houses of the farmers and their families.  These were built more or less because the residential buildings were too far away and the farmers enjoy complaining to the city government.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: Small residences have been built on the north side of the road to support the rural farmers and their families.  These small houses allow the  farmers never to be too far way from their farms in case of emergencies, since the regular city residences are located a few miles to the east or north, towards the center of town.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The intersection with Overland Drive lies to the east.  Overland Drive is one of the long roads which runs directly past the Necropolis and the Manor of Natasha de Allisk.  Golden Dolphin Way continues to the east and west, with the large, South City Walls running parallel to the road.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: Overland Drive intersects Golden Dolphin Way to the west.  The City Wall is still visible (as if you could miss it) on the south side of the  road.  On the north side of the road are the numerous, individual houses of the farmers and their families.  The individual houses were built to provide easier access to the farms, where they would be working.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: Not wanting to be like the rest of the community, the farmers decided  that they would build themselves separated houses, instead of those community housing facilities.  With the lack of space in the center of the city, individual houses could not be build.  If people wanted to live in the city, then they would have to live in the community housing facilities.  They could always build a house outside the city walls, though.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see a number of small houses used by the farmers and their families.  Since the regular houses are so far away from the farms, the farmer's federation demanded that special houses be provided for the farmers.  This would increase productivity and make everyone's lives much better.  And so it was done because the farmer's lobby is one of the largest political lobby groups in the city, and holds more power than even the government.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The omnimous City Walls lie directly to the south of you.  They must be nearly ten meters high, if not more.  The walls were built ages ago and have proved their worth many times.  In addition to keeping invaders out, they have also been proven to keep thieves and other vermin in, making them easier to capture.  It is almost impossible to scale the  City Wall from either side.

name: Marina Way
description: On the west side of the street is the Leviathan Small Boat Rental offfice. Many people in the city of Oceancrest believe the business is just a front for a gang of retired pirates, now in the smuggling trade, but since they always pay their taxes and goods can be purchased in there for a fraction of their true costs, no one ever complains.  Small shops are to the east.

name: Marina Way
description: The Adrilite Museum of Natural History lies directly to the west, but has been undergoing extensive remodeling.  Visitors wishing to see artifacts and historical memorbilia may wish to visit the wonderful museums located in adjacent cities.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: On the east side of the road is the Oceancrest Mountaineer's Supply, a store specializing in climbing equipment.  On the west side of the street is Lafyette's Blacksmith and Repair shop.  Lafyette works mostly on weapons and armor, rather than other items, and is a congenial giant of a man.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: The Dragon's Claw Tavern and Grill is a sophisticated restaurant where  patrons may eat at the grill and drink some good, old-fashoioned ale in the company of friends.  The entrance to the restaurant is located to the south along Melbourne Drive, which runs north and south from here.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: It is very important to keep the city clean.  In order to get people to help out with this, the city pays its citizens one gold piece for all the litter they pick up and deposit in the Trash Recycling Facility.  On the east side of the road is the Dragon's Claw Tavern and Grill.  This bar is much more sophisticated than the Chug-A-Lug, as people usually head to the Grill to have a good meal instead of drinking like a fish.

name: Melbourne Avenue/Monument Avenue Intersection
description: The great Allakaren Circle lies to the east along Monument Avenue.  The Circle hold the strange, Tree of Life, that has been in existance for as long as anyone can remember.  Allakaren Circle is named after the  Allakaren Pyramid, both of which have withstood the tests of time.  On  all sides of the road, there are a number of small shops and other  facilities to pass the time.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: The Chug-A-Lug is a popular hang out for students, drunks, vagrants and just about anyone else who lives in this area of town.  Ironically, the pub probably does more business than any other store or shop in the area.  On the west side of the road is Roman Iron Works, where a number of light, iron weapons may be purchased.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: Imeldia provides a number of strange and unusual potions to the consumers. Unfortunately, not all of them are useful and some may actually be dangerous to drink.  Not being a very good alchemist, Imeldia does not know, nor  really cares what she sells.  On the east side of the road is the Chug-A- Lug Pub, a downright rowdy local tavern where just about anything can  happen.

name: Melbourne Avenue/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Melbourne Avenue, running north and south, runs through most of the town's major shopping centers and also passes by the Melbourne Entertainment Arena, located on the southwest corner of the intersection.  Hillcrest Drive runs east and west, spanning most of the southern section of Oceancrest and  passing through the large farm areas to the west.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: You can hear cheers and general screaming coming from the west in the  Melbourne Entertainment Arena.  The entrance to the arena is located on the south of the facility off of Nagaritha Drive.  On the east side of the road, you can see the Generic Clerical Supplies shop, providing clerics with a number of useful items like crucifixes, holy water and other  essentials of clerical life.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: Melbourne Avenue is one of the most popular streets in Oceancrest because it runs past all the various shops and facilities located in the south- eastern section of town.  On the east, you can see the Royal Jousting Supplies shop where a number of polearms and other jousting weapons may  be purchased for general use or training.  Since this is the poorer  section of town, you can't expect much here to be of that great of quality.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: The entrance to the Melbourne Entertainment Arena is located on the  south side of the facility off of Nagaritha Drive.  On the east side of the road, you can see The Healing Hand, a small-time hospital facility that aids the physically injured in any way they can.  Melbourne Avenue continues through the southeastern portion of town to the north and south.

name: Melbourne Avenue/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: This rather busy intersection is more or less the center of activity for  the southeastern section of town.  On the northwest corner of the inter- section is the Melbourne Entertainment Arena, where criminals and other  degenerates are placed to be stoned, mutilated and killed.  Surrounding the Arena are a number of small shops and stores where just about anything may be purchased.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: The small armory is located to the west of the road, where everyday citizens may purchase light armor to use for day-to-day protection.  The armor is not nearly as strong as you'd like, but for the price range, you can't really argue.  On the east side of the road is the Bows & Arrows Unlimited Shop where various bows, mostly made by elves, may be purchased.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: There is a large building on the west side of the road.  To the south is the Medical Supplies shop and to the north is the Leather Armory.  This being the poorer part of town, most of the armor sold there is relatively inexpensive.  On the east side of the road are a number of small buildings. Directly to the east is Ian's Fletchery, where bows are made and repaired.

name: Melbourne Avenue
description: You are in the central section of this part of town where numerous shops line the street.  On the west side of the road, you can see Othan's Medical Supplies where various healing potions and supplies may be purchased.  On the east side of the road is Runfun's Archery College where young warriors are trained in the art of archery and fletchery.

name: Melbourne Avenue/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Melbourne Avenue runs north from Waterfront Way, heading past the infamous Melbourne Entertainment Arena, where criminals and other less appreciated members of society are put to their deaths by throwing them into the arena to be stones, skewered or otherwise mutilated in a horrible death.  This tends to keep crime in the city down, though.

name: Riverdell Way/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Riverdell Way, running north and south, intersects Netherworld Lane, running east and west, at this point.  Both roads literally span the city in the directions that they are heading.  Netherworld runs through the center of town, passing by the northern border and main entrance to the Necropolis.  Riverdell runs south past the Allakaren Circle and Pyramid, towards the southern City Wall.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Tranquility Park is a vast, restful place where people go to enjoy a day in the park.  It is also the home of the Riverdell Center for Tracking Training, where a number of rangers practice and improve their skills.  On the east side of the road is the Odinialli Memorial Administration Building for the Iilandi University.  The large University houses many of Ocean- crest's biggest minds in science and technology.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Iilandi University covers nearly three city blocks, starting at the Allakaren Circle and heading north from there.  The University houses the city's finest creators and thinkers.  Citizens may take classes here for their own self-enrichment or to work towards degrees in various fields  of study.  The Facility is rather modernistic for its time, but runs into a number of budget problems as it expands.

name: Riverdell Way/Kafkan Way Intersection
description: The large Iilandi University lies to the east of the intersection on both corners.  On the southeast corner is the University Library and on the northeast corner is the Odinialli Memorial Administration Building. Much of the University is privately donated and funded as the city does not take a great interest in the school, except when it is up for various honors, which it receives quite often.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The University Library, with the possible exception of the Oceancrest Ministry of Knowledge building in southwestern Oceancrest, is perhaps the largest known collection of books and tomes in the land.  The vast library contains much of what the Ministry has, but also a number of more scientific and philosophical volumes which the Ministry has yet  to accept as valid reading and learning materials. Opposite the Library, you see the mystical far seer's home.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Allakaren Circle, to the south, runs around the interesting and unique Tree of Life.  Although no special properties have very been obtained from the tree itself, the tree has survived centuries of wars, famines, droughts and various other disasters.  The Circle is a monument for the preservation of such a magnificent tree.

name: Allakaren Circle
description: The Allakaren Circle is about twice the radius of most of the other  traffic circles in the city.  This is because the city planners actually thought about growth before they built the Circle.  Fearing the industrial growth of the town might hinder the Tree's growth, the Circle was built with a lot of central space for the Tree to grow and florish, despite what went on in its surroundings.  A small fence prevents people from disturbing the tree in the center of the circle.

name: Allakaren Circle
description: The Allakaren Circle houses the Tree of Life, or so the mystics like to call the large tree which has grown at the center of this circle for  ages beyond that which can be remembered.  The Tree is guarded by a light wire fence running around the Circle.  It was believed to be the tree of the Pharaoh Allakaren, after which the Circle is named.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Panther Guards are a small subset of the city guard garrison, charged with maintaining peace and order in this section of town.  Since most of the buildings in this area are residential in nature, the Panther Guards are more specially equiped to handle domestic affairs instead of street violence.  On the west side of the road is a narrow, pink building called  "Penelope's Musical Instruments" where bards and other minstrels can buy various musical instruments to annoy people with.

name: Riverdell Way/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Hillcrest Drive runs to the east and west from here, extending the city's boundaries further to the east to encompass the great Allakaren Pyramid. Riverdell Way is a north-south street.  About a block to the north, there is a large oak tree in the center of a small traffic circle.  The Tree has been here longer than the city.  Small shops line the west side of the road.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Directly to the west, you can see Hanabal's Light Swords shop, where some inexpensive, but useful swords and daggers may be purchased.  To the  south a little bit is the Panthor Academy of the Fighting Arts, where  galiant, aspiring Fighters go to train during their first few months of experience.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Allakaren Pyramid was built centuries ago before the city of Oceancrest even existed.  However, after many years of looting and wear by the  elements, the Pyramid has started to deteriorate.  After the City of  Oceancrest was formed and the walls around the city were being planned, the administrators decided that it would be in the best interests of the community to protect the Pyramid within the City Walls.  It is said that the Pyramid is still haunted by its previous owner, but this hasn't stopped archeologists from digging around inside.

name: Riverdell Way
description: Uland is the name of a small island off the coast of the Respitial Sea, about twenty miles or so south of Oceancrest.  Why the proprietor decided to name his shop after this small island is still a mystery to most people.  The repair shop will fix almost any weapon or armor for a small amount of gold, depending on how much the item in question is worth.

name: Riverdell Way/Nagaritha Drive Intersection
description: Nagaritha Drive heads off to the west from Riverdell Way, making its trek through the southern parts of Oceancrest.  Riverdell Way runs north and south from the intersection, notably running through the eastern section of town from one City Wall to the other.  On the southwest corner of the road, you can see the Bows & Arrows Unlimited Shop where you can purchase a number of finely crafted bows made by the finest elven fletchers.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The impressive Bows & Arrows Unlimited bow shop satisfies both the beginner and the expert archer, and everyone in between.  All sorts of bows and  arrows my be purchased in the shop, run by a number of elves who can also craft weapons to your exact proportions.  The fine bows are cherished by all those who purchase from the shop and envied by those who do not have the money to buy the best.

name: Riverdell Way
description: the impressive City Walls on the east side of the road stand nearly ten meters high at some points, protecting the city and its citizens from  attacks and raids from the outside world.  The realm ouside the City Walls is very deadly and not very fun to visit.  Only the bravest people venture out into the wilderness.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Runfun Outstanding Archery Academy is designed for superior archers to train and perfect their archery skills.  Furthermore, the academy  provides expert training in making and repairing bows.  The fletchery work is difficult to understand and even harder to master, which is why elven bows always costs so much.

name: Riverdell Way/Waterfront Way Intersection
description: Waterfront Way heads west from Riverdell Way, which runs north and south. On the east side of the road, you can see the large City Walls which encompass the city.  The Dentra Central Archery Range is located on the southwestern corner of the intersection, the entrances to which are  located on Waterfront Way.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Dentra Archery Range is divided into two separate ranges, one for the advanced archers and another for beginners and novice archers.  The Range improves archery skills and often holds tournaments to see who  can hit the target's bull's eye from the furthest distance.  The entrance to the facility is located off of Waterfront Way.

name: Riverdell Way
description: The Dentra Archery Range is located on the east side of the road.  On the east side of the road is the City Wall, marking the city's border on the east side.  The City Wall does not travel in a straight line at this corner of the city, though.  It will head east again in order to enclose the  Pyramid of Allakaren.

name: Riverdell Way/Golden Dolphin Way Intersection
description: Golden Dolphin Way runs west from here, running parallel to the City  Walls on the south side of the road.  Riverdell Way runs north through the main parts of the city.  To the south, you can see the South  Oceancrest Observational Station, a large guard station at the southern end of the city.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: You are getting close to the easternmost borders of the city, which lie but a block to the east.  Wakeforest Drive runs north and south through the eastern section of the city, past the Wakarimasu Parks.  Netherworld Lane runs east and west past the main entrance of the city's Necropolis  towards the center of town.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Iilandi University is a more or less privately funded school which promotes academics in all fields of study, but mostly technology.  Directly to the west, you can see the Oceancrest Technological Research Facility where mystical phenomena like earthquakes are studies and recorded.  On the east side of the road are the Highland Stables, where guests of the town may leave their horses while visiting.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: It is important to note that riding a horse in town, especially in a busy section of town, is dangerous to both the pedestrians and to the horse. Therefore, a large stable has been placed near the eastern entrance to the city for the convinience of the guests.  There are also a number of small inns near the eastern gates where visitors may relax after a long day of riding.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Kafkan Way Intersection
description: Wakeforest Road runs north and south through a good part of the eastern side of town.  To the south, you can see it running parallel to the City Walls, which have been re-built to incorporate the Allakaren Pyramid  within the safty of the city's protection.  The Dwarven shrine of  Moradin lies on the southwestern corner of the intersection.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: Wakeforest Drive runs north and south past the eastern City Walls, which run parallel to Wakeforest on the east side of the road.  On the west  side of the road is the Dwarven Shrine of Moradin, the creator god of  the dwarven race.  All dwarves in the city are required to make an annual pilgrimage to the Shrine to give thanks or repentance to the god. The Oceancrest Orphanage is further south on Wakeforest Drive.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: Moradin is the Creator of the Dwarven Race, and the dwarves worship him regularly as if the end of the world were going to come tomorrow.  The fanatic worship of a god has inspired many wars and many victories for the dwarves, but now they live in relative peace with the humans and other races of the world (although they still don't really like the elves too much.)  On the east is the Oceancrest Orphanage.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The large City Walls dwarf the largest half-giant in sheer size, making it nearly impossible to scale from either side.  This is useful in that it  prevents outside invaders from infiltrating the city and also prevents criminals from escaping.  On the west side of the road is the Shrine of Moradin, the dwarven God of Creation.  The Oceancrest Orphanage is north.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Monument Avenue Intersection
description: The intersection of Wakeforest Drive and Monument Avenue is relatively uneventful being at the easternmost point in town.  The large City Walls on the east side of the road mark the boundaries of the vast city.  On the southwest corner, you can see the Obidian Community Housing Complex where most of the citizens who need to live inside Oceancrest live.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The Obidian Community Housing Complex houses most of the citizens of  Oceancrest in relatively spacious accomodations for a relatively inexpensive cost.  One of the two major housing complexes in Oceancrest, nearly one third of the entire population lives in these complexes, which are capable  of housing over ten thousand people.

name: Wakeforest Drive
description: The massive Obidian Complex is only dwarved by the high City Walls on the opposite side of the road.  Although the Complex is much higher than the City Walls, there has not been a recorded case where someone has actually tried to jump over the walls from this direction.  Being so close to the City Walls can sometimes be a problem as the large buildings are the first to be hit.  This poor planning, however, has not resulted in any casualties.

name: Wakeforest Drive/Hillcrest Drive Intersection
description: Both Wakeforest Drive and Hillcrest Drive end here. (or begin, depending on  your perspective.)   Wakeforest Drive heads north through the eastern area  of town, which is mostly administrative, and Hillcrest Drive runs west through the more rural farming lands in south central Oceancrest. A dirt road leads east, off into the wilderness and farmland

name: Highland Avenue/Netherworld Lane Intersection
description: Highland Avenue runs north and south, parallel to the eastern City Walls through most of the eastern half of the city.  Netherworld Lane runs west from Highland and eventually runs into the western City Wall on the other side of the city.  The Highland Stables are located on the  southwestern corner of the intersection and the Crimson Dragon Traveler's Lodge is located on the northwestern corner.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The massive City Walls run parallel to Highland Avenue for almost the  entire span of the road.  On the west side of the road is the Highland Stables, where visitors and guests may leave their steeds in order to walk around town without having to worry about the safety of their  horses and the people on the streets.

name: Highland Avenue
description: The Highland Stables provide comfortable accomodations for the horses of visitors and guests to Oceancrest.  Safety among the citizens of Oceancrest is a high priority, so guests are strongly suggested to leave their steeds in the stables during their visit to Oceancrest.

name: Highland Avenue/Kafkan Way Intersection
description: The City Walls make a turn towards the north and the west, running parallel to both Highland Avenue and Kafkan Way.  A lone Guard Tower stands on the southeastern corner of the intersection, watching over and protecting the town from various invaders from the mountains and plains.  It has been a long time since the city was last attacked, but as soon as the guard slacks, invaders will probably attack again.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The Highland Stables are located on the north side of the road, the  entrance to which is located on the east side, off of Highland Avenue. On the south side of the road, you can see the large City Walls, standing proud to protect the city from all forms of invasion.  Oceancrest has remained free for centuries and plans to stay that way.

name: Kafkan Way
description: Occasionally, you can see a couple of guards patrolling the City Walls, watching out for invasion forces.  No one is really stupid enough to try to invade Oceancrest, but the threat always exists.  The only people who really venture out past the City Walls are caravans and mercenaries looking for a quick gold piece.

name: Kafkan Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the Highland Stables, where visitors may leave their horses while staying in Oceancrest.  It is very hazardous to be riding a horse in Oceancrest, both for the horse and for the pedestrians walking the streets.  Furthermore, it's almost impossible to find a place to leave your horse when you go into a shop.  Therefore, the city asks that people leave their steeds at one of the many stables in town.

name: Kafkan Way
description: Kafkan Way is one of the many roads that forms the boundry of the city of Oceancrest.  The border along the southeastern corner of Oceancrest is not a straight line, and curves with the rugged landscape.  To the west, you  can see the intersection with Wakeforest Drive.  Kafkan way continues to the east and west.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The Dwarven Shrine of Moradin lies on the south side of the road where numerous dwarves annually pilgrimage to.  The Shrine is one of the  largest in the city.  On the north side of the road is the Oceancrest Technological Research Facility where various studies are going on to figure out why the earth moves, why there is day and night, and why do people still insist on killing themselves to gain proficiency.

name: Kafkan Way
description: A small postal facility lies on the south side of the road.  Being that communications are the most important thing in a good society, the mail system tends to be very accurate and prompt.  On the north side of the road is a small fountain.  The fountain seems to be sitting in the  middle of the large park on the Iilandi Campus.

name: Kafkan Way
description: There is a rather nice-looking fountain on the north side of the road on the Iilandi University campus.  The fountain has been dedicated to the  founding pioneers in the sciences.  The University gives out an award each year on the basis of science, and new inductees get their names put on the plaques around the fountain.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The Iilandi University Library is one of the largest facilities of its kind in Oceancrest, surpassed only the by the Ministry of Knowledge in southwestern Oceancrest.  On the north side of the road is the Odinialli Memorial Administration Building where various schedules and forms are lost for the public good.  That good of course being that if the forms  were lost, the administrators would have something to do, thus would not be fired, and not contribute to the unemployment level of the city.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The large park on the north side of the road provides a nice, relaxing atmosphere for picnics or other festivities in the open air.  There not being much open spaces any more where people can go to eat lunch with  nature, the Park has become a permanent fixture in the city.  Furthermore, the Riverdell Tracking Facility has also been established in the park to provide tracking training to Rangers and other specialists.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The city is very serene and peaceful near the Riverdell Tranquility Park, which is probably why the park got its name.  The University is also in the neighborhood, further to the east.  On the south side of the road is the Oceancrest Mountaineers Supply, a store where any number of specialized items may be purchased.

name: Melbourne Avenue/Kafkan Way
description: Melbourne Avenue runs south from Kafkan Way, through most of the large stores and shops in downtown southeastern Oceancrest.  Southeastern Ocean- crest is known to be mostly a poor section of town, so most of the shops cater to the low-income families and workers.  Kafkan Way runs east and west from here, east towards the eastern end of town and west towards the Necropolis. A steady stream of weak looking adventures are going through a door to a training area. It looks like an easy place to gain experience.

name: Kafkan Way
description: The Park facilities are open all day and night for the benefit of all the citizens of the city, knowing that not everyone quits when the sun goes down.  The entrance to the large facility is located on the west side of the Park off of Leviathan Drive.  Kafkan road continues to the east and west from here, heading west towards the Necropolis.

name: Kafkan Way
description: Lafyette's Blacksmith Shop offers superior and quality craftsmanship in the repair of armor and weaponry,  But Lafyette is a simple man, and does not guarantee anything.  (Nor do his competitors.)  Like all blacksmiths in the Land of Mordor, he has an aversion to enchanted items and will tell you it is difficult to repair items without them losing that special magical glow.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Crimson Dragon Traveller's Lodge is located on the north side of the road, conviniently near the eastern entrance to the city.  On the south side of the road are the Highland Stables, where travellers are urged to leave their horses while in town.  Head to the east, you can see Netherworld Lane coming to an end when it intersects Highland Avenue.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Crimson Dragon Traveller's Lodge provides accomodations for just about anyone wandering in from outside the city.  The lodge also provides  information about travel conditions and possible locations for raids and other looters.  The eastern gate is the most popular entrance and exit out of the city, and usually the safest as it is the most travelled.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The eastern section of town is fairly clean, with a lot of parks and other non-tampered recreational facilities.  The fresh air is, of course, quite refreshing, and a nice change from the industrialized sections of town where the smell of alcohol is always in the air.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Thenardier's Inn is well known for its lack of hospitality and general vulgarity of the host.  Nonetheless, it is a relatively popular place because it is very cheap and affordable.  Many travellers, coming through the eastern city gate, often stop here to get the city's gossip.  Students also visit the Inn since they really can't afford to eat anywhere else, and the awful brew they serve here is relatively cheap.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Iilandi University was created some decades ago by a grant from the Iilandi family in order to bring a higher education campus to  Oceancrest.  The city of Oceancrest then took up the funding for the school since maintaining it was virtually free.  The school grew and propered, and has since become a major force in the intellectual community.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: On the north side of the road is the Iilandi University's Chancellor's  Hall, where a majority of the classes are held.
