The Hall is very large, and supports nearly ten thousand people simultaneously in just over one hundred separate lecture halls and classrooms.  On the south side of the road, you can see the various research facilities such as the Oceancrest Technological Research Facility and Tholian Hall.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The large Chancellor's Hall building on the north side of the road covers much of this city block and has over one hundred separate lecture halls and classrooms.  Most of the classes are taught in the Chancellor's Hall building, but most of the research is done on the south side of the road in Tholian Hall or the Technological Research Facility.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Odinialli Memorial Administration Building is located on the south side of the road next to Riverdell Way.  On the north side of the road, you can see the great Iilandi University Chancellor's Hallwhere most of the classes are held.  The large university spans nearly three city blocks and is virtually free to students.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Riverdell Tranquility Park, aptly named, is one of the quieter, more peaceful parks in the city, primarily because it is so large.  There is  more than enough room in the park for everyone's interests without having to bother someone else.  The park is also used to train Rangers in the ways of tracking and searching in the woods, without having to actually leave the safety of Oceancrest.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: The Rodaisl Community Housing Complex is one of two community housing  complexes in Oceancrest.  The Rodaisl Complex is much larger than the  Obidian Complex, located off of Wakeforest Drive, and has room for nearly fifteen thousand people, or roughly four thousand apartments that can house up to four people each.  On the south side of the road, you can see the Riverdell Tranquility Park, where people usually go to relax after a long day of work.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: Housing is usually not a problem in Oceancrest as long as you don't mind living in one of the two large housing complexes.  There is no room for individual houses within the borders of Oceancrest, so many people build houses outside of the city.  However, most feel more secure living inside the City Walls and have learned to survive, in relative comfort, in these housing complexes.

name: Netherworld Lane
description: On the south side of the road, you can see the Riverdell Tranquility Park and the Riverdell Center for Tracking Training.  Being as large as it is, the Riverdell Park is ideal for studying the skills of tracking and  searching in the rather dense woods.  On the north side of the road is the Rodaisl Community Housing Complex, where numerous Oceancrest residents live.  There are no houses within the city, so if people wish to live  inside the city, they must live in one of the housing complexes.

name: Monument Avenue
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the Dwarven Shrine of Moradin, the creator of the Dwarven Race.  All dwarves worship Moradin as if the world is going to end tomorrow.  Such dedication and faith has in the  past given dwarves the extra moral boost they need to defeat nearly  impossible odds.  On the southern side of the road is the Obidian  Community Housing Complex, where most of the city's citizens, who want to live in the city, live.

name: Monument Avenue
description: Citizens of Oceancrest who wish to live in the city itself must live in the community residences provided for by the city as there is not enough empty space inside the City Walls for everyone to build a house.  However, spacing is not really limited, and anyone who wants to live in the city, both for protection and convinience, may do so by applying at the Obidian Community Housing Complex or the Rodaisl Complex, located more towards the center of town off of Leviathan Way.

name: Monument Avenue
description: The small, abandoned building on the north side of the road was recently renovated by some rebellious believers as the Shrine of Annam.  Annam  is the Great Creator of all life in the universe.  This believe was  primarily believed only by the giants and half-giants of the realm, but their word has spread to some of the other races, most notably including humans.

name: Monument Avenue
description: You can see the Allakaren Circle to the west and the interesting Tree of Life that the Circle surrounds.  The tree has been in that same place  as far as people can remember into the past, and was rumored to be the sacred tree of Allakaren himself.  Allakaren is the pharaoh of the ancient lands that would later (much, much later) become Oceancrest.  A monument to his great existance still stands on the southeastern corner of the town.

name: Allakaren Circle
description: The mysterious Tree of Life lives in the center of Allakaren Circle, and has existed at this point for as long as anyone can remember.  It was thought that the Pharaoh Allakaren once planted the tree and fed it the blood of his wives when they died.  Whether or not this is true remains to be seen as no blood has been spilled on the tree for centuries.

name: The Tree of Life
description: Well, there's nothing really overly remarkable about this tree except for the fact that it has been in existance longer than anyone or anything you can remember.  The tree is relatively small for a thousand year old tree, but its branches are strong and its roots are solid.

name: Allakaren Circle
description: The mysterious tree which grows inside the Allakaren Circle is said to have existed long before any humans had inhabitted the area now known as Oceancrest, and could have been the product of the elves.  Nevertheless, the Pharaoh Allakaren adopted the long-living tree as his own and gave the blood of his wives as a sacrifice to the tree.  It is also believed that the blood of Allakaren also runs through the roots of the tree.

name: Monument Avenue
description: The mysterious Allakaren Circle and the even more mysterious Tree of Life lies to the east along Monument Avenue.  On the north side of the road, you can see the Dragon Claw Tavern and Grill, where a number of citizens go to enjoy a good steak, and to talk about the disasterous day they've had.  The entrance to the tavern is arond the corner to the west, on Melbourne Avenue.  Directly south is a shabby little shop known as the welfare office.

name: Monument Avenue
description: On the north side of the road is the Oceancrest Trash Recycling Plant.  One of the biggest problems in Oceancrest, as with all major cities, is the  problem of trash.  As an incentive to keep the town clean, the city pays one gold piece for each bit of junk anyone leaves in the Recycling center. On the south side of the road is the Iron Works shop where small but sturdy weapons may be purchased.

name: Monument Avenue
description: On the north side of the road, you can see Catherine's Weapons shop, where some simple weapons may be purchased.  On the south side of the  street is the Holy Order of the White Rose, a training center for young Paladins, just learning the basic skills of knighthood.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: Due to the lack of space within the City Walls, Oceancrest cannot support the building of individual home within the limits of the city.  However, since there is a need for people to live inside the city, large housing complexes like the Obidian Community Housing Complex have been built.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: You can start to see the impressive Allakaren Pyramid a short distance to the southwest.  The south side of the road is completely barren except for the shadow the Pyramid casts on the land.  On the north, you can see the Obidian Community Housing Complex where numerous citizens live.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The impressive Allakaren Pyramid is almost directly to the south of you. It has been said that the Pyramid is quite haunted, but that hasn't stopped archeologists from exploring the caverns in great detail over the many centuries the Pyramid has been standing.  No doubt looters have already taken most of the valuables within the Pyramid.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The large Allakaren Pyramid stands high above the city as it towers  towards the sky, surpassing even the City Walls in height.  The Pyramid has withstood the various ravages of time, and remains standing even  centuries after Pharaoh Allakaren was buried deep within its chambers. Rumor has it that the Pharaoh still wanders the halls of his Pyramid, trying to find the people who have stolen treasure from his tomb.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Panther Guards are a small sub-division of the regular city guards that patrol the southeastern section of town.  Since much of this area is residential, they are more capable of handling simple disputes in the housing complex or stopping small bar fights in any of the many local bars.  On the south side of the road, you can see the impressive Allakaren Pyramid as it stands towering above the city.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: You are in one of the larger shopping districts in the city of Oceancrest, but nothing compared to the shopping district near the Lyanden Bay in the norrthwest section of town.  On the south side of the road there is a small sword shop where fine swords are sold at very high prices.  On the north side is Penelope's Toy Store and Musical Instruments.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Chug-A-Lug Pub is a pretty filthy night club where various people of any class go to have a fairly good time, depending on what one's definition of a good time is.  The entrance to the Pub is located on the west side of the building off of Melbourne Avenue.  On the south side of the street is the Generic Clerical Supply shop where various articles of religion may be purchased.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The fantastic Melbourne Entertainment Arena is designed to amuse the law- abiding citizens by throwing criminals and other degenerates into the  pits to battle gladiators and sometimes lions.  The spectators are often given stones to throw at the people in the arena if things get a little boring.  On the north side of the road is Imeldia's Potions and Stuff arguably a magic shop.

name: Hillcrest Drive
description: The Melbourne Arena is by far the most interesting building in the area, but you can also see a number of small shops and other stores to the east. On the north side of the road, you can see the building which houses the Order of the White Rose, where young knights aspiring to be Paladins of  the King go to get their basic training.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: A small business that calls itself Bows & Arrows Unlimited does pretty good work for the price and supplies a number powerful bows and various  ammunition to go with it.  Most of the bows are elven in nature, many of which were made next door at Ian's Fletchery.  On the north side of the  road you can see the Uland Repair Shop.  Entrances to both shopping centers are located off of Riverdell Way.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: Very few charities give out aid for free anymore, but the Helping Hand still exists to serve the destitude of life.  Many people go here after battles with numerous wounds to have dressed up.  The rather small  facility only holds a couple of people at a time, so you may have to wait in line if you want to enter.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Melbourne Entertainment Arena provides citizens with the much needed emotional releases of revenge against criminals and other dregs of  society.  These people, accused and convicted of crimes, are thrown into the pits to do battle with gladiators, and sometimes lions.  The  spectators also get to join in by throwing rocks and other garbage at the contestants.  On the south side of the road is D'Tan's Armory, where some light armor may be purchased before entering the arena.

name: Nagaritha Drive
description: The Shrine of Victory, located south of the Melbourne Entertainment Arena, symbolizes hope against impossible odds.  It is often visited by warriors about to leave for battle, but otherwise generally ignored by most of the other citizens.  On the north side of the road is the Melbourne Entertain- ment Arena where contestants fight everything from common criminals to  gladiators, and even lions.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The entrance to the Advanced Archer's Archery Range is located on the south side of the road.  This range is used by only the finest archers in the land.  To prevent some embarassment, young archers are urged to get permission before entering this area of the Dentra Archery Range. Competition can be fierce, but always a lot of fun.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The large archery range is flanked by a number of small shops and centers to benifit the archer and other warriors.  On the north side of the road, you can see a small center dedicated towards archery and fletchery.  This area is primarily run by the elves since they are the best archers and  know how to make the best bows and arrows in the land.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range is located on the south side of the road. You are at the beginner's level area of the range where anyone is welcome to shoot a few bolts.  The young archers in this range are fairly good  shots, and come here to practice between school lessons.  It is important for young elves to learn the art of archery at a young age.

name: Waterfront Way
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range is divided into two separate ranges so that the experienced archers don't have to deal with the inexperienced ones at the same target range.  You are in front of the main entrance to the Beginner's Archery Range where a number of younger archers and their tutors are practicing and improving their skills.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range is located on the north side of the road. Unfortunately, you are standing behind the targets.  However, since the range you are standing behind is for advanced archers, it is unlikely that they will miss their targets.  On the south side of the road, you can see the City Walls as they merge into the South Oceancrest Observational Station.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range has two separate facilities, one for  beginners and another for advanced marksmen (markspeople?).  The eastern range is reserved for the advanced archer, so although you are behind the archery targets, it is very unlikely that you will actually get hit by a stray arrow unless you are the target.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: On the north side of the road, you can see the Dentra Central Archery  Range, where many archers and civilians alike go to practice their bow and arrow skills either for the hunt or just self-defense.  As with most archery ranges, elves are always present, trying to prove that they're better than anyone else.

name: Golden Dolphin Way
description: The Dentra Central Archery Range is the finest archery facility in  Oceancrest, and perhaps throughout the lands, with the possible exception of some elven ranges.  Golden Dolphin Road runs along the rear side of the archery range, where all the targets are.  Standing around behind the archery targets is a good way to collect on life insurance.

name: The Wizard's Eye
description: This is the Wizard's Eye, where souls are kept in fine gems.  Any and all who seek to learn the arts of necromancy and magic must come here to train and advance in level.  Neophytes up to level two should go through the  silver arch.  If you seek a level from four to nine, you may enter the ruby encrusted door.  Those powerful mages who hope to advance to level ten and above must fly to the diamond and gold balcony.

name: The Shrine of the Protectors
description: This shrine is a monument to the heroism and bravery of the ancient Protectors.  It is watched over carefully by one of the last remaining members of the order, the High Templar of Oceancrest, who has been  appointed to be in charge of granting new levels to aspiring young clerics.

name: The Rusty Dagger Training Room
description: Only assassins aspiring to be Rutterkins may train in this center.  Once you reach the level of Rutterkin First Class, you may no longer train in this center.  Your brothers suggest trying to find the Dripping Dagger in northeast Oceancrest to further develop your skills.

name: Advanced Range
description: This area of the archery range is restricted to only the best archers in the lands, so that they can practice without having to worry about others less talented interfeering with them.  Most of the archers are pretty stuck up and may actually attack non-archers when they enter the facility.

name: Beginner's Range
description: Numerous young elves and various other races often come here to work on their archery skills.  Although they are not very good shots yet, they  are tough and can be a challenge to beat in a contest.  It's funny to see they young elves easily outscoring nearly every other race present at the range.

name: The Salamander's Cave
description: The salamander is a giant, demon-like creature from the depths of the elemental plane of fire.  The cave in intensely warm and feels almost like you're standing in a fire.  The rest of the cave is otherwise empty and has nothing of real value.  Besides, almost any object in  here for more than a short period of time would probably melt or burn. It appears the salamander is sitting on something, however its large frame obscures your view.

name: Hidden Mountain Path
description: Although the path leads into the mountain, it appears to head downward instead of up.  The path leads you straight into a cave that was otherwise not visible from the road.  You can feel a lot of head coming from the cave, which is slightly lit with a faint red glow.

name: South Oceancrest Post Office #56
description: One of the great benifits of living in a large city like Oceancrest is that you can get mail to people on the other side of town without having to travel all the way over there.  Post Offices are scattered throughout the land for this purpose.  You can even send mail to other cities as well.

name: Thenardier's Inn
description: You are in the infamous Inn of the Thenardier's.  Monsieur Thenardier serves his guests in disgust, singing "My den of soaks, my den of dissolutes, my dirty jokes, my always pissed as newts, my sons of whores spend their lives in my inn.  Homing pidgeons homing in, then fly through my doors.  And their money's good as yours!"  The guests are not all that pleasant either, but for the price and company, who can argue.

name: The Barbarian's Trading Post
description: It is very rare that barbarians have money, but occasionally, they will require new or more improved stuff.  So when they do come into some unforseen wealth, they will come here to purchase just about anything they need.  The Post also sells a number of trinkets and other useful junk that might have some use outside the Barbarian Pits.

name: The Barbarian Trading Post Storage Shack
The Shaman's Hut
description: The Shaman is a very powerful wizard who protects his people with  magical healing powers.  He seldom leaves the safety of his hut, but always has some barbarian guards around in case anyone should try to take his life.  As is the case with most mages, he has very few hit points, but can easily toast your eyeballs.

name: The Children's Playpen
description: This small pit is used by the barbarians to put their young for the  day while they go out and plummet local city resources.  The young barbarians are typically grunts or lower, but can sometimes pack quite a punch if backed into a corner.

name: The Sporting Pit
description: The Sporting Pit allows barbarians and their kind to experiment with new weapons and armors in battles with outsiders or other worthy  barbarian opponents.  You are in the higher of the two pits, the other lying to the north, more depressed into the landscape.  Less barbarians wander into this pit than into the deeper one to the north.

name: The Sporting Pit
description: The large pit you are in is used by the barbarians as their sporting  arena.  Here, brave barbarians and other outsiders can challenge the most powerful of the barbarian kin.  You are in the deeper of the two pits, making it more likely that more barbarians will fall into this pit than the one to the south.

name: The Barbarian Chief's Hut
description: Barbarians are typically very trusting and don't really mind outsiders wandering around, but they do not allow just anyone into the Chief's Hut.  It is strictly off limits even to most barbarians that live here. There are a number of guards waiting to pounce as you enter, making life very tough.

name: The Hot Mud Pits
description: A large number of half-giants usually come here to rest after a long battle against nearly impossible odds.  As usual, they return victorious, but heavily wounded.  The mud, although quite dirty and very smelly, appears to help them recover much faster than the Shaman can personally tend to each of them.

name: The Northern Path
description: To the east, you can see a small trading post which is set up to allow the wealthier barbarians to buy some larger sized armor to better  protect themselves.  Most barbarians tend to either go naked or just wear a loincloth.  Very few are able to afford some of the higher quality metallic and leather armors.  Furthermore, not many people  actually make that large of size of armor.

name: The Northern Path
description: The northern path curves sharply to the east and south here.  To the south, you can see the entrance where you entered the Barbarian Pits. Looking to the east, you can see that the path heads towards the  Ramdes River.  A giant hedge is located north of the Pits, but you cannot leave that way.  The heavy brush and steep slope prevent you  from leaving anywhere except the entrances.

name: The Northern Path
description: You have reached the northern most boundry of the Barbarian Pits, which borders a giant hedge.  The thick brush and steep hill prevent you from leaving the pits from this direction.  The northern path heads east  towards the Ramdes River and west back towards the entrance to the  Barbarian Pits.

name: The Central Path
description: The center path train joins the other trails coming from the southern part of the Barbarian Pits at the bridge crossing the Ramdes River to the southeast.  The large river divides the Pits into two sections, the larger one being on the west side of the river.  Not much lies on the eastern side of the river except an access path to a deep valley.

name: The Northern Path Junction
description: The barbarians are not much for names, let alone intelligent dialogue. Therefore, not much around here is named except for the most vital areas.  The barbarians don't really have a need for much of the fancy directions everyone uses in town, and just resort to pointing and  grunting to get their point across.

name: The Center Path
description: You are now just north of the Barbarian Chief's Hut, where all the major planning and strategies are drawn up and torn apart.  Since they are just barbarians, it's unlikely that any plan they have would make much sense anyway.  The path weaves around the Trading Post, located to the west along the Center path.

name: The Center Path
description: The Barbarian Pits were more or less carved out of the surrounding country to suit the needs of the half-giants who live here.  To the north, you can see the small Trading Post where some of the richer barbarians can trade or buy better armors to wear instead of the loincloths most are sporting.

name: The Center Path
description: The bottom of the Pits is northeast of here, while the Barbarian Chief's Hut is located directly north in a small section of land separated by the two center paths.  On the south you can see a great many barbarians relaxing in a huge puddle of hot mud, if you can call that relaxing.

name: The Center Path Junction
description: Tow paths lead around the center of the Barbarian Pits to the northeast and southwest.  Heading to the west takes you to the only entrance of the Pits. Directly east, you can see the Barbarian Chief's Hut, although you will have to take a less direct route to get there.  On the south side of the path is an area for the village's young to play.

name: Entrance to the Barbarian Pits
description: Society, deeming the barbarians as just too barbaric, has set aside this small park to the east of the Northern Highway as a place reserved only  for their use.  Here, the barbarian culture is nurtured and passed down through the generations instead of simply being forgotten, as was done in the past before they moved here.  Not particularly happy with their small park, the barbarians are still content enough to stay here and not overrun the city to the south.

name: The Southern Path
description: The Southern Path brings you around towards the low-level training  grounds, located to the west.  In order to advance as a barbarian, you must prove yourself to the barbarian leaders by defeating another who is one level greater than you.  Only then will you be allowed to advance to the next level.  The path circles back toward the entrance to the north and heads towards the southern border to the south.

name: The Southern Path
description: Descending into the Barbarian Pits isn't as bad as you had imagined.   As you walk around., you notice that the path now curves to the east as you reach the southern end of the Pits.  There seems to be quite a bit  of excitement a little further to the east.  You have already seen a number of younger grunts of varying ability wandering around

name: The Southern Path
description: The mysterious Shaman's hut is located to the north of the path.  You can see a number of children being entertained by the witch doctor as he blows fire from his hands.  The Shamen are an important part of the barbarian's culture in that they provide most of the healing powers to the wounded after battle.

name: The Southern Path
description: There is a warm, bubbling pool of mud located to the northwest of the path where a number of barbarians are resting.  It appears to be some sort of hot water spring bubbling through the mud that gives off the heat.  The path curves to the northeast where it meets the Center Path. The path to the west runs towards the Shaman's hut.

name: The Southern Path Junction
description: The Center Path, naturally, runs through the center of the Barbarian  Pits.  The Southern Path runs along the southern border of the Pits.  The barbarian race isn't all that bright and do not have a lot of fancy  names for their roads, especially since they're just dirt paths.  The primative training facility for the tribesmen is located to the south here.  The barbarians are known to test their own before allowing them to advance to higher levels.

name: The Center Path
description: The path you are walking on runs northeast to southwest.  On the east, you can see the deep river Ramdes.  A bridge crosses the river to the northeast.  To the northwest, you can see a great pit area where a number of barbarians have gathered to watch others fight for honor and glory.  The large pit looks like it's covered with blood.

name: Western Shore of the Ramdes Bridge
description: The narrow bridge crosses over the relatively calm, but very deep Ramdes  River, which eventually empties into Lyanden Lake.  The river runs from the northern mountains through Oceancrest, and eventually ends up in the ocean.  The eastern half of the Barbarian Pits are pretty much deserted and reserved for very powerful barbarians who would rather be left alone.

name: Barbarian Training Compound
description: The straw hut is for those of you wishing to advance to level seven, while the wooden hut is for level eight.  Of course, that means the stone hut is for level nine.  The Shaman is in charge of this place.  Talk to him about  more advanced training.

name: The Barbarian Yellow Training Hut
description: In order to advance to a grunt, second class, you must first defeat a barbarian of that level to prove your worth to your barbarian brothers. If you are unable to defeat this barbarian, perhaps you are not yet worthy of advancing to the next level.

name: The Yellow Training Hut
description: The secret to a good and powerful barbarian is the ability to overpower opponents that are even more powerful than you.  In order to advance to higher levels, you must be prepared to fight with a barbarian of the level you are applying for.  Barbarians don't rise to power by being wimps.

name: The Barbarian Orange Training Hut
description: The Barbarian Training Huts are designed to test the aspiring barbarian with another barbarian of the next level.  In order to advance to the next level, you must defeat the first class grunt which awaits you in this hut.

name: The Orange Training Hut
description: As you probably now know, barbarians don't let their kind advance without making sure that they earn the title they are planning to advance to.  Now that you have defeated the grunt, first class, you are now allowed to  train to that class rank.  Unfortunately, as a grunt, first class, your skills have exceeded the skills being taught at this section of the  Barbarian Pits, and you must now search for the Tribesman Training Huts.

name: The Barbarian Blue Training Hut
description: Well, barbarian, the time has come to test your skills and prove your worth to the barbarian community.  In order to advance to the level of Tribesman, you must first defeat the barbarian who stands in front of you.  The large barbarian awaits your first move.

name: The Blue Training Hut
description: You are now worthy of the title Tribesman.  It is important for barbarians to use their size and strength in battle.  You should return to this site when you are ready to advance to Tribesman Second Class.

name: The Green Training Hut
description: Only the true and brave tribesman may advance to the next level.  To  prove this to your elders, you must first defeat the barbarian who stands in front of you.  Only through this trial by combat can you advance to the next level.  The barbarian awaits your first move.

name: The Green Training Hut
description: Congratulations.  You are now worthy to train to the level of Tribesman, Second Class.  With this rank, you will have additional hit point and more healing power.  When you are ready to advance again, come back to this location and enter the red training hut.

name: The Red Barbarian Training Hut
description: Before any barbarian advances to the next level, they must first face the trial of combat.  Being that combat is the most important factor in the development of the barbarian's character, the elders of the barbarian community demand that you show proof of your skills and worthiness to advance to the next level.

name: The Red Training Hut
description: You have completed your training on this side of the river and now should begin adventuring in the higher level barbarian pits across the Ramdes  River.  Your next training location will be located on the east side of the river.

name: Penelope's Toy Store
description: Penelope doesn't really like to sell toys, but prefers to buy them. She makes her living selling musical instruments in the next room of the store, but likes to display her collection of toys in here.  Most of the toys were hand made by master craftsmen and there are signs asking you to please not handle the merchandise.

name: Gustave and Hanabal's Fine Swords
description: Gustave is a rotund little dwarf who owns this shoppe and sells swords by day, but visits the ladies by night.  He has been known to stagger down the streets at dawn, singing at the top of his voice, with several dwarven ladies on his massive arms.  But he does make very fine swords. A list is available for prospective customers.

name: The Barbarian Training Pits
description: The barbarian tribes do not like to promote their own kind without some proof of their worthiness to live up to the barbarian codes of battle, those being kill, maim, destroy.  If you wish to advance to the level of Tribesman, you should enter the blue hut.  If you are already a  Tribesman and wish to advance to second class, you should enter the green hut.  If you wish to assume the highest ranking of Tribesman, first class, you should enter the red hut.

name: The Barbarian Training Pits
description: These pits are designed for the lower level barbarians aiming to advance beyond the title of grunt.  If you are seeking to rise to the level grunt second class, you should enter the yellow hut.  If you are now ready to be called a grunt, first class, you should enter the orange hut, and be prepared for a good battle.

name: Temple of the Rising Moon Foyer
description: The Temple of the Rising Moon is a shrine dedicated towards the Human Greek Goddess Artemis, known primarily for patronizing the hunter and the act of hunting.  Artemitis is the sister twin of Apollo and daugther of Zeus and Leto.  She is almost always associated with the full moon.   Hunters and adventurers often come here to pray before heading out of the city to the unknown.

name: Main Hallway
description: The long hallway you are walking down is decorated in the finest golds and silvers the lands have to offer.  Donations from the wealthy and the poor all go towards dedicating the temple to Artemis, who demands only the best from her worshippers.  On the south wall, there is a door which leads to the New Worshippers Office.  On the east wall is an unmarked door.

name: Main Hallway
description: The hallway turns to the west, heading towards a large room a bit further to the west.  The hall heads towards the entrance of the Temple to the southeast.  The walls are covered with portraits of Artemis in various locations in the wilderness.  Artemis is the goddess of the hunt and  provides strength and courage against enemies of greater power.

name: Main Hallway
description: The hallway opens into a large chapel to the west where anyone may  enter to pray, study or just rest under the watchful eye of Artemis. There is a door to the north which reads "Priestess' Quarters".   There is another door on the south which reads "Meditation Chamber". The chapel is relatively deserted at this time, but shows a bit of movement occasionally.

name: New Member's Office
description: All new members must come to this office before the goddess Artemis will accept them.  The old lady tells you that the main chapel is located to the northwest down the main hall.  In the chapel, the pulpit is towards the north and the prayer chamber is to the south.  The door in the  hallway to the north leads to the priestess' chambers, where she would be willing to train you in the ways of Artemis.

name: Open Air Altar
description: The altar is covered with voodoo symbols and blood.  A still twitching corpse of a headless human lies on top of it, with fresh blood running into troughs designed to funnel the warm, red liquid into a basin at the end of the altar.  Behind you, at the jungle edge, you hear a low, monotonous chanting.

name: Fire Walker's Coal Bed
description: The heat from the coals makes the air shimmer, distorting figures of dancing images on the other side of the pit.  A black man stands in the middle of the pits, wearing nothing but a pair of white canvas pants, and laughs as he waves for you to join him.  the live coals beneath his bare feet sizzle and pop as he waits for you.

name: Bed of Hot Coals
description: The heat sears and swirls around you but strangely you are unharmed by it. It's difficult to see through the wavering heat flow, but a shirtless black man is apparently standing in the midst of the flames, totally untouched by the blistering heat.  He seems to have a protective aura around him that is also enveloping you.

name: Venus Gardens Plant Shoppe
description: The Venus Gardens are known for their carniverous plants.  Unfortunately, the plants have seemed to gain some intelligence and have overpowered the shoppe owners.  The store is now run by very large venus fly traps and lillianril, waiting for some unsuspecting victim to come in and feed them.  There is a porch outside where some of the larger plants are basking in the sun.

name: Venus Gardens Porch
description: The porch area is rather nicely decorated, but has started to deteriorate since the carnifers took over.  The sunny porch area is optimal for the  plant's growth.  Large plants seem to be moving everywhere about you.

name: The Angry Camper Hunting Supplies
description: The Angry Camper Hunting Supplies shop is dedicated towards the lay  person who wants to be protected from the dangers of the wilderness. This shop specializes in simple weapons that just about anyone can  use.  Although they're not very powerful, a simple show of force is  sometimes all you need to ward off a hungry bear.

name: The Invisible Hand
description: The small, cramped guild is filled with all sorts of weapons and other junk.  It looks like they'll fence any of the booty you've recovered during your conquests in exchange for gold.  You had better make sure that you only left the things you want to leave behind.  You never know who might be picking your pocket.

name: Bysantal's General Goods and Services
description: Bysantal prides himself on being able to get just about anything anyone wants, for a reasonable price.  The general store is proof of this fact. Everything from mountain climbing gear to torches and lanterns may be bought here.  The exit back to the street is to the west and the Angry Camper Hunting Supplies shop is located to the south.  It is a small subsidiary of Bysantal's shop.

name: Bysantal's General Goods and Services Storage Shack
Leonardo's Foundry
description: The plaza provides access to the three shops Leonardo's Foundry services. The Custom Swords shop is located to the north, where fantastic swords of unequalled quality (and price) may be purchased.  To the west is Unblemished Armor, where fine chain and and brigandine armor may be purchased.  To the south is Cast Iron Shields, where strong shields of the finest iron are built to stand the toughest battles.  The exit to Main Street is to the east.

name: Custom Swords
description: Various types of weapons may be purchased from Leonardo here, but his specialty is swords.  Almost every known type of sword may be purchased here.  There are a couple of gold swords also for sale as well, but  since gold is so soft, they do not make very good weapons.  They are worth quite a bit, though, more as collector's items.

name: Unblemished Armor
description: Armors are Leonardo's specialty, specifically chain and brigandine.  Chain Mail is made of interlocking metalic rings which provide excellent protection against enemy swords.  Brigandine mail is similar to chain,  but made with light plates of metal rivited in between cloth and leather. It provides less protection, but is an inexpensive alternative to chain.

name: Cast Iron Shields
description: Shields are essential to any warrior's equipment lists, and only the finest iron and metal shields are sold here.  All shields are pretty generic, but as is usually the case, the larger the shield, the more protection it give you.  A good shield complements all the other armor you are wearing.

name: The Rusty Nail Saloon
description: The Rusty Nail is just west of the Golden Dolphin Inn and is probably the first thing people see when they enter the city from the South Gate.  It is therefore almost always filled with visitors and guests from all over the realm.  Brawls are unlikely, but possible if some people drink a little too much.  The waitresses are running around frantically trying to serve everyone.

name: Coffin
description: Being so dark, it's unlikely you will actually see anything even if you happen to have a torch.  By the way, what are you doing in a coffin? Most people are dead if they find themselves in here.  To get out, try opening the casket.

name: The Davis Brothers Mortuary
description: A mortuary isn't always the funnest place to visit.  In fact, it's down- right boring.  You might be able to find some friends who have died in battle in the Arena or have fallen down a mountain.  The mortuary exits to the west onto Marina Way, and east to Eidenhoft Boulevard.

name: The Golden Dragon Cantina
description: The Golden Dragon Cantina caters to the more elite crowd from the  administrative districts to the south.  Commoners are typically unwelcome, unless it's dwarf tossing night, whence most dwarves and other strong competitors are welcome to come in for a drink before the games begin.  Otherwise, the bouncers are likely to throw you out or try to kill you (or both).

name: Oceancrest Central Arena Reception Area
description: The Oceancrest Central Arena is divided into a number of smaller  arenas and combat zones for the pleasure of the viewing audience.  To the southeast is the Central Arena, where combatants engage strong opponents in hand-to-hand combat.  The Central Arena is divided into many small areas of individual skill including a one-on-one combat arena.  To the southwest are the Pits of Doom.  The Pits are heavily guarded at all times and house a number of large dragons.  To the north is the Game Arena, where combatants use wit and skill to eventually defeat the great Wizard of Kaldais.

name: Arena Events and Information Center
description: The Oceancrest Central Arena is not a place for the weak-natured, weak- stomached or weak-of-heart.  It is divided into three major Arenas: the Central Arena, where players engage in hand-to-hand combat with various gladiators and other fighters for victory and glory.  The map shows the various degrees of difficulty in the arena.  The Pits of Doom are holding pens for large dragons.  These should not be tampered with without extreme care.  Dragons enjoy gladiators for lunch or at least a light snack before dinner.  The Game Arena is the largest of them all which combines skill and strategy to defeat the Wizard of Kaldais.

name: Central Arena Preparation Room
description: The Preparation Lounge is designed to be a locker room for the  gladiators before they venture out into the arena.  To the east is the Warm-Up Arena, where young gladiators and knights may challenge you.  Further south is the Knight's Honor Arena.  Knights do not initiate the fighting, but will fight a frightening battle once  engaged.  To the south of the Ready Room is the One-on-One Combat Arena.  Only one person may enter this arena at a time to battle the lone gladiator in a one-on-one, hand-to-hand, to the death combat.

name: Warm-Up Arena
description: The Warm-Up Arena is designed to prepare combatants for the thrills  and excitement which awaits them to the south in the Knight's Honor Arena and the Gladiator's Pits.  There's not much of a crowd watching you here as they're all down further south where all the excitement and killing is.  There does seem to be quite a bit of blood on the ground, though.

name: Knight's Honor Arena
description: The Knight's Honor Arena provides participants the challenge of the mighty and powerful knights, rangers and other honorable fighters, who primarily attack only when attacked first.  But just because these knights do not initiate a fight, that doesn't mean that they are unwilling to finish you off.

name: The Gladiator Pits
description: The coarse sand beneath your feet absorbs the blood of past victims of both the gladiators and the participants (mostly the latter).  The gladiators are ruthless fighters who will waste no time in attacking you when you least expect it.  There are a number of different levels of gladiators, but most of them look the same.  To the west is the Monster's Feeding Grounds, where combatants fight non-humanoid monsters who are hungry for dinner.

name: Monster Feeding Grounds
description: The Monsters seldom pick up after themselves, and the guards don't like to even enter this dangerous arena.  Those who die here are left to be digested by the monsters that ate them.  The Gladiator Pits are to the east and the One-on-One combat arena is to the north.  Only one person can be in that arena at once.  The monsters are starting to smell some fresh meat so you had better be on your guard.

name: One-on-One Arena
description: The ultimate test of a warrior's ability is their ability to stand up  to a single gladiator in a one-on-one, hand-to-hand, battle to the  death combat.  Not just anyone can do such a feat, but there's no  shame in a proud fight to the death.  A quick escape back into the Preparation Room is not available as the door to the room has been sealed from the opposite side.

name: Pits of Doom Training Room
description: The Pits of Doom are typically reserved for the most famous and most powerful gladiators.  What lies beyond the door to the south are perhaps the most powerful creatures to roam the world.  Luckily, the great fighters have subdued these dragons and now there are here for your fighting enjoyment.  You have been warned, and the management claims no responsibility for anyone or anything in the Pits of Doom.

name: Pits of Doom - Yellow Level
description: The Pits of Doom are constructed into three levels of difficulty,  Yellow being the easiest, if there is such a thing, and Red being the most difficult.  To live up to its name, as you descend down the levels of the Pits, the danger increases.  It is rumored that there is a fourth level below Red, but no one has ever survived to verify that rumor.

name: Pits of Doom - Orange Level
description: As you work your way down to the Pits of Doom, you can feel the heat rising and your adrenaline kicking in.  This level is exclusively dominated by metallic dragons.  You can hear them moving around and see flashes of fire from their nostrils in the dim light.  It's a hard climb going up or down.  Don't you wish you had some climbing equipment? On the other hand, it might not be advisable to go any further down.

name: Pits of Doom - Red Level
description: The Red Level is caked with the singed blood of past victims.  The most dangerous and mean-tempered dragons dwell on this level and are always on the lookout for food.  Since not very many people think about coming in here, they don't get to eat very often.  Well, at least you now know that these dragons exist and they're not just some made-up fantasy.   Whether or not you'll be able to tell anyone may be another story.

name: Pits of Doom - Black Level
description: The question is whether or not you can survive long enough not only to get out of this level, but to survive the other three levels on your way out.  Then again, this place doesn't look all that bad.  It's very dark, and silent.  You wouldn't think anything could live this far down.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: This is a very high class neighborhood with several swank shops to the south.  Further to the east is the famous Ashton Falls Resort.  Many of the city's most wealthy and influential residents live there, and the  small shopping center on the south side of the avenue caters to their needs.  One of the best restaurants in the city, Antoine's Grill, is in there.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: A large wall on the north side of the road surrounds the famous resort, but a very ornate gate is set into a portico and a guard station stands just inside.  There is a broad walkway to the south, leading to a shopping center with small shops and restaurants.  An exclusive night spot is near the entrance to the midway.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: It's very expensive to live in the Ashton Falls Resort, but many of the higher level people in Oceancrest consider it worth it.  The gardens inside are said to rival any in the world, and the living spaces are secluded and very private.  The main entrance is further to the east, and a quaint little shopping center is a little way to the west.

name: Oceancrest Avenue
description: Further to the east you can see the intersection of Oceancrest Avenue and Riverdell Way.  Immediately to the north is a wide marbled stairway which leads to a guarded entrance to the most expensive place to live in all of the city.  On the south side of the avenue is a small park with large shade trees and well kept lawns.

name: Under the Ashton River Bridge
description: There is a stench that's difficult to ignore coming from a pile of rusted armor nearby.  There are a lot of scattered bones lying about, and a number of weapons on the ground.  A small cave is just above the waterline and a snuffling noise seems to be coming from its interior.  What was it that sign up there said about trolls?  A path leads to an orchid above.

name: Waterfront Plaza
description: Waterfront Plaza boasts a number of specialty shops.  To the northeast is Rudolph's Fighting Academy, where fighters of low to middle level experience train.  To the northwest is the Adventures Unlimited shop called Treasure Maps and Accessories.  Although they sell treasure maps and other scrolls, it has not been determined if these are very useful. To the southeast is Renee's Elven Leather Works for fine leather crafted material, made the way elves like it.  To the south is the Tired Camel Fine Imports shop where useful items may be traded.  Finally, on the southwest is Michael's Repair Shop, where all weapons and armors may be repaired for a modest fee.

name: Adventures Unlimited Treasure Maps and Accessories
description: Adventures Unlimited is a franchise service which buys and sells treasure maps and other artifacts for the treasure hunter.  Although they have a reputation for being reputable, no one has ever seemed to survive long enough to find the treasure they claim to have bought a map to.  Whether or not treasure exists probably depends on the skill of the purchaser, and not the reputability of the seller.

name: Renee's Elven Leather Works
description: Leather is one of the easiest hides to work with and elves have mastered the art of making goods with the fine hides.  A variety of imported elven leather works have been put on sale here and line the walls.  The most common are suits of leather which protect slightly better than normal leather suits because they are custom-fitted for each individual.  It is an outstanding choice for mages and thieves who rely on light, easy to wear armor.

name: Renee's Elven Leather Works Storage Shack
The Timid Camel Fine Imports Shop
description: Since not many people like to travel through the desert, goods from the other side of the world seldom ever reach Oceancrest, and even moreso the other way around.  Various interesting daggers and swords from a completely different society are for sale here, but at a very expensive price.

name: The Timid Camel Fine Imports Storage Shack
Michael's All-Purpose Repair Shop
description: O'Nalle does a lot of work on swords and armors, but can fix just about anything known to man and even a few things not known by man.  The  price is fairly modest for simple items, but gets rather expensive for exotic and enchanted items.  But some things are just irreplacible if they're broken.

name: Rudolph's Fighting Academy
description: Rudolph's Fighting Academy is a moderate-level training location for  Fighters wishing to obtain Warrior status.  If you are applying for  Warrior status for the first time, you should enter the blue door.  If you are applying for Warrior Second Class status, enter the green door. If you are applying for Warrior First Class status, enter the red door. Behind each door, you will find a single opponent that you must defeat. Once defeated in hand-to-hand combat, you will be allowed to train.

name: The Blue Training Room
description: The fighter must be strong and wise in battle.  You are to match strengths with this warrior in order to advance to the status of Warrior yourself. The Blue Warrior awaits your first move.

name: The Blue Training Room
description: This is the training location for the Warrior Class.  If you have the money to train, you may do so now.  If you do not have the money, you   will have to come back at a later time and defeat the Blue Warrior again. The training academy cannot afford to train people for free.

name: The Green Training Room
description: The fighter must be strong and wise.  In order to advance to the next level, you must be able to defeat this warrior in single-handed combat. The Green Warrior awaits your first move.

name: The Blue Training Room
description: You have proven your strength in battle.  In order to advance, you must donate a sum of money to the academy for your training.  Unfortunately, running an academy is anything but free.  Once this fee is paid, you will  be formally declared a Warrior, Second Class.

name: The Red Training Room
description: The Red Warrior stands before you, waiting for your first move.  He is very experienced, and has dashed the hopes of many young warriors who were not really ready for the added responsibilities of the next level.  Once you defeat the Red Warrior, you may train for Warrior, First Class.

name: The Red Training Room
description: Congratulations!  You have advanced to the highest rank of Warrior, which  is Warrior, First Class.  Your skills have advanced beyond the training capabilities of this facility.  When you are ready to advance again, please  consult Roland's Royal Fighting Academy on Nissiau Lane.

name: Riverdell Center for Tracking Training
description: The large complex to the east provides you with the best training  facilities for rangers through the fifteenth level and beyond.  Only Rangers may enter the park to work on their skills.  All training locations are well hidden, so you must use your tracking and searching skills to find them.  Once you have entered the park, you must find one of the training locations before you can leave.

name: The Swift Hand
description: This small building houses a small group of pickpockets who will gladly fence just about anything you might want to get off your hands quickly and without any questions.  The Swift Hand is a low level guild and  does not offer too many services to the advanced thief, but caters to the rogues of the land.

name: The Swift Hand Training Room
description: This secret initiation and training location allows young thieves to  advance their way up the thieving ladder.  Thieves may train up to the level of Rogue, First Class, after which they must seek out a more suitable guild in perhaps a richer neighborhood in order to advance  to the status of a Footpad.

name: The Silent Knife Training Room
description: Only lower level Minor Assassins may enter this area to train in some  basic assassination skills.  Once you reach Minor Assassin, First Class, this center becomes much too simplistic for your talents, and you are  forced to go out and look for a higher quality Assassins' Guild.  Some of your brothers suggest a place known as the Rusty Dagger, but are  hesitant to tell you where that is.

name: The Silent Knife
description: This rustic location, pretty much falling apart everywhere you look, is one of the major Assassin's Guilds in Oceancrest.  Luckily, it is not a very popular one, and its current use now is primarily for training low level Assassins in the art of cuthroat killing without the victim knowing what hit them.  Only Minor Assassins may enter the training room to the  south.

name: Silk Dreams Nightclub
description: Well, just about everyone knows that the Silk Dreams Nightclub isn't really a night club at all.  It's more of a brothel, except it has some class.  There are a couple of large bouncers standing around waiting to throw out anyone who makes any trouble.  The full bar towards the rear of the establishment provides drinks for customers.

name: Silk Dreams Bar
description: The bar is a less active location than the main seating area to the east. Most people will just leave you alone to drink away your problems.  The bouncers will also probably leave you alone in here, but an occassional criminal may come by to pick your pocket.  The bar is well-stocked with all the finest human, elven and dwarven brews, including a very strong dwarven lager which will straighten any man's beard.

name: Silk Dreams Dancing Stage
description: Now you've really pissed some people off.  It's not a very good idea to jump onto the stage while the girls are dancing.  A number of  bouncers try to get you off the stage as the dancers are running about creating more of a havoc.  You best return to your table, to the north, if you want to avoid a conflict.

name: Silk Dreams Backstage Area
description: The backstage area is not a very smart place to be right now, because all the bouncers are likely to be after you.  Nevertheless, you have made your way back here and might as well take in the scenery before being kicked out of the club.  The stage is to the north and the dressing room is to the south.

name: Silk Dreams Dressing Room
description: Somehow you have managed to find your way backstage and now find yourself in the dressing rooms of the stage dancers.  Not that you're really  complaining, but the dancers sure are and the bouncers are likely to come in at any moment now to throw you out or at least hurt you very badly.  You can get out to the backstage area to the north.

name: Entrance to DeNail's Corn Fields
description: DeNail is always willing to hire unskilled labor because he doesn't  really have to pay them anything to clear out the crows and other pesty creatures that eat up the corn.  The exit to the west leads out to  Hafnia Way in the southwestern part of town.  The corn fields are pretty large so you best watch out that you don't get lost.

name: DeNail Corn Fields
description: The corn smells sweet in the warm air.  Crows are constantly picking at the corn and your job is to scare them away.  The corn field is very  large and seems to expand in all directions.  The stalks are so tall, you can hardly see over the top.  It's even worse if you're already short.  Occassionally, you'll see some farm workers hauling away the corn.

name: DeNail Corn Fields
description: The corn smells sweet in the warm air.  Crows are constantly picking at the corn and your job is to scare them away.  The corn field is very  large and seems to expand in all directions.  The stalks are so tall, you can hardly see over the top.  It's even worse if you're already short.  Occasionally, you'll see some farm workers hauling away the corn.
