The corn field is very  large and seems to expand in all directions.  The stalks are so tall, you can hardly see over the top.  It's even worse if you're already short.  Occassionally, you'll see some farm workers hauling away the corn.

name: Entrance to DeNail's Corn Fields
description: DeNail is always looking for young, strong people that he doesn't have to pay to do his work.  Therefore, he only lets unskilled labor into  his ranch.  The large corn fields are immense, spanning to the west as far as the eye can see.  The talk corn stalks prevent you from  seeing very far in any one direction.  There sure is a lot of corn here.

name: Millwood Memorial Mayor's Office Foyer
description: The Mayor's Office is the seat of power for the city, or so the people who work there believe.  Mayor Millwood was in fact a very powerful mage and therefore, when his time came, he did not feel like just giving up and dying.  Although it cannot be proved that Millwood's experiment in the afterlife worked, many people do belive that the Mayor still haunts the office.  The first successor to Millwood was mysteriously killed  (thought to have committed suicide) by a letter opener through his temple. No one has since volunteered to be the next mayor.  Somehow or another, though, things still get accomplished.

name: Millwood Mayor's Office Hallway
description: The lavishly decorated hallway contains many portraits of the many mayors of Oceancrest, beginning with Millwood of Uxtiva.  The halls are said to be haunted by the second-to-last Mayor of Oceancrest, also ironically named Millwood.  It is also said that Millwood is a lich, and therefore no life insurance claims have been paid to his heirs, and will not be until he is proven to be dead.  The office is pretty desolate now, and seems abandoned.

name: Millwood Mayor's Office Hallway
description: The long hallway seems to drag on, but you know you haven't really gone all that far.  After all, the building wasn't that big.  You finally come to two large doors, one on the east wall and one of the west wall. The plaque above the east door says "Mayor's Office" and the one on the west door has "Keep Out" scribbled across it in dried blood.  There is no plaque on this door, but you can see by the dust outline that  it was there originally.

name: The Mayor's Office
description: The dust has settled rather uniformly across the entire room.  Just by walking around, you are kicking up dust.  So much so, your vision begins to look obscured.  You can see a large desk to the west with a giant chair behind it.  The deskplate says "Mayor Millwood", but you can't tell if there's anyone sitting behind the desk.

name: The Room of Souls
description: Kaldeas built this room to house the undead creatures he consulted.    Not only does this seem like some purgatory for undead creatures, it also appears to be some sort of dimensional door into another world. Unfortunately, you can't really see enough to make any sense out of any of this.  However, the large number of undead creatures in the room makes you believe that perhaps you will be joining their ranks soon.

name: Dante's Daggers and Darts Shoppe
description: No self-respecting thief or assassin would be caught dead without a good dagger or a couple of poisoned darts.  These fantastic weapons are ideal for backstabbing and throwing.  You have to watch Dante, though.  he's been in  business for ages, and knows how to con people out of a lot of money.

name: Dave's Darts and Daggers Storage Shack
Ennia's Venemous Pets
description: Poisions and venoms have always been somewhat of a curiosity, and Ennia has made her life dealing with such things.  Of course, since she  deals so much with the venomous and poisonous pets, she always has antedotes and other remedies ready at a moment's notice.  There is a small exhibit to the west with various exotic animals.

name: Ennia's Pet Playroom
description: This large room is surrounded by glass and protected from the outside world.  Oddly, you have found yourself curious about the animals in the room and have foolishly entered.  The large scorpions and spiders probably think you're dinner.  They're obviously not in the mood for playing around.  It's a good think Ennia carries a good number of  poison remedies.

name: Ivanhouse Sporting Arena - Challenger's Ready Room
description: All players must enter the Challenger's Ready Room before they can enter the main combat arenas.  The large sporting facility supports a number of lower-level arenas where small groups of low level gladiators can challenge single monsters.  There are three main arenas:  The first is a low-level arena where less-experienced players may challenge a large gladiator. The other two are one-on-one arenas where you may challenge single  gladiators in hand-to-hand, mortal combat.

name: Ivanhouse Sporting Arena - Entrance
description: At this point, you have a number of choices.  To the north, you may enter the Beginner's Circle.  Up to three gladiators may engage a single  opponent.  This area is exclusively for lower-level characters who have not quite mastered the art of gladiator fighting.  To the northeast is the Gladiator Pit, a small arena where you may challenge a human gladiator in one-on-one combat.  To the northwest is the Mul Pit, another small arena where you may challenge a mul gladiator, a human/dwarven half-breed, in hand-to-hand combat.  Again, this arena only permits one competitor at a time.

name: Ivanhouse Sporting Arena - Beginner's Circle
description: The Ivanhouse Sporting Arena is designed for more one-on-one combat with equally matched opponents.  The Beginner's Circle allows you, with up to two of your comrades, to take on a human gladiator.  The gladiator is tough, but you have a three-to-one advantage on him.  If this isn't enough, you can always run away very quickly.

name: Ivanhouse Sporting Arena - Gladiator Pit
description: The Gladiator's Pit faces you off with an equally-capable human  gladiator.  Althoguh gladiators are trained nearly from birth to be efficient killing machines, they are only strong in sheer brute strength. Chances are you can outwit him without too much effort.  Although they are strong, they're not all that bright.

name: Ivanhouse Sporting Arena - Mul Pit
description: Taking the height of the human and strength of the dwarven parents, the mul has come to be one of the most feared gladiators.  Being outcasts from almost all society, they tend to find themselves in arenas anyway, fighting for their right to survive and gain glory.  The Mul Pit may be a dangerous arena because only one fighter may be in here at once, but the muls have no such restrictions.

name: Evander's World Of Weapons Plaza
description: The Main Plaza gives you access to all the major shops in this complex, all owned and managed by Evander.  On the east is the largest building which houses the Evander Repair Shop.  Here, Evander or one of his trusted laborers will repair damaged weapons.  On the northwest is the Polearms Emporium where all sorts of unique and interesting weapons may be bought.  On the west is the Armory, dealing mostly with chain mail and other metallic armor.  On the southwest is the Swordsmith, where  various swords and daggers may be bought.

name: Evander's Repair Shop
description: The Repair Shop is one of the best around.  The skilled workers provide  the best service, especially on metallic armors and weapons.  A large worker covered in soot comes up to the front desk and asks you if he can help you with something.

name: Evander's Poles and Polearms
description: You can see a number of large pole weapons on display here, including  some strange ones you might not have seen before.  Most pole weapons consist of a long, wooden pole, topped with a large metal blade.   Variaties of the blades make some weapons better than others for  certain types of battles.

name: Evander's Poles and Polearms Storage Shack
Evander's Armory
description: Evander's foundry specializes in metallic armors and some weapons.  You  won't find any cloth or leather supplies here.  Only the finest metals and materials go into these fine armors.  Evander's Armory is about the only armory in town that also uses adamantine metal to make their scale mail. Although scale mail is less protective than chain, it lasts significantly longer than virtually all other conventional metals.

name: Evander's Swords
description: This large shop stocks all kinds of swords and weapons of all kind.  The selection seems pretty good, but the weapons are not of that great of quality.  However, if you just need a simple long sword because the one you have broke, this is the place to go.

name: Evander's Pawn Shop
description: Buying back weapons is not looked upon highly by the great powers that be, especially if the items are stolen after a battle or other conquest. Nevertheless, Evander isn't one not to bend the rules.  So, he'll try to give you an honest price for whatever it is you have to offer.

name: Path To The Manor
description: There are two paths here.  The larger brick-laid one heads west towards the Manor, while the smaller and less traveled one goes to the southern side of the estate.  Absolutely nothing appears to be growing anywhere, and the atmosphere is all together creepy.  Some say they can hear wolves howling into the night when the moon is full, but it's kinda silent right now.

name: Path To The Manor
description: The Manor looks much bigger than it did from the road.  The creaky wood that has deteriorated over the many years looks like it might fall apart if you sneeze in just the right direction.  There is a door directly to the west of you that obviously leads into the creepy manor itself.  You have to keep saying to yourself, it's just an old house, nothing more...

name: Path Around the Manor
description: You are on a strange path that leads around the Manor towards a large cave-like structure to the west.  You can hear a lot of howling and growling from within the cave.  The path appears to lead directly into the cave.  The path heads back towards the entrance to the Manor to the north.

name: Werewolves' Den
description: You have wandered into the deadly realm of the dreaded werewolves.  Some are a little tougher than others, but they will all try to convert you to their way of thinking with a poisonous bite.  The path leads deeper into the cave if you go west, but back out to the manor entrance if you go east.

name: Werewolves' Den
description: Werewolves appear to come from every direction once they smell blood.  Now that you have invaded their sanctuary, the larger werewolves come out in packs looking for prey.  Hopefully, you won't be a statistic in the morning papers.  The trail outside the den leads east to the front of the Manor and the gate, and it also leads west to the rear of the estate.

name: Path West of the Manor
description: As you walk along the path, you can see the impressive Mausoleum located towards the northeast.  The path apparently circles around it and then eventually goes to the front entrance if you follow it to the north.  If you go east you will come to the Werewolves Den south of the Manor.

name: Path West of the Manor
description: The path ends at the front door of the Mausoleum.  It is a large, stone door that doesn't seem to want to budge.  There is a small window that you can look into.  The Mausoleum is pretty small and holds but a single coffin in the center of the room.  Other than that, the room is virtually empty, with a few pictures lying thrown about.

name: Natasha's Mausoleum
description: The large mausoleum looked much smaller than it did from the outside.   The jet black coffin in the center of the room looks like it hasn't been touched in ages.  Once you step inside the mausoleum, the door slams shut behind you and the coffin opens up to reveal the Countess Natasha de Allisk, no longer in hibernation as you had wished.

name: Dryfus' Elephant Leather Works
description: Dryfus' Elephant Leather Works is one of the few dwarven-owned businesses in Oceancrest.  There isn't much of a demand for smaller-sized armors, but Dryfus carries most styles.  The Elephant Leather is twice as strong as regular leather armor, and usually lasts quite a bit longer as well.  The light leather armor is also custom made for dwarves, gnomes and halfings, and lasts significantly longer than standard leather armor.

name: Dryfus' Elephant Leather Works Storage Shack
North Oceancrest Post Office #19
description: In order to better serve the people of Oceancrest, the postal system was enacted to provide superior communications between various people in the city.  Because of the vast size the city had grown to, it became quite a task to walk from one end of the city to the other, just to  visit for a few hours.

name: Kista's North Gate
description: Outside the city gates is a very long road which connects to the great city of Oceancrest to the west.  As you stand here just inside the huge gate, you notice there are stables to the east where you may leave your horses, or whatever you may be riding.  Further to the south is the center  of town, where you may find more information about this famous city.

name: Kista Stables and Exercise Yard
description: The exercise yard is a large field which extends to the north and east of the stables.  It is primarily a large track where people can train their horses for everything from simple trail riding to knightly jousting and fox hunting.

name: Lake View Road
description: Lake View Road circles around Lake Kista on the northeast side of the town.  To the west, you can see the generic stables used by all the citizens of the town.  On the east side are the stables for visiting dignitaries who come to Kista to discuss important issues of the day.

name: Dignitary Stables
description: The various dignitaries who visit Kista prefer not to have their horses associated with the other riff-raff that come wandering into the town.  The facility here is more exclusive and the guards do not like commoners such as yourself poking their noses around here.

name: Granary
description: The granary is a storage facility for grains and rices.  Since the forests around Kista are not capable of producing grains, they are often imported from towns such as Brownhaven where corn and wheat almost grow naturally.  This facility stores these grains as supply lines are not very reliable and caravans might not arrive for as long as six months at a time.

name: Dairy Production and Storage Facility
description: The town of Kista is rather small and requires a minimal amount of  dairy cows to produce their necessary dietary requirements.  However, some of the cheeses that come out of this plant are said to be the very best in the world.  All the cheese is churned by hand making the process very time consuming.  When the cows are not in their stables, they are resting in the field enclosed by the facility.

name: Lake View Road
description: Lake View Road proceeds around the city's granary and dairy storage areas bringing you towards Lake Kista.  The shimmering blue water of the lake is breathtaking, even though the lake itself isn't much  bigger than the city.  To the west you can see the dairy cows and  production area.  There is a small field of grass where the cows are sleeping under thick and bountiful fruit trees.

name: Lake View Road
description: The lake is higher and to the north and towards the east, but it is said to be an easy climb from here.  Kista is close by in the southern direction. Kista is known far and wide throughout the Land of Mordor as a beautiful place to visit, with wonderful gardens and pleasant people.  Many of the political decisions that affect the entire land are made here, because politicians also recognize the beauty of Kista and hold many conferences in the famous Towers of Kista.

name: Myrr Lane/Kista Avenue Intersection
description: On the southeast side of the intersection there is a lot that seems to be  covered with a giant growth of some sort of fungus.  It seems to be alive, as you can see it move occasionally.

name: Myrr Lane/Pearl Avenue Intersection
description: Pearl Avenue comes to an end here (or starts here, depending on how you look at it.)  Pearl Avenue leads into the heart of the city of Kista passing by the Great Library and the Towers of Kista.  The library is     where the greatest wise men in the Land of Mordor come to meet.

name: Myrr Lane/West Lake View Road
description: Lake View Road actually joins Myrr Lane again a few kilometers east of here.  Going north will bring you close to the cold shores of the beautiful Lake Kista.  To the south, you see Hogoth's Beer Garden, a large public structure where weary travelers can rest before continuing on their way.

name: Myrr Lane/Charybdis Way Intersection
description: Charybdis Way runs through the center of Kista and takes you close to the Towers themselves.  The Red Dragon Pub is located on the west side of Aquamarine Way just south of here.  The Great Observatory is on the southeast corner of the intersection.

name: Myrr Lane/Ivory Way Intersection
description: Ivory Way runs along the eastern side of the City of Kista.  On the southwest corner of the intersection is the Great Observatory.  The public entrance is on Tiamat Lane to the south.   Iilandi University  maintains several research centers here in the city of Kista.  The  Althemanian Campus is southeast of here.

name: Lake View Road
description: East Lake View Road runs around Lake Kista located north of the city.  On the south side of the road is the famous Rhinefield Building where researchers have been studying beasts who are capable of mind-control. There are a number of buildings located on the campus to the south, but the main entry is through the Rhinefield Building.

name: Kista Detention and Correctional Facility
description: The detention and correctional facility was designed to hold criminals and other rogues who continue to plague our society, and keep them off the streets.  To date, no one has escaped from this facility.

name: Hogoth's Beer Garden
description: This pleasant little beer garden has both indoor and outdoor drinking areas, and is a favorite place for both travelers and locals in the afternoon and evening.  Travelers can walk across the way from the stables to the north and find good company here.  It's always nice to hear the latest stories of adventure and catch up on the gossip.

name: The Red Dragon Tavern
description: The tavern is well kept by Kaliv and Crystal, who have claimed (while under the influence) that they have single-handedly killed a red dragon after it had burned off all their armor and melted their weapons.  They claim to have used their last remaining magic spells to finally subdue the dragon.

name: The Rhinefield Building
description: This is one of four buildings on the campus which is dedicated to the study of para-psychology.  An intense effort is being made to understand exactly how people can learn to control the forces of the mind.  Its been known for a long time that there are lower beasts which use mind-control to capture their prey, and although the study of such beasts is dangerous, several researchers have undertaken the project.

name: Tiamat Lane/Kista Avenue Intersection
description: Tiamat Lane heads to the east from here, and Kista Avenue continues to the north and south.  There is a small publishing company on the corner. Farther south, on the east side of the avenue, you see a building painted with pastel stripes.

name: Tiamat Lane/Pearl Avenue Intersection
description: You are at the northwestern corner of the Kista Towers.  Four large Towers rise high above the rest of the city, making the city visible for many kilometers in any direction.  The Towers are actually a great fortress surrounded by a moat which is filled with terrible monsters.  The entrance   to the Towers is located on Tower Lane.

name: Tiamat Lane/Charybdis Way Intersection
description: The northeastern corner of the Kista Towers looks similar to the north- western corner at the intersection of Tiamat and Pearl.  The moat seems much wider here than at Pearl Avenue.  Some say the monsters are bigger  on this side.  The entrance to the Great Observatory is east of here.

name: Tiamat Lane/Commerce Street Intersection
description: There is a small street to the south which is called Commerce Street. A number of book dealers have opened up there to sell various books to travelers.  To the north, you see the great doors of the equally Great Observatory.

name: Tiamat Lane/Ivory Way Intersection
description: To the east, you see a large and modern complex facility that was built to accomodate the people's desire to learn more about para-psychology.  To the northwest, you can see the large dome of the Great Observatory.   Its entrance is to the west.  Ivory Way runs north and south.

name: Kista Post Office
description: The researchers on the Althemanian Campus who study mental telepathy have devised a most interesting method of delivering messages to the citizens of the land.  Simply type sendmail <person> and you can then send a message. (Be sure to hit the Enter key at the end of each line, as there is no word- wrap.)  When you are finished, hit the Enter key twice. If you are here to receive mail, type readmail.

name: Commerce Street
description: The street you are in travels north and south from here.  On the north end is the Great Observatory and to the south is the Museum.  This small street is well traveled by tourists and scholars alike, and is lined with book stores and small shops specializing in arcane and odd items.

name: Gypsy Pawn Shop
description: The gypsies are relatively quiet people, but need to make their money  somehow.  They offer to tell you your future for a share of your gold. Although most of the things they might tell you are the same thing you'd get out of a fortune cookie, your future might be in for a few surprises.

name: Randolf Lane/Ivory Way Intersection
description: Ivory Way continues to the north and south from here.  The seldom used east gate of the city is within sight eastward.   The famous Althemanian College, where studies in para-psychology are conducted, lies northeast of here.  The Kista Amphetheater is over to the southeast.

name: Randolf Lane
description: The Kista amphitheater is to the south.  Many lectures and sophisticated forms of entertainment are presented there, and it is a popular place for the city's citizens.  To the north is the entrance to the Rhinefield Building located on the Althemanian College Campus.

name: Tower Lane/Kista Avenue Intersection
description: Tower Lane is a major east-west throughfare in the city of Kista.  Directly west it dead-ends at the city's Detention and Correctional Facility, where society's ingrates are incarcerated.  It doesn't really have a correctional program, but it certainly has an excellent detention policy.  Even innocent visitors have been known to go in and never come out.

name: Tower Lane/Pearl Avenue Intersection
description: One of the great Kista Towers is on the northeast corner surrounded by a deep moat.  From time to time you see bubbles rise from the moat's waters and remember the tales told in the pubs about the monsters there.  Looking to the north you see the famous Kista Library on the west side of Pearl Avenue while to the south you see a magnificient cathedral.

name: Tower Lane
description: There is a guard house to the north that leads into the Towers, but you can see that the drawbridge is still up.  Swimming through the moat doesn't sound like a very smart thing to do.  To the south is the main town meeting hall.  The meeting hall is usually pretty busy most of the day, but is used for social gatherings in the evenings as well. The entry for the Town Hall is on Pearl Avenue.

name: Tower Lane/Charybdis Way Intersection
description: On the north side of Tower Lane are the famous Towers of Kista surrounded by a deep moat.  Further to the east, on both sides of the street, you can see the Royal Kista Arms, a hotel that caters to the upper class of society. The Milsene Museum is beyond the Kista Arms to the east.

name: Tower Lane/Commerce Street
description: There is a street to the north known as Commerce Street, which is rather narrow, but nicely lighted.   To the south is the Milsene Museum where valuable artifacts of ancient times are kept along with other unique and interesting items.  The museum is covered in a fantastic red metallic  coating which brightly reflects the sun's rays in all directions.

name: Tower Lane/Ivory Way Intersection
description: Ivory Way leads both north and south of here, following a line of trees that may be as old as the town itself.  Tower Lane leads to the west through the heart of the city.  There is a large amphitheater to the east where some of the most renouned speakers in the land are often heard to lecture.  The facility is also used for entertainment, which usually draws larger crowds.

name: Alturis Road/Kista Avenue Intersection
description: On the northeast side of the road is the magnificient Cathedral of Veratus. The Cathedral was built at the time of Randolf the Blue against the wishes of his council, but since the monks paid their taxes, they were allowed to build it anyway.  The main entrance is a little way to the east, on the south side of the road.

name: Alturis Road/Pearl Avenue Intersection
description: The Cathedral of Veratus stands proudly to the northwest.  The entrance to the Cathedral is to the west.  Pearl Avenue runs through the center of the city heading past the great Towers.  To the south, you can see  a number of archers practicing on a large field.  Better not get too  close, or you might be catching arrows.

name: Alturis Road/Garden Circle West
description: Garden Circle Road travels around the magnificent Hanging Gardens, a  monument to the queen Isaria from her husband, King Randolf the Blue. Randolf got his title by swimming in Lake Kista in the winter.  It was pretty much a ritual for him as he dove into the nearly frozen lake  every year on his birthday.

name: Alturis Road/Charybdis Way Intersection
description: The Hanging Gardens of Kista are perhaps the most impressive monument to any person ever built.  The giant monument has three levels and looks like a great fountain with exotic plants and trees growing wherever there is room.  The base of the monument is almost completely made of gold with  scattered bits of platinum and silver to give it some contrast.

name: Alturis Road/Ivory Way Intersection
description: The large amphitheater to the east is very impressive and actually fills with customers if someone of interest comes to entertain the citizens.  This does not happen as often as the council would like, but it's a great revenue for lesser known minstrels who are traveling between towns.  To the south is the great Hanging Gardens monument.  Annetol Way is to the southeast.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: The Hanging Gardens monument was built centuries ago by King Randolf the Blue for his wife, Queen Isaria, long before Kista was more than just a simple town.  The Hanging Gardens were the only things left of his glorious reign when his empire crumbled merely decades ago.  An archery range is   located on the west side of the road.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: There is a trail to the south leading out of Kista into the dense woods. Kista was founded by the Triad of Wisdom after the fall of Randolf, the creater of the Hanging Gardens.  The Triad represent the three dominant races whom the elves had contact with: the humans and the dwarves.  Although the elves were not comfortable with dwarves, they persuaded them to be a part of the Triad to promote peace in the land.  The Gardens were maintained in honor of the coming together.

name: Garden Circle Road/Ivory Way
description: Ivory Way runs along the east side of Kista and borders the city's famous Amphitheater, where many traveling minstrels play nightly.  Garden Circle takes you around the great Hanging Gardens momument to the southeast.  The Kista Temple of Jinsuti lies to the east.  Jinsuti is a high art form of  self defense taught to more advanced fighters.

name: Archery Range
description: A large mesh prevents anyone from entering the range itself, as absolutely no one is allowed in, for obvious reasons.  Unfortunately, the mesh is wide enough that an arrow can easily go through it.  There are circular targets about 50 meters to the west, and another set perhaps 25 meters south. Elena's tackle shop is through the door.

name: Elena's Archery Emporium
description: The Archery Emporium sells a number of good elven bows that work  significantly better than the ones used by humans.  Elena claims that she can't even shoot with a human crossbow.  She will be happy to teach you some basic archery skills for a price.

name: Kista Amphitheater Grass Seating
description: The grass seating here was actually unintentional.  This area was not developed, so when the Amphitheater became such a success, the regular seating was no longer sufficent and people began sitting up on the grass. Pretty soon, the grass seating area was permanently made a part of the Amphitheater.  On some occasions, even all this space isn't enough. The stage area is north of here.

name: Kista Amphitheater Main Seating
description: There are excellent seats near the stage area, and vendors are selling hot drinks and food on the side.  There are some very rich people attending, if the quality of their dress is any indication.  You can hear an orchestra tuning up, waiting for the oboe to give them an "A".

name: Kista Amphitheater Stage
description: The upper stage is rather impressive and the lower stage, designed for larger performances requiring an orchestra, is also well constructed.   The black floors make it almost impossible to see where you're stepping, but you can see the audience seating to the south.

name: Jay's Smith Shoppe
description: Several young boys are working the bellows as a stout dwarf hammers out a sword from a rod of glowing iron.  There is a clerk also near the front of the shop.  It looks like you can purchase new and used armor here, as well as get a few things repaired.

name: Eastern Entrance to the City of Kista
description: The city of Kista has a relatively short history as it was built on the ruins of the empire of Randolf the Blue.  The city operates as the center of the Triad of Wisdom, representing the three major races in the Land of Mordor.  Together, the elves, humans and dwarves built this city to be a depository of all knowledge.  The faerie folk added their touch, as well.

name: Moat Around the Kista Towers
description: The moat is depressed about three meters from the surface of the town.  Luckily, you know how to swim relatively well, but that's probably not going to save you from the alligators and other ugly creatures the  rulers of Kista keep unfed in here.  It looks like a long way up the slippery sides of the moat.

name: Moat Around the Kista Towers
description: The moat is depressed about three meters from the surface of the town.  Luckily, you know how to swim relatively well, but that's probably not going to save you from the alligators and other ugly creatures the  rulers of Kista keep unfed in here.  It looks like a long way up the slippery sides of the moat.

Luckily, you know how to swim relatively well, but that's probably not going to save you from the alligators and other ugly creatures the  rulers of Kista keep unfed in here.  It looks like a long way up the slippery sides of the moat.

name: Drawbridge Entrance to the Kista Towers
description: This small wooden room controls the opening and closing of the drawbridge which spans the tower's moat.  The moat below is a very dangerous place as it tends to be crawling with very hungry crocodiles and other monsters  that have not been categorized yet.  There are four buttons on the west wall of the guard station which control the drawbridge.

name: Front Foyer of the Kista Towers
description: The foyer is rather spacious.  Down the hall, there are two great oak doors.  A plaque on the hallway wall says "Throne Room:  Access by Appointment Only!"  Two hallways lead out of the foyer to the east and west.  To the south is the large drawbridge that leads you back out to the city.  There is a very small door also, with a very large sign over it.  "Keep Out - DANGER"

name: Throne Room
description: The thrones are empty and will remain empty so long as the twin brothers, Ragnar and Rutger, continue their violent argument for the crown of their  dead father, King Lyanden.

name: East Hallway
description: There are a number of portraits lining the walls.  Each show a group of people, usually of varying races, gathered together.  They appear to be former Council members as you recognize the faces of some of the  representatives in the newer portraits.  The long hallway continues to the north and heads west back into the main foyer.

name: East Hallway
description: The Towers of Kista (or Kista Towers) were built on the ruins of the former tyranical empire that crumbled due to the resistance by factions of human, elven and dwarven fighters.  The Towers were built as a general meeting place for the three races to get together and discuss the major problems of the world.  The four Towers represent strength, wisdom, valor  and piety.

name: East Hallway
description: Surprisingly, this place seems to be much smaller inside than it appears to be from the outside.  Although the hallway seems pretty long, there's not much to see.  The door on the east wall says "Alchemist - Keep Out".    You see a small wisp of smoke rising from the crack under the door.

name: Alchemist
description: You've never seen so many potions before, but none of them look like they are ready yet.   This is the laboratory of the chief alchemist for the Lords of Kista, and he doesn't like visitors.  He often asks the guards to throw out the people who come in here.  There is a odd papyrus scroll on the wall.

name: Healer
description: No doubt this must be some sort of healing room.  The smell of the air suggests that something is perhaps amiss.  The odor is horrible, but you seem to be getting stronger or at least feel rejuvenated.  This must be where the King's elite knights come after a long and drawn battle.

name: West Hallway
description: From what you can tell, there is only one level to the Towers.  For the most part, it's just this floor and the large towers looming above you. The corridor is well kept and seems to be fairly busy with visiting representatives from the human and dwarven races.  The walls are fairly bare, though.  Perhaps they ran out of pictures to put up.

name: West Hallway
description: There is a stairway here that appears to lead up into the western tower. As you look up, you notice that the climb up will be long and hard.  No telling what's up there.  The west hallway itself continues to the north and south.  The floor is covered with a red carpet that is slightly worn due to excessive use.

name: West Hallway
description: The long hallway is drapped in blue velvet cloth covering up much of the  walls, providing an outstanding backdrop for some large pictures of the  early stages of the building of the Towers.  The hallway continues to the  south.  There is a small, wooden door on the west wall.

name: Kista Planning Room
description: With all the blueprints and other documents lying around, this place must  be where all the great planners come to work on building new cities for  their ever-expanding population.  There are enough chairs for eight people here, no doubt for two representatives from each race plus two chairs for guests.  There are also a few chairs along the wall.

name: Izitara's Meditation Chamber
description: Izitara is the spiritual leader of the City of Kista, and is a devout   Priestess of the Philosophy of Wisdom.  Izitara dedicates her work to the teaching of this philosophy, especially for those who are seeking knowledge and wisdom for personal gain instead of providing excuses for those events of catastrophic nature, including death.  She will no doubt try to pursuade  you that philosophy is mighter than strength.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: This seems to be an endless set of steps, although you are certainly moving your feet you don't seem to be making any progress.  A wonderful odor wafts down from the top of the tower.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: These stairs have been unused for a very long time.  The smell of dust and mustiness is mixed with a perfume which seems to get stronger near the top of the tower.  A small window allows you to see a grand view of Kista below.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: The tall tower seems to make the stairway seemingly endless.  Every time you go further up, it seems like you haven't moved at all.  The stairway smells of mildew and mold, as if it hasn't been used ages.  There's a faint  perfumed odor that seems to be coming from the top of the tower.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: A wonderful fragrance comes from the top of the stairs, but there is also a smell of decay as well.  The stairs have not been used in a very long  time.  Seems as though every time you take a step on the stairs it doesn't seem as though you have gotten any closer to your goal.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: The tall tower seems to make the stairway seemingly endless.  Every time you go further up, it seems like you haven't moved at all.  The stairway smells of mildew and mold, as if it hasn't been used in ages.  There's a faint, perfumed odor that seems to be coming from the top of the tower.

name: East Tower Stairway
description: This tower seems to be endless in in height.  At least the stairwell seems to go forever.  Every time you take a step, either up or down, it seems as though you have not moved at all.  The stairwell smells of mildew and wood rot.  However, there is a wonderful smell of perfume coming from above.

name: Second Floor Hallway
description: The hallway is fantastically designed with many gold ornaments and arches throughout.  The long red carpet on the floor spans the entire hallway.   On the north side, you can see a railing which surrounds a large opening in  in the floor.  Apparently, you can watch the activities on the floor below. That must be the throne room down there.

name: Second Floor Hallway
description: To the north, there is a large opening below you, allowing you to see the  grand throne room with two large, golden thrones in it.  There doesn't seem to be anyone in the throne room right now.  The hallway continues to the east and west.  There is a green-painted door to the south.

name: Second Floor Hallway
description: The long hallway proceeds east from here and ends at a wall some eighty meters down.  On the west wall, there are life-size portraits of Lord Aaileman and Lady Drianna.  The floor is covered with a fine red carpet made completely of rare minusk fur.  There is an orange door to the north  next to the northern hallway, and a sky-blue painted door to the south.

name: Lord Aaileman's Personal Chambers
description: The chambers are about ten meters wide and long, covered with ornate golden trinkets and other items that appear to have no real bearing on anything.  There are a couple of small statues and models of new cities being planned.  There's also a large map of the region of  Kista.  Aaileman is usually in his chambers, here, but sometimes  he's in the throne room or talking in the council chambers.

name: Lady Drianna's Private Chambers
description: Lady Drianna is the stunningly beautiful elven wife of Lord Aaileman. This is the chamber where she goes when she's not accompanying him on his various duties.  She also uses this chamber for meeting with important individuals from the city.  Drianna is typically more understanding of the city's people and their problems.

name: Mannish Dignitary's Quarters
description: Each of the dignitaries have their quarters here so that they can remain in Kista for any duration of time.  Guests of the dignitaries must stay at the suites in the Inn.  The human quarters are quite lavishly furnished with curtains, a desk and bed.  It's also quite a mess.

name: Elven Dignitary's Quarters
description: Illia is usually at her desk, signing papers and other important documents. She is a strong fighter from the elven community of Riverdell and is  considered an expert bowyer.  The elven city of Riverdell is quite a distance to the north of Kista, so Illia tends to stay here for many days or even weeks at a time.  Her quarters are less lavish and not decorated near as much as Travis' and Drowlin's quarters.

name: Dwarven Dignitary's Quarters
description: Drowlin spends time traveling between Tragular and Kista so he's not always in town.  He usually shows up every two or three days depending on the condition of the roads.  Tragular is a large dwarven city deep within the mountains to the south.  The quarters are rather nicely  decorated with lots of gold and metals around, displaying some artifacts of Drowlin's heritage.

name: Forest Trail
description: A voice speaks out to you:  "You have chosen the path of danger, as would   any worthy adventurer.  Careful, as you will find the Adamantine Dragon's cave to the west.  A smart adventurer does not fight when he or she does not have to."  The voice ends on a single musical note.   The trail seems to travel in a full circle.  You can walk to the northeast and southeast from here.  The dense forest and a mysterious force shield prevent you from leaving the path's circle.

name: Forest Trail
description: You continue to walk around the circle, well aware that you are going around in circles.  However, each time you go around, you start to  notice more and more.  There is a small cave to the south that is  barely visible through the brush and trees.  The question is whether or not the force shield will let you through to it.  A reddish haze is  curling around you, even now.

name: Forest Trail
description: As you continue around the circle, you notice a strange, reddish haze all around you.  It appears to be some sort of dense red fog, although you are unsure where exactly it leads.  The path you are on continues to the south and southwest.  When you look at the trees, they almost  appear to be making faces at you.  This forest is very strange.

name: Adamantine Dragon's Cave
description: The Adamantine Dragon is perhaps the greatest dragon in the land, but because she is still so young, her powers of magic are not yet fully developed.  But even at this point, Elise is considered a master of magic and wizardry.  The Adamantine Dragon may someday be more powerful than the Platinum Dragon. Although this cave is huge, the Adamantine Dragon will grow larger with age and will one day fill it completely.

name: Alligator's Pit
description: The Alligator's Pit was designed to remove pesky intruders from entering the throne room and asking to be heard.  This was a problem at first, but people soon realized that the lords in the towers had better things to do than listen to the commoner's drivel about how poorly crops are doing this year, etc.

name: West Tower Stairway
description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

name: West Tower Stairway
description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

name: West Tower Stairway
description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

name: West Tower Stairway
description: The tower staircase appears to spiral up infinitely into the sky.  The further you progress up the stairway, the further away the top appears to get.  There is an odd, musty smell in the stairwell that puzzles  you.  It doesn't look like this stairway is used often, although you know the towers are inhabited.  There must be some sort of great magic at the top of these stairs.

name: West Tower
description: Elise is one of the most powerful mages perhaps in the world.  It is quite puzzling that such a young woman is already a White Moon and a Preserver Wizard, the highest rank that can be achieved.  The Order of the White Moon is an elven sorority of lawful, good wizards whose ranks are limited only to those who have proven their skill and devotion to goodness.  Any wizard may petition to enter, as the sorority is not limited to elves nor females.  The Order of the White Moon is a powerful ally of the Red-Robed wizards in the City of Oceancrest.

name: East Tower
description: You are in a well-lit, red room with numerous glowing orbs and other  interesting artifacts.  There is a large, worm-like drawing shaped  like a C on the wall on a blue background.  There are also different phases of the moon mapped out and a large map of the Kista Valley. Unfortunately, you can't seem to make out exactly what the map says. The scroll with the moon phases looks pretty readable, though.

name: Front Entry of the Great Library
description: The great entry is surrounded with mirrors and glass, with a large sun- roof letting the brilliant sunlight illuminate the Library.  There are a number of fantastic displays for everyone to see and experiment with. There are three doors here.  The oak door leads to an "Archives" room.   The green door to the north says "Research" on a old and tarnished bronze plaque.  The blue door to the west says "Reference" on it's plaque.

name: The Research Room
description: On the north wall, you see a number of glowing buttons, each with a different elven rune on it.  All the buttons are white with a black rune enscribed on it's face that can be pressed.  There is a bit of writing on the west wall that looks rather cryptic.

name: Reference Desk
description: The reference desk contains a number of scrolls that are used to locate objects or provide information on certain items.  These scrolls, collected through the ages, date back to as early as the dragon scrolls of the Dragon's Citadel.  No doubt, there will be quite a bit of interesting material in here.

name: Women's Restroom
description: Large mirrors cover the walls, and bright lights surround them. Near the back of the room are several massage tables where an attendent masseuse waits.  Comfortable furniture forms a sitting area by the door, and one wall has lockers avaiable for a price. A steaming spa sits in the center of the room.

name: Golden Shield Shoppe
description: Theodenes is an old and wizened little gnome, but at one time, in the service of his king, he was a mighty warrior.  After he was disabled in combat he returned to the craft he had apprenticed in as a young gnome.  Today, he is known as a master craftsman for the fine shields he makes.  Both Prince Ragnar and Prince Rutger, of the Lyanden line, consider his shields the highest quality available.

name: Mehetable's Hut
description: Mehetable's home has at least six large rooms that you can see, and there are more rooms upstairs.  Fine tapestries and silk rugs are everywhere, and the furniture would be fit for a king.  Polished wood and rare brocades were used in the making of the elegant furniture.

name: Megan's Silver Apple Tree
description: Several large silver apples hang heavily on the tree, and even the leaves seem to shine with the luster of silver.  The simple hut has a flap over the doorway, and you can smell apples being cooked inside.

name: Mordith's Silver Apple Tree
description: Mordith, the middle daughter of Mehetable, intends to give the silver apples to whomever she marries.  Many have been the suitors, but her mother has rejected all of them, waiting for the sons of Trantori to return from the mountains to the east where they have sought adventure.

name: Marlea's Silver Apple Tree
description: Marlea is the wild one, and Mehetable has to watch her closely as she often allows young men to enter her hut late at night.  Mehetable has been known to paralyze with fear those who visit, and feed them to the neighboring trolls.

name: Mehetable's Golden Apple Tree
description: The tree rustles in the cool breeze, and you see a single, golden apple sway on its branch near the center of the limbs.  The tree is in robust health, and looks like it could produce golden apples for a good many years.

name: Mehetable's Apple Orchid
description: There are rows and rows of gnarled old apple trees, each loaded with beautuful fruit.  The earth is rich and freshly turned, and not a weed in sight.  Mehetable the Witch takes good care of her orchid.  Farther to the east you see four huts surrounding some very special apple trees. Lelion Way is just outside a small wooden fence on the north.

name: Mehetable's Apple Orchid
description: Mehetable refuses to let young men court her beautiful daughters, waiting for the three sons of Trantori to return from their adventures in the east. She owes Trantori a favor, and has promised him wives for his sons. The path leads back to Lelion Way, but under the bridge there.

name: Mehetable's Apple Orchid
description: You are in an apple orchid which is tended by Mehetable and her daughters. The ancient crone lives in the largest of the huts you see at the east end of the orchid.  Each of her three beautiful daughters lives in a separate hut near her.  There are some very special trees growing by the huts.  Mehetable and her daughters take very good care of this grove.

name: Mehetable's Apple Orchid
description: The oldest daughter is Megan, said to have a breathtaking beauty and a voice to match.  She sings very lovely ballads.  Megan has coal black hair, and wears gossermer gowns spun from spider's silk.  Mordith is the middle daughter, with flaming red hair, and a quick temper.  She plays the lute. Marlea, the youngest daughter has blonde hair and a sweet disposition.  She dances with the grace of a bird.

name: Mehetable's Yard
description: In front of each hut there is a very special apple tree, each bearing a single remarkable apple.  Three of them are silver, and one of them is gold. Mehetable and her three beautiful daughters don't mind the occasional visitor helping themselves to an apple from the orchid, but one dares not reach for one of these.

name: Megan's Hut
description: There's nothing here but a simple straw mattress and small fireplace with a cauldron over it.  Three books are stacked neatly near the pile of straw. The title of the book on top is, "Precious Metals and Horticulture, A New Approach."  It lies open to page 312.

name: Mordith's Hut
description: The room is simple but elegant, with many musical instruments in view. Mordith longs to be married, and her music is often about lost loves and forgotten promises.  Her favorite instrument is the finely crafted lute you see on the chair by the window.

name: Marlea's Hut
description: A large mirror hangs on the wall and there's even one on the ceiling over the largest feather bed you have ever seen.  Partially hidden from view is a small satchel filled with eye liner, lip blush and other cosmetics.  The satchel would be burned if Mehetable knew of it.

name: Museum Gift Shoppe
description: The Museum Gift Shop carries all sorts of trinkets and supplies that are replicas of those you might have seen in the Museum.  Since much of the Museum is based on magic, a number of magical potions may also be obtained here as well.  The door to the west leads out onto Tower Lane.  The exit to the east leads into the Museum itself.

name: Milsene Museum Entrance Foyer
description: The Museum branches off into four directions.  To the west is the gift shoppe from where you entered.  To the north, there is a small child's exhibit on lizards and other small, interesting creatures.  To the east is a larger exhibit for people who are interesting in magic and other unexplainable wonders of the world.  To the south, a corridor leads to even more exhibits.

name: Milsene Children's Exhibition
description: This exhibit is usually of interest to everyone, since there is a child in all of us.  The things you see here are not very dangerous in reality, but they do look terribly frightening at first.  Small but exotic animals from all over the land have been brought here for the children's pleasure.

name: Milsene Museum Forest Exhibit
description: The large hall is filled with trees and shrubs which delicately cover the grey walls of the Museum.  There are a number of exhibits here showing scenes from the Enchanted Forest.  The area has tree sprites and dryads and other magical, mystical creatures who may be found in the Enchanted Forest.  Of course, if you would like to see them in their natural setting, you should consider an adventureous trip to the forest.

name: Dark Forest Exhibit
description: It's hard to say where the light, happy forest turned into this dark, gloomy forest with a number of nasty or otherwise evil creatures lurk behind the dense bushes.  The trees have grown taller and cover the Museum's skylight, making this area dark and spooky.  Mysterious  creatures lie in wait behind every stone.

name: Milsene Museum's Hall of Doom
description: The Hall of Doom is a magnificent hallway of the greatest terrors  ever to be collected into a single exhibit.  The hallway continues to the south and back into the main foyer to the north.  On the  east wing, you see a sign that says "The Undead Aren't Really Dead". On the west wing, you see a sign that reads "Dragons and Brimstone".

name: Milsene Museum Hall of Doom
description: The hallway continues here with even more exhibits.  There are rooms to the east, west and south with varying monsters from various exotic locations from around the world.  To the west, there is a sign above the arch that says "Dragons and Brimstone".  To the south, there  appears to be some sort of desert environment, though you can't really make much out and there are no descriptions.  To the east, there is  a sign saying "Terrors from the Underground".  The hallway leads back towards the main foyer to the north.

name: Milsene Museum's Theatre of Doom
description: The set is very gothic and looks like it's inhabited by ghosts and  goblins.  Perhaps even worse.  The stage and the set are just props that you can't seem to move, but everything around you seems to be moving.  Chairs rattle, tables move and small drinking glasses  tumble to the ground and shatter.  A very scary place, indeed.

name: Dragons and Brimstone Exhibit
description: There are a number of dragons you've never seen before, but also several  of your favorites.  This room is quite large and there are two very wide exits to the east, one on the north side of the east wall and one on the south side of the wall.  When the sign said "Brimstone", they meant it. There are lots of hot rocks and what appears to be simulated lava flow.

name: Milsene K'tral Desert Exhibit
description: This place gets stranger and stranger.  There's a lot of sand in here and the sun blazes down from an open ceiling.  A small signpost says "Welcome to the Unexplored Domain of K'tral".  K'tral is the desert valley hidden deep within the mountains with supposedly fantastic riches  and deadly monsters, like sandworms.

name: Milsene Museum's Caverns of Doom Exhibit
description: The caves are remarkablly well reproduced here, although on a much smaller scale than in real life.  There are a number of small things moving on the dusty, damp floor, mostly consisting of venemous rats and other vermin.  Every so often, you see some orcs or worms wandering around in the depths of the caves.

name: East Side of Stump
description: The path circles around the massive stump to the north and to the south. High on the remains of the ancient tree that once stood her you can see where someone has carved something, perhaps a message, or perhaps just graffiti.  A prickly hedge on the east side of the path requires you to stay close to the tree stump as you follow the path.

name: Giant Tree Stump
description: The tree that once stood here must have been a world-wonder, if the girth of the stump is any indication.  Looking up, you see the top of the tree trunk is considerably over your head, but there may be a way to climb up there.  The path splits and goes around the tree in two different directions, and also leads away to the north.  A short distance that way there is a heavy rope bridge cabled across a shallow gorge.  The Ashton creek follows the gorge.

name: Bear Marked Tree
description: The mark is easily a meter over your head, and was no doubt put there by a bear defining his territory.  There is a rope bridge to the west, evidently leading to a cave you see in the distance. That may be the cave of the hermit who inhabits this part of the forest.  If he is willing to talk to you, he may tell you some of the secrets of this place.

name: Rope Suspension Bridge
description: The old bridge sways with each step you take, forcing you to walk slowly to keep it from going into wild oscillations and perhaps dumping you into the water below.  Only one person at a time can be on the bridge, but fortunately it doesn't look like you could be attacked easily while here.  Unless the attack came from the air.  What's that overhead?

name: Hermit's Cave Entrance
description: Hermits are always strange, and for some reason they always seem to have long, flowing white hair and long beards.  The one who lives here is no exception.  He is also very wise.  The outside of the cave is scattered with small animal bones and other bits of refuse.  The skin of some unknown animal is stretched on a frame which provides a sort of door for the cave.

name: Hermit's Cave
description: You had expected rocks to sit on, and perhaps a small fire in the center of the cave, but instead the place is nicely furnished with old but expensive furniture.  One wall is floor to ceiling with books and a comfortable chair is positioned for the best light to read by.  He is a wise hermit, afterall.  A fireplace and hearth has been constructed of stone and provides a cheerful atmosphere to the cave.

name: Redwood Giants
description: The trees are the biggest you have ever seen, and disappear into the clouds above.  The lowest branches are far overhead and form a canopy, filtering the sunlight during the day.  Not far to the southwest you can see a rope bridge across a narrow chasm, and to the north are what appear to be even bigger redwood trees.

name: Giant Redwood
description: A spiral staircase winds around the massive trunk of the tree, but stops about ten meters above the ground.  High overhead, you see a wooden landing midway up, but from there the stairway disappears into the clouds.  A sign at the bottom says: 	"This is the home of Trantori, the High Invoker. 	 Visitors are not welcome, unless they wish to 	 be turned into toads.  If so, please come up." . ************************************************************

name: Hedged Pathway
description: Although the path is very broad, the hedge is so thick you cannot step off the path.  To the west there is a clearing where you can see towering redwood trees.  To the east the path takes a turn, but the trees are more normal in size.  You can smell the pleasant smoke of a wood fire on the breeze coming from the east.

name: Gap in the Hedge
description: The gap in the hedge is not very wide, and the cleared area on the other side is rather small.  There's a dust in the air that makes you feel a little light-headed, but in spite of that you are sure you can hear  giggling on the other side of the hedge.

name: Pixie Glenn
description: You feel a little lightheaded because of the pixie dust in the air.  As you stand here, the air snaps and sparkles as pixies dart about.  There is a tension in in the air as well, as though magic was all about you. The glenn is totally surrounded by a tall hedge, and a gap can be seen to the south.  To the north, on the other side of the hedge, you hear a yowling noise like a tomcat in heat.

name: Crow's Tree Village
description: A path leads through the hedge going north, and another path continues to the south.  There are a number of large birdhouses hanging from the trees all about you.  A group of crows, larger than any you have ever seen before, are talking above your head.  Strangely, you understand every word they say.  You might be able to join in their conversation.

name: Gravel Walkway
description: Brightly colored wildflowers are on both sides of the walkway, which is well tended and has been recently raked.  The gravel walkway meanders through a meadow deep in the enchanted forest.  To the east you see the source of the pleasant smoke you have been smelling  a small cottage with a large smokestack at its north end.  At the south side of the cottage is a pond of water and a great waterwheel is on the wall of the cottage. A stream keeps the waterwheel turning slowly.  Thick trees are at the back of the cottage.

name: Path Fork
description: A gravel walkway leads east through a meadow, while the main path continues to the north and south.  You are surrounded by a grove of trees which gets thicker to the north, while to the south the path narrows and makes it way between huge rocks and boulders.  A steep rock face looks like it can be climbed, if you had climbing equipment.

name: Path by the Rockface
description: The rockface rises at a steep angle, but looks safe to climb if you have the proper equipment.  It's hard to tell what might be up there, as there is a rock shelf a few meters up.  It looks like the fissures up there are big enough to enter, and they might prove interesting to explore.

name: Edge of the Pond
description: The pond covers a large area to the east, where you see a thick forest of trees on the other side.  On the north side of the pond you see a large cottage and waterwheel.  Smoke rises from the cottage's chimney.  Directly north is a jumble of rocks and boulders and a rockface.  the path continues to the north through the rocks, and south through a swampy looking area.

name: Wet Forest Path
description: the pond is rather shallow here, but appears to get deeper toward the north. trees grow in the water, and moss hangs from everything.  The path is not well defined, and the mud is rather slippery.  It's kinda gloomy, don't you think?  An owl hoots in the distance, and there's some noise you can't identify closer by.

name: Swampy Path in the Enchanted Forest
Allisk Labyrinth Entrance
description: The Allisk Labyrinth was constructed many centuries ago by one Natasha de Allisk, now rumored to be one of the most powerful vampires in the lands.  Of course, no one reputable has seen her lately.  The Labyrinth was created as an escape from reality, as Natasha was quite psychotic. In her later years, the Labyrinth was used to lure victims to their doom.  Lately, nothing has really surfaces about the Labyrinth and it's probably just filled with some minotaurs and flying snakes.  The vampires have long since abandoned this old tomb.

name: Allisk Labyrinth
description: You are apperently lost inside the Allisk Labyrinth.  The stone-grey walls appear identical in every direction you look.  Although you feel like you haven't been in this direction before, you also feel that somehow you're going around in circles.  The Labyrinth was built many centuries ago and rumor has it that minotars and flying snakes still roam the corridors  looking for food.

name: Countess Brianna's Chambers
description: Countess Brianna has long since thought to have been destroyed as a  vampire, as she hasn't been seen for ages.  Unfortunately, it appears that she has just been hibernating until she could regain enough strength to re-enter the world of the living.  There is a large coffin in the  center of the room which is used by the Countess when she is resting.
