The Labyrinth was built many centuries ago and rumor has it that minotars and flying snakes still roam the corridors  looking for food.

name: Allisk Labyrinth
description: You are apperently lost inside the Allisk Labyrinth.  The stone-grey walls appear identical in every direction you look.  Although you feel like you haven't been in this direction before, you also feel that somehow you're going around in circles.  The Labyrinth was built many centuries ago and rumor has it that minotars and flying snakes still roam the corridors  looking for food.

name: South Oceancrest Post Office #29
description: The need for communications is essential for a working city to prosper. The Oceancrest Post Offices will send mail to anyone you like, free of charge.  If you have mail at the Post Office, type "readmail".  If you'd like to send mail to someone, type "sendmail <player>" and enter your message.

name: Oceancrest Mountaineer's Supply
description: The store provides various supplies to mountain climbers, from the simple to the exotic.  If you need a specialized piece of gear, you will probably find it here.  A new section of the store is devoted to spelunkers as a number of caves have been discovered within the city walls.

name: Melbourne Pawn Shop
description: Fencing is not taken lightly in Oceancrest, so most of the pawn shops in the city won't be visible from the street.  In fact, most pawn shops are in fact thieves' guilds that are more than happy to make a little extra gold off of some poor, unsuspecting sap.

name: Back Alley
description: This small access alley provides access to the back doors of most of the small shops on the other side of the road.  More importantly, though, it allows the recycled garbage to be taken to the Central Recycling Plant near the center of town.  The alley smells of urine and alcohol.  As you walk along, you stumble over a number of passed-out drunks.

name: Back Alley
description: The alley is very dark and really smells bad.  As you walk along, you  stumble over drunks and knock down their make-shift houses of discarded tree bark.  You're not sure anything could survive down here, but then again,you're not sure you'd want to meet anything that could.

name: South Oceancrest Trash Recycling Plant
description: In order to keep the city clean, the city has managed to finance a recycling option to the citizens of the city.  For each item you bring in to be  recycled, you will get five gold pieces.  Hopefully this incentive will keep the streets clean and save the city even more tax dollars to clean up the streets themselves.

name: The Dragon's Claw Tavern and Grill
description: The Dragon's Claw Tavern and Grill provides a good meal at a good price with all the ale you can drink.  The grill is located outside the bar, and serves steaks, venison and other meats from all over the land.  This is a good place to meet people and have a bite to eat.  Numerous people wander in and out of here, going about their own business.

name: Lafyette's Blacksmithing and Repairs
description: Lafyette also fixes armors and almost anything else that can be broken. Repairing metals is a costly job, though, and will require quite a bit of gold from you if you want it repaired.  If it's too expensive for you, then there's a trash recycling facility in this same complex on the  west side of Melbourne Avenue.

name: Catherine's Weapons Shop
description: A variety of simple, easy to use weapons may be purchased here.  Most of the weapons Catherine sells are for self-defense, but most could render an opponent permanently disabled for life if used properly.  A list of the various weapons for sale is available for you to look at.

name: The Holy Order of the White Rose
description: The path of the Paladin is difficult and trying.  In order to advance in the ranks of the holy knights, you must show skill in defeating a knight of a level higher than you.  The Gallant Warrior should enter the blue door, if you are ready to be tested.  A Gallant Warrior, Second  Class should enter the green door when you are ready to advance to the next level.

name: The Blue Training Room
description: Worthy Paladins should be able to defeat an opponent a level above you. Since you have a slight disadvantage, this will prove that you are indeed ready to advance to the level of Gallant Warrior, Second Class.

name: The Green Training Room
description: In order to advance to the level of Gallant Warrior, First Class, you must first defeat the knight who stands before you.  The test of strength in front of an enemy who is of a higher level than you proves your  worthiness to advance to the next level.

name: The Paladin's Training Room
description: Congratulations, you have succeeded in defeating the holy knight in  training.  You are now worthy of training to the level of Gallant,  Second Class.

name: The Holy Order of the White Rose Training Room
description: You are now worthy to train to the level of Gallant Warrior, First Class. You have exceeded the standards set by this facility and we commission you go out out into the world standing proudly for good and justice.  In order to be commissioned to a Protector, you must seek out the Shrine of Truth and Fairness in northwestern Oceancrest.

name: Panthor Academy of Fighting Arts
description: Fighting is not all brute strength, and a good fighter must realize this. In order to advance in levels as a fighter, you must first defeat an equally capable fighter one level higher than you.  If you are a veteran aspiring to advance to second class, you should enter the red door.  If you are already a Veteran, second class, you should enter the blue door.

name: Panthor's Training Room
description: In order to train to the level of Veteran, Second Class, you must first defeat the knight which stands before you.  A worthy fighter should be able to defeat an enemy of a higher level then he is.  The knight  at the center of the room awaits your first move.

name: The Red Training Room
description: The skill of being a good fighter is a combination of intelligence and  strength.  Combined, the fighter can take on almost any opponent even if they are of a higher level than you are.  Come back when you are ready to advance again, and the Panthor Fighting Academy will train you.

name: Panthor's Training Room
description: Strong fighters do not fear opponents higher then they are in skill and power because strength lies in knowing just how to use it.  In order to advance, you must defeat the fighter who stands before you.  The knight awaits your first move.

name: The Blue Training Room
description: You are now ready to move on.  The Panthor Academy of Fighting Arts no longer satisfies your needs for higher training.  The instructors suggest going to the Rudolph Fighting Academy in southeastern Oceancrest to  continue your training.

name: Panther Guard Headquarters
description: Young fighters use the headquarters as a training facility, but as they advance in level they need to go to a more professional establishment. You will learn some of the best street fighting techniques known to the guard here, but if you wish to advance to level three, you must go to Rudolph's over on Main Street in the Plaza.

name: Roman Iron Works
description: The Roman Iron Works shop is dedicated to cast-iron weapons and shields that last for a while, but may not do as much dammage or protect as well. As usual, the price you pay for inexpensive goods has benifits, but also has drawbacks.  The Roman Iron Works employees are more than happy to provide you with anything you might want.

name: Imeldia's Potions and Stuff
description: Imeldia is not the greatest alchemist in the land, but provides her customers with a number of essential potions and powerders that might be useful in their adventures through Oceancrest.

name: Imeldia's Potions and Stuff Storage Shack
The Chug-A-Lug Pub
description: The Chug-A-Lug is a down right rowdy tavern where just about anything can happen.  Anyone can come in for a drink and to talk about the local news such as who is going to be fighting in the Melbourne Entertainment Arena in the evening.  Gamblers and hookers abound in this sleezy bar, not to mention drunks, vagrants and even a few sailors.

name: Penelope's Musical Instruments
description: Bards and minstrels love to shop at Penelope's Musical Instruments Shop because of all the unique instruments she stocks.  A number of the larger  instruments can also be used in self-defense, but usually end up  breaking after knocking someone over the head.

name: Hanabal and Gustave's Light Swords
description: These swords are renouned around Oceancrest as being very strong and long  lasting.  Hanabal and Gustave's swords are made by hand and slowly polished and sharpened.  They take great pride in their handywork and guarantee that you'll like any weapon you buy from them.

name: The Healing Hand
description: A number of clerics and priests give their time to come to help people  who have been severely injured.  They give their time freely because it  is the way of their religion, and a helping hand is never really ever forgotten.  You may rest here in peace without being disturbed until you have been completely healed.

name: Uland Repair Shop
description: A large man stands behind the counter and asks if he can be of some service to you.  The Uland Repair Shops fixes just about any broken weapon, armor or even enchanted items.  Unfortunately, one cannot guarentee not having an accident, so the smith might end up breaking something now and then.

name: Generic Clerical Supplies
description: No cleric could go out adventuring without his or her trusty crucifix or a vial of holy water.  A number of small potions and other clerical  supplies line the shelves of the shop.  A kindly old man waits behind the counter for you to place an order.

name: Royal Jousting Supplies
description: The jouster must properly balance his lance and his horse.  But in preparing for the joust, these fighters also train using various pole-type weapons, usually with strong, metal hooks and blades attached to them.  A good polearm in the hands of a skilled fighter can be a deadly weapon.

name: D'Tan's Leather Armory
description: D'Tan's Armory fits all races and all sizes, but is limited to cloth and leather armors.  Mages have trouble with the heavy metal armors because they tend to interfere with their magical powers and thieves prefer  leather because it makes them move much more quietly.  D'Tan realizes these need and happily provides for them.

name: Melbourne Entertainment Arena - Challenger's Ready Room
description: The large Ready Room does not seem to provide you with much of anything to fight with.  They suggest visiting D'Tan's Armory across the street and maybe a couple of weapons shops around town before entering the arena. The arena is a dangerous place, and should be entered with caution.

name: Melbourne Entertainment Arena - Entrance Foyer
description: The Melbourne Entertainment Arena has two levels of difficulty.  To the  north is the entrance to the Beginner's Circle, where young warriors can get acquainted with the various criminals and vermin of Oceancrest.  To the east is the Center Ring arena where just about anything can happen.  The fighting rages from within both areans, beckoning you to enter.

name: The Beginner's Circle
description: The Beginner's Circle provides young, less experienced warriors with the experience of killing off Oceancrest's criminals.  Rather than take up  space in prisons, the criminals are given a chance for freedom if they can survive in the ring with other warriors.  Hardened criminals are thrown into the Center Circle.

name: The Center Circle
description: The heart of all the activity is inside the Center Ring where hardened criminals and other dregs of society are thrown to be executed by the various warriors and knights who enter the arena to practice.  Moving targets are the best way to practice, and targets that fight back are even more challenging.

name: The Invisible Hand Training Room
description: Congratulations on making it to the training room!  You may train here and advance to the next level.  However, when you are ready to go to level seven, you will have to find another training place.  Perhaps you should ask the little match girl if she knows where higher level thieves are supposed to train.

name: The Poisoned Dagger
description: The Poisoned Dagger is a large operation running out of the back of the Crimson Tales Saloon.  Contacts are usually made in the Saloon because  it is less suspicious.  The Guild provides high-level assassinations for a modest sum, half up front, and half on completion, full refund if the victim lives.

name: The Poisoned Dagger Training Room
description: No one ever survives an assassination attempt by the Guild of the Poisoned Dagger.  If you wish to advance into their ranks, you must train with them, learning their techniques of stealth and backstabbing.

name: The University Library
description: The University Library is filled with tomes and scrolls of all kinds.   Many are locked behind strange doors, not having been disturbed for  ages.  Others are behind combination locks that prevent tampering.  In any case, there is more knowledge contained here than there will ever be in even the greatest mage.

name: The Great Library Basement
description: As you blow off the dust on the various tomes and books in the basement, you can clearly see that no one has been here in ages.  Some of the books crumble apart as soon as you touch them.

name: Eiden Public Storage Facility
description: Public storage is often a problem to people visiting the city in that there's always too much to carry around.  Besides, the stuff is heavy! The Eiden Public Storage Building allows people to store their valuable stuff here for a price.  Storage rooms are located to the north, east and west.  Netherworld Lane is to the south.

name: Eiden Public Storage East Hallway
description: Each storage room door is secured with a special key, which costs $2000 to replace.  A magic aura protects the rooms from inadvertant teleports. No one can break into these storage rooms.  However, the managment makes no other claims and will not be held responsible for any losses.

name: Dragonwares
description: Dragonwares is a specialty shop which used to be owned by Conan, the Dragon-Slayer.  Conan was a high level leader of Oceancrest's heros and warriors, and often had rare items for sale.  This was his shop before he died on April 1, 1994, to get a 'real life.'  Conan was a member of the Mordor elite for more than three years, but decided an addiction like this was just too time consuming.  It may happen to you.

name: North Hillborough Plaza
description: This large plaza hosts a number of small specialty shops.  To the southwest is the Hillborough Adamantine Works where adamantine is formed into strong shields, weapons and armors.  To the west is Deni's World of Spices.  To the north is Jallud's Missing Persons, where people can leave messages for people believed to be lost or missing.  To the east is the rowdy Crimson Tales Saloon, and to the southeast is the Lankshire Hall of Wonders.

name: South Hillborough Plaza
description: The southern section of the Hillborough Plaza boasts a number of fine specialty shops for you to look through.  To the northwest is the mysterious Might and Magic Mystery Shop.  To the west is the House of Hides.  To the south is Merdock's Hidden Weapons Shop of Wares.  To the east is Platinum Eyes, and to the northeast is Nathan's Light Armory.

name: Jallud's Missing Persons
description: As luck would have it, there are no post offices in the center of town. This is because the town was already built before the city decided to adopt the post offices as their official means of communications.  Jallud's small shop acts as a message service to get important information to lost or missing people you haven't seen in a while.

name: Hillborough Adamantine Works
description: Adamantine is one of the most expensive metals known, second possibly to mithril.  It is also one of the strongest known metals.  Armor made with adamantine is likely to last much longer than regular metalic armors, even though their degree of protection is equivalent.

name: Deni's World of Spices
description: Some spices are said to have magical or mystical powers associated with them.  Most, however, are just used for seasonings or to preserve meats. There are shelves upon shelves of herbs and spices along the walls, most of which you've never seen before.

name: Deni's World of Spices Storage Shack
Crimson Tales Saloon
description: There's nothing like being in a barfight, and that looks like where you've landed yourself in this time.  The rowdy bar quiets down from time to time, but the constant barrage of disorderly drunks, morality police and other unfriendly faces always makes for an interesting time.

name: The Might and Magic Mystery Shop
description: ====================]  This Shop is For Sale  [====================== To purchase it you must first obtain and read the Rules of Business, which is available at the Sleeping Deer Real Estate Office.

name: The Might and Magic Mystery Shop Storage Room
Nowhere Fast Traveler's Guild
description: The large guild sells guides to just about every city and about almost anything going on in the cities.  The Traveler's Guild is an essential stop for all visitors to Oceancrest, and to those planning to leave Oceancrest for other cities.

name: Nowhere Fast Traveler's Guild Storage Room
The Fiesty Kitten Nightclub and Bar
description: The Fiesty Kitten is one of the more popular places in Oceancrest for high level adventurers looking for more than a good time.  Because of the nature of the action which goes on inside the Fiesty Kitten Bar, minors (under level 10) will not be admitted.

name: The Fiesty Kitten Nightclub and Bar
description: The nightclub is notorious for barfights and other rocking parties.  For this reason, the management doesn't take responsibility for any loss of possessions by any patrons.  Morality patrol officers often have to stop by to clean out the bloody bodies of those not so skilled in the ways of defense and bar-style fighting.

name: Sick Bay
description: Pirates don't really care to take care of the sick, but this is a good place for the sniveling whiners.  And besides, it's better to put them here instead of keeping them around where others could catch something.  The room is small and cramped, and smells like someone has puked in the corner.  The place is overrun with mice.

name: Cargo Hold
description: Pirates don't really carry cargo, but instead use this area to store the loot they get from other ships.  The sick bay is south, toward the stern, while the chief bosun has his quarters toward the bow.  A locked door has the word "brig" crudely painted on it, and the rest of the hold is filled with chests and barrels.  One keg has a candle sputtering on it.

name: House of Hides
description: Metal shields and armor interfere with the casting of magic spells, making it difficult for masters of the occult to find decent armor.  The House of Hides prides itself on being able to produce leather armor and leather shields which are almost the equal of the best metal armor.  Such equipment is not cheap, however, and because the leather is strengthened with magic it cannot be repaired by the various repair shops around town.

name: Glacier Cavern
description: The ice caverns allow you to see beyond the mountain landscape, into the massive and seemingly endless Ituk Glacier.  The passage walls glow with sunlight and reflect your every movements.  Reflections of yourself mesh in with the strange designs and creatures trapped within the ice.

name: Glacier Cavern
description: Although it must be at least five meters of ice through to the outside world, the ice is so clear, it looks like you could just walk through it. The cavern runs east and west through the mountain above and the glacier within.  Who knows what lurks in these cold realms of forever.

name: Glacier Cavern
description: The glacier pass comes to an end at the cliffs overlooking the Abyss to the north and continues through the glacier to the west.  A cold breeze comes up from the Abyss almost on a regular basis.  Looking down into the Abyss, you can see nothing.  The Abyss appears to continue forever in all directions.  You must fly to go north.

name: High Over the Dennanl Abyss
description: Blackness surrounds you totally, and it is so quiet you can hear your blood pumping in your body.  There is an occasional flash, but you can't be sure it isn't your mind playing tricks with your eyes.

name: Mountain Trail
description: The mountain trail leads through the mountains towards the Ituk Glacier, a massive piece of ice that seems to grow higher each year.  The glacier is a potentially dangerous place in that it is very easy to get lost in such a massive wasteland.  It would be wise to have a good ranger guiding your party.

name: Mountain Trail
description: As you round the northern side of the mountain, you can see down into the Ituk Glacier.  The glacier is particularly dangerous because one can easily become quite lost in such a place.  Scavenging animals are always on the prowl for stranded and helpless prey.  The most dangerous of these animals is the white dragon, which is quite common up here.

name: Mountain Trail
description: The Nellan Mountain Range spans to the north and southeast, expanding nearly indefinitely.  It seems to form the border around the Ituk Glacier. There is a small path leading down onto the Glacier.  Due to the dangerous and deadly conditions of the glacier, only experienced players may venture down into the icy realm.

name: Mountain Trail
description: The large Ituk Glacier comes into view as you round the southern end of the large mountain you are walking around.  The path you are on continues around the mountain.  A small path leads down the mountain onto the glacier.  The glacier is notorious for its ferocious predators in search of a scrap of food.

name: Cave in the Nellan Mountain Range
description: It's cold.  Very cold here.  The cave shelters you somewhat from the snowy weather outside, but the air is still very frigid.  There is a small circle on the floor that appears to glow with a bright golden yellow hue.  The rest of the cave is quite desolate.

name: The Great Glacier Ituk
description: The glacier is surrounded by high mountains all around, preventing any of the water from ever leaving this zone.  The massive block of ice seems to stretch on for miles and miles in every direction.  Hopefully you will have a ranger to help you track through this wasteland.

name: The Great Glacier Ituk
description: The glacier is surrounded by high mountains all around, preventing any of the water from ever leaving this zone.  The massive block of ice seems to stretch on for miles and miles in every direction.  Hopefully you will have a ranger to help you track through this wasteland.

name: The Great Glacier Ituk
description: The glacier is surrounded by high mountains all around, preventing any of the water from ever leaving this zone.  The massive block of ice seems to stretch on for miles and miles in every direction.  Hopefully you will have a ranger to help you track through this wasteland.

name: Ituk Igloo
description: Oddly, the igloo you see lies slightly below the plane of the glacier, leading into the massive chunk of ice.  There is a heavy, metal door located to the north with a new lock on it.  There is no key around that you can see, and the door looks like it's been undisturbed for ages.

name: Underground Cavern
description: The glacier appears to be but a few meters deep here as you look up through the ice.  Ahead, to the north, you can see the beginning of a rope bridge which crosses over a massive abyss.  Unfortunately, it looks like the bridge has been cut, and lies dangling over the edge of the cliff.

name: Over the Dennanl Abyss
description: The sight of the vertigo directly below you almost makes you nauseous as the abyss seems to spiral downward into nothingness.  Hopefully your magical spells will last long enough to get you across this cavern. You wouldn't want to meet whatever is down there going freefall.

name: Underground Cavern
description: To the south, you can see the other side of the cliff which overlooks the Dennanl Abyss.  The rope bridge which would normally allow you to cross the abyss in relative safety appears to be cut, and hangs limply on the other side of the cavern.  The cliff you are on appears to be lower than the cliff on the other side, suggesting the caverns head deeper into the ground.

name: Cavernous Intersection
description: The further north you head, the deeper into the ground you appear to be heading.  Looking up, you can still see the massive glacier over your head and the sky above the ice, which gets darker and darker the further down you go.  The cavern splits in two directions here, one going east and the other going west.  The cavern heads back towards the Dennanl Abyss to the south.

name: Darkened Cavern
description: The cold cavern you were in has now become quite dark and damp.  It's very hard to see where you're going, but you somehow manage.  To the east, you can see a heavy iron door blocking your passage.  The lock appears to be very old and rusted.  Perhaps it will be quite easy to pick.

name: Darkened Cavern
description: a massive oak door blocking your passage through the cavern.  There doesn't appear to be any sort of key that can open this huge door, but the lock looks pretty rusted, and might be easy to pick.

name: Emerald Room
description: The odd looking room seems to radiate the light from above the glacier, through the emerald ceiling, creating an eerie, greenish hue throughout the entire room.  There are three doors in the otherwise empty room heading to the west, north and south, respectively.

name: Dark Cavern
description: There is a strange door in the middle of the hallway, facing the north, which appears to lead into a larger room.  The cavern descends further into the depths of the planet towards the east.  The floor slopes  steeply down the corridor and is covered with slime, making it tough to walk around on without slipping.

name: Descending Cavern
description: Even though it appears that you can't get any lower into the ground, the cavern continues to descend into the depths of the planet.  To the west, you can barely make out a light on the upward slope.  Unfortunately, there isn't much light down here, so you can't really see anything.

name: Cavern Cliff
description: To the south you can see a cliff, but beyond that there is nothing but blackness.  It's the great abyss.  It's going to be impossible to cross it without some serious help.  Far overhead is a great ice cap which is slightly luminous, but apparently very thick and several thousand meters away.  You have descended to a much deeper level than when you came in.

name: Over the Dennanl Abyss
description: The eerie feeling you get while crossing over the empty blackness of the Abyss with only your magic keeping you from falling is amplified by even more mysterious things you see below you.  Occasional flickers of light and sounds of movement come from the Abyss.

name: Cavern Cliff
description: The apparently endless Abyss located to the north drops nearly endlessly towards the center of the planet, but oddly, you hear some sounds of movement and see occasional flickers of light from deep within the chasm.  The cavern heads north across the cliff and east through a cave.

name: Dark Passage
description: No doubt this foul place is the home of some even worse creatures who probably wouldn't mind having you for dinner.  The green covered walls appear to be smeared with slime and grime, created by the dripping of water from the glacier above you.  The floor is smooth and a little slippery.  There is a door to the south.  The passage continues to the north.

name: Dark Passage
description: The smooth floor tells you that the odd passage was not created by nature, but must have been build for some purpose.  The stench in the air gets worse to the east.  The grim, green stone walls are covered with green slime and muck.  There appears to be some light far to the east.

name: Dark Corridor
description: The musty corridor smells of rotting flesh and bones, getting much stronger to the east.  There is a bright light source to the east which is odd to see in the perpetual darkness you're used to.  The hallway heads into the darkness to the west.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The massive cavern hallway runs north and south, with a small passage leading back to the Emerald Room to the west.  The cavern is roughly ten meters high, covered in ice and rock.  Seeing how large the hallway is, it would probably not be such a good idea to meet the inhabitants of such size.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The massive cavern has been carved out of the stone and ice by some very large people.  The hallways smell of decaying flesh and bones, rotting on the very floor you are walking on.  You can see patrols of troops wandering around the halls, but they don't look much like frost giants.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: Frost giants roam around the caverns freely, along with their dreaded skeletal warrior armies.  Obviously, the best way to combat a frost giant is through magic and fire.  In hand-to-hand combat, just about no one would survive the deadly blows of the frost giant's mighty club.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The massive ice formation makes walking around quite difficult.  Since the walls are more or less transparent, it's hard to tell where the other hallways are.  However, there are always frost giants and skeletal warriors to greet you as you wander around.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The massive cavern is nearly ten meters high.  You can see the gleeming sun coming through the ice of the massive glacier this cavern is built from.  The hallways of this cavern are wandered by frost giants and their hideous skeletal warrior armies.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The passageway continues to the south and the west.  There is a distinct odor of rotting, decaying flesh in the area, but you can't really tell  which direction it's coming from.  The halls of this cavern are wandered by massive frost giants and armies of skeletal warriors.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: The corridor appears to get smaller as you head to the south.  The ceiling is getting so low that you don't think a frost giant could fit through the tight cavern.  Also to the south, you can hear the loud chantings of some strange cult, probably preparing some sacrifice.

name: Darkened Hallway
description: The dark corridor is much too small for any frost giant to be able to move in, so it is unlikely that any will bother you here.  However, you can hear some sort of chanting from some devilish source.  It sounds like they're getting ready for battle.

name: Darkened Hallway
description: The hallway is not as large as the hallways to the north, but apparently large enough to comfortably hold armies of skeletons and skeletal warriors, craving for some new flesh.  You can hear some loud chanting to the west, but you can't see anything that would tell you where it's coming from.

name: Riverdell Training Facility
description: Tracking is an essential part of any ranger's training.  Without the ability to track, you would be completely lost in such a vast park. As you continue to walk through the park, you notice how similar all the trees look and how hard it is to find your way around.

name: Riverdell Training Facility

name: Riverdell Tree
description: Being able to track is essential for any ranger.  Your ability to track this far shows that you are ready to advance to the next level.  If this is your goal, go to the tree branch.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to continue in the park, you must look for more tracks.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: If you are a level one or level two searcher, you may train here to advance to the next level.  After you finish your training here, you  will need to seek out the next training location to advance to the  level of scout.  Do this by practicing your tracking skills out of  the tree you came in from.

name: Hole in the Ground
description: Your tracking skills are greatly improving.  If you have come to train up to the level of scout, this is the place.  Enter the cavern to train.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to continue tracking, you must find tracks out of the hole.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: If you are a level three searcher, or a level four scout, you may train here to advance to your next level.  After training up to level five,  you must seek out the next training site by continuing on through the park.

name: Riverdell Shrubbery
description: Nevertheless, you have found another training location.  Your tracking skills have improved and you are ready to advance to the next level.  If your goal is to train, enter the hole in the ground.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to continue in the park, you must track out of this room.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: If you are a level five or level six scout, you may train here to advance to the next level.  Once you have advanced to the level of tracker, you must continue your search through the park, constantly improving your ranger tracking skills.

name: Riverdell Bush
description: The bees don't really bother you if you leave them alone.  Your ranger tracking skills are improving with each level.  If your goal is to train, you should enter the hole below the small shrub.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to remain in the park, you must track out of  here.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: You are allowed to train at this location if you are a level seven or level eight tracker.  Upon reaching level nine, you must seek out the next training location, also located within the park.  As you advance in  levels, your abilities to track also improve.

name: Oak Tree
description: The large oak tree appears to support your weight well.  You have reached one of the major points in the park.  If you wish to train, you should go onto the tree limb.  If you wish to leave the park, you should go out.  If you wish to continue through the park, you will need to find tracks at the bottom of the tree.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: If you are a level nine tracker or a level ten underhillsman, you may train here to advance to the next level.  Once you have reached level eleven, you must track down the next training site.  Subsequent training sites  will be for a single level only, instead of for two levels, as have all the previous training sites, including this one.

name: Birch Tree
description: Tracking is essential to any good ranger, and your tracking skills have improved greatly (or you're very lucky).  This is the training location for rangers of the eleventh level.  If you are ready to train, enter the tree branch.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to  continue in the park, you must track your way out.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: Since you have progressed this far, you are worthy to train at this  location to advance to the next level.  You will need to track further into the forest to train at level twelve.

name: Thorny Bush
description: This is not the most comfortable place to be, but you have managed to find it.  If you are a level twelve ranger and ready to train, you should enter the hole in the ground.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you desire to continue your quest in the park, you must track out of here.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: As your levels increase, your skills do as well.  Your tracking skills will be required by many parties on fantastic quests beyond the realms of mankind.  A reward awaits you at the end of the park, but you have a long way to go still.

name: Walnut Tree
description: The great walnut tree has served as a reminder of the great powers of the forest, and all the creatures great and small that make it what it is.  If you are ready to advance to the next level, you should go to the tree branch.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to continue through the park, you must track out of the tree.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: As your skills improve, you will be able to track long distances in no time at all.  This will be important, if you haven't already figured that out.  You may train here to advance to the next level.

name: Redwood Tree
description: The tall tree towers above the rest of the park, giving you a good look at all the other strange and interesting objects in the park to look for.  If you are ready to train, you should go to the tree branch. If you wish to leave the park, go out.  If you wish to remain in the park, you must track out of the tree.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: You have almost exhausted the resources of the Riverdell Tracking and Training Facility.  The final training location within the park will advance you beyond level fifteen.  That, however, is still quite a  distance away.

name: Rose Bush
description: This is the final destination of the Riverdell Tranquility Park.  Here, a ranger who is level fifteen or above may train.  If this is your desire, you should enter the rose bush.  If you wish to leave the park, go out.

name: Ranger Training Location
description: Your tracking skills will mislead you if you attempt to track out of the rose bush.  In the grassy hill, you will find what you are seeking to help you find people, lost in the forest or deep within the bowels of the city.

name: Grassy Hill
description: The hill is delightfully quiet, and quite a relaxing break from the hectic bustle of the city.  The grassy hill will give you some time to relax while you build up your strength to fight whatever happens to come after you next.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: This cavern runs east and west through the large glacier.  This passage is smaller than the other passages through the caverns.  You can hear some loud chanting to the northwest somewhere.  The hallways are patrolled by skeletal warriors who don't care to much for intruders.

name: Desolate Corridor
description: The dark corridor runs north and south through the glacier into the rocks surrounding it.  The corridor appears to be quite desolate and the dust on the ground looks undisturbed.  Who knows what might be hidden under the thick dust.

name: Desolate Corridor
description: The quiet corridor looks like it hasn't been walked through for ages.  The thick dust has been collecting for what appears to be centuries.  The hallway continues to the north and the west.  You can hear some activity brewing to the north, but you can't really see much, though.

name: Desolate Corridor
description: Oddly, there is not a lot of activity along this corridor, but you do see quite a bit of decaying bones scattered about along the floor.  The dust is so thick along the floor that you might actaully find something hidden, obscured by the dust.

name: Desolate Corridor
description: The dimly lit cavern doesn't appear to have supported any life of any kind for the past century or so.  The dust is so heavy, it's likely to cover up anything that might be lying around on the floor.  The hallway runs to the north and east.

name: Desolate Corridor
description: The small cavern is too small for any frost giants to move around in and the cumulation of dust and cobwebs suggests that the passage hasn't been used much at all in the past few years.  The cavern continues to the north and south.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: You are at a small intersection in the caverns.  A smaller cavern runs to the east, while the main cavern continues to the north and south.  As you head further south, you notice that the corridor gets smaller as the ceiling starts to lower.

name: Frost Giant Cavern
description: This section of the cavern is much smaller than the rest of the caves in the area, and are patrolled primarilly by the massive armies of skeletal warriors who are here to protect and serve the giants.  The cavern continues to the east and west.

name: Secret Passage
description: The large room to the north appears to be the source of all the chanting. Peeking through the keyhole, you can make out at least six skeletons and a couple of skeletal warriors.  The door to the north is locked with what looks like a bone lock, which is not easily pickable.

name: Secret Passage
description: The passage heads north back into the frost giant caverns.  The door to the south is protected by what appears to be a bone lock, one of the most secure devices and nearly impossible to pick.  Through the keyhole, you can see at least six skeletons and a couple of skeletal warriors chanting loudly.  There is also a key in the center of the room.

name: Skeletal Warrior Sanctum
description: This sanctum is used by the skeletal warriors to train, regroup, and prepare for the biddings of the frost giants, who they serve fanatically.  There are already a number of warriors in here training with other skeletons, preparing them for battle.  The angry skeletons don't appear to like being disturbed.

name: Frost Giant Hallway
description: Two spectacular golden doors lie to the north of the great hallway, which presumably lead to the great throne room of the frost giant king.  The doors are locked and guarded by frost giants and other skeletal warriors. The hallway to the south leads back out to the caverns under the glacier.

name: The Great Frost Giant Throne Room
description: Frost giants are not very friendly types, but the king may allow you to talk to him for a little while before his guards throw you out.  The lavish palace is carved out from the massive glacier, garnished with jewels and gold.  The exquisite palace was no doubt paid for by taking the jewels and gold from the people who so foolishly wandered into this deadly glacier.

name: Royal Treasure Room
description: The magnificent room glitters with gold and jewels beyond which the mind can possibly comprehend.  In addition to the various pots of gold scattered about the room, there are also a few strange, magical wands and scrolls which may also be useful to a successful campaign.

name: Lyanden Park
description: The large park stands as a gathering place for the people of the city to hear the royal decrees from the Speaker of Lyanden Castle, Lord Ponternal. The drawbridge is located to the east, but as is usually the case, the drawbridge is raised.  There appears to be a small guard station to the east near the drawbridge.

name: Commerce Street
description: Tiamat Lane is directly north, and a potions shop is located on the west side of the lane.  Scholars have long known that books and artifacts of all kinds can usually be found in the shops along here.

name: Commerce Street
description: Several small shops are crowded along both the east and west side of this shopping district.  Although the street is small, there are a number of  shoppers going in and out of the business places.  Some of these shops are famous even in Oceancrest.  Tiamat Lane is the street you see to the north,  where you also see the doors of the Great Observatory.

name: Tower Lane
description: The entrance to the museum appears to be west of here.  A tiny temple is on the north side of the road, barely coming to your chest in height.  The door is open, and you can see pixies and other small creatures inside.  On the south side, next door to the museum, is a research center for a dwarven mines and tunnels society.

name: Charybdis Way
description: The building, located on  west side of the street, is a research hospital financed by one of the paladin orders.  Seems they are interested in the process of life and death, and as such have built this hospital for the purpose of investigating this interesting cycle.

name: Charybdis Way
description: The intersection with Alturis Road is directly south.  From here, you can see the famous Hanging Gardens which are built along Alturis Road.  There is an entrance to the great medical research hospital run by the Holy Order of the White Rose.  The entrance is on the west side of the street.

name: Pearl Avenue
description: The Great Library covers the entire western side of the block while the Towers of Kista are on the east side.  The library has a massive door which never seems to close, while the Towers are surrounded by a forbidding moat.

name: Archives of the Great Library
description: There are many books, tomes, scrolls and other sources of knowledge that have been brought here for safe storage that have never been examined.  The curators simply haven't had the time, and are constantly busy indexing and cross-indexing everything for the scholars who come here.

name: Pearl Avenue
description: Sweetwater Lane is directly north.  The Great Library on the west side of the avenue was built by King Lyanden to be a research center for scholars. The library has most every original document ever published, but has loaned some of them to the Oceancrest library for study.

name: Tiamat Lane
description: The Towers soar far into the clouds over your head, making you feel like a country bumpkin as you tilt your head back to look.  But the Towers are  impressive!  On the north side of the street you see a fellowship hall for members of the Royal Order of Trackers and Rangers.

name: Tiamat Lane
description: A formidable wall protects you from the moat at this point.  As you look closely, you realize this must be the wall where the moat keepers have installed a maintenance lock so they can do repairs and other necessary duties involving the moat monsters.

name: Charybdis Way
description: A sturdy wall keeps you from the Great Observatory grounds to the east. on the west side are three pubs in a row.  The northernmost pub has the the largest sign, which reads "Red Dragon Pub - Coldest Ale in the City." You have to descend some steps to get there.

name: Myrr Lane
description: The intersection with Pearl Avenue is directly west, while to the east you can see where West Lake Circle begins.  This section of the city is  mostly inhabited by gnomes who have established a small enclave here.

name: Kista Avenue
description: Travelers must present their papers whenever they enter or leave the grand city of Kista.  Their is a tax for all but true scholars, since this city was built as a repository for knowledge.  Scholars are welcome to stay and study, but others must pay a toll if they are simply visiting or stopping for the night.  The gate is immediately north of here.

name: Myrr Lane
description: Lake Kista is directly north of the city and Myrr Lane runs along its southern shore.  There are several small homes, shops and buildings between you and the lake's edge.  Farther to the east or west you will find Lake View Drive, which completely encircles the alpine lake.  On the south side of the lane is a wall which surrounds the Great Observatory.

name: Myrr Lane
description: Several factories and stores are along the north side of the street. The closest one seems to be associated with the Institute of Investigations into Ball Lightning.  the roof seems to have an array of lightning rods mounted very close together.  The Great Observatory is on the south side.

name: Myrr Lane
description: A very large but ruined building stands on the north side of the lane. Kista is a city devoted to research and the advancement of knowledge, but the Institute of Investigations into Ball Lightning simply ran a particular experiment with too little safeguards.  Part of the building was destroyed, but you see there were several left intact.

name: East Gate of the City of Kista
description: The walls of the city are snow-white and sparkle with an irrediscent twinkle of pastel colors.  To the east lies a great oaken forest, dark and lonely.

name: Randolf Lane
description: The group of buildings to the north form the Althemanian College, a school for graduate students in the Iilandi University System.  On the south side of Randolf Lane is one of the barracks for the Kista Security Forces.

name: Ivory Way
description: The intersection of Randolf Lane is directly to the north.  There is a giant amphetheater on the east side of the street.  Looks like the  entrance may be located to the south, judging by they way the foot traffic is headed.  A small cafe with outdoor seating is on the west side.

name: Ivory Way
description: The pub seems to enjoy the patronage of the many graduate students who do research over at the college.  Once they get out of the lab, they seem to be no different than the undergraduates in Oceancrest.  Always drinking. Randolf Lane is south of here.

name: Ivory Way
description: A very low building sits on a grassy lot to the west.  A sign out front proclaims it to be the "Center for Research on Anti-Gravity and Levitation." From here you can see several humans inside the building, all of whom appear to be wearing white coats and carrying clipboards.

name: Alturis Road
description: There is a research park on the north side of the road, and the famous Hanging Gardens on the south side.  The city of Kista seems to be a mix of of wonderful grand scale art and the latest in science.  Kista was built by the three major races in Mordor as a place for all knowledge.

name: Teal Avenue
description: On the west side of the avenue you can see the amphitheater and hear the music of the orchestra.  Must be something interesting there tonight.  On the east side there are several small foundries and specialized factories which produce the latest in armor and professional equipment for people who can afford their wares.

name: Teal Avenue
description: Many of the new ideas and concepts which basic research produces are turned into usable products by the factories on this street.  On the east side you see a bright green building and a sign which says they specialize in enchanted rods and staves.  They proudly state that they use only the latest spells in production.

name: Teal Avenue
description: There is a fenced hill to the south, and the avenue jogs to the east to avoid it.  Looks like it might be the overflow seating for the amphitheater  located west of here.  Small factories are on the east side of the street.

name: Teal Avenue
description: Several factories and testing areas are located to the north.  The craftsmen who work there take a great deal of pride in their work, as they reputedly use only the latest technology to produce their wares.

name: Teal Avenue
description: There is a huge pillar of flame shooting out of the ground just south of here.  A small building is at the southern end of Teal Avenue, and it looks like it is the entrance to a testing grounds.  The flames are blow-torch  hot, and there are several dwarves in flame retardent suits testing shields in the pillar of flames.

name: Annetol Way
description: On the south side of the road you see an asbestos covered wall made of lava rock.  The wall feels very warm to the touch.  Looks like the road comes to an end a little farther east, where you see a very bright light.

name: Annetol Way/Teal Avenue Intersection
description: A huge blue-white pillar of flame shoots out of the ground behind a small building situated south of here.  A fiery sign burns brightly near the  entrance, and identifies this as the pyro testing grounds administered by the Iilandi University School of Pyrographic Phenomena.

name: Ivory Way
description: To the south you can see the intersection with Myrr Lane, and to the north is the entrance to the granary.  Several botanists are measuring grain as it comes down a chute, and a distiller's cart is being loaded nearby.

name: Myrr Lane
description: There is an empty lot on the north side of the lane, but close to the edge of the street is a watchman's shack.  This empty lot is not the normal, overgrown-with-weeds lot you may be used to.  This is an EMPTY LOT.   There's nothing there but a black hole.

name: Myrr Lane
description: On the north side of the lane is a fence around an empty lot.  On the south side you see another lot, but a huge multi-branched fungus covers it.  The fungus seems to writh and move, but only slowly.  There is a path through the tangled mass, but why would anyone want to walk through it?

name: Kista Avenue
description: There is a flower shop that specializes in rare and exotic plants and flowers on the east side of the avenue.  A retired botanist lives in the quarters above the shop, although some whisper that he isn't really retired, but  simply found something in his research that he didn't want to share with the University.  They say he continues his research in secret now.

name: Kista Avenue
description: On the east side of the avenue you see Jaspar's Printing and Publishing Company.  Jaspar found a way to print scrolls that destroy themselves once they are studied or used.  It seems to make for a steady business, as people continually want to carry spares.

name: Kista Avenue
description: You are on Kista Avenue, south of the intersection with Tiamat Lane. The Great Library takes up all of the east side of the block, but on the west side of the avenue there is a three story building painted with broad pastel stripes.  Carved into the corner stone you see, "Iilandi University - School of Astrology."  The entrance seems to be farther south.

name: Kista Avenue
description: A pink and green door on the west side of the avenue leads into a three story building maintained by the Iilandi University System.  Although the building is called the School of Astrology, there are no students there. The University reserves this place as a seminar and conference building for the best minds concerned with astrology.

name: Kista Avenue
description: A shopping center and several good restaurants are along the avenue here. On the west side of the avenue you see Haxel's New Antiques next door to the Tail o' the Ox Fine Foods.  On the east side of the avenue there is a custom armorsmith and a tiny restaurant specializing in Fresh Fowl and Old Wine.

name: Kista Avenue
description: The charming old house you see on the east side is the home of the Gaddion Light Opera Company, world renowned for their intepretation and performance of the operas written by Stanaslov and Stirenski.  The company is on tour six months of the year, but spend summer and fall in Kista.

name: Kista Avenue
description: Alturis Road is directly south, giving you a good view of the great Hanging Gardens.  There is an apothecary shoppe on the corner just opposite the Cathedral.  They charge high prices, but it all goes for a good cause since it is used to support the building fund for the Cathedral.

name: Red Haze
description: It's almost like a luminescent fog, making it impossible for you to see even your hand when you put it in front of your eyes.  It's neither warm nor cold however, but it is as silent as a tomb.  The only thing that draws your attention is an area in the haze that is slightly more intense in the color red than its surroundings.  You might try going that way.

name: Red Haze
description: It's almost like a luminescent fog, making it impossible for you to see even your hand when you put it in front of your eyes.  It's neither warm nor cold however, but it is as silent as a tomb.  The only thing that draws your attention is an area in the haze that is slightly more intense in the color red than its surroundings.  You might try going that way.

name: Alturis Road
description: The grand Cathedral of Veratus is on the south side of the road, a monument to a cluster of gods and immortals who inhabited the mountains long ago.  The strangest thing about the gods who are worshipped here is that they are no longer in residence.  Some say they are simply sleeping, awaiting the time when they are truly needed to save the world.  A single immortal remains.  She is the oracle.

name: Cryptographer's Research Room
description: Papers cover the desk and the floor, and books are piled everywhere. There are charts covering every wall with tables and transposed alphabets. Although there isn't anyone here right now, this seems to be a very busy room in the Tower.

name: Second Floor West Hallway
description: On the east side is another orange painted door.  Must be the same room with the orange door in the main hallway south of here.  This hallway is not as well decorated as the main one, but it still seems pretty ornate by most standards.  There seem to be some offices further north.

name: Second Floor West Hallway
description: On the west side there is an office with the door slightly ajar.  This is not as well lighted an area as the rest of the hallway, but a bright light  comes from under the office door.  Odd that you cannot hear anything,  though.  Maybe there is nobody in there.

name: Alturis Road
description: You are on Alturis Road, between the Cathedral and the Hanging Gardens. The Cathedral is run by an order of monks who believe they must forever cover their eyes to simulate blindness, and thus approach the attainment of knowledge without being corrupted by worldly attractions.  They once had many gods who resided in the Cathedral whom they believe taught them this strange behaviour, but now there is only the Oracle remaining.

name: Alturis Road
description: A great many travelers from distant places stop here, because Veratus, the oracle who is inside, will answer at least one question from anyone. If the questioner asks interesting questions, the oracle will sometimes continue to answer them.  If you seek knowledge, this is a good place to start.  Be sure to cover your eyes inside.  The monks insist on that.

name: Pearl Avenue
description: The Kista Town Hall is on the east side of the Avenue.  Although the true leaders of Kista hold offices in the Towers, There is a mayor and a council who handle the day-to-day business of running the city.  Kista is a very democratic city, and everyone can come to the Town Hall and be  heard, if they have an opinion. The Grand Catheral is west of you.

name: Charybdis Way
description: On the west side of the street you see a quiet moat around the Towers of Kista.  Occasionally bubbles rise from the depths, and sometimes you see the tail of some giant beast splash the surface.  Other than that, the moat is rather quiet.  On the east side is a line of small shops.

name: Ivory Way
description: A small tree-lined park can be seen to the east, and a wall around the Great Observatory is on the west.  Most people think there is only one entrance to the Observatory which they point out as the one on Tiamat Lane. But sometimes, early in the morning hours, the really big wigs who run that place can be seen leaving the park, and nobody saw them go in there.

name: Gotland Glenn Trail
description: The pass over the mountains to the north is blocked at this time of year, but when you can travel that way you will find it takes you to a vast grasslands.  The Gotland Glenn is a mysterious place that some report is  inhabited by a mole-like people who have built an entire city under the ground.  The wind never stops blowing across the Glenn, and earth-magic  is said to work very well there.

name: Great Observatory Entry
description: Great columns of white marble line the hallway you see to the north. On either side of this entry there are small offices and public information rooms.  There is also a shop where you may purchase charts and other items related to the work of this wonderful place.  The exit is south.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: There is a large, thick hedge on either side which prevents people from entering the Garden at this point.  The entry probably is to the south. On the west side there is an archery range.  The hedge no doubt protects a lot of people from being accidently sent back to the Tree of Life.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: Although the Gardens were built for Queen Isaria a long time ago, It is Elise who enjoys them today.  Elise is the most powerful mage in Kista, a White Moon, a Preserver Wizard.  She is well respected in the Towers. She spends much of her free time in the Garden.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: The base of the many-tiered Hanging Gardens is made of solid gold, with an occasional gemstone set in for contrast.  There are also places where you see runes and cryptograms cut into the gold.  There's probably a message here, if you could understand it.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: On the west side of the road you can hear the "thwacking" sound of an arrow hitting its target.  There is an archery range on the other side, but you are protected by a thick hedge.  The Great Hanging Gardens are on the east.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: The road is quiet, tree-lined and very pleasant.  The Hanging Gardens are immediately west and a delectable odor of ripening fruit comes from that way.  Just about any kind of tree you can imagine has been planted in the living monument.  On the east side you see a small shrine.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: The sound of small animals and birds can be heard from the trees and ferns in the famous Gardens.  There is a story that there is a mirror pool located in the Garden, but that only the pure of heart can ever see it.  At one time the citizens of the old realm suggested that evil-doers be brought there to  administer justice, but unfortunately the judges could never find the pool.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: The base of the living monument is made of pure gold mined from a dwarven mine in the mountains and forest to the south of here.  The eastern slopes  of the Nartiz Mountains lie to the south, and the Kista Forest covers them.

name: Garden Circle Road
description: Dark forests grow almost to the edge of the City here.  To the south you can see the famous Kista Forest, a dense oak and pine growth that provides much of the lumber and hardwood for the city.  There is a mill not far to the south, but after that there is simply wild woods.

name: Kista Town Hall
description: There is a meeting here every week, even if the council has nothing to do. The council members get paid for attending meetings, and it doesn't matter if there is nothing on the agenda, so long as they are here.  Some evenings they barely have time to call the roll before they all go home again.

name: Mayor's Office
description: The mayor isn't really dishonest, but there really isn't much for him to do.  The real leaders of the city are in the Tower and Mayor Kreech simply takes his orders from them.  He does, however, have to run for  re-election every few years, and tries to satisfy his most important backers.  He's not above taking a bribe or two.  Do you have any money?

name: Emergency Room
description: The hospital is actually run by an order of paladins, the Order of the White Rose.  In the Land of Mordor there is an everlasting cycle of life and death, one followed by the other in an eternal search for adventure and treasure.  The paladins would like to learn the meaning of it all.

name: Tower Lane
description: The citizens of Kista are very proud of their library, as it is known throughout the land as the depository of all knowledge.  Actually, many of the books owned by the Kista Library are on loan to the library in Oceancrest, but the rarest books have never left this building.  Pearl Avenue is to the east.

name: Tower Lane
description: A tall building on the north side of the lane has a frieze on its side. The frieze depicts the planets, the sun and the moon.  Large icons of  astrological figures ring the frieze.  To the west is Kista Lane, and  the entrance to the building is there.

name: Tower Lane
description: A very large and tall hotel is on both sides of the street, and if you look overhead you can see a walkway bridge which spans Tower Lane.   The narrow bridge seems to connect both buildings together, and you see people up there looking down on the street.  A sign on the bridge proclaims it to be the Royal Kista Arms.  The Milsene Museum is east of here.

name: Evan's Quarters
description: Actually, Evan gave himself the title since no one else ever considered giving him one.  Evan probably could have been a better than average mage, but he had an opportunity to open this shop and became too interested in making money.  It's a decision he regrets every day.

name: Curator's Office
description: The Curator is responsible for all of the books and other research material found in this great building.  There is more material to study than any single person could ever assimilate, but if anyone has, it is the Curator.

name: Cathedral of Veratus
description: At the end of the stations to the north is the chambers of the Oracle. She is jealously guarded by the monks who maintain this shrine to long forgotten gods of the mountains, as she is the only one of the gods who  still listens to them.  If you wish to ask her a question, you must go to the first of the stations.  She takes the form of an owl, and if she likes your question, you may see her at the next station.

name: First Station of the Oracle
description: Veratus the Oracle often takes the form of a small owl at this first station, and will answer one question only here.  If you pique her interest, you may advance to the second station, and ask another.  Unfortunately, the  monks here do not like you taking up her time with your questions, when they have questions of their own.

name: Second Station of the Oracle
description: This Grand Cathedral was once the home of several gods from the mountains, but they decided they liked the mountains better than staying here around a bunch of monks who always kept their eyes covered.  The monks believed the gods wanted them to do that, but there was a real lack of communication. Veratus can be found here if she liked your first question.

name: Third Station of the Oracle
description: Candles and burning incense are set into niches in the wall, and a small fountain of water cascades down the tiled wall on the other side.  If you have reached this place and Veratus is still here, in the form of an owl,  then you have gained her interest in your quest.  Once you enter her  chambers, you will see her in her true form.

name: Chambers of Veratus
description: The room is dim, and slightly cool with a strange perfume in the air. There is no furniture that you can see, but pillows and rare murask furs cover the floor.  A pool of shimmering amber liquid is set in the center of the room, in a raised soffet with a blue robe across it.

name: Reflecting Pool Bridge
description: To the north you can see the wall around the Hanging Gardens, and to the south you see a very restful spot with comfortable benches.  Below you is a quiet pool, almost like a mirror in appearance.  A face looks back at you, but it's not your face!

name: First Station of the Oracle
description: Veratus the Oracle often takes the form of a small owl at this first station, and will answer one question only here.  If you pique her interest, you may advance to the second station, and ask anoter.  Unfortunately, the monks here do not like you taking up her time with your questions, when they have questions of their own.

name: Second Station of the Oracle
description: This Grand Cathedral was once the home of several gods from the mountains, but they decided they liked the mountains better than staying here around a bunch of monks who always kept their eyes covered.  The monks believed the gods wanted them to do that, but there was a real lack of communication. Veratus can be found here if she liked your first question.

name: Third Station of the Oracle
description: Candles and burning incense are set into niches in the wall, and a small fountain of water cascades down the tile wall on the other side.  If you have reached this place and Veratus is still here, in the form of an owl, then you have gained her interest in your quest.  Once you enter her chambers, you will see her in her true form.

name: Hanging Gardens Entry
description: Some of the rarest and most exotic plants in the world can be found here. Ferns and flowers adorn the grounds under giant trees, while succulent vines grow up the sides of the trees.  There is a heady perfume from almost every plant, and the air is damp with a fine mist.  The Garden is alive with the calls of small animals and insects.  Randolf the Blue spared no expense when he built this place as a monument for his wife.  However, be warned:  this place is reserved for royalty, and commoners are forbidden.

name: Arboretum Way
description: The path to the northeast will take you to the second level of the Garden. This walkway was the favorite of Queen Isaria, for whom the Hanging Gardens were built, and some say her ghost can still be heard whispering though the trees when the breeze is just right.  Have you noticed the breeze has picked up?  Seems a little chilly, too.

name: Arboretum Way
description: Actually, this is really just a very wide path through the trees, but it is well maintained and you find it quite clean.  There are a number of owls  overhead, and strangely, you can understand their conversation.  They invite you to join them, if you can fly.  To the east you can see the second level.

name: Hedge Rows
description: It looks as though the hedges have been planted to form a maze, where one might wander around for a long time.  At the moment, you stand on a raised area where you can look over the entire hedge garden, and you can choose to enter if you wish, but you might be lost forever.  The second of the Garden is to the southeast.

name: North Wall
description: Tropical plants abound here, and the banana trees are ready to harvest. Soft ferns brush against your boots as you walk, and low hanging shade trees obscure your vision in all directions.  A small stream of water is to the south, where you see a high-arched bridge over a pool.

name: Fruit Orchid
description: Every variety of fruit tree that exists seems to be here, and each has been carefully tended so that it produces only the very best fruit.  A  pair of trees near the path are drooping with beautiful ripe pears.  The second level of the Garden is up a winding path to the southwest.

name: Weeping Willows
description: this is the eastern side of the Hanging Gardens, between the rose garden and the fruit orchid.  Many say there is magic associated with the trees you find here, and some even say the willows truly weep for the sins of men.  Occasionally you see sprites flit from tree to tree.  Mostly they ignore you, but some stop and stare from a distance.  The second level is located up the path to the west.

name: Rose Garden
description: There is a gardner stationed here to prevent anyone from picking the beautiful blooms, as these are the roses used by the council in the Kista Towers when they wish to discuss something in secret.  One of  these roses is suspended over the meeting table, placing the members under the rose, or "sub rosa."  The second level is northwest.

name: Orchid Wetlands
description: This is the second level of the Gardens, but you can get back to the first level by taking either of the southern exits.  A sign warns you     not to pick the flowers, as they have great magical properties and are used by Elise for her potions.  To the north is a tower, which forms the the third level of the Gardens.

name: Field of Foxglove
description: For a reason unknown to most people, the faerie folk are very fond of the foxglove blossom.  This field must certainly be attractive to them, for  the riotous color, if nothing else.  This is the second level of the Hanging Gardens.  The first level is to the west, and a beautiful tower  forms the third level to the east.

name: Carnivorous Plant Area
description: You are on the second level of the famous Hanging Gardens, in an area shunned by most visitors.  And for good reason, since the plants here seem to have some mobility, and although very beautiful, they do look dangerous.  You can get down to the first level by taking any of the northern exits.  A tower is south of you, covered with vines.

name: Poppy Field
description: This is the second level, but you can get down to the first level by going east from here.  The third level is actually a tower you see to the west, more or less in the center of the entire Garden.  The tower seems to be covered with honeysuckle and other climbing vines.  Pixies use the gum from the poppies to make a fine dust for parties.

name: Base of the Tower of Kuroth
description: Kuroth Tower is not very tall, and at one time was designed to be the third level of the Garden.  The tower is covered with flowering vines, hiding  even the ancient door, which must be around here somewhere.  Unfortunately, a demon has taken possession of the structure, and now resides inside. There is a tale that the demon stole one of the three crystal masks belonging to Elise, and dares her to come here for it.

name: Reflecting Pool
description: Great slabs of flat rock hang over a reflecting pool, while fruit trees are heavy with their perfect produce.  Someone has lodged a keg of mild brandy into the bole of a walnut tree, and it seems to never empty.  There are  bright, sparkling points of light in the air.  A bridge goes to the north.

name: Hedge Row
description: The hedges have been cut and shaped into animals and symbols by the  gardners who work here.  Perhaps if you note the shapes carefully,   or drop something, you can map your way out of here.

name: Kuroth Tower
description: the single room is dark and damp, with cobwebs everywhere.  One ceiling beam has fallen to the floor.  The stairway goes both up and down from  this room.  You can see the roof on the second level above, but there  seems to be an evil smell from that direction.  The stairwell descending into the depths is simply black and silent.

name: Hedge Row
description: The hedges have been cut and shaped into animals and symbols by the gardners who work here.  Perhaps if you note the shapes carefully, or drop something, you can map your way out of here.

name: Hedge Row
description: The hedges have been cut and shaped into animals and symbols by the  gardners who work here.  Perhaps if you note the shapes carefully,   or drop something, you can map your way out of here.

description: The hedges have been cut and shaped into animals and symbols by the gradners who work here.  Perhaps if you note the shapes carefully, or drop something, you can map your way out of here.

name: Hedge Row
description: The hedges have been cut and shaped into animals and symbols by the gardners who work here.  Perhaps if you note the shapes carefully, or drop something, you can map your way out of here.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: You are in a dark and evil smelling tunnel under the Hanging Gardens. There are bats and other creatures here, and its not a good place to be. Water trickles down the center of the muddy floor making the way rather slippery.  Be careful not to fall into some sort of trap.  The light you  see to the west is the tunnel entrance in the hedge maze.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: The muddy floor makes squishy sounds as you move, and sometimes when you stop there is another squishy sound in the distance down the tunnel. If you stand very quiet though, you cannot hear it anymore.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: This tunnel seems to be mostly inhabitated by rats, spiders and bats, but occasionally you sense something bigger moving in the darkness.  It doesn't seem to get any closer to you, but you can feel the presense as you continue your way through the damp and slippery tunnel.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: The slime on the walls is almost alive, and makes the going very slippery. The demon Kuroth built this tunnel as an escape from his tower, in case he was ever attacked by Elise, whom he dared to come after him after he had stolen her crystal mask.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: The air is damp and makes it hard for your lungs to draw in a breath. You find yourself gasping from time to time.  This tunnel seems to have doors about every ten meters that are self closing and locking.  Kuroth never meant for anyone to be here, but he took no chances.

name: Kuroth's Tunnel
description: The tunnel is rather large, which makes you wonder at the size of Kuroth. the door to the north is not locked, but the south door requires a key. Could this be where Kuroth has hidden the crystal mask?

name: Kuroth Tower Basement
description: The stairwell continues to descend into an even blacker abyss, and also goes up to the ground floor.  The demon Kuroth lives somewhere in this  miserable place, having transformed a once beautiful tower into an ugly and evil entry to hell.  Kuroth has hidden one of three crystal masks down here.  It belongs to Elise, the White Moon wizard.

name: Kuroth Tower Roof
description: Large birds of prey have been here and left a partially eaten body of an elf on the stone work.  The smell is terrible.  There's no telling whom it might have been because the face is missing.  Kuroth the demon considers the vultures as pets and encourages them to roost here.

name: The Gold Room
description: The golden brilliance of the room radiates from every direction as light from the sun shines through the glacier into this room.  However, other than the fact that the room is composed of gold, the rooms is otherwise unremarkable.  There are three doors in the room, heading to the north, east and west, respectively.

name: Hallway
description: The hallway is finely crafted out of the rock and ice into square edges which makes walking around very easy.  The long hallway continues as far north as you can see.  To the south is a strange door seemingly in the middle of nowhere.  It appears to be locked, but shouldn't be too hard to pick.

name: Hallway
description: The main hallway continues to the north and south, while a second hallway juts off to the east.  It is very quiet in these halls  almost too quiet. You don't see many monsters in these caverns, but perhaps something has scared them away.

name: Hallway
description: Strangely, the walls of the hallway are perfectly square.  It's almost like you're walking through a regular building, except the walls are  composed of granite and ice.  The hallway continues to the north and south.  An eerie silence continues as you walk around the desolate hall.

name: Hallway
description: The main hallway continues to the north and south, while an equally wide hallway breaks off to the east.  Both hallways are very quiet.  Nor can you hear the movement of rats or other vermin through the desolate caverns.  As you head to the north or east, it also starts getting dark.

name: Hallway
description: It has gotten rather dark as you have passed into the rocky surface below the great ice glacier.  The sun can no longer illuminate your path and you must resort to torches or magic to proceed.  The hallway runs north and south, intersecting another hallway, which heads west.

name: Hallway
