description: It's strange not to hear any noises at all, deep within the caves and caverns below the glacier.  You would expect some squeaks or other shifting sounds, but nothing can be heard.  The air is oddly stale, but does not smell of decay or death.

name: Hallway
description: The long, dark hallway continues to the north and south seemingly without end.  The silent air gives you an eerie feeling that somehow you are being watched, but you can't see anything in either direction that might be a threat.

name: Hallway
description: The long hallway runs south from here.  On the east wall is a relatively unremarkable door with a silver lock on it.  As you peek through the key- hole, you can see the door enters a large room approximately fifty meters wide.  Something is moving inside, but you can't tell what it is in the darkness.

name: Hallway
description: To the east and west, you can see two long hallways running north and  south, parallel to each other.  The short hallway you are in connects  them together.  The passage is about thirty meters long between the two main hallways, and remains quite dark even with your light sources.

name: Hallway
description: The door to the south is sealed shut, almost as if with magic.  A hazy, shimmering aura surrounds the mysterious door which cannot be opened by even the strongest barbarian.  The door has an arcane pattern on it, and if you had the ability to detect invisible things, you might be able to make out what's there.  It's hard to look directly at the door.

name: Hallway
description: The long hallway extends out to the north and south as far as you can see, even in the darkness.  There is a small hallway to the east which appears to connect this and another, longer hallway further to the east. The dark tunnels are still strangely quiet and tranquil  an obvious sign that something is amiss.

name: Hallway
description: The odd door to the north is decorated in fine gold and platinum.   Unfortunately, you cannot see through a keyhole into the adjacent room because there is no keyhole to look through.  Along the wall are four strange buttons in mysterious colors which are hard to identify.

name: Hallway
description: Light reaches this part of the hallway, but just barely.  You can see the massive block of ice above you, but there's no way of telling just how far the ice extends and exactly how far underground you are.  As you head further to the east, you can see the darkness setting in as you head into the rocks under the glacier.

name: Hallway
description: There is a small hallway which breaks off to the south from here, leading into darkness.  To the east, all you can see is the pitch blackness of the dark rock and granite which has never seen the bright light of the sun shining through the ice.

name: Hallway
description: The eerie silence has returned.  The deathly quiet atmosphere is an almost sure sign of danger as nothing would be stupid enough to stick around  when their very livelihood is threatened.  The hallway continues to the east and west through the darkness.

name: Hallway
description: The corner of the hallway is just as unremarkable as the rest of the  hallways you have seen  however, you feel the presense of some evil force at work here.  Or maybe it's just the evil assassins in your party planning to backstab one of you for your weapon.

name: Hallway
description: The dark hall heads back to the south into the darkness.  On the north side of the hall is a large, silvery door with some arcane writing on it. It's pretty hard to read, but the symbols seem to say BEWARE.  There doesn't seem to be a lock on the door.

name: Triangular Room
description: The odd shaped room gets wider to the north, with the door forming the apex of the triangle.  There is some arcane, ancient writing on the wall which reads "Those who seek wisdom will prevail.  Those who seek gold will die."  There are odd symbols around the room, but otherwise, the room is quite empty.

name: Hydra's Den
description: The hydra is a ferocious, five-headed beast of the underworld who feasts on the bones of adventurers who are too curious for their own good.  The room is about thirty feet wide and seventy feet long, providing a lot of room for all the treasure the hydra likes to keep, assuming it hasn't been plundered already.

name: Dark Hallway
description: The desolate and dark hallway continues to the east, and enter the main  hallway to the west.  It appears that the people who built these halls forgot to seal them off when they were done.  They were apperently used as an access hall to the other side of the main hallway.

name: Dark Hallway
description: The seldom used hallway appears to be left over from the time when the caverns were being built.  The hall doesn't appear to fit into the main scheme of the hallway layout and looks even dustier than the main hallways. The dark hallway continues to the north and west.

name: Dark Hallway
description: This hallway was probably just an access way to some area beyond the main hallway before it was built.  It is now seldom used, as you can see by the layers of dust and grime on the floors.  The hallway runs into the main hall to the north.

name: Gold Hallway
description: The strange golden hallway continues to the west and ends in a odd looking door to the east.  The door to the east is not locked.  Looking through the keyhole, you can see a larger, gold room, to which this hallway must be connected.  The hallway is sparkling and clean without a speck of  dust to see seen.

name: Gold Hallway
description: The fancy hallway comes to a corner here where it turns to the north and to the east.  The gold which makes up the hallway's walls is not in the least bit tarnished and the hallway appears to be kept very clean.  The only odd part about the hall is the deathly silence.  There is almost no activity to be heard in any direction.

name: Gold Hallway
description: The odd looking door to the north seems to glow with a strange, bluish hue.  The otherwise majestic hallway is composed almost completely of  gold.  The gold door on the north wall appears to be locked magically. Careful examination of the south wall will reveal four rings that  you probably didn't see before.  That is, if you can detect invisible things.

name: Amber Rose Anteroom
description: The magnificent Amber Rose Anteroom is a fantastically carved and  decorated room with portraits and other fancy artworks lying around.  There is a large podium in the center of the room with a strange scroll lying on it.  A mysterious, shadowy creature guards the scroll.

name: Secret Hallway
description: There are doors on both ends of the hallway.  The north door leads back into the Adamantine Hallway.  The south door is bolted and locked with a strange, silverish lock.  You can see a powerful, golden light shining through the keyhole of the south door.  The light is so bright, you can't seen anything else in the room.

name: Secret Hallway
description: There are two doors on both ends of the hallway.  The door on the south appears to lead back into the main hallway under the glacier.  The door on the north is bolted and locked with a shimmering, silvery lock.  An odd but powerful gold glow is radiated out from the room behind the north door that you can see through the keyhole.  The light is so bright that you can't see anything else in the room.

name: Archive Room
description: The magnificent room glows with a powerful golden aura which almost blinds you as you enter.  There is but one object in the room, which is the source of the powerful, golden glow (assuming someone hasn't already looted the archive room).  You can see some script carved into the wall which reads "The power of the scroll can only be unleashed by a wizard of great power."

name: Adamantine Hall
description: The great hall shines with a radiance of silver adamantine unlike anything you've seen in your life.  Even the dwarves would be in awe at such a lavish use of the precious metal.  A sharp-eyed dwarf will also notice traces of mithril in the walls.  There are two doors leading out of the hall to the east and west.  You can hear some gurgling sounds to the east, but there is nothing to the west.  The hall is otherwise quite empty.

name: Grey Hallway
description: There appears to be a lot of activity around here.  The grey walls are occasionly painted with blood and some scattered bones lie dormant on the floor.  Pieces of rotting flesh and half-eaten body parts are also scattered about.  There is a large door to the west that appears to be locked.

name: Grey Hallway
description: The dark and desolate hallway appears to be patrolled by flesh-eating trolls who would love to have you for dinner, quite literally.  Scattered bones and half-eaten remains lie along the floor, rotting silently with the passage of time.

name: Grey Hallway
description: A couple of trolls are waiting here to ambush a wandering party who so foolishly would wander into their lair.  The trolls enjoy a good fight even though they don't like to fight very fair.  The grey hallway continues  to the north and west.

name: Grey Hallway
description: The grime covered grey walls seem to disappear into the lake as you  head off to the north.  You can hear sounds of fighting and arguing to the south.  The lake to the north does not look very friendly.  You can  occasionally see some air bubbles rising to the surface, a sure sign of some sort of life form down there.

name: Plasnelt Lake
description: Plasnelt Lake is a rather large body of water that somehow got trapped below the surface of the glacier.  Surprisingly, the lake water is very salty, as if it were ocean water.  Perhaps there is an underground cavern to the ocean from here.

name: Plasnelt Lake
description: The salty water suggests that there might be a way out into the ocean from here, but it'd be hard to find without some serious help.  The lake is very deep.  Occasionally, you hear gurgling noises coming from the center of the lake.

name: Plasnelt Lake
description: The lake is a very dangerous place to be wandering around because there really isn't anyplace to run.  Dangerous sahuagin have been said to roam the surface and depths of salt water lakes and oceans.  The center of the lake appears to also be the center of activity.

name: Plesnelt Lake
description: The surface of the lake is relatively calm, but you notice some sort of disturbance to the west, near the center of the lake.  It is rumored that sahuagin roam the salt water lakes and oceans.  These ferocious demons of the deep kill without mercy.

name: Plasnelt Lake
description: The center of the lake is quite deep and murky.  Who knows what inhabits the depths of the large lake, including a number of sahuagin warriors. It is possible that an entire civilization of sahuagin exist below the surface of this large lake.

name: Cave of the Yeti
description: For some reason, there is a lot of snow in this cave from some unknown source.  The Yeti Lord rules over his kingdom from here, so there must be some way back up to the surface from the cave.  The yeti are quite powerful creatures, and dine on whatever happens to wander by.  They are especially fond of sahuagin.

name: Plasnelt Lake Shore
description: You can see a small hallway forming to the west.  The walls are of  magnificent gold and silver, sparkling with scattered gemstones and jewels.  To the east, you can see the large underground, salt-water lake that seems to have formed under the glacier.

name: Silvery Corridor
description: The majestic cavern is quite odd to see in such a strange place, especially with the lake full of sahuagin and trolls nearby.  Nevertheless, the hall exists, but doesn't travel very far.  To the west, you can see a massive door covered with even more gemstones and jewels.  There is a strange, diamond and emerald lock on the door.

name: Marbella's Chambers
description: The magnificent decor of the room is composed mostly of gold and jewels with scattered pictures of the great wizard with such creatures as the great gold dragon, a massive cloud giant and other notable creatures of good will.  Well hidden from the outside world, the archmage Lena Marbella  can live in comfort without having to deal with the evil creatures lurking around every corner.

name: Crimson Hallway
description: The mysterious hallway seems to glow through the crimson colored walls carved out of the massive glacier.  To the east, there is a large door which appears to be magically sealed with a strange lock on the door. The hallway continues to the west.

name: Crimson Hallway
description: There is not a lot of activity around this corner of the crimson hallway but the halls are kept very clean.  The glimmering ice shines with a radiance unlike anything you've ever seen.  The hallway continues to the south and east.

name: Crimson Hallway
description: The hallway again turns to the north and west, winding through the strange corridors under the glacier.  The hallways are very desolate, but you can hear some activity in the distance to the northeast and southwest. The crimson hallways glitter with magnificent radiance.

name: Crimson Hallway
description: The crimson hallway heads east and south from this corner.  The shimmering ice and light from throughout the glacier shines through the magnificent hallway producing a powerful crimson aura.  You can here more distinct voices to the south.

name: Crimson Hallway
description: The mysterious powers at work here produce a powerful crimson aura as the light from the surface travels through the glacier into this hallway. There is a door on the south side of the hallway leading into what  appears to be a large room.  The door does not look locked.

name: Marbella's Study
description: As you enter the room the crimson aura that surrounded you in the hallway disipates and you notice a key hanging on the west wall.  On a table near the key is a cat, which must be Marbella's pet cat.  The cat glares at you suspiciously.

name: Depths of Plasnelt Lake
description: The underground lake appears to narrow at this point, and then expands in both directions (up and down).  You can barely make out the surface of the lake looking up.  Heading down, you can see the making of a large civilization underwater.

name: Plasnelt Lake Middle Depths
description: The center depths of the vast Plasnelt Lake are guarded by armies of sahuagin warriors, protecting their homes.  The sahuagin are vicious creatures of malace who dine on the flesh of the surface dwelling races. A large rock formation prevents you from going further down from this location.

name: Kaldeas' Mansion Entry
description: This is the famed Kaldeas Mansion of Illusion.  Not all is what it appears to be, once you enter this place.  The place is reputed to be empty, but that may not be true.  From here, near the front door, you can see the rooms apparently have a large number of mirrors in them.

name: Kaldeas' Mansion Foyer
description: The room is opulent and rich, but dusty, as though it had not been used for a very long time.  Mirrors hang at odd angles, and there are a number of doors along the hallway.  Mardic Kaldeas was known as a master of illusion, and everything you see behind those doors may not be exactly as they appear.

name: Kaldeas' Mansion Hallway
description: Far, far to the north is the foyer, which is the main entrance to this place. Not only was Kaldeas interested in illusion, of which he was the leader in that particular field of magic, but he was also a dabbler in mythology.

name: The Gate
description: This strange room located next the the hidden level of the Pits of Doom answers the question of where the monsters come from that inhabit this unholy place.  Before you is a large gate which appears to take you to some dark place deep within the bowels of the universe itself.  What lies beyond the gate may not even be of this world.  The gate radiates a faint goldish glow, and will not allow you to take anything beyond it.

name: Avernus
description: Avernus is the top layer of the Nine Hells, the plane of evil where evil manifests itself.  This plane is a rocky wasteland, guarded by hideous demons, ferocious dragons and unnatural devils.  Avernus is the most heavily guarded level of the Nine Hells, and you're likely to meet much resistance in this deadly realm.  The gateway to Dis, the second plane of the Nine Hells is guarded by Tiamat himself.

name: Avernus
description: This desolate wasteland is the place where all evil manifests itself.  No doubt, you will encounter many monsters of strange and mystical origins. The outer fringe of Avernus is patrolled by abishai and other lesser  devils.  The inner sanctuary is guarded by dragons, and the center of Avernus is guarded by Tiamat himself.

name: Avernus
description: The massive wasteland of rocks and mud seem to amplify the powers of the earth realm.  The outer fringes of Avernus are patrolled regularly by abishai.  The lower level abishai tend to travel in groups, and attack ruthlessly when encountered.

name: Avernus
description: The first plane of Hell is not at all what you might have expected.  With the exception of some hideous monsters which roam these parts, it's not all that bad.  Of course, you're still on the outer fringe of Avernus. Avernus is the most heavily guarded of the planes of Hell, as it is the gateway plane into the dimension of reality.

name: Avernus
description: The outer fringes of the first plane of Hell are constantly patrolled by the abishai, a dangerous group of lesser baatezu who are in charge of keeping intruders out of Avernus.  The inner sanctum of Avernus is guarded by powerful dragons.

name: Avernus
description: As you close in on the center of this strange and mysterious land, you notice that more powerful monsters dwell in these areas.  The overwhelming feeling of evil and hate get stronger as you approach the center of  Avernus.  Occassionally, you can see a dragon flying by dangerously close.

name: Avernus
description: The inner sanctuary of Avernus is not a fun place to be.  As you close in on the center of the plane, you notice that there is much more activity here than in other areas of the plane.  Furthermore, you can see a number  of rather large dragons circling around you, waiting for just the right  moment to pounce.

name: Avernus
description: Avernus consists of a vast plain of rocks and gravel, covered with a grey sky that allows no light through.  The result is a flat world of infinite proportions where it is always just dark enough to make it extremely hard to get around.  Occasionally, you see some dragons flying overhead, looking for a good meal.

name: Avernus
description: The outer fringes of Avernus are patrolled by a number of abishai.  The abishai come in various colors, depending on their rank and status among the baatezu.  The less powerful abishai almost always travel in packs, while the powerful abishai are content to kill alone.

name: Avernus
description: The various craters and rocks scattered about by angry devils and demons who have nothing better to do, is a show of their awesome powers over their world.  Those who would dare to challenge them would surely perish. Each level of Hell has its own guardian, who protects the level below it. In order to proceed down the planes of hell, you must defeat these powerful guardians.

name: Avernus
description: The outer fringe of Avernus is guarded and patrolled by abishai, a lesser form of baatezu, guardians of the planes of Hell.  Of course, if these are lesser baatezu, you can't quite imagine what greater baatezu might look like.

name: Avernus
description: The inner sanctum is not a very safe place to be.  It is constantly patrolled and guarded by fierce abishai and occassional dragons.  At the center of Avernus is Tiamat, the Chromatic Dragon.  She is one of the fiercest dragons known to all the universe, and perhaps beyond.   Tiamat can attack with all five heads and claw with her body at the same time, making her one of the most formitable opponents around.

name: Tiamat's Lair
description: If Tiamat is here, chances are you won't be around much longer.  The powerful dragon is the root of all of the evil dragons, and can summon them at will.  Each of Tiamat's five heads is capable of attacking  simultaneously, in addition to her massive body, using her tail to attack with deadly force.  Tiamat guards the entrance to the second level of Hell, Dis.

name: Avernus
description: Avernus is a desolate wasteland of rocks and gravel with no real scenery to look at.  The vast plane stretches out in all directions.  It would remind you of a desert, but it's not at all very hot.  The strange rocks and rock-like formations suggest that earthen magic might be more powerful here than other realms of magic.

name: Avernus
description: The strange land that you find yourself trapped in seems to radiate evil from every rock and grain of sand you find.  The further you go into the strange land of Avernus, the more powerful the evil becomes.  The outer fringes of Avernus are guarded by abishai, while the inner sanctum is guarded by dragons.  At the center of everything is Tiamat, the Chromatic Dragon.

name: Avernus
description: Avernus has not really lived up to what you might have considered Hell, but this is only the first of nine levels which compose Hell.  The  dangerous abishai sees to be coming out everywhere, as you seem them in each direction out of the corner of your eye.

name: Avernus
description: The outer fringes of the first plane of hell are characterized by the deathly grey sky and the vast plain of rocks and gravel with absolutely no life of any kind walking on its surface, except for the demons  themselves.  Countless scores of abishai wander the area, searching for intruders and trespassers to their domain.

name: Avernus
description: You can feel the ground sinking below you as you travel further towards the center of the plane.  At the very center of the plane lies Tiamat, the dreaded Chromatic Dragon.  The entrance to the lair is protected by a button lock.  Each color represents a color of abishai.  Press the buttons in order of power from least to greatest to open the lock.

name: Avernus
description: The first plane of Hell is guarded by Tiamat, the Chromatic Dragon.  She is a fierce dragon with five heads, each capable of attacking simultenously. She is the guardian of the gate into the second level of Hell, Dis.  Of course, the reason she is up here is to protect Dis from being invaded by the powers of good.

name: Avernus
description: This is typically not a very safe place to be wandering around by yourself, but then again, this is the first level of Hell.  You can see an occassional dragon circling above you, waiting for just the right moment to pounce.

name: Avernus
description: The mysterious layers of Hell are organized in a hierarchial pattern, with each level protecting the levels below it.  Eventually, you will come to the ninth plane of Hell and will either defeat Asmodeus or forfeit  your soul to him.

name: Avernus
description: This first plane of Hell is not quite what you imagined Hell to look like, although it's pretty close.  There doesn't appear to be any life forms around other than your own and the unnatural things which inhabit this level of Hell.

name: Avernus
description: The desolate wasteland is patrolled constantly by abishai demons, a  lesser form of baatezu who guard the levels of Hell.  These unnatural beings come in a variety of colors, displaying their rank and status among the other abishai.  The weaker abishai tend to travel in groups while the stronger abishai are content to fight on their own.

name: Avernus
description: The strange and mystical creatures which inhabit this level of Hell are  not too friendly when it comes to astral travelers.  The deadly abishai like to gang up on unsuspecting victims.  As you approach the inner  sanctum of Avernus, be warned that dragons often fly by to stop attempts to reach the center of Avernus.

name: Avernus
description: Being so far away from the center of Avernus, most of the creatures in this plane will leave you alone, assuming you are planning to leave the plane, and not just regroup for a later attack.  Nevertheless, you have been granted a slight rest, but remember, the monsters are also regrouping while you wait around.

name: Dis
description: Dis is almost like a city in itself, dominated by four large citadels at each cardinal point of the compass.  At the center of everything is Dispater himself, afterwhich this realm was named.  The powerful devil will do  anything to prevent you from reaching him, including sending out some very dangerous and deadly minions to destroy you.

name: Swampy Path Through the Forest
description: The path is the only clear way through the swamp, but it's not very pleasant.  Moss hangs from the branches, and you have to continually push it out of your way.  Water snakes slide away as you make your way along the path, and water spiders glare menacingly at you.  The brush is so thick you can't see very far in any direction.

name: Swamp Entrance
description: The swamp water is still and dark, with both living and dead trees standing in it.  Moss seems to hang from almost everything, and bubbles slowly form in the mud and burst, emitting a foul stench.  The gas from the mud may even be slightly toxic.  Strange there doesn't seem to be birds in this part of the forest.

name: Short Valley
description: the trees are not very thick here in the valley, but they are strange. Each one seems to have a door and windows cut into it, and some very small people apparently live here.  There is a stream near the western edge of the valley, and several of the small folk are setting fish nets.  A lilting music seems to pervade the valley, although faintly.  The path you are on continues north and south.  An almost unseen path heads west.

name: CrossRoads
description: The path goes through very thick woods to the north, while the small road heads east and southwest.  Wagon tracks have made ruts in the road, but it appears to be easy to walk.  A small rest area with a wooden table is on the south side of the road.  A road sign says the city of Oceancrest is to the southwest, and the home of Khallazar is to the east.  The elven city of Hafnia is far to the northeast.

name: Small Road
description: Birds sing in the trees and the sky overhead is clear.  A horse and wagon has passed this way recently, as there are wheel ruts and steaming manure in the road.  Beside the road, there are fruit trees laden with ripe fruit and vines covered with plump berries.  A small stream gurgles nearby.

name: East Forest Road
description: On the north side of the road is a swampy looking area where trees stand in water and moss hangs from their limbs.  The road is on high ground, however, and appears to be climbing to the east.  The south side of the road is overgrown with a thicket and large trees, and appears quite dark and cold.

name: West Side of Stone Bridge
description: The bridge is arched high over the Ashton River below, and provides a good view of the rushing water below.  The bridge is gated, and a  gatekeeper's tower is on the south side of the road.  It's difficult to determine what may be on the other side of the bridge because of its high arch.  Must be something nice though, else why is there a gate guard?

name: Middle of the Stone Bridge
description: The western end of the bridge has a gate across it, but the eastern end is clear, and connects to a road running south along the river bank. The center of the bridge is wide, high and solid, providing a wonderful view of the Ashton Falls in the river to the south.

name: East Side of the Stone Bridge
description: Cattails and pussywillows grow in the water below the bridge's footing, and a small boat is tied to an iron ring set in the stone.  The bridge crosses to the west, and the road on this side continues to the north alongside the river's bank.  Frogs and small birds can be seen all along water's edge.  The east side of the road is thick with trees.

name: Ashton River Road
description: Further north, the road has been washed out, but through the woods to the east you can see a strange sight...  There's a house built on a canopy of ropes strung between the trees!  It seems to be swaying gently in the strong breeze coming from the mountains, creaking as it flexes on its odd foundation.  A rope ladder hangs to the ground.

name: Khallazar's Compound
description: Most of the vegetation around you looks in good health, but toward the back side of the house there is a steady trickle of acid, creating a small stream flowing to the south.  The vegetation in that direction has grown wildly and turned wierd colors, and writhes with a life of its own.  A rope ladder hangs from the overhead canopy.

name: Khallazar's Front Door
description: There is a bounce to your step as you walk on the criss-crossed ropes and survey the house.  A sign over the door proclaims this to be the home of Khallazar the Alchemist.  In smaller letters it says, "You bring the lead, and I'll turn it into gold for a price."  You do have some lead in your inventory, don't you?

name: Inside Khallazar's Hut
description: Several bubbling vials and cauldrons stand in the middle of the room, and a crude piping system overhead delivers a dripping acid to each of the them.  Lead bars are stacked in one corner, and a smaller pile of gold bars is near the door.  Khallazar has evidently found that part of the secret of turning lead to gold is complete isolation from the ground below.  The hut sways gently as you walk in here.

name: Elven Workshop Front Door
description: The colors all about you are sharp and vivid, a perfect place for this snow white cottage with the red trim.  A good smelling smoke puffs from the chimney around the corner to the north, while to the south you see a great waterwheel connected to the house.  It turns slowly as the   water from a stream cascades down its paddles.  A small sign on the door bids you to enter, if you are interested in purchasing elven crafted jewelry.  As a sort of after thought, the sign adds, "Please do not use magic inside."

name: Elven Workshop
description: Several elves work at one end of the room near the fireplace, pouring molten gold into molds.  A display case is nearby, and you can see some very rare magical jewelry inside.  Probably expensive, though, right? A large sign proclaims, "Danger!  Magical items in a state of flux in this room.  Do not use magic in here."

name: Jactac's Home in the Trees
description: You have to stoop to avoid the ceiling, but other than that the place is rather large and airy.  It's a little dirty, however.  There are piles of trash in every corner, and even the remains of a dead mouse.  Odd trinkets are scattered in the room, and a broken mirror hangs from a string in the center of the room.  This is the home of Jactac, the largest and wisest old raven in the enchanted forest.

name: Mud Island
description: The mud at your feet is slippery and seems to move as you slog through it. Bubbles of gas rise in the mud and go "plop", leaving a terrible odor in the air.  Large slabs of mud seem to slide away from you as move, while other slabs of mud appear to be about to rear up and block your path. Water spiders and snakes are the only form of life you can see, and you have heard stories of the spiders getting as large as a man.

name: Spider Island
description: Some of the webbing seems to be as thick as ropes!  What size spider makes webs that large?  The only spiders you see as you look around are normal water spiders, skating on the surface of the deep and dark swamp waters. You can hack your way through the stuff, but do you really want to?

name: Thick Brush
description: The forest path is not far to the west, but you are presently in an area that is not well traveled.  The forest floor is soft and quiet with damp leaves, and you cannot even hear your own footsteps.  There is a clear spot between two young trees to the east.

name: Forest Camp
description: A campfire has been recently put out and the lingering smell of the smoke is rather pleasant.  The ground is quite scuffed, as if a large number of people have been here, and there are the remains of a deer hanging from a tree, gutted and cleaned.

name: Shaded Glen
description: The air is almost a pastel blue, and the haze softens your vision as you look around the glen.  The fog at your feet flows gently across the ground, and is as white as glistening snow.  There is movement at the edge of the glen, but it's hard to make out what's causing it.

name: Reflecting Pool
description: As you gaze into the pool, it's difficult to avoid becoming totally disoriented, as up appears to be down and down looks up.  There are wild flowers everywhere, creating a blanket of vivid colors to the water's edge.  Saplings and older trees stand back, making the pond a world to itself in this tiny meadow.

name: Hollow Log
description: The west end of the log is the small end, and the entrance is overgrown with heavy brush.  The eastern end is open, and a large garden can be seen in that direction.  Small animals have made thier homes in here, and your passage sends them scurrying toward the dark end of the log.

name: Hera's Outer Garden
description: The trees here are all fruit bearing trees, and it is evident that a great deal of planning went into their selection, as several of the trees are always in bloom, regardless of the time of year.  The thicket you see is heavy with berries, and sweet smelling honeysuckle climbs on an almost hidden stone wall.  There is an opening in the wall leading to the inner garden.  Rumor says that a Sleepless Dragon guards the inner garden.

name: School of Pyrographic Phenomena
description: The back door leads to a testing ground where a blue-white flame shoots from a hole in the ground.  There seems to be a set of stairs in another hole beside the one with the flames.  To the north is the street.

name: Tristram's Home
description: The walls of this room are covered with beautiful tapestries from all parts of the world.  Each tapestry is partially transparent, and by squinting your eyes you can see through them to the parts of the world from which they come.  Behind one tapestry you can see some of your friends fighting a monster, as if in a movie.

name: Inner Sanctum
description: The Gods must be smiling on you, for no mortal man or woman could enter this blessed ground without divine assistance.

name: Barn
description: Light filters in from between the poorly laid boards that make up the walls and ceiling.  Huge farm tools lie scattered about, and dust and cobwebs mark the fact that no one has tended this farm in a long time.  On the floor, partially obscured by hay, is a cellar door.

name: Southwest Corner of Cellar
description: Old, empty crates are loosely stacked in large piles near the corner here. A dextrous adventurer could probably work his way back up through the cellar door by carefully scaling the largest stack.

name: Southeast Corner of Cellar
description: The cellar is extremely large.  A thick coat of dust covers most parts, but a well worn path is clearly visible leading from the southwest corner to the door in the northeast.

name: Northwest Corner of Cellar
description: It looks like someone has fashioned a bed in the sawdust, well hidden behind a couple of crates.  Perhaps some unfortunate soul actually lives here in the cellar.

name: Northeast Corner of Cellar, by Sign
description: To the north a wooden sign is set in the stone wall.  "Behold the entrance to the underground city."  The small city down here is not near as large as Oceancrest, but is much older.  Young adventurers come here in search of the legendary Emerald Armor, said to keep the wearer safe from all magical weapons.  However, the young adventurer would be well advised to ask a veteren to accompany them in their quest.

name: Entrance Chamber
description: The residents of the underground city guard this room well, and turn back all those who would raid their home.  There are few portals to the sub- terrainin city, so it is easy for the denizens to keep track of any who might enter here.  Often they will try to overpower visitors by sheer  numbers, so stay hidden when possible.

name: Tunneled Hallway
description: A soft luminous glow comes from the rock surface, giving little light. To the east the hallway fades off into pitch darkness, and a putrid smell floats on a slight breeze coming from that direction.  There's an old adage about "follow your nose," but was it meant for a situation like this?

name: East End of Long Hallway
description: You are now very close to the source of the horrible stench, which seems to be just to the east.  However, it is too dark to see far in that direction.  Far off to the west there is a point of light.

name: Goblin Lair
description: If you are looking for the underground city and its legendary Emerald Armor, you have clearly found the ghetto of the fabled city.  Goblins and other nasty small creatures roam these dark tunnels and hallways, always looking for the flesh of others.  Humans and goblins have long been at war with each other, but their past skirmishes were unrewarding to both sides, so now they simply keep their distance.  If you are human, be especially watchful.  If you are alone, you will probably be a feast for a goblin family soon.

name: Goblin Lair
description: To the west of here, the rough walls of the lair even out into a carved east-west corridor.  Smaller goblin-hewn passages lead northeast and southeast into the darkness.  A horribly misfigured image of a goblin head is carved into the rock here, probably as an idol.

name: Goblin Lair
description: To the northeast, you can hear the high-pitched shreeks of baby goblins, and the nearly-as-high-pitched answers from apathetic goblin mothers.  The goblin tongue, as you're learning to appreciate, is not a pleasing one. Passages lead to the southwest and southeast.

name: Goblin Nursery
description: The goblins are horrible parents, especially when it comes to teaching their children good hygiene.  Still, they are fiercely protective of their young, so it's probably not a good idea to stick around here.

name: Goblin Lair
description: Although you would have thought it impossible, the smell eminating from the Goblin Chief's lair is even worse than the ambient smell in here. Perhaps you have discovered a valuable lesson in what it takes to be a goblin leader.

name: Goblin Chief's Lair
description: Bones lie strewn about the floor: not from defeated enemies, but from massive greasy meals.  The walls and floor reak of old urine and vomit stains.  Goblins wander in and out of this room constantly, talking to the chief in the grating, high-pitched goblin tongue.

name: Goblin Lair
description: To your immediate south is a downward slope which looks quite slippery. Beyond that is a large room, which is too dark to see.  There is a smaller room off to the east side of the slope.  Finally, rough cut passages lead to the northwest and northeast.

name: Goblin Lair Pit
description: The slope is a combination of small pebbles and larger flat rocks.  The combination makes a quite impassible barrier, as every time you try to climb it, you slide back down.  In the center of the room is a pit, from which light glows softly.

name: Goblin Treasure Room
description: Goblins search for treasure by raiding farming villages at night, and by killing unsuspecting adventurers who walk into their lair.  Unfortunately, the goblins' idea of treasure does not exactly coincide with the average adventurer's idea.  The goblins tend to steal those things that amaze and confuse them, without regard to precious metal content.  Still, the goblins are bound to have something worth taking.

name: Goblin Lair
description: Ahead of you, the passage turns around a corner and disappears. You see a strange glow and hear a soft chanting in a forgein tongue coming from around the corner.  To the east you can still hear the echoes of the screams coming from the pit you pasted.

name: Goblin Priest's Lair
description: Several small half melted candels are scattered throughout the room  provide the only means of light.  Along the walls you see various crudely made religous symbols for the goblin god Maglubiyet.  The room is filled with scent of putrid smelling insents.  In the middle of the room you see a goblin priest reciting the words to a golbin prayer.

name: Underground Passage
description: And it stinks too.  The tunnel does seem to be rather short, though, and an exit can be seen at both ends.  There's a slime on the walls, and you have just put your hands in something very squishy.

name: Goblin Shrine Entrance
description: Ahead of you lies a wide, long torch lit tunnel leading into the goblin shrine. You hear wails and shrieks coming from the tunnel in front of you.  Inscribed on the western wall is the warning: "All unbelievers will answer to Byhtme, the high priest of Maglubyet." You ponder the question if your decision to come here was such a good idea.   c

name: Goblin Underground Tunnel
description: Torches flicker along the tunnel's walls providing the only means  of light in the dark and dreary tunnel.  The air becomes increasingly  stale as you travel deeper into the goblin's domain. Closer examination  of the walls reveal the surface to be quite rough, and filled  with numerous small cracks and crevices. It appears this tunnel was  carved in haste by crude tools.  Then again goblins were never known for their architectural skill.  The tunnel continues north, deeper into the heart of the goblin shrine.

name: Goblin Underground Passage
description: Smoky torches flicker and sputter along the tunnel's walls, providing the only source of light in a dreary tunnel.  It's difficult to breath such stale air, and the torches indicate there really isn't much oxygen down here anyway.  There are numerous cracks and small crevices in the tunnel wall, some large enough that they seem to provide homes for rats and other vermin.  There is a rather large crack in the eastern wall.

name: Goblin Underground Intersection
description: Strangely, you notice the light is not coming from any torches, but instead there is a glow being emitted from panels in the ceiling.  To the north, an archway leads to what may be the goblin's altar.  There are several bronze statues of various goblins surrounding the archway.  One particularly large and vicious looking chiseled statue has the name "Bythme" inscribed at the base.  As you stand here, you hear a gratingly harsh sound of chanting and you smell burning flesh coming from that archway.  Now you remember  stories you heard in the pubs, of goblin blood sacrifices.  The passage leads off into darkness in all directions.

name: Goblin Guard Post
description: The room is totally encased in darkness except for a few streams of light coming though cracks. Peering through the cracks,  you notice the cracks are actually peep-hole to the intersection at end of hall. As you walk across the floor, small bones crunch  underneath your feet.  Probably the remnants of the goblin guard's meal.  The smell of spoiled meat, ale, and urine permeate the air.

name: Goblin Church
description: This is the place where the goblin masses gather to hear their priests exort them to kill all humans and elves, for the good of their souls. When they have been worked into a frenzy by the priests, they are sent out to bring back prisoners to be turned over to the priesthood.  There are candles in niches in the walls here, providing a soft glow and  flickering shadows on the rough walls.

name: Altar of Maglubyet
description: Only a few select goblins are ever allowed in here, and no outsider has ever lived to leave this room.  A blood altar stands ready for its next victim.  A low, stone table is near the altar, and its top is covered with various small hand instruments of vivisection.  As you look closely at the altar you see it has straps to hold the victim in place, and a silver urn to collect the blood.

name: Private Altar
description: Though not as large and ornate as the altar on the other side of the curtain, this one also has straps and an urn for collecting blood.  The urn here looks to made of gold studded with gems, and sparkles in the dancing candle light.  Pillows and furs line a niche in the wall, evidently a love nest for someone, and also high enough to see what happens at the  altar.  A great piece of smoky, amber glass covers one wall.

name: Goblin Underground Passage
description: No light can be seen anywhere in the passage, but the sound of the chanting from the goblin church echos off the cold stone walls.  Most of the passage is easy to walk in, but this particular section seems to only tall enough for you to stand if you stoop slightly.  If you are not careful, you might bang your head on the ceiling.  Your armor and weapons seem to make a lot of noise down here as you walk.

name: Underground Passage
description: The passage is devoid of light, and twists and turns every few meters. The goblins built the tunnels down here for their use, but recognized that in case of an invasion from above, twists and turns would make it difficult for invaders to move quickly.  A trickle of sewage runs down the center of the floor, making the floor a little slippery with slime.

name: Goblin Dump
description: Piles of garbage fill the floor. A fat scrupulless goblin eagerly watchs for any valuable item you might throw away.

name: Underground Passage
description: Except for the torches and lanterns you might be carrying there is no source of light in this part of the passage.  Your footsteps echo from the cold stone floor, and a trickle of water runs down the center of the passsageway.  Further north you can hear mechanical noises and garbled shouts in what sounds like a foreign tongue.

name: Goblin Underground Passage
description: There is no light source in the tunnel, and the walls are cold and dry to the touch.  Although dark, the tunnel is not empty.  You can hear shouts and drunken laughter coming from one of the doors along the way.  The  passage continues in two different directions.

name: Passageway Dead End
description: Although you are somewhere in the eastern section of the great goblin shrine, perhaps hundreds of meters underground, you feel as though it might as well be on one of the moons.  This part of the passage is a dead end, although in ages past it looks like it was part of the network of tunnels down here.  The sealed up section looks relatively new compared to the rest of the ancient tunnel.

name: Goblin Guard's Quarter
description: Several goblins playing dice did not notice as you entered.  The room smells like almost all barracks, reeking of bad ale and unwashed bodies. Bedrolls are scattered haphazardly around the room, and a rack of weapons stands in the center of the room.  A number of spears, swords and other weapons also lie about.  Over in one corner is a pile of broken bottles and moldy garbage, the remains of meals from long ago.  Rats run freely throughout the room, and one peers at you from atop the garbage.

name: Goblin Officer Quarters
description: The officer's quarter appears to be orderly.  Cots line the northern and southern walls, and two wooden tables are against the eastern wall. A heavy curtain running the width of the room can be drawn to separate the sleeping quarters from the tables.  Next to some of the wooden cots you notice there are piles of armor, probably government issue.  The smell of foul ale is in the air.

name: Drow Elves Quarters
description: Along the wall are several beds and small footlockers, while over in the corner is a small shrine which you recognize as being dedicated to the drow goddess Loth.  You ponder the meaning of drow elves in a goblin shrine. Ah.  Now you remember the rumors of an alliance between dark elves and the goblins.  It looks like there is more truth to that rumor than people want to believe.  You need to get this information to the authorities in Ocean- crest.  That is, if you can get out of here alive.

name: Goblin Dining Hall
description: All around you, goblin soldiers slurp and belch as they disgustingly chew what might be called their meal.   Broken dishes, bottles and bones lie tossed about the room.    Needless to say, there is an overpowering smell of rotten meat in the air.

name: Goblin Underground Intersection
description: The intersection is devoid of all light, except for the torches and  lanterns you carry.  You hear clanking of metal and garbled shouts coming from the hall to the east. To the northeast you blood chilling and inhuman shrieks of pain and the smell of brimstone. The room immediately  to the west appears to be empty.

name: Goblin Underground Passage
description: The passage is devoid of all light, except for the torches and lanterns you carry.  The walls around you are cold and dry to the touch.  Through the arch you see flashes of light and hear mortal shrieks of pain.

name: Goblin Meeting Room
description: A full wall size map of Oceancrest and the surrounding lands covers the northern wall.

name: Goblin Experiment Room
description: Not to your old age of course, but to how long you can live with most of your blood removed, or how long you can live with your heart and stomach surgically exposed to the open air.  A stone slab with cuffs and belts is the centerpiece of the room, and sharp instruments of all sorts hang on a wall behind you.  Scattered on a table close by are tubes and needles, and someone has thoughtlessly tossed the cut-off top of a skull there, still matted with bloody hair.

name: Ghelta's Secret Summoning Room
description: Except for the light coming from the circle of half melted candles, the room is encased in total darkness.  Even the light from your torches and your magical items seem ineffective against the darkness.   Inside the circle of candles, mist rises from a pulsating crimson pentagram.  You realize Ghelta was not unsuccessful in his attempts to summon creatures from other dimensions.

name: Goblin Prison
description: Mostly, the inmates here are goblins who cannot conform to the mores of goblin society.  Non-goblins, especially humans and elves, never see this place, as they are usually taken directly to the holding cell for immediate disposal of their cases.  There is a lot of yowling and agonized grunting taking place around you in the various cells here, but you don't see anyone you know.  There is a strong smell of unwashed bodies and goblin waste.

name: Goblin Torture Chamber
description: A stretch rack is against one wall, and a hot brazier is against another, with several orange-red pokers lying in the coals.  Chains with cuffs hang from the ceiling, ready for service.  A vat of seething acid gives off fumes that makes your eyes and nose burn.  Laid out on an instrument cart are long needles, easily twenty centimeters in length, used to probe the inner parts of eyes and ears and other body cavities.

name: Victims of Maglubyet Holding Cell
description: What nasty fate has awaited the many who have been here before you can only be guessed at, since none have ever lived to tell of it.  Screams echo from far away, but occasionly there is a nearby scream which sets your teeth on edge.  The cell was never meant to be a place for someone to live, only a place to wait while the goblin priests decide how best to take you apart, small piece by small piece.

name: Goblin Underground Passage
description: Unlike most of the other passageways and tunnels down here, there are a few smoky torches occasionly along the way.  certainly not enough to see by, but perhaps enough to serve as landmarks.  This section of tunnels is different in another way, too.  The walls are smooth, and feel warm to the touch.

name: Goblin Underground Hall
description: Smoky torches are high on the ceiling, giving scant light.  They seem to have burned out entirely up ahead in the direction you are traveling. The passageway is dry and quiet as you move through it, almost eerie in its silence.  A great wooden door with a single, massive symbol carved on it is over to the west.

name: Goblin Underground Hall
description: At times your footsteps ring loudly, indicating close walls, although you cannot see them, and at other times they sound dull and distant as though the sound had nothing to bounce from for a long distance.  Dimly to the east there is an archway which leads to a library.  A torch set high in the ceiling gives off more smoke than light.

name: Goblin Underground Hall
description: Your footsteps echo hollowly on hard stone as you make your way slowly down the corridor.  It's difficult to tell just how big the passageway might be, because you cannot see from edge to edge.  You pass several doors as you walk as quietly as possible through this strange area. Oddly, it sounds like snoring is coming from the doorway on the west side.

name: Goblin Underground Hall
description: The passage is devoid of all light except for what light you bring with you. In the dim light, you notice the floors and walls in the musty old corridor are smooth and highly finished, like the passage had been bored.  There is a slight breeze, which you can feel on your cheek, which is definitely coming from the east.

name: Underground City
description: The way is quite dark, and the light you have brought with you illuminates only a small circle around you.  As your hand reaches out to the walls, you marvel at how smooth and dry the surface is.  Not far from your hand is a heavy oak door which opens to the north.  The door is bound with heavy metal.

name: Goblin Secret Passage
description: You have heard stories of goblin treasure rooms down here, but of course you cna't believe everything you hear.  And another thing - the stuff that goblins think of as treasure is often pure junk.  Of course, now that you are here, you probably ought to find out for yourself.

name: Goblin Treasure Room
description: The room is roughly twenty by thirty meters in size, and three tapestries hang on the northwest wall.  The middle tapestry is the most interesting, as it shows a goblin priest standing over a large pile of treasure after a battle.  The largest of the three tapestries depicts a huge battle  between goblins, humans and elves.  A lone goblin stands guard here below the tapestries.

name: Goblin Treasure Guard Post
description: On the northern wall there are several peep holes at about the height of your stomach.  You realize they allow someone to peer into the goblin treasure room next door.  Next to each hole is a small wooden stool, and a table for drinks and snacks.  There seems to be a system of alarms overhead.

name: Goblin Secret Treasure Room
description: Lying in the middle of the floor, you see several glowing weapons as well as potions and scrolls.  You suddenly realize that you're not alone as two cloaked figures start to move out of the shadows, seemingly displeased with your discovery.

name: Bythme's Chamber
description: These quarters are far more opulent than should be required by a priest devoted to the services of his god.  Great paintings are on the walls, and the floor is covered with silks and furs.  It isn't particularly clean, however.  Are all goblins simply dirty by nature?  A voice enters your head, and in a gravelly tone seems to say, "Maglubyet will be pleased with his newest victim."

name: Bythme's Private Library
description: The room is filled with books on various aspects and religious rites of Maglubyet.

name: Bythme's Bedroom
description: As you entered the room, several small and naked female goblins were startled by your presence and fled out the door.  An unmade bed takes up most of the room, and piles of clothing and goblin religous objects seem to take up the rest of the it.  Regardless of how powerful the high priest Bythme is, his housekeeping skills are not good.  he seems to like very young females, too, although he is one of the oldest goblins alive.

name: Goblin Priest's Sleeping Quarters
description: The room is divided into two parts by a heavy cloth curtains which run the length of the room.  On one side of the room are cots arranged in rows along side each other, and on the wall behind each cot is a heavy ceremonial robe hanging on a hook.  At the foot of each bed is a small wooden chest, presumably where a goblin priest stores his meager possessions.  On the other side of the room are tables and chairs and the remains of a recent meal.  On the wall is a grusome painting of a goblin diety devouring his foes, surrounded by his priestly servants.

name: Goblin Priest's Sleeping Quarters
description: Straw mats line the floor, and blankets are folded neatly on each one. Whether or not the priests actually use these straw mats is a matter of conjecture, as some suspect there are more deluxe quarters hidden else- where for the priests, and these simple pallets are more for show than actual sleeping.  In any case, the room is quiet now.

name: Goblin Library
description: Several goblins ignore your presense and continue to work, while others rise to object.  You never imagined goblins could read or write, let alone have a library.  Along the back wall are several shelves filled with both large and small books, many old scrolls and a few hefty and ancient tomes. A few wooden tables and chairs run the length of the room.  Scattered atop the tables are piles of parchment, open books and writing instruments. Closer examination of the titles reveals that some of the books are written about magic and mages.  They may contain the incantations and words for great spells, or perhaps directions to lost treasure.  Too bad you don't read goblin.  You also notice some of the books appear to be in elvin.

name: Temple Passage
description: The passage is rather broad here due to a missing section of the wall. On the east side of the passage it looks like several stones have fallen and revealed a nest of hextrils.  If you have never seen one before, you are quite lucky.  They look like a land-dwelling octopus with a big head and mouth, and six strong tentacles.  Luckily, their size is about like a small cat.  Unluckily, they usually come in groups.

name: Temple Passage
description: the broken stones which were once part of the walls and floor make it difficult to traverse the passageway, and in places you must crawl where you would rather walk.  From time-to-time, you hear the sound of falling stones or timbers somewhere in the distance.

name: Temple Passage
description: Even now, years after the Temple was abandoned due to its partial destruction by earthquakes, the Temple still occasionally shakes, shudders and trembles  for no apparent reason.  Each tremor seems to bring new damage.  An old legend says the priests let a spell of some kind get out of control.

name: Temple Passage
description: There is a peep hole on the north wall of the passage.  Looking through it will reveal the main chamber of the temple, with the altar directly to the north.  On the south side of the passage there used to be an opening which is now blocked by a fallen stone.  Looks like it allowed light from outside to fall on the altar, but for what purpose?

name: Temple Passage
description: There are a series of doors along here, probably going to apartments for the priests, but the destruction has long since blocked easy access to them. The passage continues to twist and turn, and seems to go both northwest and east from this point.

name: Temple Passage
description: The wall has buckled and you must squeeze sideways if you want to continue in either direction.  It looks as though another passage connected here long ago, and probably ran to the west, but now there is nothing but debris in that direction.  Looks like it is impossible to go that way.

name: Temple Passage
description: The passage is overrun with spiders and rats.  What do you suppose rats find to eat in this terrible place?  On the floor there are also signs of droppings by ettercaps.  The dung of an ettercap is quite singular and easy to recognize.  It seems to consist of blackish-green pebbles in a pile.

name: Temple Passage
description: There are crushed doorways along the western side of the passage, which means it would be impossible to enter them from this narrow tunnel.  Perhaps there is another passage elsewhere in the Temple that would provide access.

name: Hextril Nest
description: They seem to be crawling all over each other in their attempt to get to you.  Each of the hextrils has six powerful tentacles, and each tentacle has rows of two types of pods on them.  They are lined with both sucker pods and acid secreeting pods.  Nasty creatures.  Why did you come in here?

name: Shuddering Room
description: Something tells you that the force of life, which binds all living things together, has been horribly twisted and mutilated here by some unthinkable magic.  There is another room to the west, from which you can see a fireworks-like abundance of light, and hear constant booming and screaming noises.  To the south, a passage leads back into the more normal regions of the underground city.

name: Wizard's Lair
description: The residents of the underground city all avoid this place, not only because of the evil aura but also because the wizard keeps killing trespassers. It is not at all adviseable to disturb the wizard while he is busy.

name: Temple Passage
description: The passage will take you to the Temple Holding Room and various private chambers.  It looks like it could also become quite confusing, as it seems to twist and turn.  Not all of the twists in the passage were designed by the priests.  Some of these turns look like they were caused by an ancient earthquake which evidently caused the temple to be abandoned  The Sacred Holding Room is directly south of you.

name: Broken Wall
description: You really can't go anywhere from here, except back to the passage.  There is a small hole in the floor, but the only way you could possibly go down it would be if you removed everything you are wearing.  It's a very small  opening, and it looks like you probably could not come back up.

name: Ulandian Temple Air Vent
description: You can only go in one direction because there is no room to turn around. There's also no light in this dark shaft, and when it gets dark outside  the little bit of sunlight that filters in will be gone.  The stones about you feel very loose, and this place might collapse at any time.

name: Uland Temple Air Chamber
description: A section of the wall has fallen in, and you cannot go but one way.        There is a grate overhead, but debris has fallen on most of it, and only a  little light comes through.  It doesn't look possible to go that way.

name: Ulandian Temple Air Vent
description: The passage tilts down at an awkward angle, and it's almost easier to simply slide down then it is to push along the sides.  The only direction you can go is down.

name: Air Box Above Uland Temple Tunnels
description: There is a small hole below you where you could probably lower yourself into the tunnel beneath it.  It will be a tight scrape, and then a long  drop to the floor.

name: Temple Passage
description: This passage has not been used in a very long time.  The priests who used to worship here left after a series of earthquakes destroyed most of the temple, making it very unsafe.  Many of the stones you see look like they could fall at any moment.  There is a bad odor along here.

name: Temple Passage
description: there is a black hole in the floor which you must be careful of, if you want to continue making your way through this passage.  There is also a soft hissing sound occasionally coming from the hole.  Around the edges of the opening you see the bones of rats and ettercaps, as though they had been tossed there from down below.

name: Tristram's Temple
description: True children of Tristram may rest here, where the palpable glow of holiness will speed the healing of their wounds.  The beauty of this place, from the marble pillars to the intricate statue of Tristram, will also gladden their hearts.  To the south, steps lead back into the underground city.

name: Tristram's Temple
description: True children of Tristram may rest here, where the palpable glow of holiness will speed the healing of their wounds.  The beauty of this place will also gladden their hearts.  Magnificent light green marble pillars line the walls, rising up to a ceiling that is so high, it's lost in the swirling mist.  A magical rope rises up from the floor into the mist, with no end in sight.   o

name: Tristram's Temple
description: True children of Tristram may rest here, where the palpable glow of holiness will speed the healing of their wounds.  Unlike the temples on the higher levels, this temple is not beautiful at all, but dark and gloomy.  Mists obscure the high ceiling.  A magical rope rises up from the floor into the mists, with no end in sight.   o

name: Shadowy Hall
description: The walls of the passage

name: The Crypt of Sorrow
description: A cloaked black marble statue of the famed dark elf Sorrow, stands in the centre of the crypt holding

name: The Grinning Sailor Pub
description: Only the youngest and most junior of sailors and pirates drink in this section of the pub.  However, it does tend to be crowded and noisy.  The main public room is west, through the arched doorway.  The Grinning Sailor is a popular hangout for seafaring advneturers when they are in the city of Oceancrest.  The owner of this place, Madame Ruthie, also has another business popular with sailors and pirates.

name: Public Room of the Grinning Sailor.
description: This is the main center room of the pub where most of the drinking takes place.  Of course, since most everyone in here is usually drunk, the friendly fights that occur here tend to get out of hand.  Near the middle of the floor is a wooden trap door, and bloody drag marks end there.

name: Officer's Mess
description: This room is normally reserved for the older and wealthier clients of the pub.  But since only pirates and other seafaring adventurers come here, it  tends to be for officers only.  The low lamp light throws flickering  shadows on the wall, making it difficult to see where you are going.    Don't trip on some drunken bosun.  He might not understand.

name: Grinning Sailor Cellar
description: Directly below you is a disposal pit where bodies and other garbage is  thrown.  Although dark, you can see a shuffling movement down there. As a matter of fact, the entire cellar is dark.  Over near the west wall  is a small table with but a single candle on it.  Most of the space is    taken up by great kegs of ale and rum.

name: Disposal Pit
description: A small cave provides a sleeping place for him.  The pit is littered with both old and new corpses.  The newest one are still oozing blood.  This  place really stinks!

name: Wine cellar
description: Although the room is unlighted, you see odd luminous shapes flitting between  the wine casks.  Now what could that be?  From the next room, you hear the trap door open and then a thumping noise.  A howl of glee comes from the pit below.  Something just brushed up against you!

name: East Uland Way
description: The way meanders through a small settlement of rickity shacks and rundown shops.  The Cold Drake Inn is on the south side of the way, and a bed and breakfast establishment is tucked behind some banana trees to the north. East Uland Way continues toward the island's bluff on the eastern side.

name: East Uland Way
description: Calling this a street would be a real travesty, since its mostly a mud path, but there are a number of small businesses along here.  A few cottages can be seen further back in the thick jungle brush.  If you look eastward, you can see the bluffs which rise above the Respitial Sea.  Looking to the south is a strip of land with a few brightly colored tents on it.  Looks like a flea market from the number of people carrying odd looking stuff.

name: East Uland Way
description: One of the most notorious pirates that ever sailed the Respitial Sea built his mansion on the bluffs overlooking the sea he loved.  Or so the stories say.  No living sober person has ever found the place.  However, there are  plenty of tales of its existance back in the pubs and bars along Rum Road.

name: Eastern Bluffs
description: The Respitial Sea stretches out before you to the east.  The coast of Mordor lies in that direction, and the great city of Oceancrest has a seaport there.  The bluffs look impossible to scale, but down below is a glistningly white beach.  The rutted road which leads east also turns and makes its way for a short distance to the north, but it soon disappears because of little use and fast growing jungle.

name: The Pink Drake Inn
description: As you look around you notice that most of the patrons seem to be Orcs. Even the bartender and the serving girls are Orcs, but there are a few other races here.  Most of the noise sounds to be coming from a betting table set up near a veranda overlooking an outdoor pit.  A lot of high pitched hissing and growling seems to be heard from directly below the crowd gathered on the veranda.  When you look closer, you realize there are pink drakes in a fighting pit down there!

name: Pink Drake Gaming Pit
description: Inside the cages are pink and cold drakes, which are found locally in the interior of the jungle near the old ruined temple.  The Orcs on the veranda above like to see them fight, and they usually bet on the outcome.  What are you doing down here?  The cages are about to be opened!

name: Research Office
description: If you wish to study here, you must have the permission of the librarian. the staff here is very proud of the facilities, as it is widely believed that the Great Library may even surpass the legendary library that was  burned hundreds of years ago and far to the south of the city.

name: Crew's Quarters
description: A large table stands in the middle of the room, and bunks line the bulkhead.  Strangest of all the sights you have seen on board this sunken pirate ship is the lighted lantern sitting on the table.  Some of the bunks are well made, while others are simply a jumble of blankets.  Playing cards still litter the table and the floor.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: this is where Captain Morgan no doubt stood during his fatal encounter with the Oceancrest Navy.  In the center of the deck is the great wheel used to steer the ship, and it looks like it's in good working condition.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: The Snap Dragon creaks and groans as it rolls slowly with the tide.  The motion is almost enough to make you seasick, and you feel a little queasy in the stomach.  A portion of the rail, which you were thinking of leaning over, is gone, evidently shot away during the battle with the Oceancrest Navy.  Other than a few battle scars, the ship is really in quite good shape.  Strange that marine life hasn't taken it over. It's almost like it's a living ship.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: Nearby are a line of heavy brass cannons, neatly shoved into place with block and tackle.  Stacked in pyramids you see the iron balls and metal shards used to cut through the rigging of the Snap Dragon's prey.  Until this ship went down, it was the most feared pirate ship in existance. There is a rumor that much of the booty and treasure is buried somewhere near this bay.  But then, only a fool believes rumors.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: The Snap Dragon is a heavy man-o-war, and when it sailed the seas it carried a complement of over 100 men, all of them mean and nasty pirates. Often the mere sight of the ship on the horizon caused merchant captains to abandon their ships and leave them to be plundered by Morgan's men. It's been estimated that billions in gold and jewels have been carried in the hold of this very ship.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: the strangest thing you notice about the Snap Dragon is that it appears to be a ship ready for action, with decks cleared and sails unfurled. It looks like the ship was sunk only a few minutes ago, yet you know the Oceancrest Navy did the dirty deed years ago.  Everything you can see is apparently in place and ready to use.  How odd.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: Oddly, all of the rigging is still in place and the sails are unfurled as if the ship were underway.  The ship is taut and clean, ready for inspection except for the cannon holes which pierced her side and sunk her.  Captain Morgan was quite proud of the Snap Dragon.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: Captain Morgan's ship, the Snap Dragon, appears to be in excellent condition except for the large hole in the side which sank it.  There are no traces of barnacles or other sea creatures that you would expect to find on a sunken ship.  Even stranger, the skull and crossbones flag is still on the mast, wavering in the tide.  You wonder whatever happened to the crew of this ship.

name: Sunken Pirate Ship
description: Extending from the bow, below the water line, is a sturdy ramming pike covered with steel plate.  It appears to be a deadly ship-killer, able to pierce another ships side and flood it with seawater.  Captain Morgan was one of the most feared pirates on the Respitial Sea, responsible for sinking over a thousand merchant craft.  Now you see one of his methods.

name: The Plank of the Widow Maker
description: Peering over the edge you see several large hungry sharks circling waiting to be fed their dinner. Behind you, you hear the shouts and cheers of the pirates as they watch another victim walk the plank.

name: Waters Near the Mooring Dock
description: As you thrash in the water, you see various forms of sea life swimming around you.  You also see the half-eaten remains of previous victims in the water.  Several hungry sharks have begun to take notice of your  presense here.  Nearby you see a rope hanging from the side of the ship. Looks like you have two choices  back to the ship full of pirates, or swim toward the open sea.  What are you going to do?

name: The Sea Outside Nylandian Bay
description: There are a number of sea creatures feeding and swimming around you. You also notice large quantities of Oceancrest garbage in the water as well.  Far to the east you can still make out the port of Oceancrest and the dreaded pirate ship widow Maker.  Perhaps you had better head back to shore before you become lost at sea.

name: West of Nylandian Bay
description: It's very easy to get lost at sea because every wave looks like the next, and the sky is very overcast.  A strong swimmer could easily stay out here for days.  There doesn't seem to be any immediate danger except perhaps from the weather.  Right now it's fine, but it could change without warning.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: You have the sinking feeling (pardon the pun) that you have become lost in the sea.  You are probably wondering if you will ever see the land again. Wouldn't it be nice to be back in Oceancrest and telling lies to to your buddies again?  (You just know they tell 'em to you.)

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: You have the sinking feeling (pardon the pun) that you have become lost in the sea.  You are probably wondering if you will ever see land again. actually, its not so bad out here.  Just boring.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: Each wave pretty much looks like another, making it difficult to determine your position.  It's too bad the sky is os overcast, or you might be able to determine where you are by the stars in the night sky.  That is, if you hadn't mudded so much and flunked celestial navigation.  Oh well, keep swimming.  You're bound to find something sometime.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: You are going to have to find land soon.  The weather can't stay like this forever.  If it gets rough you might be swept even further out to sea, and thus eliminate any chance at all of ever getting back to Oceancrest.  Have you ever heard the stories in the pubs of the pirate ship Snapdragon?

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: The sea is calm and you seem to have no trouble swimming for hours at a time. However, you are lost, you know.  Each wave you see looks pretty much like the last one and you haven't seen land in a long time.  At night, the stars may help you navigate, but then again, maybe not.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: The weather is still pretty calm, but it could change at any moment.  The weather wizards in the city of Oceancrest like to practice their talents on days like this.  Too bad the sky is so overcast, or you might be able to determine which way to land by the position of the heavenly bodies.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: Smooth waves and a gray sky.  Its difficult to determine where one starts and the other leaves off as you look at the horizon.  The sky and sea seem to blend into one in all directions.  There is no land in sight, but you have seen a few shark fins in the water occasionally.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: This is the type of weather that makes the weather wizards in Oceancrest very happy.  It gives them a chance to watch their apprentices practice their magic their skills.  It also lets them do a little showing off to  fellow wizards.  Anyway, you might expect the weather to change drastically any minute now.  Maybe you ought to quit playing around and find land.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: As you practice your backstroke you wonder if you will ever see land again. There is certainly no way to tell which way you should be swimming, so for all you know you might be headed straight out to sea.  But you have to keep swimming, because there's nothing else to do.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: As you practice your backstroke you wonder if you will ever see land again. there is certainly no way to tell which way you should be swimming, so for all you know you might be headed straight out to sea.  But you have to keep swimming, because there's nothing else to do.

name: Lost in the Respitial Sea
description: This is the type of weather that makes the weather wizards in Oceancrest very happy.  It gives them a chance to watch their apprentices practice their magic skills.  It also lets them do a little showing off to their fellow wizards.  Anyway, you might expect the weather to change drastically any minute now.  Maybe you ought to quit playing around and find land.

name: Waters Near a Tropical Island
description: the island isn't very big, and from here you see a few coconut and banana trees growing near the center.  there seems to be sandy beach leading to the jungle further up on the shore.  Colorful and noisy birds can be seen everywhere.

name: Tropical Beach of Uland
description: The beach stretches around the island, out of sight, while above you is a sandy cliff that might be difficult to climb.  There seems to be a jungle up there, as you see cocanut trees and palms growing up on the high ground above the sand.  The surf rolls in with a crashing noise and runs up the beach, wiping out your footprints.

name: Lost at Sea
