description: As you bob up and down in the water, you occasionly see what look to be great cliffs in the distance to the north.  The distance is so great that you can't really be sure, but isn't it worth the effort to swim in that direction?

name: Lost in a Vast Sea
description: A decrepit old boat swings at anchor nearby and you can see a friendly wave from a person standing near the rail.  Not far from the boat is a large raft, also anchored.  The raft appears to be quite comfortable and has a canvas sunshade over most of its deck.  There doesn't seem to be anyone aboard the raft.

name: Below High Sea Cliffs
description: The cliffs are at least 100 meters high, and appear to be unscalable. There is a strong current pulling you toward the base of the cliffs, and you wonder how many ships have been dashed against the rocks there.

name: Below High Sea Cliffs
description: The water is decidely warmer than the water in the open sea, and actually feels quite invigorating.  Although the current is strong, you easily can swim against it.  The cliffs are even higher here, and seem impossible to climb.  The waves crash against great rocks at the base of the cliffs.

name: Surf Below the Sea Cliffs
description: The cliffs are not as tall at this point, but they are very steep and impossible to climb.  The direction of the tide has changed, and seems to be pulling you north, in the direction of rocks and cliffs.  It's almost as if there is a passage for the water straight into the rocks.

name: Whirlpool Below the Cliffs
description: You could probably swim away from this whirlpool if you wanted, it doesn't seem to be that strong, but if you are curious you will see where it takes you.  The cliffs are almost directly overhead, but the whirlpool seems to be pulling things down a little closer to the cliffs in the north.

name: Eye of the Whirlpool
description: A high waterfall drops from the top of the cliff and adds to turmoil of the swirling water.  From this point in the center of the whirlpool you can hear the hollow echoing sound of water crashing into what sounds like some kind of a chamber.  The water is not moving so fast that you could not break free if you wished, so at the moment you are not in any danger.

name: Sea Dragon Cave
description: A sandy shore is nearby, and there appears to be drag marks in the sand. Heavy drag marks.  Very heavy drag marks.  Damn, what kind of creatures made those marks?  The silence is disturbed by the dripping of condensation from the cave's ceiling and an almost inaudible bubbling and chanting noise coming from the north.

name: Sahuagin Altar
description: On a coral reef jutting from the center of the chamber is an altar, constructed from a rainbow of different colored coral.  The center of the altar is dark red, stained with what looks like blood.  From your childhood, you recall the horrifying tales of the sadistic rituals of the Sahuagin race of creatures said to inhabit the depths below the seas. Beyond a high part of the small island of coral, where you cannot see, the chanting seems to be getting louder.

name: Hidden Sea Alcove
description: The area is almost completely hidden form the main cave and has a cool breeze moving across the surface of the water.  There must be a hidden chimney near here, with access to the tops of the cliffs.  There is a faint sound of water dripping from the ceiling onto the water's calm surface.  Although the water is clear, it is so deep that you cannot see the bottom.

name: Below the High Sea Cliffs
description: The cliffs are craggy and look to be impossible to scale.  High on the rock face you can see the nests of sea eagles, perhaps the only creatures who will ever inhabit those dark places.  The Land of Mordor is a strange place indeed.

name: Waters Below High Sea Cliffs
description: The cliffs are forbidding and dark, and the current sweeps you past them with a rush.  A rugged base is a jumble of giant rocks with waves crashing on them sending spray high into the air.  In the distance you can see seals and sea lions playing in the water.

name: blank
description: The cliffs stand at least 100 feet tall, and appear to be unscaible.  There is a strong current pulling you into the cliffs. You wonder how many have become shipwrecked on the cliffs.

name: Pirate Bay Entrance
description: The high cliff walls surrounding the pirate bay provide excellent protection for ships which drop anchor here.  In past years, the private nature of the bay made it an ideal hiding place for ships wishing to avoid certain legal restrictions on trade.  It is rumored that this  bay was often used by the most feared of all pirates, Captain Morgan. This is the very bay where the Oceancrest Navy found Morgan one fateful and fatal night.  There was a bloody battle, with no room to manuever  for the pirates, and the Navy was able to sink Morgan's ship here.

name: Pirate Cove
description: Several shovels are beside a deep hole dug in the sand well above the high water line.  There are signs that pirates have used this area for a long time to hide their booty, and apparently there is a crew of pirates nearby right now.  This cove is well hidden and difficult to enter, so they probably are not expecting anyone.

name: Pirate Bay
description: The northern end of the bay is perhaps the deepest, and many people think this is where Morgan's ship went down.  One thing for sure, he was sunk by the Oceancrest Navy somewhere in this bay.  And it really isn't that big a bay.

name: Pirate Bay
description: The cliffs form a protective cove around this part of the bay and cast long shadows across the surface of the water.  The water is quite deep and dark, making it impossible to see what lies below.  From here you can see the entrance to this bay, probably the very spot where the Oceancrest Navy blocked the way when they found Morgan's ship in here. There are tales in the pubs of Oceancrest that Morgan climbed into the rigging of his ship as it went under and screamed he would have his revenge.

name: Pirate Bay
description: The water at this end of the bay is more shallow than the rest of the bay, and is quite clear.  Tropical fish dart between your legs, and you can see a number of larger fish near the bottom.  Looking down, you can make out the outlines of a number of things buried in the sea bed below. Curious.  Could this be the spot where Morgan's ship went down?

name: Cargo Hold
description: Some of the cargo has evidently shifted during the years and there is a jumble of smaller kegs and containers blocking any further exploration in this direction.  Some of these kegs look like they might still contain a high proof rum.  Odd.  Although the ship is eeriely clean, you see some strands of kelp floating before you.

name: Cargo Hold
description: the hold was original designed to carry heavy loads of provisions for a large crew, but it appears to be empty now except for a few barrels and heavy boxes.  There is a 12 meter hole in the side, big enough to squeeze through.  The inside of the cargo hold is strangely clean except for some loose strands of kelp floating about.

name: Second Level
description: Are you sure you want to be here?  The fabled Emerald Armor may be just a myth, you know.  It seems to get more dangerous the deeper into the underground city you descend.  But then, no pain no gain, right?  And the Emerald Armor might actually be down here somewhere.  I say lets go for it!  I'll be right back here behind you.

name: Charon's Skiff of Dread.
description: Charon, the dread ferryman, guards these flowing streams, ragged and  aweful, his chin covered with untrimmed masses of ghoary hair, and his eyes a steady flame  from his shoulders hangs a sordid cloak.  Alone he poolles his craft and trims the sail of his vessel, the steel-blue galley with its freight of dead.  Thick with mud, a whirlpool out of a vast abyss boils up into the River Styx.

name: Lake View Road
description: You are at the top of a wide valley, protected from the elements by high mountain ranges.  The city of Kista is to the south and Lake Kista is to the east of you.  You have heard that the lake has purifying powers, but not everyone believes it.  The runoff from the lake provides the drinking water to the city below, and the entire city enjoys good health, if that is any indication of the water's ability.

name: Lake View Road
description: Lake View Road takes you around the town's grainery and dairy storage areas bringing you towards Lake Kista.  The beautiful blue water of the lake is almost always near freezing, even in the short summers here.   The crystal-blue waters and snow-white shores are lovely to look at, though.

name: Lake View Road
description: There is a beautiful valley spread out below you, with long, sloping meadows and rolling hills on either side.  The scene is quite bucolic and pleasant, making you wonder why you don't give up the adventurer's life and find a place to settle down and raise a bunch of kids.... Nah, just a passing thought.

name: Lake View Road
description: The view from here is magnificient, and looking east you see the clear blue waters of Lake Kista.  There is some activity out on the water, but you cannot make out what it is from here.  Gotland Pass is east of you.

name: Lake View Road
description: Lake Kista is between the road and the city, and the great range of the Nartiz Mountains looms to the south.  Over the Gotland Pass just to the north lies the vast Gotland Glenn.  There are tales of an entire city built beneath the grasslands out there.

name: Lake View Road
description: Not far from here is another road that heads north to the Gotland Pass. Lake View Road continues to the northwest not far from here, and will eventually turn back to the south and return to Kista.  The view of the  lake is very good from this height.  In the drinking rooms back in the city there are stories of monsters who inhabit the lake.  How silly.

name: Lake View Road
description: As you look out across this beautiful lake, you catch a glimpse of something, or someone, playing in the waters and bathing in the sun. Since you are caught by the beauty of the lake, you should consider a  relaxing swim.  Just ignore those tales you heard about monsters.

name: Lake Kista Shore
description: This is certainly not a lifeless lake, as you see a lot of activity in the water as you stand here.  From here it looks like it might be easy to wade in the lake rather than stay on the shore.  Most of the rocks at the water's edge appear to be quite slippery.

name: Outside the East Gate
description: The gate to the west leads into Brownhaven, one of the oldest cities anyone can remember.  It has been around since before the founding of Oceancrest.  To the east is a Quick Car terminal to Kista.

name: Small Cavern
description: You feel uneasy as you enter this cramped cavern, you sense life all around, little squeaks from mice underfoot, bigger squeaks from somewhat bigger mice, and then you noitice that thing!

name: Elise's Chamber
description: She is young, but mastered her art at a very early age, and now has many years experience.  Seeing what she has collected in this room, you realize it must take a great deal of intelligence and courage to want to become a master of the magick arts.  There are strange things here, some with arcane runes and symbols on them.  A glowing blue stone set in the wall seems to pulse with the runes IHN and JUX.  It would be better not to use that.

name: Dangerous Destinations Main Lobby
description: Call it foolhardy, but some adventurers find the need to explore beyond the reaches of thier travel, so they come to Dangerous Destinations where, for a small fee, they can find adventure almost for sure.

name: Transporter Room
description: You are in a small room with a transporter in ther center, the Dangerous Destinations transporter is a small looking booth which is emiting a faint rumbling sound.  You look at it questioningly, it seems too small for you to fit in, but maybe you arent 't supposed to, better try it thought, because you already poaaid.

name: Outside Kista
description: The city of Kista lies on the other side of the gate to the south, but the gate appears to be locked.  Unless you can find someone with a key, you might have to try some other way to get into the city.  You can't see anyone on the other side of the gate, but there is a guard house nearby, and that might be snoring you hear coming from it.

name: Mulberry Road
description: The side of the road is lined with Great Mulberry trees, which are old trees that turn the road into a wonderful panarama of vivid colors in the autumn when the leaves turn and fall to the ground.  This walk is well patrolled and is considered a very safe road.  Young lovers often stroll here in the moonlight.

name: Mulberry Road
description: The serenity of this beautiful roadway fills your mind with tranquility and peaceful thoughts as you walk along here.  In the distance to the  south is the city of Kista, while Oceancrest lies to the north.  On a moonlit night the view of the Lithium Inlet to the east is truly an awe inspiring sight.

name: Bridge Over The Bay
description: From here you can see far out to sea.  Pirate ships often lie in wait  just outside the bay, waiting to ambush foreign merchant ships as they  approach the city anchorage.  Be assured though, that the city is well  fortified.

name: Mulberry Road
description: Oceancrest is one of the largest cities in this part of the continent, and as you stand out here and observe its walls, you note they must be at least twenty meters high, with the guard towers and lookout stations going even higher.  No wonder there has never been a successful invasion of the city of Oceancrest.

name: Oceancrest South Gate
description: The south gate is an engineering triumph in itself, because it obviously weighs tons, yet a single man can open and close it.  The gate is made of giant ironwood, and bound in metal.  It looks like it could hold back an army, and in fact has done so many times.  Looking overhead, you see two guards at their stations, peering down at you.  Gate guards are not noted for their kindness.

name: Tangled Thicket
description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

name: Tangled Thicket
description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

name: Tangled Thicket
description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

name: Tangled Thicket
description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

name: Tangled Thicket
description: You can't tell which way you came from, nor which way you are going because every step you take is lost behind you.  It sure would be  nice to have a ranger in here.

name: South Gate Guard Post
description: Before you stands a large gate, nearly 20 feet high.  The gate is made of thick iron and looks strong enough to hold back an army. Guarding over the gate to make sure unwelcome visitors don't enter are two guards, they look pretty mean.

name: Hidden Meadow
description: You have found your way into a bandit hideout.  There are lots of  somewhat filthy looking people wandering about,  you better hope they don't see you.  There seems to be some sort of attraction  at an overturned cart on the other side of the meadow, perhaps it is where someone important lives.

name: Danzig's Cart
description: This cart is quite a sight.  Danzig sits on his throne, a wooden chair in the center of this reasonable large cart, which has been turned o over and built up to form a simple room with four walls with a  piece of heavy cloth over the doorway.  Danzig is a leader among the outlaws that you met on your way through the thicket, but he thinks he is a king.

name: Water's Edge
description: Birds wheel in the air and occasionly dip to the water's surface, scooping up small fish and other marine life.  The lake looks inviting enough to take a swim, but who knows what might be out there?  It's probably better to be safe than sorry, and staying on the shore is a prudent action.

name: Lake Kista East Shore
description: The lake is fed from springs and and streams, but there are rumors that the underground springs provide the lake with healing powers.  The water is dark and placid, and although it might be good for you, it doesn't look that way.

name: Lake Kista West Shore
description: An earthen bank overhangs the water here on the western edge, and a great tree has fallen, making a bridge from the high ground to the water.  The top of the tree lies submerged in the water.  Moss covered trees stand in the shallow water, impeding your travel as you wade in the cold water.

name: Lake Kista East Shore
description: An odd ripple on the surface of the water seems to be centered just off shore, and periodically repeats itself.  Must be something down there causing it.  It looks like it was a good idea to not go into the water, in spite of the rumors that the lake has healing powers.

name: Middle of Lake Kista
description: From here in the middle of the lake, you can see all of the surrounding mountains, and perhaps on a clear day you could see parts of Oceancrest as you look down the valley towards the east.  The nearby mountain tops are covered with snow, and you can see large bird-like creatures flying about the peaks.  There's something odd about them, however, as they appear to be too large to actually fly.

name: Lake Kista West Shore
description: :Large trees, hung with heavy moss, stand in the water making an eerie sight as you duck through them on your journey.  The roots come out of the water in places, and the moss covers everything.  Water snakes and frogs dart away from you as you make your way.

name: Lake Kista West Shore
description: Just to the west is a gravel beach, and a gravel bar runs into the water here, providing a place for small fry to hide from the bigger fish who like to feed on them.  Water lilies and other water plants are almost choking the shallow waters, and they certainly make it hard to wade in the lake's healing waters.

name: Lake Kista East Shore
description: Hunting and fishing parties have been here in the past, and you see the remains of a beach camp fire near some large sheltering rocks near the mouth of the river.  Looking out over the water you can see where the cold river water continues for quite a ways out into the lake, before it spreads into the lake proper.  Funny how waters of two different temperatures seem to avoid each other.

name: Lake Kista North Shore
description: The shore line is too muddy to walk there, but the water seems to get rather deep just a short distance from the shore.  This is the north shore of the lake, and trees and vegetation come right down to the water's edge here.  If it doesn't get any deeper, this is probably easier to walk than up there on the muddy shore, fighting your way through the brush.

name: Sunshine River Valley
description: The ground is almost frighteningly cold and barren.  Everything you can see lies frozen under a bright sun.  Although the sun shines brilliantly, you are overcome with cold, and a chill passes through your body.  As you look closely at the ground around you, you find evidence of the creatures who roam this area.  There are large footprints pressed into the frozen ground.  Then you hear them.

name: Kista Beach
description: The snow-white sands and cool, gentle breezes help you relax at this wonderful beach.  Here you can rest and enjoy the surroundings.

name: Yellowish-Orange Brick Road
description: This road is paved with large yellowish orange bricks, but you were  never very good at telling colors.  The bricks look like they might  have some value if you could pry one out, but they look as if they  were set by powerful magic.

name: Yellowish-Orange Brick Road
description: This road is paved with large yellowish orange bricks, but you were  never very good at telling colors.  The bricks look like they might  have some value if you could pry one out, but they look as if they  were set by powerful magic.

name: Yellowish-Orange Brick Road
description: This road is paved with large yellowish orange bricks, but you were  never very good at telling colors.  The bricks look like they might  have some value if you could pry one out, but they look as if they  were set by powerful magic.

name: Yellowish-Orange Brick Road
description: This road is paved with large yellowish orange bricks, but you were  never very good at telling colors.  The bricks look like they might  have some value if you could pry one out, but they look as if they  were set by powerful magic.

name: Crossroads
description: There is a sign posted here that tells you what lies to which direction. Conditions can change, so be careful.

name: Yellowish-Orange Brick Road
description: This road is paved with large yellowish orange bricks, but you were  never very good at telling colors.  The bricks look like they might  have some value if you could pry one out, but they look as if they  were set by powerful magic.

name: Brownhaven West Gate
description: The village has grown so much in recent years that it probably should be referred to as a town or even a small city, but the residents like to think of their home as a friendly little village.  The great walls around it have served the village well in keeping out invaders, but they have also added to rumors concerning what may be untold wealth hidden inside.

name: Underwater Alocove
description: The room is large enough for about three people to fit inside comfortably. At the end of the alcove you see a creature sitting atop a pile of decaying dead bodies, quietly gnawing on an arm.  He eyes you silently, never looking away from you.  The smell in here is really bad.

name: Ogden Villa Guard Post
description: Several security guards patrol the Villa grounds with great mastiff dogs.   A security station is close by, and a posted sign says intruders will be dealt with severly.  If you have not been invited, it's probably not a good idea to stay.  There's really not many places to hide on the grounds.

name: Carriage Lane
description: to the north is the gate which exits to Overland Drive, and on both sides of you are well kept gardens and grounds.  Your view is blocked by hedges  on the southwest side.

name: Carriage Lane
description: South of you is the front entrance to the Ogden Family home, and north along the carriage lane is the main gate.  To the west are the spacious grounds and gardens.  If you have not been invited you are considered a trespasser, and trespassers are often killed on sight. The rich really  cannot take any chances, now can they?

name: Front Entrance
description: The Ogden family is not royalty, but because they have so much money the members of the Lyanden court consider very carefully any requests that come from them.  Not only are the family members rich, but they like to show it off as well.  This estate is a good example of that.

name: East Grounds
description: The house is palatial in appearance, with at least sixty rooms.  A long sun porch, built to catch the morning rays, stretches the length of the mansion on this side.  The grounds are beautifully landscaped around a monument and open-air tomb where the founder of the Ogden Dynasty rests.

name: West Grounds
description: The lush green grass is almost carpet-like in appearance, with every blade trimmed to the exact same length.  South of you is a high wall surrounding a garden.  A gate allows you a glimpse inside, and you see it radiates a soft glow, hinting there is more to the garden than just nature.

name: Evan's Potion Shoppe
description: Evan the Most Magnificent always thought he was a powerful mage, and had intelligence to become one, had he not had such an ego.  His potions are every bit as good as the ones you can buy in Oceancrest, but his selection is poor.  Don't tell him that or you might get him mad.

name: Evan's Storage Room
description: You are in the storage room for Evan's Potions, in Kista.

name: Temple of Jinsuti
description: However, just because peace is impossible does not mean it should not be  sought.  Many legendary fighters and young knights have been in this small temple seeking guidance in how best to achieve the impossible.  The Jinsuti  Master who resides here will help you in your training.  He believes that peace is achieved when you have the ability to defend yourself with the advanced fighting techniques he advocates.

name: Outside the Magical Garden
description: The garden draws you to it, you feel it beckoning you.  Its walls stand about four meters high, covered with dense ivy all over, except at the gate which is made of golden bars shaped into the the gate with the outline of a rose in the center.  Not even the smallest humanoid could pry his way through the bars, but there's no need, the gate looks open.

name: Inside the Garden
description: The magical glow you felt radiating from the garden as you approached it is now very intense.  There are rows of fabulously beautiful plants lining the paths which lead up and down the inside of this garden, and the walls form an area which, once inside, is surprisingly large.  You cannot see the other end of the garden from where you stand as it simply fades into a mystically white radiance.  The gate, which has shut behind you, looks nothing like it did from the outside.  It is now a solid gold surface and prevents you from looking back in that direction.

name: The Magical Garden
description: You stand a short walk to the south of the gate which so rudely closed behind you upon entering the magical garden.  There is a path which leads to the north and south, but if no one is looking, you can hop over a row  of strange looking flowers to the west or climb over a tranquil little brook to the east which comes out of nowhere and probably ends nowhere also. To the south you see a statue which stands in a small clearing.

name: A Wall in the Garden
description: The brook which you are walking along does not appear to have started  anywhere inside the garden it just sort of comes out of nowhere and  travels off into the mist.  It looks as if you could climb over the wall here if you had the sufficient climbing equipment.

name: Surrounded by Flowers
description: As you enter this room, you begin to feel a little drowsy, perhaps its just the effects of a long daysadventuring, but maybe its the polen of the many flowers that surround you, which you don't recognize but all the same, the room starts to spin and you feel like sitting  down, or at least staying a while.

name: Middle of the Garden
description: A statue framed by a white glow--the mystical white mist that fills the garden--stands before you.  At the base of this statue there is a brass plate which reads 'Solitude is best'.  The statue appears remarkably lifelike and somewhat sad.  There are exits to the north, south, east, and west.

name: Through the Mist
description: The mist around you has become quite thick, and it glows with bright color.  You look more carefully and notice that the color is formed by light playing around the transparent edges of an amorphous shape which slowly shifts shape around you.

name: End of the Dock
description: Looking out into the Nylandian Bay, you see several small vessels either making their way into the bay, or out into the treacherous Respitial Sea. While Pirates are fairly calm when on shore leave, they can get pretty aggressive when out of the bay, looking for prey.  This dock is the home of the pirate ship Widow Maker, and occasionally it sets sail unexpectedly with some of the citizens of Oceancrest still aboard.  The swashbucklers aboard turn ugly when that happens, and become aggressive. To the north you see a seaside cove, however the path down is not easy to find. It may be worthwhile searching for the entrance.

name: Oceancrest Necropolis Entrance
description: The gate to the south commands a second look, its simple construction belies the immense feeling of mortal terror that overcomes you as you look upon the gate.  It gives off the impression that it is not only an entrance to the necropolis, but also stands to keep whatever has been buried in the necropolis inside.  The way back to the road is to the north, and it is advised that you take that route.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The path you are on leads north and south, and is paved with simple crushed gravel.  On both sides to the east and west you see a well kept cemetery with plain tombstones imbedded in the cold earth.  An eerie mist is curling around you as walk on the path, a mist that is not visible from outside the gate.  Perhaps you are imagining it, but perhaps the residents of the necropolis don't like sunny days or visitors.

name: Necropolis Path
description: A light mist has slowly crept up and surrounded you and the path you are on.  Trying to lose it seems futile, as it clings to you and follows every step you take.  At this point it has become difficult to see any further than the edge of the path.  The main gate is to the north, and the Necropolis Fountain is south. To the west, you see what appears to be a  giant golden pyramid, floating in the sky.

name: Necropolis Circle
description: It wasn't this cold when you entered the gate, but a suddenly you are aware of a chill breeze and light mist that has settled on you.  This place is very quiet.  There are no birds nor crickets, and all you can hear is the soft sound of your boots on the gravel.  In the distance to the south there is also a sound of gentle splashing from the fountain you see there.

name: Necropolis Circle
description: The gravel shifts under your feet strangely, like something is not quite  right.  This place is really spooky, especially as you look to the east along the Necropolis path, where untold stories of brave warriors and  legendary soldiers await you.

name: Necropolis Circle
description: A white, great marble fountain looks appealing.  Maybe you can rest there from the chilling breeze which whistles through a small grove of dead and ugly looking trees to the south.  The low, white building appears to be the  administration building, where you will go to arrange a resting place for your companions if you make it out.

name: Necropolis Fountain
description: Three statues, sculpted in bronze, stand in the center of the fountain. The first is a Holy Knight, fully clad in plate armor and wielding a sword that, even though bronze, appears to flame brightly.  The second statue is of a priest dressed in simple black robes and wearing about his neck a medallion with an inlaid skull of silver.  The third statue is Zelinx, the astonishingly powerful illusionist.  No one understands why, but he chose to be buried with his tower.  The water washes over the statues, but nothing can conceal their power.

name: Necropolis Circle
description: The gravel path leads south, up to a low, white building.  Outside the building there is a sign which reads 'Administration'.  Next to the building is a small grove of trees which appear to be dead and quite ugly.   Standing here, in the middle of the city's necropolis, they seem to have  taken on a new appearence, twisted and gnarled with age, and very unfriendly looking...

name: Necropolis Path
description: The path here passes to the north of a grove of trees.  To the north, you see a large expanse of ground covered by tombstones belonging to commoners who were buried there.  The stones are not large or fancy,  but each has its own special meaning to the family of the deceased.

name: Necropolis Path
description: A chill mist seems to follow you as you move along the path, and is perhaps getting a little thicker to the north.  The mist seems to envelope you, making you shiver as you search through this place of the dead.  A voice in the mist seems to whisper to you, "don't stray from the path, or you might become a permanent resident with us."

name: Necropolis Path
description: Not far from here, to the east, is the Tomb of Eldritch.  Eldritch was one of the later heros of Oceancrest and rose to a very high level before he was killed in a fight with the undead, not far from this very spot.   In the distance you see several white marble monuments and statues.

name: Necropolis Administration Office
description: A clerk behind a simple desk greets you as you enter the building.  You saw the clerk flinch as you came in, probably surprised that anyone would be here at this time.  They must not do much business.  The clerk tells you that you can sometimes find the undertaker here, as he is in charge of the Necropolis and probably knows everything you want to know about it. You should speak to him.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The Great Fighters Hall is southeast of here, and the Tomb of Eldritch is east.  The chill wind brings sounds you really don't want to hear... a cacophony of wailing and groaning.  At times it almost dies down to a low moan, but it never ceases.  No doubt it is restless souls turning over in their graves.  However, as you look around you realize you really don't see any grave sites near hear, but only a vacant plot of bare ground.

name: Necropolis Path
description: You are outside the magnificent fighter's hall where a grand stairway leads up to the entrance, which is elevated high above the ground.  Atop the entrance there are two golden statues stoically guarding  the entrance to the hall.  Inside are buried many of the greatest warriors Oceancrest has ever known. The Tomb of Eldritch is northeast.

name: Vacant Plot
description: Looking around you notice that it really isn't just a vacant plot of ground at all.  There is a depression in the earth, as though a grave had been dug up and the dirt removed was not enough to fill in the hole. Whatever monument was here, which might have told you who's grave was descrated, has been removed.  You get an uneasy feeling about the area, and decide that perhaps it may not be safe to stay here.

name: Entrance to Eldritch's Tomb
description: Great white pillars surround the entrance to Eldritch's Tomb.  There is a cosmic aura about this place, like it is etherially connected with another plane of existance.  It could be your imagination, but every now and then, you feel blessed, perhaps by Eldritch himself.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The Walk of Lords is farther to the south and is a glittering display of the adage that you can take it with you.  The Walk of Lords is a wonderful testimonial to the power of money, and the rich and powerful families of Oceancrest.  The path continues both north and south from here.

name: Walk of Lords
description: The path is surrounded by monuments to nobility and people with lots of money.  Except for the Lyanden family tomb which is to the the south, many of the royal family's relatives are buried on the Walk of Lords.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The Walk of Lords, a monument to the lords and ladies of Oceancrest's past, lies to the north.  Should you continue to the west, there is a similar monument to the great Heroes of Oceancrest, along with the Sage's Rest. The southern path leads directly to the entrance of the Lyanden Tomb.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The famous Lyanden Tomb lies to the southeast.  The tomb is without doubt a very beautiful monument in the Necropolis.  It rises splendidly above the surrounding monuments and cemeteries .

name: Necropolis Path
description: The Lyanden Tomb, last resting place of the great kings who built and lived in the Lyanden Castle, is farther to the south.  The grounds near here are especially well kept, and there is a quality of serenity you have not experienced since you came into the Necropolis grounds.

name: Lyanden Tomb Site
description: The tomb floats quietly about three meters above ground.  White marble  sheets and columns reflect the light of day quite beautifully, although your vision is somewhat impaired by the chilly mist that has been following  you around.  A crypt guardian hovers over the portico entrance to the  tomb, so watch your step.

name: Necropolis Path
description: Coming from the north you hear the awful sounds of the vacant plot you may  have passed on your way into the necropolis.  Over to the west there is   the entrance to the Sage's Rest, a monument surrounded in deep mystery, confusion, and disbelief.

name: Sage's Rest
description: The granite and pink marble, gridded with silver and gold, has an entrance where there is a staircase descending into darkness.  Although it looks like an expensive tomb, there is something about its appearance that pulls at your curosity.  Something about it seems out of place, almost turned around.  Whatever it is, it's very disturbing.  The entrance is north.

name: Walk of Heroes
description: The crushed gravel here becomes a walk to honor heroes of Oceancrest's past.  North and south, off of the walk, you will find monuments erected in their honor.  A grassy knoll is south, and you see a monument there.

name: Walk of Heroes
description: The walk is impressive with its great monuments to the north and south. To the northeast the Sage's Rest comes into view, a monument somewhat strangely erected to the illusionist Zelinx.  it is rumored that he buried himself with his tower, but most people are too scared to go in and see for themselves.

name: Walk of Heroes
description: To the north and south you see tombs belonging to people whose untold stories of glory and honor could fill many volumes.  Perhaps you should go take a look at the inscriptions on these revered tombs.

name: Walk of Heroes
description: The walk has statues erected in honor of the heroes of Oceancrest.  When a great hero dies, be it by old age or by less fortunate means, and should the powers that be deem he or she worthy, a monument is erected in their memory.  Small paths lead off the walk towards the burial sites of some  of the greatest heroes in Oceancrest's history.

name: Necroplis Path
description: From the west there is a grove of trees, strange for a Necropolis, but indeed, the ground coverage prevents you from seeing what lies beyond the barrier of trees.  The path here leads west around the Necropolis and south to the Walk of Heroes.  From the north a cold breeze sends a  chill down your spine.  it comes from the mausoleum.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The path becomes a bit overgrown, as if it hasn't been cared for in quite some time.  The mausoleum is still visible to the north, but you shiver just looking at it.  To the southeast, the Walk of Heroes comes into view, a place where the greatest heroes in Oceancrest's ancient history are buried, each with monuments in their name.

name: Necropolis Path
description: A gravel path and a grass covered walkway converge at this point on the grounds.  To the northwest there is one of several entrances to the commoners' cemetery.  Inside that area are a great many simple headstones and inset plaques, all on a well tended grassy hill.  A crew of gardners and a few grave diggers are taking a break under a tree, eating something odd.

name: Necropolis Path
description: The the northeast and to the west you see the commoner's cemetery, where many a citizen has been buried.  Oceancrest believes in honoring the dead. To the south you get a glimpse of the mausoleum, which some say has been taken over by evil forces.  You are warned to stay away.  To the southwest are the great burual vaults, which serve as a monument to Onydonn.

name: Necropolis Path
description: There is a footpath leading north to a cemetery through an iron gate, which has been left open.  The path on the other side of the gate is only a dirt path, slightly overgrown now with grass, but it is not poorly kept.  You see signs of loving care at some of the grave sites.

name: Eldritch's Tomb Entrance
description: Walls of pitch black obsidian converge upon you.  Hallways depart from the base of the stairs you are near, leading off to the north, south east, and west.  The hallways are lined with glowing scpeters in place of torches, which leave the air inside clean but stale.  It is light enough  to see shadows on the walls, but you cannot see to what the shadows belong. Eldritch was known for his kindness and benevolence in life, but you aren't sure he would appreciate grave robbers in his tomb.  would you?

name: Obsidian Hall
description: The walls are so well polished you can see your reflection and those of whatever is accompanying you.  There is an invisible being lurking at the side of the hall which jumps up to confront you!

name: Eldritch's Tomb
description: Eldritch was a mighty warrior long ago in the history of Oceancrest, and was known throughout the Land of Mordor.  He was always a protector of the weak and innocent, and rose to a very high level in the services of the king.  He fell here in the Necropolis while battling dark forces and evil spirits, and now he rests forever in this tomb.  Do not disturb him.

name: Fighter's Hall
description: The great door swings shuts behind you and you feel as if you are disturbing  something sacred, as you enter the long, silent room.  If you look carefully you see ghostly dark figures wandering aimlessly about the hall, nothing but their eyes giving off light.  At the end of the long hall, a statue  has been erected in honor of the brave warriors interred here.

name: Staircase
description: As you stand here on the stairway, you realize the air is much hotter down below than the air above you.  Coming from below you hear the sound of a heavy hammer striking an anvil. Each step on the stairs produces a  squeak as you put your weight on it.  A ghostly voice speaks to you. You would be well served to talk with the apparition.

name: Draknal's Forge
description: Nearby in a huge hearth a blue white fire gives off an incredible amount of heat.  Three anvils, each a different size stand in the middle of the room.  Several pieces of armor are in various stages of assembly in the forge, and a two-handed sword lies on a nearby table.  Looking to the east, you see the chamber of Draknal, the Death Knight.

name: Vacant Plot
description: What an unholy sight lies before you.  Cast aside is a broken headstone with something scribbled on it, but you cannot make out what it says. The ground is uneven, and a shallow grave makes it difficult to determine if someone was trying dig a new grave, or uncover an existing one.

name: Vacant Plot
description: Not even a weed grows here, and the ground is as sterile as the moon. A chill wind moves around you, constantly shifting direction and bringing the sounds of wailing and moaning to you.  This ground may no longer be hallow, which means the lost souls here will never find peaceable rest.

name: Vacant Plot
description: There is a terrifying sound of shrieks all about you, although you see nothing.  The sounds of the restless souls are the very essence of life- long nightmares, and you hold your ears to shut out the horrible shrieks. When you pull your hand away from your head, you notice a drop of blood has trickled from your ear.

name: Sage's Rest Entrance
description: Somber looking sentinels stand a patient watch over the black entrance. Looking down, you see there are no stairs in the entry, but instead there is simply a dark hole in the ground.  Light does not seem to penetrate very far into the entrance.

name: The Vaults
description: The ground of the hallway, which is covered with smooth stones, leads  north and south.  A large iron door leads out of the vaults to the east.  A silver skull has been laid into the wall across from the  entrance, warning of the Cult.

name: The Vaults
description: A small wooden door is set into the west wall.  Footsteps have worn the stones outside the door from the subdued sheen of the rest of the hall to dullness.  The door looks locked, but certainly pickable.

name: The Vaults
description: The hallway shows little signs of use, but has been kept very clean. Looking down the hall to the west, you see several doors which open out to the hallway, also two passages branch off to the south towards the center of the vaults.  You begin to notice a distinct smell, you aren't sure what it is, but should you proceed further in, you might not want to know.

name: The Vaults
description: The purple door to your north reminds you of one you would see at athe entrance to a throne room.  It is made of a purple metallic  sort of material.  A passageway leads off to the southwest towards the center of the vaults a little to the west of here.

name: The Vaults
description: A passage leads off of the main hallway here towards the center of the vaults.  To your east a purple door opens to the north.  To your west you see another passage leading inward.

name: The Vaults
description: The door to your north resembles the purple door to the east but is  instead just a plain metallic grey color.  To your west the hallway turns to the south, and to the east leads back towards the entrance to the vaults.

name: The Vaults
description: To the south you can barely make out a door to the west.  Back to the east you see several doors and passageways.  The air about you is a bit drafty, though you wonder where it could be coming from.

name: North End of the Onydonn Cavern
The Dracolich's Lair
description: You have foolishly stumbled upon the dracolich's lair.  The treasure which lies before you is beyond your wildest imagination, and even if the dracolich were to let you carry any of it off, you wouldn't be able to take more than a small fraction of the wealth which lies on the floor. The dracolich is one of the most feared beings in existance.  It has  almost no physical being left and must exist on pure magical power alone. The wealth on the ground begs to be picked up, but beware the dracolich!

name: Commoner's Cemetery
description: The tombstones are neither lavish nor disrespectful, each having  the name and occupation of the person buried at that plot of ground. A few of the tombstones look as if they are frequently visited, having flowers scattered around them, or small gardens growing  around them.

name: Commoner's Cemetery
description: The tombstones are neither lavish nor disrespectful, each having  the name and occupation of the person burried at that piece of ground. A few of the tombstones look as if they are frequently visited, having flowers scattered around them, or small gardens growing  around them.

name: Dead Poet's Tombstone
description: As you approach the tombstone, you hear a voice speaking, perhaps to  itself.

name: Arioch & Dragonmaster weird but cool hang out cafe
Draknal's Cove
description: Draknal the Death Knight was once a respected lord, serving in the services of King Lyanden.  But he was responsible for a dark deed, and was found out by the council of mages.  As punishment for breaking his knight's code, he has been cursed with afterlife as a knight of death.  Unlike a mortal fighter, he possesses wonderful magical power in addition to being a great fighter.  This is the chamber where he must spend eternity.

name: Custodian's Closet
description: You wonder how the custodian of this room could possibly find anything, it's very disorderly.  There are various tools and keys lying all over the place.  But be careful taking things that don't belong to you, it could get you into all kinds of trouble.

name: The Vaults Guard Room
description: If you've found the room empty you're lucky, because it allows you  access to rooms all over the vaults, but if you found angry guards, be careful, they're mean.

name: Advanced Training
description: Once reaching your leve, you no longer have to prove to the High Templar that you are worthy.  It's just through the door.

name: Acolytes Antechamber
description: For acolytes of first rank, use the door on the right, for those of  second rank, wishing to advance to third, use the middle door.  And, for those of you wishing to advance to the rank of protector, use the left door.

name: Protector's Antechamber
description: For those protectors of first rank, use the door on the right.  Those who are second rank wishing to advance to the third rank protector, use the middle door, and those wishing to advance to the rank of adept, use the left door.

name: Adept's Antechamber
description: For those of first rank wishing to advance to second rank, use the  right door, for those of second rank wishing to advance to third,  use the middle door, and those of third rank wishing to enter  priesthood, use the left door.

name: Priest's Antechamber
description: For those of first rank, take the door on the right.  Those of second rank may take the middle door, and the door on the left is reserved  for those wishing to advance to the rank of cardinal.

name: Clerics Training Room
description: All you need to do, is type "train".

name: Outer Drawbridge for Castle Ragnar
description: The great bridge is not lowered during the night to keep out trolls.  A massive gate is on the other side, and guards can be seen on the parapet directly above the it.  Several guards also stand near the entrance.  The castle seems to soar into the clouds, and its upper turrets are lost to sight.  On either side of the bridge are the quiet waters of the moat,  broken by bubbles rising to the surface at several places.

name: Massive Gate
description: Traffic during the daytime is very heavy, but the gate is closed at night.  The palace guard is in good numbers here, and they inspect carts and vendors waiting at the gate.  Some of the stranger looking travelers are stopped and asked their business.  As you look about you, you see a door to the side that seems to lead to the guard headquarters.  Through the massive arch you see the immense courtyard of the castle, and looking north there is a well traveled road leading away from the castle.

name: Castle Arch
description: The corridor is a north-south connection between the castle's courtyard and the great gate at the drawbridge.  Directly south is a busy intersection where the corridor seems to widen before leading to the courtyard.  There is a cross corridor in that direction.  As you look about you, you realize that each stone in the arch overhead must weigh at least six tons.  What a marvel of construction is this castle.

name: Guard Headquarters
description: Several clerks move about the room, and a couple of lieutenants lounge at a table, casually playing cards.  The Captain of the Guard has an office here, and the place is neat and clean.  Against one wall is a weapons bank, lined with halbards, swords and other brightly glittering hand weapons.  Troop banners hang from the high ceiling.

name: Corridor Intersection
description: The great corridor runs east and west from here, while the main courtyard is directly south.  Many of the visitors to the castle have set up vending booths on the flagstone courtyard of the castle.  Directly north is the great arch leading to the castle's main gate and the palace guard head- quarters.  West of here is the Knight's Walk, while the Ladies Walk is to the east.

name: West Tunnel Arch
description: The tunnel seems to have a gradual decline as it goes deeper into the  castle heading west.  East of here is the main intersection near the castle's gate and guard headquarters.  Heavy torches set in the walls on either side of the tunnel seem to provide adequate light.  Looking west you can see the tunnel does not go far in that direction, but continues around the corner to the south.

name: East Tunnel Entrance
description: The stairs rise only a few meters and then lead to a broad tunnel going east.  The tunnel is open on one side to the castle's courtyard, but several meters above it, providing the women of the castle a nice view of the activities taking place there.  Several shoppes are located along the tunnel promanade.

name: Main Courtyard Anteroom
description: Massive columns support great beams overhead, providing a solid foundation for the upper reaches of the castle above you.  To the south is the open air courtyard, a huge flagstone and quarried marble assembley area.  Going north from here will take you to the main gate of Castle Ragnar.

name: Knight's Walk
description: The tunnel continues to the east and west, gradually rising toward the east.  Further to the west the Knight's Walk ends, but a hallway appears to continue to the south from there.  The stone wall is cold to the touch on both sides of you, and a cool breeze whistles around you.  Graffitti covers the north wall.

name: Knight's Walk
description: Directly north is a barracks for the unwed members of Prince Ragnar's troops.  On the south side of the tunnel is the castle's armory where most of the small arms are stored.  The tunnel rises gradually to the east, and goes deeper into the castle's cellars to the west.  Great torches set high on the wall provide the only light here.

name: Knight's Walk
description: A narrow, circular hallway seems to descend deeper into the castle from here.  The hallway runs south for a short distance before starting its downward spiral.  To the east the floor rises at an angle, going past the armory and the bachelor's barracks.

name: Ladies Walk
description: Looking east you see a broad tunnel with a couple of shoppes and rooms on the north side.  The south side of the tunnel is open, and overlooks the castle's courtyard.  the stairs will take you to the main corridor which leads to the Knight's Walk and the main gate.

name: Ladies Walk
description: To the east the tunnel comes to an end, but a major hallway intersects there, going north and south.  You see a couple of shoppes and an unmarked door on the north side of the tunnel.  To the west is a wide promanade which is open to the courtyard below.  A stairwell landing is in the north wall, and the stairs go both up and down from there.

name: Ladies Walk
description: The Ladies Walk continues to the west from here.  A hallway runs north and south, giving you a choice of directions.  The hallway is lighted with heavy candles high on the wall every few meters, but appears to fade away in the distance at either end.  Oaken doors are closed along the hallway, but a few have light coming from under them.

name: Main Courtyard Northeast
description: Steps lead down to a cellar door which has been cut into an upper and lower half.  The top half of the door is open, and you see the cellar appears to be cool and dimly lighted.  A sign over the door says "Clerical Supplies." The main courtyard to the south seems to have a number of tents and open air booths where a variety of goods may be bought and sold.

name: Main Courtyard Northwest
description: The interior wall of the castle is covered with a rambling grape vine which was growing here when the castle was built centuries ago.  Some of the vines are as thick as a man's arm, providing a good handhold for anyone adventure- some enough to want to climb them.  A small booth has been set up here, and a bright canopy flies above it.  The vendor seems to be selling charms  against evil spirits and ghosts.  A small sign says he will also buy your  charms and amulets.

name: Main Courtyard West
description: A stone soffet overhangs the courtyard here, providing relief from both the sun and rain.  You see three doors set in the marble wall, each a different color.  There is nothing here to identify their purpose.  To the east is the troop assembly floor, and further south is a couple of tents where you can hear the vendors hawking their wares.  A narrow  opening in the wall appears to make a right angle after a few meters  inside the wall.  If you go in there, you will have to squeeze to get in.

name: Main Courtyard West
description: The broad stone floor is scrubbed clean by a cleaning crew, but there seems to be a heavy stain of blood next to a hallway which disappears into the depths of the castle.  Standing near the entry to the hall is a pushcart and a wizened old woman.  She sells potions and oils, and mutters under her breath as she gazes around the huge courtyard.

name: Main Courtyard West
description: There are a small group of tents here, each a different color and size. this is a favorite spot for the money lenders and money changers to gather.  Travelers from far places often prefer to get their money  changed to the local currency to avoid looking like what they are,  tourists, and thus being charged higher than normal prices.  This is a good place to trade-in your foreign bills for Oceancrest gold.

name: Western Courtyard
description: There is a wide set of stone stairs winding out of sight in a turret here. the stairs look wide enough for a great many people to go up or down at the same time, so its probably meant for the fast deployment of troops to the upper reaches of the castle.  High overhead is a beam canterlevered over the courtyard, with a block and tackle arrangement and ropes and chains hanging from it.  Looks like some very heavy equipment has been  hoisted to the top of the turret.  the courtyard continues to the north and south, and a larger area is directly east.

name: Main Courtyard West
description: The garden lies further to the west through a small gate set in a fence. A great stone turret stands at the corner of the courtyard here, and a stairwell winds around the outside of it, seemingly going forever, since it disappears into the mist above.  The courtyard continues to the north, south and east from here.

name: Main Courtyard West
description: Directly east you can see a wonderful garden surrounded by a small fence. There are fruit and nut trees of every description, and rows of interesting plants.  A white mist rises on the far side, so it is impossible to see how big the garden is.  To the south you can see the southern wall of the castle, and to the east is a great expanse of flagstone with a small fountain and pool forming a rest area.

name: Main Courtyard Southwest
description: To the east is a fenced garden where you see a great many trees and plants. some of the plants grown there are used in the healing arts, while others are said to have magical powers if mixed together in the right proportions. of course, some of the plants are just food, but the garden is tended by a select group of the castle's residents.  The entrance to the garden is to the north.  Looking to the northeast you see a small fountain and pool.

name: Center Courtyard North
description: It is here that troops are called to muster every morning, and once a month an inspection of the fighting men and women takes place.  The inspection is generally a lot of pomp and ceremony, but woe to the soldier who doesn't pass.  A week in the castle's dungeon with only water and crusty bread is no fun.  Further to the south is the review stand and the drummer's kiosk.

name: Courtyard
description: The review stand is covered with bunting and flags, and has a great many box seats for the important people who sit here.  In the center is a dais a little higher than the rest of the stand with a massive throne on it. Nearby is an open-air drummer's kiosk.  The area is large enough for all of the castle's troops to assemble here, and room for visitors to stand to the sides.

name: Courtyard
description: The walkway leads to the reviewing stand to the north and the center to the Lyanden Statue in the south.  When the troops are assembled for inspection and the Prince comes from the eastern arch, this walkway is cordoned off and guards are stationed shoulder-to-shoulder along here. The walkway is at least 30 meters across, and is open to the sky above. As you look up you marvel at the heights of the towers rising into the clouds above.  On the east side one tower in particular stands alone.

name: Center of Main Courtyard
description: The bronze statues above you depict the battle where King Lyanden was felled in his defense of the city of Oceancrest.  It shows Prince Ragnar kneeling with the head of his father cradeled in his hands, as the king lies mortally wounded.  You see that the king is handing Ragnar his Sceptre of Power as he is dying, symbolizing the passing of power from the old king to the new one.  Surrounding the figures are several clerics and mages, each pledging their loyalty to the Prince.

name: Southern Courtyard
description: Further south is a tranquil rest area surrounded by trees and a hedge. This part of the courtyard is often used as an area for falcon training, and falconeers come here to show off and trade their birds of prey.  A coop of pigeons stands off to the side, with a number of unsuspecting birds inside.  A hedge blocks the way to the east, but looking west you can see the castle's garden.

name: Fountain and Pool
description: A number of trees surround this area, making it a quiet and peaceful place to relax.  Directly to the north is the famous statue of King Lyanden and Prince Ragnar, while to the south is the southern tunnel through the back part of the castle.  A hedge separates this area from the east side of the courtyard, muffling the sounds you hear coming from there.

name: Center Courtyard South
description: To the north is a vast expanse of courtyard used for all manner of castle activities.  To the east is an enclosed garden area, while to the west is a small arms practice area.  The great castle's storage rooms are located through the tunnel running to the south.  The smell of animals is wafted from the animal keep directly to the south, near the tunnel entrance.

name: Main Courtyard Southeast
description: This is an area reserved for the practice of small arms.  Only blunt weapons and wooden swords are allowed in here, and at times it can get to be a real free-for-all.  Several of the young squires and newly knighted warriors of the castle play a sort of king-of-the-hill, taking on all comers, and hoping to be the last standing when the game is over.  To the north is a jousting alley, and to the west is the southern exit for the castle.

name: Main Courtyard East
description: The wide alley runs to the east between the main building of Castle Ragnar and the great storage rooms on the south.  Several squires are walking giant war horses while a number of knights stand in groups, getting ready to make a run down the jousting path.  On the west side is a thick hedge, and further south there is a small arms practice area.  Directly north is the preparation area and the eastern entrance to the main building.

name: Main Courtyard East
description: On the east side is the main building of Castle Ragnar, and on the west side is a large hedge.  Together they form a natural alcove for the wide alley just to the south which is used as a jousting run.  Further south is the small arms practice area.  Prince Ragnar himself can often be found here, either participating or watching the knights as they charge down the jousting run.

name: Eastern Arch
description: Through the eastern arch are the grand formal rooms of the castle.  The great Hall of Heros is directly east, and further that way is the throne room of Prince Ragnar himself.  Many more glorious halls and rooms branch from the Hall of Heros.  To the west is the center of the castle's court- yard where the great statue of King Lyanden stands.  Looking south you see a number of knights preparing a practice joust, while to the north is an assortment of vendors and tourists.

name: Main Courtyard East
description: A large red and white tent stands just north of you, its tent flap open and obscured by a blue steam or mist coming from inside.  To the west is a great expanse of flagstone and marble where you see an odd assortment of people gathered.  As you look up, you see towers and turrets which  seem to get lost in the clouds above.  Castle Ragnar has never been fully explored, and every so often a new room or hallway is found.

name: Main Courtyard East
description: A small alcove in the east wall leads to an apothecary shoppe.  Partially blocking the way to the south is a bright red and white striped tent whose entrance appears to be around to the south.  A great oaken tree grows here, long ago having burst from the floor and put roots down through the stone crevices.  A number of crows and ravens inhabit the upper limbs of the tree.

name: Main Courtyard East
description: A wide oak door is closed in the east wall of the castle, but a cross burned in the center of it identifies it as the entrance to the Chapel. A rain barrel stands by the door, full of fresh water.  The great court- yard to the west is often used to assemble the fighting forces of Prince Ragnar, and the monks in the chapel use the water to bless each warrior before he goes to battle.

name: Armory Adet
description: The large room to the south is the main storage for Prince Ragnar's troops. Several of the kingdom's best weaponsmiths and armormasters work there, and quiet whispers in the castle say there are a number of experienced mages doing research on new weapons in a secret laboratory area behind the armory.  Perhaps that explains the reason you feel the charge of magic in the air.

name: Main Armory
description: Hanging from the rafters you see all manner of armors and hoods, and in all sizes, too.  One corner seems to be devoted to leather while another contains only mithrill.  Directly above you hangs a knight's full suit of chain mail, and a variety of hoods.  A rack along the  wall is filled with shields bearing the crest of Ragnar, and a counter top is covered with leggings and gloves.  A great hot forge can be  seen in the room to the east, while the room on the west appears to be used to manufacture archery tackle.

name: Fletching Room
description: Master bowyers are at work on long benches, busy making strong yew bows and fletching war arrows.  A group of apprentices carry great armloads of arrows to the storage room through the passage.  In one corner a mage works with one of the bowyers, waving a black wand over a stack of newly made crossbows.  The main armory is through the arch to the east.  There is a practice range for archers on the south side.

name: Hot Forge
description: This is the foundry room where the heat is truly intense.  The forge gives off a searingly bright light and a vast amount of heat.  Strong smiths stand over their anvils shaping the great metal sheets into beautiful pieces of armor.  West of here is the armory adet, while the arches lead to the main armory of the castle.

name: Small Arms Storage and Repair
description: This is the storage and repair shop for small arms and personal armor. Several weaponsmiths and an armoror are busy in the work area behind the counter, and one looks up as you come in.  Prince Ragnar's knights store their extra weapons here in the racks lining the walls.  The passage to the south appears to go to the archery tackle shop.

name: Magician's Research Shop
description: The room has a very high ceiling and a smooth, stone floor with a permanent pentagram inscribed on the floor.  A ring of candles form an outline of the pentagram.  Floating in mid-air there is a great two-handed sword which gleams so brightly it hurts your eyes to look at it.  Thrown over the back of a tiny stool you see a bright blue woolen shroud imprinted with yellow stars and lightning bolts.    A silver and gold wand lies on top of it.

name: Dark Tunnel
description: The air is stale and the humidity is very low.  Every sound of your moves seems to be magnified in this silent tunnel.  The tunnel apparently runs to the south, and deep under the castle.  The floor seems to be heavy marble and the walls are great pieces of quarried granite stone.

name: Dark Tunnel
description: The tunnel continues to the north and south, silent and pitch black in both directions.  Your boots echo loudly against the walls on either  side, but the sound is lost ahead of you and behind you.  This is a very long tunnel.  The air is stale and dry.

name: Dark Tunnel
description: The walls are smooth and dry, with not a cobweb to be found.  Beneath your feet is some of the rarest rose marble in the land of Mordor.  Only your own movements can be heard in this silent tunnel.  The still air has a dry, stale quality to it, and you lick your lips to keep them from cracking. The tunnel continues to the north and south.

name: Dim Tunnel
description: The tunnel is wide enough that you cannot touch both walls at the same time. The tunnel is hot, and water condenses on the ceiling.  The drops run down your back, making you shiver.  Or is it the water?

name: Dim Tunnel
description: There is nothing but blackness to the south.  You have come far enough north, that you must be close to the armory of Prince Ragnar.  This tunnel is wide enough to pull a cart through it.  Small animals and large insects infest this place, and seem to be at war with one another.  Looking through the crawlway, you see the armory.

name: Armory Vault Anteroom
description: Next to the treasury, this is the most highly guarded room in the entire castle.  Prince Ragnar has a staff of armorsmiths and mages constantly doing research on weapons and armors, and when they have perfected a new piece of armor or a new weapon, it is stored in the vault in the next room. There are four colored stones set in the otherwise grey stone wall, and they must be pressed in the correct sequence in order to enter the vault.

name: Armory Vault
description: Only the most highly prized of Prince Ragnar's secret weapons and armor are stored here in the vault.  The hair on your body stands out in all directions as you feel the charge of the magic in this room.  As you look about, you see most of the weapons are locked in place, but a few can be taken immediately.  There is a crystal table in the middle of the room with a weapon on it.

name: Dim Tunnel
description: there is a trickling sound of water coming from the south, and there seems to be a light in that direction also. There is nothing but silence and blackness in the northern direction.

name: Circular Room
description: A broken clay pipe protrudes through the wall and pours water into a tiled basin set against the south wall.  The water coming from the pipe is chilled to almost freezing, but the water in the huge basin is at warm  bath temperature.  A single gas jet high overhead has been lighted and the flame gives the room a comfortable glow.

name: Shadow Room
description: The mages who have pledged their allegiance to Prince Ragnar maintain a weapons research room directly south of here, but be warned, if you go in there, you will not be able to bring anything back out the one-way portal you see at the south wall.  A cool breeze swirls through the room as you stand here, and the shifting shadows occasionly show you a skeleton hanging from chains on the wall.  The main armory is north.

name: Cross Tunnel
description: The tunnel going north and south seems to be quite a bit larger than the one which travels in the east-west direction.  The walls of the main tunnel are clean and dry, and the floor is a very expensive rose marble. A soft and cool breeze moves gently down the smaller tunnel, coming from the east.  There are also cobwebs in the tunnel going to the east.

name: Trokkawilff's Tunnel
description: Over a hundred years ago, a master torturer lived down here below the main castle.   He was in charge of a grusome dissection room and dungeon, and eagerly awaited new victims.  (Although he was never known to smile.)  He  died long ago, but his body was never removed from his quarters.  It wasn't because they didn't want to remove the corpse, but because they couldn't find it.

name: Trokkawilff's Tunnel
description: Legend tells of the master torturer Thokkawilff who would flay his prisoners to the point where they were barely alive but conscious, and then roast and eat strips of their flesh in front of them.  Thokkawilff preferred to live down here, below the great castle, so he could be close to his work. Because he once did a secret favor for a powerful dark mage, some say his shade still resides in his chambers.  The shimmering darkness is a portal which leads to those chambers.

name: Trokkawilff's Private Chambers
description: Although the master torturer died over a century ago, his name is still a word that brings terror to prisoners of Ragnar.  This chamber is rather stale and dusty, and all of the furniture has been removed, but some how it doesn't seem empty.  You have the strangest feeling of someone watching you, and there is an evilness here which makes your skin crawl.

name: Trokkawilff's Stair Landing
description: A wide circular stairway descends deeper into the castle from this point. The stairway is west of here, and directly south is a shimmering darkness in the form of a door.  Trokkawilff, the master torturer, lived behind  that door over a century ago.  His name still brings a shudder to prisoners unlucky enough to be brought down to the prison in these tunnels.

name: Tunnel Split
description: The main tunnel continues to the north, while two others run southwest and southeast.  A light breeze comes from the southeast direction, and the floor rises at an upward cant in that direction.  The tunnel going in the southwest direction is barely wide enough for you to turn sideways and squeeze through.  The sound of a rusty hinge slowly opening comes from that direction.

name: Old Tunnel
description: Heavy cobwebs block the way and a slime covers the walls.  The air has a putrid smell, as of decaying flesh.  Small animal sounds can be heard further to the east.  Sounds of clawed feet scratching on the floor and hissing sounds occur occasionly, and something just brushed against your leg.  Directly west is an intersection with a larger tunnel.

name: Old Tunnel
description: A rotting animal corpse is in the middle of the tunnel floor, giving off a horrible odor.  As you look closer, you realize its not an animal you have ever seen before.  There are eight eyes completely encircling the head, and they are quite large, as though to enable the animal to see in the dark.  The corpse has four large sabre teeth.  Whatever killed  it must be fearsome.

name: Old Tunnel
description: Many of the tunnels down here look like they are regularly traveled and maintained, but not this section.  Cobwebs are thick and small animals scurry out of your way, although once or twice a couple of them held their ground longer than usual before slowly retreating into dark recesses. Beneath your feet is an iron grate and you can hear water trickling down below.  There is a wretched smell coming from the south.

name: Old Tunnel
description: Several great oaken doors are wedged tightly shut on the west side of the tunnel.  The entry to the first one is overgrown with a gelatinous slime that seems to quiver as you get closer.  A number of skeleton bones lie just below it, and several rusted pieces of armor lie on the tunnel floor.  Further south you hear the trickling sound of water.

name: Old Tunnel
description: The massive stone blocks most of the way to the west, but with a bit of effort you can probably squeeze by it.  The tunnel walls are moldy and the air has a stink to it.  It doesn't look like anyone has been in this part of the tunnel complex in many years.  Maybe even hundreds of years. There are several closed doors in the tunnel further to the south.

name: Old Tunnel
description: This is usually referred to as the old tunnel, when people talk about it, but most people have forgotten it is even here.  The door to the west is broken and hangs partially open, while to the east a huge grey stone has fallen from the ceiling and blocks the way.  Cobwebs cover everything and the dust makes you sneeze.   There doesn't seem to be anything of interest here except some sort of crytogram scratched on the wall.

name: Trokkawilff's Torture Chamber
description: This was once the pleasure chamber of Trokkawilff, the master torturer. Although he has been dead for over a century and this place abandoned since then, some say there are nights when one can still hear faint screams coming from this part of the castle.  Several of the more common torture devices are in evidence around the room, but you wonder what the bar-b-que in the corner was used for.  Three iron maidens stand against the wall. Directly south is a holding dungeon, open to view.  Trokkawilff liked for his prisoners to see what he was doing to their compatriots.

name: Trokkawilff's Dungeon
description: The dungeon is small and has moldy straw ankle deep on the floor.  Several chains with open manacles hang from the low ceiling, and iron wristlets and leg clamps are attached to the south wall.  Any prisoner here would have a full view through the open door of the torture chamber in the next room.  There is a table in the room, set with a very fine bone china and expensive looking silver.  The table cloth has long since disintegrated. A repulsive green slime seems to cover most of the room.

name: Damp Tunnel
description: The green slime seems to bubble and burp beneath your feet, and at times it actually seems to be holding on to you.

name: Damp Tunnel
description: There is a horrible green slime on the floor, and it seems to pulsate anytime you get particulary close to it.  The water that trickles to  the floor has a very bad smell to it.

name: Damp Tunnel
description: There's a smell of unwashed bodies coming from the southern direction, and there's also a sound of people arguing in that direction.  The north  is rather dismal.  The water is flowing from that direction.

name: Broken Wall
description: A trickle of water coming from the tunnel to the north disappears into a hole in the floor, gurgling and swirling as it goes.  Looks like the tunnel continued to the southeast long ago, but now the way is blocked by a collapsed wall.  Directly south is a castle guard station.  Only the lowest recruits are assigned to this miserable duty, and they spend most of their time sleeping and playing cards.  North is a group of cells where the castle's petty thieves and criminals are kept.

name: Thieve's Passage
description: You can see several criminals below you, and a black crawlway leading to the east.  The stones are cold and clammy, and  you can hear rats in the distance.  Big rats.  It's hard to make a decision as to which is worse, hungry rats or hungry prisoners.  Which way to go?

name: Thieve's Passage
description: There is a sound of trickling water and the scurry of small feet.  From time to time, you hear the sharp sounds of rats or other high pitched  squeals.
