Sounds like either a fight or lovemaking.  You might not want to get caught in the middle of either.  A circular room is to the east.

name: Thieve's Passage/Circular Well
description: A faint luminous light comes from the walls, making the room glow with a ghostly aura.  The ledge you are on travels around a circular well, which must must be very deep, considering how long it takes for small debris dislodged by your feet to hit the water below.  You have to inch along the ledge, but it looks like you can go clear around on the ledge.

name: Thieve's Passage
description: This part of the passage is much wider than the part going east, but it's still only big enough for two.  There is a sound of a rusty door being moved coming from the north.  The sound isn't constant, but comes and goes.  It's difficult to stand in here, and you certainly wouldn't want to get in a fight in this cramped space.

name: Thieve's Passage
description: The passageway is so narrow that only one person at a time can crawl through it.  Of course, several rats can travel through here together. The sound of a rusty, squeaking hinge is louder to the west, but the sound can only be heard occasionly.  You may have to lie on your back to get through the next section to the west.

name: Thieve's Passage
description: Many years ago a number of thieves escaped from their prison cells and were found here, but no one has ever been willing to crawl through the darkness to see where it goes in the western direction.  A major tunnel is just to the northeast.  It's probably not right to call this narrow crawlway a passage.  It's more like a rat's run.

name: Tower Tunnel
description: Nothing but darkness and an occasional scraping sound is in the oppoisite direction.  There is also that constant sound of dripping water.  There are some odd scratchings on the wall, and an arrow to the southeast, but it was evidently put there a long time ago, and now it's unreadable.

name: Petty Thieve's Prison Cell
description: Most of the crimes committed in the castle involve some sort of petty theft, so Prince Ragnar decreed that anyone guilty of such a crime would have to spend a year in these cells.  Of course, since only relatives and friends provide food to the prisoners, and the guards never bring any, many of the petty criminals die in here.

name: Tower Tunnel
description: At times, when the tunnel twists, you can barely make it around the turn. The tunnel seems to have a steep slant to it, going up in the southeast direction and down into blackness towards the northwest.

name: Tower Tunnel
description: The tunnel seems to get taller in the northwest direction, but that is also the descending direction of the tunnel.  The floor is steeply slanted in that way.  Water drips continually from the low ceiling, and a steady but small stream is in the center of the floor, moving rapidly northwest.

name: Tower Tunnel
description: Cold stone, covered with condensation form the walls.  They are clammy to the touch.  Steps lead upward from here, and the tunnel slants down at a steep angle from here.

name: Tower Tunnel
description: The steps lead down into quiet blackness, the only way out.  There is a ledge overhead and you can see the wall is set back a few meters from there to the ceiling.  You could probably climb up there if the walls were not so slippery with slime and fungus.  But why would you want to?

name: Guard Station
description: Several cots are around the room, and a heavy table in the center is  littered with dishes and playing cards.  There are a number of empty Uland rum bottles on the floor.  Four large candles burn brightly, providing the room with excellent light in this otherwise gloomy place.

name: Circular Well
description: The air is cool and damp, and far below you can hear the sound of water dripping into a larger pool of water.  Must be condensation.  Although the ledge is narrow and difficult to traverse, you are fortunate there are a lot of rough stones for your hands.

name: Circular Well/Thieve's Passage
description: There is an occasional noise in the air, and something brushes your body from time to time.  Probably bats, but they are most likely very hungry bats.  Do you like this place?  Why do you spend so much time here?

name: Circular Well
description: You are on a rough but narrow ledge inside a circular well. A small door is directly above your head, but it would be really difficult to climb up there.  The narrow ledge has a few broken places in it, so be careful where you step.  You wouldn't want to fall into the well.  It's probably a long, long way down.

name: Main Mast
description: The rigging is an organized mess, which probably makes sense to the pirates who work here, but not to you.  High overhead you see the crow's nest, a large wicker basket attached to the top of the mast.  It's there that the ship's lookout spends his time, watching for merchant ships on the horizon. Below you is the main deck of the ship, while to either side are the great booms that carry the sails.

name: Main Mast
description: Far below is the deck of the ship, which now looks very small and narrow. From here you can see several of your friends standing and talking, or fighting with the ship's personnel.  The crow's nest is higher still on the mast, and someone just looked at you from over the edge of the nest.

name: Crow's Nest Entry
description: Below you is a dizzying distance to the ship's deck, and from here it looks so small that if you fell, you might not even hit it, but would probably take a dive into the surrounding waters.  There is a tangle of lines and sails just below your feet.  The small sway that you hardly noticed when you were below is greatly magnified from this height.  It seems to be making you sick.  Wouldn't it be terrible to erp on your friends below?

name: Crow's Nest
description: From here you can see the entire Nylandian Bay and Lithium Inlet which  feeds fresh water to the bay.  A great deal of the city can be seen, and there are some wonderous sights indeed.  The famous Lyanden Castle can be seen in the distance.  You have heard that the castle is where the  council of mages meets, and that Princess Runella represents the city of Oceancrest on that council.

name: Charity and Welfare Office
description: Not wishing to find starved bodies on the street, the city has provided this office for the use of various religions to use as an outlet for donated items.  Several chests are around the wall, and each contains the things needed by the poor.  You may donate any items you do not need, simply by putting them in the chests.   If you are in need, feel free to help yourself to what ever you may find in them.  It's all free.  To take everything is equivalent to robbing the poor, and to do so is to bring the punishment of Styx down on you.  Please be prudent in what you take.

name: Northwest Oceancrest Postoffice
description: Mail clerks scurry around you pushing great carts of mail in all directions. Of course, if you really want your mail to go through quickly, you will not depend on hand delivered mail.  The faster method is to simply use the command:  sendmail <person>.

name: The Sleeping Deer Real Estate Office
description: The company handles all real estate transactions in the city, both residential and commercial.  If you would like to purchase an exclusive apartment in the Ashton Falls Resort, you must be at least level 14. However, anyone with enough gold may purchase a business in Oceancrest. There are various pubs, shops and small businesses in the city that may be owned by players.   This office is also a postal facility, and you may send mail to Styx if you wish to purchase real estate.  You can also buy a Rules of Business, or an Ashton Falls Agreement here.  A list is available for your perusal.

name: Storage Room for the Sleeping Deer
Lyanden Tomb Portico
description: You hover in the air a few meters above the ground, held by magic.    The portico you are under shelters you somewhat from the chill wind and wet mist, but you cannot seriously be thinking of entering the tomb of the Lyanden family, can you?  Kings lie in stately rest inside, but surely you will disturb them if you enter.

name: Eidenhoft Park
description: An alabaster statue of Conan the barbarian stands life-size in the section of the small park next to the boulevard.  He is surrounded by lesser heros of Oceancrest, and a maiden is on his left arm.  He wields a glittering dragon blade, and battles several chromatic dragons.  Conan died a true hero in the Land of Mordor.  He is remembered by many.

name: Platinum Eyes
description: =============]   This Shop is For Sale   [=============== If you wish to purchase this shop, you must first get the Rules of Business from the Sleeping Deer Real Estate Office.  After you have read the rules, contact one of the Dungeon Masters who will relieve you of your hard-earned gold, and give you a key to the place.

name: Vestibule of the Dragon Tooth Inn
description: The Dragon Tooth Inn has quite a history in the city of Oceancrest. At one time there was a hidden meeting room in the back part of the inn, and a group of anti-royalist terrorists met there.   After a number of visiting Viscounts were murdered in their locked rooms, the inn was closed and the owner hanged.  Now the inn is open again, under new management.

name: Secret Meeting Room
description: Many years ago a group of anti-terrorists met here.  [4~[D[D[D[D[D[D

name: Grand Ballroom
description: Huge oil paintings of the Lyanden line of royalty are around the room, and each is draped in beautiful royal purple velvet.  The ballroom is well lighted from glittering golden candlebras and crystal lamps.  At one end of the room is a small chamber orchestra, led by a tall, thin man with a great mane of hair.  he appears to be almost human.   Dancers swirl around the room, and small groups stand at the side, laughing and talking.  Are they laughing at you?  You do appear out of place in here.

name: Grand Stairway Landing
description: Below you is the foyer and the registration desk for the inn, and looking north you see the vestibule at the main entrance.  Above you is a hallway going to the west.  The carpet beneath your feet is a deep, dark, wine red plush and matches the beautiful velvet draperies on the wall.  A polished mahogany rail runs around the landing, and a locked closet door is in the south wall.

name: Upstairs Hallway
description: The hallway is richly carpeted and dimly lighted.  Light comes from under the doors of several of the rooms, but all of the doors are closed.  The sound of your feet is lost in the thick pile of the new carpeting.  To  the east is the top of the stairway, while further to the west the hallway seems to intersect another hallway.

name: Ragnar Royal Suite
description: This suite of rooms is reserved for members of his royal family and high level aides who have pledged their allegiance to Prince Ragnar.  The new owner of the Dragon Tooth Inn has made a public oath to stay neutral in the dispute as to who should become the new king of Lyanden Castle.  After the king died, both Prince Ragnar and Prince Rutger, once loving brothers, lay claim to the Sceptre of Power, but the Mage Council withheld it until its true owner could be determined.

name: Rutger Royal Suite
description: The new owner of the Dragon Tooth Inn reserves rooms for both Prince Rutger and Prince Ragnar, but they have never been known to stay here at the same time.  When King Lyanden died, both Rutger and his brother Ragnar made a claim to the throne, but no one could conclusively say to which of them it truly belonged.  A war has split the kingdom since that time.  Princess Runella, a member of the council of mages, holds the Sceptre of Power in escrow until one brother or the other is named king.

name: Cross Hallway
description: Directly to the east is the main second floor hallway.  The cross hallway is much narrower and runs north and south in the inn.  The carpet is a little more worn and not as expensive as that in the main hallway, and the lighting is not quite as bright.  Shadows covers some of the doorways, especially those in the alcove to the south.  To the north there seems to be a single room where the door is slightly ajar.  There are rumors of a haunted room in the Dragon Tooth Inn.

name: Hallway
description: No light comes from the only room opening onto this part of the hallway. Strange that the door should be slightly open if no one is in there.  At one time, long ago, the previous owner of the Dragon Tooth Inn was a member of an anti-royalist group of terrorists.  He kept a room reserved just for visiting members of the royal family, but unknown to them it had a secret passage which allowed terrorists to murder the occupants.  Now there is a rumor that the ghost of a Viscount keeps a room here, waiting for revenge.

name: Visiting Royalty Suite
description: When the Inn was remodeled, a secret passage was found in the wall in this room.  It led to a meeting room for anti-royalist terrorists.  The owner  of the inn was hanged in a public ceremony after it was discovered he was a member of that group.  Several viscounts were murdered in this very room. There are dark stains on the floor which workmen said would never come out, and the secret passage has been boarded and sealed.

name: Hallway
description: The room on the east side of the hallway used to be the private quarters of the previous owner of this inn.  When it was discovered that he was a leader in the anti-royalist terrorists, he was hanged in Dillsdale Memorial Park in a public ceremony and his property was confiscated by the crown. The Dragon Tooth Inn has been closed for a number of years now, and the present owner has not yet done anything with this part of the building.

name: Dusty Sitting Room
description: There is a stale quality to the air, as though the room had not been open for a long time.  This is the living quarters of the previous owner of the inn.  A small kitchen and two bedrooms can be seen in adjoining rooms, but they are as silent and musty as this one.  After the owner was hanged, his body was returned here in a body bag, similar to the one you see on the floor now, to await reclaimation by relatives.

name: Back Hallway
description: You must not have seen the sign telling you to keep out.  There's a reason for signs, you know.  This long hallway stops at the southern wall of the inn, with only one doorway going to a storage room on the east.  The desk is to the north.  The storage room has a new lock on it, and another but bigger sign says, "KEEP OUT."  The desk clerk probably has the key, but why do you insist on violating the rules?

name: Storage Room
description: Several years ago, when the previous owner of this inn was declared an enemy of the crown, this building was confiscated and closed pending his trial and subsequent execution.  At that time this room was locked, but little did the workers know that a crazy old woman was in here when they locked the door.  She couldn't possibly be here now, of course.

name: Dragon Tooth Inn Public Room
description: This is a nice, quiet little bar devoted to serious drinking.  As long as you are not loud, you can get as drunk as you please in here.  There are a number of officers from the city guard in here, each sitting alone and drinking at a steady rate.  Must be something about the job, eh?  The new owner of the Dragon Tooth Inn, a half-giant named Tharonwold, spends his time here serving drinks.  He's been known to take one or two himself.

name: Restrooms Hallway
description: The door on the west goes to the Public Room where you will find Theronwold, the owner of the inn, serving drinks to a quite clientele.  The hallway continues to the north.  Theronwold is the new owner of this establishment, having recently opened the doors again after the previous owner was taken across the street to Dillsdale Memorial Park one Saturday afternoon and hanged for activies against the crown.  Restrooms are located on the east.

name: Dragon Tooth Inn Registration Desk
description: The vestibule and main entry is to the north,while the grand ballroom is immediately to the east.  You see a sweeping stairway leading to the upper floors of the inn, where a number of luxurious rooms are located. There is a dark hallway behind the desk with a sign over the door that says, "keep out."

name: Tormal's Magic and Wonder Shoppe
description: Although Tormal is seldom here, his young apprentice will sell almost  anything.  The shop seems to have anything and everything you might need, from weapons to armor to wands, and especially scrolls.  Everything has a price however, but if you are lucky she might give you a discount.  As you gaze around the shop, you spot some rare scrolls under a stack of dusty maps on the floor.  And isn't that a dragon blade mixed in with some short swords?  Hmm..  She might be willing to sell the entire lot for $100. Tormal would never know, would he?

name: World of Magical Wonders Storage
description: If you are not Tormal, then you are trespassing and your fate is already sealed. The room is dimly lit, and is bare except for three storage chests sitting at the back of the room.

name: Green Knight's Arena
description: You have shown you are willing to fight against evil by advancing as far as you have, but now you must challenge the Green Knight to serve at a higher level.  If your heart is pure, and your love of God is great, than no matter how hard the Green Knight tries, you will prevail. Good luck, mighty paladin.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: Only the brave and pure are allowed to advance in the holy order of the paladins.  You must be very proud of the order, yet humble in your own accomplishments.  One day you will take your place in the council and look back at your adventures as a grand time in the Quest for Mordor.

name: Red Knight's Arena
description: The Red Knight will try you in the eyes of God.  He has been chosen from amongst several who volunteered from the order of red paladin knights who  serve God in their fight against the evil that inhabits this land called Mordor.  If you are ready, and God has chosen you, you will defeat the Red Knight no matter how hard he tries.  He knows that, and wishes you the best of luck, but he will fight his hardest.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: You have successfully defeated the Red Knight and may take you place as an advance Paladin in the service of God.  Remember, never flee from evil, and always defend the weak and innocent.  Search out evil in all its many forms, and an angel will be your strong sword arm as you do  battle.  Soon you may serve the kingdom of Lyanden.

name: White Knight's Arena
description: You have done well to reach your present level, but now you must once again challenge the White Knight to show you are truly worthy of advancement. The knight who awaits your move is at the level to which you aspire, and he will do his best to defeat you, although he wishs you well.  You may strike the first blow when you are ready.  The White Knight knows that if God accepts you, you will defeat him.  He is ready.

name: Paladin Training Room
description: Only the pure and devoted may advance to such an exalted level of holy paladin as you have done.  You should be justifiably proud of your accomplishment.  When you go forth into the land of Mordor once again, be always faithful and ever watchful.  Do not let the forces of evil prevail against God's innocents.  And be warned... never flee from evil.

name: Eiden Public Storage North Hallway
description: Each room is locked with a special key, and the lock cannot be picked. No one can teleport into the storage rooms.  A notice on the wall says, "If you lose a key, it will cost you $2000 to replace it."  In small letters it says the management will not be held responsible for any losses.

name: Eiden Public Storage Office
description: This office is also a post office.  You may send mail to Styx if you wish to purchase a storage room.  The cost is $50k.  You receive a key to a locked room and one storage chest which will hold 50 items.  Additional chests cost $50k each, with a maximum of eight chests.  Additional keys cost $2k each. the room is a one-player room, and is also a fast heal room.

name: Oceancrest Orphanage
description: This orphanage is supported by the dwarven populace of Oceancrest as a haven for children of all races.  The dwarves, as part of their reverence for Moradin, administer and support this home for kids.  Unfortunately, the kids are so destructive, the place is in constant need of repair, and many of the rooms are overcrowded.  But oddly, even though there is a lot of spare room in the cellar, the kids refuse to go down there.

name: Orphanage Stairs
description: Directly above you is the main room to the orphanage, and further down, below the stair landing, is the cellar of the old building.  The steps squeak as you move, probably alerting anyone who might be listening. There is a strong odor wafting up the stairwell from the damp cellar below.

name: Orphanage Cellar
description: The room is dark and musty, with a strong smell of soap and dirty clothes. Clutter abounds, and the floor is covered with boxes and stacks of odd items.  When kids are brought to the orphanage, most of the stuff they had with them is placed down here, out of the way.  The only person who ever comes down here, though, is a nasty old caretaker whom the children fear and hate.  They tell tales to anyone who will listen that he has turned bad children into soap, by rendering them in a large vat down here.

name: Cellar Annex
description: This seems to be the dirtiest living quarters you have ever seen.  It's also cramped and cold in here, but it's obvious that someone live in this place. The children in the orphanage upstairs believe Miculash,  the caretaker of the place, turns bad kids into soap.  They tell visitors that he slits their throats, lets them bleed dry, then renders their bodies in a huge vat of lye and ash to make soap.  Of course no one believes such wild tales.

name: Acoma's Sarcophagus
description: The body of Acoma lies in state, shielded by a magical transparent cover. The heavy sarcophagus, made of adamantine and mithrill, stands on a grassy mound and the body of Acoma can be seen through the magical shield.  There is not a mark on the body, and it appears to be vibrant and alive, smiling softly with eyes closed and hands folded across the chest.  Acoma clutches a golden scroll.

name: Lyanden Lighthouse Base
description: An intense magical light comes from the top of the tower about twelve meters overhead, almost blindingly bright even in the daytime.  The base of the tower is smooth and seamless, with no apparent entry.  The tower also appears to be larger at the top than at the base, like it was inverted.  The surface is almost slick, and provides no handholds, making it impossible to climb.  (But why would you want to?)

name: Mortuary Cellar Stairs
description: The stairs lead between the main floor of the mortuary and the cold storage room below.  When the dead are brought here, they often spend a day or more down below while the next of kin are notified.  The Davis Brother Mortuary is one of the busiest places of business in all of Oceancrest.  Seems like people die constantly.  If you wait just a  moment, you may become aware of another death as you stand here.

name: Mortuary Cellar
description: Bodies on cold marble slabs are covered with white sheets, still and stiff. One body lies uncovered however, and as you look closely you see it has been partially devoured!  Loose body parts lie on the slab, and the stomach has been gouged out.  Most of the organs are gone.  Bloody footprints on the cold floor around the slab look like those belonging to ghouls.  Must have been a feast going on just before you got here.

name: Park Path
description: The path is steep at this particular point, and looking down you can see the Lithium Inlet as it empties into the north end of Nylandian Bay.   Perhaps five meters above you is the top of the path which disappears over the rim of the cliff there.  There is an extremely bright light coming from just over the top of the cliff.

name: Park Path
description: Below you is a narrow, sandy, sheltered beach area which is part of a wild- life preserve.  Gulls and other seabirds wheel overhead, and there is one very strange bird which is much bigger than the others.  The path continues in a northwest-southeast direction as it runs along the face of the cliff.

name: Wildlife Preserve Path
description: The path drops steeply to the northeast, and rises gradually to the west, forming a tranquil and quite place to overlook a wildlife preserve on the north side of the Lelion Beach and Park.  Great birds of some type you have never seen anywhere else float in the sky above, occasionly diving into the water to the north.  Across the Lithium Inlet you can see several shops and a pub which you know is the Might and Muscle Tavern.

name: Wildlife Preserve Path
description: The area is rather hevily wooded, although you can see there are few trees on the path which climbs to the west.  There is a rocky cliff face on the south side of the park, and you can see some huge bird nests up there.  No, not just huge.  Those nests are really big!  High overhead, above the wide Lithium Inlet on the north side, you see the birds that must inhabit those nests.  Must be the biggest birds in existance.

name: Lithium Inlet North Walkway
description: You are inside a wildlife preserve that takes up most of the northern part of the Lelion Beach and Park.  The walkway continues to the east  and west, and seems to rise toward the west where the Nylandian Bay is located.  Across the inlet you see a number of shops and stores in the northwest section of Oceancrest.  There are heavy woods to the east, and a walkway to the south that rises above the tree tops.

name: Lithium Inlet North Walkway
description: Old and heavy cypress trees stand tall here, and below them is a lush growth of heavy vegetation.  If a person went in there, he might become lost.  Odd snuffling sounds seem to come from the woods, but when you stop and look in that direction, they also stop.  You can hear birds in the distance, but none immediately around you.

name: Cypress Grove
description: The trees are old, and moss hangs from them in green tendrils, gently swaying in the breeze.  Underneath your feet is a carpet of long dead  moss, making it impossible to hear even your own footsteps.  The hanging moss makes it difficult to see very far, even though you know the woods are not very deep.   There is a cliffside to the south.  The walkway continues to the east and west.

name: Cypress Trees
description: The trees get denser to the south and the east, forming a dark, shadowy canopy where you hear small sounds unlike anything you have ever heard in a forest before.  The walkway, however, is broad and well maintained by the groundskeepers here in the park.

name: Cypress Woods
description: The walkway skirts along the bank of the Lithium Inlet on the north side and the woods on the south.  There are several paths going south, deeper into the woods, but the walkway is much wider and more comfortable.  Above the tree tops to the south you see a cliff face, so the woods cannot be too deep in that direction.  Across the water you can see several of the nicer stores in Oceancrest.

name: Lelion Wildlife Preserve
description: You are on a small piece of land which juts into the stream, forming a break for the fast moving water coming from the east.  The Lithium Inlet is between the Laynden lake to the east and the Nylandian Bay to the west, and is an excellent fishing waters.  A wooden pier extends to the north, into the quieter water of the inlet.  The path you are on continues in both the east and west directions.

name: Lelion Wildlife Preserve
description: The waters of the inlet swirl and eddy here, not moving near as fast as the center of the inlet to the north.  The banks leading to the water's edge are grassy and inviting, and a wooden pier, apparently in good condition, extends into the clean and cold water.

name: Lelion Wildlife Preserve
description: Actually, this is a gravel beach leading down to the water's edge, rather than sand.  It's also one of the few places where you can easily get to the water, as most of the way along the Lithium Inlet the banks are pretty high.  To the west you can see a walkway which follows the bank but is obscured by giant cypress trees which grow down to the water line.  The path continues to the east.

name: Lelion Wildlife Preserve
description: A tall fence is across the walkway, but the gate is open and and a sign pointing to the east says this is the exit for the Lelion Beach and Park wildlife preserve.  A walkway extends to the east and west from here. To the north you can see Lithium Inlet flowing from east to west, and emptying a lot of fresh water into the bay.  On the south is a wooded area between the walkway and a cliffside.

name: Lithium Beach
description: A tall fence crosses the walkway to the west, but the gate is open and you are invited to explore the wildlife area further west.  You would expect this to be a nice quiet place, form the way it looks, but you can hear a lot of people shouting and the sound of a steam organ playing music.  The sounds seem to be coming from the east and farther south.

name: Lithium Beach
description: The waters of the Lithium Inlet cut deeply into the banks here, and wash a lot of the gravel and sand down to the water's edge.  The water is cold and moving very fast as it comes from the Lyanden Lake to the east.  The Lelion Beach and Park is located to the west, along the southern bank of the inlet.  A sign not far to the west says, "Explore this area at your own risk.  The city is not responsible for the actions of wild animals or birds."  A set of stairs climbs to the south, and up above you hear the sounds of happy crowds of people.

name: Lelion Beach Stairs
description: These are wide stone stairs, leading from Lelion Way above, to the Lelion Beach and Park below.  You are half down or up, depending on which way you are going, and the stairs form a landing here, and an observation deck.  Looking north you see the Lithium Inlet, and across it you see the northwest section of the city.  Going down will take you to the path which leads west towards the Nylandian Bay.

name: Lookout Point
description: This is the famous lookout point of the Lelion Beach and Park.  It is the highest point in the western part of Oceancrest, and from here you can look east over the city and see most of the landmarks which have brought fame to this metropolis.  As you look west, you see that the carnival and fair has arrived and pitched its tents on the eastern end of the peninsula which forms the park.  The Nylandian Bay is located to the southwest, and you see many of the merchant vessels which visit the city docked there.

name: South Beach
description: Students from the Iilandi University like to party here on weekends, and there are several fire rings on the beach which look recently used.  There are also a couple of empty beer kegs in sight.  The white sand is dazzling during the day, and at night it sparkles in the moonlight.  Tourists say it is one of the nicest beaches on the coast of Mordor.

name: Nylandian Beach Promatory
description: There are high rocks between you and the water at this part of the beach. Seals and sealions bask on the rocks, and occasionly slide off with a  plop to play in the bay.  The sand glistens under your feet.  This area extends into the bay where you can see another island farther south.

name: Nylandian Beach
description: looking southwest, you see the entire Nylandian Bay and the guarded exit to the Respitial Sea.  In the middle of the bay is an island that houses the Marina Guard and the Oceancrest Marines.  If you look north, you see the famed Lyanden Lighthouse at the western point of the Lelion Beach and Park peninsula.  Large rocks are at the water's edge here, providing the marine mammel life a place to sun themselves.

name: Sandy Road
description: To the southwest is a stretch of white, sandy beach which should give a good view of Nylandian Bay and the ships anchored there.  Wisps of fog creep in and curl around the landscape, partially obscuring your view, but what you see looks interesting.  To the north you can see a group of tents with flags and banners whipping in the breeze coming from the bay.  The Oceancrest carnival and fair is opened every spring over there.

name: Sandy Road
description: The road runs between high sand dunes on either side, making it difficult to see very far at times.  When the winter storms lash this area, as they do every year, they shift the sand and often uncover things that washed ashore hundreds of years ago.  In the pubs there has been talk of finding chests of jewels, and sometimes mysterious things with no apparent purpose.

name: Sandy Road
description: Not far to the south is the blue water of a natural deep bay.  The Nylandian Bay is a very busy seaport, linking Oceancrest with the rest of the Land of Mordor.  The Respitial Sea carries a great deal of the commerce between the city and the rest of the continent, with merchant ships traveling up and down the coast.  Of course, such riches as they carry means pirates are also out there.  There is a rumor that pirates have sometimes used the grottos and caves near here.

name: South Beach
description: You stand at the southern tip of the beach area, looking over the Nylandian Bay.  There are several large merchant ships moored together near the ship- masters pier, and in the distance you see the dock used by the dreaded Widow Maker.  From here you also see the Marine Commandant's offices and Marine barracks.  Oceancrest suffered from attacks from sea for many years until the marines were trained by some of the city's great heroes.  A good distance from here to the west you see some beach caves and grottos.

name: South Beach
description: You are north of the bay, and looking further north you see the beginning of a high cliff that gets higher as it reaches into the waters to the west. There are a number of both large and small caves on the cliff side, and it looks like they might be interconnected inside.  A little bit to the north is a path leading to the top of the cliffs.  The waters of the bay lie to the south.

name: Beach Path
description: The path climbs the southern face of some very old and weather worn cliffs overlooking the Nylandian Bay.  The top of the cliffs is perhaps another ten meters up, and the beach is spread out below.  There's a good view of most of the bay from here.  Down at water level there is a cold fog creeping in over the sand dunes, but you can see a road going to the east.

name: Cliff Top
description: The top of the cliffs is very flat, forming a high table running east and west.  From here you can see that most of the Nylandian Bay is located to the southwest.  Looking north you see the Lithium Inlet where fresh water from the Ashton River pours into the bay.  Across the inlet there are a group of shops and several streets in the northwest part of Oceancrest. The cliff tops slope gradually down to the east, and you see a number of colorful tents in that direction.  A path goes down to the south.

name: Prxtl Cave
description: The mouth of the cave is huge, but the ceiling gets lower towards the back where a great many tunnels are located.  A flickering red light comes from several of the tunnels, making it easy to see, but casting shadows that dance on the wall around you.  They're very distracting.

name: Cliff Top
description: The cliffs on either side run down to the beach areas to the south and the Lithium Inlet on the north.  The flat part of the cliff extends to the west and east.  You are much higher than the fog, but the bay is shrouded in a dense blanket of grey to the southwest.  The clifftops  provide a nice view of the ships in the bay, and the city to the east.

name: Cliff Tor
description: You are on top of a peninsula which extends into the Nylandian Bay to the west.  There is a lighthouse on the high point in that direction.  The city of Oceancrest hires weather wizards to maintain the climate, but just to be safe, they also maintain a brilliant, magical light out there to warn ships and help them locate themselves when the fog rolls in.

name: Seaside Carnival Entrance
description: Excited humanoids of all races gaily pass by on their way to enjoy the sights and sounds that the fair has to offer.  Pickpockets and cutpurses abound, as people's pockets overflow with gold.  Hold on to your wallet! The midway lies to the west, while the main attraction is farther north.

name: Carnival Midway
description: To the west lies the bustling midway.  There are many sights to see and crowds of people waiting for their turn to see them.  The midway is home to bizarre and exciting sideshows, and features wierd and unusual life forms and strange artifacts.  You can hear the roar and screech of animals to the west.  A large banner tells you that a Puppet Show is to the south.

name: Carnival Midway
description: Excited groups of people make their along here, and the noise level is pretty high.  Bright flags and banners fly overhead, and the tents are in wild colors, many of them multi-hued in stripes, and some with odd symbols painted on them.  Wedged between two large tents you see a small one with an old silver star hanging over the entrance.

name: Central Midway
description: Making your way through the curious spectators, you take a look at the main attractions on the carnival midway.  You can either see the amazing bearded lady or watch the strongman perform unbelievable feats.  Go in  and enjoy the show!  Someone says they even have a giant dwarf in there. Directly south is the snake charmers side show.  North is the bearded lady.

name: Carnival Midway
description: The crowd surges and pushes as the barker proclaims the wonders of the world for only one gold piece.  You see dwarves, elves, orcs, half-giants, gnomes, and humans all pushing each other to get a glimpse of the inside of the tents.  Looks like the barker has deliberately left the flap open a little to give the crowd a tantalizing peek.  It's a strange world where people will pay money to laugh at a freak.

name: Back Lot Gate
description: The gate is locked and probably the key is with the circus guard you can see here.  To the east is the crowded midway, and the lights and noise  keep the mobs in a festive mood.  Looking south you can see many  spectators watching the Illusionist's show.  Better hurry up before you miss another of his amazing prestidigitations.

name: Milus' Magic Miracles
description: The Illusionist and his beautiful assistant are talented gnomish  prestidigitators who are entertaining the visitors with various illiusions which you have never seen before.  The illiusions require deep concentration and thought, so try to be quiet and not disturb the masters of magic.  Maybe there is something else here which you will find more interesting?

name: The Illusionist's Lab
description: The illusion is so realistic that you can even touch it.  The lab is full of mysterious objects from all over the world.  Some of them are  priceless and exist only once in time and space.  Interesting that you see Shishkin's painting on the imaginatory wall.  It represents a forest in so realistic way, that you even hear birds's songs and smell clover, as you approach it.  On the opposite wall you can spot a mirror.  You were just going to see how ugly you are, when you are struck by it's emptyness.  The mirror offers no reflection!

name: Multi-Dimensional Spatial Rift
description: To the left you could see an endless field of whiteness and good.   However, your right shoulder and leg stay in the blackness of evil. This is the place where good and evil meet trying to solve the oldest and everlasting conflict in the universe.  You may not like some of the "beings" which could come from your right, but you may find  yourself lucky and meet God without even bothering to die!

name: Carnival Midway
description: Although the midway is crowded, there are only a few people wandering around back here between the various tents and booths.  There are a couple of park benches here where a weary patron can rest his feet, before taking in more of the wonders of the sideshows.  From here, you can still see the midway and hear the shouts of the carnival barkers.  A loud steam organ is playing lively music close by.

name: Snake Charmers' Side Show
description: You see snakes and snake charmers of all descriptions about you.  The basket to the side is filled with several varities, and a young lady wearing pantaloons and an open vest reaches for one.  A tiny, wizened old human sits in a circle of snakes and charms them with his rythmic movement of his body.  Everywhere you look there are snakes and people handling them.  They don't seem to be watching all of them very carefully, though, as a couple just slithered beneath the canvas of the tent.

name: Carnival Midway
description: Several smaller booths are around you, but the one to the south looks the most interesting.  It seems to be selling charms and amulets, and you recognize the hyperactive elf standing near the back of the booth as a crazy old wizard. He was kicked out of the city of Brownhaven for causing the weather to do silly things.  It rained frogs there for six weeks.

name: Puppet Show
description: The puppet show is a gathering place for young ones of all races.  You can see puppeteers entertaining enthralled kids, while their parents update one another on the goings on in Oceancrest.  A little to the west, you can hear the sounds of snake charmer's flutes.  The midway entrance is north of here.

name: Back Lot
description: From here you might go visit the carnival's cook wagon which is parked to the south.  The carny workers say the food is actually quite good.  The animal wagon is to the west, and you hear roars and strange sounds coming from that direction.  There are some really strange animals over there. If you go northwest you will be in the carnival's backstage area where  the performer's gather between acts.

name: The Cook's Wagon
description: This is the place where one might forget about his current and future adventures and sink into the dream world of sumptuous delicacies such as luscious lasagnas, outstanding hors d'ouvres, creamy chocolate mousse, big red strawberries with freshly whipped cream, juicy baklava pieces, large and flat meatballs, reddish orange lobsters, all kinds of recenty picked fruits and vegetables, haskovian pork chops and many many other things you've dreamt to eat.  The Cook is obviously one of the best known around and he has some serving boys who help him in the creation of the delicious foods.

name: The Animal Wagon
description: The wagon is full of cages which are occasionaly left open and may cause danger to people who are not guided by a trainer.  You see different kinds of tigers, lion, bears and elephants around.  Most of them are not pleased  with their living conditions and may try to lash out at you.  The view and the air here are not too pleasent, and even the trainers, themselves, try not to come here, as long as possible.  You can hardly make your way through the dung and bones which cover the floor.

name: The Blaster's Bunker
description: You have unwisely entered the Blaster's Bunker, where Gospodin, the  Bulgarian Pyrotechnician, holds his dangerous experiments.  The bunker is full of different tools, chemicals, flasks and elaborate glass tubework. You see several kegs marked with skulls and crossed bones.  If you get "lucky" you may witness an exclusive science experiment.  However, the risk might be too great.

name: Back Stage
description: Visitor are not allowed to come here, so lookout for any guards that may pass by.  You can find three tents, allocated to the north, northwest and west.  The one on the north is beautifully decorated.  It seems that it's the Director's tent.  Although the tent on the northwest is very neat too, it is much smaller than the Director's tent.  That is obviously the  Ringmaster's Tent.  The performers usually go to the tent on the west  to rest and put their make up on.

name: Ringmaster's Tent
description: Looking around, you see very well kept living quarters.  The Ringmaster's wife keeps this tent very clean and still has time for her mystical endeavors.  Some say she is more powerful than the Ringmaster himself because of her abilities in the magical realms.  Her part of the tent is filled with artifacts from far places.  The Ringmaster does not seem to have many possessions as he is out performing most of the time.  His wife decorates the tent nicely, though not expensively.

name: Performers' Tent
description: Wow!  What a view!  Topless female acrobats, muscular master trapeze artists, funny clowns in underwear, contortionists looking for their backs,  maintenance men trying to pick up on the cabaret orchestra, a nosy kid  peeking behind the bearded lady's dress, midgets, another nosy kid trying to steal a snake charmer's flute and various other spectacles better left unmentioned.

name: Director's Tent
description: The Director's tent is a pleasant place to stay.  You wish you could take a break from adventuring and set up your own business.  The tent looks very comfortable, obviously Pavlovich-Barnum has good taste.  Oriental objects hang all over the walls, his desk is made from abanosian wood, his chair is beautifully carved from white brezza.  The Director is wearing expensive clothes with diamond buttons and cuffs.  Unlike you, he wears 16 rings - two on each finger.  "He must be really rich!" you think.

name: Under The Grandstand
description: Peanuts and popcorn shower down on top of you from the grandstand as you crouch uncomfortably under the crowds of people.  You had best be careful, for you never know what awful things those pesty village children might drop from the stands.  There is an awful  stench down here, due mainly to the sticky, moldy foods dropped from above and the hoards of stray dogs and cats which have made their homes here where the maintenance people must come to chase them away.  Find your way out before you fall victim to the pesti- lence breeding here.  The noise which comes from the north is your clue that the center ring might be in that direction.

name: Small Ring
description: You are standing in the center of the right ring, among several acrobat and clowns.  Soon you get in the mood to amuse people and start doing  what the others do.  The audience is very excited and shows you with  its thundering applause that you could be as good a clown as you are an  adventurer.  You, yourself, notice for the first time how good you are in standing on your head.  The whole world seem to be in your feet and you have reached the top of it...

name: Right Platform
description: Perched high above the ground, you stand amidst trapeze artists waiting their turn to perform.  They make swinging through the air, doing flips and dives, look like children playing on a swing.  You would probably not have a problem getting to the main platform if you jumped with some effort and held on tight.  A tiny ladder is attached to the post supporting the platform. Directly below, clowns and acrobats perform in the small ring.

name: Main Platform
description: This is the platform shared by both trapeze artists and tightrope walkers. It is much larger than the other two platforms and a little higher.  A large ladder is the only way down from here.  You can make out people cheering in the audience and performers in the rings below.  Some of them are pointing in your direction.  They are probably wondering why you are up here, and why you don't have a costume on.  The trapeze looks like the safest way to exit from here.  Maybe if you were quite dextrous, you could walk across the highwire.

name: Left Platform
description: Sitting high above the tigers, the view from here is extraordinary.  You can see just about everywhere, although everything looks so small.  The only exits are back to the highwire and, heaven forbid, down.  It looks like you could just about miss the cage directly below if you jumped out far enough.

name: Center Ring
description: The Center Ring is the biggest of the three rings under the Big Top. The Ringmaster announces the different attractions one after another while trained elephants dance around him.  They come from a country far, far away where people use them instead of horses.  Above you is the main platform where skillful acrobats swing on trapezes and walk tighrtropes In the adjoining rings tigers roar and clowns entertain.

name: Small Ring
description: You are wise not to enter the ring because there are tigers walking over there.  They might be dangerous if their trainer was not here.  In the middle of the ring there is a large cage where there is a black panther. Looking up, you notice the highwire, where the performers balance on their way between platforms.  Be careful because some of the amateurs may fall down on your head!

name: Ferocious Beast Cage
description: In the corner of the cage is a small bit of straw being used as a bed for the beast that is kept here.  Outside of the cage you can see tigers and their tamers performing tricks.  Fortunately, none of those tigers can get in here.  Unfortunately, the beast that resides in this cage is far more deadly.  At first, displacer beasts, as they are called, look like panthers with two tentacles springing out of their shoulders.  Closer examination reveals a much more deadly trait.  As the beasts move, their bodies shift dimensions, making them very difficult to focus on and hit.  Maybe there is one stalking you right now...

name: Carnival Grandstand
description: You are bewildered by all the goings on here.  You have a view of three rings, and a show in each ring.  High above the rings there are three platforms, and a trapeze and highwire.  The Ringmaster is announcing the shows in the center ring, while dancing elephants plod around him.  In the ring on the right, clowns make you laugh, and acrobats do fast flips and somersaults.  On the left, tiger tamers coax tigers to jump through hoops and stand on two legs.  In the air high above the ground, trapeze artists gracefully fly from their perches onto the trapeze, literally holding on with sheer will.  Next to them, a tightrope walker delicately crosses from one platform to another.  Someone shouts, "Down in front!"

name: Entrance to Grandstand
description: The Grandstand is the place where people go to watch the main attractions at the carnival.  Many amazing acts of breathtaking beauty are performed by skilled trapeze artists.  Acrobats entertain with their funny antics. Dancing elephants prance around with surprising grace while tiger and lion tamers risk life and limb showing off with their animals.  Be sure to visit the concession stand if you get an urge for food and drink.  Go west if you want to get to the grandstand.  Food and drink is to the east. South is the entrance to the Carnival.  But wherever you go, remember to enjoy the show!

name: Concession Stand
description: You can smell many delicious things being cooked here at the concession booth.  You can buy both exotic and everyday foods, although the prices are a little steep.  Fried bat wings, lizard shishkebab, and grizzley bear liver sautee are among the regular selection.  Special orders like pork chops are not uncommon, but nonetheless expensive.  A special shelf lined with candy, for the kids, should keep your sweet spot happy.  Don't linger too long, you'll miss the show!

name: Highwire
description: The highwire is the only way to get between the main platform and the left platform.  It is quite dangerous, not only because of the long fall you would take if you fell, but also because of the beasts waiting below. Hopefully, you would not fall into the cage.  Very nasty beasts are kept there.

name: Oceancrest Mercernary Services
description: Long ago when Oceancrest was a new city, a group of adventurers banded together and made their services available to any who would pay.  After a number of years the older adventurers retired or died, and today only a few old-timers are left, and a few unproven new members.  You get what you pay for.

name: Beneath the Secret Fireplace
description: Somehow you have found the storage chamber beneath the merceranry head- quarters.  If you do not belong here, it would be a good idea to leave before guards come...  Or even worse, one of the Dark Lords.

name: Dark Lord's Storage Annex
description: The air is dry and musty, perfect storage conditions for ancient scrolls and  magical items.  The shelves are lined with arcane objects.

name: Oceancrest Post Office - Branch Office
description: you may send mail to anyone in the Land of Mordor by typing   sendmail <player>.  Because this is a very primitive line editor,   be sure to hit the return key at the end of a line.  Two blank lines  will exit the mail system.

name: Side Show Tent
description: A crowd is gathered around the bearded lady, and an even bigger group is around JoJo the dog faced boy.  A little distance away you can see a a muscular weight lifter performing incredible feats of strength. Everywhere you look there is a crowd of people, all with their mouths hanging open, and their wallets totally unprotected.

name: North Oceancrest Guard Station Gate
description: this gate is normally closed at night, but there is a door inside the Guard Station for citizens willing to assume the risk of leaving at night. No one is allowed to enter from outside during the night hours, however. During the day a constant stream of visitors and farmers use this gate.

name: North Oceancrest Guard Station Gate
description: The huge gate is ponderous to open or close, and stays open all day, but at  night it is shut tightly and the guards peer down from the City Wall above. A small but sturdy metal door is available for emergency use at night. It goes directly into the Guard Station.

name: North Highway
description: Of all the roads converging on Oceancrest, this may be the safest.  That's   not to say the highway has no danger, but fewer crimes are reported along here.  There is a guard patrol, but its only during the day.  The guards tend to think that anyone dumb enough to be out here at night deserves what they get.  In the distance to the north you see snow covered mountains.

name: Guard's Holding Cell
description: Although this cell was supposed to be a temporary place to keep prisoners detained by the guards, it looks like they must have forgotten a few.   By the way, the lieutenant is the only one with a key to this cell.

name: North Highway
description: This close to the city there are plenty of farms and small villages that supply the city with a great many products.  Of course, Oceancrest is almost totally self-sufficient, but in time of peace they don't mind letting outsiders bring their wares to the markets.

name: North Highway
description: The highway tends to meander as it cuts across fields and meadows, choosing the easiest way to go.  From time to time you see carts and waving peasants either going or coming from Oceancrest.  Not far to the north there is a traveler's inn where you might spend the night.

name: North Highway
description: A large country inn and a few small shops make up a small village in a grove of trees to the east.  From this elevation you can see a river in the distance even farther to the east.  Wheat fields are on the west side of the highway, and an old house and barn are over there.

name: North Highway
description: To the south you can see a large but decrepit old inn where they serve good food, or so the peasants along the road have said.  A few small buildings and shops around the inn make up a village.  A produce stand is just off the road.

name: North Highway
description: The highway runs almost directly north and south along here, and to the north it looks like there is an entrance to some sort of outdoor inhabited area.  If you want to go in there, you might have to climb over some of these rocks and boulders.  They seem to block the highway, and any further travel northward might be extremely difficult.

name: North Highway
description: It looks like great boulders have been rolled across the highway, but who could have done so much work?  The boulders are huge.  Over to the  east there is an entrance to some sort of park.  The Golgoth Ice Mountain can be seen in the distance to the northwest.

name: Uland Trading Center
description: A variety of small shops are tucked into this quaint little plaza of cobblestones and ancient buildings.  Evidently the owners of several of the shops live in quarters above them.  Directly east is a friendly looking place known as the Adventurer's Haven.  To the north is a tiny little neighborhood pub called the Tail-o-the-Dragon.  It's said that a retired hero of Oceancrest owns it and entertains patrons with his heroic tales.

name: Adventurer's Haven
description: However, they do wish to sell this place, and have listed it with the Sleeping Deer Real Estate Office.  If you wish to purchase it, please obtain a copy of the Rules of Business, and contact a DM.

name: Marina/Eidenhoft Alley
description: On the south side of the alley you see a narrow stairwell going to the second floor of a dilapidated building.  A sign hangs over the door, and it appears this is the meeting place for a group of hobbits who like to practice low-level magic.  Handwritten on the wall is, "Frodo Lives." A storefront church is slightly to the west, and the alley twists out of sight to the east.  Directly south is a post office branch.

name: Marina/Eidenhoft Alley
description: A number of speciality shops are here in the alley, and there is a lot of foot traffic going between the narrow walkway and Eidenhoft Boulevard to the east.  A story you overheard in the Dragon Claw makes you think this is the alley where a school for pickpockets is located.  Hold on to your wallet as you walk through here.  On the south side of the alley is a narrow doorway leading to the headquarters of a mercernary group.

name: Marina/Eidenhoft Alley
description: Along the north wall of the alley is a very large building which is the Adrilite Museum of Natural History.  This must be the delivery entrance, as there are two really tall doors and a guard station.  Several shops and guilds line the south side of the alley.  One shop, which is closed, used to be an alchemy shop.  A very old and faded sign over a door says,  "School of-"  But the sign is broken and you cannot read the rest of it.

name: Jungle Trail
description: Not far from here is the village on Uland Island, but this is almost a different world.  You are surrounded by thick jungle growth forming a tunnel path through the vegetation.  The path generally takes an east to west direction, and to the north you can see a few buildings.  In all the other directions, there is nothing but jungle.

name: Jungle Trail
description: This trail is evidently not used vey much, because it almost doesn't exist.  The brush from either side has invaded the path and its difficult to be sure you are on it for long stretches.  Over to the south you can hear the sound of water falling and splashing into a pool, but you can't see it.  A bird screams directly overhead, sounding exactly like a human in extreme pain.

name: Steamy Jungle Trail
description: Heavy vines hang from the trees and monkeys chatter overhead, watching you as you travel along the poorly defined path.  A family of ettercaps has been reported to live on this section of the island, but you haven't seen any evidence of that yet.  It's surprising how quiet the jungle can be, and then suddenly it erupts with noise.  When the monkeys stop their chattering it may be a bad sign that something dangerous is nearby.

name: Steaming Jungle Trail
description: It's almost impossible to step off the path to either side because of the thick, wet brush.  Low ferns and young palms grow everywhere, and tall banana trees hang ripe with fruit.  Ancient trees, covered with moss and vines, stand tall and obscure the light.  The path is dim and hard to see, and twists around frequent obstacles.

name: Jungle Trail
description: The path twists constantly and changes direction every few meters, but is generally taking a north-south direction.  The path looks old, and will probably be fully overgrown by next year.  Evidently no one travels this way any longer.  The jungle is actually a rather noisy place, and birds overhead make a terrible racket.  In the distance you hear growls and roars, and an agonizing scream.

name: Jungle Clearing
description: Looking to the east through the heavy brush, you can barely make out a ruined temple, long abandoned and forgotten.  It looks like it was built in the form of a truncated pyramid, but several large stones, which must weigh tons, are in a jumble near the entrance.  Looks like an earthquake might have shattered the ediface, as the entrance is caved in.

name: Jungle Quicksand
description: The quicksand has the appearance of solid ground, but as you slowly sink you realize there is probably no bottom.  Unfortunately, you are too far from the banks to grasp any of the branches hanging over the area.  If you don't do something quickly, you may slide under the surface and die.

name: Aquaduct
description: The tunnel is dark and damp, and a small stream of water flows down the center of it.  The slope is downward toward the east.  As you stand here, knee deep in water, you feel slithery things nudge your legs.  You can go southeast or west from here.

name: Aquaduct
description: The sides of the aquaduct are covered with moss and feel slimy to the touch.  The humidity down here is quite high, and any metal you may be carrying is probably starting to rust.  You should probably feel assured that no doubt nothing could live down here.  And no doubt you are as safe as if you were home in bed.

name: Aquaduct
description: The way is slippery and wet, and you have to be verey cautious as you move along the tunnel.  Its also quite dark.  Hard to tell what you might find down here.  Of course, nothing could live down here, right?  The water flow is from west to east, so the water source must be further west.  This old   waterduct was probably built by the ancient islanders who worshipped at the ruined jungle temple located to the east.

name: Aquaduct Cistern
description: Water bubbles from a spring at your feet and flows into a dark tunnel to the east.   The tunnel appears to form a brick lined aquaduct.  The water is flowing in a steady stream in that direction, but not enough to fill the tunnel.  You could wade into the aquaduct if you choose to go that way.

name: Brick Cistern
description: The cistern is lined with a ceramic brick, making a smooth surface for the circular well.  The ledge you are on spirals around the wall, but provides very little in the way of hand holds.  From here, its still a long way in either direction, up or down.  Although there is a bright sky up above, there is very little light here, and even less below you.

name: Top of a Brick Cistern
description: Looking down you see a narrow ledge which winds around the circular well, giving access to the dark waters below.  There doesn't seem to be any handrails, and the sides are quite slippery with moss.  A pebble dropped over the side takes a long time to splash in the water below.

name: Fresh Water Pool
description: The water looks dark and deep, and hardly a ripple can be seen.  As you look across it, you see one spot where a bubble forms every few minutes and pops at the surface.  Its the only thing disturbing the otherwise quiet pool.  Trees form a canopy over the surface, and a path runs around edge of the water.  Not far from here you see the top of a small brick structure.

name: Locked Grate
description: The stream gurgles and runs through the ancient iron grate, swirling away out of sight.  This must be at a point somewhere underneath the ruined temple in the jungle above.  The brickwork lining the old tunnel is crumbled and in a heap here, almost like it had been destroyed by an earthquake.  If you don't have a key to the grate the only exit from here is to the northwest.

name: Ulandian Temple Entry
description: The temple is completely overgrown with jungle vines and plants, and all you can see is where the entry used to be before massive stones fell from above and sealed it.  Looks like an earthquake caused the top of the temple to tumble down on the rest of it.  Maybe that's why its abandoned now. Not too far to the east you can see the waters of the Respitial Sea out over a sea cliff.  The jungle seems to come to an end there.  At one time this temple probably had a fantastic view of the ocean, since it is built on a high cliff overlooking the beach below.

name: Jungle Grove
description: High overhead you occasionally see shadowy forms watching you with glowing red eyes.  Out of the corner of your eye there is movement, but when you turn your head, its gone.  At the Iilandi University in the city of Ocean- crest there is a research group that says there is a nest of Ettercaps living in the jungle of Uland Island.  Ettercaps are ugly bipeds that get along well with spiders.  Around two meters tall, they have spindly legs and large pot-bellies.  Their arms reach nearly to their ankles.

name: Ettercap Nest
description: The ettercaps are nasty creatures with pot-bellies, long arms, and razor sharp claws.  Their bodies are covered with tufts of thick, wirey black hair.  They have long, hypodermic like fangs, and can inject a fast acting toxin capable of death in an instant.  Like spiders, they can spin silk strands to make elaborate traps.  There are several skeletons here, their flesh long ago sucked dry.

name: Ettercap Burrow
description: The nest is very old, and generations of ettercaps have lived and died here, with everything simply getting packed down into the floor of matted debris.  The remains of previous adventurers are mixed with the remains of dead ettercaps, and all of it is underfoot in the mass of stinking vegetation making the nest.  The largest and oldest female sleeps here  almost constantly, waiting for the others to bring her food from outside.

name: Open Grate
description: The grate can be opened from this side without a key, but it looks like it would require a key to come back in here.  The tunnel is dark in both directions, but it cannot go east forever.  You must be getting close to the eastern side of the island by now.  The temple is directly overhead.

name: Aquaduct
description: The way is dark and the walls are slimy to the touch.  As you wade through the cold water, you realize something alive is in the stream and keeps bumping you gently, perhaps out of curiosity, or perhaps trying to decide if you would be good to eat.  The brick-lined walls are getting wider to the east, and there might be a landing in that direction before the waters empty into an underground lake in that direction.

name: Temple Aquaduct
description: At one time this tunnel was the only fresh water supply for the great Ulandian Temple above you, but now the water simply flows into an under- ground lake down here, before it drains in a waterfall off the eastern cliff of the island.  Further east is the lake.  The aquaduct runs west. There is a stone landing on the north side.

name: Stone Quay
description: A stone arch rises overhead, and several tunnels exit from the landing. close below is a cold stream of water that enters via the old aquaduct. Water condenses on the ceiling and drips down your back, making you shiver. To the east you see some stairs leading up and down into the temple, but great tumbled stones block any access to them.

name: Circular Stairs
description: You are in a stairwell which follows a tight spiral, going both up and down. The temple priests were very secretive before the temple collapsed, and loved to confuse people who might come to visit.

name: Long Tunnel
description: the dampness makes a great environment for slime and bacteria growth which probably isn't good for your health.  Everything you touch seems to be slick with some sort of nasty, living slime.  This tunnel is very confusing, too.

name: Long Tunnel
description: There are structural signs of some sort of a disaster here.  Great stones are dislodged from their normal places, and there are cracks in the floor and walls.  It looks as though the temple was shaken by a giant hand.

name: Circular Stairs
description: You are in a stairwell which follows a tight spiral, going both up and down. The temple priests knew their way around the temple, but tried to make it difficult for intruders.

name: Circular Stairs
description: You are in a stairwell which follows a tigh spiral, going both up and down. The temple priests were very secretive before the temple collapsed.

name: The Tomb of Achunter
description: A sense of peace overwhelms you as you enter the room.  The undead of the Necropolis seem unable to contaminate the tomb with their presence.  A soft glow emits from the center of the the room.  Upon closer examination, you see the actual body of Achunter himself, levitating from the floor.  Suprisingly, his body shows no signs of decay and he seems to be in a state of sleep rather than the cold trance of death.  In his lifetime, no creature in the whole of Oceancrest could slay him and in the end, only an intangible force known only as the "The Erasure" took his life.

name: Finesse's Second Hand Shop
description: Although retired from the adventuring business, Finesse still likes to stay in touch with his old friends.  Many of them drop in here to laugh and share a drink, and tell lies about their exploits.  Occasionally, Shadowhawk and Sisyphus are here, and Finesse's cousin Fin even stops by sometimes.

name: Circular Stairs
description: You are in a stairwell which follows a tight spiral, going both up and down. The temple priests were very secretive before the temple collapsed.

name: Circular Stairs
description: You are in a stairwell which follows a tight spiral, going both up and down. The temple priests knew their way around the temple, but tried to make it difficult for intruders.

name: Main Temple Chamber
description: At one end is an altar, and in front of it is a stone table with straps attached to it.  Looks like a place to hold an unwilling participant in some kind of ceremonial rite.  There are heavy, dark stains down the sides.  This room is huge, but no one is here.  However, there is a soft, occasional hissing sound coming from behind the altar.  A heavy stone door just sealed behind you.  As a matter of fact, you can't even see it now.

name: Sacred Holding Room
description: There is an opening overhead which probably goes to the priest's private  chambers.  There are hissing noises up there, and rumbling can be heard in  the background.  There is something strange going on in this room, and you  can feel your energy draining away as you stay here.

name: Subterrain Chamber
description: The temple worshipers considered puzzles to be sacred, and took great pride in creating labyrinths and mysteries.  This room doesn't appear to have any exits, but the fact that you are here means there must be at least the one you came in.  Sometimes, the most obvious is quite invisible.  There is a  hole far over your head, but it would be impossible to go that way.

name: Shrine Entry
description: The high ceiling appears to be covered with gold foil, inlaid with precious gems.  The wavering flames of the high set torches produce a dancing sparkle which is beautiful to behold.  Everywhere you look you see evidence of elven quality workmanship.  This one entry room alone must be worth the ransom of a couple of kings.  There is a sign in the elven language on the wall near the east door.

name: Audience Chamber
description: To the east you see a great golden statue of Larethian surrounded by an immense ebony and silver altar.  Below the statue is a reflecting pool of an amber liquid, and beside the exquisitely carved statue there are banks of sweet smelling candles.  Looking north you see the wedding chapel.  An elegantly thick carpet covers the floor, and velvet drapes  hang on the walls, producing a very quiet ambience.

name: Wedding Chapel
description: Although this chapel is smaller than the main audience chamber outside, it is no less richly appointed.  Unlike many other races, the elves have always been very rich, and enjoy showing their wealth in this, their shrine to Larethian.  A canopy stands near a small altar of white marble, the place of honor for the bride and groom, and lush, indoor plants create a wonderful aroma of blooming flowers.

name: Eiden Public Storage West Hallway
description: Each of the rooms in the Eiden Facility is protected by a magic aura  which prevents people from teleporting into them.  In addition, they  are locked with a special key and the locks are unpickable.  No one can  break into these rooms.  However, the management makes no other claims.

name: Thieve's Guild
description: There are three doors here, each painted a different color.  If you are level 3 and wish to train to level 4, please go in the green door.  Level 4 players should select the blue door, and level 5 should go in the red door.  There will be a fee charged for the training.  Should you fail the the training session, you may come back later and try again.

name: Thieve's Guild Green Room
description: A master training thief is here with you, and if you are successful in his assessment, you will be given the key to the training room door. If not, you will have to fight to obtain the key.  Now... your test is  to see if you can steal the key from the master without his detecting it.

name: Thieve's Guild Blue Room
description: The guild requires that all thieves must pass a qualification test before they are allowed to advance to the next level.  A master training thief is here in the blue room, waiting to test you.  If you sucessfully steal the training room key from him, you will not have to fight him.  But woe to you if he detects your crude attempts.

name: Thieve's Guild Red Room
description: If you are successful in stealing the training room key from the master training thief, you will not have to fight to the death.  The guild doesn't allow just any inept and bungling would-be thief into the training room.

name: Thieve's Guild
description: Only seasoned adventurers are allowed in here, and training classes are conducted for mid-level thieves in the side rooms.  At the moment, all master training thieves are either serving time or out on a job, so if you want to advance in level without a fight, this is your lucky day. Just go to the training room and pickup your advancement.

name: Werewolve's Cellar
description: Werewolves have mommies, too.  And this is where she stays.  All those bad-breathed doggies upstairs are hers, and she really doesn't like them being killed.

name: Nobunaga's Flea Market
description: There are several tents around you, and a number of sellers have open-air tables set up.  Sellers and buyers crowd around, trying to get the best bargains.  Nobunaga has a large tent to the south, and he takes a cut of all the sales that happen here.  If you would like to trade or swap some armor, or a nice weapon, you should contact Nobunaga the orc.

name: Nobunaga's Tent
description: Nobunaga nevers buys or sells anything, but he loves to trade.  If you have anything he might like, make him an offer.  He often will trade just for the pleasure of trading.  Nobunaga and his buddies sometimes come here  to drink the dwarve's Ulandian rum.

name: Neophyte Training
description: At this point in your career, the training center accepts all who apply, but  as you seek higher levels of learning you will find the red robed mages here to be harsh task masters.  Only the elite amongst you will eventually reach your goals.  For those of you seeking to advance to the second level, you must enter the green door.  If you wish to train for the third level, go in the blue door.

name: Emerald Room
description: You are in the Wizard's Eye, in a room flooded with emerald green light. A wizard, wearing a red robe and a green sash stands near the entrance to the training room door.  He offers you the key to the door, but also has his hand out.  Perhaps you should talk to him.

name: Opal Room
description: A red-robed follower of the thoughts of Marbella, one of the Arch Mages, floats slightly above your head, rocking gently back and forth.  A tiny key on a silk pillow floats nearby.  The wizard waits for you to speak.

name: Sapphire Room
description: The walls are covered with sapphires, which cast an eerie blue light. There is a single chair in the room, which hovers slightly off the floor. Seated there is a wizard wearing a red robe with a blue collar.  He has a tiny, glittering key to the training room in his hand.  He does not speak, but points to the glittering key with his other hand.

name: Ruby Hallway
description: Enlightenment shall be yours.  This hallway is the path to mystical and powerful knowledge.  As your brethern above you know, going west shall eventually bring you to the east hallway.  However, unless misfortune  befalls you, once you travel east you shall never travel west again.

name: Diamond and Gold Balcony
description: You are suspended high over the entry floor of the Wizard's Eye, the world-famous training facility for young mages through level nine.  If you aspire to level ten and above, there are some older members of the order whom you must meet, that they may pass judgment on you.  Go through the  arches and learn what you must.

name: Arched Entry
description: level ten mages and above are considered the aristocracy in the Land of Mordor.  This special entrance to the training room is reserved to those who will one day aspire to the council of mages at Lyanden castle.  The training room floor is down below you, but you must be at least level 12 to go that way.  If you are level nine, ten or eleven, go in the amethest door.

name: Garnet Room
description: Reflections in reflections in reflections.  There are ten thousand images in blood red garnet all about you.  An elderly woman is seated between two elven cats, and they reflect into infinity.  She teases one of the cats with a tiny key on a dangling silver chain.   She wears a red robe.

name: Jade Room
description: Glistening jade in rich carvings set in ivory pillars distinguishes the room. The room is cut in triangular shapes of all sizes, each piece meshing with the next one, forming a geodesic structure of jade and ivory columns at odd angles.  A jade tiger, wearing a red robe, paces the floor.

name: Ruby Hallway
description: There are three arches here, and you will find your way if you try them. Flickering lights behind ruby panels cast moving shadows on the walls and floor.  Each shadow seems to have a face and form, and each tries to gain your attention.  The shadows pull at your robes and scream silently in your ear.  Ignore them.

name: Ruby Hallway
