description: Now that you know something of your craft, you are hereby charged with the duty of helping those below you who also aspire to become a mage.  As you become older and wiser, the young mages will look to you for guidance.  Be sure it is not lacking on your part.

name: Silver and Ruby Room
description: It is said that each gem in this building holds the soul of a person.  Maybe. A great many mages, wizards and sorcerers seem to be busy in the building. Perhaps you could ask one of them.  Reclining on a bright red couch you see one of the most beautiful women you have ever seen.  Perhaps you could ask her.  She looks as though she would like to talk to you.

name: Gold and Ruby Room
description: You are in a spherical gold room, with rings of red rubys around you. It looks as though you are inside a great golden ball, at the exact center. You appear to be floating in a red mist while an old man's face watches you you from near a circular door which probably goes to the training room. The face smiles, and a hand appears in the mist, holding a small key. You probably ought to ask him what he would like for the key.

name: Platinum and Ruby Room
description: There are but three highly polished walls in this room, representing the alignment of forces in the Land of Mordor.  One wall represents goodness, another represents evil, and the third is neutral in alignment.  It ties the the other two wall together.  The training room door goes through that wall. A statue of a griffon stands in the middle of the room, it's ruby eyes

name: Amethest Room
description: On the walls are pictures of long dead mages who are remembered today for their work with the order.  A triple amethest, mounted on an alabaster pillar, stands in the center of the room.  There are three red-robed wizards seated about the room, and you are invited to sit and talk to them.  They will tell you what you must do to train.

name: Hab's Sitting Room
description: You are in the wizard Hab's sitting room.  A lone wooden bench is here. A single amethest on a single alabaster pillar stands at the end of the carved wooden bench.  The room is stark save for the radiance of the gem. Someday, to advance to the very highest levels, you must learn the secrets of the gems.

name: Nab's Sitting Room
description: The room is furnished in tasteful pieces of carved cheerywood and rich tapistries in bright colors.  A pot of tea and tiny crystal cups stand on the sideboard.  There is an alabaster pillar by the door, with a single amethest mounted atop it.  When you look closely, you see dark shadows swirl inside the gem.

name: Yab's Sitting Room
description: Yab is the most powerful of all who have chosen to master the craft of illusion.  Others before her time gained power and respect by learning to make things appear differently than what they really are.  Yab taught Trantori, the High Invoker, how to make the mice at Khallazar's to appear as powerful three-headed snakes.  A pillar supports a sparkling amethest. Is it an illusion, or is there nothing else here?

name: Training Room
description: Only those who have passed the requirements may enter this magic room. Congratulations!  You have been accepted to the next level, and are but a simple command away from it.  You may train now.  Before you leave, be sure to ask the sorceress to cast resistive spells on you.

name: North Oceancrest Guard Station
description: There is evidence of a drunken party taking place, and the guards don't look to happy to see a visitor.  It's probably not a good idea to stay. You see three doors here, and one of them apparently leads to a holding  cell, while the sturdy one leads outside.  The other door goes to the city.

name: Ramdes Bridge
description: This bridge is really nothing more than a few old ropes tied together.  Beneath you are the dark waters of the famous Ramdes River, whose source   has never been explored because no one can find the headwaters.  You would think that all one would have to do is follow the river, but looking north you see it comes down from the mountains through a very deep, foggy valley. That terrain looks forboding.

name: Under the Hofton Avenue Bridge
description: The deep and dark Ramdes River flows from outside the city under an opening below the city Wall.  From here, it continues to the south and makes its way through the old forest before turning west to Lyanden Lake.

name: Ramdes River
description: You are traveling fast in the water, and rocks flash by as the current drags  you southward, toward the Oceancrest City Wall.  Looks like the river goes under the wall a little farther that way.

name: Straw Hut
description: of course, you must first wrest the key to the training room from the brute standing in front of it, but that should be an easy matter for you.  He is   only one level higher than you.  Go for it!

name: Wooden Hut
description: there's only one more small thing to take care of, however.  You see that goliath of a barbarian standing in front of the training room door?  He's   not going to let you enter, and he has the only key.

name: Stone Hut
description: The Chief has stationed a level 10 guard here to make sure you are worthy of the expensive training.  He stands ready for you, slightly crouched and wary.  You can see the training key stuck in his loin cloth.

name: Shaman's Hut
description: You have certainly come a long way, and now may take a seat around the campfire to give advice and council to the Chief.  You may also select a  second mate and a larger hut if you wish.

name: Spiral Landing
description: The staircase either begins or ends here, depending on your point of view. Looking down, you see its at least ten meters to the ground.  If you can't fly, you are going to get hurt if you try to go that way.

name: Spiral Staircase
description: only the very tallest trees in the forest come to this height, and there are not very many of them.  From the looks of the trunk of this redwood, there could be a small village inside the tree, even at this height.  A small hole in the tree at the base of a large branch seems dark and deep.

name: Spiral Staircase
description: This huge redwood tree is the largest in the entire forest, and the staircase winds around it through the clouds.  Trantori, the High Invoker, is a member of the red-robed mages.  He makes his summer home at the top of this redwood tree, and occasionally holds conferences for the order up here.

name: Spiral Staircase
description: A rope ladder hangs down to a spiraling staircase below, which disappears in the clouds below you.  Your's so high, it's hard to see anything on the ground below you.  There's a message burned into the tree here.  Looks like Trantori doesn't want any visitors.  "Leave now, or become a toad for the rest of your life."

name: Trantori's Portico
description: Far below, over the edge, you can see smaller trees making up the Enchanted Forest.  Looking east you see Khallazar's hut, suspended in a clearing. There seems to be a misty valley on the other side of the city wall, and occasionally great winged monsters of some sort drift through that mist. An open door leads inside to a single, large room.

name: Trantori's Summer Home
description: Windows are on every side, and there is a 360 degree view of the forest and the city of Oceancrest.  In the middle of the room a crystal globe floats  in mid-air, bobbing slightly on the air currents.  A red robe is thrown across a comfortable chair, and a table nearby is littered with books of all sizes.  The one that is open on top is an ancient, hand-written tome that must be at least half a meter in length.  It's written in a language you do not understand.

name: Trantor's Workshop
description: Trantori receives the fine jewelry made by the elves and casts his magic on each piece before it is put in the display case outside.  The speciality of the shop is magical jewelry, and Trantori and the Chief Jeweler both contribute to the final product.  You may purchase from the elven maid in the sales room.

name: Elven Sales Room
description: A slight, elven maiden stands nearby, ready to show you anything you might desire in the way of magical jewelry.  If you wish to see anything, you must ask the maiden about her selection.  Then, if you decide to buy, you must tell the maid purchase <item> elven maid.  She's pretty, but blond, so you have to be very explicit.

name: Gnarled Oak Valley
description: The path seems well worn, but also well maintained.  Wildflowers grow in neat borders along the way.  Looking west you see that the path splits and takes a southern route and also a northern one.  Both paths seem equally well taken care of.  Great oaks make a dense woods in that direction, and you see small homes cut into some of them.

name: Llanandar Path
description: This path is named after Llanandar, the oldest living elf in the village.  Over three hundred years ago, he mastered the honorable craft of bow making, and his bows are known throughout the land.  Even royalty visits him here in this tiny little village.

name: Llanandar Village
description: There seems to be a village square in the middle of a small clearing. A great many elven folk are busy doing their daily chores, and most simply ignore you as they go about their business.  A sign post points west, but  you cannot read the language.  The houses seem to be built into living trees in the oak forest around you.

name: Llanandar Creek
description: Elven fishmen are setting nets across the creek, and elven children are playing in the water.  Tall grass runs down to the water's edge from here. A path seems to meander towards the oldest oak tree in the meadow.

name: Llanandar Creek
description: Sparkling lights seem to pop all about you, and tiny wings flutter at your ear.  You can hear a tinkling little laughter and the sound of a musical instrument somewhere close by.  The great oaks make a ring around this meadow, bounded on the west by a wonderful little creek.  The path continues to the north and south.

name: Llanandar Creek
description: The Enchanted Forest is home to many races and animals, some rare, and some very common, although it seems the common animals often have extraordinary talents.  Even the trees around this lovely meadow somehow seem alive and watchful as you make your way along the path.

name: Llanandar Meadows
description: Around are old growth oaks, and you realize that many of them are centuries old, but still healthy and productive.  Small animals chatter in the tree  tops, and birds flit from tree to tree.  The meadow too, seems alive with rodents and other tiny animals.

name: Llanandar Meadows Edge
description: A particularly large old oak stands here at the meadow's edge, slightly apart from the others.  A ladder is set against its base, and high in the tree there is a ramshackle little wooden platform.  It's hard to tell exactly what's up there, but something colorful flutters occasionally at the perimeter.

name: Giant Oak Copse
description: these woods are cool and shady, and not much brush grows at the base of the giant oaks.  The path seems rather well taken care of, almost as if it had been swept.  There's not much in the way of dead brush, either.

name: Llanandar's Tree House
description: The giant old oak has doors and windows cut in the living tree, and an  old elf can be seen working inside.  Another old elf appears to be asleep  by the door.  A small sign, with a cursive script, proclaims this to be a bowyer's workshop.  The creek runs along the side, and you see a small bridge over it, and a path which goes deeper into the woods.

name: Llanandar's Tackle Shop
description: The small room is neat as a pin, and the work bench has all the tools in a neat rack nearby.  There is a crossbow on the bench which looks to be completely finished.  A small blue ball, shining brightly, lies beside it. The room is so tiny, and you are so big, that you have probably scared everyone into hiding.

name: Llanandar's Private Quarters
description: Llanandar likes his privacy, but not particularly your presense here. The room is even smaller than the shop downstairs, and you have to bow your head to keep from hitting it on the ceiling.  A tiny bed is shoved against the wall, and a private collection of bows are on the wall above it.

name: Fern Gulley
description: Dotted throughout the gulley are quaint little houses, perhaps as tall as your waist.  They are all brightly painted in vivid primary colors, and  are as clean as though newly made.

name: Straw Hut Training Room
description: The Chief regrets that he could not be here personally to watch you advance, but he sends his warmest regards.  You will henceforth have a new title as well as an increase in your abilities.

name: Wooden Hut Training Room
description: You hear a lot of applause outside as your fellow barbarians realize you you have become one of the leaders of the group.  The Shaman has a standing invitation for you to come to his hut for dinner.

name: Stone Hut Training Room
description: Both the Chief and the Shaman would like you to stop by later, so that they can personally congratulate you on your achievement.  The next time you advance, you will receive a new title.

name: Khallazar's Gold Room
description: However, Khallazar has asked his friend, Trantori the High Invoker, to  place a high level monster here to guard the precious  metal.  There are  a number of three-headed snakes in the room. The snakes coil around the ingots and glare at you, as if to say, "touch the gold... we dare you."

name: Trantori's Redwood
description: there is hole leading out onto a large branch nearby, and ladder rungs are nailed to the inside of the huge trunk.  They disappear into the dark as you look both up and down.  Outside, you can see a staircase attached to the side of the tree, and it seems to spiral out of sight also.  But at least its not dark out there.

name: Trantori's Redwood
description: You are clinging to ladder rungs nailed to the inside of this great tree. You can go up or down, but it would be silly to stop here.  It's dark and silent all around you.  Think of it this way:  where you go, you won't be here, and that's better, don't you think?

name: Trantori's Redwood
description: There is a small ledge here, just big enough to stand on.  The ladder rungs continue above and below you.    A small group of knotholes nearby allow  light to enter, but not enough to see any detail in here. The ledge seems  to get wider on the northern side of the tree.

name: Trantori's Redwood Ledge
description: directly overhead there is a trapdoor, and as you look across the empty space between you and the center core of the great tree, you realize there is a door over there.  There is no place to stand, but the door seems to open into the heart of the mighty tree, while the trapdoor opens above you.

name: Trantori's Locked Door
description: You are inside the biggest redwood tree in the Enchanted Forest.  A hollow shaft inside the trunk of the tree seems to serve as a bad-weather entry for the High Invoker.  The door seems to be locked with a silver filigree lock.  This might be a store room of some sort.

name: Trantori's Store Room
description: There's not much in here except a pile of dirty clothes and a stack of dull blue balls in a net, hanging from the ceiling.  The blue balls look to be the sort that carry enchantments, but these must be either duds or ones that are not ready yet.   They don't have that pretty glow to them. On a table is a red sash, carelessly thrown there.

name: Trantori's Redwood
description: The interior of the redwood is spacious, and there seems to be plenty of room to climb either up or down, your choice.  Ladder rungs are on the inside of the tree, making it easy to climb.

name: Trantori's Redwood
description: A smooth tunnel seems to run towards the southeast from here.  The only other way you can go is up some ladder rungs you see nailed to the inside  of the tree.  This is the biggest redwood in the entire forest, and the High Invoker lives at the top of it.

name: Forest Tunnel
description: The walls are like glass, as though intense heat was used to fuse the earth into a bore sighted tunnel.  It runs straight as an arrow from northwest to southeast.  Although its not enough light to see by, the walls glow with an eerie greenish luminescense.

name: Forest Tunnel
description: The tunnel is a remarkable piece of work, although it's apparent nothing living could produce such incredibly smooth walls.   It looks as if a giant fireball roared through here, and the earth melted.

name: Forest Tunnel
description: The walls are smooth and slippery, and they glow with a greenish hue. The tunnel is as straight as if it had been laid out with a surveyor's line. It continues in both directions, but even with the greenish glow, it is too dark to see what might be in either direction.

name: Forest Tunnel
description: The walls glow with a steady green hue, but not with enough light to see by. coming from the southeast is a breath of fresh air, but it doesn't change the fact that this place is a silent as a tomb.

name: Forest Tunnel
description: Its the strangest tunnel you have ever been in, probably, because the walls seems to be made of a fused silicon and earth, like glass.  A soft glow emanates from the walls.  You can feel fresh air on your cheek, coming from the southeast direction.

name: Glass Bubble
description: The bubble doesn't seem to have any distinguishing marks, but is a great round bubble of glass under the earth.   You are on a small ridge which runs around the inside perimeter of the bubble. It seems to spiral around the interior.  A very strong rush of air is going somewhere.

name: Glass Bubble
description: A ridge allows you to walk on the inside of the bubble, and it seems to spiral around the inside. There is a red glow in the exact center of  the bubble, but you would have to fly to get there.

name: Glass Bubble
description: Toward the empty space of the center, there is a dull, reddish glow. The walls are smooth and warm to the touch.  If you slip, you may never  get your footing again.  Stay on the ridge.

name: Glass Bubble
description: You are following a spiraling ridge around the inside of the great glass bubble.  Your only reference is a reddish glowing spot near the center  of the bubble.  It hangs in empty space there.

name: Glass Bubble
description: The ledge you are traveling on is quite narrow, and it seems to rise and widen as it circles around the interior. There is a red light near the center of the bubble, or at least something red out there. It seems to be turning as you make your way around the inside of this place.

name: Glass Bubble
description: Somewhere above ground there is a hidden entry to this place, but why? The small ledge continues around the interior of the ball.

name: Glass Bubble
description: You are edging along a narrow walkway inside an underground bubble.   You seem to be going in circles around the inside of this wierd bubble. For what purpose was this bubble created?  Why is the sky blue?  What   is that red glow at the center of the bubble?  Why does evil exist? Why, why, why?

name: Glass Bubble
description: There is a frightening reddish light near the center of the interior, but you would have to fly to get to it.  That is, if you wanted to get to it. There's not much to this place except for that light.  What could it be for, and what is it?  Why is it there?

name: Glass Slide
description: Hold on to your stuff, because you may need it where ever you are going. You are never going to get back up this way, unless perhaps you can fly.

name: Wind Tunnel
description: you can't go back below because of the strong blast of wind coming through the very small tunnel.  And this is a terrible place to stay, so you might as well let the wind carry you to where ever the tunnel ends.

name: Harikari's Addiction Deprivation Chamber
description: This huge room appears limitless in space, with dark shadows as the only visible boundaries.  However, a faint noise which resembles the clicking of keyboards seems to incessantly extend itself from the darkness.  In what appears to be the center of the room, Harikari, master of the occult and technology, is seen manipulating a microcosmic representation  of Oceancrest.

name: Shrine of Corellion Larethian
description: The shrine shares a similar design with the traditonal Greek  ampitheaters.  Hundreds of onlookers are seen gazing towards the central altar, as if in a hypnotic trance, as the sacred invocation of Corellion Larethian is being performed by the high priestess.

name: Cellar Hall
description: No one has been here in a long time, as you can see by the dust and cobwebs. Under the dust there is a heap of old bones, and if you are not careful, your own may be there also.  There is an animal-like smell coming from the cellar, and its not very plesant.

name: Cellar Alcove
description: Apparently, someone long ago sealed the hallway here.  The bricks blocking the hall are newer, and of a different kind than the bricks in the wall. Scrawled on the wall is the word, "BEWARE" and under it is an icon of  a wolf, with dripping fangs.  On the same wall is the cryptic, "YAB 371."

name: Mausoleum Stairs
description: You are on the stairs leading between the mausoleum and the cellar. The walls are are very old brick, and are covered with ancient graffiti. Looks like you can go up or down, but standing here is not fun.

name: Training Room Observation Deck
description: A few of the very important visitors to the Wizard's Eye are occasionally allowed to stand here to watch the training that takes place on the floor below.  However, no mage under level twelve may fly from this point to the training room.  Down below you see a very high level red-robed sorceress who is congratulating young mages who have left their mentor's rooms to receive the final instructions.

name: Brownhaven Guardshack
description: Of course, what they really want to protect is their naps, and if you set off an alarm, which is connected to the entrance to the dragon pits, they get very upset and wide awake.

name: Gracella's Herbal Shoppe
description: Gracella has a special rapport with the nymphs who live on the south side of the garden, and has often been blessed by the nymph queen herself.  She uses most of the profits from this shoppe for the betterment of the nymph community.  A sign says that love potions are discounted this month.

name: Matriarch's Hidden Sanctuary
description: Contrasting with the grandeoise hall outside, this small, rather austere room has dark stone walls and very little furniture.  There is a window on one side of the room and rays of sunlight shine down onto Alliyana as she reads the Divine Scripture, as if a divine blessing.

name: Hall of Worldly Bliss
description: Perfectly aligned rows of chairs face the main altar at the east side of the cathedral.  The altar itself is a raised platform, from which sermons can be delivered.  Above the alter, golden statues of angels appear to be guarding this holy place from harm.  On the ceiling, a huge, colorful mural depicts the epic struggle between the heavenly forces of good and the hellspawned armies of underworld.

name: Cathedral of Worldly Bliss
description: The massive walls of the cathedrals seem to extend to the heavens, As you gaze at the structure, you wonder how human hands alone could have built something of such splendor and magnificence.  The faint echo of a female voice delivering sermon reverberates throughout, as if calling out the very essence of your soul.

name: Base of Golgoth Mountain
description: Various types of snow flowers and vegetation cling to the lower regions of the mountain.  However, the higher elevations are obscured by dark and foreboding clouds, making it impossible to distinguish the peak.

name: Golgoth Mountain Path
description: Along one side of the trail there is a sheer drop to a thick fog which swirls below.  Some of the rocks along here occasionally let loose and roar down the mountainside, disappearing into the grey fog without a sound.

name: Golgoth Mountain Path
description: The path has become difficult in both directions, slowing your efforts. Not far from the lonely path is a strange tangle of long, brown hairs hooked onto a nearby tree branch.  The tree has been rubbed smooth at least two meters above the ground, and strange prints are under the tree. All other signs of animal life have seemingly disappeared from around the area, and now only the incessant howling of a forlorn wind remains.

name: Golgoth Mountain Path
description: The trail is a soft earth and easily imprinted, but even so, whatever made the footprints you see must be very heavy.  A short distance along the path the footprints lead away from it.  Although man-sized, the markings indicate that the creature which made them has only two large toes.  If you look in the direction of the tracks you see the entrance to a cave which was previously obscured by trees.

name: Cave of the Deadly Sasquatch
description: Due to the humidity and absence of sunlight, strange forms of slimy moss are seen growing on rocky protrusions throughout the cave.  The very dim source of light limits your vision, blinding you to the vast, shadowy expanses of the huge cave.  However, you have the strangest suspicion that something is lurking nearby in the darkness.

name: Mountain Stream
description: If you listen closely, it seems the stream murmurs in a language you can almost understand.  The path twists and turns as it traverses the mountain, making it difficult to see very far in either direction.  This might be a  good place to rest.  There is a shallow cave where the stream issues.

name: Golgoth Mountain Path
description: The air is thinner at this altitude, and very difficult to breath.  To make matters worse, the path is even steeper along this section of the mountain. At this height, and everywhere above, the path is perpetually covered with  snow and ice, regardless of seasonal changes.

name: Golgoth Frozen Falls
description: Around a particularly sharp corner of the trail the sparkling waterfall comes into view.  It appears to be frozen in both time and space, and the light falling on it creates a kaleidascope of shifting rainbows and prismatic reflections.  Closer examination reveals that a section of the waterfall is clearer, and slightly more transparent than the rest of it. The trail apparently ends here.  Nice view.

name: Crystalline Caverns Entrance
description: Ice crystals meld with rose quartz crystals as the waterfall becomes an  intricate crystalline formation which completely covers the wall of the cave.  However, the floor, which is also composed of a translucent stone, is completely flat and polished smooth to perfection.

name: Crystalline Tavern Tunnel
description: The vibration of your steps cause the crystals to resonate with harmonics which echo and re-echo throughout the cavern.  The beautiful and natural crystals look much like the ones you have seen which carry enchantments  and are used by the people who understand magic.  The tunnel slopes down in the western direction, and a sparkling light appears there.

name: Crystalline City
description: you see an entire underground world spread out before you.  Hundreds of crystalline buildings can be seen, each shimmering in a different color of the the spectrum.  Not only the buildings, but all of the inhabitants - every man, woman and child - seems to be composed entirely of different types of crystals.  Each seems to glow in a unique hue.

name: Southern Crystalline City
description: Although most of the buildings in the city share a similar size and shape, one structure really stands out in terms of sheer, breath-taking beauty. A hugh tower, composed completely of diamonds, rises from the center of the city.  The builders of the tower managed to secure the foundation at ground level and also to connect the top to the cavern ceiling, hundreds of meters above.  The light glinting from the building makes it hard to look at it.

name: Southern Crystalline City
description: The structures in this section of the crystalline city seem to be of greater importance to the citizens than the other buildings.  A huge, hexagon shaped building made entirely of sapphire is apparently a military complex, as you see crystalline guards and warriors marching endlessly in and out of it.

name: Western Crystalline City
description: To the north you see the bustling movement of a large crowd of crystallines. It's not possible to determine what they are doing without getting closer, but they seem to be excited about something.  To the east there is a tower which is protected by a squadron of crystalline guards standing before the tower's gate.  You probably cannot enter from this side.

name: Northern Crystalline City
description: This section of the city is simply alive with bustling activity, and a crowd of crystallines have gathered to watch a fight taking place in the middle of the way.  The crystallines simply ignore you.  On both sides of the street are shops and stands where you can apparently buy almost anything.

name: Northern Crystalline City
description: To the south you can see a tall tower which sparkles like one huge diamond. There is no visible entry to the tower from this direction, however, and it looks as though any movement towards the structure would be thwarted by a high gate.  To the north you can hear the sound of running water.

name: Northern Crystalline City
description: As in every civilization, there are those who exist as the lower ranks of society.  This section of the city seems to be inhabited by those less fortunate individuals.  Despite their social position, these beings are necessary to society as they provide needed services to the upper class. Someone has to take out the garbage.

name: Antechamber of the Imperial Crystal Tower
description: The entrance to the tower seems to be two massive doors which seem totally immovable by any natural force.  There are crystalline warriors standing at sentry posts, while others seem to be patrolling the area.  They apparently provide a very tight security to the only visible entry of the entire tower.

name: Imperial Crystal Tower Lobby
description: This is a vast reception area which seems to be composed almost entirely of diamonds.  In place of furniture, you see smooth, sculptured protrusions rising from the floor and shaped as chairs or desks.  A magnificient set  of broad stairs rises in a spiral to the upper levels of the tower.

name: Crystal Spiral Staircase
description: The diamonds form the entire second level of the crystalline tower complex. Polytonal "voices" resonate from the levels below, while from above there is a wild crackling of sporadic lightning and electrical energy.  Odd, the two sounds are quite pleasant to the ear.

name: Crystalline Tower Hallway
description: You are in a beautiful diamond studded hallway which is patrolled by the crystalline warriors.  It's difficult to determine what pattern they use to patrol, and seem to appear on a random basis.  There are two guards at the far end of the hallway.  They don't seem to be aware of you right now.

name: Imperial Chamber of Lord Kree
description: This is a cylindrical room with a magnificent 360 degree view of the city below.  From this height, the crystal buildings below look like mere dots on the ground and the people are all but indistinguishable. The chamber itself is simple in design, with a turning throne chair as it's main feature.

name: Emerald Fountain
description: This fountain is a place for both young and old crystallines to relax and be entertained.  The fountain itself illuminates the entire area in a relaxing green glow.  The water which is sprayed into the air is instantly shaped into beautiful designs which hold their form for a few seconds and then fall towards the ground in millions of tiny dew drops.

name: Garden Path
description: The back yard for the inn is to the northeast, as well as a fairly new building where Hagbert, the second son of Granovetter, has established a  local blacksmith shop.  In the middle of the garden to the west you can see the residence of Gracella, the oldest daughter.

name: Garden Path
description: Gracella, the oldest daughter of the Granovetter's, tends this garden with the help of a group of nymphs who live on the south side of the herbal  plot.  Some of the herbs grown here have strange powers, and when mixed together they often take on magical properties.  Gracella sells these to the herb shops in the cities.

name: Garden Path
description: Huge jacintha plants, taller than a half-giant, nod in the breeze.  They appear ready to harvest.  There are rows and rows of them stretching to the south.  A tiny building is in the garden to the southeast.

name: Charikawa's House of healing
description: On the wall behind the table are a number of surgeon's tools, and a few carpenter's tools.  On the wall is a certificate stating that Charikawa graduated from the School of Astrology at Iilandi University in the city of Oceancrest.  Charikawa thinks of himself as a surgeon.

name: Phluebluts Pawn Shoppe
description: Phluebluts himself stands behind the counter, quietly rubbing his hands as  he waits for you to speak.  He is almost as wide as he is tall, which doesn't really say much, considering how short he is.  Phluebluts is a midget gnome, and is both lacivious and mercenary.

name: Granovetter's Corner
description: the large old inn was hand-built by Granovetter the dwarf and his wife more than a century ago.  They carried river stones from the Ramdes River which is a little way further east of here.  The newer buildings were built by their sons and daughters as the family grew, and now there is a thriving little village starting to spread out near this bend in the North Highway.

name: Granovetter's Inn
description: Rough tables and chairs are around the room with most of them near the fire  place.  There is a large kitchen in the back, and the smell of good food is in the air.  Hanging on the walls are trophy size heads of animals, but most of them are animals you have never seen before.

name: Granovetter's Kitchen
description: An open roasting pit is in the center of the room, and two smaller fire places are on the north wall.  Pots and pans hang from hooks in the ceiling and a butcher's block stands in the middle of the room.  One side area seems to be devoted to cakes and pastries.

name: Granovetter's Cellar
description: There are racks of wine and great kegs of Uland rum close by, but in the dark areas you see nothing but dust and vegetable bins.  Although the  innkeeper and his family are well liked, there are whispered stories occasionally about a mad brother who is kept out of sight.  Might this  be his private world, down here?

name: Garden path
description: To the west is the large yard in front of the inn, and to the east you see one of the newer buildings in this small village built around the old inn.  A good smelling garden is on both sides of the path you are on.  The innkeeper's daughter sells some very potent herbs that she grows herself.

name: Back Yard of Granovetter's Inn
description: This small village is called Granovetter's Corner by people who live in this region, and they often prefer to do business here rather than go clear into the big city of Oceancrest.  There is a blacksmith here who can fix most anything, and a no-questions-asked pawn shop.

name: Granovetter's Iron Works
description: A forge and foundry makes the room hot, but you can see from the armor hanging from the ceiling that the smithy does good work.  Looks like he can repair weapons and other items too.

name: Hobar's Second Hand Store
description: You are in the shop of Hobar, eldest son of Granovetter the dwarf. All about you are pieces of farm equipment, armor, old furniture, strange pieces of scientific apparatus, and just plain junk.  One wall seems to be ocvered with an assortment of weapons.  Looks like Hobar will buy just about anything, but does he ever sell any of this stuff?

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: Not far below you is the dragon pits near the western edge of the village of Brownhaven.  In the distance to the west, you can see the Nartiz mountain Range.  To the north is Mount Aphinix, home of the mountain trolls.  Looking east, you see the Kista Forest.

name: Steep Path
description: As you look below you, you see that rocks and boulders have been rolled across the King's North Highway.  It's evident, though, that road crews have been working on the problem, as you can see where they have setup a camp and have brought in equipment to clear the road.  To the west is  an icy path, leading to a cold looking mountain.

name: Steep Path
description: The wind is cold here, and the path is covered with patches of ice.  This  trail gets colder and even more rugged in the westward direction where you   see the base of an ice and snow covered mountain.  The path drops pretty quickly to the southeast.

name: Golgoth's Cave
description: shallow.  An icy stream of water trickles off the back wall and forms a small runnel to the cave's entrance.  Mushrooms grow all about you, and they look good to eat.  You probably could spend a relaxing time here.

name: North Highway
description: Huge boulders and large rocks look as though they have been deliberately placed across the Highway.  A road crew has pitched a small camp on the west side of the road.  Another camp is for several of the King's militia who are here to protect the road crew from bandits and Golgoth, the monster from the ice mountain.

name: North Highway
description: Deep crevices and valleys run east to west on the eastern side of the Highway.  They appear to form a labrynth of interconnecting passages where one might become lost, were he to venture into them.  An old map tacked to the wall of the Boar's Arse Pub marks this area as the home of a large number of hobbits.

name: Rocky Cove on the Ramdes River
description: Before you lies a vast valley, filled with plant and animal life which are from another time.  A thick fog clouds the landscape, making it difficult to see beyond a few meters.  the humidity and temperature are uncomfortable, and biting insects swarm around you constantly.

name: Valley of Time
description: An enigmatic prehistoric swampland surrounds you, alive with strange plants and beasts.  Great lizard-like birds swoop down to get a better look at you, and flesh-eating plants seem to twist in your direction as you wade through the marsh.  A cold fog drifts across the water.  The river is close by.

name: Eastern Swamplands
description: Marshy swamplands extend in every direction, and at times the water comes to your knees.  Occasionally something brushes against your legs as you wade through the muck.  Although fog limits your vision, the movement of tremendously large creatures can be seen in the vicinity.

name: Prehistoric Swamplands
description: There are primative broken weapons and crude tools strewn on the ground in this area, but no sign of intelligent life.  The skinned remains of a giant wooly mammoth suggests there may be a more dangerous animal here.

name: Western Swamplands
description: The smell of rotting flesh mixed with the malodor of the bubbling tar pits lingers in the damp air.  There are large-clawed tracks imprinted into the soft, muddy ground that forms an island in this swamp you have been wading in.  Volcanic ash mixes with the fog, and there are low rumbling sounds in  the distance coming from active cinder cones.

name: Entrance to the Storm Giant Stronghold
Ramdes River
description: The water is deep and swift, making it difficult to swim in any direction but with the current.  It looks like the center, being deepest, is the least dangerous.  There are rocks jutting out of the water along the shore.

name: Hermit's Storage
description: Wooden boxes and chests with contents unknown are neatly stack on one side of the tunnel, while on the other side, a large oak rack supports the weight of numerous potion bottles and vials.  Despite the  organization of the items, everything seems to be covered in dust.

name: Darkened Tunnel
description: Strange varieties of fungus can be seen growing on the moist walls of the tunnel.  Frogs and small lizards seems to crawl about, often crossing your path in a nervous frenzy.  Their croaks and movements echo throughout the passage, creating almost a musical noise.

name: Darkened Tunnel
description: The floor is slick with a slimy liquid which is probably a mixture of mud and mildew.  Now, the only noise which can be heard is the melodic dripping of water.  All signs of reptilian life has disappeared as you enter this section of the tunnel.

name: Mud Pool
description: Before you, you see a vast underground pool which has been muddied by the soft dirt walls which contain it.  The murky, dark waters make it impossible to see what may lie within the pool itself.  However, several small ripples which move toward your direction indicate that something may be approaching, completely submerged and masked from your sight.

name: Mud Slope
description: The soft muddy ground beneath your feet sinks under your weight, forcing you to replant your feet every so few seconds or so.  Large mounds of mud can be seen at different places on the slope.  Often these mounds turn out to be living monsters, and have been revealed to be frighteningly huge frog-like creatures that have dragged themselves onto the slope.

name: Arioch & Arcana's Suite
description: This spacious suite is furnished with modern designer pieces.   A few priceless oil paintings casually spaced along the walls  produce an effect which shows affluent, yet stylish tastes.  To one side of the room, a full-featured entertainment center equiped with the latest in stereo / wide-screen television technology has been set up for convenience, while to the other side, a crystal table for two stands ready for those romantic candle-light dinners.

name: Storage Closet
description: A room sized walk-in closet, holding the both Arioch's & Arcana's posessions lies before you.  To the left, Arioch's designer suits hang neatly next to his shinning dragon-slaying armor.  To the right, Arcana's dresses, blouses, and skirts create a virtual rainbow of clothing.  Strangely enough, even two treasure chests lie on the ground, holding riches beyond imagination.

name: Z Bed Room
description: This fantanstic bedroom is the highlight of entire suite with a magnificent view of the Ashton Waterfalls themselves.  In the center of the bedroom, a king-sized waterbed seems to ripple with the motion of long past nights.  While on the ceiling, a bed-sized mirror has been strategically placed above the waterbed.  The lights dim, the music begins to play softly, and your pulse quickens...

name: Gates of Castle Rutger
description: This huge castle is built almost vertically, to best utilize the mountain side it is constructed on.  The lower level is used for troop assembly and social events, such as exhibitions and contests.  The massive gates are always closed at night, but gate guards are always here on duty.  The guard  station is located to the south.  On the north side is an information  office.  The main courtyard is to the east.

name: Castle Rutger Information Office
description: There are maps on the walls, and several clerks scurry about with slips of paper.  A few are putting colored pins in the largest map.  A sign on the wall says that Prince Rutger is recruiting warriors and adventurers in his battle with his brother, Prince Ragnar.

name: Guard Station
description: You see a simple desk where you may state your business.  Behind the desk there are two doors, which apparently lead to a barracks room and an office for the Lieutenant of the Guard.  Several off duty guards are lounging  near the main entry door.  They wear gleaming black and silver uniforms.

name: Stone Archway
description: There is a covered hallway running north and south from here, while to the east you can see the busy courtyard of the castle.  West is the castle entry and you can see the great gates there.

name: Guard Barracks
description: Unless you are wearing a black uniform with silver piping and are a member of Rutger's Force, you are in trouble.  The guards are not happy to have people simply wander into their quarters.

name: Office of the Lieutenant of the Guards
description: Several officers rotate through this office, and each of them is very jealous of the position and rank he holds.  the room is immaculate and  quite spartan in appearance.  There is a well-made small bed with a book shelf above, and a tidy desk with a single map spread out on it.

name: Main Courtyard Entry
description: directly west is the castle's gates through a great stone archway.  The main courtyard opens up to the east.  Over to the north you can see a tier of  seats and a group of noblemen and ladies in colorful silks.  Evidently the seats are for spectators of the troop assembly which takes place twice a  day.  Several knights in black armor and silver helmets are already here.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The castle is built in the form of concentric levels, each one atop the other.  This level is the lowest and hence the largest.  The hallway you are in completely encircles the base level where troops and other members of Rutger's fighting forces are garrisoned.  On the upper floors you will  members of the royal family and counselors to the Prince.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: You are in the great hallway which completely encircles the lowest level. Prince Rutger had his builders create this castle in the form of concentric levels, each one smaller than the one below it.  At the very top you will find the private quarters of the Prince and his family.  This circular hallway completely encircles the base level of the castle where troops are garrisoned.  On the floor above you will find administrative offices.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: There is a series of doors on the east side of the hall, some of which are open.  They look like shops and stores.  This castle has a lot of people living in it, and is almost a small city in its needs.  Merchants are quite happy to meet that need, and have provided many services.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The hallway makes a turn here, and heads southeast.  This section of the   castle is mostly inhabited by the lowest level of troops and servants. They don't really have the nice manners of the lords and ladies who reside on the north side of the castle.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: Looks like several doors along here all go into the same place, a barracks for the troops in the service of the castle.  In time of emergency, the  several doors provide a fast exit for the knights inside.  There is a repair shop for weapons and armor through the iron gate.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The wooden door you see on the outside wall looks well used.  It probably does not go directly out of the castle, but since the castle wall is so wide at the ground level it might go someplace within the wall itself.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: From here, the circular hallway stretches into a dimly lit distance to the east.  Several torches have burned out along here, and someone is going to be punished for not replacing them.  The open door on the north side goes to the Griffon's Heart Pub, a drinking place for the castle's troops.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The lighting is dim along here, and the hallway is wide and high.  You can hear the rustle and squeak of bats high overhead.  The closed doors along here lead to the servant's quarters and a dirty little pub frequented by  the lower classes who live in the castle.  To the east is a barracks entry.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The special forces of the castle's garrison who maintain the heavy battle equipment have their barracks just to the north.  The great double doors on the north side of the hallway lead to those barracks.  On the other side is the castle armory.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: Farther to the east you can see that the hallway turns sharply to the north, while to the west it continues a good distance.  There is a small healing room for the infirm on the north side of the hallway, and a couple of healing mages can be seen inside.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The door with the three brass balls suspended over it is exactly what you think it is.  yes, its a pawn shop.  There is also a red and white striped  pole next door, indicating a barber shop.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: There is an intersection with Apstone Tunnel farther to the north, while to the south you see a line of shops which serve the needs of the castle's inhabitants.  Not far from here is a pawn shop, usually frequented by some of the younger and less well paid members of the castle's defense force.

name: Level One Circular Hallway/Apstone Tunnel Intersection
description: Apstone Tunnel leads in a northwest direction towards the center courtyard. The tunnel carries the name of a very talented and very old wizard who has chosen to support the claim of Prince Rutger against his brother, Prince Ragnar.  Apstone believes that it is Rutger who has a lawful claim to the crown at Lyanden.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The hallway turns at this point, and continues to the north and to the southwest.  The southern side of the castle on the ground floor is used mostly by the troops, while the commanders generally reside on the north side of the castle.  Heavy battle equipment is in storage along the hall.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The door on the west side of the great circular hallway shimmers with a bluish glow.  Energy snaps and crackles from it, producing an eerie light in the hallway.  There is no sign or other indication where the door leads, but it is well known as the Weather Wizard's Climate Control Room.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: North of you is the castle's chapel, and south of you is the castle's Weather Wizard's Climate Room.  The walls along here are covered with banners and flags of famous commanders of the past and present.  The large green and gold flag with the red dragon in its field belongs to Franchot.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The open door lets you see that the chapel is a small place with a simple altar and a confessional booth.  Confession is good for the soul, and  several knights evidently want a good soul, as there is a line to the booth.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: This is the widest hallway in the entire castle, and from here it heads south and northwest.  The ceiling is high and torches are close spaced  along the way, providing a well lighted throughfare.

name: Level One Circular Hallway/Franchot Tunnel Intersection
description: Franchot Tunnel will take you to the center courtyard.  It heads in a southwest direction, and goes past the chambers of Franchot the paladin, commander of the Black Guard which is an elite force pledged to Prince  Rutger.  The Black Guard believes that only Rutger has the rightful  succession to the Lyanden throne.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: This castle was built in the form of a great tower, and is made up of many circular levels.  This ground level is the largest of the several levels. the door you see leads to the castle library.   Farther to the southeast there is a side corridor leading towards the center courtyard.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: This is the northern section hallway on the ground floor of Castle Rutger. The castle armory is located down the hall to the west.  To the east you   can see a well lighted room with an open door which is the library.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: There are four sentries on duty here at all times, and every once in a while a sergeant comes by to check on them.  Please do not speak to them, as they are not supposed to be diverted from their duties.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The armory is a little farther to the east where you see the sentry guard. The more expensive and better weapons are stored in the armory, so several guards keep an eye on them.  Many people visit the castle who are not actually part of the castle's company, and a few seem to be accomplished theives.  Equipment has been found missing more than once.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The tunnel on the south side of the hallway opens to the Grand Hall, a huge assembly room for the upper class of the castle.  Large banners hang on the walls and battle flags adorn the tables.  The Grand Hall is where Prince Rutger addresses his commanders when the need arises.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: the hallway continues to the east and turns to the southwest.  The main gate is located to the southwest.  This part of the hallway is reserved for higher ranked officers, and the rooms along here are generally occupied by  off duty commanders and officers.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: The nobility of the castle maintains rooms and apartments along this northern hallway.  Rutger and his family live on the fourth floor, and many of his closest advisors and friends are housed on the third floor.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: This part of the hallway has a divider down the center, and the ladies of the castle generally separate when they come to it, with the single maidens taking the side closest to the inside wall and the matrons the other side.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: It goes completely around the castle's ground level, and eventually will come back to this place.  There are a great many doors along the way, and several side corridors running towards the center of the castle.  Most of the castle's activities are held in the courtyard.

name: Level One Circular Hallway
description: There are several levels to Rutger's Tower, each a circular hallway above the others.  This is the largest, and it rings the main courtyard.  The next level up is much smaller and is mostly administrative offices.

name: Chambers of Franchot
description: Franchot singlehandedly once slew two red dragons in a battle that lasted three days.  He came upon the beasts in the Valley of Dragons while they  were mating and was able to strike the first blow, but mighty was their anger at being interrupted, and he suffered greatly, but he did kill them.

name: Chambers of Apstone
description: The sound is mind-numbing and you cannot see anything because of the swirling haze, which seems to be a sweet smelling incense.  A vague form of a man or perhaps an upright animal occasionlly appears in the room.  A voice says, "mortals should not remain in this room very long."  Fear makes you tremble.

name: Main Courtyard - Center West
description: The review stand is to the north, and a tier of seats for visitors and observers is to the northwest.  On the north wall of the castle you can see a silk banner with the crest of Rutger on it.  The banner is in black edged with silver trim.  The troops who assemble here also wear black uniforms or armor with silver piping and silver accessories, colors of Lyanden Castle.

name: Main Courtyard - Northwest Corner
description: There are seats arranged in tiers here, and a place for a band to play as the troops assemble for inspection.  The ladies of the castle mostly come here to show off their silks and jewelry, and the noblemen come here to show off their ladies.  the squad leaders are here just to show off the troops.

name: Main Courtyard - Southwest Corner
description: There is a ramp here that leads up to the battlements on the west side of of the Tower Castle over the front gates.  The castle, built on the steep side of a mountain, needs to be defended from only the west side.  The ramp is wide and looks like a lot of troops could be moved quickly over it.

name: Center Courtyard
description: A reflecting pool takes up most of the center area of the courtyard.  There are several statues around the edge and in the center, and together they tell the story of the struggle between the twins, Prince Rutger and Prince Ragnar, for the crown of their dead father, King Lyanden.

name: Main Courtyard - Center North
description: A tall statue and several smaller ones are arranged in a fashion to tell the story of how Rutger and Ragnar, twin sons of King Lyanden, have both proclaimed themselves as the rightful successor to the crown.  Since no one knows which of them was born first there is no way to settle the dispute by law.  Many of the inhabitants of the land have taken sides, and there is rumor of war soon.

name: Main Courtyard - North
description: Several small doors and one great door are located in the north wall of the castle.  To the south is the central courtyard where the young warriors  often go before taking up battle.  There is a reflecting pool there that some say has magical powers of healing.

name: Main Courtyard - Center South
description: The reflecting pool to the north is a quiet place where some of the older knights occasionally counsel the younger ones.  The pool is known to have curative powers, and even the near-dead who have been brought to it have been restored to full health.  On the south side you see a heavy equipment storage area.

name: Main Courtyard - South
description: A lot of heavy battle equipment is in storage here.  There is a ramp leading up to the castle's battlements over to the northeast.  The equipment waits at the foot of the ramp, ready for use at the sound of the alarm trumpets. A fire is kept burning at all times, and cauldrons of oil are bubbling, constantly in readiness.

name: Main Courtyard - Center East
description: To the west is a beautiful reflecting pool with large statues surrounding it.  This area is a small garden filled with lush ferns and exotic plants,  providing a nice setting to observe the pool in the center of the courtyard.

name: Northeast Courtyard/Franchot Tunnel Intersection
description: The lower class members of the fighting forces are restricted from this area, and only castle's troop commanders and knights are allowed to be here.  The tunnel leads into the interior of the castle, and to the quarters of one of Prince Rutger's most loyal friends, Franchot the paladin.

name: Main Courtyard/Apstone Tunnel Intersection
description: The tunnel you see leads to the eastern interior of the castle.  The chief   wizard of the castle, Apstone, maintains quarters just off the north side of the tunnel.  South of you are the castle stables, where most of the war horses are kept.  There are other steeds and mounts there as well.

name: Main Courtyard - East
description: The open courtyard is to the west, but this part is under a parapet which extends a considerable distance overhead.  There are many small and locked doors along here.  Some are used for storage, others are private apartments of some of the people who live in the castle.

name: Franchot Tunnel
description: The old oak door here leads to the private apartment of one of the greatest paladins in the land, Commander Franchot.  Franchot is a life-long friend of Prince Rutger, and supports Rutger in his battle with Prince Ragnar for the throne at Lyanden Castle in Oceancrest.

name: Apstone Tunnel
description: Apstone, one of the oldest wizards in the entire land, has chosen the side of Prince Rutger.  Apstone is almost alone in his decision, as most of the mages and wizards who live in the kingdom have decided to stay neutral in the struggle between the twin sons of King Lyanden.  The door you see leads to his apartments.

name: Griffon's Heart Pub
description: This place is the favorite drinking spot for the lower level members of the castle's fighting men and the female chamber maids who clean the castle's rooms.  The low ceiling and dim light makes it hard to see very far, and the room apparently stretches into darkness in a number of directions.  You hear a lot of laughter from the dark corners.

name: Bombardier's Quarters
description: The bombardiers are specially trained to man the heavy equipment stationed on the upper battlements.  These fighters handle the catapults and boil the oil which gets poured over the side in case the castle is attacked.

name: Servant's Stairwell
description: You are on the ground floor, but since the stairs appear to spiral both up and down there must be rooms or dungeons in the lower regions too.

name: Servant's Stairwell
description: You can either go up or out the door, but there is nothing else here of interest.  The walls are heavy gray stone, and cold and clammy to the touch. The door does not look as though it has been opened in a long time.

name: Servant's Stairwell
description: You are on the second floor of the servant's stairwell in Castle Rutger. the second floor of the castle is almost exclusively offices and archives used in administrative work.  Its just amazing how much paperwork there is to running a castle of this side.

name: Servant's Stairwell
description: The third floor is where many of the high level warriors and adventurers who have pledged their loyalty to Rutger have taken residence.  There are storage rooms available for those who spend little time in the castle as  well.  There is a window here, where you can the countryside to the west of the castle.  You seem to be very high in the air, as you look out.

name: Servant's Stairwell
description: Prince Rutger and his family maintain quarters on this floor, and this is the servant's entry to the residence.  There is a ladder which continues to the roof where the battlements are located.

name: Tower Castle Roof Battlements
description: There are archery nooks and catapult launching ramps along here, and in the distance there is a hot oil station.  A huge sled of rocks, held in place by a net, stands nearby.  Looks like the fighting forces are ready for any kind of a siege.

name: Thoto's Emporium
description: Thoto the gnome opened this shop the day the room was completed when the castle was built.  He has been in business here for a very long time, and doesn't mind cheating you out of a month's pay.  No guarantees with anything you purchase in here.

name: Tubold's Blacksmith Shop
description: Smoke from the fires which burn eternally in here have blackened the walls and the ceiling.  Around a short wall you can hear the clang of a heavy hammer, and can feel the heat of the forge.

name: Healing Room
description: A healing mage seems to be attending to those in need, and moves about the room taking care of the sick.  If you are in need of anything, you should talk to the mage in the white gown.

name: Thixel and Thortle's Pawn Shop
description: Everywhere you look are piles of goods and strange items which have been left here to be redeemed later.  Thixel and Thortle, twin sons of Thoto, don't really care about cleaning this place up, but they know exactly where everything is.  They will give you about half of what something is actually worth.  Are you sure you want to do business with them?

name: Castle Rutger Library
description: Evidently the people who live here in the castle don't do much reading, as there is a heavy coat of dust everywhere.  The dust is so heavy you  cannot read the titles of the books and manuscripts stored here.

name: Knight's Chapel
description: Sir Anton Therix, before his rise to sainthood, was known for his dedication to a single-minded purpose of retrieving a lost glove belonging to his king. His entire life was devoted to the quest, and after his death he was much admired for such a quality.  He never did find the glove.

name: Weather Wizard's Climate Control Room
description: A transparent globe floats in the center of the room, with a miniature landscape of the country surrounding The Tower Castle of Prince Rutger inside it.  There are dials and controls under the globe, and several are marked with such words as Rain, Storm, Wind, and Lightning.  A stack of black wands are arranged near the door.

name: Grand Assembly Hall
description: There are rows and rows of feasting tables along the side, but the center of the room is clear.  The floor is a single piece of highly polished black onyx, which gives the room a quality of being in the depths of space.  Great banners and tapistries hang on the walls, and flags and pennants hang from the ceiling.  A golden balcony overhangs the room on the north side, between two sweeping stairways that ascend on either side.

name: Stairway of the Nobles
description: This is the stairway used by the castle's nobility. Prince Rutger occasionally joins his friends who reside on the third level and comes down this way, but he generally descends the east stairway which is reserved for the royal family.  Immediately to the south you can see the Grand Assembly.  On the east side, you see the room where the fallen may   rescind their pledge to Prince Rutger.

name: Royal Stairway
description: Rutger seldom invites guests to use this stairway, preferring instead to use the Stairway of the Nobles on the north side of the balcony when he is with someone.  Looking west you can see the golden door leading to the pledge room.  The Grand Assembly Hall is south of you.

name: Prayer Room
description: You are advised to consider carefully before you rescind your pledge to Prince Rutger.  This room has been set aside so that you may seek devine guidance concerning the choice you are about to make, and so you may be  sure it is the correct one.  If you decide to renounce your loyalty, enter the small docket wreathed in black velvet.  Prince Rutger will observe.

name: Benediction Room
description: If you are seeking to pledge your loyalty to Prince Rutger, you must first read the covenant you see on the altar before you.  If you still wish to join Rutger's Keep, climb the steps to the balcony above where you will find Prince Rutger waiting to receive you.

name: Golden Balcony
description: You are about to become one of Rutger's chosen warriors and the assembly below waits in hushed silence for your pledge.  Prince Rutger stands beside you, and you may speak to him before agreeing to the covenant you have read.

name: Rutger's Docket
description: A hooded and masked cleric stands with you as you wait to rescind your  pledge to Prince Rutger.  Speak only to him, as the Prince will not respond to one who has turned his face from him.  The cleric will tell you the words of the ritual which you must speak.  The people assembled on the floor wait silently for you to reveal your shame.

name: Stairway of the Nobles
description: A dreary and narrow hallway leads to several little offices along here. These are the administrative offices of the castle, where clerks maintain files and records.  Nothing ever gets lost here, and the archives are filled to overflowing, but the clerks know where every piece of paper is located.

name: Stairway of the Nobles
description: A long hallway runs east and west, and several closed doors appear to have access here.  These are the apartments of some of Rutger's closest friends, adventurers who have pledged their loyalty to him.  Along the  hall you see oil paintings and banners of some of the residents.

name: Stairway of the Nobles
description: The hallway you see leads to the family chambers and apartments of Prince Rutger, master of this Tower Castle.  There are several doors and open rooms on the south side of the hallway, and it looks like another short stairway leads to the roof.  A secretary's desk blocks your entry to the hallway.

name: Hallway of the Nobles
description: the doors you see lead to the apartments of some of the finest adventurers in the Land of Mordor.  All of them have distinguished themselves in battle against the forces of Ragnar, and have earned their positions here.

name: Royal Stairway
description: There is a hallway going west which seems to be bustling with clerks and accountants, all of them busy with the the paperwork of the castle.  Most people never consider how much administrative work is associated with the workings of a castle, but just stop one of these clerks, and you will see just how upset he can become over being delayed in his work.

name: Royal Stairway
description: The short eastern hallway is reserved for the noble friends of the Prince. Only the highest level and most trustworthy of Rutger's friends are allowed to take chambers in this part of the castle.

name: Top of the Royal Stairway
description: Several doors are open which apparently lead to the family quarters of the Prince.  There is also a metal door with a bar across it, and another door from which you hear the sounds of guards.  Could this be the castle's fabled vault?  Rutger is reported to have fabulous wealth.

name: Rutger's Vault
description: You are in one of the most famous vaults in all the kingdom.  Prince Rutger is rumored to have one of the most fabulous collections of treasure ever assembled in any kingdom.  Perhaps the only other person to be so wealthy is Rutger's brother, Prince Ragnar.

name: Guard Station
description: This particular station is for the elite personal guards who constantly surround Prince Rutger.  A rack on the wall is filled with hand weapons, and in the center of the room is a table with a map of the castle spread out on it.  There is a lot of activity in here.

name: Rutger's Hallway
description: Several doors along here open to plush rooms which are the main residence for Prince Rutger's family.  To the west is a secretary's desk at the head of the noble's stairway, and to the east you see a guard station and a metal door.  Sweet smelling candles light the hallway along here.

name: Courtyard Pool
description: Statues around you are arranged in an orderly fashion to tell the story of the twin sons born to King Lyanden at Lyanden Castle.  The midwife died under mysterious circumstances shortly after their births, and thereby was lost the order of birth between Ragnar and Rutger.  Now no one knows which is the elder of the brothers, nor which is the rightful successor to the  throne at Lyanden Court.

name: Night Entry Chamber
description: The metal door on the west wall is only used at night when the castle's main gates are closed.  Many beasts and vile things prowl the night, so its very dangerous to go out after dark, but for those who insist, the metal door is available.

name: Vertinio's Apothecary Shoppe
description: you may purchase a varity of potions, balms, and other items of magic here. There is a list available for customers.

name: Castle Ragnar Chapel
description: You are in a quiet littel chapel, west of a simple altar. There is a smell of incense in the air, and warm candles light statues along the side of the chapel.  Severl paladins pray quietly near the altar, and shrouded monks move silently about the room.

name: Vestuary
description: Long black robes hang on hooks, and there are bibles and hymnals near a  north door.  The door seems to be slightyl ajar.  A narrow stairway leads to the pulpit above the altar.  There are ropes hanging here, and as you look up, you see moving shadows in the bell tower above.

name: Clerical Supply Room
description: As you look around, you realize this place is exactly what the name says. There are bibles, hymnals, prayer shawls, strings of beads, icons and and a variety of cassocks and albs on hangers.  A small silver keg appears to hold ceremonial wine, and there are a lot of small silver cups nearby. Looks like the acolytes have been drinking the wine.  Ask the acolyte for a selection.  (type:  selection acolyte)

name: Hall of Heros
description: On either side is a raised dais.  A long line of enormous chairs sit side by side on each dais, and over each is a banner and a portrait.   Black      bunting covers an occasional picture, and a helmet and sword are in the chair there.  To the east is the throne room.  West leads to the courtyard.

name: Hall of Heros
description: Oil paintings of famous fighters and paladins are on the wall, each hung above a huge chair sitting on a raised dais.  The ceiling is so high above that birds fly about the room, nesting in crannies and niches.  The floor has a rich multi-hued oriental rug running the length of the hall.  To the east is the throne room of Prince Ragnar.

name: Hall of Heros
description: You are at eastern end of the grand hall, at an intersection.  To the east there are a pair of massive doors leading to the throne room.  The hall to the west is the famous Hall of Heros.  Another smaller hallway runs   north and south from here.

name: Heraldry Hall
description: Shields and coats-of-arms hang on every square centimeter of the walls, identifying famous clans and families.  Sweet smelling torchs line the way, providing a warm light.

name: Broad Hallway
description: This hallway serves as a throughfare for the castle's clerical personnel who work in offices further south.  The dining hall is north of here, through Heraldry Hall.  Much further north is the famed Ladie's Walk.  Immediately south is the library and the music room.

name: Prince Ragnar's Waiting Room
description: In the center of the room is a small table with a single parchment on it. The parchment is a covenant between you and Ragnar if you choose to honor it.  A priest and a palidin stand nearby, ready to witness your oath of fealty to the realm.  To pledge, you must step to the south, where you  will be given a last chance to decide this important step in your life.

name: Prince Ragnar's Throne Room
description: The floor is glass, covering an immense bottomless chasm, and a brilliant light falls on a bejeweled golden throne floating in the center of the room. No light at all falls on the occupant of the throne, and all you can see is an inky blackness where Ragnar is reputed to sit.   You are invited to become a member of Ragnar's Keep.

name: The Throne of Prince Ragnar
description: There is a multitude of people dressed in their finest garments and armor surrounding the throne.  They have pledged their loyalty to this Prince. You may speak to Ragnar.

name: Heraldry Hall
description: The hallway is wide, clean and well lighted.  Heraldic banners cover the the walls, each with its distinctive markings and colors.  Famous families from generations back have placed their identifying flags here.  At one time, this castle was the summer palace for the Lyanden royal family and it was known for its pomp and ceremonies.  All royal families participated.

name: Heraldry Hall
description: The hall is wide and grand to the south, but becomes smaller going north. The smaller hallway to the north leads to private chambers and bedrooms. Beyond the apartments is the famed Ladies Walk.

name: Private Chambers Hallway
description: There are many private apartments along this hallway.  High level members  of the royal court make their homes here.

name: Private Chambers Hallway
description: the long hallway has a great many closed doors, some with light under them, and others quite dark.  Voices occasionally drift from the rooms.  To the is the famed Heraldry Hallway.

name: Private Chambers Hallway
description: there are several door and alcoves along the way, but almost all of them are closed.  The candles high on the stone walls give off a sweet smell from the burning incense.

name: De-registration Room
description: This is a solemn moment, as you wait to rescind your pledge to Prince Ragnar. The Prince wants only unwavering loyalty, and if you feel you can no longer give that, then in a moment you will be free to leave.  But first, you must remove your name from the Registry of Champions.  Speak to the cowled clerk, and he will tell you the proper way to rescind your pledge.  Prince Ragnar waits beside the clerk.

name: Prayer Room
description: Before making a pledge, or deciding to rescind a pledge, a warrior should   seek devine guidance and advice.  If you still wish to rescind the pledge you made to Prince Ragnar, you should go through the black door.  If you desire to pledge, please enter the throne room.

name: Animal Training Compound Gate
description: Looking inside, you see several separate areas where different animals are kept and trained.  To the west is the path leading to the road which runs around the village of Brownhaven.  Overhead, you can see several copper dragons high in the air with riders on their backs.  The riders seem to be naked and are carrying long lances, which glint in the light.

name: Training Compound
description: A white sign post, with several wooden signs nailed to it, points in four directions.  To the east is the copper dragon training area, north is the pegasus grounds, and south takes you to the administration building.  To the west is the gate where you may go out to the road.

name: Copper Dragon Training Compound
description: Copper dragons are easily trained to accept a rider, and the Brownhaven Guards, who form the village's militia, have commissioned the administration here to do just that.  The skies are full of monsters and the guards must constantly patrol in order to keep some hapless citizen from being plucked from the streets and eaten.  Close aerial combat is not advisable, so the dragons are fitted with a long lance mounted on the saddle for the rider's use.  This place is heavily guarded.

name: Copper Pits - First Level
description: The pits are carefully guarded by Brownhaven guards to keep just anyone from riding the beautiful copper dragons who live it the pits below.  Right now, they are probably sleeping on duty, but you can see an alarm rigged on the entrance to the pits below.  If you want to joy ride a dragon, you might have to fight for the privilege.

name: Copper Pits - Second Level
description: Milling about you are dragons in various shades and hues of copper.  Many are already saddled, and they all look eager to fly.  One of the dragons snuffles at your shoulder, apparently wanting you to mount her.  A light breeze flutters a windsock on a tall staff nearby.

name: Copper Pits - Mounted on a Dragon
description: There is a light leather harness, securely fastened to a saddle , and a gleaming lance set in its socket at your side.  On the other side of you is a saddle bag and a small shield.  Mounted on the saddle pummel is a direction indicator.  Right now, it reads:  0.0.0.0.0

name: Sky Over Brownhaven Village
description: Your direction indicator says you are 50 meters up, and over the dragon's home pit.  The cardinal directions on the pummel indicator are north, east, south and west.  All of them presently read zero.  Dragons always fly in a straight line if you urge them forward.  You are headed north.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: A road makes it way from the west, and travelers appear in the distance. to the south are the foothills of the great Nartiz moutains.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: A little to the east is the great Baldywyne River, which flows through  the village.  The source must be somewhere to the north, across the Gotland Glenn.  To the east is the Kista Forest.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
