description: High winds can greatly increase the speed of the dragon's flight, and the upper air has some some air streams that can more than quadruple the the dragon's normal flight ability.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: You can see farmers working in their fields, and children playing in farm yards.  the fields look like there will be a bountiful crop this year.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: The copper dragon swoops down toward the old caravan road to get a better look at the pack train of horses, mules, camels, llamas, and other exotic creatures.  Startled faces look up as you drop low toward them.  They seem to be carrying a rich variety of trade goods.  One group of camels seem to be particularly well guarded.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: Farms are well tended in this area, and the soil is very rich.  The homes are thatched-roof single story dwellings.  The thatch  comes from  the grasslands to the east.

name: Rain Clouds
description: You can no longer see where the dragon is going, so all you can do is hope that she can see where she's going.  You can't even see the ground anymore.

name: Dark Skies
description: Dragons don't really mind the dark, but they definitely do not like water. You can feel the big beast start to twitch as you fly ever deeper into the rain.  It might be better to return to nicer weather.

name: Open Sky
description: To the west there is a rain storm brewing, but that is also the way to  Vallenda Pass, which traverses the lowlands between Mount Aphinix on the north, and the Nartiz Mountain Range on the south.  Oceancrest and the  Respitial Sea is to the west.

name: Open Sky
description: From time to time there have been reports of a floating city, which may or  may not be true.  As you scan the skies, you note there is seldom a long, clear patch of open air, but instead there are lots of clouds everywhere. If there is such a thing as a floating city, it could easily stay hidden.

name: Light Cloudy Sky
description: The clouds obscure your view of the ground, but its patchy and you will soon be out of the them.  The clouds seems to be drifting with the prevailing winds, which are coming from the west.

name: Open Sky
description: The northern cliffs are much too high for your steed to fly over, so you will have to avoid them.  You can fly higher, however, if you want a better look at the sheer rock face coming down from the mountain.  To the east it looks like the southern face of Mount Aphinix has a more steep slope to it.  A long way to the west, there is a jutting shoulder of the high cliffs, and you will probably have to turn south.

name: Dark Rain Clouds
description: It's impossible to see the direction indicator, so you cannot tell which way to steer the great dragon you are riding.  It feels like the dragon is swooping, and at times is gaining a lot of elevation, and other times is losing it.  Ever wonder how high a dragon can fly?

name: Above the Rain Clouds
description: you can no longer see the ground because of the dark clouds below you. At least, however, you can see your direction indicator, and should be able to find your way back to Brownhaven.  Now if you can only find a hole in the clouds, so you can go down a bit lower to get your bearings.

name: Blue Skies
description: Down below you can see trees growing along the banks of a small river. A well traveled road follows the river to the east and west, eventually making its way to the village of Brownhaven.  The road goes to Vallenda  in the west.

name: Breezy Skies
description: To the north is the mysterious Mount Aphinix, where a clan of trolls live. The mountain extends to the south, but you have to look west to see that. The Nartiz Mountains and Mount Aphinix almost merge, forming the Vallenda pass, which runs east to west.

name: Blue Skies
description: The pass is narrow a bit to the west, with a high bluff overlooking the caravan trail.  There are large boulders atop the cliff, poised like huge birds of prey.  They almost look like they were deliberately placed there.

name: Blue Skies
description: There are clouds on either side of you, but it looks like you can fly between them with no trouble.  Down below you can see the caravan road which leads east and west.  There is a terrible waste land far to the west, and caravans often have troubles there.

name: Blue Skies
description: The mountain is considered to be the domain of a clan of blood thirsty trolls, and the dragons have been trained to not fly there, lest it anger the trolls and another long war erupts between the people of Brownhaven and the mountain trolls.  To the west is the Nartiz Mountain Range, just over  some low hills.  South of you is the Vallenda Pass, which connects Gotland Glenn with the Vallenda Plains.

name: Above the Rain Clouds
description: A small hole in the clouds allows you to see the ground below, but it's scudding fast, and it may disappear soon.  The dark clouds are starting  to look even darker to the west.

name: Rain Storm
description: You can't see anything on the ground, nor can you see anything in the sky around you.  The copper dragon is getting uneasy in the rain storm, and you can tell she wants to get out of it.

name: Dark and Cloudy Skies
description: You can turn left or right, or even fly forward, but the trouble is, if you turn left or right for too long, you start to go in circles.  And if you fly forward, how can you tell how much drift is occuring?  Flying blind is a terrible way to try to get anywhere.

name: Open Skies Over Nartiz Hills
description: There are wooded foothills below you, and from time to time you see tiny villages or lone cottages.  This area is known for its large number of  open gold and silver mines.  Although this part of the sky is clear, there are a lot of clouds over the entire area.

name: Warm Air
description: There are rolling grasslands for as far as the eye can see.  The warm air causes a thermal lift, and the dragon soars a bit higher.  Far to the east is the Baldywyne.

name: Skies Over Gotland Glenn
description: The great Gotland Glen is a vast grassland, home to a number of wierd and wonderful animals and sentient beings.  There is reputed to be an entire underground city built by burrowing mole people down there.

name: Cloudy Sky
description: The skies are getting darker around you, especially to the east.  Far in the distance to the north, you can see the top of a single mountain poking through the clouds.  The base is obscured with fog and clouds.

name: Cloudy Skies
description: You cannot see through the clouds, but your direction indicator is still visible.  It's about the only thing you can see, except the great dragon  you are riding.

name: Light Clouds
description: Off to the east is a great river, flowing south towards the Gotland Glenn. directly below is a vast grassland, which gently rises to the north.

name: Open Skies
description: There is a cold and gray sky to the west.  It might be best to turn away from it.  Even your dragon seems a little nervous about the weather in  that direction.

name: Gray Skies
description: the ground below is rather normal looking, without much to distinguish it. There are trees dotted across rolling hills, and a small creek which follows the lowest part of the terrain.  Several game trails can be seen crossing each other, each going in hap-hazard directions.

name: Skies Over Gotland Glenn
description: Brownhaven is far to the west, and there is nothing but grassland beneath you.  There are a lot of clouds in the skies around you, and dragons lose their sense of direction when flying in bad weather.

name: Sky Over Gotland Glenn Creek
description: In the distance you see mounds of earth around large holes in the earth. Stories have been told by wandering bards of a strange mole-like people who live beneath the ground somewhere on the grassy Gotland Glen.

name: Sky Over Gotland Glenn Creek
description: The creek evidently splits off from the Baldywyne, and takes a route more towards the southeast, in the direction of the city of Kista, where the beautiful towers are located.   The great copper dragon beneath you flies effortlessly.

name: Light Clouds Over Gotland Glenn
description: To the east is a sparkling river which flows to the south across the vast Gotland Glenn.  There are light clouds in that direction, and if you don't want to get lost in them, you could turn away, or perhaps fly higher.  To the north there is a dark mountain range.

name: Open Skies
description: Far to the south there is an eery dark storm, which seems to be localized over a black castle.  Looking down, you can see the great oaken forest which stretches for vast distances in all directions.

name: Cloudy Skies
description: You can feel the great dragon veering away from any turns to the east. Below you are valleys and streams which cut through the oaks and pines of the Kista Forest.  There doesn't seem to be anything to the east but more of the same, while somewhere to the north is the city of Kista.

name: Fog Bank
description: It looks like a hard left may take you back to where you entered this blanket of wetness.  The fog is not so thick in that direction.  Directly ahead is the thickest and densest part of the fog.

name: Fog Bank
description: You can still feel the might muscles of the copper dragon as she beats her wings in a rythmic slowness, but it's really hard to discern movement or that you are actually flying.  With luck the dragon will find her way out of this pretty soon.

name: Fog Bank
description: There's nothing but a whiteness all around you, and at times it's so dense you cannot even see the dragon on which you are mounted.  However, if you let the dragon find his own way out, it might be a little faster than you trying to do it.

name: Skies West of Kista
description: Down below, you can see where the grasslands of the Gotland Glen pushes up against the forest of Kista.  The grassland makes a gentle but consant rise to the south, where more and more trees appear, and become the  famous Kista Forest.  The towers of the city glint like jewels in the distance, giving it a fairytale quality.

name: Nartiz Tor
description: A rocky tor, part of the Nartiz Mountain Range, juts north toward the village of Brownhaven.  You will have to climb higher to stay above the hot, sharp rocks you see below.  Not much vegetation down there, and you see very little animal life.  To the east however, you can see the great Kista Forest, which is south of the beautiful city of Kista.

name: Skies Over Brownhaven
description: There is a hot and arid region slightly to the south.  Geothermal activity has made the southern area a hellish place to exist.  Looking east or west however, shows a green and lush landscape.

name: Cloudy Sky
description: The hillsides below you are quite wild and rugged, and would be difficult for travelers.   There doesn't seem to be any level places at all.  The  gorge is dark and covered in an evil fog.

name: Open Sky
description: You cannot fly any further to the north because of the sheer rock wall in that direction.  The upper reaches of the rock face is covered in dark clouds, making it impossible to see how high it goes.  It looks like there might be a mine entrance directly below you.

name: Turbulent Air
description: Toward the west is the Vallenda Pass, located between two great mountain ranges to the south and to the north.  Much further to the west is the Vallenda Plains, a strange land where a great waste land exists.  To the east there are several major villages and towns, and the city of Kista.

name: Misty Air
description: The sheer rock face of the mountain stops you from going north. Clouds  are near the top of the mountains, and a jumble of rocks lies below. There seems to be a mine entrance further east.

name: High Over Baldywyne River
description: The great river below you rushes from the mouth of the Tasletek Gorge, and rolls south towards the Gotland Glenn.  Eventually, it will pass through the village of Brownhaven on its way to the grand city of Rhivlintz.  From there, it will empty into the Gulf of Tarquin.

name: Open Sky
description: The open sky is dotted with clouds, and occasionally there is fog or rain. Dragons don't normally like to fly in inclement weather, because they get lost so easily.  If you fly into a cloud, there's no telling where you might wind up.  The winds aloft can often carry you miles off course, if you fly that high.

name: Black Skies
description: the dragon turns his head and looks at you questioningly, but keeps flying. Since you can no longer see the ground, it's hard to get your bearings. It hasn't happened very often, but copper dragons have been known to crash when they were flying blind.  Perhaps you should turn back, if you know where back is.  You do, don't you?

name: Rain Squall
description: Dragons don't really like the rain, you know.  perhaps you should consider trying to find a way out of the bad weather.

name: Turbulent Air
description: To the west is the Vallenda Pass, which provides a caravan trail for   commerce between the seaport at Oceancrest and the inland towns and cities. On the south side of the pass is the Nartiz Mountain Range, while to the north is the mountain home of a clan of trolls.

name: Turbulent Airways
description: The turbulent air makes it difficult to hold on and scan the skies at the same time.  There have been reports of griffons in this area of the Vallenda Pass.  Right now would not be a good time to meet one of them.

name: Foggy Skies
description: You can no longer see your direction indicator, and cannot tell which way is north.  You might have to let the great beast under you find its head. If you start turning, no telling where you might wind up, but of course as soon as you can see your direction indicator again, you will be all right.

name: Fluffy White Clouds
description: It's like being inside a wet marshmallow, and you can't see a thing. It's hard to determine just how far a left or right turn will take you, and often when you come out of a cloud, you are many kilometers from where you think you should be.

name: Heavy Cloud Layer
description: The dark clouds around you occasionally part to allow you to see your direction indicator.  Last time you looked, you were a long way from  the spot where you entered the cloud bank.

name: Dark Clouds
description: The dark clouds turn to an even darker looking fog down below in the gorge. From time to time, through patches in the terrible mist you can see the dark river and sharp rocks.  The end of the gorge is to the southeast.

name: Damp Fog
description: The fog itself seems to have an evil life force, and even your fearless dragon is a little reluctant to fly any closer to it.  You can continue in an east-west direction, but you can no longer fly to the north.

name: Light Cloud Layer
description: The wind is picking up, and it's hard to tell where the dragon is being blown.  You might be many kilometers from where you entered the clouds.

name: Very light Clouds
description: Actually, the light filtering through makes the clouds look like cotton candy, but the similarity ends there.  You can sense the unease of the great dragon between your legs everytime you enter these forbidding areas.

name: Skies Over Kista Forest
description: The sky to the west is heavy clouds, and probably would hide your position indicator if you flew in there.  The forest appears to be unbroken for vast distances, except to the south, where a small, black castle sits alone in  the forest, surrounded by a moat.

name: Sky Over the Kista Forest
description: Nothing but trees, for as far as you can see.  From this height, it's like  a green carpet covering the land.  From time-to-time, there is another rider in the sky.  He seems to be riding a copper dragon also, but is pretty far away, and may not see you.

name: Skies Over Kista Forest
description: The great forest seems to go on and on, but somewhere to the north is the city of Kista.  The beautiful towers at Kista are known throughout the land.  Looking south, there is a solitary break in the forest where a black castle, with a single turreted tower, stands.

name: Light Rain Over Kista Forest
description: the rain splatters and collects to run down the copper platelets on the great dragon beneath you.  She seems to have picked up a little speed, perhaps to get out of this weather.  Maybe you should let her pick the way, until you can see where you are.

name: Skies Over Kista Forest
description: The beautiful Kista Forest spreads out below you, stretching for as far as you can see.  In the skies to the east, you occasionally catch a glimpse of a copper flash in the clouds.  There are other riders in the air, but wild copper dragons also inhabit this area.

name: Over Lake Kista Shores
description: You are near the western shore of the lake, where you can see a pier and several boats.  The pines, cedar and oaks come almost to the water's edge. The pier seems to have some activity, and a small number of cabins are near its end.  South is a dark storm.

name: Violent Upper Winds
description: Your air speed has picked up tremendously, and you are being buffeted and tossed in all directions.  Below you, the Gotland Glen rushes by at a terrible rate.

name: Over Western Lake Kista
description: The copper dragon you are riding signals she would like a drink, and would like to descend.  You are at the eastern limit of how far the dragon will fly, and she normally rests here before returning to Brownhaven.

name: Turbulent Air
description: Further to the south the low foothills give way to the jagged Nartiz Mountains.  The mountains are snow covered at their peaks, and cloud cover lies in layers all the way to the jagged tops.  Looking west, there is a pass that seems to get very narrow, between the northern Nartiz and the southern face of Mount Aphinix.

name: Lake Kista Rest Area
description: Half buried in the snow-white sand is the hilt of a blade, different from any you have ever seen before.  The water's edge is to the south, and in the distance further south you can see the city of Kista.

name: Lake Kista Sandy Beach
description: Half buried in the snow-white sand is the hilt of a blade, different from any you have ever seen before.  The water's edge is to the south, and in the distance further south you can see the city of Kista.

name: Nartiz Ror
description: The area below is hot and covered with jagged rocks, and there is no ground cover.  The only life you see are a few reptiles.  Hard to determine how big they are from this height, from the back of a dragon.  Brownhaven is  to the north.

name: Apothecary
description: Did you ever wonder what might happen if you mixed a lot of different chemicals together, applied an intense heat over a prolonged time, and then had hundreds of magic spells cast in the vicinity of the cooking mess?  Well, that's exactly what happened a couple of hundred years ago during the great battle that occurred here.

name: Castle Jail
description: This room is absolutely bare, and was once used as the castle's jail. There is an iron door which is locked, and steps descending into the inky blackness below.  Nothing else is here, except a bad feeling and  a horrible stench coming from below.

name: Dumbwaiter Shaft
description: Evidently this was the means of delivering food to somewhere deep down in the depths of the castle.  You might be able to go down there, but the shaft is so small you could never do it with all of the equipment you have with you.  There is a terrible stench coming from down there.

name: Dumbwaiter Shaft
description: There is an almost overpowering stench coming from below, and the shaft is so small it feels like you can barely wriggle through it.

name: Dumbwaiter Shaft
description: This shaft is very small, and the only way you can go up is without any of the equipment you normally carry.  There is a green slime covering the floor, and it might not be a good idea to touch it.

name: Mage's Quarters
description: When the Witch murdered the duke and his family, the mages who lived here tried to help, but the witch and her brother were just too powerful. Although they could not kill the mages, they were able to change their shapes and imprison them here in altered form.  If you stay here in the castle long enough, you will occasionally hear whispers and crying.  Be not afraid of them, but you cannot help them.  They are truly lost.

name: Quarters of Galgorith
description: It was Silventh himself who managed to cast a complicated spell on Galgorith. Now, the young mage who had such great promise is an immortal in cat form, forever hunting the mice in this tower.

name: Rothchild's Chambers
description: His fate was sealed when he came face to face with the Witch of Kayleigh, and she turned him into living stone.  Only the most powerful of magic can cancel that spell, and none today know the spell.  It may have been lost forever when the books and other treasures in this room were burned.

name: Tinneya's Quarters
description: Long ago she tried to help the Duke of Kayleigh to fight off the powerful witch who invaded this castle, but she was forever turned into a mouse, doomed to run throughout the ruins.   It was she who placed the tempest over the castle, in an attempt to put out the flames.  Galgorith hunts her.

name: Dark Tempest Over Castle Kayleigh
description: From this height you can see that only a single turreted tower remains standing in the fire-blackened ruin.  However, the stone deck of the tower looks quite sturdy, and big enough for the copper dragon to land.  Odd, but there's not a tree or bush within a mile of the old castle.  The moat is still there, but the drawbridge burned away long ago.  Looks like the only entrance is by air.

name: Castle Kayleigh Turret Deck
description: Long ago, the witch of Kayleigh, along with her brother, a warlock of considerable power in his own right, was imprisoned here.  It has been at least two hundred years since anyone has seen them, so the prison must be holding them.  A copper dragon with a black and silver saddle waits here.

name: Castle Kayleigh Tower
description: The stone is blackened from a long ago fire, and all the doors have turned to ashes.  Every portal seems to be open.  As you look over the side, you can see a seething, bubbling moat.  It appears to be filled with acid.

name: Castle Kayleigh Stairwell
description: Huge timbers, partially burned through, have fallen in to the center of the tower.  Down below are a number of archways going to the castle proper. a little way overhead you can see the open doorway to the turret deck. You have apparentley disturbed some rather large bats, which are circling above you.  Scrawled in the soot on the wall is the single word, "Silventh."

name: Castle Kayleigh Stairwell
description: The witch of Kayleigh and her brother terrorized the countryside around the city of Kista until the powerful Archmage Tellia Aphrotine found them here one night.  A five day battle ensued, and the castle was burned. Aphrotine was able to remove the power of flight from both the witch and  her brother, and they have been imprisoned here ever since.

name: Castle Kayleigh's Main Floor
description: Dark and forbidding archways lead to old hallways and forgotten rooms. A stone stairway spirals around the tower, leading to the roof.   Everywhere you look, you see fire damage.  The fire must have been very intense, as even the metal hand rail has melted into a grotesque pile of sludge.

name: East Hallway
description: A lot of structural damage occurred here during the battle between the Archmage Tellia Aphrotine and the two dark powers that lived here.  One part of the wall has collapsed, and ceiling beams hang at odd angles, casting deep shadows.  A low wail can be heard down the hall.

name: South Hallway
description: This was actually the feasting hall where the duke's men joined him around his table.  Many were the parties that lasted till dawn in this room after a successful hunt in the forest of Kista.  It was in this very hall that the Witch murdered the duke and his family.  Now it is ashes.

name: West Hall
description: This is the hall of nobility, which leads to the private quarters of long  dead royalty.  The scorched hallway is a sad reminder of glorious days of past ages.  After the Witch made this her home, she brought in pigs to keep in the royal bedchambers, as an insult to the family.  Now, there are pig  skeletons littering the floor.

name: North Hall
description: Before the Witch of Kayleigh and her brother drove out the legitimate owners of the castle, this hallway was where the Duke's banners were proudly hung. There are three dark and musty rooms on the west side of the hall.

name: North Hall
description: The walls, once so proudly draped with the castle's banners, now are covered with dark soot.  There are footprints on the floor, and strangely, they seem quite fresh.  There is a hollow echo of your own footsteps.

name: North Wall
description: You may continue around the perimeter of the castle, or take the south hallway to the castle's center court.  You would think this place would  be deathly quiet, but there's an odd moaning sound drifting through the hallways.  Occasionally, it seems to turn into a low cackle.

name: Broken East Wall
description: A small wooden door, the only one you have seen that wasn't burned, is on  the inside wall.  The door is either locked or wedged, but it's impossible to open.  there might be a place to climb in, however, considering the broken area of the inside wall.

name: North Castle Concourse
description: An expansive archway leads to the ruined remains of the castle's library. Evidently, the fire didn't do as much damage in there, but most of the destruction came from the collapsed ceiling.  The smell of acid from the moat outside is strong in here.  There must be an opening somewhere.

name: East Wall
description: The hallway branches to the north and south from here, or you can go east toward the castle's main courtyard, where most of the castle activity took place during a happier time.  The Witch of Kayleigh murdered the duke who once owned this castle, and drove his followers into the forest.

name: East Wall
description: A large water basin is set into the wall, and a clay pipe pours water into it.  There is a face carved behind the clay pipe, and it looks like a gargoyle with its tongue out.  The hallway continues to the northeast  and the southwest.

name: Collapsed Concourse
description: A gentle rush of air comes from the broken wall, and you can see the hellish acid filled moat outside.  There is no apparent way across it, as the draw- bridge was burned during the battle.  The acid makes your eyes water and your throat burn.  This is not a pleasant place.

name: Castle Kayleigh Library
description: From what you have seen, the fire raged throughout the hallways, but never in this room.  The ceiling fell in, making it difficult to move around in here, and the smoke covered everything with soot, but the tomes and books are still mostly undamaged on their shelves.

name: South Hall
description: Long tables once ran the length of the hall, and servants proudly brought fresh game and other foods from the kitchen.  Now the tables are charred timber under a collapsed ceiling.  The kitchen can be seen through the west doorway.  Not much damage seems to have occured in there.

name: Southern Castle Wall
description: Evidently the fire couldn't do much damage here, as it seems to be mostly stonework.  A wide, iron door with rusted hinges is set into the west wall. The hallway continues to the northeast and to the northwest, curving out of sight in both directions.  There is a great hallway to the north.

name: Kitchen
description: Although the rest of the castle is in total ruin, this kitchen appears untouched.  There is no damage in here at all.  Some smoke across the high ceiling is about all there is.  Pots, pans and other cooking equipment are still ready to be used.  A dumbwaiter shaft on the south wall is open.

name: South Castle Wall
description: Not much to see here but a few rats and spiders.  Something larger seems to be crouched in the darkness, but you can't quite make out what it is.

name: Servant's Quarters Hallway
description: The arches seem to go to several small private quarters, probably used by the castle's servants.  The southern hallway is rather narrow in this area.

name: Stone Stairway
description: Old graffiti has been scratched into the stones, untouched now for several hundred years.  Everywhere you have been in this ancient stone ediface has been covered in soot and ashes, but the steps here look to be frequently used.  It's impossible to see very far in either direction, as the steps twist in a tight pattern going down.

name: Stone Stairway
description: The stone is cold to the touch, and there isn't much light.  A flickering bluish light from below is the only light to see by.  An awful odor comes from below as well.  Make up your mind which way to go, but you only have two choices.  A scrawl on the wall says, "PREPARE...!"  Be careful of the slime you see moving slowly up the stairs.

name: Alcove Entry
description: The stairway goes up in a tight, twisting pattern, disappearing quickly. The room you can see has a flickering light coming from it, but you cannot see what is creating it.  There is a stinking smell coming from the floor, and a green slime covers the walls.

name: Witch's Antechamber
description: This tiny alcove offers you a dark spot to stand, and the shadows provide a place from which to observe the large room.  There seems to be movement in there, and a flickering fire.  The shadows move about, but you cannot see anyone other than several large and savage looking black cats.  From time to time, the single word, "Silventh" floats on the air, and a chuckle.

name: Chambers for Kaleigh and Silventh
description: In the center of the cluttered room you see an unholy, intense flame, ready to spring to full force any moment.  Blue tongues of heat simmer in  a silver brazier, and flickering shadows fill the room.  Great black cats stalk the room, or lie watchfully in favorite spots.  Some say the witch herself was responsible for the fire during the battle with Aphrotine.

name: West Wall
description: the room to the north appears to be an armory.  In the dim light you can see stacks of weapons and pieces of armor.  Any leather that might have been in  there was probably ruined by the fire.

name: Western Wall of Castle Kayleigh
description: Grime, dirt and ashes cover everything with a fine, black powder. The hallway is as quiet as a tomb, and your own footfall is muffled in the soft soot on the floor.

name: Castle Kayleigh Armory
description: There's nothing left here now but memories and ghosts.  stacks of equipment going to waste.  Weapons gleam in the dim light, never to be used again. When the duke was murdered, the entire keep was driven into the forest, and everything that wasn't burned was left behind.

name: West Wall
description: The interior wall is grimed and caked with soot.  Large, charred beams hang from the ceiling, and the wall has bulged in places, as though pushed out by a terrible force.  The hallway continues to the north and south, or you can go east toward the center courtyard.

name: Western Concourse
description: A few centuries ago, when this was a thriving and happy castle, this was the main concourse leading to the drawbridge at the front of the castle. The hall is wide enough that servants of the castle used it to bring wagons  this way for deliveries to the kitchen.

name: Western Hallway of Castle Kayleigh
description: Nothing has been in this section of the castle since that intense battle long ago.  Now it is simply a forlorn place for old ghosts.  To the east is the center courtyard, while to the west is the interior of the castle's outer wall.

name: Western Hall
description: Now, it is an ashen graveyard for the skeletons of swine. The Witch who who murdered the duke drove swine into the castle, and kept them in this great hall.

name: Western Concourse
description: Someone has written their name in the black soot on the wall, and a word. The word appears to be "Krakenvoch."  Is it also a name?  or a warning? There's more writing, but in a language you do not speak.

name: Skies above Galgorie Pond
description: The monster used to feed on lone travelers, and kept well hidden.  None knew of the monster's existance for a long time, but when he was was found out, Galgorie battled him for three days in the copse of trees below.   The beast lived in the nearby pond.

name: Grassy Knoll
description: This is often the resting place for riders of the copper dragons.  From here, you are within walking distance of Prince Ragnar's castle.  This spot is also a favorite for the dragons too, as they like to roll in the grass and wildflowers.  There is a quiet pond to the east, and a wooded copse to the south.  A copper dragon waits for your command.

name: Grassy Knoll
description: This is often the resting place for riders of the copper dragons.  From here, you are within walking distance of Prince Ragnar's castle.  This spot is also a favorite for the dragons too, as they like to roll in the grass and wildflowers.  There is a quiet pond to the east, and a wooded copse to the south.  A copper dragon waits to be mounted.

name: Ragnar's Road
description: A wonderful white castle, with spires and turrets and snapping banners and pennants is immediately south.  It looks to be a very busy place, with   many people coming and going.  The trees to the east are near a placid pond. Immediately north is a toll booth for the Lyanden Road.

name: Galgorie's Copse
description: Near the northern edge is a still pond and a grassy knoll.  A granite and ebony headstone marks the single grave at the foot of a giant oak tree.   It is the resting place of Galgorie.  Galgorie was mortally wounded in his battle with the monster from the pond, but since that day the beast has never been seen again.  Lyanden Road is west.

name: Galgorie Hill
description: Many were the onlookers that day, as Galgorie fought against the multi-armed  monster.  At the end of the three days, they saw the monster slide lifeless back into the pond from whence it came.  Galgorie lived for another day, cradled in the arms of his beloved.  He was buried nearby.

name: Galgorie's Pond
description: Although the water is quiet, it is also murky.  You cannot see very far through it, although nearby you see small bubbles rising and strands of waving waterweeds.  The bottom of the pond is littered with pieces of armor and bones.  The muddy bottom makes it difficult to move.

name: Blue Skies Over Vallenda Plains
description: Not far to the north is the western entrance to the pass between the dark mountains.  If you follow the pass to the east, you will eventually come to the village of Brownhaven, and farther east is the city of Kista.  To  the north is Prince Ragnar's castle.  The Vallenda Plains are west of here.

name: Light Clouds
description: You are also near the southwestern end of Mount Aphinix, which is the home of a clan of mountain trolls that occasionally try to invade surrounding cities.  Long ago, the village of brownhaven had a pitched battle with them, and almost wiped them out.  Now, they are mostly just a nuisance.

name: Sky Over Vallenda Pass
description: great mountains.  To the south is the Nartiz, while to the north you can see the Aphinix.   Farther west is the Vallenda Plains, and a badlands. The village of Brownhaven lies to the east.

name: Light Clouds
description: The sides of the pass are steep and rocky, making it difficult to fly. The dragon requires your constant attention, as it flys fast through the narrow and dangerous mountain pass.

name: Dark Squall
description: Below is a well traveled road which carefully picks its way between large boulders, and over rushing streams.  It's the old caravan road, and has been in use for centuries.

name: Dark Squall
description: Although you cannot see your direction indicator, the wind provides you with a steady from the east.   Weather is a funny thing - down here the winds push you westard, but if you fly higher, the winds are blowing from west to east.  Mordor is a strange land indeed.

name: Fast Moving Rain Cloud
description: Because the wind is so strong, you cannot turn in any direction, but must simply follow the airstream.  The winds have probably pushed you many kilometers from where you entered the upper stream.  Looks like you can dip down, however.

name: East City Gate
description: The gates close at night and and open at sunrise.  Many have been the cries heard outside during the blackness of night, but the guards here will never open the gates for fear that the mountain trolls will be out there.  If you decide to make the journey outside, be aware that you cannot come back at night.

name: Oceancrest East Gate
description: You are outside the east gate of the greatest city in the Land of Mordor.  The gate is never open after sunset, for fear that mountain trolls will overrun this weak part of the eastern city wall.  Looking east, you see a wide, well traveled road which disappears over a small hill not far away. Occasionally members of the city guard will come out here in the evening to show each other how brave they are.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The city of Oceancrest can be seen in the distance to the west.  Small hills to the east hide the road, but the road is well traveled and looks safe.  There are a several wagons on the road to the east.  Open fields and  groves of trees are to the north.  On the south are rocky plains.

name: Lyanden Road
description: This is the top of a small hill, and looking west you can see the walls of Oceancrest in the distance.  The road runs down the hill in the southern direction.  There is a grove of walnut and oak trees down in the valley to the north.

name: Lyanden Road
description: To the northwest is a short but steep hill, and below it to the north is a walnut and oak covered valley.  From here you see a group of small houses in the valley.  There are large rocks and boulders in the plains to the south, part of the  badlands a long way to the south.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The trees are thick on the north side of the road, but strangely none are growing on the south side.  The road is a true demarcation for two really different environments.  There is nothing but rocks and sand to  the south. Far to the northeast you can see snow covered mountains.

name: Lyanden Road
description: Tall trees come right to the edge of the road on the north side, but only rocks and sand can be seen on the south side.  A pleasant breeze drifts through the forest, contrasting with the hot one from the south.

name: Lyanden Road
description: A great forest stands on the north side.  Dry, hot sand is to the south. The road rises and falls as it covers small hills rolling toward the east. The eastern cities of the Land of Mordor are far away.  Oceancrest is much closer to the west.

name: Lyanden Road
description: the road builders found there was a natural break between the northern forest and the southern desert.  It was easy to simply follow the natural break in the topology.  The K'tral Desert to the south gives way to a  truly badlands much farther to the south.

name: Lyanden Road
description: Great trees are on the north side, while hot sand is on the south side. The road follows the natural curves and hills of the area, where ever  the roadworkers could make best use of the landscape.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The consortium of cities pays a contractor and his roadworkers to keep the highway in good repair, but a band of Highwaymen have been operating in this area lately, and the militia have not been able to get rid of them. Probably the road will be repaired when the militia is successful.

name: Lyanden Road
description: the trees are on both sides of the wide road, but you can see where the trees abruptly end and the great desert begins on the other side of a very large outcropping of rock a little way to the south.  There is a gulley across the road, which should be repaired.

name: Lyanden Road
description: Dark Forest hangs on both sides of the road, cutting out almost all of the light from the sky.  The road has dipped down here, so you are in an area where it's hard to see in any direction. Bird noises and other sounds, some of which you have never heard before, come from the trees aroound you.

name: Lyanden Road/Forest Road Intersection
description: Lyanden Road is wide and well maintained, but it looks like Forest Road could use a little work.  The trees seem to hang excessively low as you look to the north.  You can't see very far to the west, but a road sign says that Oceancrest is in that direction.  It also says Brownhaven is east.

name: Lyanden Road
description: To the north and east you see a forbidding mountain range in the distance and occasionally feel a chill gust of wind that came down off the snow- covered peaks.  Rumors speak of a race of giants who live there, and of course there are the mountain trolls.  The Enchanted Forest is north of you.

name: Lyanden Road
description: There is a pass between the Nartiz Mountains to the south and the home of the mountain trolls to the north.  Looks like this road has turned toward that pass.  Prince Ragnar's castle is somewhere southeast of here.

name: Lyanden Road
description: Lyanden Road connects several of the towns and cities to the east with the great city of Oceancrest.  Several crossroads lead to important villages and towns as well.  Prince Ragnar's castle is southeast of here, near the Vallenda Pass.  The trail seems to shortcut the road.

name: Lyanden Road
description: To the north there is an Enchanted Forest where many strange peoples and animals are said to live.  To the west the Lyanden Road will eventually lead to the great city of Oceancrest by the Respitial Sea.  Oceancrest was built on the Nylandian Bay, and serves as a major trading port for other parts of the world.  They say you can get anything at all in Oceancrest.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The desert actually forms a buffer with the badlands farther south. Entire caravans have beeen lost in the K'tral, but it is a faster route between Brownhaven and Oceancrest.  However, no one has ever been known to enter the badlands and return, except a few raving lunatics.

name: Lyanden Road
description: To the southwest is the hot and searing K'tral Desert, a forbidding buffer to the even worse badlands many kilometers to the south.  There is an old caravan trail through the K'tral, and occasionally the desert has swallowed a few caravans without a trace.  The caravan trail runs south of Prince Ragnar's splendid castle.

name: Lyanden Road
description: As you travel along this wide highway, you sometimes spot a village on the east side of the road, up in the foothills.  Wagon trails seem to be the only way of getting there.  Looking southwest you see nothing but rocks  and hot sand, although there are people reported to live there, too.

name: Lyanden Road
description: the hills rise steadily towards the stark mountains in the east.  There is another mountain range farther to the east and south.  Looks like that must be the direction of the Vallenda Pass.

name: Lyanden Road
description: There is a militia that patrols this road making it safe during the day, but they retire during the night leaving it unprotected.  Highwaymen and trolls are the most common problems at night, so the militia recommends that only experienced groups travel after sun down.

name: Lyanden Road
description: East of here is the infamous Timarask Valley, known as a dangerous place along the great Lyanden Road.  Overhead, occasional rain showers drift from the valley to the east.  Another valley which is off the road converges here with Timarask Valley.  A sign indicates it is the Valley of Timeron.

name: Lyanden Road/North Timarask Valley
description: Heavy rain and gusts of wind soak you and bend you near double.  It's very hard to see very far in either direction.   To the west the rain appears to be a mere shower, while deeper in the valley you see it is almost a storm. Experienced travelers tell of stormhawkes which live in the rainstorms.

name: Lyanden Road/Timarask Valley
description: Timarask Valley is generally shown on maps as a place to avoid.  Rain is a constant force in this small valley, blown down from Mount Aphinix over to the east.  There is almost a funnel effect, with the rain and wind all converging on this short valley.  You might ask why the road builders came this way, but you would learn that other ways are worse.

name: Lyanden Road/Timarask Valley
description: A fierce wind drives a stinging rain from the east.  This valley is in a perpetual rainstorm, and travelers are warned to hurry through this area, as giant birds of prey, known as stormhawkes, make their home in the driving rain.

name: Lyanden Road/South Timarask Valley
description: You are on Lyanden Road in Timarask Valley, where it rains constantly. The rain never lets up in this valley, but occasionally it is less violent than other times.  A fierce wind whips down from the majestic and dark Mount Aphinix, driving the rain before it.  At times you cannot see your hand  before your face, and the rain stings your eyes.

name: Lyanden Road
description: To the north you see the road runs through a valley in rolling hills.  Over to the east, the hills get steeper, eventually rising to meet Mount Aphinix, home of the mountain trolls.  Looking southeast, the grand Lyanden Road disappears around a curve heading towards the Vallenda Pass which skirts the Southern Nartiz Range.

name: Lyanden Road Toll House
description: A tax collector is stationed here, with a small garrison of troops.  He will not let you pass until you have paid a toll tax for the use of the road.  The bored militia would be very interested in anyone who did not pay.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The tower seems to be made of stone, but you will have to get closer to be certain.  It stands on the north side of the road, up on a small hill. a small meadow on the north side of the road here ends at the watch tower.

name: Lynaden Road/Valdune Watch Tower
description: A meadow on the north side of the road is fenced and you see sheep and goats grazing there.  There's no apparent entry to the tower from the road. The ancient tower was once used as a signal station, one of many along the way taken by invading trolls.  A fire atop the tower was the signal to prepare for an invasion.

name: Lyanden Road
description: Lyanden Road seems to run right past the tower, but you cannot see anyone on top of the tower nor around it.  It seems to set in a clearing you see  on the northwestern side.

name: Lyanden Road
description: the Lyanden Road was built only a few years ago, but there is another way to travel between the eastern cities and Oceancrest.  Long ago, a caravan trail was established, and it is still in use, but it lies far to the south. The caravan trail is not considered safe for lone travelers.

name: Lyanden Road/Gulley
description: The stream flows from the Enchanted Forest on the north side and has cut the road on its way to the desert on the south side.  Within a few meters, the water disappears into a great sinkhole in the desert floor.  The stream swirls violently with a loud roar before going under the sand.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The road continues to slope downward to the west and upward to the east. This is a strange land, with a forest on the north and a desert on the south.  There are stories in the city pubs of a nomadic race of people who live on the K'tral, and of huge sandworms which burrough deep under the hot dunes.  Looking across the desert you tend to not believe that anything could live out there.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The Lyanden Road follows a definite line between the forest and the desert. Normally, one might expect a gradual change between a forested area and sun-baked desert with nothing growing on it except sand dunes, but that doesn't seem to be the case with the K'tral Desert and the Enchanted Forest.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The K'tral Desert on the south side of the road seems to have a definite demarcation point, abruptly ending at the edge of the road.  On the north side there is green grass and trees.  This seems to be the only place that sand has invaded the northern side of the highway.

name: Lynaden Road
description: To the east is a steep hill which will provide the traveler with a good viewpoint of the surrounding countryside.  To the west, the road slopes downward, eventually reaching sea level when the road gets to Oceancrest.

name: Lyanden Road
description: The road follows the boundary set by the K'tral Desert and the forest.  there are more hills to the east, and they appear to get steeper in that direction.  Looking west they apparently level off in the distance.  On the north side of the road are large pines, oaks and redwoods.  There's nothing on the south side except hot sand.

name: Lyanden Road
description: There's not much to see toward the south, as it seems to be an endless expanse of sand and desert.  Over to the north there is a very old forest. Far to the northeast you can see two of the biggest mountains you have ever seen.  The tops are hidden in clouds.

name: Forest Road
description: The headquarters is built in one of the old watch towers that once served as a signal station.  Long ago, when trolls apppeared, guards lit fires on  top of the towers to signal an invasion.  Now, of course there is a much more modern way of signaling.

name: West Forest Lane
description: heavy ferns and damp underbrush are on either side of the lane, making it difficult to leave the path at this point.  The lane seems to be a popular path, if the amount of discarded items is any indication.

name: West Forest Lane
description: Heavy brush is on either side, and has apparently been cut back recently. You can see fresh wagon marks and steaming piles of horse manure in the middle of the lane, all evidence that this is a well traveled path in the woods.  A cross lane is over to the west.  The path disappears around a bend going in the southeast direction.

name: West Forest Lane
description: The forest lane continues on the ground, but it looks like some very good craftsmen have built a road up in the trees.  To the west there is a long ramp leading up to a solid looking highway going westward and overhead.

name: Forest Road
description: There are pleasant sounds from the forest around you, and although the trees appear thick and forbidding, everything looks normal enough.  The road could use a little work, as it seems the winter's rain has left its mark and cut a few channels across it.

name: Forest Road
description: The road has gotten a little wider, and with the trees further off there seems to be more light from overhead.  Wildflowers grow along the wayside, and birds can be heard in the distance.  Occasionally, there's a sound you cannot identify.  oh, well.

name: Forest Road/Redwood Tree
description: This redwood towers over the other trees nearby and looks like it is much older than the rest of the forest.  The road splits and circles around it. Looks like there is a path going from east to west.

name: Forest Road/West Forest Lane
description: Over to the west is a lane which turns to the north after a short distance. The road encircles the largest redwood tree in this section of woods. What a strange sight... looks like a window cut in the tree!

name: Forest Road/East Forest Lane
description: The Forest Road continues to the north and south in both directions.  Now isn't that strange.  Looks like a door right there in the tree!  A forest lane from the east ends here.

name: Redwood Tree/Forest Road
description: The huge redwood tree grows directly in the middle of the road. The road splits to go around the biggest tree in this part of the woods. North of here there is a footbridge over a small forest stream, and a path almost as wide as this road.  There is a fence and a "no hunting" sign along the west side of the road.

name: Forest Road
description: A small stream is flowing across the road, and a footbridge crosses over it.  A sign is on the other side, but you cannot read it from here. You can hear an odd noise underneath the wooden structure, sort of a snapping sound.  A good forest path is to the northeast.

name: Ashton River Road
description: The beautiful city of Hafnia, built by the elves after their wars with the mountain trolls and the dragons, is at the headwaters of this sparkling river.  If you follow this road, it will eventually take you there, but the way may be dangerous.  Oceancrest is southwest of here.

name: Ashton River Road
description: There is a gentle rise to the northeast, but in the distance you see the road turns through the foothills, and you can see parts of the road high in the mountains beyond that.  There is snow on the mountain.

name: Ashton River Road/Foothills Trail Intersection
description: A sign post points southeast and says the dwarven mining community of Nyyron is a few kilometers in that direction.  There are rolling hills in between, so you cannot see any sign of buildings in that direction.

name: Ashton River Road
description: The road is rather steep to the east, but has a downward slope going to the west.  The Ashton River looks like it calms down further west, but is pretty wild coming from the foothills.  It looks like fishermen have made a nice little camp under the trees by the river bank.

name: Khallazar's Compound
description: Khallazar is not known for his gardening work, but there is a steady drip od acid from his tree house which seems to be feeding the tangle of plants growing to the southeast.  Khallazar's Hut is northwest, and a path is southeast of here.

name: Wild Botanical Gardens
description: There is a narrow path through here, and it looks like it has been maintained by someone.  You see pieces of vegetation that have been hacked and left on the trail, clearing a way to the east and northwest.  The brilliantly colored plants seem to reach out for you.

name: Wild Botanical Gardens
description: The trail starts to get steep as it goes eastward towards the foothills. On both sides of the trail are wierd looking plants which move constantly. You recognize some of these plants, but they have been terrribly changed by something.  What was once a beautiful snapdragon has become a rather awful looking chomp dragon.  With teeth.

name: Foothills Trail
description: The dwarves make a pretty good living by mining the foothills, but some of the best ores come from deep under the mountains you see far to the east. The dwarves have never said how deep their tunnels go.

name: Foothills Trail/Garden Path Intersection
description: The Enchanted Forest is on the west side of the trail, and steep foothills are on the east.  There are some strange looking plants and vines on the west side which seem to creep and move even as you watch.  Looks like there is a small path cutting over to the west, through that wild vegetation.

name: Foothills Trail
description: The dwarves don't mind visitors to their small community, so if this is your first time to their mining town, be sure to stop at the Hog's Breath Saloon for some good Uland rum and a talk with the bartender.  He knows the complete history of the area.

name: Enchanted Forest Garden
description: There is a major trail located a little distance to the east, while the narrow trail you are presently on seems to go through a very strange garden. Looking east you see rolling foothills which eventually turn into a formidble looking mountain range.

name: Fish Camp
description: The river flows rapidly to the west, eventually making its way to the Nylandian Bay on the Respitial Sea.  A camp fire still smolders here, and someone has stocked a camp kitchen with everything needed to fix a meal. the trees provide a nice canopy overhead, giving this place a comfortable and relaxing feeling.

name: Ashton River Road
description: This is an excellent road following the Ashton River.  West is a fish camp. The road meanders to the northeast and southwest.  The foothills are much higher here, and you can look westward over the Enchanted Forest.  To the east the road continues to climb, and now the mountains are close by.  Looks like the road narrows.  The elven city of Hafnia is somewhere up there.

name: Ashton River Road
description: You are at the point along the trail where the species of trees is changing. the trees that grow on the lower part of the trail are different from those up higher.  this is the place where the mountains start and the Enchanted Forest ends.  Or is it where the mountains end and the forest starts?

name: Ashton River Road
description: Down below you can see where the river enters a forest as it continues on its way to the city of Oceancrest and the Nylandian Bay.  From this vantage high on the road you can also see the tops of the forest trees.

name: Ashton River Road
description: The road is steep at times, and makes it way along a sheer bluff on the north side.  Down below in the gorge you can see the Ashton River as it  flows from the mountains which are hidden in clouds to the east.

name: Ashton River Road/Phexton Tunnel
description: The tunnel is dark however, and a hard climb.  If you continue on the road to the east it will take longer to get to the other end of the tunnel.  The tunnel was an old mine shaft, and a road engineer decided it could be used as part of the road, but after many mishaps inside, it was decided it was safer to have the road outside the mountain.

name: Ashton River Road/Phexton Bridge
description: A small footpath leads down into the canyon below the bridge, but it soon disappears out of sight and you cannot see where it goes.  A spectacular waterfalls is at the eastern end of the gorge and a plume of fine mist is everywhere.  The falls is much higher than the road at this point of your journey.  the road drops considerably to the west.

name: Phexton Bridge
description: Although the bridge is wide, it has no side rails of any sort.  Heavy planks were laid over a web of ropes and cables to form the bridge, but it looks like they didn't consider it necessary to add handholds at the sides.  The water below looks deep and swift, as it leaves the falls to the east.

name: Phexton Bridge
description: The Ashton River tumbles over a ledge high overhead to the east, and falls to the bottom of the gorge, providing you with a breathtaking view of the great falls.  Looking to the northeast you see the road splits and one part leads north around the mountain cliff, while another disappears under the the great wall of water.

name: Ashton River Road/Phexton Bridge
description: This is the eastern end of the Ashton River Road.  A sign post indicates that the road to the north leads to the elven city of Hafnia, while the road to the south leads to the castle of Prince Rutger.  Both roads lead  higher into the mountains.  Over the bridge to the west is a road that leads down out of the mountains.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The road climbs through some very steep mountain passes to the northeast, but drops swiftly if you are going south.  There is snow here all year  round.  Several smaller trails seem to converge on the road at this point.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road/Phexton Road
description: Phexton Road continues to the north while Hafnia Mountain Road heads east and southwest.  In the distance to to the southwest you can see Phexton Bridge.  The elven city of Hafnia is still a long way to the east.  Phexton is a small mountain community north of here.  An old watch tower stands  silent guard nearby.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: There is an old watch tower on the north side of the road farther west. The road you are on continues to climb towards the east where there is a  lot of snow to be seen.  the road also drops swiftly to the west.  At times there are hairpin turns and it's impossible to see very far along the road when that occurs.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Above you is an overhanging cliff, providing you with some degree of protection from the cold wind and occasional snow flakes.  The wind seems to be particulary violent as it comes howling from the east, down from the mountain.  Mountain trolls are said to enjoy such weather.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: A narrow crevice in the cliffside looks pretty deep, but you might be able to squeeze in there, if you want to get out of the inclement weather. A draft of warm air from the opening creates a fog around this part of the road, but it seems to be for only a few meters on either side.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: there is a fog covering the road to the west, but it's not very dense. As you look northeast from here, you see a trail which meets the road and apparently goes to the stone structure you see on the north side of the road you are traveling.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road/Saint Anne's Road
description: The retreat looks a little like a small castle, with twin towers at either end, and a rampart in between.  You can see movement at the windows, and  there is a good woodsmoke coming from a chimney.  The great door is closed but even from here you can see there is a bell tower where a visitor might  ring for admittance.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The stone retreat has been here longer than anyone can remember, and did not always belong to the church.  When the clerics who have retired here first came to this part of the mountain, they had to exorcise a terrible demon who had taken it over.  When he was gone, the clerics simply moved in.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Further west you can see the twin towers of the stone church and the bell tower near the front.  The rear of the building appears to have a small garden behind it.  Funny thing about graveyards, no matter how well kept they are, they always seem to be haunted.  This one is not well kept.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Ice and rime has formed on the slowly moving stream, and the small valley is pristine, clear and cold.  You can see animal prints in the snow.  Large animal prints.  Looks like wolf tracks, and a lot of them.  Those are very,  very large animal prints.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: the road is snow covered, and the creek is almost completely iced over. the mountains rising higher and higer in the east are hidden in dark clouds, promising more snow.  A stiff breeze comes from the east, making you shiver.  Across the creek, in a wooded clearing, you see a hut.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Snow covers everything you see, and a flurry of snow is driven by the east wind coming down from the mountain peaks.  Northwest of here, off the road, there is a woodsman's hut.  Because of the wind, you can't tell where that howling noise is coming from.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road/Nyyron Trail Intersection
description: The road continues to follow a twisting and turning route as it makes its way through the great canyon, while the Nyyron Trail cuts off more to the south.  A faded sign warns travelers that mountain trolls have often been sighted along the north Nyyron Trail.  A creek flows from the north.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The road has patches of snow in places, which the wind occasionally pick up and blows in your face, almost laughing at you.  This area of the mountains is desolate and bleak, and there is no place to avoid the cold wind.

name: Kerston's Bank
description: There are low banks on both sides of the road, but that's not the reason  for the name.  Kerston the highwayman and his band of robbers consider this lonely area to be their personal source of funds, hence Kerston's Bank.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Deep wagon ruts in the snow and mud make it difficult to stay on the road, but its best to stay here.  Many a party of adventurers have become lost  after deciding to cut across country.  Pretty soon one rocky peak begins to look like the other.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: This road follows a natural trail between Mount Tasletek on the north, and Mount Aphinix on the south.  The mountains to the south were formed by active volcanos, and are the homes of horrible mountain trolls.  Peaceful,  but dumb giants live on the slopes of the Tasletek.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Mount Tasletek is slightly northwest of you, and directly north, far in the distance you can see Plasnelt Mountain and the Plasnelt Range.  Mount Caledonia is that peak just to the east of the Plasnelt Mountain, and the closest peak to the east is Hafnia Mountain.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: Snow swirls around you, and at this elevation snow stays on the ground all year round.  Several times a year the road crew finds a frozen traveler, so be warned.  This is not a friendly part of the world.  There is an odd occurance of a hot draft of wind occasionally from the south, probably from one of the active cinder cones that make up the Aphinix Mountain Range.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: the rest area is quite a bit higher than where you are presently, but the road is wide and clear along here, making it an easy climb.  The road looks  cold and bitter to the west, and gusts of wind sweep in that direction.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road/Tasletek Village Road
description: Five small homes and shops lie to the northwest, built on the edge of a deep gorge along the east end of the village.  From here, it looks like a traveler could get a hot meal and a warm bed for the night in the inn near the middle of the small community.  The mountain road continues to climb eastward, and drop off to the west.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: the road is on a ledge, high on the southern face of the mountain with a cold rock face beside you.  As you look overhead, you see twin castles built opposite each other on opposing sides of the gorge.  Far below is the mighty Ashton river, looking like a blue line from this height.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The Ashton River is in the gorge, so far away it looks like a small blue thread.  You are high enough that you see eagles and other birds of prey in the air a long way below you.  The gorge is a sheer drop from here to the bottom, and a vertical rock wall is on the other side of you.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The road does not descend to the bottom of the gorge, but follows a narrow ledge along the southern side of it.  High on either side, at the top of the north and south peaks there are twin castles built almost to the very edge.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: All of the snow has melted, even though there is snow at lower elevations. Higer up, and over to the south, there are several active volcanos, each  providing a welcome warmth to the air and the road.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: This is the western end of a short mountain valley leading east/west. to the southwest the road spirals lower through a field of old lava flows. The peak directly to the south is an active volcano, although it is not  doing anything at the moment except putting out a little smoke.  East are the towering peaks of the Hafnia Mountain Range.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: You are on a narrow road in a short valley which protect you from the wind. the road climbs out of the valley to the east, and drops deeper into it towards the west.  High mountains are all around you now, stark and cold in the mountain air.  Being this high really takes your breath away.   A pall of volcanic smoke hangs in the air.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: There is a sharp drop on the north side, with a snow white valley below you. The south side has a gentle slope leading to a rocky tor overlooking the road.  Great eagles wheel above the rocks, occasionally diving and picking up some squealing animal you cannot identify.  Smoke rises from a volcano south of here.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: A mountain pasture is on the south side of the road, and the rugged snow slopes rise to the east.  The mountain road curves around the pasture to the southwest.  Far out over the valley, near a great cloud bank, you see a copper dragon with a rider on its back.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: On the south side there is a pleasant mountain pasture, where you see a shepherd and his flock of sheep.  Looks like a small stone building is in the pasture, perhaps to provide shelter from the frequent mountain storms. The road drops swiftly to the southwest.  Hafnia Mountain towers over you.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: On one side of you is a sheer drop, while the other side is a steep cliff. It would be impossible to leave the road at this point, unless you could fly.  There are clouds hanging over the valley which you could almost touch if you would just lean out over the edge of the road.

name: Hafnia Mountain Road
description: The city of Hafnia is not far above you, built on a rugged mountain plateau. The elves were looking for an easy place to protect when they found these peaks which rise above the city at either end.  To the north there is one single peak which towers over all the others.  Atop it is a small castle.

name: West Gate of the City of Hafnia
description: To the west you see a waterfall and the Ashton River which flows eastward toward the great city of Oceancrest.   That city is located on the coast of the Respitial Sea.  This gate is closed at nightfall, and does not open until sunrise.  Hafnia is a bright and beautiful city built be the elves.

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: Prince Rutger and his royal family have a mountain castle to the southeast. You can see it from here, if you tilt your head back and look high on the east mountian face.  The road you are on winds through several passes to go there.  Just to the south there is grove of trees which the roads skirts.

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: Prince Rutger, son of King Lyanden, keeps a well trained garrison at his  mountain home.  He welcomes adventurers and rewards them handsomely if they  pledge their loyalty to him.  There is a guard post south of here.

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: A small kiosk stands on the east side, and a barracks building is a few meters away.  There is a red and white striped bar lowered across the road. It would be easy to walk around the barrier, but would it be wise?

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: There is a tiny kiosk, painted with red and white stripes, standing at the the side of the road.  A few meters away you see a barracks for the troops that maintain this post.  A long pole has been lowered across the road, apparently to require travelers to stop.  It would be easy to walk around.

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: The road is built on a long north-south mountain ridge, but drops slightly to the southeast before starting a long uphill series of switchbacks going to Castle Rutger high on the east mountain face.

name: Rutger Castle Road
description: rises in both directions from here.  To the northwest, you can see a building beside the wide road, and to the southeast you see the bottom of a series of winding switchbacks leading to the mountain fortress of Prince Rutger.  The fortress itself is high on the side of the mountian.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: The road is wide and covered with gravel to prevent it becoming a mire during the winter months.  Troops must be able to be deployed in a hurry, and it wouldn't look good for them to get stuck on their own road.  The road gets very steep to the northeast.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: From here, you can look down on the road as it makes a final turn before going north across a mountain ridge.  You can see a guard barracks far below.  The castle is still a good distance above you.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: Actually, you might be on a steep mountain road leading up to Castle Rutger. It's hard to say whether a road is leading up or down, so perhaps one should just say it runs between Castle Rutger and the mountain ridge below.  This road certainly changes direction often.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: The road hugs the mountain face as it turns back and forth, connecting the castle above with the main road below.  A game trail leads north. The road climbs to the northeast, and drops going northwest.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: One turn on this road looks pretty much like another, but at the turn below you see where a game trail crosses the road, and heads north.  The trail looks recently used, and you have heard there are magical stag deer that roam here.  The horns of the stag are said to give life to the almost dead, and help the ill recovery with fantastic speed.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: Not to far above you are the gates to Castle Rutger.  From here, you can see the towers and spires, and the ramparts guarded by archers.  Flags and pennants can be seen whipping in the breeze.  There seems to be a level lot near the gate where you can see a lot of empty carts and wagons waiting to  be used by merchants and travelers who visit here.

name: Castle Rutger Road
description: You are almost at the same elevation as the gates to Castle Rutger. The sheer wall of the castle makes you crane your neck to see the tops of the turrets and spires, but several of them are lost in the clouds.  The great gate closes at night, but there is a small door, suitable for one person to use, beside the huge metal gate.  At night, after the gates close, harpies have been known to attack people outside the castle.

name: Gates of Castle Rutger
description: There is a level lot with carts and wagons pulled up and waiting for their owners.  A small door, for use after dark, is beside the huge gate.  Farther north is an animal keep and stable.  On the west side of the wagon lot is a strange device:  Looks like a tubular slide to take you to the bottom of the mountain face so you won't have to travel down the road.

name: Castle Rutger Slide
description: You are traveling swiftly down a careening slide, and have come to a point where you must reverse direction as you continue your downard journey.  This slide is not nearly big enough to bring much equipment down it, but it sure provides a fast attack for troops who must get from the castle above to the road below in time of emergency.

name: Road Guard Barracks Compound
description: The guards who man this post don't consider it especailly good duty, and are often in a bad humor because they would rather stand guard on the castle wall, so they could be part of the feasting and drinking when they are not on watch.  The slide exit you see is one-way, and provides troops in the castle quick access down here if there is trouble.

name: Castle Slide
description: The slide is so slick that you cannot possibly go up, but there is always the road.  This place provides you with a good place to stay out of the the rain and snow, however.  You can see the east side of the guard barracks from here.

name: Road Guard Barracks
description: A warm fire and beds with wool blankets look very inviting.  A hot soup is simmering over the fire in a black cauldron, and you see a crusty bread on the table, with a huge round of cheese.  An ale keg stands at the end of the table.  Apparently, this barracks is also a post office.

name: Tasletek Village
description: The Snow Flower Inn is the largest of the five buildings in the village.  looks like a few retired hobbits have settled here, from the signs on  the doors.  Toby's appears to be a smithy, while Trabin might sell a few pieces of armor and weapons.  Tillie runs a small pawn shop.

name: Toby's Iron Works
description: Although Toby has retired, he still likes to earn the occasional gold piece by repairing armor and weapons.  Mostly he spends his time making a few custom made weapons for some of the nobility at Prince Rutger's castle. His half-wit brother has a shop and home next door where he sells a few of the things he makes.

name: Snow Flower Inn
description: This looks like a good place to relax and take off your armor.  The smell of hot food from the kitchen is wonderful, and the roaring fire in the  fireplace feels good after the cold mountain road you have been traveling  on.  The innkeeper's name is Trago, a small, fat hobbit with an even fatter wife.  Several customers are here.

name: Trabin's Fine Armor and Weapons
description: Most of the stuff in here was made by Trabin's brother, Toby, who likes to try to make the unique piece of armor or the exceptional weapon.  Most of the stuff Toby makes is for the nobility at Prince Rutger's castle, but he also makes things that Trabin can sell.

name: Tillie's Curio Shop
description: Tillie will buy anything if she thinks she can turn a profit on it. Although she retired long ago, buying cheap and selling dear is in her blood, and she enjoys the exchange even though she doesn't need the money. A family picture on the wall shows Tillie with her two brothers, Toby and Trabin.  It must have been taken a very long time ago.

name: Rue Caledonia
description: Directly south is the city's central park.  To the north is Hafnia Circle Road.  A grove of trees line the street, and small homes are built on the tree limbs.  There are shops below them.

name: Rue Caledonia
description: To the south is the circle road which travels all the way around the city. On the west side of the street is a large lot covered with tents and a lot of people.  Looks like another caravan is getting ready to leave the city.  A lot of stuff comes here from Oceancrest, but Hafnia also exports some very finely made elven crafts, such as archery tackle.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: To the west is the entrance to the training grounds.  You can hear a lot of cheering and roaring.  On the north side of the Circle there is a tall, white spire which seems to be a temple of some sort.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: A majestic white temple stands on the north side of the circle.  The entrance appears to be a little bit to the west.  Beside the temple is a smaller building with a sign outside that says, "Fraternal Order in the Mystical Self-Appreciation of Tall Elves."  The door is open.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: There is a lot of yelling and other crowd noises over to the northwest. Just west is an inn, and a sign outside says you can watch the fights at the training grounds from any of the upstairs rooms that are for rent.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: People whisper that there is a thieve's guild in one of the alleys near here. It might be true, since the city patrol has picked up a number of inept pickpockets in this area who appeared to be practicing.  They say the guild runs a school for pickpockets, and a more advanced school for burglers.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: A jewelry shop on the west side announces a new shipment of enchanted material direct from the Enchanted Forest work shop.  next door is a wedding shop, and across the street is the comfortable Dandelion Tea Shoppe.

name: Rue Caledonia
