description: There is a long line of manufacturing shops, all looking alike, on the east side of Rue Caledonia.  Farther south, on the west side, you see a big vacant lot where caravans form to make the journey to other cities.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: On the west side of the road you see a tree shaded building with a statue standing near the entrance.  The steps are wide and there seems to be an open door at the top of the steps.  Engraved in the stone are the words, "Fraternal Order of Rangers."

name: Hafnia Circle
description: There are four large buildings located on the west side of the road. They do not appear to be public buildings, but rather private clubs and organizations.  On the east side of the street, farther south, you can see the Hafnia Public Library.

name: Western City Gates
description: The gates are left open during the day, but at sunset they are swiftly closed for the night.  A number of elven guards are always here, and tourists like to gather at noon for the changing of the guard platoons.

name: West Hafnia Circle Road
description: This is the western side of the city, near the west city gates.  Small shops and interesting little homes line the street on either side, and a number of temples are grouped on the eastern side.  There is a lot of cheering  and other noises coming from the north.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: On the east side of the road is the Hafnia Public Library, a depository of much of the history and lore of the elven culture.  You probably can learn the entire story of how the war between the mountain trolls and the elves got started, and the outcome of it, if you are willing to do the research.  The library is open twentyfour hours a day.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: A long and narrow public park runs along side the eastern city wall, ending at the library on the north side of the road.  Over on the west side you see there is a private school that teaches hand-to-hand combat.  Not a bad thing to know in these dangerous times.

name: Hafnia Circle
description: On the east side of the road is a building with several guards at the door. The Elven War Council maintains a meeting place here, and hosts seminars on a monthly basis.  They often invite representatives from other races to speak, and are very attentive to any proposals to get rid of the dragons that hold the lost city of Caledonia.

name: Zelda's Capes and Fine Furs
description: Although the windows show the latest fads in capes and other finery, the owner knows that she can make money on the old standbys too.  Near the back of the shop you can find old favorites that never go out of style.

name: Home of Tragirsha
description: Tragirsha was not always a toad, having been born of humans who made their home on the Nyyron trail.  Her mother was a herbilist who could cure the  blind, but when an evil demon from one of the watch towers sought her help, she permanently blinded him.  To her sorrow, he was able to turn her only daughter into a giant toad.  Tragirsha lives here alone, in the cellar.

name: Cellar of Tragirsha
description: Tragirsha has lived here alone for almost 180 years, suffering from the spell of the demon.  She waits for someone to break the curse cast on her, and has vowed to reward anyone who does.  During the years she has lived here she has learned much because of her power to listen to the thoughts of  people who pass by on the road outside.

name: Boar's Arse Pub
description: A lot of different races seem to enjoy this pub.  You are in the main tap room, and can see the pub also has a dining room in a separate part of the building.  An oaken stairway on the south side of the room goes to an upstairs section.  Looks like a couple of bouncers or guards are at the bottom of the stairs.  Something interesting is up there, no doubt.

name: Boar's Arse Dining Room
description: As you look about you, you realize that some foods are common to all races, but on the other hand, there are some things that only an orc or gnome would eat.  A large trestle table stands in the center of the room, loaded with strange meats and foods.  looks like a buffet, so help yourself.

name: Bottom of the Stairs
description: As you approach, a couple of bouncers stand and stare at you.  If you want to go up these stairs, you had better have the right answers to their questions.  Give the wrong answer, or make the wrong move, and you will probably have to fight your way out of here.

name: Boar's Arse Stairs
description: There's a lot of drinking going on down below, and a lot of laughter, too. but occasionally someone gets their feeling hurt, and when that happens a fight breaks out.  Even the waitresses take part, and when someone gets killed the body is simply dragged to the alley door.

name: Bottom of the Stairs
description: As you come down the stairs, the bouncers smile and wave to you.  Evidently you have given them the right answers to their questions.  However, these guys have short memories.  If you go to the pub and try to come back, they will act like they don't know you.

name: Hallway in the Boar's Arse
description: There is a only one large room at the end of the hall.  Looks like a meeting place of some kind.  There is a small crowd, and a speaker is at the front of the room.  You see a red banner on the wall, with a white circle on it. An upraised fist, with a single finger erect, is inside the circle.

name: Anti-Royalist Meeting Room
description: These people are opposed to the concept of royalty, and want to inflame the populace so as to overthrow the crown.  Most people simply ignore them. Rumors are that they are responsible for many assassinations.  They used to have a secret meeting place in the Dragon's Tooth Inn in Oceancrest, but the city guard found them out and hanged the innkeeper.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: You are on Nyyron Trail, just south of Hafnia Mountain Road.  The Trail was important at one time, but since the old watch towers were abandoned after better signaling methods were found, this trail has not been used much.  In the distance to the south you can see a single stone tower, overgrown with heavy vines.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: The trail is almost overgrown now, but wagon ruts still show the way along the rocky outcroppings.  Further south is one of the old signal watch towers which used to be used by the militia to warn the cities when there might be danger of invasion.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: Heavy vines cover the ancient tower, and a fallen stone blocks the only doorway.  However, if you are interested in exploring, it looks like the  vines are heavy enough to climb, and you could probably make it to the top. Further south is a small glen and a burned out house and barn.

name: Gorgan's Tower
description: Gorgan took this tower as his own almost 300 years ago, and was the terror of the countryside until he accidently got acid in his many eyes.  He consulted the herbilist who lived on the farm down the trail, but she saw through his disguise and made his blindness permanent.  As his last act of terror, he burned the farm and turned the daughter into an ugly toad.

name: Vine Covered Side of Gorgon's Tower
description: The Nyyron Trail can be seen to the east, and further south is a burned farmhouse.  The top of the tower is about the same distance as it is to the ground  A stinging vapor comes from cracks in the stone, causing your eyes   and lungs to burn.  Acid oozes from the tower in places.

name: Top of Gorgon's Tower
description: Although the vines are lush and green on the sides of the tower, nothing lives here on the top.  You can hear a bubbling noise below inside the   stone tower, and acid vapors rise all about you.  There is a closed hatch which appears to be locked with a heart-shaped lock.  Some say Gorgon still hides inside, blinded forever by the herbalist who once lived on the farm  south of here.

name: Gorgon's Tower
description: A dim light from above is the only light to enter, but there are black  shadows on dark shadows which seem to shift as you turn to look at this awful place.  You are standing on rotting planks while below your feet   is a great vat of poisonous acid, which seeths and bubbles constantly.   The demon Gorgon used this vile poison to terrorize the travelers on the Nyyron Trail, but it eventually blinded him.  Poetic justice, eh?

name: Gorgon's Acid Vat
description: Above you are rotting planks and a dark room where Gorgon is said to still hide and sulk.  For many years he grew wealthy and fat by killing, robbing and eating the travelers along the Nyyron Trail, but this very acid which he used in his evilness eventually blinded him.  Even now the poisonous vapors are stinging your eyes and making you very sick.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: A small creek tumbles alongside the trail, making a very pleasant sound. The dirt path is wide enough for a wagon, but there are no wagon ruts in the path.  However, you do see plenty of three-toed footprints which look exactly like troll prints.  Only bigger.  The trail disappears around a massive boulder to the northeast.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: A great boulder, larger than a house, sits on the east side of the trail. Grafitti mars the stone, but it seems to be in a language you do not understand.  Some of it looks to be dried blood.  In the sand at the base  of the boulder you can see some rusting pieces of armor, and a few broken weapons and gnawed bones.

name: Nyyron Trail
description: To the south the trail continues out of sight around a great boulder, while to the north you see a recent avalanch has wiped out part of the path.  The mountain sides here are steep and rugged, and slides occur often.  If you follow the creek, however, it should take you back to the trail.

name: Nyyron Creek
description: As you look up to the mountain on the east side, you see where an avalanch of dirt and boulders has covered the trail which used to traverse the mountain. A little to the northeast the creek spills over the debris, forming a small waterfall about three meters in height.  South of you is the Nyyron Trail which continues down the mountain.

name: Nyyron Creek Waterfall
description: Like almost every waterfall that exists, there seems to be a tunnel almost hidden by the cascading water, but you don't immediately see how to enter it.  The wreckage of a wooden sign is strewn about, but you can still read the words, "Beware of Mountain Trolls!"

name: Nyyron Water Chamber
description: The slabs of stone in here are warm to the touch, and steam from the water fills the room, making your sore muscles relax.  The chamber looks clean and comfortable, and is certainly well hidden.  This might be a good place to rest awhile.  There are some runes on the wall, which indicates this place may have been used for magic spells at one time.

name: Avalanch
description: above you is a gulley where the avalanch debris came from.  It looks like you could climb up there, if you have climbing gear with you.  Often gold is discovered after a fresh avalanch, and this one only occurred since the last winter.  Below you is the Nyyron Creek, where you see a small waterfall has formed because of the newly deposited earth in the creek's path.

name: Glabor Gulley
description: To the east the gulley climbs out of sight into the towering mountains, and the west it drops out of sight over the crest of the remains of a recent avalanche.  There seems to be hundreds of small caves dug in the slopes of the gulley, and it looks like a community area in the center of them.

name: Glabor Gulley Northern Path
description: The path meanders randomly across the northen face of the gulley, passing near the entrances to many of the caves you see farther east.  A large clump of bushes hides a portion of the path immediately east, but as you look down, you see many campfires and dark, troll-like figures gathered there.

name: Glabor Gulley Southern Path
description: There are many signs of troll activity here, and you see movement down below in the center of the gulley where there is a great circular firepit near a  stone altar and a busy community area.  There are several cave openings farther east on the gulley slope.

name: Glabor Gulley Northern Path
description: The path wanders up and down as it traverses from west to east along the northern side of Glabor Gulley.  Several caves can be seen along the way. There are torches occasionally along the path, and you can see even more  on the floor of the gulley.  They appear to lead to the eastern end.  There is a large hedge or clump of bushes hiding the path going west.

name: Glabor Gulley Commoner's Area
description: Farther east you can see a monstrous structure seemingly made from the bones and skulls of deceased adventurers who have come this way before.  About you is a stone altar and wide steps leading up to the top of the altar.

name: Glabor Gulley Northern Path
description: There are several smaller caves to the east and the west, but this one  appears to be a community cave rather than one of the residences.  Trolls have been known to enjoy a drink or two, so perhaps this is a gathering place for those desiring some of the good Uland rum made by the dwarves.

name: Glabor Gulley Altar
description: From this height, you can look down on a community gathering area for the mountain trolls which is between you and the vile structure to the vile structure to the east.  Behind the altar you can see a great circular firepit with a roaring flame.

name: Entry to Glabor's Skull Throne Room
description: The throne room is actually not very tall, but as you look closely, you see it is made entirely of bone.  Skulls decorate the entry door, which is shaped like a giant open mouth of a larger skull.  Inside, in the shadows, you can hear the hissing and clicking of the troll language.  Sounds like guards are just inside the door.

name: Glabor's Throne Room
description: Once every ten years, the strongest of the trolls fight to the death amongst themselves for the privilege of challenging the current holder of the throne.  Glabor has lasted longer than any previous king, and has been here fifty years.  His strength and love of a fight is legendary.

name: Glabor Gulley Southern Path
description: there are a lot of three-toed footprints in the soft dirt of the path, and from time to time you can hear the harsh tongue of the mountain trolls. The trail splits here, allowing you to either go down to the gulley floor, or climb higher to the rockcropping.

name: Glabor Gulley Southern Path
description: There is a gathering place below you, and what appears to be a monstrous hut at the eastern end of it.  From here you can see guards coming and going from the place.  There is a firepit down there too, which is putting out a lot of heat and flickering light.

name: Glabor Rock
description: The rocks you are standing on are extremely hot, although the weather is cool.  Perhaps the heat comes from beneath you.  Large boulders are covered with smaller ones, and you see many crevices and openings.

name: Glabor Cave
description: A group of troll musicians are at one end of the cave, playing something that sounds horrible to your ears, but no doubt enjoyed by the patrons. Most of the people in the bar are trolls, but you see a few orcs as well.

name: Noob Training Centre
description: You find yourself in an area specially designed for the weak. Here, you should try to learn the basics in fighting and resting. Using the "help" command, you can learn more about commands such as cast, kill, bash, circle, etc. You should start by seeking help on your class. Directly to the east of here is a safe room, where you can heal faster. To the north and south are training rooms where you can gain exp, gold and items. These facilities are only accessible to those under the level 3.

name: Noob Training Room 1
description: You are in the training area for the weakest of the weak. The smell of dried blood hangs in the air. While this is a good place to gain experience, you should flee if find yourself in trouble, it is worthwhile to flee. While weak, those who show up here are unforgiving, and will take your life without a second thought. If you do flee, they will not forget that you attacked them, and will attack you as soon as they see your face again.

name: Noob Training Room 2
description: You are in the second training area of this facility. The majority of those that gather here are stronger than those in the other training room. Those that fight here are using weapons, and will drop them upon their death, much like you. It is worth taking everything you see, as some items may be valuable to sell or just recycle.

name: Noob Healing Room
description: You find yourself within a room lined with hospital beds. The wounded appear to recover quickly. A poster of the wall says "fast healing room!". You feel you energy returning to your body at an unnatural rate. You know this poster speaks the truth, and that you are gaining more  magic and health than you would in other rooms. There are many like it throughout the world.

name: In Front Of The Floating Pyramid
description: A giant floating pyramid stands before you. Magic power reverberates through your body. Ancient inscriptions line the pyramid, and glow with mysterious power. Ethereal steps lead from the ground towards the pyramid. They seem to fade in and out of existence as you look at them.

name: Pyramid Entrance
description: You stand and the entrance to the great floating pyramid. Up closer, it is much larger than you originally thought. To the north there is a large  rectangular opening on the side of the pyramid reveals a black abyss.  A  cold eerie draft draws you towards the pyramid and makes the hairs on the  back of your neck stand on end.

name: Inside The Pyramid
description: As you step into the pyramid the darkness swallows you. All light has been stripped away by an unknown force. You can feel the warmth of the outside  world to the south, but a magical veil prevents you from seeing anything. A dark corridor stretches out in front of you, the sound of metal dragging on stone echoes forth.

name: Within The Labyrinth
description: The unmarked walls that surround you make it difficult to recognize where  you are. No natural light is able to piece the darkness around you, making  it impossible to orientate yourself. Faint footsteps echo around you, and  the sinister sound of dragging metal grows louder.

name: Within the labyrinth
description: The unmarked walls that surround you make it difficult to recognize where  you are. No natural light is able to piece the darkness around you, making  it impossible to orientate yourself. Footsteps echo around you, and the  sinister sound of dragging metal grows louder.

name: Within the Labyrinth
description: The unmarked walls that surround you make it difficult to recognize where  you are. No natural light is able to piece the darkness around you, making  it impossible to orientate yourself. The darkness around you is suffocating, no sound or light can pierce it.

name: A Dead End
description: As you round the corner you come face to face with a large jackal-headed  deity. A pool of blood lines the floor. As he turns to face you, your blood runs cold. Whatever this guardian is protecting must be very valuable.

name: Pyramid Atrium
description: You find yourself within a vast, well-lit room with luxurious ornaments  lining the walls. To the north, you see a golden staircase. Multiple  hallways branch off this main room in all directions. A thick dark veil surrounds the doorway to the west, swallowing all light it touches.

name: Pyramid Atrium
description: You are within the pyramid atrium, in front of a solid gold staircase. You cannot see what is up the top, but you feel powerful magic emanating from there. To the south, you see a doorway covered in darkness. To the east and west, hallways branch off in various directions.

name: Top of the Golden Staircase
description: You are at the top of the staircase. Ethereal platforms continue to the  south, and you can make out a ledge carved into the top of the pyramid above you. To the north, a large golden throne sits in the middle of a room. A solitary figure sits in the room.

name: The Throne Room
description: You stand before a large golden throne. Nu, one of the primordial beings of creation sits before you. A massive amount of magic that threatens to tear the very fabric of existence emanates from him. Yet here he sits, alone, with a scowl stamped on his face. Nothing would be able to contain such a  powerful creature, he is here by choice, and his choice alone.

name: Western Wing
description: You are within the wet wing of the pyramid. To the north there is an abrupt end to the hallways, while the wing continues to the south. Various statues line the walls. Looking at them makes you feel uneasy, as if they were about to spring to life and attack

name: Western Hallway
description: You are within the central area of the west wing. There are doors on each of the walls surrounding you. A low growl can be heard from the golden door to the west. A refreshing breeze can be felt from the green door to the south, while you sense nothing from the yellow door to the east.

name: Treasure Trove
description: You find yourself within the treasure room of the pyramid. A great griffin  stands before you, preventing you from taking any of the riches. The floor  is lined with the bones of looters who have come before you. As you move,  you feel the beasts great eyes watching you closely, ensuring you do not  take what is not yours.

name: Rejuvenation Centre
description: The pharaohs were often buried with luxuries to ensure a comfortable  afterlife. You find yourself in a room filled with incense and medicinal  herbs. The smell alone seems to rejuvenate and revitalize you. The longer  you stay, the more you forget the harsh reality of the outside world. A  gentle draft blows towards the north, the only obvious exit from this haven.

name: The Armory
description: You find yourself staring at the hundreds of weapons and creates scattered  throughout the room. A lone sarcophagus stands at the end of the room. Each weapon hums with power, and is locked in place by some sort of magical  spell. If you look close enough, you might be able to find one that is free. You get the feeling that you are being watched. The occasional image flashes through your head, increasing in frequency as you move closer to the  sarcophagus.

name: Crawlspace
description: You find yourself in a narrow crawlspace above the rejuvenation Centre. A  gentle breeze blows and seems to fill you with power. Before you sits a  beautiful, meditating goddess. She looks at you kindly, and you feel the  warmth of a mothers embrace. Before you is Isis, the goddess of love. You  cant help but notice the sheer power emanating from her. Only fools confuse  her kindness for weakness.

name: Inside The Sarcophagus
description: You are within the sarcophagus. In this tiny space, you come face to face  with the apparition of pride. You are unable to make out its blurry face,  but you feel as if its disgusted to be in your very presence. As you get  closer to the apparition, strange visions fill your head. They are memories, but not your own. Perhaps releasing this spirit from its earthly bonds will release all the memories it contains.

name: The Eastern Wing
description: You find yourself in the eastern wing of the pyramid. The hallway ends  abruptly to the south, but continues to the north. You can hear shouting  coming from the north. In the distance you see two figures in the heat of an argument. They seem oblivious to your presence, for the moment.

name: Eastern Hallway
description: You stand in the eastern hallway. It has been ransacked by looters. Broken  ornaments are scattered on the ground. Two looters are here, arguing over a broken vase. There are doors on each of the walls surrounding you. From the west, a cool breeze blows from an orange door. To the north, and east a red and blue door sit respectively. The sound of flowing water can be heard from the blue door.

name: The crypt
description: Various coffins and sarcophaguses are scattered throughout the room. They  begin to creak, and the lids begin to move. Boney hands grab the frames as  skeletons emerge, angered that their eternal rest has been interrupted. The souls of the damned begin to condense and take form, ready to attack you for disrupting this sacred space.

name: Crypt Basement
description: You stand in the darkest depths of the pyramid. An earthy smell fills your  nose. A towering jackal-headed figure stands before you. Spirits swirl  around him. You feel as if his very presence will rip your soul from your  body. In his hands he holds a feather and some scales.  Before you is the  guardian of the damned: Anubis.

name: Room of Fire
description: You find yourself within a large, circular room. A large sea of lava  stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. From a distance, the heat is tolerable, but you should think twice  about getting closer. On the southern end of the room there is a door, the  only obvious exit from the room.

name: Beside the Lava
description: A large sea of lava stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. From a distance, the heat is tolerable, but you should think twice about getting closer. You can walk around it in a  clockwise or anticlockwise direction. On the southern end of the room there is a door, the only obvious exit from the room.

name: Around the Lava
description: A large sea of lava stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. From a distance, the heat is tolerable, but you should think twice about getting closer. You can walk around it in a  clockwise or anticlockwise direction. On the southern end of the room there is a door, the only obvious exit from the room.

name: Around the Lava
description: A large sea of lava stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. From a distance, the heat is tolerable, but you should think twice about getting closer. You can walk around it in a  clockwise or anticlockwise direction. On the southern end of the room there is a door, the only obvious exit from the room.

name: Around the Lava
description: A large sea of lava stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. Here, the distance to the island is smallest.  You may be able to float across if you could magically suspend yourself.  You can walk around it in a clockwise or anticlockwise direction. On the  southern end of the room there is a door, the only obvious exit from the  room.

name: Around the Lava
description: A large sea of lava stretches out in front of you with what appears to be a golden island in the middle. From a distance, the heat is tolerable, but you should think twice about getting closer. You can walk around it in a  clockwise or anticlockwise direction. On the southern end of the room there is a door, the only obvious exit from the room.

name: Golden Island
description: You stand on a plate of gold, surrounded by lava. You feel the heat sear  your skin, and every breathe fills you with pain. A lone figure stands  before you proudly, seemingly unphased by the heat. This man with the head of a falcon, has a solar disk surrounding him like a halo. He hold a large golden staff in his right hand.

name: Outside?
description: As you step through the doorway you find yourself in the middle of a forest. There is a doorway to the west, sitting in the center of a clearing. You can see the eastern hallway through it, but not beside it. The sounds of nature echo around you. To the east, you hear a waterfall. To the north, rises a  large, insurmountable mountain.

name: Beside A Creek
description: You stand beside a peaceful creek. Large insects fly around you, curious to your presence. Further to the east, you see the plunge pool of a large  waterfall. To the west you see a clearing with a strange object in its  center. A cool breeze blows, causing the leaves to rustle around you.

name: The Foot Of The Waterfall
description: You stand at the base of the waterfall in ankle deep water. You are deafened by the roaring water. Ancient fish swim around you, curious to your  presence. You are surrounded by a thick, impenetrable ring of trees. The  only clear path is to follow the creek to the west, where you can make a  clearing out in the distance.

name: On The Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you get overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not  even be able to see where you are standing. To the north, you see a large  hall with a single throne sitting in the center. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on.

name: On The Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you get overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not  even be able to see where you are standing. To the north, you see a large  hall with a single throne sitting in the center. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. the roof appears to be higher in the south.

name: On The Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you get overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not  even be able to see where you are standing. To the north, you see a large  hall with a single throne sitting in the center. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. the roof appears to be higher in the south.

name: On The Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you get overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not  even be able to see where you are standing. To the north, you see a large  hall with a single throne sitting in the center. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. the roof appears to be higher in the south.

name: On the Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you are overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not  even be able to see where you are standing. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. The roof is far above you here. The light seems to be sucked away by an unknown dark force. You feel much colder, and as if you are being watched.

name: On the Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above a doorway covered  in darkness. As you look down, you get overwhelmed by vertigo. Normal beings would not even be able to see where you are standing. Looking around, you can see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. To the west, you see the opposite of the door below. There appears to be an  impenetrable glowing white film covering the door. Your hand is easily able to pass through it.

name: On the Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you are overwhelmed by vertigo.  Looking around, you can  see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. The roof  is far above you here. As you look up, you can see one final shimmering  platform. As you look at it, memories start to burn through your head. The closer you get, the more clear the images become.

name: On The Ethereal Platforms
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform above the atrium. As you look down, you are overwhelmed by vertigo.  Looking around, you can  see various shimmering platforms that you may be able to stand on. The roof  is far above you here. There is a large spiderwebb stretching around you  with various, humnan sized cocoons are suspended around you. You feel a shiver run down your spine and the hairs on your neck stand on end.

name: The Highest Ethereal Platform
description: You find yourself standing on a shimmering platform far above the atrium. As you look down, you are overwhelmed by vertigo. Below you, you see the  various shimmering platforms you used to make your way here. The roof  is close to you, and there is not much room on the platform. Ahead of you  is the apparition of Sloth. As you look at it, memories start to flood through your head. Perhaps releasing it from its earthly bounds will  trigger a similar release to last time.

name: On Top Of The Baldachin
description: You float above the royal canopy surrounding the throne. In front you floats a shrieking embodiment of pure fury: the Apparition of Wrath. As you look  at it, you are filled with a deep, unknown sadness. Releasing this beast  from its earthly bounds will reveal the final key to the puzzle.  Below you, you can see Nu, the primordial being, his brow crumpled into a frown.

name: Top Of The Waterfall
description: You stand at the top of the waterfall. The roar of the water is deafening, however your ears a filled with a different sound, from a different time and place. Above the water floats a dark green swirling mass. As you look at it, you are filled with jealously of those you know. Their weapons, friends and  loved ones all seem better than yours.

name: Within The Labyrinth
description: The unmarked walls that surround you make it difficult to recognize where  you are. No natural light is able to piece the darkness around you, making  it impossible to orientate yourself. The floor feels hollow underfoot, and the sound of grinding metal is deafening. Whatever is causing it must be close by.

name: Phexton Road
description: The small village of Phexton is further north, and Phexton Bridge is south. Long ago, before modern signaling methods, there were a series of watch towers built throughout the mountains whose purpose was to watch for trolls and other invaders and warn the cities.  They used to light giant bonfires on top of the towers to signal one another.  They are no longer used for that purpose, and stand empty these days.

name: Phexton Road
description: Looking south you see one of the watch towers that used to be used as a lookout for warring trolls.  North is the village of Phexton, home to a race of peaceful giants who enjoy mountain life rather than the confines of a city.  Giants are not very smart, and are difficult to anger, but once they do get mad, its hard to stop them from destroying everything they see.

name: Phexton Road
description: the giants who live in the village are peaceful, and welcome travelers who can bring them news of the outside world.  They aren't especially  bright, but they do have a thriving little community and send many of their young people to Oceancrest to learn the ways of other races.

name: Phexton Road
description: You can see a few large houses along the road on either side, and in the distance you see the village proper.  The houses you see appear to be made of native boulders with heavily thatched roofs, and are almost three stories tall.  These are the homes of of the Mountain Giants.

name: Phexton Road/Hildor Lane Intersection
description: You see a village of Mountain Giants, each well over six meters tall.  Large homes and shops are on both the east and west sides of the central park which is in the center of the village.  There is an inn on the east side of the road, and a rather noisy sounding pub on the west side.  The wide Phexton Road goes down the mountain to the southwest.

name: East Hildor Lane
description: Immediately north is the village green, and to the east is a line of homes. On the south you see an open-air blacksmith's shop and a forge that is  taller than you.  Everything you see is considerably over your head.

name: West Hildor Lane/Boran Street Intersection
description: You can see quite a few shops along Boran Street, which leads north from here.  There is a wall along the south side of the lane which stands at  least three meters high.  A tower is at the southwest corner of the village.

name: Boran Street
description: Shops line the west side of the street, and the peaceful village green is on the east side.  The green is a pleasant park where many of the  residents like to spend the afternoon.

name: Boran Street
description: Clean shops and a village meeting hall are on the west side of Boran Street. This small village for large people is built on the side of a mountain, and is surrounded by sloping fields and gulleys.  Some of the buildings on the west side of the street seem to cantilever over steep slopes.

name: Boran Street
description: Many wild and exotic plants grow in the mountains, and the giants who live in Phexton make a good living by cultivating them and shipping them to other cities and towns.  The village meeting hall is south of here.

name: Boran Street/Galgorn Way Intersection
description: Boran Street runs north and south along the western side of Phexton Village, and Galgorn Way travels east and west to connect to the east side of the village.  There are a few buildings to the north, but most of the village  is south of here.  The village green is in the center.

name: Galgorn Way
description: Long ago, the Mountain Trolls had an alliance with the red dragons and tried to conquer the village of Phexton.  Galgorn, although not a Mountain Giant, helped the people of the village and defeated two of the red dragons.   When the trolls saw that, they retreated and have not been back since. Several homes are on the north side of the way, and the village green is to the south.  There appears to be a statue in the center of the green.

name: Boran's Gate
description: There is a gate across the street which leads farther to the north, and a very big hut nearby.  You can hear the sound of snoring coming from inside  the hut.  A stone building is across from the hut on the east side of the  street, and a sign above the door says, "Community Warehouse."

name: Boran's Trail
description: This is Boran's Mountain Trail near the gate to Phexton Village.

name: Boran's Hut
description: The giants who live in Phexton Village have appointed Boran, one of the larger giants, to guard the narrow trail which leads to the Valley of the  Rainflowers.  They make a lot of money by harvesting the Rainflower seeds, and don't want travelers going there.

name: Phexton Village Community Warehouse
description: There is a wide stairway, with steps so far spaced you would have to hoist yourself up to climb them.  There is also a hole in one wall which you could probably crawl through.  If it wasn't so big, you would swear it  was a mouse hole.

name: East Hildor Lane
description: On the north side of the lane is the village green, and to the east are most of the homes in the village.  The west side tends to be mostly shops and places of business.  Phexton Village is very proud to be the retirement home of one of the best fighters in the land.  Jerome's School for Fighters is just east of here.

name: East Hildor Lane
description: The building on the south side of the lane doesn't look any more imposing than the rest of the buildings in the neighborhood, and has a thatched roof just as they do.  But a sign out front proclaims it to be Jerome's School for Fighters.  Jerome no longer does the training, but leaves it to his three sons to accomplish under his supervision.

name: Jerome's School for Fighters
description: If this is your first time here, you can train in the green room, but it won't be easy!  Be prepared for the fight of your life.  Fighter's who have already accomplished that feat may train in the blue room.  The red room is reserved for fighters who have gone through both the green and blue room's training.

name: Jerome's Green Training Room
description: You are in the training room for fighters new to this school. Jarl, youngest son of Jerome, will test your ability as a fighter.  If he finds you worthy, you may have the key to the advancement room.  Be aware  that you will be in a fight to the death, and Jarl will give no quarter.

name: Jerome's Blue Training Room
description: In order to get the key to the advanvement room you must defeat Karl, the  second son of Jerome.  Of course, it will do you no good if don't have the funds to pay for your training.  Karl is big and experienced, but he's a sucker for an overhand rabbit punch.  Go for it!

name: Jerome's Red Training Room
description: Tarl, the eldest son of Jerome, stands in the far corner with his arms folded and his weapon at his side.  You must defeat him to gain the key to the advancement room.  Tarl is so confident you will not best him that he will allow you the first blow.  Why don't you wait till he blinks?

name: Advancement Room in Jerome's School for Fighters
description: When you leave here, you can tell anyone who asks that you were, "trained by Jerome."  In honor of your advancement, the school wishs to give you a  gift.  The business card you see here can be exchanged for one of the new vanadium forged shields, made by Kolar the blacksmith.

name: Alchemist Training Room
description: Train in here, Alchemists!

name: Path to Saint Anne's Retreat
description: A huge stone manor looms before you, almost a castle in size.  There are twin towers at either end, and you see lights and activity in the windows of the west tower.  The east tower is cold and dark in appearance.  Nearby is a bell tower and a sign says ring for admittance.

name: North Gate for Brownhaven
description: You are outside the north gate of the village of Brownhaven. There is a dusty caravan trail stretching in the distance.  It leads both east and west, and disappears out of sight in both directions.  A sign post indicates that Oceancrest is west, while Kista is east.  A broken pointer hangs on the post, so you have no idea which way to go for the elven city of Hafnia.  You do know it's located somewhere in the northern mountains.

name: DM'S Cross Roads
description: From here the Dm's can go to just about any place in the Land of Mordor.

name: Dungeonmaster's Storage Room
description: Do not take these items.

name: Druid Training Hut
description: Welcome Druids to your training room! Love Smithy

name: Darwin's Study
description: In addition, the plush surroundings provide a nice place to entertain guests.  The room is dimly lit by a gas lantern hanging from the ceiling, and several tables surround a roll-top desk at the northern wall.  On the desk can be seen several large stacks of papers that appear to be notes on the various species that inhabit Oceancrest.

name: A Quiet Corner
description: You find yourself in a quiet corner, away from the hustle and bustle of the city. As the sounds melt away you find yourself begining to relax. You as if it is safe to relax here. As you look around, you notice the silhouettes of other exhausted ad

name: A Calm Cove
description: You find yourself within a peaceful cove. The seawater stretches out in front of you, eerily still. As you think about entering the water, you feel the hairs on the back of your neck stand on end, as if something is watching you from the depths below. It may not be worth entering the water.

name: Waist Deep Water
description: You find yourself within the water. The water is cold to the touch, but not unbearable. You feel the water ripple around you, the vibration caused by creatures moving below the surface. Its possible to descend into the water, but this is only recommended if you can hold your breathe.

name: Underneath the surface
description: The saltwater stings your eyes.  The water stretches out around you in all directions. You no longer feel the movement of the creatures around you. You feel hundreds of eyes on you, watching your every move.

name: Northwest Corner Of The Cove
description: Visibility worsens and you feel blindly through the water until you feel a  smooth stony wall. You make out what appears to be human remains resting against the floor, picked clean by aquatic scavengers.

name: Southwest Corner of the Cove
description: You feel blindly through the wter until you feel a cold,               smooth stony wall. A small school of fish dance around you, inspecting you closely.

name: Southeast Corner of the Cove
description: Visibility worsens and you feel blindly through the water until you feel a cold, smooth stony wall. A gentle current can be felt passing your feet. It appears to be coming from a crevice.

name: Northeast corner of the Cove
description: Visibility worsens and you feel blindly through the water until you feel a cold, smooth stony wall. The water is cooler here, which makes you feel uneasy.

name: Dark Recess
description: You find yourself in dark crevice in the south eastern corner of the cove. Green slime dilutes the water, which stings your skin. The beast that calls this place home does not like you being here.

name: The Salamander's Nest
description: Beneath the salamander you find its nest. Large prehistoric eggs are  littered throughout the cavern. The heat felt above is nothing compared to the inferno surrounding you now. In a few minutes you feel like you will become a crispy treat. It is difficult to see, but you may be able to descend deeper.

name: Deep Within The Nest
description: You have descended further into the nest. The deeper you go,  the hotter it gets. The eggs have been replaced by the bones of  fallen prey. Ahead of you, you hear a low, rumbling growl. The  heat is growing more intense by the minute.

name: End Of The Small Tunnel
description: You find yourself at a dead end, face to face with angry baby salamanders. Scratch marks line the walls and their hisses echo around you. Through the walls, you feel the vibrations of something moving nearby. It  is NOT happy you are here.

name: End Of The Large Tunnel
description: As you reach the end of the tunnel, the heat reaches its maximum.  Parts of your clothes start to spontaneously catch fire and the  smell of burning hair and flesh fills the air. You have found the source of the heat, the great salamander matriarch. As it glares  down at you, you feel as if you have made a grave mistake.

name: The Far-Seer's Home
description: You stand in the great far seer's home. You are surrounded by various trinkets, parchments and instruments from various lands. The air is vibrant. It is filled with an energy you have not felt before. No one knows the far seer's tale, but everyone knows he is one to be respected. It's worth your while to talk to a man with his experience, perhaps you will learn something.

name: Oceancrest Conservatorium
description: You are within the antechamber of the Oceancrest Conservatorium. Against the west wall, you see a desk, covered in sheet music. Behind it stands a lone  man, the Maitre de la Musique. He is able to help Bards gain further  levels with their musical training, if they are experienced enough and can  afford his prices. Before he is willing to help you, you must pass a trial.  Each  trial is different depending on your current skill level.

name: Observational station
description: You are within the Oceancrest observational station. Various glowing runes  line the walls. They are part of the ancient spell placed over the city to  safeguard it. To the north lies a door that will lead you back into the  city, while to the south lies the armory which has a large crystal in the  middle of the room.

name: Oceancrest Armory
description: You are within the oceancrest armory. In the middle of the room is a large crystal which absorbs all the magic in the area. This crystal is essential for powering the defensive systems of the city. You can feel the crystal sapping your strength away. Try as you might, you are unable to cast any  magic spells in its presence.

name: Dirt Road
description: You stand on a rough dirt road that acts as thoroughfare between two cities. To the west, Oceancrest beckons with all the hustle and bustle of suburban  life. To the east, a more rural life is to be shared. This is the Kingdom of Emrae, with the main township being a fair ways northeast from here. Far in  the distance looms the namesake Castle. It seems to dominate the surrounding Perhaps as an omen. Next to the road is a large sign welcoming new  travellers to the area.

name: Dirt Road
description: ___________________________________________________________________________ | Welcome to the Kingdom of Emrae!                                         | |                                                                          | | This is a land with a troubled past, future and present.                 | | Will you discover its secrets? Here's hoping. . .                        | | Rewards aplenty for those who can uncover the true nature of this Kingdom| | Good luck!                                                               | |                                                                          | | With much love, Smithy                                                   | |                                                                          | |____Completed Areas____                                                   | | Town Square: For all players                                             | |        Farm: For players level 05 - 09                                   | |         Pub: For players level 03 and up                                 | |     Library: A great source of information  )                            | |      Sewers: For players level 06 and up                                 | |      Forest: For players level 07 - 14                                   | |      Desert: For players level 10 - 15                                   | |__________________________________________________________________________| |                                                                          | |____Coming Soon____                                                       | |           River: For players level 08 - 14                               | |        Mountain: For players level 12 - 18                               | | Floating Stones: For players level 15 - 19                               | |     Ruined City: For players level 06 - 10                               | |     King's Tomb: For players level 20 - 25                               |west

name: Dirt Road
description: This is a road leading to the main township in the Kingdom of Emrae. Gravel crunches underfoot as you walk towards your destination. Occasionally, a  horse-drawn cart passes you as they take their wares to the big city of Oceancrest to the west. To the east is the main road towards the Emrae  Township. This spot on the road is quite peculiar as you can see a  massively overgrown shrub to the south. It is certainly large enough to  contain an entire dwelling. Perhaps there is a denizen inside?

name: Main Road
description: This is a road leading to the main township in the Kingdom of Emrae. Gravel crunches underfoot as you walk towards your destination. Occasionally, a  horse-drawn cart passes you as they take their wares to the big city of Oceancrest to the west. To the east is the main road towards the Emrae  Township.

name: Main Road
description: You are on a main road paved in stone that leads north and south towards the Township of Emrae. In the southwest lies the large city of Oceancrest. To  the north is the Emrae town square. This is mostly still farm land. The occasional farmer passes and greets you in their travels. To the west you  spy a tree with a rather unfortunate cow stuck on one of its branches.

name: Main Road
description: You are on a main road paved in stone that leads north and south towards the Township of Emrae. In the southwest lies the large city of Oceancrest. To  the north is the Emrae town square. This is mostly still farm land. The occasional farmer passes and greets you in their travels. To the east you  spy a long driveway leading to a farmhouse and its surrounding fields.

name: Main Road
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life. You stand outside an inn with a sign that reads -The Dragon Blood Pub-

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Fountain
description: Noises of trickling water fill your head and the smell of fresh water greet  you as you look into this fountain pool. The streets of Emrae extend in all directions, with residents and travellers alike criss-crossing as they go  about their days. You take a seat at the edge of the water-feature and  decide to take a breath. Dipping your toes into the water makes you feel at ease. The water is clean and pure. There is a tranquility to this space that heals you. The bustle of the surroundings fades from your mind as your feet soak in the healing water.

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life. You stand outside a temple with a sign that reads -Temple of Emrae: By the  light of The Five, all will be healed-

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life. You stand outside a library with a sign that reads - Enter if you wish to enlighten your mind-

name: Town Square
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life. You stand outside a shop with a sign that reads -Harrys Supplies-

name: Harry's Shop
description: This is Harrys Shop. He seems to have a few peculiar wares for sale. Though he is probably more interested in what you have to sell. His building is  poorly lit and junk is just strewn around the floor in a heap. Generally,  if Harry doesnt want to purchase any wares offered by his customers, they  just toss it on the floor. Harry doesnt seem to mind, but it certainly  gives his shop a filthy appearance. The air in here stifles you, what with  the piles of trash. It would be best to conduct your transactions and leave  as soon as possible.

name: House
description: You step off the streets of Emrae and into a commoners house. It is a  wooden building in good condition, with nice , modern furnishings. Looking around, you can see that the owner has not been taking very good care of the dwelling recently. Dishes piled up in the sink. A fire that needs fresh wood Trash piling up in common spaces. Maps are framed on the walls of the  surrounding wilderness. The Great Forest lies to the east of the city.  Several routes and pathways are marked in red, with others dotted in black. Perhaps there is some sort of code to it? Of course, someone lives in this  place. Looking out the window is a concerned woman. She clasps her hands  over themselves and pulls anxious faces.

name: Temple of Emrae
description: This temple is an exquisitely refined space of worship. Thick red curtains decorate the walls. Finely carved wood stand in rows for the public to sit  in and pray. Large stone pillars stretch from the base of the structure to  the rafters. At the end of the central aisle is a stone altar covered in a  white cloth. A hooded priest stands behind. To the south, there is a chamber where a healing cleric prays and tends to the sick.

name: Temple
description: You step into the foyer of The Temple of Emrae. The building is an example  of beautiful design and expensive material. Marble tiles below. Polished  stone walls surround. Stained glass windows above. Whilst the rest of the township is certainly in no bad condition, this temple stands in a state of opulence. As you motion through the temple, your footsteps echo through the chamber with a great reverberence. This place stands as a reminder that you  are just one person in the eyes of an infinite universe.

name: Library
description: You step into a quiet building with even quieter patrons. You feel  underdressed. Everyone bustles about with lovely warm sweaters on their arms The librarians here greet you and ask if you need help finding what you are looking for. The tomes in this establishment detail the history of the  Kingdom of Emrae and its surroundings. The books are arranged in neat  orderly rows and indicate a careful attention to detail from the owners. If there is information you seek about this kingdom, it will be in here . . . hopefully.

name: Bookshelves
description: You step into a quiet building with even quieter patrons. You feel  underdressed. Everyone bustles about with lovely warm sweaters on their arms The librarians here greet you and ask if you need help finding what you are looking for. The tomes in this establishment detail the history of the  Kingdom of Emrae and its surroundings. The books are arranged in neat  orderly rows and indicate a careful attention to detail from the owners. If there is information you seek about this kingdom, it will be in here . . . hopefully.

name: House
description: sorry, this quest isn't available yet come back later!

name: Dragon Blood Pub
description: You have stepped into a lively and active pub: The Dragon Blood Pub. This is a wonderful spot where all of the citizens of Emrae make an appearance from  time to time. If you need a room to stay for the evening, you can talk with  the owner, Jack. If youre looking for beer, then just flag down a bartender Some of the customers turn and greet you with a stinky eye. Others grin and invite you to join in their drinking games.

name: Driveway
description: Turning into the driveway, you catch a glimpse of what is wrong with  this farm. A huge insect chomps down on a nearby shrub. Whilst the   single locust on its own would be no trouble to handle, the issue seems  to be that the entire farm is ovverun. Fretful farmhands run to and fro  trying to salvage what they can from the alarming onslaught of insects.

name: Wheat Fields
description: These fields have been visited by a plague. Locusts swarm around any  available stalk of goodness, devouring any morsel that is left. The soil underfoot looks dry and unfit for any more crops. There is a forceful breeze blowing through these rows of plants, and it seems its coming from the  windmill atop the nearby hill. The wind gusts obnoxiously around your ankles with dust and sand being kicked up in a fury. The smaller locusts dont cause too much bother, however they arent the most unsettling thing about this  field. Occasionally, locusts the size of a hound lunge forth into view.   This is no normal plague.

name: Wheat Fields
description: Looking around the wheat fields, you see that this year will not be a good  crop. Locusts swarm around any available stalk of goodness, devouring any  morsel that is left. The soil underfoot looks dry and unfit for any more  crops. There is a forceful breeze blowing through these rows of plants, and  it seems its coming from the windmill atop the nearby hill. The smaller  locusts dont cause too much bother, however they arent the most unsettling thing about this field. Occasionally, locusts the size of a hound lunge  into view. This is no normal plague. The farmers dwelling is to the south,  and you spy the owner within. He doesnt look happy with the dust storm, nor the plague of giant insects.

name: Wheat Fields
description: The plague of dust and insects is much fiercer here. Presumably because you  are closer to the source. There is a forceful breeze blowing through these  rows of plants, and it seems its coming from the windmill atop the nearby  hill. The smaller locusts dont cause too much bother, however they arent  the most unsettling thing about this field. Occasionally, hound sized locusts lunge forth into view. This is no normal plague. The windmill is  north and east from here.  Atop the windmill is a glowing light which seem  to be the cause of this great plague and dust-storm.

name: Wheat Fields
description: The plague of dust and insects is much fiercer here. Presumably because you  are closer to the source. There is a forceful breeze blowing through these  rows of plants, and it seems its coming from the windmill atop the nearby  hill. The smaller locusts dont cause too much bother, however they arent  the most unsettling thing about this field. Occasionally, hound sized locusts lunge forth into view. This is no normal plague. The windmill is  north and east from here.  Atop the windmill is a glowing light which seem  to be the cause of this great plague and dust-storm.

name: Wheat Fields
description: Looking around the wheat fields, you see that this year will not be a good  crop. Locusts swarm around any available stalk of goodness, devouring any  morsel that is left. The soil underfoot looks dry and unfit for any more  crops. There is a forceful breeze blowing through these rows of plants, and  it seems its coming from the windmill atop the nearby hill. The smaller  locusts dont cause too much bother, however they arent the most unsettling thing about this field. Occasionally, locusts the size of a hound lunge  forth into view. This is no normal plague. There is a silo nearby, but the entrance does not appear obvious

The windmill is  north and east from here.  Atop the windmill is a glowing light which seem  to be the cause of this great plague and dust-storm.

name: Inside the Silo
description: You jump feet first from the top of the silo into a pit of grain. After which, you realise that perhaps this was not the smartest move. As you  swish around in the pool of grain, there doesn't seem to be an easy way leave. it will take you some cunning and ingenuity to find a smart exit However, there seems to be company. This grain is by no means a simple  food source. The grains have appeared to coalesce into a being made of pure carbohydrate.

The farmers dwelling is to the east,  and you spy the owner within. He doesnt look happy with the dust storm, nor the plague of giant insects.

The windmill is  north and east from here.  Atop the windmill is a glowing light which seem  to be the cause of this great plague and dust-storm.

name: Farmhouse
description: Whilst there are certainly no insects nor gale-wind in this building, it is definitely no calmer. A stressed farmer paces back and forth in   his living room. He mutters swear words and shakes his fist agressively at the swarm of giant insects ouside. The building is in fine condition  though a little grimy. To the east you spy a kitchen with an inviting   smell and warmth wafting over. Perhaps you might like to sit a while?

name: Farmhouse
description: Stepping into the quiet kitchen of the farmhouse you feel a little more relaxed. The farmer's wife calmly stirs a pot of porride and invites  you to sit at her table. The rough wooden structure has clearly seen a lot of love and a lot of meals. You feel very invited in this space and  are at ease immediately. You feel like you could sit here and listen to   the fire crackle for a while as you regain your energy.

name: Outside the Windmill
description: Calamity is afoot here. Stretching your neck backwards you can see the top  of the windmill. A brilliant glowing mass of amber light protrudes from the platform on the roof. Dust and particulates jet forth from the portal and  and on the crops down below. Occasionally, you see the multi-coloured  locusts condense out of clouds of dust. A summoner is responsible for this.  Now if only you had the key to the windmill door...

name: Inside the Windmill
description: Stepping into the structure, you finally get some reprieve from the din  outside. However the noise of roaring wind is replaced with the smell of  rotting bodies. Sacks of grain line the walls of the structure, the  grindstone in the middle of the building looks worn and inefficient.

name: Inside the Windmill
description: The smell grows more wretched here as you can now see the cause. A man  stands before you with a vacant gaze on his face. This man has not seen a  bath in months. He is wearing black robes from head to toe, though under his clothes are what appear to be farmers overalls. Talking to the person for answers seems futile. Perhaps they were coerced into enacting another mans  will? To the east you see a ladder shaft up to the roof.

name: Inside the Windmill
description: You stand underneath a ladder shaft, which leads to the roof of the mill. To  the west, you see the cause of the foul stench. Its a hooded and robed man. Above you, you can see the opening to the roofs platform. The ladder up  feels sturdy enough and should be able to support your weight. Amongst the  sacks of grain you notice shards of crystal. They glimmer and shine with the same amber light of the portal you saw atop the windmill. Their placement  doesnt seem random. Tracing their outline with a finger it makes the shape  of a pentagon.

name: Ladder Shaft
description: The ladder creaks as you climb it though it shows no sign of breaking under  your weight. As you climb, the roar of the wind outside grows louder once  again. You are close to the end of this adventure, you can feel it. Or  perhaps, this mystery runs deeper than you realise?

name: Ladder Shaft
description: The ladder creaks as you climb it though it shows no sign of breaking under  your weight. As you climb, the roar of the wind outside grows louder once  again. You are close to the end of this adventure, you can feel it. Or  perhaps, this mystery runs deeper than you realise?

name: Atop the Windmill
description: You emerge from the ladder shaft and try to plant your feet on a shaky platform on top of the farms windmill. The air whips around your eyes and nose, assaulting you with wave after wave of dust and sand. The view of the field below is obscured and the sound of locusts below have been drowned out by the swirling dust storm. Hovering at the far side of the platform you finally catch a glimpse of the cause of the farms plague. A shimmering mass of amber light carves a rip in the very fabric of reality. From this portal, the dust, jets forth into the atmosphere. Standing by the portal is a hooded figure, casting his hands over the shimmering mass of brown light.

name: Inside the Amber Portal
description: Stepping through the locust callers portal, your vision fades to blackness.  The noises of the outside storm fade and the smell of dust leaves your  nostrils. The air around you is calm and still, with a note of freshness you didnt know was lacking on the rest of the farm. As soon as you adjust yourself to the stillness, a bolt of shooting pain assaults the inside of  your head. As if another occupant were fighting for its place within the  chaos. As your head throbs, you hear the echoes of another persons voice  inside your mind. The voice sounds urgent, but you cannot seem to recognise  to whom it belongs. As it speaks, it seems to beckon your movements further  into the blackness.

name: Inside the Amber Portal
description: The voice continues without you ever speaking your answer. In your hand a mysterious trinket appears. It is a wooden figurine carved into the shape of an animal. The voice calls out in your mind:  If that is truly your answer, then this object will be of use to you. Take it and begone.  I will deal with you in good time, peasant. . . .  The screeching pain in your mind dissapates. All that is left to do  here is to return to the world beyond the portal.

name: Inside the Amber Portal
description: The voice continues without you ever speaking your answer. In your hand a mysterious trinket appears. It is a wooden figurine carved into the shape of an animal. The voice calls out in your mind:  If that is truly your answer, then this object will be of use to you. Take it and begone.  I will deal with you in good time, peasant. . . .  The screeching pain in your mind dissapates. All that is left to do  here is to return to the world beyond the portal.

name: Inside the Amber Portal
description: With the splitting pain gone from your head and the voice having stopped, you see no need to stand within this realm of the portal any  longer. The voice was definitely adressing you. And it seemed as though the individual who gave you your new amber token will want to see you again. You gather your senses again and head for the exit to this  disorienting abyss

name: Tree
description: Ascending the tree, you can spie a better look of the immediate surroundings Along the main branch of the tree, there is a very grumpy cow barely  clinging to its lifeline. To the east in the distance is a farm, which seems to be under attack by a swarm of large insects. To the northeast is the main township of Emrae. The Castle looms behind it, as a warning of who is in  charge. There is much to be discovered in this land.

name: Tree Branch
description: You shimmy yourself further along the tree trunk in an effort to get closer  to the unfortunate cow. He does not look happy to see you. Frankly, you  arent sure if standing on this part of the branch will be able to support  the weight of both you and the cow. However, nothing worth doing is worth  doing without risk, right?

name: Snippy's Shrub Shop
description: You've found yourself in what is perhaps the most peculiar exercise in  marketing you have ever seen. Within the dense foliage and shrubbery lies an entire shob dedicated to selling happy little plants in pots. The shop owner seems nice enough but it's very clear he's gone a bit "off the deep end". You have no idea if a business such as this could ever be profitable. The smell of lovely green leaves fill your body and on the whole you feel a little more well-connected to nature. The shop owner says you can ask for a  selection of his most well selling plants.

name: Township of Emrae
description: You stand among the streets of Emrae, just a little ways east from the  central town square. Villagers go about their daily business. Washing  clothes, selling wares, chopping wood. They all seem happy enough to see you though their faces belie a certain weariness. Children play games of Im  the hero! amongst the houses with toy swords and shields. Life seems  relatively normal here. Further east from here is the road towards the  Great Forest of Emrae.

name: Road to the Great Forest
description: You walk along a road that connects a very large forest with the township of Emrae. The stone pathway of the city ends before long and you are forced to  walk on a dirt pathway once again. The houses out here grow further and  further spaced out. Residents here have more room for animals and farming  land. Before long enough, the farmland is replaced with thickets of trees.  The entrance to the Great Forest looms ahead, ready to swallow up any  unprepared travellers.

name: Forest Trail
description: The trees begin to grow denser as you hike further into the woods. The  township of Emrae can be seen just on the edge of the western horizon. Those who choose to live out here are definitely in favour of privacy from their neighbors. Further east you can see a small clearing and a hut with a fire  going inside. Beyond that, a mysterious fog seems to have beset the entire  forest before you. A calm breeze sets in and you are filled with the  cleanliness of pine air.

name: Forest Hut
description: You step inside a welcoming timber lodging. A fire crackles in the far  corner, and a kitchen full of food is to your left. In the centre of the  room sits a figure, warming his hands over the fire. He turns to greet you  and welcomes you into his dwelling. An elk head decorates the mans  mantlepiece, and the timber furnishings were presumably crafted from the  pine trees outside. There is a lot of pride in this hut. And perhaps a lot  to learn from its occupant.

name: Kitchen Pantry
description: Inside the forest-keepers kitchen you spy a curious creature hiding in the pantry. After opening the pantry door the sheepish goblin is forced to  reveal itself. It sighs as you approach and then returns to its work in the kitchen. The goblin fusses over cooking pots on the stove and tends to  various dishes in the oven. All manner of food is strewn around the kitchen. Half-cut onions, heads of garlic, cracked eggshells, stale bread. The food  smells good for that matter, and you wonder if the creature will cook for  you too?

name: Behind the Hut
description: Stepping out the back door you feel a cool breeze on your face. The hut- keeper has made a nice clearing amongst the dense forest. Camping and  hunting tools are littered around the place and there is a small outdoor fireplace. Amongst the ashes are numerous bones from past feasts. Further  north you spy a bear cage, with two unfortunate occupants.

name: Bear Cage
description: Behind the Forest Keepers hut is a bear cage, as you approach, you see  Patricks captive bears. His whip is also lying on the ground here too.  Perhaps he forgot to bring it inside with him? Looking at the conditions of  the cage you can see these bears are not well cared for. Their water supply smells foul and they havent had fresh food in days. The bears do not look  happy to have visitors.

name: Forest Trail
description: You are now in the heart of the Great Forest. Emraes Kingdom clearly  stretches far and wide as this forest is no small entity. The pathway winds  this way and that, with no real meaning or direction. The path ahead is  clear enough but looking into the treeline you can see a great mist. If you  were to venture off this pathway for even a second you would risk becoming hopelessly lost. Occasionally, wildlife emerges from the fog and observes  you intently.

name: Lost in the Forest
description: You stand amongst the trees and notice you are no longer on the forest path. Fog swarms in around you and confusion sets in. There seems to be no direct route back to where you were moments ago. The haze is thick and visibility  is less than a metre in front of you. Youd scream out in frustration but  fear that might attract unwanted visitors. The only option for traversal  seems to be retracing your steps back to the entrance of the forest

If you  were to venture off this pathway for even a second you would risk becoming hopelessly lost. Occasionally, wildlife emerges from the fog and observes  you intently.

name: Forest Altar
description: You stand before a roughly hewn stone altar amongst the thickets of trees.  Atop the altar lies a large, cracked emerald crystal. Perhaps it is the  source of all the fog in this forest? Or perhaps not. Forest spirits watch  you quizzically as you approach the altar. They wonder what you will do? A cloaked figure watched you, too. They are cloaked in brilliant green silk,  and have a glassy look in their eyes. Perhaps they are guarding this place against their will?

name: Clearing
description: You have managed to find yourself in a spot of small respite from the  sinister woods around you. There isnt a whole lot here except for more  trees and leaves. You feel a certain calmness, if only because you can see  further than five metres in front of you. Looking at the ground, you notice slight evidence of tracks further to the southwest from here.

name: Forest Trail
description: The Great Forest of Emrae has completely consumed you now. There are still pathways carved out clearly before you, but panic has set in a little. The  fog percolates along the edges of the treeline. One step into the fog would leave you hopelessly lost. The wildlife and tree-spirits have taken on a  more sinister gaze now. They seem to mock your efforts to navigate the trail
