description: Fog swarms in around you and confusion sets in. There seems to be no direct route back to where you were moments ago. The haze is thick and visibility  is less than a metre in front of you. Youd scream out in frustration but  fear that might attract unwanted visitors. The only option for traversal  seems to be retracing your steps back to the entrance of the forest

name: Completely Lost
description: You attempted to retrace your steps but you have found yourself walking in circles. There is no way forward or back now, just around. The fog swarms  around you and clouds your mind too. Voices and noises screech out in your  mind, or perhaps they are real? The haze is so thick you cannot even see the fingers at the end of your arm. You call out in desperation but only the  mist hears you. It swirls around mocking you. All that is left to do is  close your eyes and ponder the situation.

name: By the Campfire
description: You open your eyes and find yourself surrounded by a forest encampment.  Tents and huts litter the nearby clearing. You sit with your arms  outstretched towards a large fire. The surrounding fog seems to be kept at  bay by the warmth of the flames. Campers move back and forth between various errands and chores of their days. Even the spirits in this part of the  forest seem more at ease with their guests in this part of the wods.  Everything feels a little more tranquil here. You might stay a while and  rest up.

name: Forest Encampment
description: Amidst the forest clearing, there are campers and hunters milling about you. They are all busy with their respective tasks. Repair their hunting  equipment, wash their dirty clothes, set up camp, skin their latest catch.  Hushed chatter crosses their lips. They all talk about the state of the fog  as if it were a living entity. On the whole though, these forest denizens  mostly ignore you.

name: Forest Encampment
description: Amidst the forest clearing, there are campers and hunters milling about you. They are all busy with their respective tasks. Repair their hunting  equipment, wash their dirty clothes, set up camp, skin their latest catch.  Hushed chatter crosses their lips. They all talk about the state of the fog  as if it were a living entity. On the whole though, these forest denizens  mostly ignore you.To the north lies a hut with a sign reading -Druid Marshall- on the front.

name: Druid's Hut
description: Entering into the master druids hut, you see great evidence of his  lifestyle. Bear skin lines the floor. Deer pelts are draped over chairs.  Marshall sits at his desk, fashioning a necklace out of stones. There is a  mood of quiet contemplation in this room. Evidence of a life spent listening to nature. Runes and charms litter the corners of the hut, presumably to  dispel the fog. Tomes on the druidic arts line his bookshelves, along with various animal totems. This is a man who has devoted his life to his craft.

name: Forest Encampment
description: Amidst the forest clearing, there are campers and hunters milling about you. They are all busy with their respective tasks. Repair their hunting  equipment, wash their dirty clothes, set up camp, skin their latest catch.  Hushed chatter crosses their lips. They all talk about the state of the fog  as if it were a living entity. On the whole though, these forest denizens  mostly ignore you.

name: Foggy Pathway
description: Further away from the campfire, you can still feel its calming protection  from the fog. Visibility is decent here, but you know if you misstep you  will become lost again. There are less campers and hunters around these  parts. More of the spirits and animals of the forest instead. It is  difficult to see what is ahead of you. You will just have to pick a  direction and hope it leads you to your destination.

name: Foggy Pathway
description: Further away from the campfire, you can still feel its calming protection  from the fog. Visibility is decent here, but you know if you misstep you  will become lost again. There are less campers and hunters around these  parts. More of the spirits and animals of the forest instead. It is  difficult to see what is ahead of you. You will just have to pick a  direction and hope it leads you to your destination.

name: Hidden Staircase
description: You stand at the base of a stone staircase. It is a peculiar structure.  There are no pillars supporting the stairway, and yet it extends upwards as far as you can see. The fog consumes the furthest steps you can make out.  For that matter, you arent even able to tell if the stairway breaches the  forest canopy. It would be foolish to climb this staircase without a plan.  A sentient stone soldier has noticed your approach and seems intent on  blocking your progression on these steps.

name: Surrounded by Fog
description: The haze takes on a verdant green tinge here. There is spiritual energy  coursing through your body and mind. Something of importance is nearby.  Looking around there is nothing but trees. You could try to push through the fog but without clarity you wouldnt make much progress. Perhaps  there is  some magic you could use to contain this malicious mist?

name: Forest Encampment
description: Amidst the forest clearing, there are campers and hunters milling about you. They are all busy with their respective tasks. name: Mysterious Staircase
description: You stand at the base of a stone staircase. It is a peculiar structure.  There are no pillars supporting the stairway, and yet it extends upwards as  far as you can see. The fog consumes the furthest steps you can make out.  For that matter, you arent even able to tell if the stairway breaches the  forest canopy. It would be foolish to climb this staircase without a plan.  A sentient stone soldier has noticed your approach and seems intent on  blocking your progression on these steps.

name: Mysterious Staircase
description: Your mother warned you about climbing stairs. Now you know why. They lead nowhere. There is no indication of an end to this staircase. Fog surrounds  you and clouds both your vision and mind. The only way out of this mess is  to keep your wits about you and pray for a solution. The mist in the air  dances around as if to mock you. Or are they hunters coming to kill you?

name: Mysterious Staircase
description: Your mother warned you about climbing stairs. Now you know why. They lead nowhere. There is no indication of an end to this staircase. Fog surrounds  you and clouds both your vision and mind. The only way out of this mess is  to keep your wits about you and pray for a solution. The mist in the air  dances around as if to mock you. Or are they hunters coming to kill you?

name: Surrounded by Fog
description: By some miracle you have descended the staircase and managed to find  yourself in a position different to where you started. You stand in a  clearing surrounded by a green haze. Before you stands a cloaked figure.  They seemed to be guarding a stone that pushes back the fog. Perhaps it is something you need in order to venture deeper into these woods?

name: Surrounded by Fog
description: By some miracle you have descended the staircase and managed to find  yourself in a position different to where you started. You stand in a  clearing surrounded by a green haze. Before you stands a cloaked figure.  This cultist is the one responsible for the fog that has beset the forest.  A shining mass of emerald-green light jets forth from their hands. They are summoning a portal that cuts through the fabric of reality. They have  unleashed a disturbing weapon upon this pine forest. A haze of contagion  that infects the mind to possess any who dare breathe in the air for long  enough. This cultist is presumably the cause of the possessed druids around  the place.

name: Inside the Emerald Portal
description: Stepping through the Emerald Portal, the fog lifts. You immerse yourself in  the blackness of the other-worldly realm. As soon as you adjust yourself to  the stillness, a bolt of shooting pain assaults the inside of your head. As  if another occupant were fighting for its place within the chaos. As your  head throbs, you hear the echoes of another persons voice inside your mind. The voice sounds urgent, but you cannot seem to recognise to whom it belongs As it speaks, it seems to beckon your movements further into the blackness.

name: Inside the Emerald Portal
description: The voice fades and the pain in your head dissipates Through the blackness gleams the core of the portal. It shines with a brilliant emerald glow All that's left to do it take it and leave

name: Inside the Emerald Portal
description: The King will fall. . .  His shroud of lies will be dispelled . . . When the time comes, what will you choose? Your life, or the life of your allies? A message rings out in your mind as you pick up the crystal The exit is in sight, all you need to is step through it.

name: Foggy Pathway
description: Further away from the campfire, you can still feel its calming protection  from the fog. Visibility is decent here, but you know if you misstep you  will become lost again. There are less campers and hunters around these  parts. More of the spirits and animals of the forest instead. It is  difficult to see what is ahead of you. You will just have to pick a  direction and hope it leads you to your destination.

name: Behind the Altar
description: Behind the altar, you turn around to view the temple from the other  direction. Monks and commoners come and go from the wooden benches, offering thoughtful prayers in silence. Light bathes this space. It feels under the watchful eye of The Five that it was built to worship. Underfoot, there is a circular metal plate. It has a keyhole in it.

name: Ritual Room
description: Behind the curtain you have stumbled upon a ritual in progress. A swirling  ball of pink light dominates the space. Three priests cast their hands over the immense shape of energy. They hum softly under their breath with an incantation ritual. Staring directly at the pink energy reveals that it is a portal to another plane of existence. You can see nothing but pure blackness within the portal realm. The three priests barely acknowledge your existence Their focus is on maintaining the magical link between two realms.

name: Bookshelves
description: You step into a quiet building with even quieter patrons. You feel  underdressed. Everyone bustles about with lovely warm sweaters on their arms The librarians here greet you and ask if you need help finding what you are looking for. The tomes in this establishment detail the history of the  Kingdom of Emrae and its surroundings. The books are arranged in neat  orderly rows and indicate a careful attention to detail from the owners. If there is information you seek about this kingdom, it will be in here . . . hopefully.

name: Stairwell
description: The wooden stairs creak as your boots make contact with the treads. Given  the rest of the library, youd be sure the staircases would be made of books if the owners desired. The library directory is posted on every floor of the stairwell. This floor reads  - The immediate surroundings of the Township -

name: Stairwell
description: The wooden stairs creak as your boots make contact with the treads. Given  the rest of the library, youd be sure the staircases would be made of books if the owners desired. The library directory is posted on every floor of the stairwell. This floor reads  - The far reaches of the Kingdom -

The books are arranged in neat  orderly rows and indicate a careful attention to detail from the owners. If there is information you seek about this kingdom, it will be in here . . . hopefully. On this floor of the library, the research has reached a fever pitch. Dedicated scholars leaf through tomes in an effort to find the greatest kept secrets of Emrae.

name: Bookshelves
description: The tomes in this establishment detail the history of the Kingdom of Emrae  and its surroundings. On this floor  of the library, only the most serious of readers are allowed. They work in groups, swarming around volumes of books. After they consume the book of  words and knowledge, they discard it, leaving nothing but blank pages behind

name: Dragon Blood Pub
description: This is a wonderful spot where all of the citizens of Emrae make an  appearance from time to time. If you need a room to stay for the evening,  you can talk with the owner, Jack. If youre looking for beer, then just  flag down a bartender. Some of the customers turn and greet you with a  stinky eye. Others grin and invite you to join in their drinking games. A  fire crackles in the corner but it looks to be running out of wood soon.  Maybe someone will get cold and complain. This pub has been a fixture of the town for as long as residents can remember.

name: Staircase
description: You stand at the bottom of a wooden staircase. This is the ground floor of  the Dragon Blood Pub. It is the main drinking and dining facility. It is a  busy hive of activity, lively with patrons and waiters. Should you wish to  be served, just walk to the bar and talk with the owner, Jack. Above you  there is less activity. Upstairs are the sleeping quarters.

description: This is a wonderful spot where all of the citizens of Emrae make an  appearance from time to time. If you need a room to stay for the evening,  you can talk with the owner, Jack. A  fire crackles in the corner but it looks to be running out of wood soon.  Maybe someone will get cold and complain. This pub has been a fixture of the town for as long as residents can remember.A locked hatch to the cellar is on the ground here. Hopefully a bartender has the key?

name: Wine Cellar
description: Underneath the pubs main floor, there isnt as much light here. However,  you are still able to discern enough in this underground cellar. Rows and  rows of wine bottles litter the space. In the southeast corner is the beer keg storage. And it appears someone is helping themselves. The far end of  this cellar fades into blackness, and you cannot see what is down there.

name: Wine Cellar
description: Underneath the pubs main floor, there isnt as much light here. However,  you are still able to discern enough in this underground cellar. Rows and  rows of wine bottles litter the space. In the southeast corner is the beer keg storage. And it appears someone is helping themselves. The far end of  this cellar fades into blackness, and you cannot see what is down there.

name: Wine Cellar
description: You stand amongst rows of wine bottles beneath the main floor of the Dragon  Blood Pub. The occasional mouse squeaks across the stone floor, but there is otherwise not much activity here. The selection of wines are phenomenal.  1774 Chateau Cheval. 1683 Domaine Saint Prefet Cuve. 1325 Clarence Dillon Grenache. If only you had a corkscrew. . .

name: Keg Storage
description: Youve reached the end of the shelving for wine and now stand amongst a  large collection of beer kegs. This dank underground cellar has particularly poor lighting, which makes it difficult to maneuver around these dusty kegs. An unwanted guest is here with you. Its clear that she has been rifling  through the shelves of wine looking for the best bottles. However, given her state, she doesnt seem able to navigate her way out of this cellar.

name: Wine Cellar
description: You stand amongst rows of wine bottles beneath the main floor of the Dragon  Blood Pub. The occasional mouse squeaks across the stone floor, but there is otherwise not much activity here. The selection of wines are phenomenal.  1632 Seppeltsfield Liquer. 1524 Principia Pinot Noir. 1453 Chateaux Margaux. If only you had a corkscrew. . .

name: Wine Cellar
description: You stand amongst rows of wine bottles beneath the main floor of the Dragon  Blood Pub. The occasional mouse squeaks across the stone floor, but there is otherwise not much activity here. The selection of wines are phenomenal.  1572 Pirramimma Shiraz. 1299 Torbreck Struie Shiraz. 1745 Domaine Ponsot  Grand Cru Clos de la Roche. If only you had a corkscrew. . .

name: Underground
description: This part of the cellar is not used for wine storage. In fact, it is empty  aside from a grating on the floor. You cannot see what is down there as  there is no lighting. However, you hear the trickling of water. And you  smell the stench of tainted magic. It doesnt make sense. Why would there be a sewer grating in this cellar? It is locked by padlock, and there doesnt  seem to be much sense in destroying it for access.

name: Staircase
description: This is the first floor of the Dragon Blood Pub. It is the floor with guest rooms and sleeping accommodation. Sleepy travellers from all far and wide  set up their beds and tuck themselves in for a good night's sleep. Along the wall of the staircase are various pictures and portraits. They show valuable and treasured patrons of the pub. Wonko, Ado, Swampy, Warg,  Pinesol. Just to name a few. Above you are the personal quarters of the  pubs owner, Jack.Below you is the main drinking floor, full of lively  sounds and customers.

name: Guest Accomodation
description: These are guest rooms within the Dragon Blood Pub. They are cosy rooms with nice bedding. The linen smells clean and recently washed. Altogether, well  looked after. Perhaps you might pay for a room and take a rest? A variety of characters circulate through these spaces: Tired wanderers from other realms who seek to rest their weary bones. Drunk locals who couldnt possibly even make it back to their own homes without assistance.

name: Guest Accomodation
description: These are guest rooms within the Dragon Blood Pub. They are cosy rooms with nice bedding. The linen smells clean and recently washed. Altogether, well  looked after. Perhaps you might pay for a room and take a rest? A variety of characters circulate through these spaces: Tired wanderers from other realms who seek to rest their weary bones. Drunk locals who couldnt possibly even make it back to their own homes without assistance.

Perhaps you might pay for a room and take a rest? A variety of characters circulate through these spaces: Tired wanderers from other realms who seek to rest their weary bones. Drunk locals who couldnt possibly even make it back to their own homes without assistance.

name: Staircase
description: This is the second floor or the Dragon Blood Pub. The owner, Jacks quarters should be here. At least you assume. You look around and see nothing on this floor. It is just an empty corridor. No doors, nothing. Perhaps you are  missing something?. All you can see is a window out to the city square below Here you can see all of the other main attractions of the town. The fountain the library, the temple. Behind the city to the north looms the domineering presence of Castle Emrae. The king has spared no expense in crafting a  building that asserts his power of his country.

name: Jack's Quarters
description: You walk over to Jacks diary and flick through the pages: ' I never should have trusted Schenk. That traitorous bastard blinded me to  the facts right in front of me. Of course, Emrae is no king. He is a  terrible ruler. But that isnt to say we need to subscribe to some manifesto of - reinstate the /true/ king. I would prefer to believe that our kingdom  is just doing the best with what we have. For that reason, I have let my  portal decay. I hope that one day, I will find someone trustworthy enough to dispose of the portal for me. I know that the Four Princes quarrel. They disagree over who should succeed  the throne. If in-fighting amongst the brothers should ever cause war. . . I dont know what this town will do. If that is the case, I will retain one of my Jet Crystals here, in the hope that I can protect the people I have come  to love.'

name: Township of Emrae
description: You stand on the stone streets in the township of Emrae. Citizens and their children walk around the place, going about their business. They are all  cordial enough to greet you as a new face as you walk by. There is much  hustle in this main town square. Buildings and pavements are clean and in  good repair. Those who live here are looked after well. People do their best to maintain some sense of normality in their life.

name: Under a Sewer Grate
description: You cling to a ladder underneath a manhole cover. Above you are the roads  of Emrae. Into the darkness below extends the citys sewer system. The sound of running water can be heard below you. The smell of various waste products swarm around you - not the most pleasant. Something is off about the air  here. You sense a distortion of magical energies around you.

name: Emrae Sewers
description: You stand in an underground pipeline beneath the streets of Emrae. Whilst  this drainway is only ankle-deep in water, there is certainly a full-bodied stench in this place. Denizens of the pipeline consist of rats, cockroaches, and sewer slime, among other things. . . Navigating these passageways would  be best accomplished with a plan.

description: You stand in an underground pipeline beneath the streets of Emrae. Whilst  this drainway is only ankle-deep in water, there is certainly a full-bodied stench in this place. name: Emrae Sewers
description: You stand in a large pipeway, underneath a grating. This is directly below  the Dragon Blood Pub. A ladder extends above you, and the sewer leads east  into the darkness. To the west, a different kind of darkness absorbs any  ight you shine in that direction. A magical humming can be felt - like a rip in reality. There is sorcery afoot here.

name: Emrae Sewers
description: You cling to a ladder underneath a drainage grate. Above you is the cellar belonging to the Dragon Blood Pub. Into the darkness below extends the sewer system of Emrae. The sound of running water can be heard below you. The  smell of various waste products swarm around you - not the most pleasant. Something is off about the air here. You sense a distortion of magical  energies around you.

name: Outside the Jet Portal
description: In the sewers beneath the Dragon Blood Pub you have stumbled across an  un-guarded portal. It is a shimmering mass of blackness that extends forth  from a tear in reality itself. This portal gives no indication of where it  leads. Reaching out with your hands, the portal swallows it immediately.  However, searing agony shoots up your arm as you try to push further.  Normally, portals of this nature require crystal catalysts to operate.  Bridging the gap between different realities with portals takes considerable magical energy. Given the colouration of this particular portal, you will  require a catalyst with a gemstone made of Jet. Perhaps the owner of the  pub above you will know something of this?

name: Inside the Jet Portal
description: You step into the inky blackness of the Jet Portal. Immediately it is  obvious that something has gone awry here. The rituals and magic required to maintain a stable portal have been neglected. This pathway to another realm  is unfit for traversal. The magic is tainted and botched. You can feel your  very essence merge with the abyssal blackness. Screams of anguished souls  fill your mind. Your thoughts are overcome with sadness and frustration.  There is no air to breath or room to think. These bitter emotions seem to  have taken corporeal form

name: Inside the Jet Portal
description: Pressing onward into the abyss, you fight to maintain your senses. Screams  of tortured souls fill your mind. Your eyesight is useless in this place as  there is nothing to see. There is no air to breathe. All of your wits have  been deprived from you. Another presence is here. Not an anguished soul.  Rather, a malicious one. The crystal core that maintains this portal is  nearby All you need to do to end this madness is destroy the malice and extinguish this plane of existence.

name: Large Drain Pipe
description: This labyrinth of pipes is unforgiving. You cannot breathe and you cannot  think. There is no light and nowhere to discern your location. Rotting coagulations of mucous float past you in the water, along with decaying  corpses. Tainted water flows over your skin, draining you of your very  essence. This sewer is a foul and wretched place to be.

name: Vertical Pipe Junction
description: Swimming amongst the storm drains, you encounter a vertical junction. A  ladder shaft leads up to a pocket of air. Below you is a disgusting blockage of slime and filth. You can assume that the pipeline extends further below  you, but there is no means of traversal at the moment. The only means of  clearing this kind of blockage would be with some sort of mineral compound. Such a talc would be stored within the sewer system itself. Blockages like  this are frequent, which means water needs to be treated regularly to  prevent stormwater systems clogging and backfiring.

name: Sewer Junction
description: You stand at a junction of large pipeways. In the distance to the east,  there is an opening to the pipe system. It is some external exit outdoors.  To the west, water cascades down from various catchments in the city of  Emrae. From the south, more effluent gushes in from other locations. This junction is surprisingly not completely underwater. You have a moment to  catch your breath. The crashing of water from all directions seems to have nullified whatever draining force operates in these dank and drudgerous waterways.

name: Large Drainway
description: You are underwater in a large drainage pipe. Raw effluent gushes around you  and air is scarce here. Further to that, there is a certain foulness about  this water that goes beyond human excrement. The very pipelines seem to be draining your essence away. It would be wise to make your thoroughfare  through these sewers as quickly as possible.

name: Emrae Sewers
description: Amidst the blackness of these pipeways, you are not sure where to go. The corridors of water have no sensible organisation. Evidently, this civic engineering was not to carry water. No, it was designed to hide secrets.  Layers of muck and slime coat the walls of these drainways, with the  surprise poking out of the filth. Sometimes a gold coin, sometimes a  severed limb. If a person wished to hide something here, it would be an  easy task

name: Under a Manhole Cover
description: You cling to a ladder underneath a manhole cover. Above you is the Temple  of Emrae. Into the darkness below extends the citys sewer system. The sound of running water can be heard below you. The smell of various waste products swarm around you - not the most pleasant. Something is off about the air  here. You sense a distortion of magical energies around you.

name: Ladder Shaft
description: You cling to a rusty ladder connecting pipeways within the sewers of Emrae. Looking up, there is a faint source of light, and the regular dripping of  water onto your face. Below, there is nothing but inky blackness, and the  promise of submerged stormways. Gripping these ladder rungs is difficult.  In addition to the decaying metal, there is a thick layer of slime making  it difficult to grip.

name: Breathing Space
description: Finally within this sunken graveyard you have found breathing room. This  chamber of the sewers is not used for processing water. Rather, it appears  to be a storage place. The sound of crashing water comes from the ladder  shaft below. To the north and east of you extends a room full of wooden  crates. This storage space must contain something used for processing sewer water.

name: Mineral Storage
description: You have stumbled upon a storage location for minerals. Several crates  labeled TALC surround you, though they all lay empty. Smelling them leaves you with a harsh, astringent taste in your mouth. Touching the remnants of the mineral, your skin is left feeling tingly, with a burning sensation. If you could find a sufficient amount of such a mineral, it would cleave  through the slime and detritus lining the pipeways below. A powerful weapon in this environment, if you could find some. . .

This sewer is a foul and wretched place to be.

name: Sewer Pipe
description: Looking above you, there is a  platform sitting above the waterline, but  there is no discernable way onto it from here. If you wish to gain access  you will need to look around the area for some sort of ladder or stairway. Though, that would be the least of your concerns at the moment. Swimming  against the current of effluent within these drainways would be difficult  for even the most seasoned athlete. Especially given the dark and cramped  nature of this environment. If only there was a way onto the platform.

name: Sewer Pipe
description: Looking above you, there is a  platform sitting above the waterline, but  there is no discernable way onto it from here. If you wish to gain access  you will need to look around the area for some sort of ladder or stairway. Though, that would be the least of your concerns at the moment. Swimming  against the current of effluent within these drainways would be difficult  for even the most seasoned athlete. Especially given the dark and cramped  nature of this environment. If only there was a way onto the platform.

name: Sewer Pipe
description: You are afloat in the sewers. This pipe is completely underwater and you can no-longer breathe. Making matters worse, these pipes are tainted with a pernicious magic. You can feel your essence drain away with every passing  second. It would be unwise to dawdle about in this place.  To the west,  there is a ladder shaft out of the sewers. To the north, you spy a stairway. Here is where you can gain access to the platform above the waterline.

name: Ladder Shaft
description: under construction, come back soon!

name: Cultist Hideout
description: You stand on a platform that overlooks the sewer pipeways. This is no  ordinary addition to the sewer system. This structure has been dug out afterwards. Peering further north into the darkness, it looks to be a secret base of operations. Immediately, you can tell you arent welcome in this  place. Here with you is a hooded figure. He doesnt look very interested in apprehending you. In fact, he sighs and tries to avoid eye contact.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: You tread over an iron grating suspended above the sewer pipeways. Water  roars and gushes below you. For the organisation that works in this bunker, disposing of their secrets would be as simple and throwing it into the water The air here is fetid. It is stained with magic of the occult. This is a  place where individuals would be sacrificed for having the wrong way of  thinking. To the west is a stairway back into the sewers. To the north, are the main passageways of this treacherous hideaway.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: You tread over an iron grating suspended above the sewer pipeways. Water  roars and gushes below you. For the organisation that works in this bunker, disposing of their secrets would be as simple and throwing it into the water The air here is fetid. It is stained with magic of the occult. This is a  place where individuals would be sacrificed for having the wrong way of  thinking. To the west is a stairway back into the sewers. To the north, are the main passageways of this treacherous hideaway.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: An underground bunker has been carved into the ground and connected to the  sewer system. The walls of this structure are roughly hewn stone, chiseled  out by hand. This seems to be a base of operations for the underground  cultist activity in Emrae. There is very little lighting down here, only a  few torches that flicker in the lack of fresh air. Hooded figures eye you  off from all directions. Perhaps you arent welcome here? Blood stains the  walls and the floors. The stench of foul sorcery fills your head.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: The central space of this bunker has been decorated with a large pentagram. Its insignia is scraped out of the stone to create a small channel. Within this carving, blood has been poured. Rituals are conducted in this circle. Those who are foolish enough to follow this cult are sacrificed to perform occult magic. You stand for a moment and contemplate the space. Voices of  the departed fill your mind. They were the ones whose lives were offered as gifts to the demonic deities. In their words they express regret and hatred towards their captors.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: An underground bunker has been carved into the ground and connected to the  sewer system. The walls of this structure are roughly hewn stone, chiseled  out by hand. This seems to be a base of operations for the underground  cultist activity in Emrae. There is very little lighting down here, only a  few torches that flicker in the lack of fresh air. Hooded figures eye you  off from all directions. Perhaps you arent welcome here? Blood stains the  walls and the floors. The stench of foul sorcery fills your head. To the  east, you are met with a locked iron door. Presumably, the leader of this operation is stationed behind this door. Perhaps one of the acolytes  circulating this hideout might have it?

name: Cult Office
description: Behind the iron door lies a more civil set of conditions. Candles light the room dimly. Carpet lines the floors along with dusty and mouldy furnishings. On the walls are various schematics and drawings. They all reference ritual and sacrifice in some way. Instructions, perhaps? One poster titles itself Portal Opening Techniques and references the use of crystal catalysts as a means of gathering enough energy to traverse to other planes of existence Another blueprint discusses The duality of The Five Goddesses and the dark counterparts to each of The Five. Further into the chamber is a desk with  many tomes and books fanned out upon it.

name: Cult Office
description: You look at the desk and see a variety of horrible contraptions. Nail  remover. Eye gouger. Ear wetter. Pants ripper. All devices designed to  inflict pain and anguish upon victims.  This room is dark, dank and dripping Hardly the office for any self-respecting leader. The only benefit to  operating in a place such as this would be the absolute assurance of never being discovered. Beyond that, these conditions are feral and uncivilised.

name: Cultist Hideout
description: Blood stains on the walls. Torture devices littered on the floors. Water  dripping from the ceiling. Mould and mildew float, hanging within the air.  Hooded figures occasionally come into view. You try to stay out of their  sight to avoid confrontation. This is the base of operations for the  underground cultist activity in Emrae. There is very little lighting down  here, only a few torches that flicker weakly in the lack of fresh air. This place is unpleasant and dangerous.

name: Foul Recieving Drain
description: This drainway is supposed to receive stormwater, but something has gone awry It has now become foul. Water has been replaced with a thick coating of  dense sludge. You squeeze yourself through it and hope you might be able to wash it out of your clothes later. There are a lot of rats around here. Occasionally, a large one steps into view. Something around this place is  causing them to grow this size. In fact, you can almost feel the magical  energy that is draining you coming from a pipeway nearby.

name: Rat Throne
description: You have stumbled upon a hideous sight. A giant rat king. It sits in a pool  of pernicious sludge. In fact, this is no ordinary slime. It seems to have a will of its own. It is draining the mana from the air around it. You can  barely breathe in this place, let alone think. Dispose of the slime or leave.

name: Foul Recieving Drain
description: This drainway is supposed to receive stormwater, but something has gone awry It has now become foul. Water has been replaced with a thick coating of  dense sludge. You squeeze yourself through it and hope you might be able to wash it out of your clothes later. There are a lot of rats around here. Occasionally, a large one steps into view. Something around this place is  causing them to grow this size. In fact, you can almost feel the magical  energy that is draining you coming from a pipeway nearby.

name: Dusty Road
description: You stand amongst the streets of Emrae. Common folk bustle about on their  daily business. They greet you pleasantly but overall there is a certain  level of indifference. You could say that people here are just trying to do the best they can. From what you have heard, the arable land has shrunk dramatically in recent times. No space really exists now for farming within the western reaches of the kingdom. Ultimately, that would create a food shortage. And with a shortage of resources comes the competition for it.

name: Dusty Road
description: Travelling along the western roads of Emrae you are at a fork in the road.  To the east stands the main city, with the kingdoms castle standing proudly behind it. Directly west, the road starts to turn sandy. Shrubbery grows  more and more sparse. A road sign pointing in that direction reads Desert. To the northwest, the sign reads Ruins. Homes and dwellings are scarce in these parts

name: Dusty Road
description: Travelling along the western roads of Emrae you are at a fork in the road. To the northeast stands the main city, with the kingdoms castle standing  proudly behind it. Going southwest, the road becomes sandy and less  vegetated. A road sign pointing in that direction reads Desert. To the  south, the sign reads Floating Stones. This is wild territory.

name: Road to the Desert
description: The arable land in this region has run dry. Nothing but dust and dry  riverbeds remain. Houses have either been burned or dismantled here. No one lives here. No plants grow here. Those who travel to this desert must have business with the dead. Either to rob their graves or exploit their magic.  For that reason, anyone who comes to this place would know what they are  doing in combat and in sorcery.

name: Entrance to the Desert
description: The arable land in this region has run dry. Nothing but dust and dry  riverbeds remain. Houses have either been burned or dismantled here. No one lives here. No plants grow here. Those who travel to this desert must have business with the dead. Either to rob their graves or exploit their magic.  For that reason, anyone who comes to this place would know what they are  doing in combat and in sorcery.

name: Desert of Lies
description: You stand in a valley between sand dunes. There is thankfully a small amount of shade to be appreciated behind the tallest of peaks. However, the  atmosphere still feels like it has been set ablaze. You can feel your mind slipping as you try to traverse these sands. There is nothing to trust  except the interminable waves of hot air. Finding water soon will be a  priority, lest the desert heat claim your life.

name: Desert of Lies
description: These are dunes of delusion. At a guess, you look towards the southern  horizon and see the sun there. But you cant be certain it really is south, since your shadow falls towards the sunlight. The shadows delude you. So do the dunes. A breeze rolls in from the south. It is unbearably warm, sucking  the moisture from your skin and face. You stare at the sand and watch it  move southwards, towards the breeze. The sand is lying. So is the desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed skin starts  to bubble under the rays. You feel like you are losing your mind in this environment.

name: Desert of Lies
description: This desert is lying to you. The sun hangs low in what you think is the  eastern skyline. But when you look at the shadow your body casts, it falls towards the east as well. Such a phenomenon is paradoxical. The shadows lie. The desert lies. There is a breeze of hot air travelling from the south. You can feel it move on your face. But when you look at the sand of the dunes,  it flies towards the wind. It defies logic. The sand is lying. So is the  desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed  skin starts to bubble under the rays. This place is not hospitable in the slightest.

name: Desert of Lies
description: You stand in a valley between sand dunes. There is thankfully a small amount of shade to be appreciated behind the tallest of peaks. However, the  atmosphere still feels like it has been set ablaze. You can feel your mind slipping as you try to traverse these sands. There is nothing to trust  except the interminable waves of hot air. Finding water soon will be a  priority, lest the desert heat claim your life.

name: Desert of Lies
description: This desert is lying to you. The sun hangs low in what you think is the  eastern skyline. But when you look at the shadow your body casts, it falls towards the east as well. Such a phenomenon is paradoxical. The shadows lie. The desert lies. There is a breeze of hot air travelling from the south. You can feel it move on your face. But when you look at the sand of the dunes,  it flies towards the wind. It defies logic. The sand is lying. So is the  desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed  skin starts to bubble under the rays. This place is not hospitable in the slightest.

name: Desert of Lies
description: These sands are misleading. Whilst the sun shines brightly from what you  think is north, your shadow points that direction also. There is no logic to this occurrence. The shadows are misleading. These sands are misleading.  Wind assaults you from the south. It is hot, dry and punishing. When you  look at the grains underfoot, they drift to the south also, with the wind.  The sand is lying, so is the desert. To make matters worse the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed skin starts to bubble under the rays. You need to  find a way through this madness quickly.

name: Desert of Lies
description: You stand atop a crest in the sand dunes. You look towards the horizon in  all directions and contemplate which way you might go. High in the sky, you  can see vultures circle above you. Do they think you'll be their next meal? There are no real indicators or landmarks in this place, so navigation has  become meaningless. Hot air pierces your lungs and makes breathing a chore.  Sand whips around your ankles in gusts of wind getting amongst your clothes  and irritating skin. You feel lost amongst these dunes.

name: Desert of Lies
description: These are dunes of delusion. At a guess, you look towards the southern  horizon and see the sun there. But you cant be certain it really is south, since your shadow falls towards the sunlight. The shadows delude you. So do the dunes. A breeze rolls in from the south. It is unbearably warm, sucking  the moisture from your skin and face. You stare at the sand and watch it  move southwards, towards the breeze. The sand is lying. So is the desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed skin starts  to bubble under the rays. You feel like you are losing your mind in this environment.

name: Peaceful Oasis
description: This was once a lush and prosperous river basin. Years of neglect changed  this landscape into an unforgiving and menacing desert. No crops could ever  hope to grow here. Instead, animals and vegetation alike cling to this last promise of livelihood in this wasteland. You drink the water and feel rejuvenated. At least this quiet spot will nurture you until you decide to  travel forward into the dunes again.

name: Oasis Encampment
description: Sand sailors and camel herders congregate in this place to get some respite  from the scorching sands around them. To the north is a small lake of water. Expanding out to the west is the vastness of the desert dunes. The sun  shines upon them fervently. In the northwest appears to be an entrance to  some underground ruins

name: Oasis Encampment
description: Looking to the western horizon, you can just make out a sandstone tower. A brilliant purple glow emanates from the top of the structure. You speculate if it could be the cause of the radiant heat felt on these deathly dunes. Navigating to that tower will prove difficult, but you need only trust  yourself that you are heading towards the western skies.

Any exposed  skin starts to bubble under the rays. This place is not hospitable in the slightest.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: You stand in a valley between sand dunes. There is thankfully a small amount of shade to be appreciated behind the tallest of peaks. However, the  atmosphere still feels like it has been set ablaze. You can feel your mind slipping as you try to traverse these sands. There is nothing to trust  except the interminable waves of hot air. Finding water soon will be a  priority, lest the desert heat claim your life.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: These are dunes of delusion. At a guess, you look towards the southern  horizon and see the sun there. But you cant be certain it really is south, since your shadow falls towards the sunlight. The shadows delude you. So do the dunes. A breeze rolls in from the south. It is unbearably warm, sucking  the moisture from your skin and face. You stare at the sand and watch it  move southwards, towards the breeze. The sand is lying. So is the desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed skin starts  to bubble under the rays. You feel like you are losing your mind in this environment.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: These are dunes of delusion. At a guess, you look towards the southern  horizon and see the sun there. It is unbearably warm, sucking  the moisture from your skin and face. You stare at the sand and watch it  move southwards, towards the breeze. The sand is lying. So is the desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed skin starts  to bubble under the rays. You feel like you are losing your mind in this environment.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: The landscape miguides your senses here. The sun beams down from the west,  but you cant be too sure anymore. When you look to the ground, your shadow points towards the sun - not away.  The shadows misguide. So does the  landscape. Gusts of searing air assaults you from the south. Yet, the sand  around you floats towards the south. The sand is lying to you. So is the  desert. To make matters worse, the sunlight here is punishing. Any exposed  skin starts to bubble under the rays. You do not feel welcome here at all.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: You stand atop a crest in the sand dunes. You look towards the horizon in  all directions and contemplate which way you might go. High in the sky, you  can see vultures circle above you. Do they think you'll be their next meal? There are no real indicators or landmarks in this place, so navigation has  become meaningless. Hot air pierces your lungs and makes breathing a chore.  Sand whips around your ankles in gusts of wind getting amongst your clothes  and irritating skin. You feel lost amongst these dunes.

name: Scorching Dunes
description: You stand in a valley between sand dunes. There is thankfully a small amount of shade to be appreciated behind the tallest of peaks. However, the  atmosphere still feels like it has been set ablaze. You can feel your mind slipping as you try to traverse these sands. There is nothing to trust  except the interminable waves of hot air. Finding water soon will be a  priority, lest the desert heat claim your life.

name: Outside the Desert Tower
description: Youve successfully traversed the desert. Now before you looms a foreboding sandstone structure. The tower you spied from the oasis . Looking back in  that direction, you can barely see it anymore. The sunlight is malicious  here. A purple glow shines from the top floor of the tower. Time to  go investigate?

name: Quicksand
description: Sand is loose in this area. It is falling. In fact, you have stumbled into a sinking pit of quicksand. You scramble around, looking for something to  hoist yourself out. However there is no use. There are no trees or  structures to be seen. Just sand. Just a mass of sinking grains. If there is a way out of this mess, it will firstly involve embracing the fact that you  are in quicksand.

name: Desert Tower of Traps
description: Stepping inside the tower, you are grateful for the shade. The punishing  heat from outside has subsided. The air inside this tower has turned thick  and there is a slight purple haze about. It is difficult to see too far in  front of you. As your footsteps fall, you can hear mechanical whirring with in the walls of the tower to match them. Traps are being set as you walk.  Any further movements inside this tower will require careful planning.

name: Trap Tower
description: This is the ground floor of the Desert Tower. Wherever you step you are  afraid you might mis-step and land in a trap. The purple haze around you  blocks your magical power. There is no way to cast restorative magic in you  here. The architect of this building designed its sandstone bricks in such a way that any would-be thieves were punished for breaking in. In this main hallway, a stairway leads up and down the tower, but the passageways are  guarded by locked doors. The keys required for each door lie within the  floor itself. But searching for them will presumably be dangerous.

name: Trap Chamber
description: This is one of the trap chambers within the Desert Tower. This tower is a  burial chamber to honour the great kings of the land. However, these  chambers are designed as burial chambers for would-be robbers and thieves. A key sits atop a stone pedestal. Have you chosen the correct chamber? Have you chosen the correct key?  The only way to find out is to try it on the stairway in the central hallway.

The only way to find out is to try it on the stairway in the central hallway.

name: Top of the Desert Tower
description: Stepping up onto the top floor of the Desert Tower, you have uncovered the  source of the desolate sunlight and heat outside. Glyphs are etched into the walls here. They seem to dance on the surface of the stone bricks. In the  middle of the room glows a mass shimmering purple light. An Amethyst Portal carves a hole into reality itself. A hooded figure lays hands over the  various runes spelled out on the walls, feeding the energy of the portal.  What is supposed to be a burial site for ancient kings has now been turned  into  a haven of unholy magic.

name: Inside the Amethyst Portal
description: Stepping through the Amethyst Portal, the sunshine dissapates. You immerse yourself in the blackness of the other-worldly realm. As soon as you adjust yourself to the stillness, a bolt of shooting pain assaults the inside of  your head. As if another occupant were fighting for its place within the  chaos. As your head throbs, you hear the echoes of another persons voice  inside your mind. The voice sounds urgent, but you cannot seem to recognise to whom it belongs. As it speaks, it seems to beckon your movements further  into the blackness.

name: Inside the Amethyst Portal
description: The voice fades and the pain in your head dissipates Through the blackness gleams the core of the portal. It shines with a brilliant amethyst glow All that's left to do it take it and leave

name: Inside the Amethyst Portal
description: His radiance will be snuffed out When the time comes, what will you choose? Your pride, or the future of this kingdom? A message rings out in your mind as you pick up the crystal The exit is in sight, all you need to is step through it.

name: Suffocating Chamber
description: This chamber is a burial ground for a great king. And certainly not a  welcome place for tomb thieves. The air in here is unbreathable. A lack of  oxygen makes it difficult to think. Looking at the walls, the sandstone  bricks are etched with various glyphs and runes. They seem to dance in your vision. Perhaps they inscribe a spell. That would explain the delirium in  your mind. A charm to dispel would-be attackers of the now dead royalty.

name: Hidden Passage
description: The quicksand above has dragged you down into a secret hallway within the  tombs below. This passage is sealed away from the main hallways as a means  of security for the dead kings. Their remains rest in peace here without  fear of being burgled. However, given your current situation, you arent  sure if you will be able to get out of here alive yourself. In front of you stands a large doorway with glyphs and runes inscribed into it.  Unfortunately, there doesn't seem to be any mechanism to open it in the immediate vicinity.

name: Buried Ruins
description: The quicksand above has dragged you down into a secret hallway within the  tombs below. This passage is sealed away from the main hallways as a means  of security for the dead kings. Their remains rest in peace here without  fear of being burgled. However, given your current situation, you arent  sure if you will be able to get out of here alive yourself.

name: Buried Ruins
description: Within this hallway there is no access to any of the burial chambers. As you place your footsteps along the stone pavement below, you can hear mechanical whirring within the walls. Doorways close at your presence. The atmosphere  here is tense. You can sense the presence of others. Thieves? Raiders? Or conjured creations? Best to tread carefully.

name: Buried Ruins
description: Within this hallway there is no access to any of the burial chambers. As you place your footsteps along the stone pavement below, you can hear mechanical whirring within the walls. Doorways close at your presence. The atmosphere  here is tense. You can sense the presence of others. Thieves? Raiders? Or conjured creations? Best to tread carefully.

Doorways close at your presence. The atmosphere  here is tense. You can sense the presence of others. Thieves? Raiders? Or conjured creations? Best to tread carefully.

name: Buried Ruins
description: You stand within a structure that has been long since left to ruin and sink into the earth. The ceiling is high within these hallways and creates a grandiose atmosphere. This is a place of respect and reverence. It is also what meets the eye. Stone pillars support the roof of the building, and are inscribed with names of various kings and queens that are buried in these hallways. If only you could find the pathway to them?

name: Buried Ruins
description: You stand within a structure that has been long since left to ruin and sink into the earth. The ceiling is high within these hallways and creates a grandiose atmosphere. This is a place of respect and reverence. It is also what meets the eye. Stone pillars support the roof of the building, and are inscribed with names of various kings and queens that are buried in these hallways. If only you could find the pathway to them?

name: Burial Chamber
description: You have found yourself within a hidden burial chamber. Gold and jewels  cover the floor. The entire room is an endorsement of the dead kings power and wealth within their life. Will they really be needing their riches in  the afterlife? Why not help yourself? You can make better use of it.

name: Inside the Heliotrope Portal
description: As you step into the shimmering light, you are overcome with feelings of  calmness and serenity. Tears stream down your face as you are met in an  embrace of pure compassion and benevolence. A voice enters your head. Serene and graceful, it speaks to you directly: . My child, my child. You come here to liberate me. I speak for The Five. I am the might of Domina. The speed of Astura. Bennolas fortitude, Antryxs wit. Ferrans wisdom. These worshipers were not to blame for any crime. They  sought only to honour me. Step forth and claim which you seek.

name: Inside the Heliotrope Portal
description: The voice continues:  My child, my child. I welcome your embrace. This land of Emrae hides foul secrets. You must strive to uncover them. Cultists ransack and defile the  magic I bestowed upon this kingdom long ago. Though, they draw power from  another source also. A false idol. A deceitful ruler. A snake of a being. I beseech you, hero. Search these lands far and wide for the head of the beast Slay it. Show the leader of these cultists no mercy! Then, I will reward you with my favour. ... My child, my child. Good luck. Go forth and reclaim my world for me.

name: Healer's Chambers
description: The Healer George conducts his affairs within this chamber. Sick and blind  come to him for help. He offers to perform his miracles upon them, and grant them the gift of good health. Should you require his services, he will  gladly aid you. Help is always available to those who ask for it. To those  who are willing to pledge themselves to the teachings of The Five.

name: Altar
description: Several steps elevate the altar on a platform above the rest of the temple.  In this manner, whoever conducts a service within these chambers will appear to be above their congregation. Above their common serviles. Atop the altar  lays offerings of fruit and meat. Supposedly, they are left out to honour  The Five Goddesses. Statues of Emrae the King line the wing ailes. Light  from outside gleams in through stained glass windows depicting King Emrae receiving the gift of nobility from The Five. Does it mean to suggest that Emrae was chosen by the Goddesses?
